P_HTM[385]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[386]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ chahi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhāti …pe….**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in six ways: …*";
P_HTM[387]="*Mahallakaṃ vihāraṃ kārāpentassa saṅghādiseso kattha paññattoti?**“The offense entailing suspension for having a large dwelling built—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[388]="*Kosambiyaṃ paññatto.**At Kosambī.*";
P_HTM[389]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[390]="*Āyasmantaṃ channaṃ ārabbha.**Venerable Channa.*";
P_HTM[391]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[392]="*Āyasmā channo vihāravatthuṃ sodhento aññataraṃ cetiyarukkhaṃ chedāpesi, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**Channa having a tree that served as a shrine felled to clear a site for a dwelling.*";
P_HTM[393]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[394]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ chahi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhāti …pe….**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in six ways: …*";
P_HTM[395]="*Bhikkhuṃ amūlakena pārājikena dhammena anuddhaṃsentassa saṅghādiseso kattha paññattoti?**“The offense entailing suspension for groundlessly charging a monk with an offense entailing expulsion—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[396]="*Rājagahe paññatto.**At Rājagaha.*";
P_HTM[397]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[398]="*Mettiyabhūmajake bhikkhū ārabbha.**The monks Mettiya and Bhūmajaka.*";
P_HTM[399]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[400]="*Mettiyabhūmajakā bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ amūlakena pārājikena dhammena anuddhaṃsesuṃ, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**Those monks groundlessly charging Venerable Dabba the Mallian with an offense entailing expulsion.*";
P_HTM[401]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[402]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ tīhi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhāti …pe….**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in three ways: …*";
P_HTM[403]="*Bhikkhuṃ aññabhāgiyassa adhikaraṇassa kiñci desaṃ lesamattaṃ upādāya pārājikena dhammena anuddhaṃsentassa saṅghādiseso kattha paññattoti?**“The offense entailing suspension for charging a monk with an offense entailing expulsion, using an unrelated legal issue as a pretext—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[404]="*Rājagahe paññatto.**At Rājagaha.*";
P_HTM[405]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[406]="*Mettiyabhūmajake bhikkhū ārabbha.**The monks Mettiya and Bhūmajaka.*";
P_HTM[407]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[408]="*Mettiyabhūmajakā bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ aññabhāgiyassa adhikaraṇassa kiñci desaṃ lesamattaṃ upādāya pārājikena dhammena anuddhaṃsesuṃ, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**Those monks charging Venerable Dabba the Mallian with an offense entailing expulsion, using an unrelated legal issue as a pretext.*";
P_HTM[409]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[410]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ tīhi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhāti …pe….**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in three ways: …*";
P_HTM[411]="*Saṅghabhedakassa bhikkhuno yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjantassa saṅghādiseso kattha paññattoti?**“The offense entailing suspension for a monk who does not stop pursuing schism in the Sangha when pressed up to three times—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[412]="*Rājagahe paññatto.**At Rājagaha.*";
P_HTM[413]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[414]="*Devadattaṃ ārabbha.**Devadatta.*";
P_HTM[415]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[416]="*Devadatto samaggassa saṅghassa bhedāya parakkami, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**Devadatta pursuing schism in a united Sangha.*";
P_HTM[417]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[418]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhāti—**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in one way:*";
P_HTM[419]="*kāyato ca vācato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhāti …pe….**from body, speech, and mind. …*";
P_HTM[420]="*Bhedānuvattakānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjantānaṃ saṅghādiseso kattha paññattoti?**“The offense entailing suspension for monks who do not stop siding with one who is pursuing schism in the Sangha when pressed up to three times—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[421]="*Rājagahe paññatto.**At Rājagaha.*";
P_HTM[422]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[423]="*Sambahule bhikkhū ārabbha.**Several monks.*";
P_HTM[424]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[425]="*Sambahulā bhikkhū devadattassa saṅghabhedāya parakkamantassa anuvattakā ahesuṃ vaggavādakā, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**Those monks siding with and supported Devadatta’s pursuit of schism in the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[426]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[427]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhāti—**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in one way:*";
P_HTM[428]="*kāyato ca vācato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhāti …pe….**from body, speech, and mind. …*";
P_HTM[429]="*Dubbacassa bhikkhuno yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjantassa saṅghādiseso kattha paññattoti?**“The offense entailing suspension for a monk who does not stop being difficult to correct when pressed up to three times—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[430]="*Kosambiyaṃ paññatto.**At Kosambī.*";
P_HTM[431]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[432]="*Āyasmantaṃ channaṃ ārabbha.**Venerable Channa.*";
P_HTM[433]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[434]="*Āyasmā channo bhikkhūhi sahadhammikaṃ vuccamāno attānaṃ avacanīyaṃ akāsi, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**Channa making himself incorrigible when legitimately spoken to by the monks.*";
P_HTM[435]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[436]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhāti—**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in one way:*";
P_HTM[437]="*kāyato ca vācato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhāti …pe….**from body, speech, and mind. …*";
P_HTM[438]="*Kuladūsakassa bhikkhuno yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjantassa saṅghādiseso kattha paññattoti?**“The offense entailing suspension for a monk who does not stop being a corrupter of families when pressed up to three times—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[439]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññatto.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[440]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[441]="*Assajipunabbasuke bhikkhū ārabbha.**The monks Assaji and Punabbasuka.*";
P_HTM[442]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[443]="*Assajipunabbasukā bhikkhū saṅghena pabbājanīyakammakatā bhikkhū chandagāmitā dosagāmitā mohagāmitā bhayagāmitā pāpesuṃ, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**Those monks, when the Sangha did a legal procedure of banishment against them, slandering the monks as acting out of desire, ill will, confusion, and fear.*";
P_HTM[444]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[445]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhāti—**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in one way:*";
P_HTM[446]="*kāyato ca vācato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhāti …pe….**from body, speech, and mind. …*";
P_HTM[447]="*Terasa saṅghādisesā niṭṭhitā.**The thirteen rules entailing suspension are finished.*";
P_HTM[448]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[449]="*Vissaṭṭhi kāyasaṃsaggaṃ,**“Emission, physical contact,*";
P_HTM[450]="*duṭṭhullaṃ attakāmañca;**Indecent, and his own needs;*";
P_HTM[451]="*Sañcarittaṃ kuṭī ceva,**Matchmaking, and a hut,*";
P_HTM[452]="*vihāro ca amūlakaṃ.**And a dwelling, groundless.*";
P_HTM[453]="*Kiñcidesañca bhedo ca,**A pretext, and schism,*";
P_HTM[454]="*tasseva anuvattakā;**Those who side with him;*";
P_HTM[455]="*Dubbacaṃ kuladūsañca,**Difficult to correct, and corrupters of families:*";
P_HTM[456]="*saṅghādisesā terasāti.**The thirteen offenses entailing suspension.”*";
P_HTM[457]="*3. Aniyatakaṇḍa**3. The chapter on undetermined offenses*";
P_HTM[458]="*Yaṃ tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena paṭhamo aniyato kattha paññatto?**“The first undetermined offense was laid down by the Buddha who knows and sees, the Perfected One, the fully Awakened One. Where was it laid down?*";
P_HTM[459]="*Kaṃ ārabbha?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[460]="*Kismiṃ vatthusmiṃ?**What is it about?*";
P_HTM[461]="*Atthi tattha paññatti, anupaññatti, anuppannapaññatti, sabbatthapaññatti padesapaññatti, sādhāraṇapaññatti asādhāraṇapaññatti, ekatopaññatti ubhatopaññatti, pañcannaṃ pātimokkhuddesānaṃ katthogadhaṃ kattha pariyāpannaṃ, katamena uddesena uddesaṃ āgacchati, catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ katamā vipatti, sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ katamo āpattikkhandho, channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ katihi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhāti, catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ, sattannaṃ samathānaṃ katihi samathehi sammati, ko tattha vinayo, ko tattha abhivinayo, kiṃ tattha pātimokkhaṃ, kiṃ tattha adhipātimokkhaṃ, kā vipatti, kā sampatti, kā paṭipatti, kati atthavase paṭicca bhagavatā paṭhamo aniyato paññatto, ke sikkhanti, ke sikkhitasikkhā, kattha ṭhitaṃ, ke dhārenti, kassa vacanaṃ kenābhatanti.**Is there a rule, an addition to the rule, an unprompted rule? Is it a rule that applies everywhere, or that applies in a particular place? Is it a rule that the monks and nuns have in common, or a rule they do not have in common? Is it a rule for one Sangha or for both Sanghas? In which of the five ways of reciting the Monastic Code is it immersed and included? In which recitation is it included? To which of the four kinds of failure does it belong? To which of the seven classes of offenses does it belong? Through how many of the six kinds of origins of offenses does it originate? To which of the four kinds of legal issues does it belong? Through how many of the seven principles for settling legal issues is it settled? What is the Monastic Law there? What is concerned with the Monastic Law there? What is the Monastic Code there? What is concerned with the Monastic Code there? What is failure? What is success? What is the practice? For how many reasons did the Buddha lay down the first undetermined? Who are those who train? Who have done the training? Established in what? Who master it? Whose pronouncement was it? Who handed it down?”*";
P_HTM[462]="*Yaṃ tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena paṭhamo aniyato kattha paññattoti?**“About the first undetermined offense that was laid down by the Buddha who knows and sees, the Perfected One, the fully Awakened One—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[463]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññatto.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[464]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[465]="*Āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ ārabbha.**Venerable Udāyī.*";
P_HTM[466]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[467]="*Āyasmā udāyī mātugāmena saddhiṃ eko ekāya raho paṭicchanne āsane alaṅkammaniye nisajjaṃ kappesi, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**Udāyī sitting alone with a woman on a private and concealed seat suitable for action.*";
P_HTM[468]="*Atthi tattha paññatti, anupaññatti, anuppannapaññattīti?**“Is there a rule, an addition to the rule, an unprompted rule?”*";
P_HTM[469]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[470]="*Anupaññatti anuppannapaññatti tasmiṃ natthi.**There is no addition to the rule. There is no unprompted rule.*";
P_HTM[471]="*Sabbatthapaññatti, padesapaññattīti?**“Is it a rule that applies everywhere, or that applies in a particular place?”*";
P_HTM[472]="*Sabbatthapaññatti.**That applies everywhere.*";
P_HTM[473]="*Sādhāraṇapaññatti, asādhāraṇapaññattīti?**“Is it a rule that the monks and nuns have in common, or a rule they do not have in common?”*";
P_HTM[474]="*Asādhāraṇapaññatti.**A rule they do not have in common.*";
P_HTM[475]="*Ekatopaññatti, ubhatopaññattīti?**“Is it a rule for one Sangha or for both Sanghas?”*";
P_HTM[476]="*Ekatopaññatti.**For one Sangha.*";
P_HTM[477]="*Pañcannaṃ pātimokkhuddesānaṃ katthogadhaṃ kattha pariyāpannanti?**“In which of the five ways of reciting the Monastic Code is it immersed and included?”*";
P_HTM[478]="*Nidānogadhaṃ nidānapariyāpannaṃ.**In the introduction.*";
P_HTM[479]="*Katamena uddesena uddesaṃ āgacchatīti?**“In which recitation is it included?”*";
P_HTM[480]="*Catutthena uddesena uddesaṃ āgacchati.**In the fourth recitation.*";
P_HTM[481]="*Catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ katamā vipattīti?**“To which of the four kinds of failure does it belong?”*";
P_HTM[482]="*Siyā sīlavipatti siyā ācāravipatti.**Failure in conduct.*";
P_HTM[483]="*Sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ katamo āpattikkhandhoti?**“To which of the seven classes of offenses does it belong?”*";
P_HTM[484]="*Siyā pārājikāpattikkhandho siyā saṅghādisesāpattikkhandho siyā pācittiyāpattikkhandho.**It may be in the class of offenses entailing expulsion, in the class of offenses entailing suspension, or in the class of offenses entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[485]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ katihi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhātīti?**“Through how many of the six kinds of origins of offenses does it originate?”*";
P_HTM[486]="*Ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhāti—**It originates in one way:*";
P_HTM[487]="*kāyato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhāti, na vācato.**from body and mind, not from speech.*";
P_HTM[488]="*Catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ katamaṃ adhikaraṇanti?**“To which of the four kinds of legal issues does it belong?”*";
P_HTM[489]="*Āpattādhikaraṇaṃ.**Legal issues arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[490]="*Sattannaṃ samathānaṃ katihi samathehi sammatīti?**“Through how many of the seven principles for settling legal issues is it settled?”*";
P_HTM[491]="*Tīhi samathehi sammati—**Through three of them:*";
P_HTM[492]="*siyā sammukhāvinayena ca paṭiññātakaraṇena ca, siyā sammukhāvinayena ca tiṇavatthārakena ca.**it may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by acting according to what has been admitted; or it may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[493]="*Ko tattha vinayo, ko tattha abhivinayoti?**“What is the Monastic Law there? What is concerned with the Monastic Law there?”*";
P_HTM[494]="*Paññatti vinayo, vibhatti abhivinayo.**The rules are the Monastic Law. Their analysis is concerned with the Monastic Law.*";
P_HTM[495]="*Kiṃ tattha pātimokkhaṃ, kiṃ tattha adhipātimokkhanti?**“What is the Monastic Code there? What is concerned with the Monastic Code there?”*";
P_HTM[496]="*Paññatti pātimokkhaṃ, vibhatti adhipātimokkhaṃ.**The rules are the Monastic Code. Their analysis is concerned with the Monastic Code.*";
P_HTM[497]="*Kā vipattīti?**“What is failure?”*";
P_HTM[498]="*Asaṃvaro vipatti.**Lack of restraint.*";
P_HTM[499]="*Kā sampattīti?**“What is success?”*";
P_HTM[500]="*Saṃvaro sampatti.**Restraint.*";
P_HTM[501]="*Kā paṭipattīti?**“What is the practice?”*";
P_HTM[502]="*Na evarūpaṃ karissāmīti yāvajīvaṃ āpāṇakoṭikaṃ samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu.**Thinking, “I will not do such a thing,” one undertakes to train in the training rules for life.*";
P_HTM[503]="*Kati atthavase paṭicca bhagavatā paṭhamo aniyato paññattoti?**“For how many reasons did the Buddha lay down the first undetermined offense?”*";
P_HTM[504]="*Dasa atthavase paṭicca bhagavatā paṭhamo aniyato paññatto—**He lay it down for the following ten reasons:*";
P_HTM[505]="*saṅghasuṭṭhutāya, saṅghaphāsutāya, dummaṅkūnaṃ puggalānaṃ niggahāya, pesalānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ phāsuvihārāya, diṭṭhadhammikānaṃ āsavānaṃ saṃvarāya, samparāyikānaṃ āsavānaṃ paṭighātāya, appasannānaṃ pasādāya, pasannānaṃ bhiyyobhāvāya, saddhammaṭṭhitiyā, vinayānuggahāya.**for the well-being of the Sangha, for the comfort of the Sangha, for the restraint of bad people, for the ease of good monks, for the restraint of corruptions relating to the present life, for the restraint of corruptions relating to future lives, to give rise to confidence in those without it, to increase the confidence of those who have it, for the longevity of the true Teaching, and for supporting the training.*";
P_HTM[506]="*Ke sikkhantīti?**“Who are those who train?”*";
P_HTM[507]="*Sekkhā ca puthujjanakalyāṇakā ca sikkhanti.**They are the trainees and the good ordinary people.*";
P_HTM[508]="*Ke sikkhitasikkhāti?**“Who have done the training?”*";
P_HTM[509]="*Arahanto sikkhitasikkhā.**The perfected ones.*";
P_HTM[510]="*Kattha ṭhitanti?**“Established in what?”*";
P_HTM[511]="*Sikkhākāmesu ṭhitaṃ.**In fondness for the training.*";
P_HTM[512]="*Ke dhārentīti?**“Who master it?”*";
P_HTM[513]="*Yesaṃ vattati te dhārenti.**Those who learn it.*";
P_HTM[514]="*Kassa vacananti?**“Whose pronouncement was it?”*";
P_HTM[515]="*Bhagavato vacanaṃ arahato sammāsambuddhassa.**It was the pronouncement of the Buddha, the Perfected One, the fully Awakened One.*";
P_HTM[516]="*Kenābhatanti?**“Who handed it down?”*";
P_HTM[517]="*Paramparābhataṃ—**The lineage:*";
P_HTM[518]="*Upāli dāsako ceva,**“Upāli and Dāsaka,*";
P_HTM[519]="*soṇako siggavo tathā;**Soṇaka and also Siggava;*";
P_HTM[520]="*Moggaliputtena pañcamā,**With Moggaliputta as the fifth—*";
P_HTM[521]="*ete jambusirivhaye.**these were in India, the land named after the glorious rose apple.*";
P_HTM[522]="*Tato mahindo iṭṭiyo,**Then Mahinda, Iṭṭiya,*";
P_HTM[523]="*uttiyo sambalo tathā;**Uttiya and also Sambala,*";
P_HTM[524]="*Bhaddanāmo ca paṇḍito.**And the wise one named Bhadda:*";
P_HTM[525]="*Ete nāgā mahāpaññā,**These mighty beings of great wisdom,*";
P_HTM[526]="*jambudīpā idhāgatā;**Came here from India,*";
P_HTM[527]="*Vinayaṃ te vācayiṃsu,**And they taught the Collection on Monastic Law*";
P_HTM[528]="*piṭakaṃ tambapaṇṇiyā.**in Sri Lanka,*";
P_HTM[529]="*Nikāye pañca vācesuṃ,**And the five Collections of Discourses,*";
P_HTM[530]="*satta ceva pakaraṇe;**and the seven works of philosophy.*";
P_HTM[531]="*Tato ariṭṭho medhāvī,**Then Ariṭṭha the discerning,*";
P_HTM[532]="*tissadatto ca paṇḍito.**And the wise Tissadatta;*";
P_HTM[533]="*Visārado kāḷasumano,**The confident Kālasumana,*";
P_HTM[534]="*thero ca dīghanāmako;**The senior monk named Dīgha,*";
P_HTM[535]="*Dīghasumano ca paṇḍito.**And the wise Dīghasumana;*";
P_HTM[536]="*Punadeva kāḷasumano,**Another Kālasumana,*";
P_HTM[537]="*Nāgatthero ca buddharakkhito;**The senior monk Nāga and Buddharakkhita,*";
P_HTM[538]="*Tissatthero ca medhāvī,**The discerning senior monk Tissa,*";
P_HTM[539]="*Devatthero ca paṇḍito.**And the wise senior monk Deva;*";
P_HTM[540]="*Punadeva sumano medhāvī,**Another discerning Sumana,*";
P_HTM[541]="*Vinaye ca visārado;**Confident in the Monastic Law,*";
P_HTM[542]="*Bahussuto cūḷanāgo,**The learned Cūlanāga,*";
P_HTM[543]="*Gajova duppadhaṃsiyo.**Invincible, like an elephant,*";
P_HTM[544]="*Dhammapālitanāmo ca,**And the senior monk Dhammapālita;*";
P_HTM[545]="*rohaṇe sādhupūjito;**Rohaṇa, venerated as a saint,*";
P_HTM[546]="*Tassa sisso mahāpañño,**And his student Khema of great wisdom,*";
P_HTM[547]="*khemanāmo tipeṭako.**A master of the three Collections,*";
P_HTM[548]="*Dīpe tārakarājāva,**Like the king of the stars on the island,*";
P_HTM[549]="*paññāya atirocatha;**He outshone others in his wisdom;*";
