P_HTM[579]="*piṭakaṃ tambapaṇṇiyāti.**On the island of Sri Lanka.”*";
P_HTM[580]="*Yaṃ tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena dutiyo aniyato kattha paññattoti?**“About the second undetermined offense that was laid down by the Buddha who knows and sees, the Perfected One, the fully Awakened One—here was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[581]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññatto.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[582]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[583]="*Āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ ārabbha.**Venerable Udāyī.*";
P_HTM[584]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[585]="*Āyasmā udāyī mātugāmena saddhiṃ eko ekāya raho nisajjaṃ kappesi, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**Udāyī sitting alone with a woman in private.*";
P_HTM[586]="*Atthi tattha paññatti, anupaññatti anuppannapaññattīti?**“Is there a rule, an addition to the rule, an unprompted rule?”*";
P_HTM[587]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[588]="*Anupaññatti anuppannapaññatti tasmiṃ natthi.**There is no addition to the rule. There is no unprompted rule.*";
P_HTM[589]="*Sabbatthapaññatti, padesapaññattīti?**“Is it a rule that applies everywhere, or that applies in a particular place?”*";
P_HTM[590]="*Sabbatthapaññatti.**That applies everywhere.*";
P_HTM[591]="*Sādhāraṇapaññatti asādhāraṇapaññattīti?**“Is it a rule that the monks and nuns have in common, or a rule they do not have in common?”*";
P_HTM[592]="*Asādhāraṇapaññatti.**A rule they do not have in common.*";
P_HTM[593]="*Ekatopaññatti ubhatopaññattīti?**“Is it a rule for one Sangha or for both Sanghas?”*";
P_HTM[594]="*Ekatopaññatti.**For one Sangha.*";
P_HTM[595]="*Pañcannaṃ pātimokkhuddesānaṃ katthogadhaṃ kattha pariyāpannanti?**“In which of the five ways of reciting the Monastic Code is it immersed and included?”*";
P_HTM[596]="*Nidānogadhaṃ nidānapariyāpannaṃ.**In the introduction.*";
P_HTM[597]="*Katamena uddesena uddesaṃ āgacchatīti?**“In which recitation is it included?”*";
P_HTM[598]="*Catutthena uddesena uddesaṃ āgacchati.**In the fourth recitation.*";
P_HTM[599]="*Catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ katamā vipattīti?**“To which of the four kinds of failure does it belong?”*";
P_HTM[600]="*Siyā sīlavipatti, siyā ācāravipatti.**It may be failure in morality or failure in conduct.*";
P_HTM[601]="*Sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ katamo āpattikkhandhoti?**“To which of the seven classes of offenses does it belong?”*";
P_HTM[602]="*Siyā saṅghādisesāpattikkhandho, siyā pācittiyāpattikkhandho.**It may be in the class of offenses entailing suspension, or in the class of offenses entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[603]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ katihi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhātīti?**“Through how many of the six kinds of origins of offenses does it originate?”*";
P_HTM[604]="*Tīhi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhāti—**It originates in three ways:*";
P_HTM[605]="*siyā kāyato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhāti, na vācato;**from body and mind, not from speech; or*";
P_HTM[606]="*siyā vācato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhāti, na kāyato;**from speech and mind, not from body; or*";
P_HTM[607]="*siyā kāyato ca vācato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhāti.**from body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[608]="*Catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ katamaṃ adhikaraṇanti?**“To which of the four kinds of legal issues does it belong?”*";
P_HTM[609]="*Āpattādhikaraṇaṃ.**Legal issues arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[610]="*Sattannaṃ samathānaṃ katihi samathehi sammatīti?**“Through how many of the seven principles for settling legal issues is it settled?”*";
P_HTM[611]="*Tīhi samathehi sammati—**Through three of them:*";
P_HTM[612]="*siyā sammukhāvinayena ca paṭiññātakaraṇena ca, siyā sammukhāvinayena ca tiṇavatthārakena ca …pe….**it may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by acting according to what has been admitted; or it may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by covering over as if with grass. …*";
P_HTM[613]="*Dve aniyatā niṭṭhitā.**The two undetermined offense are finished.*";
P_HTM[614]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[615]="*Alaṅkammaniyañceva,**“Suitable for action,*";
P_HTM[616]="*tatheva ca na heva kho;**And then not so;*";
P_HTM[617]="*Aniyatā supaññattā,**The undetermined offenses have been well laid down*";
P_HTM[618]="*buddhaseṭṭhena tādināti.**By the Stable One, the Buddha who is the best.”*";
P_HTM[619]="*4. Nissaggiyakaṇḍa**4. The chapter on relinquishment*";
P_HTM[620]="*4.1 Kathinavagga**4.1 The sub-chapter on the robe-making season*";
P_HTM[621]="*Yaṃ tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena atirekacīvaraṃ dasāhaṃ atikkāmentassa nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ kattha paññattanti?**“The offense entailing relinquishment and confession for keeping an extra robe more than ten days that was laid down by the Buddha who knows and sees, the Perfected One, the fully Awakened One—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[622]="*Vesāliyaṃ paññattaṃ.**At Vesālī.*";
P_HTM[623]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[624]="*Chabbaggiye bhikkhū ārabbha.**The monks from the group of six.*";
P_HTM[625]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[626]="*Chabbaggiyā bhikkhū atirekacīvaraṃ dhāresuṃ, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**Those monks keeping an extra robe.*";
P_HTM[627]="*Ekā paññatti, ekā anupaññatti.**There is one rule. There is one addition to the rule.*";
P_HTM[628]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ dvīhi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhāti—**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in two ways:*";
P_HTM[629]="*siyā kāyato ca vācato ca samuṭṭhāti, na cittato;**from body and speech, not from mind; or*";
P_HTM[630]="*siyā kāyato ca vācato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhāti …pe….**from body, speech, and mind. …*";
P_HTM[631]="*Ekarattaṃ ticīvarena vippavasantassa nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ kattha paññattanti?**“The offense entailing relinquishment and confession for staying apart from one’s three robes for one day—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[632]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññattaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[633]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[634]="*Sambahule bhikkhū ārabbha.**A number of monks.*";
P_HTM[635]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[636]="*Sambahulā bhikkhū bhikkhūnaṃ hatthe cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā santaruttarena janapadacārikaṃ pakkamiṃsu, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**Those monks storing one of their robes with other monks and then leaving to wander the country in a sarong and an upper robe.*";
P_HTM[637]="*Ekā paññatti, ekā anupaññatti.**There is one rule. There is one addition to the rule.*";
P_HTM[638]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ dvīhi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhāti—**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in two ways:*";
P_HTM[639]="*siyā kāyato ca vācato ca samuṭṭhāti, na cittato;**from body and speech, not from mind; or*";
P_HTM[640]="*siyā kāyato ca vācato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhāti …pe….**from body, speech, and mind. …*";
P_HTM[641]="*Akālacīvaraṃ paṭiggahetvā māsaṃ atikkāmentassa nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ kattha paññattanti?**“The offense entailing relinquishment and confession for receiving out-of-season robe-cloth and then keeping it for more than a month—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[642]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññattaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[643]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[644]="*Sambahule bhikkhū ārabbha.**A number monks.*";
P_HTM[645]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[646]="*Sambahulā bhikkhū akālacīvaraṃ paṭiggahetvā māsaṃ atikkāmesuṃ, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**Those monks receiving out-of-season robe-cloth and then keeping it for more than a month.*";
P_HTM[647]="*Ekā paññatti, ekā anupaññatti.**There is one rule. There is one addition to the rule.*";
P_HTM[648]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ dvīhi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhāti—**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in two ways:*";
