P_HTM[666]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ chahi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhāti …pe….**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in six ways: …*";
P_HTM[667]="*Aññātakaṃ gahapatiṃ vā gahapatāniṃ vā cīvaraṃ viññāpentassa nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ kattha paññattanti?**“The offense entailing relinquishment and confession for asking an unrelated male or female householder for a robe—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[668]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññattaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
