P_HTM[670]="*Āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ ārabbha.**Venerable Upananda the Sakyan.*";
P_HTM[671]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[672]="*Āyasmā upanando sakyaputto aññātakaṃ seṭṭhiputtaṃ cīvaraṃ viññāpesi, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**Upananda asking the son of an unrelated merchant for a robe.*";
P_HTM[673]="*Ekā paññatti ekā anupaññatti.**There is one rule. There is one addition to the rule.*";
P_HTM[674]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ chahi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhāti …pe….**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in six ways: …*";
P_HTM[675]="*Aññātakaṃ gahapatiṃ vā gahapatāniṃ vā tatuttari cīvaraṃ viññāpentassa nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ kattha paññattanti?**“The offense entailing relinquishment and confession for asking an unrelated male or female householder for too much robe-cloth—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[676]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññattaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[677]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
