P_HTM[679]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[680]="*Chabbaggiyā bhikkhū na mattaṃ jānitvā bahuṃ cīvaraṃ viññāpesuṃ, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**Those monks not knowing moderation and asking for much robe-cloth.*";
P_HTM[681]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[682]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ chahi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhāti …pe….**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in six ways: …*";
P_HTM[683]="*Pubbe appavāritassa aññātakaṃ gahapatikaṃ upasaṅkamitvā cīvare vikappaṃ āpajjantassa nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ kattha paññattanti?**“The offense entailing relinquishment and confession for, without first being invited, going to an unrelated householder and specifying the kind of robe one wants—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[684]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññattaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
