P_HTM[1204]="*Bhikkhuṃ bhuttāviṃ pavāritaṃ anatirittena khādanīyena vā bhojanīyena vā abhihaṭṭhuṃ pavārentassa pācittiyaṃ kattha paññattanti?**“The offense entailing confession for inviting a monk, whom he knows has finished his meal and refused an invitation to eat more, to eat fresh or cooked food that is not left over—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[1205]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññattaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[1206]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[1207]="*Aññataraṃ bhikkhuṃ ārabbha.**A certain monk.*";
P_HTM[1208]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[1209]="*Aññataro bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ bhuttāviṃ pavāritaṃ anatirittena bhojanīyena abhihaṭṭhuṃ pavāresi, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**That monk inviting a monk, whom he knew had finished his meal and refused an invitation to eat more, to eat food that was not left over.*";
P_HTM[1210]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[1211]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ tīhi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhāti …pe….**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in three ways: …*";
P_HTM[1212]="*Vikāle khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā bhuñjantassa pācittiyaṃ kattha paññattanti?**“The offense entailing confession for eating fresh or cooked food at the wrong time—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[1213]="*Rājagahe paññattaṃ.**At Rājagaha.*";
P_HTM[1214]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[1215]="*Sattarasavaggiye bhikkhū ārabbha.**The monks from the group of seventeen.*";
P_HTM[1216]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[1217]="*Sattarasavaggiyā bhikkhū vikāle bhojanaṃ bhuñjiṃsu, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**Those monks eating at the wrong time.*";
P_HTM[1218]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[1219]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ dvīhi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhāti eḷakalomake …pe….**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in two ways: (as in the rule on wool) …*";
P_HTM[1220]="*Sannidhikārakaṃ khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā bhuñjantassa pācittiyaṃ kattha paññattanti?**“The offense entailing confession for storing and then eating fresh or cooked food—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[1221]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññattaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[1222]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[1223]="*Āyasmantaṃ belaṭṭhasīsaṃ ārabbha.**Venerable Belaṭṭhasīsa.*";
P_HTM[1224]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[1225]="*Āyasmā belaṭṭhasīso sannidhikārakaṃ bhojanaṃ bhuñji, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**Belaṭṭhasīsa storing food and then eating it.*";
P_HTM[1226]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[1227]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ dvīhi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhāti eḷakalomake …pe….**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in two ways: (as in the rule on wool) …*";
P_HTM[1228]="*Paṇītabhojanāni attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjantassa pācittiyaṃ kattha paññattanti?**“The offense entailing confession for eating fine foods that one has asked for oneself—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[1229]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññattaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[1230]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[1231]="*Chabbaggiye bhikkhū ārabbha.**The monks from the group of six.*";
P_HTM[1232]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[1233]="*Chabbaggiyā bhikkhū paṇītabhojanāni attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjiṃsu, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**Those monks eating fine foods that they themselves had asked for.*";
