P_HTM[1245]="*5.5. Acelakavagga**5.5 The sub-chapter on naked ascetics*";
P_HTM[1246]="*Acelakassa vā paribbājakassa vā paribbājikāya vā sahatthā khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā dentassa pācittiyaṃ kattha paññattanti?**“The offense entailing confession for giving fresh or cooked food to a naked ascetic, to a male wanderer, or to a female wanderer with one’s own hands—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[1247]="*Vesāliyaṃ paññattaṃ.**At Vesālī.*";
P_HTM[1248]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[1249]="*Āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ ārabbha.**Venerable Ānanda.*";
P_HTM[1250]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[1251]="*Āyasmā ānando aññatarissā paribbājikāya ekaṃ maññamāno dve pūve adāsi, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**Ānanda giving two pastries, thinking they were one, to a certain a female wanderer.*";
P_HTM[1252]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[1253]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ dvīhi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhāti eḷakalomake …pe….**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in two ways: (as in the rule on wool) …*";
P_HTM[1254]="*Bhikkhuṃ “ehāvuso, gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā piṇḍāya pavisissāmā”ti tassa dāpetvā vā adāpetvā vā uyyojentassa pācittiyaṃ kattha paññattanti?**“The offense entailing confession for saying to a monk, “Come, let’s go to the village or town for alms,” and then, whether he has had food given to him or not, sending him away—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[1255]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññattaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[1256]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[1257]="*Āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ ārabbha.**Venerable Upananda the Sakyan.*";
P_HTM[1258]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[1259]="*Āyasmā upanando sakyaputto bhikkhuṃ “ehāvuso, gāmaṃ piṇḍāya pavisissāmā”ti, tassa adāpetvā uyyojesi, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**Upananda saying to a monk, “Come, let’s go to the village or town for alms,” and then, without having had food given to him, sending him away.*";
P_HTM[1260]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[1261]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ tīhi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhāti …pe….**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in three ways: …*";
P_HTM[1262]="*Sabhojane kule anupakhajja nisajjaṃ kappentassa pācittiyaṃ kattha paññattanti?**“The offense entailing confession for sitting down intruding on a lustful couple—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[1263]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññattaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[1264]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[1265]="*Āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ ārabbha.**Venerable Upananda the Sakyan.*";
P_HTM[1266]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[1267]="*Āyasmā upanando sakyaputto sabhojane kule anupakhajja nisajjaṃ kappesi, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**Upananda sitting down intruding on a lustful couple.*";
