P_HTM[1296]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ dvīhi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhāti kathinake …pe….**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in two ways: (as in the sub-chapter on the robe-making season) …*";
P_HTM[1297]="*Tatuttari bhesajjaṃ viññāpentassa pācittiyaṃ kattha paññattanti?**“The offense entailing confession for asking for more medicines than that—where was it laid down?”*";
