P_HTM[1392]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ dvīhi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhāti eḷakalomake …pe….**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in two ways: (as in the rule on wool) …*";
P_HTM[1393]="*Anādiyitvā tiṇṇaṃ dubbaṇṇakaraṇānaṃ aññataraṃ dubbaṇṇakaraṇaṃ navaṃ cīvaraṃ paribhuñjantassa pācittiyaṃ kattha paññattanti?**“The offense entailing confession for using a new robe without first applying one of the three kinds of stain—where was it laid down?”*";
