P_HTM[2171]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhāti—**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in one way:*";
P_HTM[2172]="*kāyato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhāti, na vācato …pe….**from body and mind, not from speech. …*";
P_HTM[2173]="*Pādukavaggo sattamo.**The seventh sub-chapter on shoes is finished.*";
P_HTM[2174]="*Pañcasattati sekhiyā niṭṭhitā.**The seventy-five rules to be trained in are finished.*";
P_HTM[2175]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[2176]="*Parimaṇḍalaṃ paṭicchannaṃ,**“Evenly all around, covered,*";
P_HTM[2177]="*susaṃvutokkhittacakkhu;**Well-restrained, lowered eyes;*";
P_HTM[2178]="*Ukkhittojjagghikā saddo,**Lifted robe, laughing loudly, noise,*";
P_HTM[2179]="*tayo ceva pacālanā.**And three on swaying.*";
P_HTM[2180]="*Khambhaṃ oguṇṭhito cevuk-**Akimbo, and head covered,*";
P_HTM[2181]="*kuṭipallatthikāya ca;**Squatting on the heels, and sitting with clasped knees;*";
P_HTM[2182]="*Sakkaccaṃ pattasaññī ca,**Respectfully, and attention on the bowl,*";
P_HTM[2183]="*samasūpaṃ samatittikaṃ.**An even measure of bean curry, an even level.*";
P_HTM[2184]="*Sakkaccaṃ pattasaññī ca,**Respectfully, and attention on the bowl,*";
P_HTM[2185]="*sapadānaṃ samasūpakaṃ;**In order, an even measure of bean curry;*";
P_HTM[2186]="*Thūpakato paṭicchannaṃ,**Making a heap, covering,*";
P_HTM[2187]="*viññattujjhānasaññinā.**Asking, finding fault.*";
P_HTM[2188]="*Na mahantaṃ maṇḍalaṃ dvāraṃ,**Not large, round, mouth,*";
P_HTM[2189]="*Sabbaṃ hatthaṃ na byāhare;**Whole hand, should not speak;*";
P_HTM[2190]="*Ukkhepo chedanā gaṇḍo,**Lifted, breaking up, cheek,*";
P_HTM[2191]="*Dhunaṃ sitthāvakārakaṃ.**Shaking, scattering rice about.*";
P_HTM[2192]="*Jivhānicchārakañceva,**And sticking out the tongue,*";
P_HTM[2193]="*capucapu surusuru;**Chomping, slurping;*";
P_HTM[2194]="*Hattho patto ca oṭṭho ca,**Hand, and bowl, and lips,*";
P_HTM[2195]="*sāmisaṃ sitthakena ca.**With food, and containing rice.*";
P_HTM[2196]="*Chattapāṇissa saddhammaṃ,**To one holding a sunshade,*";
P_HTM[2197]="*na desenti tathāgatā;**The Buddhas do not give the true Teaching;*";
P_HTM[2198]="*Evameva daṇḍapāṇissa,**Nor to one holding a staff,*";
P_HTM[2199]="*satthaāvudhapāṇinaṃ.**A knife, or a weapon.*";
P_HTM[2200]="*Pādukā upāhanā ceva,**Shoes, and sandals,*";
P_HTM[2201]="*yānaseyyāgatassa ca;**And to one in a vehicle, and to one lying down;*";
P_HTM[2202]="*Pallatthikā nisinnassa,**To one seated clasping their knees,*";
P_HTM[2203]="*veṭhitoguṇṭhitassa ca.**To one with a headdress, and to one with a covered head.*";
P_HTM[2204]="*Chamā nīcāsane ṭhāne,**The ground, on a low seat, standing,*";
P_HTM[2205]="*pacchato uppathena ca;**Behind, and off the path;*";
P_HTM[2206]="*Ṭhitakena na kātabbaṃ,**Not to be done while standing,*";
P_HTM[2207]="*harite udakamhi cāti.**On cultivated plants, and in water.”*";
P_HTM[2208]="*Tesaṃ vaggānamuddānaṃ**This is the summary of the sub-chapters:*";
P_HTM[2209]="*Parimaṇḍalaujjagghi,**“Evenly all around, laughing loudly,*";
P_HTM[2210]="*khambhaṃ piṇḍaṃ tatheva ca;**Akimbo, and also almsfood;*";
P_HTM[2211]="*Kabaḷā surusuru ca,**Mouthfuls, and slurping,*";
P_HTM[2212]="*pādukena ca sattamāti.**And with shoes as the seventh.”*";
P_HTM[2213]="*Mahāvibhaṅge katthapaññattivāro niṭṭhito.**The section on “where it was laid down” in the great analysis is finished.*";
P_HTM[2214]="*124. Paṭhamabhāga **124.  Part one *";
P_HTM[2215]="*Katāpattivāra**The section on “how many offenses”*";
P_HTM[2216]="*1. Pārājikakaṇḍa**1. The chapter on offenses entailing expulsion*";
P_HTM[2217]="*Methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevanto kati āpattiyo āpajjati?**When having sexual intercourse, how many kinds of offenses does one commit?*";
P_HTM[2218]="*Methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevanto tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.**One commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2219]="*Akkhāyite sarīre methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevati, āpatti pārājikassa;**when one has sexual intercourse with an undecomposed corpse, one commits an offense entailing expulsion;*";
P_HTM[2220]="*yebhuyyena khāyite sarīre methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevati, āpatti thullaccayassa;**when one has sexual intercourse with a mostly decomposed corpse, one commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[2221]="*vaṭṭakate mukhe acchupantaṃ aṅgajātaṃ paveseti, āpatti dukkaṭassa—**when one inserts the penis without touching into a wide open mouth, one commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2222]="*methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevanto imā tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[2223]="*Adinnaṃ ādiyanto kati āpattiyo āpajjati?**When stealing, how many kinds of offenses does one commit?*";
P_HTM[2224]="*Adinnaṃ ādiyanto tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.**One commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2225]="*Pañcamāsakaṃ vā atirekapañcamāsakaṃ vā agghanakaṃ adinnaṃ theyyasaṅkhātaṃ ādiyati, āpatti pārājikassa;**when, intending to steal, one steals something worth five _māsaka_ coins or more than five _māsakas_, one commits an offense entailing expulsion;*";
P_HTM[2226]="*atirekamāsakaṃ vā ūnapañcamāsakaṃ vā agghanakaṃ adinnaṃ theyyasaṅkhātaṃ ādiyati, āpatti thullaccayassa;**when, intending to steal, one steals something worth more than one _māsaka_ coin but less than five _māsakas_, one commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[2227]="*māsakaṃ vā ūnamāsakaṃ vā agghanakaṃ adinnaṃ theyyasaṅkhātaṃ ādiyati, āpatti dukkaṭassa—**when, intending to steal, one steals something worth one _māsaka_ coin or less than one _māsaka_, one commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2228]="*adinnaṃ ādiyanto imā tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[2229]="*Sañcicca manussaviggahaṃ jīvitā voropento kati āpattiyo āpajjati?**When intentionally killing a human being, how many kinds of offenses does one commit?*";
P_HTM[2230]="*Sañcicca manussaviggahaṃ jīvitā voropento tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.**One commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2231]="*Manussaṃ odissa opātaṃ khaṇati “papatitvā marissatī”ti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when one digs a pit for people, thinking, “Falling into it someone will die,” one commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2232]="*papatite dukkhā vedanā uppajjati, āpatti thullaccayassa;**when the person experiences pain after falling in, one commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[2233]="*marati, āpatti pārājikassa—**when the person dies, one commits an offense entailing expulsion.*";
P_HTM[2234]="*sañcicca manussaviggahaṃ jīvitā voropento imā tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[2235]="*Asantaṃ abhūtaṃ uttarimanussadhammaṃ ullapanto kati āpattiyo āpajjati?**When untruthfully and groundlessly boasting about a superhuman quality, how many kinds of offenses does one commit?*";
P_HTM[2236]="*Asantaṃ abhūtaṃ uttarimanussadhammaṃ ullapanto tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.**One commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2237]="*Pāpiccho icchāpakato asantaṃ abhūtaṃ uttarimanussadhammaṃ ullapati, āpatti pārājikassa;**when, having bad desires, overcome by desire, one claims a non-existent, unreal superhuman quality, one commits an offense entailing expulsion;*";
P_HTM[2238]="*“yo te vihāre vasati, so bhikkhu arahā”ti bhaṇati, paṭivijānantassa āpatti thullaccayassa;**when one says, “Whatever monk lives in your dwelling is a perfected one,” and the listener understands, one commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[2239]="*na paṭivijānantassa āpatti dukkaṭassa—**when the listener does not understand, one commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2240]="*asantaṃ abhūtaṃ uttarimanussadhammaṃ ullapanto imā tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[2241]="*Cattāro pārājikā niṭṭhitā.**The four offenses entailing expulsion are finished.*";
P_HTM[2242]="*2. Saṅghādisesakaṇḍa**2. The chapter on offenses entailing suspension*";
P_HTM[2243]="*(…) Upakkamitvā asuciṃ mocento tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.**(…) When emitting semen by means of effort, one commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2244]="*Ceteti upakkamati muccati, āpatti saṅghādisesassa;**when one intends and makes an effort, and semen is emitted, one commits an offense entailing suspension;*";
P_HTM[2245]="*ceteti upakkamati na muccati, āpatti thullaccayassa;**when one intends and makes an effort, but semen is not emitted, one commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[2246]="*payoge dukkaṭaṃ.**for the effort there is offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2247]="*Mātugāmena saddhiṃ kāyasaṃsaggaṃ samāpajjanto tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.**When making physical contact with a woman, one commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2248]="*Kāyena kāyaṃ āmasati, āpatti saṅghādisesassa;**when one touches body with body, one commits an offense entailing suspension;*";
P_HTM[2249]="*kāyena kāyapaṭibaddhaṃ āmasati, āpatti thullaccayassa;**when one touches what is connected to the body with the body, one commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[2250]="*kāyapaṭibaddhena kāyapaṭibaddhaṃ āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**when one touches what is connected to the body with what is connected to the body, one commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2251]="*Mātugāmaṃ duṭṭhullāhi vācāhi obhāsento tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.**When speaking indecently to a woman, one commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2252]="*Vaccamaggaṃ passāvamaggaṃ ādissa vaṇṇampi bhaṇati, avaṇṇampi bhaṇati, āpatti saṅghādisesassa;**when, referring to the anus or the vagina, one praises and disparages, one commits an offense entailing suspension;*";
P_HTM[2253]="*vaccamaggaṃ passāvamaggaṃ ṭhapetvā adhakkhakaṃ ubbhajāṇumaṇḍalaṃ ādissa vaṇṇampi bhaṇati avaṇṇampi bhaṇati, āpatti thullaccayassa;**when, referring to any part below the collar bone but above the knees, apart from the anus or the vagina, one praises and disparages, one commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[2254]="*kāyapaṭibaddhaṃ ādissa vaṇṇampi bhaṇati avaṇṇampi bhaṇati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**when, referring to anything connected to the body, one praises and disparages, one commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2255]="*Attakāmapāricariyāya vaṇṇaṃ bhāsanto tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.**When commending the satisfaction of one’s own desires, one commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2256]="*Mātugāmassa santike attakāmapāricariyāya vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, āpatti saṅghādisesassa;**when one encourages a woman to satisfy one’s own desires, one commits an offense entailing suspension;*";
P_HTM[2257]="*paṇḍakassa santike attakāmapāricariyāya vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, āpatti thullaccayassa;**when one encourages a _paṇḍaka_ to satisfy one’s own desires, one commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[2258]="*tiracchānagatassa santike attakāmapāricariyāya vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**when one encourages an animal to satisfy one’s own desires, one commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2259]="*Sañcarittaṃ samāpajjanto tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.**When acting as a matchmaker, one commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2260]="*Paṭiggaṇhāti vīmaṃsati paccāharati, āpatti saṅghādisesassa;**when one accepts the mission, finds out the response, and reports back, one commits an offense entailing suspension;*";
P_HTM[2261]="*paṭiggaṇhāti vīmaṃsati na paccāharati, āpatti thullaccayassa;**when one accepts the mission, and finds out the response, but does not report back, one commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[2262]="*paṭiggaṇhāti na vīmaṃsati na paccāharati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**when one accepts the mission, but neither finds out the response, nor reports back, one commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2263]="*Saññācikāya kuṭiṃ kārāpento tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.**When having a hut built by means of begging, one commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2264]="*Kārāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is having it built, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2265]="*ekaṃ piṇḍaṃ anāgate, āpatti thullaccayassa;**when there is one piece left to complete the hut, one commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[2266]="*tasmiṃ piṇḍe āgate, āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**when the last piece is finished, one commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[2267]="*Mahallakaṃ vihāraṃ kārāpento tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.**When having a large dwelling built, one commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2268]="*Kārāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is having it built, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2269]="*ekaṃ piṇḍaṃ anāgate, āpatti thullaccayassa;**when there is one piece left to complete the hut, one commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[2270]="*tasmiṃ piṇḍe āgate, āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**when the last piece is finished, one commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[2271]="*Bhikkhuṃ amūlakena pārājikena dhammena anuddhaṃsento tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.**When groundlessly charging a monk with an offense entailing expulsion, one commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2272]="*Anokāsaṃ kārāpetvā cāvanādhippāyo vadeti, āpatti saṅghādisesena dukkaṭassa;**when, without having obtained his permission, one speaks with the aim of making him leave the monastic life, one commits one offense entailing suspension and one offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2273]="*okāsaṃ kārāpetvā akkosādhippāyo vadeti, āpatti omasavādassa.**when, having obtained his permission, one speaks with the aim of abusing him, one commits an offense for abusive speech.*";
P_HTM[2274]="*Bhikkhuṃ aññabhāgiyassa adhikaraṇassa kiñci desaṃ lesamattaṃ upādāya pārājikena dhammena anuddhaṃsento tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.**When charging a monk with an offense entailing expulsion, using an unrelated legal issue as a pretext, one commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2275]="*Anokāsaṃ kārāpetvā cāvanādhippāyo vadeti, āpatti saṅghādisesena dukkaṭassa;**when, without having obtained his permission, one speaks with the aim of making him leave the monastic life, one commits one offense entailing suspension and one offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2276]="*okāsaṃ kārāpetvā akkosādhippāyo vadeti, āpatti omasavādassa.**when, having obtained his permission, one speaks with the aim of abusing him, one commits an offense for abusive speech.*";
P_HTM[2277]="*Saṅghabhedako bhikkhu yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjanto tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.**When not stopping when pressed up to three times, a monk who is pursuing schism in the Sangha commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2278]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ;**after the motion, he commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2279]="*dvīhi kammavācāhi thullaccayā;**after each of the first two announcements, he commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[2280]="*kammavācāpariyosāne āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**when the last announcement is finished, he commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[2281]="*Bhedakānuvattakā bhikkhū yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjantā tisso āpattiyo āpajjanti.**When not stopping when pressed up to three times, monks who side with a monk who is pursuing schism commit three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2282]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ;**after the motion, they commit an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2283]="*dvīhi kammavācāhi thullaccayā;**after each of the first two announcements, they commit a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[2284]="*kammavācāpariyosāne āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**when the last announcement is finished, they commit an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[2285]="*Dubbaco bhikkhu yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjanto tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.**When not stopping when pressed up to three times, a monk who is difficult to correct commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2286]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ;**after the motion, he commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2287]="*dvīhi kammavācāhi thullaccayā;**after each of the first two announcements, he commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[2288]="*kammavācāpariyosāne āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**when the last announcement is finished, he commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[2289]="*Kuladūsako bhikkhu yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjanto tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.**When not stopping when pressed up to three times, a monk who is a corrupter of families commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2290]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ;**after the motion, he commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2291]="*dvīhi kammavācāhi thullaccayā;**after each of the first two announcements, he commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[2292]="*kammavācāpariyosāne āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**when the last announcement is finished, he commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[2293]="*Terasa saṅghādisesā niṭṭhitā.**The thirteen rules entailing suspension are finished.*";
P_HTM[2294]="*4. Nissaggiyakaṇḍa**4. The chapter on relinquishment*";
P_HTM[2295]="*4.1. Kathinavagga**4.1 The sub-chapter on the robe-making season*";
P_HTM[2296]="*Atirekacīvaraṃ dasāhaṃ atikkāmento ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati.**When keeping an extra robe more than ten days, one commits one kind of offense:*";
P_HTM[2297]="*Nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[2298]="*Ekarattaṃ ticīvarena vippavasanto ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati.**When staying apart from one’s three robes for one day, one commits one kind of offense:*";
P_HTM[2299]="*Nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[2300]="*Akālacīvaraṃ paṭiggahetvā māsaṃ atikkāmento ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati.**When receiving out-of-season robe-cloth and then keeping it for more than a month, one commits one kind of offense:*";
P_HTM[2301]="*Nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[2302]="*Aññātikāya bhikkhuniyā purāṇacīvaraṃ dhovāpento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When having an unrelated nun wash a used robe, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2303]="*Dhovāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is having her wash it, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2304]="*dhovāpite nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**when one has had it washed, one commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[2305]="*Aññātikāya bhikkhuniyā hatthato cīvaraṃ paṭiggaṇhanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When receiving a robe directly from an unrelated nun, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2306]="*Gaṇhāti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of taking it, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2307]="*gahite nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**when one has taken it, one commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[2308]="*Aññātakaṃ gahapatiṃ vā gahapatāniṃ vā cīvaraṃ viññāpento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When asking an unrelated male or female householder for a robe, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2309]="*Viññāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of asking, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2310]="*viññāpite nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**when one has asked, one commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[2311]="*Aññātakaṃ gahapatiṃ vā gahapatāniṃ vā tatuttari cīvaraṃ viññāpento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When asking an unrelated male or female householder for too much robe-cloth, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2312]="*Viññāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of asking, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2313]="*viññāpite nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**when one has asked, one commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[2314]="*Pubbe appavārito aññātakaṃ gahapatikaṃ upasaṅkamitvā cīvare vikappaṃ āpajjanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When, without first being invited, going to an unrelated householder and specifying the kind of robe one wants, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2315]="*Vikappaṃ āpajjati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of specifying it, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2316]="*vikappaṃ āpanne nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**when one has specified it, one commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[2317]="*Pubbe appavārito aññātake gahapatike upasaṅkamitvā cīvare vikappaṃ āpajjanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When, without first being invited, going to unrelated householders and specifying the kind of robe one wants, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2318]="*Vikappaṃ āpajjati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of specifying it, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2319]="*vikappaṃ āpanne nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**when one has specified it, one commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[2320]="*Atirekatikkhattuṃ codanāya atirekachakkhattuṃ ṭhānena cīvaraṃ abhinipphādento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When getting a robe after prompting more than three times and standing more than six times, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2321]="*Abhinipphādeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is getting it, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2322]="*abhinipphādite nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**when one has got it, one commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[2323]="*Kathinavaggo paṭhamo.**The first sub-chapter on the robe-making season is finished.*";
P_HTM[2324]="*4.2. Kosiyavagga**4.2 The sub-chapter on silk*";
P_HTM[2325]="*Kosiyamissakaṃ santhataṃ kārāpento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When having a blanket made that contains silk, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2326]="*Kārāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is having it made, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2327]="*kārāpite nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**when one has had it made, one commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[2328]="*Suddhakāḷakānaṃ eḷakalomānaṃ santhataṃ kārāpento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When having a blanket made entirely of black wool, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2329]="*Kārāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is having it made, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2330]="*kārāpite nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**when one has had it made, one commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[2331]="*Anādiyitvā tulaṃ odātānaṃ tulaṃ gocariyānaṃ navaṃ santhataṃ kārāpento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When having a new blanket made without using one measure of white wool and one measure of brown, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2332]="*Kārāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is having it made, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2333]="*kārāpite nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**when one has had it made, one commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[2334]="*Anuvassaṃ santhataṃ kārāpento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When having a blanket made every year, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2335]="*Kārāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is having it made, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2336]="*kārāpite nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**when one has had it made, one commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[2337]="*Anādiyitvā purāṇasanthatassa sāmantā sugatavidatthiṃ navaṃ nisīdanasanthataṃ kārāpento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When having a new sitting-blanket made without incorporating a piece of one standard handspan from the border of an old blanket, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2338]="*Kārāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is having it made, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2339]="*kārāpite nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**when one has had it made, one commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[2340]="*Eḷakalomāni paṭiggahetvā tiyojanaṃ atikkāmento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When receiving wool and then taking it more than 40 kilometers, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2341]="*Paṭhamaṃ pādaṃ tiyojanaṃ atikkāmeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when one goes beyond 40 kilometers with the first foot, one commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2342]="*dutiyaṃ pādaṃ atikkāmeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**when one goes beyond with the second foot, one commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[2343]="*Aññātikāya bhikkhuniyā eḷakalomāni dhovāpento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When having an unrelated nun wash wool, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2344]="*Dhovāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is having her wash it, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2345]="*dhovāpite nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**when one has had it washed, one commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[2346]="*Rūpiyaṃ paṭiggaṇhanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When receiving money, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2347]="*Gaṇhāti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of taking it, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2348]="*gahite nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**when one has taken it, one commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[2349]="*Nānappakārakaṃ rūpiyasaṃvohāraṃ samāpajjanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When trading with money in various ways, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2350]="*Samāpajjati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of trading, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2351]="*samāpanne nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**when one has traded, one commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[2352]="*Nānappakārakaṃ kayavikkayaṃ samāpajjanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When bartering in various ways, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2353]="*Samāpajjati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of bartering, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2354]="*samāpanne nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**when one has bartered, one commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[2355]="*Kosiyavaggo dutiyo.**The second sub-chapter on silk is finished.*";
P_HTM[2356]="*4.3. Pattavagga**4.3 The sub-chapter on almsbowls*";
P_HTM[2357]="*Atirekapattaṃ dasāhaṃ atikkāmento ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati.**When keeping an extra almsbowl over ten days, one commits one kind of offense:*";
P_HTM[2358]="*Nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[2359]="*Ūnapañcabandhanena pattena aññaṃ navaṃ pattaṃ cetāpento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When exchanging an almsbowl with less than five mends for a new bowl, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2360]="*Cetāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of exchanging it, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2361]="*cetāpite nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**when one has exchanged it, one commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[2362]="*Bhesajjāni paṭiggahetvā sattāhaṃ atikkāmento ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati.**When receiving medicines and then keeping them for more than seven days, one commits one kind of offense:*";
P_HTM[2363]="*Nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[2364]="*Atirekamāse sese gimhāne vassikasāṭikacīvaraṃ pariyesanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When looking for a rainy-season robe when there is more than a month left of the hot season, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2365]="*Pariyesati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of looking for it, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2366]="*pariyiṭṭhe nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**when one has looked for it, one commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[2367]="*Bhikkhussa sāmaṃ cīvaraṃ datvā kupito anattamano acchindanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When giving away a robe to a monk and then taking it back in anger, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2368]="*Acchindati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of taking it back, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2369]="*acchinne nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**when one has taken it back, one commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[2370]="*Sāmaṃ suttaṃ viññāpetvā tantavāyehi cīvaraṃ vāyāpento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When asking for thread and then having weavers weave robe-cloth, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2371]="*Vāyāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is having it woven, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2372]="*vāyāpite nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**when one has had it woven, one commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[2373]="*Pubbe appavārito aññātakassa gahapatikassa tantavāye upasaṅkamitvā cīvare vikappaṃ āpajjanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When going, without first being invited, to an unrelated householder’s weavers and then specifying the kind of robe-cloth one wants, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2374]="*Vikappaṃ āpajjati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of specifying it, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2375]="*vikappaṃ āpanne nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**when one has specified it, one commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[2376]="*Accekacīvaraṃ paṭiggahetvā cīvarakālasamayaṃ atikkāmento ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati.**When receiving a haste-cloth and then keeping it beyond the robe season, one commits one kind of offense:*";
P_HTM[2377]="*Nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[2378]="*Tiṇṇaṃ cīvarānaṃ aññataraṃ cīvaraṃ antaraghare nikkhipitvā atirekachārattaṃ vippavasanto ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati.**When storing one of one’s three robes in an inhabited area and then staying apart from it for more than six days, one commits one kind of offense:*";
P_HTM[2379]="*Nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[2380]="*Jānaṃ saṅghikaṃ lābhaṃ pariṇataṃ attano pariṇāmento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When diverting to oneself material support that one knows is intended for the Sangha, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2381]="*Pariṇāmeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of diverting it, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2382]="*pariṇāmite nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**when one has diverted it, one commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[2383]="*Pattavaggo tatiyo.**The third sub-chapter on almsbowls is finished.*";
P_HTM[2384]="*Tiṃsa nissaggiyā pācittiyā niṭṭhitā.**The thirty rules on relinquishment and confession are finished.*";
P_HTM[2385]="*5. Pācittiyakaṇḍa**5. The chapter on offenses entailing confession*";
P_HTM[2386]="*5.1. Musāvādavagga**5.1 The sub-chapter on lying*";
P_HTM[2387]="*Sampajānamusāvādaṃ bhāsanto kati āpattiyo āpajjati?**When lying in full awareness, how many kinds of offenses does one commit?*";
P_HTM[2388]="*Sampajānamusāvādaṃ bhāsanto pañca āpattiyo āpajjati.**When lying in full awareness, one commits five kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2389]="*Pāpiccho icchāpakato asantaṃ abhūtaṃ uttarimanussadhammaṃ ullapati, āpatti pārājikassa;**when, having bad desires, overcome by desire, one claims a non-existent, unreal superhuman quality, one commits an offense entailing expulsion;*";
P_HTM[2390]="*bhikkhuṃ amūlakena pārājikena dhammena anuddhaṃseti, āpatti saṅghādisesassa;**when one groundlessly charges a monk with an offense entailing expulsion, one commits an offense entailing suspension;*";
P_HTM[2391]="*“yo te vihāre vasati, so bhikkhu arahā”ti bhaṇati, paṭivijānantassa āpatti thullaccayassa;**when one says, “Whatever monk lives in your dwelling is a perfected one,” and the listener understands, one commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[2392]="*na paṭivijānantassa āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when the listener does not understand, one commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2393]="*sampajānamusāvāde pācittiyaṃ—**when one lies in full awareness, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2394]="*sampajānamusāvādaṃ bhāsanto imā pañca āpattiyo āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[2395]="*Omasanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When speaking abusively, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2396]="*Upasampannaṃ omasati, āpatti pācittiyassa;**when one speaks abusively to one who is fully ordained, one commits an offense entailing confession;*";
P_HTM[2397]="*anupasampannaṃ omasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**when one speaks abusively to one who is not fully ordained, one commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2398]="*Pesuññaṃ upasaṃharanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When engaging in malicious talebearing, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2399]="*Upasampannassa pesuññaṃ upasaṃharati, āpatti pācittiyassa;**when one engages in malicious talebearing to one who is fully ordained, one commits an offense entailing confession;*";
P_HTM[2400]="*anupasampannassa pesuññaṃ upasaṃharati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**when one engages in malicious talebearing to one who is not fully ordained, one commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2401]="*Anupasampannaṃ padaso dhammaṃ vācento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When instructing a person who is not fully ordained to memorize the Teaching, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2402]="*Vāceti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of instructing, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2403]="*pade pade āpatti pācittiyassa.**for every line, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2404]="*Anupasampannena uttaridirattatirattaṃ sahaseyyaṃ kappento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When sleeping more than two or three nights in the same sleeping place as a person who is not fully ordained, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2405]="*Nipajjati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of lying down, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2406]="*nipanne āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one is lying down, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2407]="*Mātugāmena sahaseyyaṃ kappento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When sleeping in the same sleeping place as a woman, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2408]="*Nipajjati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of lying down, then then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2409]="*nipanne āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one is lying down, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2410]="*Mātugāmassa uttarichappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ desento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When giving a teaching of more than five or six sentences to a woman, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2411]="*Deseti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of teaching, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2412]="*pade pade āpatti pācittiyassa.**for every line, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2413]="*Anupasampannassa uttarimanussadhammaṃ bhūtaṃ ārocento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When truthfully telling a person who is not fully ordained of a superhuman quality, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2414]="*Āroceti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of telling, then then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2415]="*ārocite āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has told, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2416]="*Bhikkhussa duṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ anupasampannassa ārocento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When telling a person who is not fully ordained about a monk’s grave offense, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2417]="*Āroceti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of telling, then then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2418]="*ārocite āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has told, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2419]="*Pathaviṃ khaṇanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When digging the earth, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2420]="*Khaṇati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of digging, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2421]="*pahāre pahāre āpatti pācittiyassa.**for every strike, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2422]="*Musāvādavaggo paṭhamo.**The first sub-chapter on lying is finished.*";
P_HTM[2423]="*5.2. Bhūtagāmavagga**5.2 The sub-chapter on plants*";
P_HTM[2424]="*Bhūtagāmaṃ pātento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When having plants felled, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2425]="*Pāteti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is having them felled, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2426]="*pahāre pahāre āpatti pācittiyassa.**for every strike, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2427]="*Aññenaññaṃ paṭicaranto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When speaking evasively, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2428]="*Anāropite aññavādake aññenaññaṃ paṭicarati, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when one speaks evasively without having been charged with evasive speech, one commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2429]="*āropite aññavādake aññenaññaṃ paṭicarati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one speaks evasively after having been charged with evasive speech, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2430]="*Bhikkhuṃ ujjhāpento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When complaining about a monk, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2431]="*Ujjhāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of complaining, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2432]="*ujjhāpite āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has complained, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2433]="*Saṅghikaṃ mañcaṃ vā pīṭhaṃ vā bhisiṃ vā kocchaṃ vā ajjhokāse santharitvā anuddharitvā anāpucchā pakkamanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When taking a bed, a bench, a mattress, or a stool belonging to the Sangha and putting it outside, and then departing without putting it away or taking leave, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2434]="*Paṭhamaṃ pādaṃ leḍḍupātaṃ atikkāmeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when one goes beyond the distance of a stone-throw with the first foot, one commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2435]="*dutiyaṃ pādaṃ atikkāmeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one goes beyond with the second foot, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2436]="*Saṅghike vihāre seyyaṃ santharitvā anuddharitvā anāpucchā pakkamanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When putting out bedding in a dwelling belonging to the Sangha, and then departed without putting it away or taking leave, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2437]="*Paṭhamaṃ pādaṃ parikkhepaṃ atikkāmeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when one crosses the boundary with the first foot, one commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2438]="*dutiyaṃ pādaṃ atikkāmeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one crosses with the second foot, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2439]="*Saṅghike vihāre jānaṃ pubbupagataṃ bhikkhuṃ anupakhajja seyyaṃ kappento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When arranging one’s sleeping place, in a dwelling belonging to the Sangha, in a way that encroaches on a monk that one knows arrived there before one, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2440]="*Nipajjati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of lying down, then then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2441]="*nipanne āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one is lying down, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2442]="*Bhikkhuṃ kupito anattamano saṅghikā vihārā nikkaḍḍhento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When angrily throwing a monk out of a dwelling belonging to the Sangha, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2443]="*Nikkaḍḍhati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of throwing him out, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2444]="*nikkaḍḍhite āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has thrown him out, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2445]="*Saṅghike vihāre uparivehāsakuṭiyā āhaccapādakaṃ mañcaṃ vā pīṭhaṃ vā abhinisīdanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When sitting down on a bed or a bench with detachable legs on an upper story in a dwelling belonging to the Sangha, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2446]="*Abhinisīdati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of sitting down, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2447]="*abhinisinne āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one is seated, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2448]="*Dvattipariyāye adhiṭṭhahitvā tatuttari adhiṭṭhahanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When applying more than two or three courses, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2449]="*Adhiṭṭheti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of applying them, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2450]="*adhiṭṭhite āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has applied them, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2451]="*Jānaṃ sappāṇakaṃ udakaṃ tiṇaṃ vā mattikaṃ vā siñcanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When pouring water that one knows contains living beings onto grass or clay, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2452]="*Siñcati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process pouring, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2453]="*siñcite āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has poured it, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2454]="*Bhūtagāmavaggo dutiyo.**The second sub-chapter on plants is finished.*";
P_HTM[2455]="*5.3. Ovādavagga**5.3 The sub-chapter on the instruction*";
P_HTM[2456]="*Asammato bhikkhuniyo ovadanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When instructing the nuns without being appointed, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2457]="*Ovadati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of instructing, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2458]="*ovadite āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has instructed, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2459]="*Atthaṅgate sūriye bhikkhuniyo ovadanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When instructing the nuns after sunset, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2460]="*Ovadati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of instructing, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2461]="*ovadite āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has instructed, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2462]="*Bhikkhunupassayaṃ upasaṅkamitvā bhikkhuniyo ovadanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When going to the nuns’ dwelling place and instructing the nuns, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2463]="*Ovadati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of instructing, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2464]="*ovadite āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has instructed, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2465]="*“Āmisahetu bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo ovadantī”ti bhaṇanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When saying that the monks are instructing the nuns for the sake of worldly gain, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2466]="*Bhaṇati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of saying it, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2467]="*bhaṇite āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has said it, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2468]="*Aññātikāya bhikkhuniyā cīvaraṃ dento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When giving robe-cloth to an unrelated nun, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2469]="*Deti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of giving it, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2470]="*dinne āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has given it, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2471]="*Aññātikāya bhikkhuniyā cīvaraṃ sibbento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When sewing a robe for an unrelated nun, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2472]="*Sibbeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of sewing it, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2473]="*ārāpathe ārāpathe āpatti pācittiyassa.**for every stitch, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2474]="*Bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When traveling by appointment with a nun, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2475]="*Paṭipajjati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of traveling, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2476]="*paṭipanne āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has traveled, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2477]="*Bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaṃ nāvaṃ abhiruhanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When boarding a boat by appointment with a nun, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2478]="*Abhiruhati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of boarding, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2479]="*abhiruḷhe āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has boarded, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2480]="*Jānaṃ bhikkhuniparipācitaṃ piṇḍapātaṃ bhuñjanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When eating almsfood knowing that a nun had it prepared, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2481]="*“Bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when one receives with the intention to eat, one commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2482]="*ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pācittiyassa.**for every mouthful, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2483]="*Bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ eko ekāya raho nisajjaṃ kappento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When sitting in private alone with a nun, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2484]="*Nisīdati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of sitting down, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2485]="*nisinne āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one is seated, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2486]="*Ovādavaggo tatiyo.**The third sub-chapter on the instruction is finished.*";
P_HTM[2487]="*5.4. Bhojanavagga**5.4 The sub-chapter on eating*";
P_HTM[2488]="*Tatuttari āvasathapiṇḍaṃ bhuñjanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When eating more than that at a public guesthouse, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2489]="*“Bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when one receives with the intention to eat, one commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2490]="*ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pācittiyassa.**for every mouthful, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2491]="*Gaṇabhojanaṃ bhuñjanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When eating in a group, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2492]="*“Bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when one receives with the intention to eat, one commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2493]="*ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pācittiyassa.**for every mouthful, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2494]="*Paramparabhojanaṃ bhuñjanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When eating one meal before another, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2495]="*“Bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when one receives with the intention to eat, one commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2496]="*ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pācittiyassa.**for every mouthful, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2497]="*Dvattipattapūre pūve paṭiggahetvā tatuttari paṭiggaṇhanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When accepting more than two or three bowlfuls of pastries, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2498]="*Gaṇhāti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of taking it, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2499]="*gahite āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has taken it, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2500]="*Bhuttāvī pavārito anatirittaṃ khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā bhuñjanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When having finished one’s meal and refused an invitation to eat more, and then eating fresh or cooked food that is not left over, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2501]="*“Bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when one receives with the intention to eat, one commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2502]="*ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pācittiyassa.**for every mouthful, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2503]="*Bhikkhuṃ bhuttāviṃ pavāritaṃ anatirittena khādanīyena vā bhojanīyena vā abhihaṭṭhuṃ pavārento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When inviting a monk, whom one knows has finished his meal and refused an invitation to eat more, to eat fresh or cooked food that is not left over, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2504]="*Tassa vacanena “khādissāmi bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when, because of what one says, the other receives with the intention to eat, one commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2505]="*bhojanapariyosāne āpatti pācittiyassa.**when the meal is finished, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2506]="*Vikāle khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā bhuñjanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When eating fresh or cooked food at the wrong time, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2507]="*“Khādissāmi bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when one receives with the intention to eat, one commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2508]="*ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pācittiyassa.**for every mouthful, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2509]="*Sannidhikārakaṃ khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā bhuñjanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When storing and then eating fresh or cooked food, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2510]="*“Khādissāmi bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when one receives with the intention to eat, one commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2511]="*ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pācittiyassa.**for every mouthful, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2512]="*Paṇītabhojanāni attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When eating fine foods that one has asked for oneself, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2513]="*“Bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when one receives with the intention to eat, one commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2514]="*ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pācittiyassa.**for every mouthful, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2515]="*Adinnaṃ mukhadvāraṃ āhāraṃ āharanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When eating food that has not been given, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2516]="*“Bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when one receives with the intention to eat, one commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2517]="*ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pācittiyassa.**for every mouthful, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2518]="*Bhojanavaggo catuttho.**The fourth sub-chapter on eating is finished.*";
P_HTM[2519]="*5.5. Acelakavagga**5.5 The sub-chapter on naked ascetics*";
P_HTM[2520]="*Acelakassa vā paribbājakassa vā paribbājikāya vā sahatthā khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā dento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When giving fresh or cooked food to a naked ascetic, to a male wanderer, or to a female wanderer with one’s own hands, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2521]="*Deti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of giving it, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2522]="*dinne āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has given it, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2523]="*Bhikkhuṃ—“ehāvuso, gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā piṇḍāya pavisissāmā”ti tassa dāpetvā vā adāpetvā vā uyyojento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When saying to a monk, “Come, let’s go to the village or town for alms,” and then, whether one has had food given to him or not, sending him away, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2524]="*Uyyojeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of sending him away, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2525]="*uyyojite āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has sent him away, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2526]="*Sabhojane kule anupakhajja nisajjaṃ kappento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When sitting down intruding on a lustful couple, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2527]="*Nisīdati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of sitting down, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2528]="*nisinne āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one is seated, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2529]="*Mātugāmena saddhiṃ raho paṭicchanne āsane nisajjaṃ kappento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When sitting down in private on a concealed seat with a woman, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2530]="*Nisīdati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of sitting down, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2531]="*nisinne āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one is seated, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2532]="*Mātugāmena saddhiṃ eko ekāya raho nisajjaṃ kappento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When sitting down in private alone with a woman, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2533]="*Nisīdati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of sitting down, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2534]="*nisinne āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one is seated, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2535]="*Nimantito sabhatto samāno purebhattaṃ pacchābhattaṃ kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When being invited to a meal and then visiting families beforehand or afterwards, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2536]="*Paṭhamaṃ pādaṃ ummāraṃ atikkāmeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when one crosses the threshold with the first foot, one commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2537]="*dutiyaṃ pādaṃ atikkāmeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one crosses with the second foot, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2538]="*Tatuttari bhesajjaṃ viññāpento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When asking for more medicines than that, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2539]="*Viññāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of asking, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2540]="*viññāpite āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has asked, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2541]="*Uyyuttaṃ senaṃ dassanāya gacchanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When going to see an army, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2542]="*Gacchati, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when one is in the process of going, one commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2543]="*yattha ṭhito passati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**wherever one stands to see it, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2544]="*Atirekatirattaṃ senāya vasanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When staying with the army for more than three nights, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2545]="*Vasati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is staying, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2546]="*vasite āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has stayed, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2547]="*Uyyodhikaṃ gacchanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When going to a battle, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2548]="*Gacchati, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when one is in the process of going, one commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2549]="*yattha ṭhito passati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**wherever one stands to see it, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2550]="*Acelakavaggo pañcamo.**The fifth sub-chapter on naked ascetics is finished.*";
P_HTM[2551]="*5.6. Surāmerayavagga**5.6 The sub-chapter on drinking alcohol*";
P_HTM[2552]="*Majjaṃ pivanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When drinking alcoholic drinks, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2553]="*“Pivissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when one receives with the intention to drink, one commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2554]="*ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pācittiyassa.**for every mouthful, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2555]="*Bhikkhuṃ aṅgulipatodakena hāsento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When making a monk laugh by tickling, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2556]="*Hāseti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of making him laugh, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2557]="*hasite āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has made him laugh, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2558]="*Udake kīḷanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When playing in water, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2559]="*Heṭṭhāgopphake udake kīḷati, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when one is playing in water less than ankle deep, one commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2560]="*uparigopphake kīḷati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one is playing in water more than ankle deep, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2561]="*Anādariyaṃ karonto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When being disrespectful, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2562]="*Karoti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of doing it, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2563]="*kate āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has done it, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2564]="*Bhikkhuṃ bhiṃsāpento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When scaring a monk, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2565]="*Bhiṃsāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of scaring him, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2566]="*bhiṃsāpite āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has scared, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2567]="*Jotiṃ samādahitvā visibbento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When lighting a fire to warm oneself, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2568]="*Samādahati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of lighting it, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2569]="*samādahite āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has lit it, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2570]="*Orenaddhamāsaṃ nahāyanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When bathing at intervals of less than a half-month, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2571]="*Nahāyati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of bathing, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2572]="*nahānapariyosāne āpatti pācittiyassa.**when the bath is finished, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2573]="*Anādiyitvā tiṇṇaṃ dubbaṇṇakaraṇānaṃ aññataraṃ dubbaṇṇakaraṇaṃ navaṃ cīvaraṃ paribhuñjanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When using a new robe without first applying one of the three kinds of stain, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2574]="*Paribhuñjati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is using it, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2575]="*paribhutte āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has used it, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2576]="*Bhikkhussa vā bhikkhuniyā vā sikkhamānāya vā sāmaṇerassa vā sāmaṇeriyā vā sāmaṃ cīvaraṃ vikappetvā appaccuddhāraṇaṃ paribhuñjanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When transfering a robe to a monk, to a nun, to a trainee nun, to a novice monk, or to a novice nun, and then using it without it first being relinquished, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2577]="*Paribhuñjati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is using it, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2578]="*paribhutte āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has used it, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2579]="*Bhikkhussa pattaṃ vā cīvaraṃ vā nisīdanaṃ vā sūcigharaṃ vā kāyabandhanaṃ vā apanidhento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When hiding a monk’s bowl, robe, sitting mat, needle case, or belt, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2580]="*Apanidheti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of hiding it, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2581]="*apanidhite āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has hid it, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2582]="*Surāmerayavaggo chaṭṭho.**The sixth sub-chapter of alcoholic drinks is finished.*";
P_HTM[2583]="*5.7. Sappāṇakavagga**5.7 The sub-chapter on containing living beings*";
P_HTM[2584]="*Sañcicca pāṇaṃ jīvitā voropento kati āpattiyo āpajjati?**When intentionally killing a living being, how many kinds of offenses does one commit?*";
P_HTM[2585]="*Sañcicca pāṇaṃ jīvitā voropento catasso āpattiyo āpajjati.**When intentionally killing a living being, one commits four kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2586]="*Anodissa opātaṃ khaṇati—“yo koci papatitvā marissatī”ti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when one digs a non-specific pit, thinking, “Whatever falls into it will die,” one commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2587]="*manusso tasmiṃ papatitvā marati, āpatti pārājikassa;**when a person falls into it and dies, one commits an offense entailing expulsion;*";
P_HTM[2588]="*yakkho vā peto vā tiracchānagatamanussaviggaho vā tasmiṃ papatitvā marati, āpatti thullaccayassa;**when a spirit, ghost, or animal in human form falls into it and dies, one commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[2589]="*tiracchānagato tasmiṃ papatitvā marati, āpatti pācittiyassa—**when an animal falls into it and dies, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2590]="*sañcicca pāṇaṃ jīvitā voropento imā catasso āpattiyo āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[2591]="*Jānaṃ sappāṇakaṃ udakaṃ paribhuñjanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When using water that one knows contains living beings, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2592]="*Paribhuñjati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is using it, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2593]="*paribhutte āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has used it, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2594]="*Jānaṃ yathādhammaṃ nihatādhikaraṇaṃ punakammāya ukkoṭento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When reopening a legal issue that one knows has been legitimately settled, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2595]="*Ukkoṭeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of reopening it, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2596]="*ukkoṭite āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has reopened it, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2597]="*Bhikkhussa jānaṃ duṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ paṭicchādento ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati, pācittiyaṃ.**When knowingly concealing a monk’s grave offense, one commits one kind of offense: an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2598]="*Jānaṃ ūnavīsativassaṃ puggalaṃ upasampādento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When giving the full ordination to a person one knows is less than twenty years old, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2599]="*Upasampādeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of giving the full ordination, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2600]="*upasampādite āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has given the full ordination, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2601]="*Jānaṃ theyyasatthena saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When knowingly traveling by appointment with a group of thieves, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2602]="*Paṭipajjati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is traveling, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2603]="*paṭipanne āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has traveled, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2604]="*Mātugāmena saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When traveling by appointment with a woman, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2605]="*Paṭipajjati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of traveling, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2606]="*paṭipanne āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has traveled, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2607]="*Pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When not giving up a bad view when pressed up to three times, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2608]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ;**after the motion, one commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2609]="*kammavācāpariyosāne āpatti pācittiyassa.**when the last announcement is finished, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2610]="*Jānaṃ tathāvādinā bhikkhunā akaṭānudhammena taṃ diṭṭhiṃ appaṭinissaṭṭhena saddhiṃ sambhuñjanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When living with a monk who one knows is saying such things, who has not made amends according to the rule, and who has not given up that view, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2611]="*Sambhuñjati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one living with him, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2612]="*sambhutte āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has lived with him, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2613]="*Jānaṃ tathānāsitaṃ samaṇuddesaṃ upalāpento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When supporting a novice monastic who one knows has been expelled in this way, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2614]="*Upalāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one supports him, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2615]="*upalāpite āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has supported him, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2616]="*Sappāṇakavaggo sattamo.**The seventh sub-chapter on containing living beings is finished.*";
P_HTM[2617]="*5.8. Sahadhammikavagga**5.8 The sub-chapter on legitimately*";
P_HTM[2618]="*Bhikkhūhi sahadhammikaṃ vuccamāno—“na tāvāhaṃ, āvuso, etasmiṃ sikkhāpade sikkhissāmi yāva na aññaṃ bhikkhuṃ byattaṃ vinayadharaṃ paripucchissāmī”ti bhaṇanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When legitimately corrected by the monks, saying, “I won’t practice this training rule until I’ve questioned a monk who is an expert on the Monastic Law”, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2619]="*Bhaṇati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of saying it, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2620]="*bhaṇite āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has said it, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2621]="*Vinayaṃ vivaṇṇento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When disparaging the Monastic Law, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2622]="*Vivaṇṇeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of disparaging it, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2623]="*vivaṇṇite āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has disparaged it, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2624]="*Mohento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When deceiving, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2625]="*Anāropite mohe moheti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when one deceives without having been charged with deception, one commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2626]="*āropite mohe moheti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one deceives after having been charged with deception, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2627]="*Bhikkhussa kupito anattamano pahāraṃ dento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When hitting a monk in anger, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2628]="*Paharati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is hitting, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2629]="*pahate āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has hit, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2630]="*Bhikkhussa kupito anattamano talasattikaṃ uggiranto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When raising a hand in anger against a monk, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2631]="*Uggirati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one raises it, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2632]="*uggirite āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has raised it, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2633]="*Bhikkhuṃ amūlakena saṅghādisesena anuddhaṃsento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When groundlessly charging a monk with an offense entailing suspension, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2634]="*Anuddhaṃseti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of making the charge, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2635]="*anuddhaṃsite āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has made the charge, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2636]="*Bhikkhussa sañcicca kukkuccaṃ upadahanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When intentionally making a monk anxious, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2637]="*Upadahati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of doing it, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2638]="*upadahite āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has done it, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2639]="*Bhikkhūnaṃ bhaṇḍanajātānaṃ kalahajātānaṃ vivādāpannānaṃ upassutiṃ tiṭṭhanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When eavesdropping on monks who are arguing and disputing, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2640]="*“Sossāmī”ti gacchati, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when going with the intention to listen, one commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2641]="*yattha ṭhito suṇāti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**wherever one stands to listen, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2642]="*Dhammikānaṃ kammānaṃ chandaṃ datvā pacchā khīyanadhammaṃ āpajjanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When giving one’s consent for legitimate legal procedures and then criticizing them afterwards, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2643]="*Khiyyati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is criticizing, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2644]="*khiyyite āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has criticized, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2645]="*Saṅghe vinicchayakathāya vattamānāya chandaṃ adatvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkamanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When getting up from one’s seat and leaving while the Sangha is in the process of deliberating, without first giving one’s consent, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2646]="*Parisāya hatthapāsaṃ vijahantassa āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when one is in the process of going beyond arm’s reach of the gathering, one commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2647]="*vijahite āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has gone beyond, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2648]="*Samaggena saṅghena cīvaraṃ datvā pacchā khīyanadhammaṃ āpajjanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When giving out a robe together with a unanimous Sangha and then criticizing it afterwards, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2649]="*Khiyyati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is criticizing it, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2650]="*khiyyite āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has criticized it, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2651]="*Jānaṃ saṅghikaṃ lābhaṃ pariṇataṃ puggalassa pariṇāmento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When diverting to an individual material support that he knows was intended for the Sangha, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2652]="*Pariṇāmeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is diverting it, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2653]="*pariṇāmite āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has diverted it, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2654]="*Sahadhammikavaggo aṭṭhamo.**The eighth sub-chapter on legitimately is finished.*";
P_HTM[2655]="*5.9. Rājavagga**5.9 The sub-chapter on kings*";
P_HTM[2656]="*Pubbe appaṭisaṃvidito rañño antepuraṃ pavisanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When entering the royal compound without first being announced, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2657]="*Paṭhamaṃ pādaṃ ummāraṃ atikkāmeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when one crosses the threshold with the first foot, one commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2658]="*dutiyaṃ pādaṃ atikkāmeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one crosses with the second foot, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2659]="*Ratanaṃ uggaṇhanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When picking up precious things, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2660]="*Gaṇhāti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is in the process of taking hold of it, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2661]="*gahite āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has taken hold of it, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2662]="*Santaṃ bhikkhuṃ anāpucchā vikāle gāmaṃ pavisanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When entering a village at the wrong time without taking leave of an available monk, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2663]="*Paṭhamaṃ pādaṃ parikkhepaṃ atikkāmeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when one crosses the boundary with the first foot, one commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2664]="*dutiyaṃ pādaṃ atikkāmeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one crosses with the second foot, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2665]="*Aṭṭhimayaṃ vā dantamayaṃ vā visāṇamayaṃ vā sūcigharaṃ kārāpento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When having a needle case made from bone, ivory, or horn, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2666]="*Kārāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is having it made, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2667]="*kārāpite āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has had it made, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2668]="*Pamāṇātikkantaṃ mañcaṃ vā pīṭhaṃ vā kārāpento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When having a bed or bench made that exceeds the right measure, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2669]="*Kārāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is having it made, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2670]="*kārāpite āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has had it made, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2671]="*Mañcaṃ vā pīṭhaṃ vā tūlonaddhaṃ kārāpento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When having a bed or a bench made upholstered with cotton down, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2672]="*Kārāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is having it made, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2673]="*kārāpite āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has had it made, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2674]="*Pamāṇātikkantaṃ nisīdanaṃ kārāpento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When having a sitting mat made that exceeds the right measure, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2675]="*Kārāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is having it made, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2676]="*kārāpite āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has had it made, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2677]="*Pamāṇātikkantaṃ kaṇḍuppaṭicchādiṃ kārāpento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When having an itch-covering cloth made that exceeds the right measure, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2678]="*Kārāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is having it made, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2679]="*kārāpite āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has had it made, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2680]="*Pamāṇātikkantaṃ vassikasāṭikaṃ kārāpento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When having a rainy-season robe made that exceeds the right measure, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2681]="*Kārāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is having it made, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2682]="*kārāpite āpatti pācittiyassa.**when one has had it made, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2683]="*Sugatacīvarappamāṇaṃ cīvaraṃ kārāpento kati āpattiyo āpajjati?**When having a robe made that is the standard robe measure in size, how many kinds of offenses does one commit?*";
P_HTM[2684]="*Sugatacīvarappamāṇaṃ cīvaraṃ kārāpento dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When having a robe made that is the standard robe measure in size, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2685]="*Kārāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is having it made, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2686]="*kārāpite āpatti pācittiyassa—**when one has had it made, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2687]="*sugatacīvarappamāṇaṃ cīvaraṃ kārāpento imā dve āpattiyo āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[2688]="*Rājavaggo navamo.**The ninth sub-chapter on kings is finished.*";
P_HTM[2689]="*Khuddakā niṭṭhitā.**The section on minor rules is finished.*";
P_HTM[2690]="*6. Pāṭidesanīyakaṇḍa**6. The chapter on offenses entailing acknowledgment*";
P_HTM[2691]="*Aññātikāya bhikkhuniyā antaragharaṃ paviṭṭhāya hatthato khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā sahatthā paṭiggahetvā bhuñjanto kati āpattiyo āpajjati?**When eating fresh or cooked food that was received directly from an unrelated nun who had entered an inhabited area, how many kinds of offenses does one commit?*";
P_HTM[2692]="*Aññātikāya bhikkhuniyā antaragharaṃ paviṭṭhāya hatthato khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā sahatthā paṭiggahetvā bhuñjanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When eating fresh or cooked food that was received directly from an unrelated nun who had entered an inhabited area, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2693]="*“Bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when one receives with the intention to eat, one commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2694]="*ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pāṭidesanīyassa—**for every mouthful, one commits an offense entailing acknowledgment.*";
P_HTM[2695]="*aññātikāya bhikkhuniyā antaragharaṃ paviṭṭhāya hatthato khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā sahatthā paṭiggahetvā bhuñjanto imā dve āpattiyo āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[2696]="*Bhikkhuniyā vosāsantiyā na nivāretvā bhuñjanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When eating without having restrained a nun who is giving directions, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2697]="*“Bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when one receives with the intention to eat, one commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2698]="*ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pāṭidesanīyassa.**for every mouthful, one commits an offense entailing acknowledgment.*";
P_HTM[2699]="*Sekkhasammatesu kulesu khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā sahatthā paṭiggahetvā bhuñjanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When eating fresh or cooked food after personally receiving it from families designated as “in training”, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2700]="*“Bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when one receives with the intention to eat, one commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2701]="*ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pāṭidesanīyassa.**for every mouthful, one commits an offense entailing acknowledgment.*";
P_HTM[2702]="*Āraññakesu senāsanesu pubbe appaṭisaṃviditaṃ khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā ajjhārāme sahatthā paṭiggahetvā bhuñjanto kati āpattiyo āpajjati?**When eating fresh or cooked food after personally receiving it inside a wilderness monastery without first making an announcement, how many kinds of offenses does one commit?*";
P_HTM[2703]="*Āraññakesu senāsanesu pubbe appaṭisaṃviditaṃ khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā ajjhārāme sahatthā paṭiggahetvā bhuñjanto dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When eating fresh or cooked food after personally receiving it inside a wilderness monastery without first making an announcement, one commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2704]="*“Bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when one receives with the intention to eat, one commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[2705]="*ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pāṭidesanīyassa—**for every mouthful, one commits an offense entailing acknowledgment.*";
P_HTM[2706]="*āraññakesu senāsanesu pubbe appaṭisaṃviditaṃ khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā ajjhārāme sahatthā paṭiggahetvā bhuñjanto imā dve āpattiyo āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[2707]="*Cattāro pāṭidesanīyā niṭṭhitā.**The four offenses entailing acknowledgment are finished.*";
P_HTM[2708]="*7. Sekhiyakaṇḍa**7. The chapter on training*";
P_HTM[2709]="*7.1. Parimaṇḍalavagga**7.1 The sub-chapter on evenly all around*";
P_HTM[2710]="*Anādariyaṃ paṭicca purato vā pacchato vā olambento nivāsento kati āpattiyo āpajjati?**When, out of disrespect, one wears one’s sarong hanging down in front or behind, how many kinds of offenses does one commit?*";
P_HTM[2711]="*Anādariyaṃ paṭicca purato vā pacchato vā olambento nivāsento ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati.**When, out of disrespect, one wears one’s sarong hanging down in front or behind, one commits one kind of offense:*";
P_HTM[2712]="*Dukkaṭaṃ—**an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2713]="*anādariyaṃ paṭicca purato vā pacchato vā olambento nivāsento imaṃ ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[2714]="*Anādariyaṃ paṭicca purato vā pacchato vā olambento pārupanto ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati.**When, out of disrespect, one wears one’s upper robe hanging down in front or behind, one commits one kind of offense:*";
P_HTM[2715]="*Dukkaṭaṃ.**an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2716]="*Anādariyaṃ paṭicca kāyaṃ vivaritvā antaraghare gacchanto ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati.**When, out of disrespect, one walks in an inhabited area with one’s body uncovered, one commits one kind of offense:*";
P_HTM[2717]="*Dukkaṭaṃ.**an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2718]="*Anādariyaṃ paṭicca kāyaṃ vivaritvā antaraghare nisīdanto ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati.**When, out of disrespect, one sits in an inhabited area with one’s body uncovered, one commits one kind of offense:*";
P_HTM[2719]="*Dukkaṭaṃ.**an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2720]="*Anādariyaṃ paṭicca hatthaṃ vā pādaṃ vā kīḷāpento antaraghare gacchanto ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati.**When, out of disrespect, one walks in an inhabited area, playing with one’s hands and feet, one commits one kind of offense:*";
P_HTM[2721]="*Dukkaṭaṃ.**an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2722]="*Anādariyaṃ paṭicca hatthaṃ vā pādaṃ vā kīḷāpento antaraghare nisīdanto ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati.**When, out of disrespect, one sits in an inhabited area, playing with one’s hands and feet, one commits one kind of offense:*";
P_HTM[2723]="*Dukkaṭaṃ.**an offense of wrong conduct.*";
