P_HTM[2879]="*124. Paṭhamabhāga **124.  Part one *";
P_HTM[2880]="*3. Vipattivāra**3. The section on failure*";
P_HTM[2881]="*Methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevantassa āpattiyo catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ kati vipattiyo bhajanti?**When it comes to the offenses for having sexual intercourse, to how many of the four kinds of failure do they belong?*";
P_HTM[2882]="*Methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevantassa āpattiyo catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ dve vipattiyo bhajanti—**They belong to two kinds of failure:*";
P_HTM[2883]="*siyā sīlavipattiṃ, siyā ācāravipattiṃ …pe….**they may be failure in morality; they may be failure in conduct. …*";
P_HTM[2884]="*Anādariyaṃ paṭicca udake uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā kheḷaṃ vā karontassa āpatti catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ kati vipattiyo bhajati?**When it comes to the offense for, out of disrespect, defecating, urinating, or spitting in water, to how many of the four kinds of failure does it belong?*";
P_HTM[2885]="*Anādariyaṃ paṭicca udake uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā kheḷaṃ vā karontassa āpatti catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ ekaṃ vipattiṃ bhajati—**It belongs to one kind of failure:*";
P_HTM[2886]="*ācāravipattiṃ.**failure in conduct.*";
P_HTM[2887]="*Vipattivāro niṭṭhito tatiyo.**The third section on failure is finished.*";
P_HTM[2888]="*124. Paṭhamabhāga **124.  Part one *";
P_HTM[2889]="*4. Saṅgahitavāra**4. The section on “being found in”*";
P_HTM[2890]="*Methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevantassa āpattiyo sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ katihi āpattikkhandhehi saṅgahitā?**When it comes to the offenses for having sexual intercourse, in how many of the seven classes of offenses are they found?*";
P_HTM[2891]="*Methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevantassa āpattiyo sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ tīhi āpattikkhandhehi saṅgahitā—**They are found in three:*";
P_HTM[2892]="*siyā pārājikāpattikkhandhena, siyā thullaccayāpattikkhandhena, siyā dukkaṭāpattikkhandhena …pe….**they may be in the class of offenses entailing expulsion; they may be in the class of serious offenses; they may be in the class of offenses of wrong conduct. …*";
P_HTM[2893]="*Anādariyaṃ paṭicca udake uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā kheḷaṃ vā karontassa āpatti sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ katihi āpattikkhandhehi saṅgahitā?**When it comes to the offense for, out of disrespect, defecating, urinating, or spitting in water, in how many of the seven classes of offenses is it found?*";
P_HTM[2894]="*Anādariyaṃ paṭicca udake uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā kheḷaṃ vā karontassa āpatti sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ ekena āpattikkhandhena saṅgahitā—**It is found in one:*";
P_HTM[2895]="*dukkaṭāpattikkhandhena.**in the class of offenses of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2896]="*Saṅgahitavāro niṭṭhito catuttho.**The fourth section on “being found in” is finished.*";
P_HTM[2897]="*124. Paṭhamabhāga **124.  Part one *";
P_HTM[2898]="*5. Samuṭṭhānavāra**5. The section on origin*";
P_HTM[2899]="*Methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevantassa āpattiyo channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ katihi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhanti?**When it comes to the offenses for having sexual intercourse, through how many of the six kinds of origins of offenses do they originate?*";
P_HTM[2900]="*Methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevantassa āpattiyo channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhanti—**They originate in one way:*";
P_HTM[2901]="*kāyato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhanti, na vācato …pe….**from body and mind, not from speech. …*";
P_HTM[2902]="*Anādariyaṃ paṭicca udake uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā kheḷaṃ vā karontassa āpatti channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ katihi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhāti?**When it comes to the offense for, out of disrespect, defecating, urinating, or spitting in water, through how many of the six kinds of origins of offenses does it originate?*";
P_HTM[2903]="*Anādariyaṃ paṭicca udake uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā kheḷaṃ vā karontassa āpatti channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhāti—**It originates in one way:*";
P_HTM[2904]="*kāyato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhāti, na vācato.**from body and mind, not from speech.*";
P_HTM[2905]="*Samuṭṭhānavāro niṭṭhito pañcamo.**The fifth section on origin is finished.*";
P_HTM[2906]="*124. Paṭhamabhāga **124.  Part one *";
P_HTM[2907]="*6. Adhikaraṇavāra**6. The section on legal issues*";
P_HTM[2908]="*Methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevantassa āpattiyo catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ?**When it comes to the offenses for having sexual intercourse, to which of the four kinds of legal issues do they belong?*";
P_HTM[2909]="*Methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevantassa āpattiyo catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ āpattādhikaraṇaṃ …pe….**They are legal issues arising from an offense. …*";
P_HTM[2910]="*Anādariyaṃ paṭicca udake uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā kheḷaṃ vā karontassa āpatti catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ?**When it comes to the offense for, out of disrespect, defecating, urinating, or spitting in water, to which of the four kinds of legal issues does it belong?*";
P_HTM[2911]="*Anādariyaṃ paṭicca udake uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā kheḷaṃ vā karontassa āpatti catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ āpattādhikaraṇaṃ.**It is a legal issue arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[2912]="*Adhikaraṇavāro niṭṭhito chaṭṭho.**The sixth section on legal issues is finished.*";
P_HTM[2913]="*124. Paṭhamabhāga **124.  Part one *";
P_HTM[2914]="*7. Samathavāra**7. The section on settling*";
P_HTM[2915]="*Methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevantassa āpattiyo sattannaṃ samathānaṃ katihi samathehi sammanti?**When it comes to the offenses for having sexual intercourse, through how many of the seven principles for settling legal issues are they settled?*";
P_HTM[2916]="*Methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevantassa āpattiyo sattannaṃ samathānaṃ tīhi samathehi sammanti—**Through three of them:*";
P_HTM[2917]="*siyā sammukhāvinayena ca paṭiññātakaraṇena ca, siyā sammukhāvinayena ca tiṇavatthārakena ca …pe….**they may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by acting according to what has been admitted; or they may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by covering over as if with grass. …*";
P_HTM[2918]="*Anādariyaṃ paṭicca udake uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā kheḷaṃ vā karontassa āpatti sattannaṃ samathānaṃ katihi samathehi sammati?**When it comes to the offense for, out of disrespect, defecating, urinating, or spitting in water, through how many of the seven principles for settling legal issues is it settled?*";
P_HTM[2919]="*Anādariyaṃ paṭicca udake uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā kheḷaṃ vā karontassa āpatti sattannaṃ samathānaṃ tīhi samathehi sammati—**Through three of them:*";
P_HTM[2920]="*siyā sammukhāvinayena ca paṭiññātakaraṇena ca, siyā sammukhāvinayena ca tiṇavatthārakena ca.**it may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by acting according to what has been admitted; or it may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[2921]="*Samathavāro niṭṭhito sattamo.**The seventh section on settling is finished.*";
P_HTM[2922]="*124. Paṭhamabhāga **124.  Part one *";
P_HTM[2923]="*8. Samuccayavāra**8. The section that collects together*";
P_HTM[2924]="*Methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevanto kati āpattiyo āpajjati?**For having sexual intercourse, how many kinds of offenses does one commit?*";
P_HTM[2925]="*Methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevanto tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.**One commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2926]="*Akkhāyite sarīre methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevati, āpatti pārājikassa;**when one has sexual intercourse with an undecomposed corpse, one commits an offense entailing expulsion;*";
P_HTM[2927]="*yebhuyyena khāyite sarīre methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevati, āpatti thullaccayassa;**when one has sexual intercourse with a mostly decomposed corpse, one commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[2928]="*vaṭṭakate mukhe acchupantaṃ aṅgajātaṃ paveseti, āpatti dukkaṭassa—**when one inserts the penis without touching into a wide open mouth, one commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2929]="*methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevanto imā tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[2930]="*Tā āpattiyo catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ kati vipattiyo bhajanti, sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ katihi āpattikkhandhehi saṅgahitā, channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ katihi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhanti, catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ, sattannaṃ samathānaṃ katihi samathehi sammanti?**When it comes to these offenses, to how many of the four kinds of failure do they belong? In how many of the seven classes of offenses are they found? Through how many of the six kinds of origins of offenses do they originate? To which of the four kinds of legal issues do they belong? Through how many of the seven principles for settling legal issues are they settled?*";
P_HTM[2931]="*Tā āpattiyo catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ dve vipattiyo bhajanti—**They belong to two kinds of failure:*";
P_HTM[2932]="*siyā sīlavipattiṃ, siyā ācāravipattiṃ.**they may be failure in morality; they may be failure in conduct.*";
P_HTM[2933]="*Sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ tīhi āpattikkhandhehi saṅgahitā—**They are found in three classes of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2934]="*siyā pārājikāpattikkhandhena, siyā thullaccayāpattikkhandhena, siyā dukkaṭāpattikkhandhena.**they may be in the class of offenses entailing expulsion; they may be in the class of serious offenses; they may be in the class of offenses of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2935]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhanti—**They originate in one way:*";
P_HTM[2936]="*kāyato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhanti, na vācato.**from body and mind, not from speech.*";
P_HTM[2937]="*Catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ, āpattādhikaraṇaṃ.**They are legal issues arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[2938]="*Sattannaṃ samathānaṃ tīhi samathehi sammanti—**They are settled in three ways:*";
P_HTM[2939]="*siyā sammukhāvinayena ca paṭiññātakaraṇena ca, siyā sammukhāvinayena ca tiṇavatthārakena ca …pe….**they may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by acting according to what has been admitted; or they may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by covering over as if with grass. …*";
P_HTM[2940]="*Anādariyaṃ paṭicca udake uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā kheḷaṃ vā karonto kati āpattiyo āpajjati?**For, out of disrespect, defecating, urinating, or spitting in water, how many kinds of offenses does one commit?*";
P_HTM[2941]="*Anādariyaṃ paṭicca udake uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā kheḷaṃ vā karonto ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati.**One commits one kind of offense:*";
P_HTM[2942]="*Dukkaṭaṃ—**an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2943]="*anādariyaṃ paṭicca udake uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā kheḷaṃ vā karonto imaṃ ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[2944]="*Sā āpatti catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ kati vipattiyo bhajati, sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ katihi āpattikkhandhehi saṅgahitā, channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ katihi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhāti, catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ, sattannaṃ, samathānaṃ katihi samathehi sammati?**When it comes to this offense, to how many of the four kinds of failure does it belong? In how many of the seven classes of offenses is it found? Through how many of the six kinds of origins of offenses does it originate? To which of the four kinds of legal issues does it belong? Through how many of the seven principles for settling legal issues is it settled?*";
P_HTM[2945]="*Sā āpatti catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ ekaṃ vipattiṃ bhajati—**It belongs to one kind of failure:*";
P_HTM[2946]="*ācāravipattiṃ.**failure in conduct.*";
P_HTM[2947]="*Sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ ekena āpattikkhandhena saṅgahitā—**It is found in one class of offenses:*";
P_HTM[2948]="*dukkaṭāpattikkhandhena.**in the class of offenses of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2949]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhāti—**It originates in one way:*";
P_HTM[2950]="*kāyato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhāti, na vācato.**from body and mind, not from speech.*";
P_HTM[2951]="*Catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ, āpattādhikaraṇaṃ.**It is a legal issue arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[2952]="*Sattannaṃ samathānaṃ tīhi samathehi sammati—**It is settled through three principles:*";
P_HTM[2953]="*siyā sammukhāvinayena ca paṭiññātakaraṇena ca, siyā sammukhāvinayena ca tiṇavatthārakena ca.**it may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by acting according to what has been admitted; or it may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[2954]="*Samuccayavāro niṭṭhito aṭṭhamo.**The eighth section that collects together is finished.*";
P_HTM[2955]="*Ime aṭṭha vārā sajjhāyamaggena likhitā.**These eight sections were written down through the method of recitation.*";
P_HTM[2956]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[2957]="*Katthapaññatti kati ca,**“Where was it laid down, and how many,*";
P_HTM[2958]="*Vipattisaṅgahena ca;**Failure and being found in;*";
P_HTM[2959]="*Samuṭṭhānādhikaraṇā,**Origin, legal issues,*";
P_HTM[2960]="*Samatho samuccayena cāti.**Settling, and with collecting together.”*";
P_HTM[2961]="*124. Dutiyabhāga **124.  Part two *";
P_HTM[2962]="*Katthapaññattivāra**The section on “where it was laid down”*";
P_HTM[2963]="*1. Pārājikakaṇḍa**1. The chapter on offenses entailing expulsion*";
P_HTM[2964]="*Yaṃ tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevanapaccayā pārājikaṃ kattha paññattaṃ, kaṃ ārabbha, kismiṃ vatthusmiṃ …pe…**“The offense entailing expulsion that is a result of having sexual intercourse was laid down by the Buddha who knows and sees, the Perfected One, the fully Awakened One. Where was it laid down? Whom is it about? What is it about? …*";
P_HTM[2965]="*kenābhatanti?**Who handed it down?”*";
P_HTM[2966]="*Yaṃ tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevanapaccayā pārājikaṃ kattha paññattanti?**“The offense entailing expulsion that is a result of having sexual intercourse and that was laid down by the Buddha who knows and sees, the Perfected One, the fully Awakened One—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[2967]="*Vesāliyaṃ paññattaṃ.**At Vesālī.*";
P_HTM[2968]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[2969]="*Sudinnaṃ kalandaputtaṃ ārabbha.**Sudinna the Kalandian.*";
P_HTM[2970]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[2971]="*Sudinno kalandaputto purāṇadutiyikāya methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevi, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**Sudinna having sexual intercourse with his ex-wife.*";
P_HTM[2972]="*Atthi tattha paññatti, anupaññatti, anuppannapaññattīti?**“Is there a rule, an addition to the rule, an unprompted rule?”*";
P_HTM[2973]="*Ekā paññatti, dve anupaññattiyo.**There is one rule. There are two additions to the rule.*";
P_HTM[2974]="*Anuppannapaññatti tasmiṃ natthi.**There is no unprompted rule.*";
P_HTM[2975]="*Sabbattha paññatti, padesapaññattīti?**“Is it a rule that applies everywhere, or that applies in a particular place?”*";
P_HTM[2976]="*Sabbatthapaññatti.**That applies everywhere.*";
P_HTM[2977]="*Sādhāraṇapaññatti, asādhāraṇapaññattīti?**“Is it a rule that the monks and nuns have in common, or a rule they do not have in common?”*";
P_HTM[2978]="*Sādhāraṇapaññatti.**That the monks and nuns have in common.*";
P_HTM[2979]="*Ekatopaññatti, ubhatopaññattīti?**“Is it a rule for one Sangha or for both Sanghas?”*";
P_HTM[2980]="*Ubhatopaññatti.**For both Sanghas.*";
P_HTM[2981]="*Pañcannaṃ pātimokkhuddesānaṃ katthogadhaṃ kattha pariyāpannanti?**“In which of the five ways of reciting the Monastic Code is it immersed and included?”*";
P_HTM[2982]="*Nidānogadhaṃ nidānapariyāpannaṃ.**In the introduction.*";
P_HTM[2983]="*Katamena uddesena uddesaṃ āgacchatīti?**“In which recitation is it included?”*";
P_HTM[2984]="*Dutiyena uddesena uddesaṃ āgacchati.**In the second recitation.*";
P_HTM[2985]="*Catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ katamā vipattīti?**“To which of the four kinds of failure does it belong?”*";
P_HTM[2986]="*Sīlavipatti.**Failure in morality.*";
P_HTM[2987]="*Sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ katamo āpattikkhandhoti?**“To which of the seven classes of offenses does it belong?”*";
P_HTM[2988]="*Pārājikāpattikkhandho.**The class of offenses entailing expulsion.*";
P_HTM[2989]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ katihi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhātīti?**“Through how many of the six kinds of origins of offenses does it originate?”*";
P_HTM[2990]="*Ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhāti—**It originates in one way:*";
P_HTM[2991]="*kāyato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhāti, na vācato …pe…**from body and mind, not from speech. …*";
P_HTM[2992]="*kenābhatanti?**“Who handed it down?”*";
P_HTM[2993]="*Paramparābhataṃ—**The lineage:*";
P_HTM[2994]="*Upāli dāsako ceva,**“Upāli and Dāsaka,*";
P_HTM[2995]="*soṇako siggavo tathā;**Soṇaka and also Siggava;*";
P_HTM[2996]="*Moggaliputtena pañcamā,**With Moggaliputta as the fifth—*";
P_HTM[2997]="*ete jambusirivhaye.**these were in India, the land named after the glorious rose apple.*";
P_HTM[2998]="*…pe…**…*";
P_HTM[2999]="*Ete nāgā mahāpaññā,**These great beings of great wisdom,*";
P_HTM[3000]="*vinayaññū maggakovidā;**Knowers of the Monastic Law and skilled in the path,*";
P_HTM[3001]="*Vinayaṃ dīpe pakāsesuṃ,**Proclaimed the Collection of Monastic Law*";
P_HTM[3002]="*piṭakaṃ tambapaṇṇiyāti.**On the island of Sri Lanka.”*";
P_HTM[3003]="*Yaṃ tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena adinnaṃ ādiyanapaccayā pārājikaṃ kattha paññattanti?**“The offense entailing expulsion that is a result of stealing and that was laid down by the Buddha who knows and sees, the Perfected One, the fully Awakened One—where was it laid down?”*";
