P_HTM[3167]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhāti—**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in one way:*";
P_HTM[3168]="*kāyato ca vācato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhāti …pe….**from body, speech, and mind. …*";
P_HTM[3169]="*Dubbacassa bhikkhuno yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjanapaccayā saṅghādiseso kattha paññattoti?**“The offense entailing suspension that is a result of a monk not stopping to be difficult to correct when pressed up to three times—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[3170]="*Kosambiyaṃ paññatto.**At Kosambī.*";
P_HTM[3171]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[3172]="*Āyasmantaṃ channaṃ ārabbha.**Venerable Channa.*";
P_HTM[3173]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[3174]="*Āyasmā channo bhikkhūhi sahadhammikaṃ vuccamāno attānaṃ avacanīyaṃ akāsi, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**Channa making himself incorrigible when legitimately spoken to by the monks.*";
P_HTM[3175]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[3176]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhāti—**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in one way:*";
P_HTM[3177]="*kāyato ca vācato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhāti …pe….**from body, speech, and mind. …*";
P_HTM[3178]="*Kuladūsakassa bhikkhuno yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjanapaccayā saṅghādiseso kattha paññattoti?**“The offense entailing suspension that is a result of a monk not stopping to be a corrupter of families when pressed up to three times—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[3179]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññatto.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3180]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[3181]="*Assajipunabbasuke bhikkhū ārabbha.**The monks Assaji and Punabbasuka.*";
P_HTM[3182]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[3183]="*Assajipunabbasukā bhikkhū saṅghena pabbājanīyakammakatā bhikkhū chandagāmitā dosagāmitā mohagāmitā bhayagāmitā pāpesuṃ, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**Those monks, when the Sangha did a legal procedure of banishment against them, slandering the monks as acting out of desire, ill will, confusion, and fear.*";
P_HTM[3184]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[3185]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhāti—**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in one way:*";
P_HTM[3186]="*kāyato ca vācato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhāti …pe….**from body, speech, and mind. …*";
P_HTM[3187]="*Anādariyaṃ paṭicca udake uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā kheḷaṃ vā karaṇapaccayā dukkaṭaṃ kattha paññattanti?**“The offense of wrong conduct that is a result of, out of disrespect, defecating, urinating, or spitting in water—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[3188]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññattaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3189]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[3190]="*Chabbaggiye bhikkhū ārabbha.**The monks from the group of six.*";
P_HTM[3191]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[3192]="*Chabbaggiyā bhikkhū udake uccārampi passāvampi kheḷampi akaṃsu, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**Those monks defecating, urinating, and spitting in water.*";
P_HTM[3193]="*Ekā paññatti, ekā anupaññatti.**There is one rule. There is one addition to the rule.*";
P_HTM[3194]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhāti—**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in one way:*";
P_HTM[3195]="*kāyato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhāti, na vācato …pe….**from body and mind, not from speech. …*";
P_HTM[3196]="*Katthapaññattivāro niṭṭhito paṭhamo.**The first section on “where it was laid down” is finished.*";
P_HTM[3197]="*124. Dutiyabhāga **124.  Part two *";
P_HTM[3198]="*Katāpattivāra**The section on “how many offenses”*";
P_HTM[3199]="*1. Pārājikakaṇḍa**1. The chapter on offenses entailing expulsion*";
P_HTM[3200]="*Methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevanapaccayā kati āpattiyo āpajjati?**How many kinds of offenses does one commit as a result of having sexual intercourse?*";
P_HTM[3201]="*Methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevanapaccayā catasso āpattiyo āpajjati—**One commits four kinds of offenses?*";
P_HTM[3202]="*akkhāyite sarīre methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevati, āpatti pārājikassa;**when one has sexual intercourse with an undecomposed corpse, one commits an offense entailing expulsion;*";
P_HTM[3203]="*yebhuyyena khāyite sarīre methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevati, āpatti thullaccayassa;**when one has sexual intercourse with a mostly decomposed corpse, one commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[3204]="*vaṭṭakate mukhe acchupantaṃ aṅgajātaṃ paveseti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when one inserts the penis without touching into a wide open mouth, one commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3205]="*jatumaṭṭhake pācittiyaṃ—**when one uses a dildo, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3206]="*methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevanapaccayā imā catasso āpattiyo āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[3207]="*Adinnaṃ ādiyanapaccayā kati āpattiyo āpajjati?**How many kinds of offenses does one commit as a result of stealing?*";
P_HTM[3208]="*Adinnaṃ ādiyanapaccayā tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.**One commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[3209]="*Pañcamāsakaṃ vā atirekapañcamāsakaṃ vā agghanakaṃ adinnaṃ theyyasaṅkhātaṃ ādiyati, āpatti pārājikassa;**when, intending to steal, one steals something worth five _māsaka_ coins or more than five _māsakas_, one commits an offense entailing expulsion;*";
P_HTM[3210]="*atirekamāsakaṃ vā ūnapañcamāsakaṃ vā agghanakaṃ adinnaṃ theyyasaṅkhātaṃ ādiyati, āpatti thullaccayassa;**when, intending to steal, one steals something worth more than one _māsaka_ coin but less than five _māsakas_, one commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[3211]="*māsakaṃ vā ūnamāsakaṃ vā agghanakaṃ adinnaṃ theyyasaṅkhātaṃ ādiyati, āpatti dukkaṭassa—**when, intending to steal, one steals something worth one _māsaka_ coin or less than one _māsaka_, one commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3212]="*adinnaṃ ādiyanapaccayā imā tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[3213]="*Sañcicca manussaviggahaṃ jīvitā voropanapaccayā kati āpattiyo āpajjati?**How many kinds of offenses does one commit as a result of intentionally killing a human being?*";
P_HTM[3214]="*Sañcicca manussaviggahaṃ jīvitā voropanapaccayā tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.**One commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[3215]="*Manussaṃ odissa opātaṃ khaṇati “papatitvā marissatī”ti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when one digs a pit for people, thinking, “Falling into it someone will die,” one commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[3216]="*papatite dukkhā vedanā uppajjati, āpatti thullaccayassa;**when the person experiences pain after falling in in, one commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[3217]="*marati, āpatti pārājikassa—**when the person dies, one commits an offense entailing expulsion.*";
P_HTM[3218]="*sañcicca manussaviggahaṃ jīvitā voropanapaccayā imā tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[3219]="*Asantaṃ abhūtaṃ uttarimanussadhammaṃ ullapanapaccayā kati āpattiyo āpajjati?**How many kinds of offenses does one commit as a result of untruthfully and groundlessly boasting about a superhuman quality?*";
P_HTM[3220]="*Asantaṃ abhūtaṃ uttarimanussadhammaṃ ullapanapaccayā tisso āpattiyo āpajjati—**One commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[3221]="*pāpiccho icchāpakato asantaṃ abhūtaṃ uttarimanussadhammaṃ ullapati, āpatti pārājikassa;**when, having bad desires, overcome by desire, one claims a non-existent, unreal superhuman quality, one commits an offense entailing expulsion;*";
P_HTM[3222]="*“yo te vihāre vasati so bhikkhu arahā”ti bhaṇati, paṭivijānantassa āpatti thullaccayassa;**when one says, “Whatever monk lives in your dwelling is a perfected one,” and the listener understands, one commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[3223]="*na paṭivijānantassa āpatti dukkaṭassa—**when the listener does not understand, one commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3224]="*asantaṃ abhūtaṃ uttarimanussadhammaṃ ullapanapaccayā imā tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[3225]="*Cattāro pārājikā niṭṭhitā.**The four offenses entailing expulsion are finished.*";
P_HTM[3226]="*2. Saṅghādisesakaṇḍādi**2. The chapter on offenses entailing suspension, etc.*";
P_HTM[3227]="*Upakkamitvā asucimocanapaccayā kati āpattiyo āpajjati?**How many kinds of offenses does one commit as a result of emitting semen by means of effort?*";
P_HTM[3228]="*Upakkamitvā asucimocanapaccayā tisso āpattiyo āpajjati—**One commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[3229]="*ceteti upakkamati muccati, āpatti saṅghādisesassa;**when one intends and makes an effort, and semen is emitted, one commits an offense entailing suspension;*";
P_HTM[3230]="*ceteti upakkamati na muccati, āpatti thullaccayassa;**when one intends and makes an effort, but semen is not emitted, one commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[3231]="*payoge dukkaṭaṃ—**for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3232]="*upakkamitvā asucimocanapaccayā imā tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[3233]="*Kāyasaṃsaggaṃ samāpajjanapaccayā kati āpattiyo āpajjati?**How many kinds of offenses does one commit as a result of making physical contact with a woman?*";
P_HTM[3234]="*Kāyasaṃsaggaṃ samāpajjanapaccayā pañca āpattiyo āpajjati—**One commits five kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[3235]="*avassutā bhikkhunī avassutassa purisapuggalassa adhakkhakaṃ ubbhajāṇumaṇḍalaṃ gahaṇaṃ sādiyati, āpatti pārājikassa;**when a lustful nun consents to a lustful man taking hold of her anywhere below the collar bone but above the knees, she commits an offense entailing expulsion;*";
P_HTM[3236]="*bhikkhu kāyena kāyaṃ āmasati, āpatti saṅghādisesassa;**when a monk touches body with body, he commits an offense entailing suspension;*";
P_HTM[3237]="*kāyena kāyapaṭibaddhaṃ āmasati, āpatti thullaccayassa;**when one touches what is connected to the body with the body, one commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[3238]="*kāyapaṭibaddhena kāyapaṭibaddhaṃ āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when one touches what is connected to the body with what is connected to the body, one commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3239]="*aṅgulipatodake pācittiyaṃ—**for tickling, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3240]="*kāyasaṃsaggaṃ samāpajjanapaccayā imā pañca āpattiyo āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[3241]="*Mātugāmaṃ duṭṭhullāhi vācāhi obhāsanapaccayā tisso āpattiyo āpajjati—**As a result of speaking indecently to a woman, one commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[3242]="*vaccamaggaṃ passāvamaggaṃ ādissa vaṇṇampi bhaṇati avaṇṇampi bhaṇati, āpatti saṅghādisesassa;**when, referring to the anus or the vagina, one praises and disparages, one commits an offense entailing suspension;*";
P_HTM[3243]="*vaccamaggaṃ passāvamaggaṃ ṭhapetvā adhakkhakaṃ ubbhajāṇumaṇḍalaṃ ādissa vaṇṇampi bhaṇati avaṇṇampi bhaṇati, āpatti thullaccayassa;**when, referring to any part below the collar bone but above the knees, apart from the anus or the vagina, one praises and disparages, one commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[3244]="*kāyapaṭibaddhaṃ ādissa vaṇṇampi bhaṇati avaṇṇampi bhaṇati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**when, referring to anything connected to the body, one praises and disparages, one commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3245]="*Attakāmapāricariyāya vaṇṇaṃ bhāsanapaccayā tisso āpattiyo āpajjati—**As a result of commending the satisfaction of one’s own desires, one commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[3246]="*mātugāmassa santike attakāmapāricariyāya vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, āpatti saṅghādisesassa;**when one encourages a woman to satisfy one’s own desires, one commits an offense entailing suspension;*";
P_HTM[3247]="*paṇḍakassa santike attakāmapāricariyāya vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, āpatti thullaccayassa;**when one encourages a _paṇḍaka_ to satisfy one’s own desires, one commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[3248]="*tiracchānagatassa santike attakāmapāricariyāya vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**when one encourages an animal to satisfy one’s own desires, one commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3249]="*Sañcarittaṃ samāpajjanapaccayā tisso āpattiyo āpajjati—**As a result of acting as a matchmaker, one commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[3250]="*paṭiggaṇhāti vīmaṃsati paccāharati, āpatti saṅghādisesassa;**when one accepts the mission, finds out the response, and reports back, one commits an offense entailing suspension;*";
P_HTM[3251]="*paṭiggaṇhāti vīmaṃsati na paccāharati, āpatti thullaccayassa;**when one accepts the mission, and finds out the response, but does not report back, one commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[3252]="*paṭiggaṇhāti na vīmaṃsati na paccāharati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**when one accepts the mission, but neither finds out the response, nor reports back, one commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3253]="*Saññācikāya kuṭiṃ kārāpanapaccayā tisso āpattiyo āpajjati—**As a result of having a hut built by means of begging, one commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[3254]="*kārāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is having it made, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[3255]="*ekaṃ piṇḍaṃ anāgate āpatti thullaccayassa;**when there is one piece left to complete the hut, one commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[3256]="*tasmiṃ piṇḍe āgate āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**when the last piece is finished, one commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[3257]="*Mahallakaṃ vihāraṃ kārāpanapaccayā tisso āpattiyo āpajjati—**As a result of having a large dwelling built, one commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[3258]="*kārāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when one is having it made, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[3259]="*ekaṃ piṇḍaṃ anāgate, āpatti thullaccayassa;**when there is one piece left to complete the hut, one commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[3260]="*tasmiṃ piṇḍe āgate āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**when the last piece is finished, one commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[3261]="*Bhikkhuṃ amūlakena pārājikena dhammena anuddhaṃsanapaccayā tisso āpattiyo āpajjati—**As a result of groundlessly charging a monk with an offense entailing expulsion, one commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[3262]="*anokāsaṃ kārāpetvā cāvanādhippāyo vadeti, āpatti saṅghādisesena dukkaṭassa;**when, without having obtained his permission, one speaks with the aim of making him leave the monastic life, one commits one offense entailing suspension and one offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[3263]="*okāsaṃ kārāpetvā akkosādhippāyo vadeti, āpatti omasavādassa.**when, having obtained his permission, one speaks with the aim of abusing him, one commits an offense for abusive speech.*";
P_HTM[3264]="*Bhikkhuṃ aññabhāgiyassa adhikaraṇassa kiñci desaṃ lesamattaṃ upādāya pārājikena dhammena anuddhaṃsanapaccayā tisso āpattiyo āpajjati—**As a result of charging a monk with an offense entailing expulsion, using an unrelated legal issue as a pretext, one commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[3265]="*anokāsaṃ kārāpetvā cāvanādhippāyo vadeti, āpatti saṅghādisesena dukkaṭassa;**when, without having obtained his permission, one speaks with the aim of making him leave the monastic life, one commits one offense entailing suspension and one offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[3266]="*okāsaṃ kārāpetvā akkosādhippāyo vadeti, āpatti omasavādassa.**when, having obtained his permission, one speaks with the aim of abusing him, one commits an offense for abusive speech.*";
P_HTM[3267]="*Saṅghabhedako bhikkhu yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjanapaccayā tisso āpattiyo āpajjati—**As a result of not stopping when pressed up to three times, a monk who is pursuing schism in the Sangha commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[3268]="*ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ;**after the motion, he commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[3269]="*dvīhi kammavācāhi thullaccayā;**after each of the first two announcements, he commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[3270]="*kammavācāpariyosāne āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**when the last announcement is finished, he commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[3271]="*Bhedakānuvattakā bhikkhū yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjanapaccayā tisso āpattiyo āpajjanti—**As a result of not stopping when pressed up to three times, monks who side with a monk who is pursuing schism commit three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[3272]="*ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ;**after the motion, he commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[3273]="*dvīhi kammavācāhi thullaccayā;**after each of the first two announcements, he commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[3274]="*kammavācāpariyosāne āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**when the last announcement is finished, he commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[3275]="*Dubbaco bhikkhu yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjanapaccayā tisso āpattiyo āpajjati—**As a result of not stopping when pressed up to three times, a monk who is difficult to correct commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[3276]="*ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ;**after the motion, he commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[3277]="*dvīhi kammavācāhi thullaccayā;**after each of the first two announcements, he commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[3278]="*kammavācāpariyosāne āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**when the last announcement is finished, he commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[3279]="*Kuladūsako bhikkhu yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjanapaccayā tisso āpattiyo āpajjati—**As a result of not stopping when pressed up to three times, a monk who is a corrupter of families commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[3280]="*ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ;**after the motion, he commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[3281]="*dvīhi kammavācāhi thullaccayā;**after each of the first two announcements, he commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[3282]="*kammavācāpariyosāne āpatti saṅghādisesassa …pe….**when the last announcement is finished, he commits an offense entailing suspension. …*";
P_HTM[3283]="*Anādariyaṃ paṭicca udake uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā kheḷaṃ vā karaṇapaccayā kati āpattiyo āpajjati?**As a result of, out of disrespect, defecating, urinating, or spitting in water, how many kinds of offenses does one commit?*";
P_HTM[3284]="*Anādariyaṃ paṭicca udake uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā kheḷaṃ vā karaṇapaccayā ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati.**One commits one kind of offense:*";
P_HTM[3285]="*Dukkaṭaṃ—**an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3286]="*anādariyaṃ paṭicca udake uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā kheḷaṃ vā karaṇapaccayā imaṃ ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[3287]="*Katāpattivāro niṭṭhito dutiyo.**The second section “on how many offenses” is finished.*";
P_HTM[3288]="*124. Dutiyabhāga **124.  Part two *";
P_HTM[3289]="*3. Vipattivāra**3. The section on failure*";
P_HTM[3290]="*Methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevanapaccayā āpattiyo catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ kati vipattiyo bhajanti?**When it comes to the offenses that are a result of having sexual intercourse, to how many of the four kinds of failure do they belong?*";
P_HTM[3291]="*Methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevanapaccayā āpattiyo catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ dve vipattiyo bhajanti—**They belong to two kinds of failure:*";
P_HTM[3292]="*siyā sīlavipattiṃ siyā ācāravipattiṃ …pe….**they may be failure in morality; they may be failure in conduct. …*";
P_HTM[3293]="*Anādariyaṃ paṭicca udake uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā kheḷaṃ vā karaṇapaccayā āpatti catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ kati vipattiyo bhajati?**When it comes to the offense that is a result of, out of disrespect, defecating, urinating, or spitting in water, to how many of the four kinds of failure does it belong?*";
P_HTM[3294]="*Anādariyaṃ paṭicca udake uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā kheḷaṃ vā karaṇapaccayā āpatti catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ ekaṃ vipattiṃ bhajati—**It belongs to one kind of failure:*";
P_HTM[3295]="*ācāravipattiṃ.**failure in conduct.*";
P_HTM[3296]="*Vipattivāro niṭṭhito tatiyo.**The third section on failure is finished.*";
P_HTM[3297]="*124. Dutiyabhāga **124.  Part two *";
P_HTM[3298]="*4. Saṅgahitavāra**4. The section on “being found in”*";
P_HTM[3299]="*Methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevanapaccayā āpattiyo sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ katihi āpattikkhandhehi saṅgahitā?**When it comes to the offenses that are a result of having sexual intercourse, in how many of the seven classes of offenses are they found?*";
P_HTM[3300]="*Methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevanapaccayā āpattiyo sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ catūhi āpattikkhandhehi saṅgahitā—**They are found in four:*";
P_HTM[3301]="*siyā pārājikāpattikkhandhena, siyā thullaccayāpattikkhandhena, siyā pācittiyāpattikkhandhena, siyā dukkaṭāpattikkhandhena …pe….**they may be in the class of offenses entailing expulsion; they may be in the class of serious offenses; they may be in the class of offenses entailing confession; they may be in the class of offenses of wrong conduct. …*";
P_HTM[3302]="*Anādariyaṃ paṭicca udake uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā kheḷaṃ vā karaṇapaccayā āpatti sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ katihi āpattikkhandhehi saṅgahitā?**When it comes to the offense that is a result of, out of disrespect, defecating, urinating, or spitting in water, in how many of the seven classes of offenses is it found?*";
P_HTM[3303]="*Anādariyaṃ paṭicca udake uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā kheḷaṃ vā karaṇapaccayā āpatti sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ ekena āpattikkhandhena saṅgahitā—**It is found in one:*";
P_HTM[3304]="*dukkaṭāpattikkhandhena.**in the class of offenses of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3305]="*Saṅgahitavāro niṭṭhito catuttho.**The fourth section on “being found in” is finished.*";
P_HTM[3306]="*124. Dutiyabhāga **124.  Part two *";
P_HTM[3307]="*5. Samuṭṭhānavāra**5. The section on origin*";
P_HTM[3308]="*Methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevanapaccayā āpattiyo channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ katihi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhanti?**When it comes to the offenses that are a result of having sexual intercourse, through how many of the six kinds of origins of offenses do they originate?*";
P_HTM[3309]="*Methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevanapaccayā āpattiyo channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhanti—**They originate in one way:*";
P_HTM[3310]="*kāyato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhanti, na vācato …pe….**from body and mind, not from speech. …*";
P_HTM[3311]="*Anādariyaṃ paṭicca udake uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā kheḷaṃ vā karaṇapaccayā āpatti channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ katihi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhāti?**When it comes to the offense that is a result of, out of disrespect, defecating, urinating, or spitting in water, through how many of the six kinds of origins of offenses does it originate?*";
P_HTM[3312]="*Anādariyaṃ paṭicca udake uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā kheḷaṃ vā karaṇapaccayā āpatti channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhāti—**It originates in one way:*";
P_HTM[3313]="*kāyato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhāti, na vācato …pe….**from body and mind, not from speech.*";
P_HTM[3314]="*Samuṭṭhānavāro niṭṭhito pañcamo.**The fifth section on origin is finished.*";
P_HTM[3315]="*124. Dutiyabhāga **124.  Part two *";
P_HTM[3316]="*6. Adhikaraṇavāra**6. The section on legal issues*";
P_HTM[3317]="*Methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevanapaccayā āpattiyo catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ?**When it comes to the offenses that are a result of having sexual intercourse, to which of the four kinds of legal issue do they belong?*";
P_HTM[3318]="*Methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevanapaccayā āpattiyo catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ āpattādhikaraṇaṃ …pe….**They are legal issues arising from an offense. …*";
P_HTM[3319]="*Anādariyaṃ paṭicca udake uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā kheḷaṃ vā karaṇapaccayā āpatti catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ?**When it comes to the offense that is a result of, out of disrespect, defecating, urinating, or spitting in water, to which of the four kinds of legal issues does it belong?*";
P_HTM[3320]="*Anādariyaṃ paṭicca udake uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā kheḷaṃ vā karaṇapaccayā āpatti catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ āpattādhikaraṇaṃ.**It is a legal issue arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[3321]="*Adhikaraṇavāro niṭṭhito chaṭṭho.**The sixth section on legal issues is finished.*";
P_HTM[3322]="*124. Dutiyabhāga **124.  Part two *";
P_HTM[3323]="*7. Samathavāra**7. The section on settling*";
P_HTM[3324]="*Methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevanapaccayā āpattiyo sattannaṃ samathānaṃ katihi samathehi sammanti?**When it comes to the offenses that are a result of having sexual intercourse, through how many of the seven principles for settling legal issues are they settled?*";
P_HTM[3325]="*Methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevanapaccayā āpattiyo sattannaṃ samathānaṃ tīhi samathehi sammanti—**Through three of them:*";
P_HTM[3326]="*siyā sammukhāvinayena ca paṭiññātakaraṇena ca;**they may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by acting according to what has been admitted;*";
P_HTM[3327]="*siyā sammukhāvinayena ca tiṇavatthārakena ca …pe….**they may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by covering over as if with grass. …*";
P_HTM[3328]="*Anādariyaṃ paṭicca udake uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā kheḷaṃ vā karaṇapaccayā āpatti sattannaṃ samathānaṃ katihi samathehi sammati?**When it comes to the offense that is a result of, out of disrespect, defecating, urinating, or spitting in water, through how many of the seven principles for settling legal issues is it settled?*";
P_HTM[3329]="*Anādariyaṃ paṭicca udake uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā kheḷaṃ vā karaṇapaccayā āpatti sattannaṃ samathānaṃ tīhi samathehi sammati—**Through three of them:*";
P_HTM[3330]="*siyā sammukhāvinayena ca paṭiññātakaraṇena ca, siyā sammukhāvinayena ca tiṇavatthārakena cāti.**it may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by acting according to what has been admitted; or it may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[3331]="*Samathavāro niṭṭhito sattamo.**The seventh section on settling is finished.*";
P_HTM[3332]="*124. Dutiyabhāga **124.  Part two *";
P_HTM[3333]="*8. Samuccayavāra**8. The section that collects together*";
P_HTM[3334]="*Methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevanapaccayā kati āpattiyo āpajjati?**As a result of having sexual intercourse, how many kinds of offenses does one commit?*";
P_HTM[3335]="*Methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevanapaccayā catasso āpattiyo āpajjati.**One commits four kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[3336]="*Akkhāyite sarīre methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevati, āpatti pārājikassa;**when one has sexual intercourse with an undecomposed corpse, one commits an offense entailing expulsion;*";
P_HTM[3337]="*yebhuyyena khāyite sarīre methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevati, āpatti thullaccayassa;**when one has sexual intercourse with a mostly decomposed corpse, one commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[3338]="*vaṭṭakate mukhe acchupantaṃ aṅgajātaṃ paveseti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when one inserts the penis without touching into a wide open mouth, one commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[3339]="*jatumaṭṭhake pācittiyaṃ—**when one uses a dildo, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3340]="*methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevanapaccayā imā catasso āpattiyo āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[3341]="*Tā āpattiyo catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ kati vipattiyo bhajanti?**When it comes to these offenses, to how many of the four kinds of failure do they belong?*";
P_HTM[3342]="*Sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ katihi āpattikkhandhehi saṅgahitā?**In how many of the seven classes of offenses are they found?*";
P_HTM[3343]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ katihi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhanti?**Through how many of the six kinds of origins of offenses do they originate?*";
P_HTM[3344]="*Catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ?**To which of the four kinds of legal issues do they belong?*";
P_HTM[3345]="*Sattannaṃ samathānaṃ katihi samathehi sammanti?**Through how many of the seven principles for settling legal issues are they settled?*";
P_HTM[3346]="*Tā āpattiyo catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ dve vipattiyo bhajanti—**They belong to two kinds of failure:*";
P_HTM[3347]="*siyā sīlavipattiṃ siyā ācāravipattiṃ.**they may be failure in morality; they may be failure in conduct.*";
P_HTM[3348]="*Sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ catūhi āpattikkhandhehi saṅgahitā—**They are found in four classes of offenses:*";
P_HTM[3349]="*siyā pārājikāpattikkhandhena, siyā thullaccayāpattikkhandhena, siyā pācittiyāpattikkhandhena, siyā dukkaṭāpattikkhandhena.**they may be in the class of offenses entailing expulsion; they may be in the class of serious offenses; they may be in the class of offenses entailing confession; they may be in the class of offenses of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3350]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhanti—**They originate in one way:*";
P_HTM[3351]="*kāyato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhanti, na vācato.**from body and mind, not from speech.*";
P_HTM[3352]="*Catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ, āpattādhikaraṇaṃ.**They are legal issues arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[3353]="*Sattannaṃ samathānaṃ, tīhi samathehi sammanti—**They are settled in three ways:*";
P_HTM[3354]="*siyā sammukhāvinayena ca, paṭiññātakaraṇena ca, siyā sammukhāvinayena ca tiṇavatthārakena ca …pe….**they may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by acting according to what has been admitted; or they may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by covering over as if with grass. …*";
P_HTM[3355]="*Anādariyaṃ paṭicca udake uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā kheḷaṃ vā karaṇapaccayā kati āpattiyo āpajjati?**As a result of, out of disrespect, defecating, urinating, or spitting in water, how many kinds of offenses does one commit?*";
P_HTM[3356]="*Anādariyaṃ paṭicca udake uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā kheḷaṃ vā karaṇapaccayā ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati.**One commits one kind of offense:*";
P_HTM[3357]="*Dukkaṭaṃ—**an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3358]="*anādariyaṃ paṭicca udake uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā kheḷaṃ vā karaṇapaccayā imaṃ ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[3359]="*Sā āpatti catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ kati vipattiyo bhajati?**When it comes to this offense, to how many of the four kinds of failure does it belong?*";
P_HTM[3360]="*Sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ katihi āpattikkhandhehi saṅgahitā?**In how many of the seven classes of offenses is it found?*";
P_HTM[3361]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ katihi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhāti?**Through how many of the six kinds of origins of offenses does it originate?*";
P_HTM[3362]="*Catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ?**To which of the four kinds of legal issues does it belong?*";
P_HTM[3363]="*Sattannaṃ samathānaṃ katihi samathehi sammati?**Through how many of the seven principles for settling legal issues is it settled?*";
P_HTM[3364]="*Sā āpatti catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ ekaṃ vipattiṃ bhajati—**It belongs to one kind of failure:*";
P_HTM[3365]="*ācāravipattiṃ.**failure in conduct.*";
P_HTM[3366]="*Sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ ekena āpattikkhandhena saṅgahitā—**It is found in one class of offenses:*";
P_HTM[3367]="*dukkaṭāpattikkhandhena.**in the class of offenses of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3368]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhāti—**It originates in one way:*";
P_HTM[3369]="*kāyato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhāti, na vācato.**from body and mind, not from speech.*";
P_HTM[3370]="*Catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ, āpattādhikaraṇaṃ.**It is a legal issue arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[3371]="*Sattannaṃ samathānaṃ tīhi samathehi sammati—**It is settled through three principles:*";
P_HTM[3372]="*siyā sammukhāvinayena ca paṭiññātakaraṇena ca, siyā sammukhāvinayena ca tiṇavatthārakena cāti.**it may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by acting according to what has been admitted; or it may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[3373]="*Samuccayavāro niṭṭhito aṭṭhamo.**The eighth section that collects together is finished.*";
P_HTM[3374]="*Aṭṭhapaccayavārā niṭṭhitā.**The eight sections on “as a result of” are finished.*";
P_HTM[3375]="*Mahāvibhaṅge soḷasamahāvārā niṭṭhitā.**The sixteen large sections in the great analysis are finished.*";
P_HTM[3376]="*Bhikkhuvibhaṅgamahāvāro niṭṭhito.**The large section on the monks’ rules and their analysis is finished.*";
P_HTM[3377]="*124. Paṭhamabhāga **124.  Part one *";
P_HTM[3378]="*Katthapaññattivāra**The section on “where it was laid down”*";
P_HTM[3379]="*1. Pārājikakaṇḍa**1. The chapter on offenses entailing expulsion*";
P_HTM[3380]="*Yaṃ tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena bhikkhunīnaṃ pañcamaṃ pārājikaṃ kattha paññattaṃ?**“The nuns’ fifth offense entailing expulsion was laid down by the Buddha who knows and sees, the Perfected One, the fully Awakened One. Where was it laid down?*";
P_HTM[3381]="*Kaṃ ārabbha?**Whom is it about?*";
P_HTM[3382]="*Kismiṃ vatthusmiṃ?**What is it about?*";
P_HTM[3383]="*Atthi tattha paññatti, anupaññatti, anuppannapaññatti?**Is there a rule, an addition to the rule, an unprompted rule?*";
P_HTM[3384]="*Sabbatthapaññatti, padesapaññatti?**Is it a rule that applies everywhere, or that applies in a particular place?*";
P_HTM[3385]="*Sādhāraṇapaññatti, asādhāraṇapaññatti?**Is it a rule that the monks and nuns have in common, or a rule they do not have in common?*";
P_HTM[3386]="*Ekatopaññatti, ubhatopaññatti?**Is it a rule for one Sangha or for both Sanghas?*";
P_HTM[3387]="*Catunnaṃ pātimokkhuddesānaṃ katthogadhaṃ kattha pariyāpannaṃ?**In which of the four ways of reciting the Monastic Code is it immersed and included?*";
P_HTM[3388]="*Katamena uddesena uddesaṃ āgacchati?**In which recitation is it included?*";
P_HTM[3389]="*Catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ katamā vipatti?**To which of the four kinds of failure does it belong?*";
P_HTM[3390]="*Sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ katamo āpattikkhandho?**To which of the seven classes of offenses does it belong?*";
P_HTM[3391]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ katihi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhāti?**Through how many of the six kinds of origins of offenses does it originate?*";
P_HTM[3392]="*Catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ?**To which of the four kinds of legal issues does it belong?*";
P_HTM[3393]="*Sattannaṃ samathānaṃ katihi samathehi sammati?**Through how many of the seven principles for settling legal issues is it settled?*";
P_HTM[3394]="*Ko tattha vinayo?**What is the Monastic Law there?*";
P_HTM[3395]="*Ko tattha abhivinayo?**What is concerned with the Monastic Law there?*";
P_HTM[3396]="*Kiṃ tattha pātimokkhaṃ?**What is the Monastic Code there?*";
P_HTM[3397]="*Kiṃ tattha adhipātimokkhaṃ?**What is concerned with the Monastic Code there?*";
P_HTM[3398]="*Kā vipatti?**What is failure?*";
P_HTM[3399]="*Kā sampatti?**What is success?*";
P_HTM[3400]="*Kā paṭipatti?**What is the practice?*";
P_HTM[3401]="*Kati atthavase paṭicca bhagavatā bhikkhunīnaṃ pañcamaṃ pārājikaṃ paññattaṃ?**For how many reasons did the Buddha lay down the nun’s fifth offense entailing expulsion?*";
P_HTM[3402]="*Kā sikkhanti?**Who are those who train?*";
P_HTM[3403]="*Kā sikkhitasikkhā?**Who have done the training?*";
P_HTM[3404]="*Kattha ṭhitaṃ?**Established in what?*";
P_HTM[3405]="*Kā dhārenti?**Who master it?*";
P_HTM[3406]="*Kassa vacanaṃ?**Whose pronouncement was it?*";
P_HTM[3407]="*Kenābhatanti?**Who handed it down?”*";
P_HTM[3408]="*Yaṃ tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena bhikkhunīnaṃ pañcamaṃ pārājikaṃ kattha paññattanti?**“The nuns’ fifth offense entailing expulsion that was laid down by the Buddha who knows and sees, the Perfected One, the fully Awakened One—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[3409]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññattaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3410]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[3411]="*Sundarīnandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ ārabbha.**The nun Sundarīnandā.*";
P_HTM[3412]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[3413]="*Sundarīnandā bhikkhunī avassutā avassutassa purisapuggalassa kāyasaṃsaggaṃ sādiyi, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**The lustful nun Sundarīnandā consenting to a lustful man making physical contact with her.*";
P_HTM[3414]="*Atthi tattha paññatti anupaññatti anuppannapaññattīti?**“Is there a rule, an addition to the rule, an unprompted rule?”*";
P_HTM[3415]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[3416]="*Anupaññatti anuppannapaññatti tasmiṃ natthi.**There is no addition to the rule. There is no unprompted rule.*";
P_HTM[3417]="*Sabbatthapaññatti, padesapaññattīti?**“Is it a rule that applies everywhere, or that applies in a particular place?”*";
P_HTM[3418]="*Sabbatthapaññatti.**That applies everywhere.*";
P_HTM[3419]="*Sādhāraṇapaññatti, asādhāraṇapaññattīti?**“Is it a rule that the monks and nuns have in common, or a rule they do not have in common?”*";
P_HTM[3420]="*Asādhāraṇapaññatti.**A rule they do not have in common.*";
P_HTM[3421]="*Ekatopaññatti, ubhatopaññattīti?**“Is it a rule for one Sangha or for both Sanghas?”*";
P_HTM[3422]="*Ekatopaññatti.**For one Sangha.*";
P_HTM[3423]="*Catunnaṃ pātimokkhuddesānaṃ katthogadhaṃ kattha pariyāpannanti?**“In which of the four ways of reciting the Monastic Code is it immersed and included?”*";
P_HTM[3424]="*Nidānogadhaṃ nidānapariyāpannaṃ.**In the introduction.*";
P_HTM[3425]="*Katamena uddesena uddesaṃ āgacchatīti?**“In which recitation is it included?”*";
P_HTM[3426]="*Dutiyena uddesena uddesaṃ āgacchati.**In the second recitation.*";
P_HTM[3427]="*Catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ katamā vipattīti?**“To which of the four kinds of failure does it belong?”*";
P_HTM[3428]="*Sīlavipatti.**Failure in morality.*";
P_HTM[3429]="*Sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ katamo āpattikkhandhoti?**“To which of the seven classes of offenses does it belong?”*";
P_HTM[3430]="*Pārājikāpattikkhandho.**The class of offenses entailing expulsion.*";
P_HTM[3431]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ katihi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhātīti?**“Through how many of the six kinds of origins of offenses does it originate?”*";
P_HTM[3432]="*Ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhāti—**It originates in one way:*";
P_HTM[3433]="*kāyato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhāti, na vācato.**from body and mind, not from speech.*";
P_HTM[3434]="*Catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ katamaṃ adhikaraṇanti?**“To which of the four kinds of legal issues does it belong?”*";
P_HTM[3435]="*Āpattādhikaraṇaṃ?**Legal issues arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[3436]="*Sattannaṃ samathānaṃ katihi samathehi sammatīti?**“Through how many of the seven principles for settling legal issues is it settled?”*";
P_HTM[3437]="*Dvīhi samathehi sammati—**Through two of them:*";
P_HTM[3438]="*sammukhāvinayena ca paṭiññātakaraṇena ca.**by resolution face-to-face and by acting according to what has been admitted.*";
P_HTM[3439]="*Ko tattha vinayo, ko tattha abhivinayoti?**“What is the Monastic Law there? What is concerned with the Monastic Law there?”*";
P_HTM[3440]="*Paññatti vinayo, vibhatti abhivinayo.**The rules are the Monastic Law. Their analysis is concerned with the Monastic Law.*";
P_HTM[3441]="*Kiṃ tattha pātimokkhaṃ, kiṃ tattha adhipātimokkhanti?**“What is the Monastic Code there? What is concerned with the Monastic Code there?”*";
P_HTM[3442]="*Paññatti pātimokkhaṃ, vibhatti adhipātimokkhaṃ.**The rules are the Monastic Code. Their analysis is concerned with the Monastic Code.*";
P_HTM[3443]="*Kā vipattīti?**“What is failure?”*";
P_HTM[3444]="*Asaṃvaro vipatti.**Lack of restraint.*";
P_HTM[3445]="*Kā sampattīti?**“What is success?”*";
P_HTM[3446]="*Saṃvaro sampatti.**Restraint.*";
P_HTM[3447]="*Kā paṭipattīti?**“What is the practice?”*";
P_HTM[3448]="*“Na evarūpaṃ karissāmī”ti yāvajīvaṃ āpāṇakoṭikaṃ samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu.**Thinking, “I will not do such a thing,” one undertakes to train in the training rules for life.*";
P_HTM[3449]="*Kati atthavase paṭicca bhagavatā bhikkhunīnaṃ pañcamaṃ pārājikaṃ paññattanti?**“For how many reasons did the Buddha lay down the nun’s fifth offense entailing expulsion?”*";
P_HTM[3450]="*Dasa atthavase paṭicca bhagavatā bhikkhunīnaṃ pañcamaṃ pārājikaṃ paññattaṃ—**He laid it down for the following ten reasons:*";
P_HTM[3451]="*saṅghasuṭṭhutāya, saṅghaphāsutāya, dummaṅkūnaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ niggahāya, pesalānaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ phāsuvihārāya, diṭṭhadhammikānaṃ āsavānaṃ saṃvarāya, samparāyikānaṃ āsavānaṃ paṭighātāya, appasannānaṃ pasādāya, pasannānaṃ bhiyyobhāvāya, saddhammaṭṭhitiyā, vinayānuggahāya.**for the well-being of the Sangha, for the comfort of the Sangha, for the restraint of bad nuns, for the ease of good nuns, for the restraint of corruptions relating to the present life, for the restraint of corruptions relating to future lives, to give rise to confidence in those without it, to increase the confidence of those who have it, for the longevity of the true Teaching, and for supporting the training.*";
P_HTM[3452]="*Kā sikkhantīti?**“Who are those who train?”*";
P_HTM[3453]="*Sekkhā ca puthujjanakalyāṇikā ca sikkhanti.**They are the trainees and the good ordinary people.*";
P_HTM[3454]="*Kā sikkhitasikkhāti?**“Who have done the training?”*";
P_HTM[3455]="*Arahantiyo sikkhitasikkhā.**The perfected ones.*";
P_HTM[3456]="*Kattha ṭhitanti?**“Established in what?”*";
P_HTM[3457]="*Sikkhākāmāsu ṭhitaṃ.**In fondness for the training.*";
P_HTM[3458]="*Kā dhārentīti?**“Who master it?”*";
P_HTM[3459]="*Yāsaṃ vattati tā dhārenti.**Those who learn it.*";
P_HTM[3460]="*Kassa vacananti?**“Whose pronouncement was it?”*";
P_HTM[3461]="*Bhagavato vacanaṃ arahato sammāsambuddhassa.**It was the pronouncement of the Buddha, the Perfected One, the fully Awakened One.*";
P_HTM[3462]="*Kenābhatanti?**“Who handed it down?”*";
P_HTM[3463]="*Paramparābhataṃ—**The lineage:*";
P_HTM[3464]="*Upāli dāsako ceva,**“Upāli and Dāsaka,*";
P_HTM[3465]="*soṇako siggavo tathā;**Soṇaka and also Siggava;*";
P_HTM[3466]="*Moggaliputtena pañcamā,**With Moggaliputta as the fifth—*";
P_HTM[3467]="*ete jambusirivhaye.**these were in India, the land named after the glorious rose apple.*";
P_HTM[3468]="*Tato mahindo iṭṭiyo,**Then Mahinda, Iṭṭiya,*";
P_HTM[3469]="*uttiyo sambalo tathā;**Uttiya and also Sambala;*";
P_HTM[3470]="*Bhaddanāmo ca paṇḍito.**And the wise one named Bhadda:*";
P_HTM[3471]="*Ete nāgā mahāpaññā,**These mighty beings of great wisdom,*";
P_HTM[3472]="*jambudīpā idhāgatā;**Came here from India;*";
P_HTM[3473]="*Vinayaṃ te vācayiṃsu,**And they taught the Collection on Monastic Law*";
P_HTM[3474]="*piṭakaṃ tambapaṇṇiyā.**in Sri Lanka,*";
P_HTM[3475]="*Nikāye pañca vācesuṃ,**And the five Collections of Discourses,*";
P_HTM[3476]="*satta ceva pakaraṇe;**and the seven works of philosophy.*";
P_HTM[3477]="*Tato ariṭṭho medhāvī,**Then Ariṭṭha the discerning,*";
P_HTM[3478]="*tissadatto ca paṇḍito.**And the wise Tissadatta;*";
P_HTM[3479]="*Visārado kāḷasumano,**The confident Kālasumana,*";
P_HTM[3480]="*thero ca dīghanāmako;**The senior monk named Dīgha,*";
P_HTM[3481]="*Dīghasumano ca paṇḍito.**And the wise Dīghasumana;*";
P_HTM[3482]="*Punadeva kāḷasumano,**Another Kālasumana,*";
P_HTM[3483]="*Nāgatthero ca buddharakkhito;**The senior monk Nāga and Buddharakkhita,*";
P_HTM[3484]="*Tissatthero ca medhāvī,**The discerning senior monk Tissa,*";
P_HTM[3485]="*Devatthero ca paṇḍito.**And the wise senior monk Deva;*";
P_HTM[3486]="*Punadeva sumano medhāvī,**Another discerning Sumana,*";
P_HTM[3487]="*Vinaye ca visārado;**Confident in the Monastic Law,*";
P_HTM[3488]="*Bahussuto cūḷanāgo,**The learned Cūlanāga,*";
P_HTM[3489]="*Gajova duppadhaṃsiyo.**Invincible, like an elephant,*";
P_HTM[3490]="*Dhammapālitanāmo ca,**And the senior monk Dhammapālita;*";
P_HTM[3491]="*rohaṇe sādhupūjito;**Rohaṇa, venerated as a saint,*";
P_HTM[3492]="*Tassa sisso mahāpañño,**And his student Khema of great wisdom,*";
P_HTM[3493]="*khemanāmo tipeṭako.**A master of the three Collections,*";
P_HTM[3494]="*Dīpe tārakarājāva,**Like the king of the stars on the island,*";
P_HTM[3495]="*paññāya atirocatha;**He outshone others in his wisdom;*";
P_HTM[3496]="*Upatisso ca medhāvī,**The discerning Upatissa,*";
P_HTM[3497]="*phussadevo mahākathī.**Phussadeva the great speaker,*";
P_HTM[3498]="*Punadeva sumano medhāvī,**Another discerning Sumana,*";
P_HTM[3499]="*Pupphanāmo bahussuto;**And the learned one named Puppha;*";
P_HTM[3500]="*Mahākathī mahāsivo,**Mahāsīva the great speaker,*";
P_HTM[3501]="*Piṭake sabbattha kovido.**Skilled in the entire Collection,*";
P_HTM[3502]="*Punadeva upāli medhāvī,**Another discerning Upāli,*";
P_HTM[3503]="*Vinaye ca visārado;**Confident in the Monastic Law,*";
P_HTM[3504]="*Mahānāgo mahāpañño,**And Mahānāga of great wisdom,*";
P_HTM[3505]="*Saddhammavaṃsakovido.**Skilled in the tradition of the true Teaching;*";
P_HTM[3506]="*Punadeva abhayo medhāvī,**Another discerning Abhaya,*";
P_HTM[3507]="*Piṭake sabbattha kovido;**Skilled in the entire Collection,*";
P_HTM[3508]="*Tissatthero ca medhāvī,**The discerning senior monk Tissa,*";
P_HTM[3509]="*Vinaye ca visārado.**Confident in the Monastic Law,*";
P_HTM[3510]="*Tassa sisso mahāpañño,**And his student named Puppha,*";
P_HTM[3511]="*pupphanāmo bahussuto;**Of great wisdom and learning,*";
P_HTM[3512]="*Sāsanaṃ anurakkhanto,**Guarding Buddhism,*";
P_HTM[3513]="*jambudīpe patiṭṭhito.**He established himself in India.*";
P_HTM[3514]="*Cūḷābhayo ca medhāvī,**The discerning Cūlābhaya,*";
P_HTM[3515]="*vinaye ca visārado;**Confident in the Monastic Law;*";
P_HTM[3516]="*Tissatthero ca medhāvī,**The discerning senior monk Tissa,*";
P_HTM[3517]="*saddhammavaṃsakovido.**Skilled in the tradition of the true Teaching;*";
P_HTM[3518]="*Cūḷadevo ca medhāvī,**The discerning Cūladeva,*";
P_HTM[3519]="*vinaye ca visārado;**Confident in the Monastic Law;*";
P_HTM[3520]="*Sivatthero ca medhāvī,**And the discerning senior monk Siva,*";
P_HTM[3521]="*vinaye sabbattha kovido.**Skilled in the entire Monastic Law—*";
P_HTM[3522]="*Ete nāgā mahāpaññā,**These mighty beings of great wisdom,*";
P_HTM[3523]="*Vinayaññū maggakovidā;**Knowers of the Monastic Law and skilled in the path;*";
P_HTM[3524]="*Vinayaṃ dīpe pakāsesuṃ,**Proclaimed the Collection of Monastic Law*";
P_HTM[3525]="*Piṭakaṃ tambapaṇṇiyāti.**On the island of Sri Lanka.”*";
P_HTM[3526]="*Yaṃ tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena bhikkhunīnaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ pārājikaṃ kattha paññattanti?**“The nuns’ sixth offense entailing expulsion that was laid down by the Buddha who knows and sees, the Perfected One, the fully Awakened One—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[3527]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññattaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3528]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[3529]="*Thullanandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ ārabbha.**The nun Thullanandā.*";
P_HTM[3530]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[3531]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī jānaṃ pārājikaṃ dhammaṃ ajjhāpannaṃ bhikkhuniṃ nevattanā paṭicodesi na gaṇassa ārocesi, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**The nun Thullanandā, knowing that a nun had committed an offense entailing expulsion, neither confronting her herself nor telling the community.*";
P_HTM[3532]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[3533]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhāti—**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in one way:*";
P_HTM[3534]="*kāyato ca vācato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhāti …pe….**from body, speech, and mind. …*";
P_HTM[3535]="*Bhikkhunīnaṃ sattamaṃ pārājikaṃ kattha paññattanti?**“The nun’s seventh offense entailing expulsion—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[3536]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññattaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3537]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[3538]="*Thullanandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ ārabbha.**The nun Thullanandā.*";
P_HTM[3539]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[3540]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī samaggena saṅghena ukkhittaṃ ariṭṭhaṃ bhikkhuṃ gaddhabādhipubbaṃ anuvatti, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**The nun Thullanandā taking sides with the monk Ariṭṭha, an ex-vulture-killer, who had been ejected by a unanimous Sangha.*";
P_HTM[3541]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[3542]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhāti—**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in one way:*";
P_HTM[3543]="*dhuranikkhepe …pe….**through giving up one’s duty. …*";
P_HTM[3544]="*Bhikkhunīnaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ pārājikaṃ kattha paññattanti?**“The nun’s eighth offense entailing expulsion—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[3545]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññattaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3546]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[3547]="*Chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo ārabbha.**The nuns from the group of six.*";
P_HTM[3548]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[3549]="*Chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo aṭṭhamaṃ vatthuṃ paripūresuṃ, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**The nuns from the group of six fulfilling the eight parts.*";
P_HTM[3550]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[3551]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhāti—**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in one way:*";
P_HTM[3552]="*dhuranikkhepe …pe….**through giving up one’s duty. …*";
P_HTM[3553]="*Aṭṭha pārājikā niṭṭhitā.**The eight offenses entailing expulsion are finished.*";
P_HTM[3554]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[3555]="*Methunādinnādānañca,**“Sexual intercourse, and stealing,*";
P_HTM[3556]="*manussaviggahuttari;**Person, super;*";
P_HTM[3557]="*Kāyasaṃsaggaṃ chādeti,**Physical contact, conceals,*";
P_HTM[3558]="*ukkhittā aṭṭha vatthukā;**Ejected, eight parts—*";
P_HTM[3559]="*Paññāpesi mahāvīro,**The Great Hero laid down*";
P_HTM[3560]="*chejjavatthū asaṃsayāti.**The definitive grounds for cutting off.”*";
P_HTM[3561]="*2. Saṅghādisesakaṇḍa**2. The chapter on offenses entailing suspension*";
P_HTM[3562]="*Yaṃ tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena ussayavādikāya bhikkhuniyā aḍḍaṃ karontiyā saṅghādiseso kattha paññatto?**“The offense entailing suspension for a litigious nun in initiating a lawsuit was laid down by the Buddha who knows and sees, the Perfected One, the fully Awakened One. Where was it laid down?*";
P_HTM[3563]="*Kaṃ ārabbha?**Whom is it about?*";
P_HTM[3564]="*Kismiṃ vatthusmiṃ …pe…**What is it about? …*";
P_HTM[3565]="*kenābhatanti?**Who handed it down?”*";
P_HTM[3566]="*Yaṃ tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena ussayavādikāya bhikkhuniyā aḍḍaṃ karontiyā saṅghādiseso kattha paññattoti?**“The offense entailing suspension for a litigious nun in initiating a lawsuit that was laid down by the Buddha who knows and sees, the Perfected One, the fully Awakened One—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[3567]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññatto.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3568]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[3569]="*Thullanandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ ārabbha.**The nun Thullanandā.*";
P_HTM[3570]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[3571]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī ussayavādikā vihari, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**The nun Thullanandā being litigious.*";
P_HTM[3572]="*Atthi tattha paññatti, anupaññatti, anuppannapaññattīti?**“Is there a rule, an addition to the rule, an unprompted rule?”*";
P_HTM[3573]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[3574]="*Anupaññatti anuppannapaññatti tasmiṃ natthi.**There is no addition to the rule. There is no unprompted rule.*";
P_HTM[3575]="*Sabbatthapaññatti, padesapaññattīti?**“Is it a rule that applies everywhere, or that applies in a particular place?”*";
P_HTM[3576]="*Sabbatthapaññatti.**That applies everywhere.*";
P_HTM[3577]="*Sādhāraṇapaññatti, asādhāraṇapaññattīti?**“Is it a rule that the monks and nuns have in common, or a rule they do not have in common?”*";
P_HTM[3578]="*Asādhāraṇapaññatti.**A rule they do not have in common.*";
P_HTM[3579]="*Ekatopaññatti, ubhatopaññattīti?**“Is it a rule for one Sangha or for both Sanghas?”*";
P_HTM[3580]="*Ekatopaññatti.**For one Sangha.*";
P_HTM[3581]="*Catunnaṃ pātimokkhuddesānaṃ katthogadhaṃ kattha pariyāpannanti?**“In which of the four ways of reciting the Monastic Code is it immersed and included?”*";
P_HTM[3582]="*Nidānogadhaṃ nidānapariyāpannaṃ.**In the introduction.*";
P_HTM[3583]="*Katamena uddesena uddesaṃ āgacchatīti?**“In which recitation is it included?”*";
P_HTM[3584]="*Tatiyena uddesena uddesaṃ āgacchati.**In the third recitation.*";
P_HTM[3585]="*Catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ katamā vipattīti?**“To which of the four kinds of failure does it belong?”*";
P_HTM[3586]="*Sīlavipatti.**Failure in morality.*";
P_HTM[3587]="*Sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ katamo āpattikkhandhoti?**“To which of the seven classes of offenses does it belong?”*";
P_HTM[3588]="*Saṅghādisesāpattikkhandho.**The class of offenses entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[3589]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ katihi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhātīti?**“Through how many of the six kinds of origins of offenses does it originate?”*";
P_HTM[3590]="*Dvīhi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhāti—**It originates in two ways:*";
P_HTM[3591]="*siyā kāyato ca vācato ca samuṭṭhāti, na cittato;**from body and speech, not from mind; or*";
P_HTM[3592]="*siyā kāyato ca vācato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhāti …pe…**from body, speech, and mind. …*";
P_HTM[3593]="*kenābhatanti?**“Who handed it down?”*";
P_HTM[3594]="*Paramparābhataṃ—**The lineage:*";
P_HTM[3595]="*Upāli dāsako ceva,**“Upāli and Dāsaka,*";
P_HTM[3596]="*soṇako siggavo tathā;**Soṇaka and also Siggava;*";
P_HTM[3597]="*Moggaliputtena pañcamā,**With Moggaliputta as the fifth—*";
P_HTM[3598]="*ete jambusirivhaye.**these were in India, the land named after the glorious rose apple.*";
P_HTM[3599]="*…pe…**…*";
P_HTM[3600]="*Ete nāgā mahāpaññā,**These mighty beings of great wisdom,*";
P_HTM[3601]="*Vinayaññū maggakovidā;**Knowers of the Monastic Law and skilled in the path,*";
P_HTM[3602]="*Vinayaṃ dīpe pakāsesuṃ,**Proclaimed the Collection of Monastic Law*";
P_HTM[3603]="*Piṭakaṃ tambapaṇṇiyāti.**On the island of Sri Lanka.*";
P_HTM[3604]="*Coriṃ vuṭṭhāpentiyā saṅghādiseso kattha paññattoti?**“The offense entailing suspension for giving the full admission to a female criminal—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[3605]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññatto.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3606]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[3607]="*Thullanandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ ārabbha.**The nun Thullanandā.*";
P_HTM[3608]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[3609]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī coriṃ vuṭṭhāpesi, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**The nun Thullanandā giving the full admission to a female criminal.*";
P_HTM[3610]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[3611]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ dvīhi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhāti—**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in two ways:*";
P_HTM[3612]="*siyā vācato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhāti, na kāyato;**from speech and mind, not from body; or*";
P_HTM[3613]="*siyā kāyato ca vācato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhāti …pe….**from body, speech, and mind. …*";
P_HTM[3614]="*Ekāya gāmantaraṃ gacchantiyā saṅghādiseso kattha paññattoti?**“The offense entailing suspension for walking to the next village by oneself—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[3615]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññatto.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3616]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[3617]="*Aññataraṃ bhikkhuniṃ ārabbha.**A certain nun.*";
P_HTM[3618]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[3619]="*Aññatarā bhikkhunī ekā gāmantaraṃ gacchi, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**A certain nun walking to the next village by herself.*";
P_HTM[3620]="*Ekā paññatti, tisso anupaññattiyo.**There is one rule. There are three additions to the rule.*";
P_HTM[3621]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhāti—**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in one way:*";
P_HTM[3622]="*paṭhamapārājike …pe….**(as in the first offense entailing expulsion) …*";
P_HTM[3623]="*Samaggena saṅghena ukkhittaṃ bhikkhuniṃ dhammena vinayena satthusāsanena anapaloketvā kārakasaṅghaṃ anaññāya gaṇassa chandaṃ osārentiyā saṅghādiseso kattha paññattoti?**“The offense entailing suspension for reinstating a nun who has been ejected by a unanimous Sangha in accordance with the rule, the Monastic Law, and the Teacher’s instruction, without getting permission from the Sangha that did the legal procedure and without the consent of the group—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[3624]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññatto.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3625]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[3626]="*Thullanandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ ārabbha.**The nun Thullanandā.*";
P_HTM[3627]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[3628]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī samaggena saṅghena ukkhittaṃ bhikkhuniṃ dhammena vinayena satthusāsanena anapaloketvā kārakasaṅghaṃ anaññāya gaṇassa chandaṃ osāresi, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**The nun Thullanandā reinstating a nun who has been ejected by a unanimous Sangha in accordance with the rule, the Monastic Law, and the Teacher’s instruction, without getting permission from the Sangha that did the legal procedure and without the consent of the group.*";
P_HTM[3629]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[3630]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhāti—**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in one way:*";
P_HTM[3631]="*dhuranikkhepe …pe….**through giving up one’s duty. …*";
P_HTM[3632]="*Avassutāya bhikkhuniyā avassutassa purisapuggalassa hatthato khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā sahatthā paṭiggahetvā bhuñjantiyā saṅghādiseso kattha paññattoti?**“The offense entailing suspension for a lustful nun eating fresh or cooked food after receiving it directly from a lustful man—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[3633]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññatto.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3634]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[3635]="*Sundarīnandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ ārabbha.**The nun Sundarīnandā.*";
P_HTM[3636]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[3637]="*Sundarīnandā bhikkhunī avassutā avassutassa purisapuggalassa hatthato āmisaṃ paṭiggahesi, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**The nun Sundarīnandā, being lustful, receiving food directly from a lustful man.*";
P_HTM[3638]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[3639]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhāti—**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in one way:*";
P_HTM[3640]="*paṭhamapārājike …pe….**(as in the first offense entailing expulsion) …*";
P_HTM[3641]="*“Kiṃ te, ayye, eso purisapuggalo karissati avassuto vā anavassuto vā, yato tvaṃ anavassutā.**“The offense entailing suspension for urging a nun on, saying, “Venerable, what can this man do to you, whether he has lust or not, if you’re without? Go on, Venerable, receive it yourself and then eat whatever fresh or cooked food he gives to you”—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[3642]="*Iṅgha, ayye, yaṃ te eso purisapuggalo deti khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā, taṃ tvaṃ sahatthā paṭiggahetvā khāda vā bhuñja vā”ti uyyojentiyā saṅghādiseso kattha paññattoti?* **";
P_HTM[3643]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññatto.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3644]="*Kaṃ arabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[3645]="*Aññataraṃ bhikkhuniṃ ārabbha.**A certain nun.*";
P_HTM[3646]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[3647]="*Aññatarā bhikkhunī—“kiṃ te, ayye, eso purisapuggalo karissati avassuto vā anavassuto vā, yato tvaṃ anavassutā. Iṅgha, ayye, yaṃ te eso purisapuggalo deti khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā, taṃ tvaṃ sahatthā paṭiggahetvā khāda vā bhuñja vā”ti uyyojesi, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**A certain nun urging a nun on, saying, “Venerable, what can this man do to you, whether he has lust or not, if you’re without? Go on, Venerable, receive it yourself and then eat whatever fresh or cooked food he gives to you.”*";
P_HTM[3648]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[3649]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ tīhi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhāti …pe….**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in three ways: …*";
P_HTM[3650]="*Kupitāya anattamanāya bhikkhuniyā yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjantiyā saṅghādiseso kattha paññattoti?**“The offense entailing suspension for an angry nun not to stop when pressed up to the third time—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[3651]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññatto.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3652]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[3653]="*Caṇḍakāḷiṃ bhikkhuniṃ ārabbha.**The nun Caṇḍakālī.*";
P_HTM[3654]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[3655]="*Caṇḍakāḷī bhikkhunī kupitā anattamanā evaṃ avaca—“buddhaṃ paccācikkhāmi, dhammaṃ paccācikkhāmi, saṅghaṃ paccācikkhāmi, sikkhaṃ paccācikkhāmī”ti, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**The nun Caṇḍakālī saying in anger that, “I renounce the Buddha, I renounce the Teaching, I renounce the Sangha, I renounce the training.”*";
P_HTM[3656]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[3657]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhāti—**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in one way:*";
P_HTM[3658]="*dhuranikkhepe …pe….**through giving up one’s duty. …*";
P_HTM[3659]="*Kismiñcideva adhikaraṇe paccākatāya bhikkhuniyā yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjantiyā saṅghādiseso kattha paññattoti?**“The offense entailing suspension for a nun who has had a legal issue decided against her not to stop when pressed up to the third time—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[3660]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññatto.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3661]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[3662]="*Caṇḍakāḷiṃ bhikkhuniṃ ārabbha.**The nun Caṇḍakālī.*";
P_HTM[3663]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[3664]="*Caṇḍakāḷī bhikkhunī kismiñcideva adhikaraṇe paccākatā kupitā anattamanā evaṃ avaca—“chandagāminiyo ca bhikkhuniyo, dosagāminiyo ca bhikkhuniyo, mohagāminiyo ca bhikkhuniyo, bhayagāminiyo ca bhikkhuniyo”ti, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**The nun Caṇḍakālī, who had had a legal issue decided against her, saying that, “The nuns are acting out of desire, ill will, confusion, and fear.”*";
P_HTM[3665]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[3666]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhāti—**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in one way:*";
P_HTM[3667]="*dhuranikkhepe …pe….**through giving up one’s duty. …*";
P_HTM[3668]="*Saṃsaṭṭhānaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjantīnaṃ saṅghādiseso kattha paññattoti?**“The offense entailing suspension for nuns who are socializing not to stop when pressed up to the third time—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[3669]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññatto.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3670]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[3671]="*Sambahulā bhikkhuniyo ārabbha.**A number of nuns.*";
P_HTM[3672]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[3673]="*Sambahulā bhikkhuniyo saṃsaṭṭhā vihariṃsu, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**A number of nuns socializing.*";
P_HTM[3674]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[3675]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhāti—**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in one way:*";
P_HTM[3676]="*dhuranikkhepe …pe….**through giving up one’s duty. …*";
P_HTM[3677]="*“Saṃsaṭṭhāva, ayye, tumhe viharatha.**“The offense entailing suspension for urging nuns in this way: “But, Venerables, you should socialize; don’t live separately;” and then not stopping when pressed up to the third time—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[3678]="*Mā tumhe nānā viharitthā”ti uyyojentiyā yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjantiyā saṅghādiseso kattha paññattoti?* **";
P_HTM[3679]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññatto.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3680]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[3681]="*Thullanandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ ārabbha.**The nun Thullanandā.*";
P_HTM[3682]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[3683]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī—“saṃsaṭṭhāva, ayye, tumhe viharatha, mā tumhe nānā viharitthā”ti uyyojesi, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**The nun Thullanandā urging nuns in this way: “But, Venerables, you should socialize. Don’t live separately.”*";
P_HTM[3684]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[3685]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhāti—**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in one way:*";
P_HTM[3686]="*dhuranikkhepe …pe….**through giving up one’s duty. …*";
P_HTM[3687]="*Dasa saṅghādisesā niṭṭhitā.**The ten rules entailing suspension are finished.*";
P_HTM[3688]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[3689]="*Ussayacori gāmantaṃ,**“Litigious, a criminal, the next village,*";
P_HTM[3690]="*ukkhittaṃ khādanena ca;**Ejected, and with fresh food;*";
P_HTM[3691]="*Kiṃ te kupitā kismiñci,**What to you, angry, a legal issue,*";
P_HTM[3692]="*saṃsaṭṭhā ñāyate dasāti.**Socializing, the same method: those are the ten.”*";
P_HTM[3693]="*3. Nissaggiyakaṇḍa**3. The chapter on relinquishment*";
P_HTM[3694]="*Yaṃ tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena pattasannicayaṃ karontiyā nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ kattha paññattanti?**“The offense entailing relinquishment and confession for collecting almsbowls that was laid down by the Buddha who knows and sees, the Perfected One, the fully Awakened One—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[3695]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññattaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3696]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[3697]="*Chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo ārabbha.**The nuns from the group of six.*";
P_HTM[3698]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[3699]="*Chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo pattasannicayaṃ akaṃsu, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**The nuns from the group of six collecting almsbowls.*";
P_HTM[3700]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[3701]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ dvīhi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhāti—**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in two ways:*";
P_HTM[3702]="*kathinake …pe….**(as in the sub-chapter on the robe-making season) …*";
P_HTM[3703]="*Akālacīvaraṃ “kālacīvaran”ti adhiṭṭhahitvā bhājāpentiyā nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ kattha paññattanti?**“The offense entailing relinquishment and confession for determining out-of-season robe-cloth as “in-season”, and then sharing it out—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[3704]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññattaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3705]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[3706]="*Thullanandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ ārabbha.**The nun Thullanandā.*";
P_HTM[3707]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[3708]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī akālacīvaraṃ “kālacīvaran”ti adhiṭṭhahitvā bhājāpesi, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**The nun Thullanandā determining out-of-season robe-cloth as “in-season”, and then sharing it out.*";
P_HTM[3709]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[3710]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ tīhi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhāti …pe….**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in three ways: …*";
P_HTM[3711]="*Bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ cīvaraṃ parivattetvā acchindantiyā nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ kattha paññattanti?**“The offense entailing relinquishment and confession for swapping a robe with a nun and then taking it back—where was it laid down?”*";
