P_HTM[3715]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[3716]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ cīvaraṃ parivattetvā acchindi, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**The nun Thullanandā swapping a robe with a nun and then taking it back.*";
P_HTM[3717]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[3718]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ tīhi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhāti …pe….**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in three ways: …*";
