P_HTM[4757]="*Chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo ārabbha.**The nuns from the group of six.*";
P_HTM[4758]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[4759]="*Chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo dadhiṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjiṃsu, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**The nuns from the group of six asking for curd and then eating it.*";
P_HTM[4760]="*Ekā paññatti, ekā anupaññatti.**There is one rule. There is one addition to the rule.*";
P_HTM[4761]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ catūhi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhāti—**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in four ways:*";
P_HTM[4762]="*siyā kāyato samuṭṭhāti, na vācato na cittato;**from body, not from speech or mind; or*";
P_HTM[4763]="*siyā kāyato ca vācato ca samuṭṭhāti, na cittato;**from body and speech, not from mind; or*";
P_HTM[4764]="*siyā kāyato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhāti, na vācato;**from body and mind, not from speech; or*";
P_HTM[4765]="*siyā kāyato ca vācato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhāti …pe….**from body, speech, and mind. …*";
P_HTM[4766]="*Aṭṭha pāṭidesanīyā niṭṭhitā.**The eight offenses entailing acknowledgment are finished.*";
P_HTM[4767]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[4768]="*Sappiṃ telaṃ madhuñceva,**“Ghee, oil, and honey,*";
P_HTM[4769]="*phāṇitaṃ macchameva ca;**Syrup, and fish;*";
P_HTM[4770]="*Maṃsaṃ khīraṃ dadhiñcāpi,**Meat, milk, and curd:*";
P_HTM[4771]="*viññāpetvāna bhikkhunī;**A nun asked for—*";
P_HTM[4772]="*Pāṭidesanīyā aṭṭha,**The eight offenses entailing acknowledgment,*";
P_HTM[4773]="*sayaṃ buddhena desitāti.**Taught by the Buddha himself.”*";
P_HTM[4774]="*Ye sikkhāpadā bhikkhuvibhaṅge vitthāritā te saṅkhittā bhikkhunivibhaṅge.**The training rules given in full in the monks’ analysis are contracted in the nuns’ analysis.*";
P_HTM[4775]="*Katthapaññattivāro niṭṭhito paṭhamo.**The first section on “where it was laid down” is finished.*";
P_HTM[4776]="*124. Paṭhamabhāga **124.  Part one *";
P_HTM[4777]="*Katāpattivāra**The section on “how many offenses”*";
P_HTM[4778]="*1. Pārājikakaṇḍa**1. The chapter on offenses entailing expulsion*";
P_HTM[4779]="*Avassutā bhikkhunī avassutassa purisapuggalassa kāyasaṃsaggaṃ sādiyantī kati āpattiyo āpajjati?**When a lustful nun consents to a lustful man making physical contact with her, how many kinds of offenses does she commit?*";
P_HTM[4780]="*Avassutā bhikkhunī avassutassa purisapuggalassa kāyasaṃsaggaṃ sādiyantī tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.**She commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4781]="*Adhakkhakaṃ ubbhajāṇumaṇḍalaṃ gahaṇaṃ sādiyati, āpatti pārājikassa;**when she consents to him taking hold of her anywhere below the collar bone but above the knees, she commits an offense entailing expulsion;*";
P_HTM[4782]="*ubbhakkhakaṃ adhojāṇumaṇḍalaṃ gahaṇaṃ sādiyati, āpatti thullaccayassa;**when she consents to him taking hold of her above the collar bone or below the knees, she commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[4783]="*kāyapaṭibaddhaṃ gahaṇaṃ sādiyati, āpatti dukkaṭassa—**when she consents to him taking hold of something connected to her body, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4784]="*avassutā bhikkhunī avassutassa purisapuggalassa kāyasaṃsaggaṃ sādiyantī imā tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[4785]="*Vajjappaṭicchādikā bhikkhunī vajjaṃ paṭicchādentī kati āpattiyo āpajjati?**When a nun who conceals offenses conceals an offense, how many kinds of offenses does she commit?*";
P_HTM[4786]="*Vajjappaṭicchādikā bhikkhunī vajjaṃ paṭicchādentī tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.**She commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4787]="*Jānaṃ pārājikaṃ dhammaṃ paṭicchādeti, āpatti pārājikassa;**when she knowingly conceals an offense entailing expulsion, she commits an offense involving expulsion;*";
P_HTM[4788]="*vematikā paṭicchādeti, āpatti thullaccayassa;**when, being unsure, she conceals it, she commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[4789]="*ācāravipattiṃ paṭicchādeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa—**when she conceals a failure in conduct, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4790]="*vajjappaṭicchādikā bhikkhunī vajjaṃ paṭicchādentī imā tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[4791]="*Ukkhittānuvattikā bhikkhunī yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjantī kati āpattiyo āpajjati?**When a nun takes sides with one who has been ejected and does not stop when pressed up to the third time, how many kinds of offenses does she commit?*";
P_HTM[4792]="*Ukkhittānuvattikā bhikkhunī yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjantī tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.**She commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4793]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ;**after the motion, she commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4794]="*dvīhi kammavācāhi thullaccayā;**after each of the first two announcements, she commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[4795]="*kammavācāpariyosāne āpatti pārājikassa—**when the last announcement is finished, she commits an offense entailing expulsion.*";
P_HTM[4796]="*ukkhittānuvattikā bhikkhunī yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjantī imā tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[4797]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ vatthuṃ paripūrentī kati āpattiyo āpajjati?**When fulfilling the eight parts, how many kinds of offenses does she commit?*";
P_HTM[4798]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ vatthuṃ paripūrentī tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.**She commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4799]="*Purisena—“itthannāmaṃ okāsaṃ āgacchā”ti vuttā gacchati, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when she goes to such-and-such a place when told by a man to do so, she commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4800]="*purisassa hatthapāsaṃ okkantamatte āpatti thullaccayassa;**when she enters within arm’s reach of the man, she commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[4801]="*aṭṭhamaṃ vatthuṃ paripūreti, āpatti pārājikassa—**when she fulfills the eight parts, she commits an offense entailing expulsion.*";
P_HTM[4802]="*aṭṭhamaṃ vatthuṃ paripūrentī imā tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[4803]="*Pārājikā niṭṭhitā.**The offenses entailing expulsion are finished.*";
P_HTM[4804]="*2. Saṅghādisesakaṇḍa**2. The chapter on offenses entailing suspension*";
P_HTM[4805]="*Ussayavādikā bhikkhunī aḍḍaṃ karontī tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.**When a litigious nun initiates a lawsuit, she commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4806]="*Ekassa āroceti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when she tells one other person, she commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4807]="*dutiyassa āroceti, āpatti thullaccayassa;**when she tells a second person, she commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[4808]="*aḍḍapariyosāne āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**when the lawsuit is finished, she commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[4809]="*Coriṃ vuṭṭhāpentī tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.**When giving the full admission to a female criminal, she commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4810]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ;**after the motion, she commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4811]="*dvīhi kammavācāhi thullaccayā;**after each of the first two announcements, she commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[4812]="*kammavācāpariyosāne āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**when the last announcement is finished, she commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[4813]="*Ekā gāmantaraṃ gacchantī tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.**When walking alone to the next village, she commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4814]="*Gacchati, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when she is in the process of going, she commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4815]="*paṭhamaṃ pādaṃ parikkhepaṃ atikkāmeti, āpatti thullaccayassa;**when she crosses the boundary with her first foot, she commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[4816]="*dutiyaṃ pādaṃ atikkāmeti, āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**when she crosses with her second foot, she commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[4817]="*Samaggena saṅghena ukkhittaṃ bhikkhuniṃ dhammena vinayena satthusāsanena anapaloketvā kārakasaṅghaṃ anaññāya gaṇassa chandaṃ osārentī tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.**When reinstating—without getting permission from the Sangha that did the legal procedure and without the consent of the group—a nun who has been ejected by a unanimous Sangha in accordance with the rule and the Monastic Law and the Teacher’s instruction, she commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4818]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ;**after the motion, she commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4819]="*dvīhi kammavācāhi thullaccayā;**after each of the first two announcements, she commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[4820]="*kammavācāpariyosāne āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**when the last announcement is finished, she commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[4821]="*Avassutā bhikkhunī avassutassa purisapuggalassa hatthato khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā sahatthā paṭiggahetvā bhuñjantī tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.**When a lustful nun eats fresh or cooked food after receiving it directly from a lustful man, she commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4822]="*“Khādissāmi bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti thullaccayassa;**when she receives fresh or cooked food with the intention of eating it, she commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[4823]="*ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti saṅghādisesassa;**for every mouthful, she commits an offense entailing suspension;*";
P_HTM[4824]="*udakadantaponaṃ paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**when she receives water or a tooth cleaner, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4825]="*“Kiṃ te, ayye, eso purisapuggalo karissati avassuto vā anavassuto vā, yato tvaṃ anavassutā. Iṅgha, ayye, yaṃ te eso purisapuggalo deti khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā, taṃ tvaṃ sahatthā paṭiggahetvā khāda vā bhuñja vā”ti uyyojentī tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.**When urging a nun on, saying, “Venerable, what can this man do to you, whether he has lust or not, if you’re without? Go on, Venerable, receive it yourself and then eat whatever fresh or cooked food he gives to you,” she commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4826]="*Tassā vacanena khādissāmi bhuñjissāmīti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when, because of her statement, the other nun receives it with the intention of eating it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4827]="*ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti thullaccayassa;**for every mouthful, she commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[4828]="*bhojanapariyosāne āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**when the meal is finished, she commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[4829]="*Kupitā bhikkhunī yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjantī tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.**When an angry nun does not stop when pressed up to the third time, she commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4830]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ;**after the motion, she commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4831]="*dvīhi kammavācāhi thullaccayā;**after each of the first two announcements, she commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[4832]="*kammavācāpariyosāne āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**when the last announcement is finished, she commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[4833]="*Kismiñcideva adhikaraṇe paccākatā bhikkhunī yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjantī tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.**When a nun who has had a legal issue decided against her does not stop when pressed up to the third time, she commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4834]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ;**after the motion, she commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4835]="*dvīhi kammavācāhi thullaccayā;**after each of the first two announcements, she commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[4836]="*kammavācāpariyosāne āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**when the last announcement is finished, she commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[4837]="*Saṃsaṭṭhā bhikkhuniyo yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjantiyo tisso āpattiyo āpajjanti.**When socializing nuns do not stop when pressed up to the third time, they commit three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4838]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ;**after the motion, they commit an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4839]="*dvīhi kammavācāhi thullaccayā;**after each of the first two announcements, they commit a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[4840]="*kammavācāpariyosāne āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**when the last announcement is finished, they commit an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[4841]="*“Saṃsaṭṭhāva, ayye, tumhe viharatha. Mā tumhe nānā viharitthā”ti uyyojentī yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjantī tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.**When urging a nun on, saying, “Venerables, you should socialize; don’t live separately;” and not stopping when pressed up to the third time, she commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4842]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ;**after the motion, she commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4843]="*dvīhi kammavācāhi thullaccayā;**after each of the first two announcements, she commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[4844]="*kammavācāpariyosāne āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**when the last announcement is finished, she commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[4845]="*Saṅghādisesā niṭṭhitā.**The offenses entailing suspension are finished.*";
P_HTM[4846]="*3. Nissaggiyakaṇḍa**3. The chapter on relinquishment*";
P_HTM[4847]="*Pattasannicayaṃ karontī ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati.**When collecting almsbowls, she commits one kind of offense:*";
P_HTM[4848]="*Nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[4849]="*Akālacīvaraṃ “kālacīvaran”ti adhiṭṭhahitvā bhājāpentī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When determining out-of-season robe-cloth as “in-season”, and then sharing it out, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4850]="*Bhājāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of sharing it out, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4851]="*bhājāpite nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**when she has shared it out, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[4852]="*Bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ cīvaraṃ parivattetvā acchindantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When swapping robes with a nun and then just taking it back, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4853]="*Acchindati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process taking it back, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4854]="*acchinne nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**when she has taken it back, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[4855]="*Aññaṃ viññāpetvā aññaṃ viññāpentī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When asking for one thing and then for something else, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4856]="*Viññāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of asking, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4857]="*viññāpite nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**when she has asked, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[4858]="*Aññaṃ cetāpetvā aññaṃ cetāpentī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When getting one thing in exchange and then something else, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4859]="*Cetāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of getting it in exchange, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4860]="*cetāpite nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**when she has received it in exchange, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[4861]="*Aññadatthikena parikkhārena aññuddisikena saṅghikena aññaṃ cetāpentī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When exchanging for something else a requisite belonging to the Sangha that is designated for a specific purpose, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4862]="*Cetāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of getting it in exchange, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4863]="*cetāpite nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**when she has received it in exchange, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[4864]="*Aññadatthikena parikkhārena aññuddisikena saṅghikena saṃyācikena aññaṃ cetāpentī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When exchanging for something else a requisite belonging to the Sangha that is designated for a specific purpose and was asked for, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4865]="*Cetāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of getting it in exchange, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4866]="*cetāpite nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**when she has received it in exchange, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[4867]="*Aññadatthikena parikkhārena aññuddisikena mahājanikena aññaṃ cetāpentī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When exchanging for something else a collective requisite that is designated for a specific purpose, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4868]="*Cetāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of getting it in exchange, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4869]="*cetāpite nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**when she has received it in exchange, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[4870]="*Aññadatthikena parikkhārena aññuddisikena mahājanikena saṃyācikena aññaṃ cetāpentī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When exchanging for something else a collective requisite that is designated for a specific purpose and was asked for, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4871]="*Cetāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of getting it in exchange, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4872]="*cetāpite nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**when she has received it in exchange, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[4873]="*Aññadatthikena parikkhārena aññuddisikena puggalikena saṃyācikena aññaṃ cetāpentī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When exchanging for something else a personal requisite that is designated for a specific purpose and was asked for, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4874]="*Cetāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of getting it in exchange, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4875]="*cetāpite nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**when she has received it in exchange, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[4876]="*Atirekacatukkaṃsaparamaṃ garupāvuraṇaṃ cetāpentī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When getting in exchange a heavy cloak worth more than four _kaṃsa_ coins, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4877]="*Cetāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of getting it in exchange, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4878]="*cetāpite nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**when she has received it in exchange, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[4879]="*Atirekaaḍḍhateyyakaṃsaparamaṃ lahupāvuraṇaṃ cetāpentī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When getting in exchange a light cloak worth more than two-and-a-half _kaṃsa_ coins, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4880]="*Cetāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of getting it in exchange, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4881]="*cetāpite nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**when she has received it in exchange, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[4882]="*Nissaggiyā pācittiyā niṭṭhitā.**The rules on relinquishment and confession are finished.*";
P_HTM[4883]="*4. Pācittiyakaṇḍa**4. The chapter on offenses entailing confession*";
P_HTM[4884]="*4.1. Lasuṇavagga**4.1 The sub-chapter on garlic*";
P_HTM[4885]="*Lasuṇaṃ khādantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When eating garlic, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4886]="*Khādissāmīti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when she receives it with the intention of eating it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4887]="*ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pācittiyassa.**for every mouthful, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4888]="*Sambādhe lomaṃ saṃharāpentī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When removing hair from the private parts, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4889]="*Saṃharāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of removing them, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4890]="*saṃharāpite āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has removed them, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4891]="*Talaghātakaṃ karontī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When slapping her genitals with the palm of her hand, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4892]="*Karoti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of slapping, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4893]="*kate āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she is done, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4894]="*Jatumaṭṭhakaṃ ādiyantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When using a dildo, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4895]="*Ādiyati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is using it, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4896]="*ādinne āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she is done, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4897]="*Atirekadvaṅgulapabbaparamaṃ udakasuddhikaṃ ādiyantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When cleaning herself with water by inserting more than two finger joints, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4898]="*Ādiyati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of cleaning, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4899]="*ādinne āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she is done, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4900]="*Bhikkhussa bhuñjantassa pānīyena vā vidhūpanena vā upatiṭṭhantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When attending on a monk who is eating with drinking water or a fan, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4901]="*Hatthapāse tiṭṭhati, āpatti pācittiyassa;**when standing within arm’s reach, she commits an offense entailing confession;*";
P_HTM[4902]="*hatthapāsaṃ vijahitvā tiṭṭhati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**when she standing beyond arm’s reach, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4903]="*Āmakadhaññaṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When asking for raw grain and then eating it, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4904]="*“Bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when she is in the process of receiving with the intention to eat, she commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4905]="*ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pācittiyassa.**for every mouthful, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4906]="*Uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā saṅkāraṃ vā vighāsaṃ vā tirokuṭṭe vā tiropākāre vā chaḍḍentī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When disposing of feces, urine, trash, or food scraps over a wall or over an encircling wall, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4907]="*Chaḍḍeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of discarding it, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4908]="*chaḍḍite āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has discarded it, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4909]="*Uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā saṅkāraṃ vā vighāsaṃ vā harite chaḍḍentī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When disposing of feces, urine, trash, or food scraps on cultivated plants, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4910]="*Chaḍḍeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of discarding it, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4911]="*chaḍḍite āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has discarded it, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4912]="*Naccaṃ vā gītaṃ vā vāditaṃ vā dassanāya gacchantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When going to see dancing, singing, or music, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4913]="*Gacchati, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when she is in the process of going, she commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4914]="*yattha ṭhitā passati vā suṇāti vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**wherever she stands to see or har it, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4915]="*Lasuṇavaggo paṭhamo.**The first sub-chapter on garlic is finished.*";
P_HTM[4916]="*4.2. Rattandhakāravagga**4.2 The sub-chapter on the dark of the night*";
P_HTM[4917]="*Rattandhakāre appadīpe purisena saddhiṃ ekenekā santiṭṭhantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When standing alone with a man in the dark of the night without a lamp, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4918]="*Hatthapāse tiṭṭhati, āpatti pācittiyassa;**when she stands within arm’s reach, she commits an offense entailing confession;*";
P_HTM[4919]="*hatthapāsaṃ vijahitvā tiṭṭhati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**when she stands beyond arm’s reach, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4920]="*Paṭicchanne okāse purisena saddhiṃ ekenekā santiṭṭhantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When standing alone with a man in a concealed place, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4921]="*Hatthapāse tiṭṭhati, āpatti pācittiyassa;**when she stands within arm’s reach, she commits an offense entailing confession;*";
P_HTM[4922]="*hatthapāsaṃ vijahitvā tiṭṭhati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**when she stands beyond arm’s reach, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4923]="*Ajjhokāse purisena saddhiṃ ekenekā santiṭṭhantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When standing alone with a man out in the open, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4924]="*Hatthapāse tiṭṭhati, āpatti pācittiyassa;**when she stands within arm’s reach, she commits an offense entailing confession;*";
P_HTM[4925]="*hatthapāsaṃ vijahitvā tiṭṭhati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**when she stands beyond arm’s reach, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4926]="*Rathikāya vā byūhe vā siṅghāṭake vā purisena saddhiṃ ekenekā santiṭṭhantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When standing alone with a man on a street, in a cul-de-sac, or at an intersection, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4927]="*Hatthapāse tiṭṭhati, āpatti pācittiyassa;**when she stands within arm’s reach, she commits an offense entailing confession;*";
P_HTM[4928]="*hatthapāsaṃ vijahitvā tiṭṭhati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**when she stands beyond arm’s reach, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4929]="*Purebhattaṃ kulāni upasaṅkamitvā āsane nisīditvā sāmike anāpucchā pakkamantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When visiting families before the meal, sitting down on a seat, and then departing without taking leave of the owners, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4930]="*Paṭhamaṃ pādaṃ anovassakaṃ atikkāmeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when she goes beyond the roof cover of the house with the first foot, she commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4931]="*dutiyaṃ pādaṃ atikkāmeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she goes beyond with the second foot, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4932]="*Pacchābhattaṃ kulāni upasaṅkamitvā sāmike anāpucchā āsane nisīdantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When visiting families after the meal and then sitting down on a seat without asking permission of the owners, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4933]="*Nisīdati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of sitting down, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4934]="*nisinne āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she is seated, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4935]="*Vikāle kulāni upasaṅkamitvā sāmike anāpucchā seyyaṃ santharitvā vā santharāpetvā vā abhinisīdantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When going to families at the wrong time, putting out bedding without asking permission of the owners, or having it put out, and then sitting down, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4936]="*Abhinisīdati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of sitting down, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4937]="*abhinisinne āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she is seated, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4938]="*Duggahitena dūpadhāritena paraṃ ujjhāpentī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When complaining about someone else because of misunderstanding and a lack of proper reflection, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4939]="*Ujjhāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of complaining, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4940]="*ujjhāpite āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has complained, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4941]="*Attānaṃ vā paraṃ vā nirayena vā brahmacariyena vā abhisapantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When invoking hell or the spiritual life to curse oneself or someone else, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4942]="*Abhisapati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of cursing, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4943]="*abhisapite āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has finished cursing, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4944]="*Attānaṃ vadhitvā vadhitvā rodantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When crying after repeatedly beating herself, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4945]="*Vadhati rodati, āpatti pācittiyassa;**when beating herself and crying, she commits an offense entailing confession;*";
P_HTM[4946]="*vadhati na rodati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**when beating herself but not crying, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4947]="*Rattandhakāravaggo dutiyo.**The second sub-chapter on the dark of the night is finished.*";
P_HTM[4948]="*4.3. Nahānavagga**4.3 The sub-chapter on bathing*";
P_HTM[4949]="*Naggā nahāyantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When bathing naked, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4950]="*Nahāyati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is bathing, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4951]="*nahānapariyosāne āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she is finished bathing, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4952]="*Pamāṇātikkantaṃ udakasāṭikaṃ kārāpentī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When making a bathing robe that exceeds the right size, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4953]="*Kārāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of making it, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4954]="*kārāpite, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has made it, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4955]="*Bhikkhuniyā cīvaraṃ visibbetvā vā visibbāpetvā vā neva sibbentī na sibbāpanāya ussukkaṃ karontī ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati.**When unstitching a nun’s robe, or having it unstitched, and then neither sewing it oneself nor making any effort to have someone else sew it, she commits one kind of offense:*";
P_HTM[4956]="*Pācittiyaṃ.**an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4957]="*Pañcāhikaṃ saṅghāṭicāraṃ atikkāmentī ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati.**When not moving one’s robes for more than five days, she commits one kind of offense:*";
P_HTM[4958]="*Pācittiyaṃ.**an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4959]="*Cīvarasaṅkamanīyaṃ dhārentī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When wearing a borrowed robe, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4960]="*Dhāreti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is wearing it, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4961]="*dhārite, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has worn it, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4962]="*Gaṇassa cīvaralābhaṃ antarāyaṃ karontī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When creating an obstacle for a group to get a robe, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4963]="*Karoti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of creating it, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4964]="*kate, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has created it, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4965]="*Dhammikaṃ cīvaravibhaṅgaṃ paṭibāhantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When blocking a legitimate distribution of robe-cloth, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4966]="*Paṭibāhati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of blocking it, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4967]="*paṭibāhite, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has blocked it, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4968]="*Agārikassa vā paribbājakassa vā paribbājikāya vā samaṇacīvaraṃ dentī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When giving a monastic robe to a householder, a male wanderer, or a female wanderer, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4969]="*Deti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of giving it, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4970]="*dinne, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when it has been given, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4971]="*Dubbalacīvarapaccāsāya cīvarakālasamayaṃ atikkāmentī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When letting the robe season pass because of an uncertain expectation of robe-cloth, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4972]="*Atikkāmeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of letting it pass, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4973]="*atikkāmite, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has let it pass, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4974]="*Dhammikaṃ kathinuddhāraṃ paṭibāhantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When blocking a legitimate ending of the robe-making season, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4975]="*Paṭibāhati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of blocking it, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4976]="*paṭibāhite, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has blocked it, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4977]="*Nahānavaggo tatiyo.**The third sub-chapter on bathing is finished.*";
P_HTM[4978]="*4.4. Tuvaṭṭavagga**4.4 The sub-chapter on lying down*";
P_HTM[4979]="*Dve bhikkhuniyo ekamañce tuvaṭṭentiyo dve āpattiyo āpajjanti.**When two nuns to lie down on the same bed, they commit two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4980]="*Nipajjanti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when they are in the process of lying down, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4981]="*nipanne, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when they are lying down, they commit an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4982]="*Dve bhikkhuniyo ekattharaṇapāvuraṇā tuvaṭṭentiyo dve āpattiyo āpajjanti.**When two nuns lie down on the same sheet and under the same cover, they commit two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4983]="*Nipajjanti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when they are in the process of lying down, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4984]="*nipanne, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when they are lying down, they commit an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4985]="*Bhikkhuniyā sañcicca aphāsuṃ karontī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When intentionally making a nun ill at ease, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4986]="*Karoti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is doing it, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4987]="*kate, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has done it, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4988]="*Dukkhitaṃ sahajīviniṃ neva upaṭṭhentī na upaṭṭhāpanāya ussukkaṃ karontī ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati.**When not nursing a suffering disciple, nor making any effort to have someone else nurse her, she commits one kind of offense:*";
P_HTM[4989]="*Pācittiyaṃ.**an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4990]="*Bhikkhuniyā upassayaṃ datvā kupitā anattamanā nikkaḍḍhantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When giving a dwelling place to a nun, and then, in anger, throwing her out, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4991]="*Nikkaḍḍhati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of throwing her out, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4992]="*nikkaḍḍhite, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has thrown her out, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4993]="*Saṃsaṭṭhā bhikkhunī yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When a socializing nun does not stop when pressed up to the third time, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4994]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ;**after the motion, she commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4995]="*kammavācāpariyosāne āpatti pācittiyassa.**when the last announcement is finished, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4996]="*Antoraṭṭhe sāsaṅkasammate sappaṭibhaye asatthikā cārikaṃ carantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When wandering without a group of travelers where it is considered risky and dangerous within one’s own country, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[4997]="*Paṭipajjati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is traveling, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[4998]="*paṭipanne, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has traveled, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4999]="*Tiroraṭṭhe sāsaṅkasammate sappaṭibhaye asatthikā cārikaṃ carantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When wandering without a group of travelers where it is considered risky and dangerous outside one’s own country, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5000]="*Paṭipajjati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is traveling, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5001]="*paṭipanne, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has traveled, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5002]="*Antovassaṃ cārikaṃ carantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When wandering during the rainy season, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5003]="*Paṭipajjati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is traveling, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5004]="*paṭipanne, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has traveled, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5005]="*Vassaṃvuṭṭhā bhikkhunī cārikaṃ na pakkamantī ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati.**When a nun who has completed the rainy-season residence does not go wandering, she commits one kind of offense:*";
P_HTM[5006]="*Pācittiyaṃ.**an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5007]="*Tuvaṭṭavaggo catuttho.**The fourth sub-chapter on lying down is finished.*";
P_HTM[5008]="*4.5. Cittāgāravagga**4.5 The sub-chapter on pleasure houses*";
P_HTM[5009]="*Rājāgāraṃ vā cittāgāraṃ vā ārāmaṃ vā uyyānaṃ vā pokkharaṇiṃ vā dassanāya gacchantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When visiting a royal house, a pleasure house, a park, a garden, or a lotus pond, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5010]="*Gacchati, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when she is in the process of going, she commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5011]="*yattha ṭhitā passati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**wherever she stands to see them, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5012]="*Āsandiṃ vā pallaṅkaṃ vā paribhuñjantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When using a high or luxurious couch, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5013]="*Paribhuñjati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is using it, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5014]="*paribhutte, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has used it, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5015]="*Suttaṃ kantantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When spinning yarn, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5016]="*Kantati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is spinning, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5017]="*ujjavujjave, āpatti pācittiyassa.**for every pull, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5018]="*Gihiveyyāvaccaṃ karontī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When providing services for a householder, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5019]="*Karoti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of providing them, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5020]="*kate, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when they have been provided, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5021]="*Bhikkhuniyā—“ehāyye, imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasamehī”ti vuccamānā—“sādhū”ti paṭissuṇitvā neva vūpasamentī na vūpasamāya ussukkaṃ karontī ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati.**When consenting to resolve a legal issue—when asked by a nun—but then neither resolving it nor making any effort to resolve it, she commits one kind of offense:*";
P_HTM[5022]="*Pācittiyaṃ.**an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5023]="*Agārikassa vā paribbājakassa vā paribbājikāya vā sahatthā khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā dentī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When personally giving fresh or cooked food to a householder, a male wanderer, or a female wanderer, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5024]="*Deti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of giving, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5025]="*dinne, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has given, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5026]="*Āvasathacīvaraṃ anissajjitvā paribhuñjantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When not relinquishing and continuing to use a monastery robe, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5027]="*Paribhuñjati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is using it, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5028]="*paribhutte, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has used it, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5029]="*Āvasathaṃ anissajjitvā cārikaṃ pakkamantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When going wandering without relinquishing one’s lodging, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5030]="*Paṭhamaṃ pādaṃ parikkhepaṃ atikkāmeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when she crosses the boundary with her first foot, she commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5031]="*dutiyaṃ pādaṃ atikkāmeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she crosses with her second foot, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5032]="*Tiracchānavijjaṃ pariyāpuṇantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When studying pointless knowledge, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5033]="*Pariyāpuṇāti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is studying, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5034]="*pade pade āpatti pācittiyassa.**for every line, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5035]="*Tiracchānavijjaṃ vācentī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When teaching pointless knowledge, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5036]="*Vāceti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is teaching, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5037]="*pade pade āpatti pācittiyassa.**for every line, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5038]="*Cittāgāravaggo pañcamo.**The fifth sub-chapter on pleasure houses is finished.*";
P_HTM[5039]="*4.6. Ārāmavagga**4.6 The sub-chapter on monasteries*";
P_HTM[5040]="*Jānaṃ sabhikkhukaṃ ārāmaṃ anāpucchā pavisantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When entering a monastery without asking permission, but knowing that there are monks there, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5041]="*Paṭhamaṃ pādaṃ parikkhepaṃ atikkāmeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when she crosses the boundary with her first foot, she commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5042]="*dutiyaṃ pādaṃ atikkāmeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she crosses with her second foot, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5043]="*Bhikkhuṃ akkosantī paribhāsantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When abusing or reviling a monk, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5044]="*Akkosati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of abusing, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5045]="*akkosite, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she is done, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5046]="*Caṇḍīkatā gaṇaṃ paribhāsantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When reviling a group while enraged, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5047]="*Paribhāsati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of reviling, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5048]="*paribhāsite, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she is done, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5049]="*Nimantitā vā pavāritā vā khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā bhuñjantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When refusing an offer or invitation to eat more, and then eating fresh or cooked food, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5050]="*“Khādissāmi bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when receiving with the intention to eat, she commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5051]="*ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pācittiyassa.**for every mouthful, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5052]="*Kulaṃ maccharāyantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When being stingy with families, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5053]="*Maccharāyati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of being stingy, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5054]="*maccharite, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has been stingy, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5055]="*Abhikkhuke āvāse vassaṃ vasantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When spending the rainy-season residence in a monastery without monks, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5056]="*“Vassaṃ vasissāmī”ti senāsanaṃ paññapeti pānīyaṃ paribhojanīyaṃ upaṭṭhapeti pariveṇaṃ sammajjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when thinking, “I’ll stay here for the rainy-season residence,” and she prepares a dwelling, sets out water for drinking and water for washing, and sweeps the precincts, she commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5057]="*saha aruṇuggamanā āpatti pācittiyassa.**At dawn, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5058]="*Vassaṃvuṭṭhā bhikkhunī ubhatosaṅghe tīhi ṭhānehi na pavārentī ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati.**When a nun who has completed the rainy-season residence does not invite correction from both Sanghas in regard to three things, she commits one kind of offense:*";
P_HTM[5059]="*Pācittiyaṃ.**an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5060]="*Ovādāya vā saṃvāsāya vā na gacchantī ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati.**When not going to the instruction or taking part in a formal meeting of the community, she commits one kind of offense:*";
P_HTM[5061]="*Pācittiyaṃ.**an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5062]="*Uposathampi na pucchantī ovādampi na yācantī ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati.**When not asking about the observance day and not going to the instruction, she commits one kind of offense:*";
P_HTM[5063]="*Pācittiyaṃ.**an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5064]="*Pasākhe jātaṃ gaṇḍaṃ vā rudhitaṃ vā anapaloketvā saṅghaṃ vā gaṇaṃ vā purisena saddhiṃ ekenekā bhedāpentī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When being alone with a man and having him rupture an abscess or a wound situated on her thigh, without getting permission from the Sangha or a group, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5065]="*Bhedāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of having it ruptured, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5066]="*bhinne, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when it has been ruptured, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5067]="*Ārāmavaggo chaṭṭho.**The sixth sub-chapter on monasteries is finished.*";
P_HTM[5068]="*4.7. Gabbhinivagga**4.7 The sub-chapter on pregnant women*";
P_HTM[5069]="*Gabbhiniṃ vuṭṭhāpentī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When giving the full admission to a pregnant woman, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5070]="*Vuṭṭhāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of giving the full admission, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5071]="*vuṭṭhāpite, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has given the full admission, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5072]="*Pāyantiṃ vuṭṭhāpentī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When giving the full admission to a woman who is breastfeeding, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5073]="*Vuṭṭhāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of giving the full admission, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5074]="*vuṭṭhāpite, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has given the full admission, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5075]="*Dve vassāni chasu dhammesu asikkhitasikkhaṃ sikkhamānaṃ vuṭṭhāpentī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When giving the full admission to a trainee nun who has not trained in the six rules for two years, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5076]="*Vuṭṭhāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of giving the full admission, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5077]="*vuṭṭhāpite, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has given the full admission, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5078]="*Dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhaṃ sikkhamānaṃ saṅghena asammataṃ vuṭṭhāpentī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When giving the full admission to a trainee nun who has trained in the six rules for two years, but who has not been approved by the Sangha, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5079]="*Vuṭṭhāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of giving the full admission, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5080]="*vuṭṭhāpite, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has given the full admission, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5081]="*Ūnadvādasavassaṃ gihigataṃ vuṭṭhāpentī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When giving the full admission to a married girl who is less than twelve years old, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5082]="*Vuṭṭhāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of giving the full admission, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5083]="*vuṭṭhāpite, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has given the full admission, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5084]="*Paripuṇṇadvādasavassaṃ gihigataṃ dve vassāni chasu dhammesu asikkhitasikkhaṃ vuṭṭhāpentī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When giving the full admission to a married girl who is more than twelve years old, but who has not trained in the six rules for two years, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5085]="*Vuṭṭhāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of giving the full admission, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5086]="*vuṭṭhāpite, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has given the full admission, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5087]="*Paripuṇṇadvādasavassaṃ gihigataṃ dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhaṃ saṅghena asammataṃ vuṭṭhāpentī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When giving the full admission to a married girl who is more than twelve years old and who has trained for two years in the six rules, but who has not been approved by the Sangha, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5088]="*Vuṭṭhāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of giving the full admission, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5089]="*vuṭṭhāpite, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has given the full admission, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5090]="*Sahajīviniṃ vuṭṭhāpetvā dve vassāni neva anuggaṇhantī nānuggaṇhāpentī ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati.**When giving the full admission to one’s disciple, and then, for the next two years, neither guiding her nor having her guided, she commits one kind of offense:*";
P_HTM[5091]="*Pācittiyaṃ.**an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5092]="*Vuṭṭhāpitaṃ pavattiniṃ dve vassāni nānubandhantī ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati.**When not following the mentor who gave one the full admission for two years, she commits one kind of offense:*";
P_HTM[5093]="*Pācittiyaṃ.**an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5094]="*Sahajīviniṃ vuṭṭhāpetvā neva vūpakāsentī na vūpakāsāpentī ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati.**When giving the full admission to one’s disciple, and then neither taking her away nor having her taken away, she commits one kind of offense:*";
P_HTM[5095]="*Pācittiyaṃ.**an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5096]="*Gabbhinivaggo sattamo.**The seventh sub-chapter on pregnant women is finished.*";
P_HTM[5097]="*4.8. Kumāribhūtavagga**4.8 The sub-chapter on unmarried girls*";
P_HTM[5098]="*Ūnavīsativassaṃ kumāribhūtaṃ vuṭṭhāpentī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When giving the full admission to an unmarried girl who is less than twenty years old, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5099]="*Vuṭṭhāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of giving the full admission, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5100]="*vuṭṭhāpite, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has given the full admission, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5101]="*Paripuṇṇavīsativassaṃ kumāribhūtaṃ dve vassāni chasu dhammesu asikkhitasikkhaṃ vuṭṭhāpentī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When giving the full admission to an unmarried girl who is more than twenty years old, but who has not trained in the six rules for two years, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5102]="*Vuṭṭhāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of giving the full admission, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5103]="*vuṭṭhāpite, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has given the full admission, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5104]="*Paripuṇṇavīsativassaṃ kumāribhūtaṃ dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhaṃ saṅghena asammataṃ vuṭṭhāpentī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When giving the full admission to an unmarried girl who is more than twenty years old and who has trained for two years in the six rules, but who has not been approved by the Sangha, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5105]="*Vuṭṭhāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of giving the full admission, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5106]="*vuṭṭhāpite, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has given the full admission, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5107]="*Ūnadvādasavassā vuṭṭhāpentī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When one who has less than twelve years of seniority gives the full admission, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5108]="*Vuṭṭhāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of giving the full admission, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5109]="*vuṭṭhāpite, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has given the full admission, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5110]="*Paripuṇṇadvādasavassā saṅghena asammatā vuṭṭhāpentī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When one who has twelve years of seniority gives the full admission without approval from the Sangha, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5111]="*Vuṭṭhāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of giving the full admission, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5112]="*vuṭṭhāpite, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has given the full admission, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5113]="*“Alaṃ tāva te, ayye, vuṭṭhāpitenā”ti vuccamānā “sādhū”ti paṭissuṇitvā pacchā khīyanadhammaṃ āpajjantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When verbally consenting when being told, “Venerable, you have given enough full admissions for now,” but then criticizing it afterwards, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5114]="*Khiyyati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is criticizing, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5115]="*khiyyite, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has criticized, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5116]="*Sikkhamānaṃ—“sace me tvaṃ, ayye, cīvaraṃ dassasi, evāhaṃ taṃ vuṭṭhāpessāmī”ti vatvā neva vuṭṭhāpentī na vuṭṭhāpanāya ussukkaṃ karontī ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati.**When telling a trainee nun, “Venerable, if you give me a robe, I’ll give you the full admission,” but then neither giving her the full admission nor making any effort to have her fully admitted, she commits one kind of offense:*";
P_HTM[5117]="*Pācittiyaṃ.**an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5118]="*Sikkhamānaṃ—“sace maṃ tvaṃ, ayye, dve vassāni anubandhissasi, evāhaṃ taṃ vuṭṭhāpessāmī”ti vatvā neva vuṭṭhāpentī na vuṭṭhāpanāya ussukkaṃ karontī ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati.**When telling a trainee nun, “Venerable, if you follow me for two years, I’ll give you the full admission,” but then neither giving her the full admission nor making any effort to have her fully admitted, she commits one kind of offense:*";
P_HTM[5119]="*Pācittiyaṃ.**an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5120]="*Purisasaṃsaṭṭhaṃ kumārakasaṃsaṭṭhaṃ caṇḍiṃ sokāvāsaṃ sikkhamānaṃ vuṭṭhāpentī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When giving the full admission to a trainee nun who is socializing with men and boys and who is temperamental and difficult to live with, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5121]="*Vuṭṭhāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of giving the full admission, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5122]="*vuṭṭhāpite, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has given the full admission, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5123]="*Mātāpitūhi vā sāmikena vā ananuññātaṃ sikkhamānaṃ vuṭṭhāpentī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When giving the full admission to a trainee nun who has not been given permission by her parents or her husband, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5124]="*Vuṭṭhāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of giving the full admission, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5125]="*vuṭṭhāpite, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has given the full admission, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5126]="*Pārivāsikachandadānena sikkhamānaṃ vuṭṭhāpentī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When giving the full admission to a trainee nun when any given consent has expired, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5127]="*Vuṭṭhāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of giving the full admission, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5128]="*vuṭṭhāpite, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has given the full admission, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5129]="*Anuvassaṃ vuṭṭhāpentī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When giving full admission every year, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5130]="*Vuṭṭhāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of giving the full admission, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5131]="*vuṭṭhāpite, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has given the full admission, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5132]="*Ekaṃ vassaṃ dve vuṭṭhāpentī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When giving the full admission to two women in one year, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5133]="*Vuṭṭhāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of giving the full admission, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5134]="*vuṭṭhāpite, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has given the full admission, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5135]="*Kumāribhūtavaggo aṭṭhamo.**The eighth sub-chapter on unmarried girls is finished.*";
P_HTM[5136]="*4.9. Chattupāhanavagga**4.9 The sub-chapter on sunshades and sandals*";
P_HTM[5137]="*Chattupāhanaṃ dhārentī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When using a sunshade and sandals, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5138]="*Dhāreti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is using them, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5139]="*dhārite, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has used them, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5140]="*Yānena yāyantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**“The offense entailing confession for traveling in a vehicle—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[5141]="*Yāyati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is traveling, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5142]="*yāyite, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has traveled, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5143]="*Saṅghāṇiṃ dhārentī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When wearing a hip ornament, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5144]="*Dhāreti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is wearing it, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5145]="*dhārite, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has worn it, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5146]="*Itthālaṅkāraṃ dhārentī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When wearing jewellery, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5147]="*Dhāreti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is wearing it, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5148]="*dhārite, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has worn it, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5149]="*Gandhavaṇṇakena nahāyantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When bathing with scents and colors, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5150]="*Nahāyati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is bathing, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5151]="*nahānapariyosāne, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she is finished bathing, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5152]="*Vāsitakena piññākena nahāyantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When bathing with scents and oil-seed flour, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5153]="*Nahāyati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is bathing, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5154]="*nahānapariyosāne, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she is finished bathing, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5155]="*Bhikkhuniyā ummaddāpentī parimaddāpentī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When having a nun massage or rub oneself, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5156]="*Ummaddāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is getting rubbed, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5157]="*ummaddite, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has gotten rubbed, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5158]="*Sikkhamānāya ummaddāpentī parimaddāpentī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When having a trainee nun massage or rub oneself, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5159]="*Ummaddāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is getting rubbed, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5160]="*ummaddite, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has gotten rubbed, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5161]="*Sāmaṇeriyā ummaddāpentī parimaddāpentī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When having a novice nun massage or rub oneself, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5162]="*Ummaddāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is getting rubbed, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5163]="*ummaddite, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has gotten rubbed, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5164]="*Gihiniyā ummaddāpentī parimaddāpentī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When having a female householder massage or rub oneself, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5165]="*Ummaddāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is getting rubbed, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5166]="*ummaddite, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has gotten rubbed, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5167]="*Bhikkhussa purato anāpucchā āsane nisīdantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When sitting down on a seat in front of a monk without asking permission, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5168]="*Nisīdati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of sitting down, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5169]="*nisinne, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she is seated, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5170]="*Anokāsakataṃ bhikkhuṃ pañhaṃ pucchantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When asking a question of a monk who has not given permission, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5171]="*Pucchati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ;**when she is in the process of asking, then for the effort there is an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5172]="*pucchite, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she has asked, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5173]="*Asaṅkaccikā gāmaṃ pavisantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When entering an inhabited area without wearing her chest wrap, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5174]="*Paṭhamaṃ pādaṃ parikkhepaṃ atikkāmeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when she crosses the boundary with her first foot, she commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5175]="*dutiyaṃ pādaṃ atikkāmeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when she crosses with her second foot, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5176]="*Chattupāhanavaggo navamo.**The ninth sub-chapter on sunshades and sandals is finished.*";
P_HTM[5177]="*Khuddakaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The section on minor rules is finished.*";
P_HTM[5178]="*5. Pāṭidesanīyakaṇḍa**5. The chapter on offenses entailing acknowledgment*";
P_HTM[5179]="*Sappiṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When asking for ghee and then eating it, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5180]="*Bhuñjissāmīti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when she receives it with the intention of eating it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5181]="*ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pāṭidesanīyassa.**for every mouthful, she commits an offense entailing acknowledgment.*";
P_HTM[5182]="*Telaṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When asking for oil and then eating it, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5183]="*Bhuñjissāmīti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when she receives it with the intention of eating it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5184]="*ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pāṭidesanīyassa.**for every mouthful, she commits an offense entailing acknowledgment.*";
P_HTM[5185]="*Madhuṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When asking for honey and then eating it, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5186]="*Bhuñjissāmīti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when she receives it with the intention of eating it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5187]="*ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pāṭidesanīyassa.**for every mouthful, she commits an offense entailing acknowledgment.*";
P_HTM[5188]="*Phāṇitaṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When asking for syrup and then eating it, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5189]="*Bhuñjissāmīti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when she receives it with the intention of eating it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5190]="*ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pāṭidesanīyassa.**for every mouthful, she commits an offense entailing acknowledgment.*";
P_HTM[5191]="*Macchaṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When asking for fish and then eating it, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5192]="*Bhuñjissāmīti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when she receives it with the intention of eating it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5193]="*ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pāṭidesanīyassa.**for every mouthful, she commits an offense entailing acknowledgment.*";
P_HTM[5194]="*Maṃsaṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When asking for meat and then eating it, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5195]="*Bhuñjissāmīti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when she receives it with the intention of eating it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5196]="*ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pāṭidesanīyassa.**for every mouthful, she commits an offense entailing acknowledgment.*";
P_HTM[5197]="*Khīraṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When asking for milk and then eating it, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5198]="*Bhuñjissāmīti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when she receives it with the intention of eating it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5199]="*ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pāṭidesanīyassa.**for every mouthful, she commits an offense entailing acknowledgment.*";
P_HTM[5200]="*Dadhiṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**When asking for curd and then eating it, she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5201]="*Bhuñjissāmīti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when she receives it with the intention of eating it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5202]="*ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pāṭidesanīyassa.**for every mouthful, she commits an offense entailing acknowledgment.*";
P_HTM[5203]="*Aṭṭha pāṭidesanīyā niṭṭhitā.**The eight offenses entailing acknowledgment are finished.*";
P_HTM[5204]="*Katāpattivāro niṭṭhito dutiyo.**The second section on “how many offenses” is finished.*";
P_HTM[5205]="*124. Paṭhamabhāga **124.  Part one *";
P_HTM[5206]="*3. Vipattivāra**3. The section on failure*";
P_HTM[5207]="*Avassutāya bhikkhuniyā avassutassa purisapuggalassa kāyasaṃsaggaṃ sādiyantiyā āpattiyo catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ kati vipattiyo bhajanti?**When it comes to the offenses for a lustful nun consenting to a lustful man making physical contact with her, to how many of the four kinds of failure do they belong?*";
P_HTM[5208]="*Avassutāya bhikkhuniyā avassutassa purisapuggalassa kāyasaṃsaggaṃ sādiyantiyā āpattiyo catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ dve vipattiyo bhajanti—**They belong to two kinds of failure:*";
P_HTM[5209]="*siyā sīlavipattiṃ, siyā ācāravipattiṃ …pe….**they may be failure in morality; they may be failure in conduct. …*";
P_HTM[5210]="*Dadhiṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjantiyā āpattiyo catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ kati vipattiyo bhajanti?**When it comes to the offenses for asking for curd and then eating it, to how many of the four kinds of failure do they belong?*";
P_HTM[5211]="*Dadhiṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjantiyā āpattiyo catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ ekaṃ vipattiṃ bhajanti—**They belong to one kind of failure:*";
P_HTM[5212]="*ācāravipattiṃ.**failure in conduct.*";
P_HTM[5213]="*Vipattivāro niṭṭhito tatiyo.**The third section on failure is finished.*";
P_HTM[5214]="*124. Paṭhamabhāga **124.  Part one *";
P_HTM[5215]="*4. Saṅgahavāra**4. The section on “being found in”*";
P_HTM[5216]="*Avassutāya bhikkhuniyā avassutassa purisapuggalassa kāyasaṃsaggaṃ sādiyantiyā āpattiyo sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ katihi āpattikkhandhehi saṅgahitā?**When it comes to the offenses for a lustful nun consenting to a lustful man making physical contact with her, in how many of the seven classes of offenses are they found?*";
P_HTM[5217]="*Avassutāya bhikkhuniyā avassutassa purisapuggalassa kāyasaṃsaggaṃ sādiyantiyā āpattiyo sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ tīhi āpattikkhandhehi saṅgahitā—**They are found in three:*";
P_HTM[5218]="*siyā pārājikāpattikkhandhena, siyā thullaccayāpattikkhandhena, siyā dukkaṭāpattikkhandhena …pe….**they may be in the class of offenses entailing expulsion; they may be in the class of serious offenses; they may be in the class of offenses of wrong conduct. …*";
P_HTM[5219]="*Dadhiṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjantiyā āpattiyo sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ katihi āpattikkhandhehi saṅgahitā?**When it comes to the offenses for asking for curd and then eating it, in how many of the seven classes of offenses are they found?*";
P_HTM[5220]="*Dadhiṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjantiyā āpattiyo sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ dvīhi āpattikkhandhehi saṅgahitā—**They are found in two:*";
P_HTM[5221]="*siyā pāṭidesanīyāpattikkhandhena, siyā dukkaṭāpattikkhandhena.**they may be in the class of offenses entailing acknowledgment; they may be in the class of offenses of wrong conduct. …*";
P_HTM[5222]="*Saṅgahavāro niṭṭhito catuttho.**The fourth section on “being found in” is finished.*";
P_HTM[5223]="*124. Paṭhamabhāga **124.  Part one *";
P_HTM[5224]="*5. Samuṭṭhānavāra**5. The section on origins*";
P_HTM[5225]="*Avassutāya bhikkhuniyā avassutassa purisapuggalassa kāyasaṃsaggaṃ sādiyantiyā āpattiyo channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ katihi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhanti?**When it comes to the offenses for a lustful nun consenting to a lustful man making physical contact with her, through how many of the six kinds of origins of offenses do they originate?*";
P_HTM[5226]="*Avassutāya bhikkhuniyā avassutassa purisapuggalassa kāyasaṃsaggaṃ sādiyantiyā āpattiyo channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhanti—**They originate in one way:*";
P_HTM[5227]="*kāyato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhanti, na vācato …pe….**from body and mind, not from speech. …*";
P_HTM[5228]="*Dadhiṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjantiyā āpattiyo channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ katihi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhanti?**When it comes to the offenses for asking for curd and then eating it, through how many of the six kinds of origins of offenses do they originate?*";
P_HTM[5229]="*Dadhiṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjantiyā āpattiyo channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ catūhi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhanti—**They originate in four ways:*";
P_HTM[5230]="*siyā kāyato samuṭṭhanti, na vācato na cittato;**from body, not from speech or mind; or*";
P_HTM[5231]="*siyā kāyato ca vācato ca samuṭṭhanti, na cittato;**from body and speech, not from mind; or*";
P_HTM[5232]="*siyā kāyato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhanti, na vācato;**from body and mind, not from speech; or*";
P_HTM[5233]="*siyā kāyato ca vācato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhanti.**from body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[5234]="*Samuṭṭhānavāro niṭṭhito pañcamo.**The fifth section on origins is finished.*";
P_HTM[5235]="*124. Paṭhamabhāga **124.  Part one *";
P_HTM[5236]="*6. Adhikaraṇavāra**6. The section on legal issues*";
P_HTM[5237]="*Avassutāya bhikkhuniyā avassutassa purisapuggalassa kāyasaṃsaggaṃ sādiyantiyā āpattiyo catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ?**When it comes to the offenses for a lustful nun consenting to a lustful man making physical contact with her, to which of the four kinds of legal issues do they belong?*";
P_HTM[5238]="*Avassutāya bhikkhuniyā avassutassa purisapuggalassa kāyasaṃsaggaṃ sādiyantiyā āpattiyo catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ—āpattādhikaraṇaṃ …pe….**They are legal issues arising from an offense. …*";
P_HTM[5239]="*Dadhiṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjantiyā āpattiyo catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ?**When it comes to the offenses for asking for curd and then eating it, to which of the four kinds of legal issues do they belong?*";
P_HTM[5240]="*Dadhiṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjantiyā āpattiyo catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ—āpattādhikaraṇaṃ.**They are legal issues arising from an offense. …*";
P_HTM[5241]="*Adhikaraṇavāro niṭṭhito chaṭṭho.**The sixth section on legal issues is finished.*";
P_HTM[5242]="*124. Paṭhamabhāga **124.  Part one *";
P_HTM[5243]="*7. Samathavāra**7. The section on settling*";
P_HTM[5244]="*Avassutāya bhikkhuniyā avassutassa purisapuggalassa kāyasaṃsaggaṃ sādiyantiyā āpattiyo sattannaṃ samathānaṃ katihi samathehi sammanti?**When it comes to the offenses for a lustful nun consenting to a lustful man making physical contact with her, through how many of the seven principles for settling legal issues are they settled?*";
P_HTM[5245]="*Avassutāya bhikkhuniyā avassutassa purisapuggalassa kāyasaṃsaggaṃ sādiyantiyā āpattiyo sattannaṃ samathānaṃ tīhi samathehi sammanti—**Through three of them:*";
P_HTM[5246]="*siyā sammukhāvinayena ca paṭiññātakaraṇena ca, siyā sammukhāvinayena ca tiṇavatthārakena ca …pe….**they may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by acting according to what has been admitted; or they may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by covering over as if with grass. …*";
P_HTM[5247]="*Dadhiṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjantiyā āpattiyo sattannaṃ samathānaṃ katihi samathehi sammanti?**When it comes to the offenses for asking for curd and then eating it, through how many of the seven principles for settling legal issues are they settled?*";
P_HTM[5248]="*Dadhiṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjantiyā āpattiyo sattannaṃ samathānaṃ tīhi samathehi sammanti—**Through three of them:*";
P_HTM[5249]="*siyā sammukhāvinayena ca paṭiññātakaraṇena ca, siyā sammukhāvinayena ca tiṇavatthārakena ca.**they may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by acting according to what has been admitted; or they may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[5250]="*Samathavāro niṭṭhito sattamo.**The seventh section on settling is finished.*";
P_HTM[5251]="*124. Paṭhamabhāga **124.  Part one *";
P_HTM[5252]="*8. Samuccayavāra**8. The section that collects together*";
P_HTM[5253]="*Avassutā bhikkhunī avassutassa purisapuggalassa kāyasaṃsaggaṃ sādiyantī kati āpattiyo āpajjati?**When a lustful nun consents to a lustful man making physical contact with her, how many kinds of offenses does she commit?*";
P_HTM[5254]="*Avassutā bhikkhunī avassutassa purisapuggalassa kāyasaṃsaggaṃ sādiyantī tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.**She commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5255]="*Adhakkhakaṃ ubbhajāṇumaṇḍalaṃ gahaṇaṃ sādiyati, āpatti pārājikassa;**when she consents to him taking hold of her anywhere below the collar bone but above the knees, she commits an offense entailing expulsion;*";
P_HTM[5256]="*ubbhakkhakaṃ adhojāṇumaṇḍalaṃ gahaṇaṃ sādiyati, āpatti thullaccayassa;**when she consents to him taking hold of her above the collar bone or below the knees, she commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[5257]="*kāyapaṭibaddhaṃ gahaṇaṃ sādiyati, āpatti dukkaṭassa—**when she consents to him taking hold of something connected to her body, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5258]="*avassutā bhikkhunī avassutassa purisapuggalassa kāyasaṃsaggaṃ sādiyantī imā tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[5259]="*Tā āpattiyo catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ kati vipattiyo bhajanti?**When it comes to these offenses, to how many of the four kinds of failure do they belong?*";
P_HTM[5260]="*Sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ katihi āpattikkhandhehi saṅgahitā?**In how many of the seven classes of offenses are they found?*";
P_HTM[5261]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ katihi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhanti?**Through how many of the six kinds of origins of offenses do they originate?*";
P_HTM[5262]="*Catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ?**To which of the four kinds of legal issues do they belong?*";
P_HTM[5263]="*Sattannaṃ samathānaṃ katihi samathehi sammanti?**Through how many of the seven principles for settling legal issues are they settled?*";
P_HTM[5264]="*Tā āpattiyo catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ dve vipattiyo bhajanti—**They belong to two kinds of failure:*";
P_HTM[5265]="*siyā sīlavipattiṃ, siyā ācāravipattiṃ.**they may be failure in morality; they may be failure in conduct.*";
P_HTM[5266]="*Sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ tīhi āpattikkhandhehi saṅgahitā—**They are found in three classes of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5267]="*siyā pārājikāpattikkhandhena, siyā thullaccayāpattikkhandhena, siyā dukkaṭāpattikkhandhena.**they may be in the class of offenses entailing expulsion; they may be in the class of serious offenses; they may be in the class of offenses of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5268]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhanti—**They originate in one way:*";
P_HTM[5269]="*kāyato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhanti, na vācato.**from body and mind, not from speech.*";
P_HTM[5270]="*Catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ āpattādhikaraṇaṃ.**They are legal issues arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[5271]="*Sattannaṃ samathānaṃ tīhi samathehi sammanti—**They are settled in three ways:*";
P_HTM[5272]="*siyā sammukhāvinayena ca paṭiññātakaraṇena ca, siyā sammukhāvinayena ca tiṇavatthārakena ca …pe….**they may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by acting according to what has been admitted; or they may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by covering over as if with grass. …*";
P_HTM[5273]="*Dadhiṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjantī kati āpattiyo āpajjati?**When asking for curd and then eating it, how many kinds of offenses does she commit?*";
P_HTM[5274]="*Dadhiṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjantī dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**She commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5275]="*Bhuñjissāmīti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when she receives it with the intention of eating it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5276]="*ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pāṭidesanīyassa—**For every mouthful, she commits an offense entailing acknowledgment.*";
P_HTM[5277]="*dadhiṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjantī imā dve āpattiyo āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[5278]="*Tā āpattiyo catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ kati vipattiyo bhajanti?**When it comes to these offenses, to how many of the four kinds of failure do they belong?*";
P_HTM[5279]="*Sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ katihi āpattikkhandhehi saṅgahitā?**In how many of the seven classes of offenses are they found?*";
P_HTM[5280]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ katihi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhanti?**Through how many of the six kinds of origins of offenses do they originate?*";
P_HTM[5281]="*Catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ?**To which of the four kinds of legal issues do they belong?*";
P_HTM[5282]="*Sattannaṃ samathānaṃ katihi samathehi sammanti?**Through how many of the seven principles for settling legal issues are they settled?*";
P_HTM[5283]="*Tā āpattiyo catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ ekaṃ vipattiṃ bhajanti—**They belong to one kind of failure:*";
P_HTM[5284]="*ācāravipattiṃ.**failure in conduct.*";
P_HTM[5285]="*Sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ dvīhi āpattikkhandhehi saṅgahitā—**They are found in two classes of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5286]="*siyā pāṭidesanīyāpattikkhandhena, siyā dukkaṭāpattikkhandhena.**they may be in the class of offenses entailing acknowledgment; they may be in the class of offenses of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5287]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ catūhi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhanti—**They originate in four ways:*";
P_HTM[5288]="*siyā kāyato samuṭṭhanti na vācato na cittato,**from body, not from speech or mind; or*";
P_HTM[5289]="*siyā kāyato ca vācato ca samuṭṭhanti na cittato,**from body and speech, not from mind; or*";
P_HTM[5290]="*siyā kāyato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhanti na vācato,**from body and mind, not from speech; or*";
P_HTM[5291]="*siyā kāyato ca vācato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhanti.**from body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[5292]="*Catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ—āpattādhikaraṇaṃ.**They are legal issues arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[5293]="*Sattannaṃ samathānaṃ tīhi samathehi sammanti—**They are settled in three ways:*";
P_HTM[5294]="*siyā sammukhāvinayena ca paṭiññātakaraṇena ca, siyā sammukhāvinayena ca tiṇavatthārakena ca.**they may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by acting according to what has been admitted; or they may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[5295]="*Samuccayavāro niṭṭhito aṭṭhamo.**The eighth section that collects together is finished.*";
P_HTM[5296]="*124. Dutiyabhāga **124.  Part two *";
P_HTM[5297]="*Katthapaññattivāra**The section on “where it was laid down”*";
P_HTM[5298]="*1. Pārājikakaṇḍa**1. The chapter on offenses entailing expulsion*";
P_HTM[5299]="*Yaṃ tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena kāyasaṃsaggaṃ sādiyanapaccayā pārājikaṃ kattha paññattaṃ?**“The offense entailing expulsion that is a result of consenting to physical contact was laid down by the Buddha who knows and sees, the Perfected One, the fully Awakened One. Where was it laid down?*";
P_HTM[5300]="*Kaṃ ārabbha?**Whom is it about?*";
P_HTM[5301]="*Kismiṃ vatthusmiṃ …pe…**What is it about? …*";
P_HTM[5302]="*kenābhatanti?**Who handed it down?”*";
P_HTM[5303]="*Yaṃ tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena kāyasaṃsaggaṃ sādiyanapaccayā pārājikaṃ kattha paññattanti?**“The offense entailing expulsion that is a result of consenting to physical contact was laid down by the Buddha who knows and sees, the Perfected One, the fully Awakened One. Where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[5304]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññattaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5305]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[5306]="*Sundarīnandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ ārabbha.**The nun Sundarīnandā.*";
P_HTM[5307]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[5308]="*Sundarīnandā bhikkhunī avassutā avassutassa purisapuggalassa kāyasaṃsaggaṃ sādiyi, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**The lustful nun Sundarīnandā consenting to a lustful man making physical contact with her.*";
P_HTM[5309]="*Atthi tattha paññatti, anupaññatti, anuppannapaññattīti?**“Is there a rule, an addition to the rule, an unprompted rule?”*";
P_HTM[5310]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[5311]="*Anupaññatti anuppannapaññatti tasmiṃ natthi.**There is no addition to the rule. There is no unprompted rule.*";
P_HTM[5312]="*Sabbatthapaññatti, padesapaññattīti?**“Is it a rule that applies everywhere, or that applies in a particular place?”*";
P_HTM[5313]="*Sabbatthapaññatti.**That applies everywhere.*";
P_HTM[5314]="*Sādhāraṇapaññatti, asādhāraṇapaññattīti?**“Is it a rule that the monks and nuns have in common, or a rule they do not have in common?”*";
P_HTM[5315]="*Asādhāraṇapaññatti.**A rule they do not have in common.*";
P_HTM[5316]="*Ekatopaññatti, ubhatopaññattīti?**“Is it a rule for one Sangha or for both Sanghas?”*";
P_HTM[5317]="*Ekatopaññatti.**For one Sangha.*";
P_HTM[5318]="*Catunnaṃ pātimokkhuddesānaṃ katthogadhaṃ kattha pariyāpannanti?**“In which of the four ways of reciting the Monastic Code is it immersed and included?”*";
P_HTM[5319]="*Nidānogadhaṃ nidānapariyāpannaṃ?**In the introduction.*";
P_HTM[5320]="*Katamena uddesena uddesaṃ āgacchatīti?**“In which recitation is it included?”*";
P_HTM[5321]="*Dutiyena uddesena uddesaṃ āgacchati.**In the second recitation.*";
P_HTM[5322]="*Catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ katamā vipattīti?**“To which of the four kinds of failure does it belong?”*";
P_HTM[5323]="*Sīlavipatti.**Failure in morality.*";
P_HTM[5324]="*Sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ katamo āpattikkhandhoti?**“To which of the seven classes of offenses does it belong?”*";
P_HTM[5325]="*Pārājikāpattikkhandho.**The class of offenses entailing expulsion.*";
P_HTM[5326]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ katihi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhātīti?**“Through how many of the six kinds of origins of offenses does it originate?”*";
P_HTM[5327]="*Ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhāti—**It originates in one way:*";
P_HTM[5328]="*kāyato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhāti, na vācato …pe…**from body and mind, not from speech. …*";
P_HTM[5329]="*kenābhatanti?**“Who handed it down?”*";
P_HTM[5330]="*Paramparābhataṃ—**The lineage:*";
P_HTM[5331]="*Upāli dāsako ceva,**“Upāli and Dāsaka,*";
P_HTM[5332]="*soṇako siggavo tathā;**Soṇaka and also Siggava;*";
P_HTM[5333]="*Moggaliputtena pañcamā,**With Moggaliputta as the fifth—*";
P_HTM[5334]="*ete jambusirivhaye.**these were in India, the land named after the glorious rose apple.*";
P_HTM[5335]="*…pe…**…*";
P_HTM[5336]="*Ete nāgā mahāpaññā,**These mighty beings of great wisdom,*";
P_HTM[5337]="*Vinayaññū maggakovidā;**Knowers of the Monastic Law and skilled in the path,*";
P_HTM[5338]="*Vinayaṃ dīpe pakāsesuṃ,**Proclaimed the Collection of Monastic Law*";
P_HTM[5339]="*Piṭakaṃ tambapaṇṇiyāti.**On the island of Sri Lanka.”*";
P_HTM[5340]="*Vajjappaṭicchādanapaccayā pārājikaṃ kattha paññattanti?**“The offense entailing expulsion that is a result of concealing offenses—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[5341]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññattaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5342]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[5343]="*Thullanandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ ārabbha.**The nun Thullanandā.*";
P_HTM[5344]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[5345]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī jānaṃ pārājikaṃ dhammaṃ ajjhāpannaṃ bhikkhuniṃ nevattanā paṭicodesi na gaṇassa ārocesi, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**The nun Thullanandā, knowing that a nun had committed an offense entailing expulsion, neither confronting her herself nor telling the community.*";
P_HTM[5346]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[5347]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhāti—**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in one way:*";
P_HTM[5348]="*dhuranikkhepe …pe….**through giving up one’s duty. …*";
P_HTM[5349]="*Yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjanapaccayā pārājikaṃ kattha paññattanti?**“The offense entailing expulsion that is a result of not stopping when pressed up to the third time—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[5350]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññattaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5351]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[5352]="*Thullanandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ ārabbha.**The nun Thullanandā.*";
P_HTM[5353]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[5354]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī samaggena saṅghena ukkhittaṃ ariṭṭhaṃ bhikkhuṃ gaddhabādhipubbaṃ anuvatti, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**The nun Thullanandā taking sides with the monk Ariṭṭha, an ex-vulture-killer, who had been ejected by a unanimous Sangha.*";
P_HTM[5355]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[5356]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhāti—**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in one way:*";
P_HTM[5357]="*dhuranikkhepe …pe….**through giving up one’s duty. …*";
P_HTM[5358]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ vatthuṃ paripūraṇapaccayā pārājikaṃ kattha paññattanti?**“The offense entailing expulsion that is a result of fulfilling the eight parts—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[5359]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññattaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5360]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[5361]="*Chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo ārabbha.**The nuns from the group of six.*";
P_HTM[5362]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[5363]="*Chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo aṭṭhamaṃ vatthuṃ paripūresuṃ, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**The nuns from the group of six fulfilling the eight parts.*";
P_HTM[5364]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[5365]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhāti—**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in one way:*";
P_HTM[5366]="*dhuranikkhepe …pe….**through giving up one’s duty. …*";
P_HTM[5367]="*Pārājikā niṭṭhitā.**The offenses entailing expulsion are finished.*";
P_HTM[5368]="*2. Saṅghādisesakaṇḍādi**2. The chapter on offenses entailing suspension, etc.*";
P_HTM[5369]="*Yaṃ tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena ussayavādikāya bhikkhuniyā aḍḍaṃ karaṇapaccayā saṅghādiseso kattha paññatto?**“The offense entailing suspension that is a result of a litigious nun initiating a lawsuit was laid down by the Buddha who knows and sees, the Perfected One, the fully Awakened One. Where was it laid down?*";
P_HTM[5370]="*Kaṃ ārabbha?**Whom is it about?*";
P_HTM[5371]="*Kismiṃ vatthusmiṃ …pe…**What is it about? …*";
P_HTM[5372]="*kenābhatanti?**Who handed it down?”*";
P_HTM[5373]="*Yaṃ tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena ussayavādikāya bhikkhuniyā aḍḍaṃ karaṇapaccayā saṅghādiseso kattha paññattoti?**“The offense entailing suspension that is a result of a litigious nun initiating a lawsuit that was laid down by the Buddha who knows and sees, the Perfected One, the fully Awakened One—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[5374]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññatto.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5375]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[5376]="*Thullanandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ ārabbha.**The nun Thullanandā.*";
P_HTM[5377]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[5378]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī ussayavādikā vihari, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**The nun Thullanandā being litigious.*";
P_HTM[5379]="*Atthi tattha paññatti, anupaññatti, anuppannapaññattīti?**“Is there a rule, an addition to the rule, an unprompted rule?”*";
P_HTM[5380]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[5381]="*Anupaññatti anuppannapaññatti tasmiṃ natthi.**There is no addition to the rule. There is no unprompted rule.*";
P_HTM[5382]="*Sabbatthapaññatti, padesapaññattīti?**“Is it a rule that applies everywhere, or that applies in a particular place?”*";
P_HTM[5383]="*Sabbatthapaññatti.**That applies everywhere.*";
P_HTM[5384]="*Sādhāraṇapaññatti, asādhāraṇapaññattīti?**“Is it a rule that the monks and nuns have in common, or a rule they do not have in common?”*";
P_HTM[5385]="*Asādhāraṇapaññatti.**A rule they do not have in common.*";
P_HTM[5386]="*Ekatopaññatti, ubhatopaññattīti?**“Is it a rule for one Sangha or for both Sanghas?”*";
P_HTM[5387]="*Ekatopaññatti.**For one Sangha.*";
P_HTM[5388]="*Catunnaṃ pātimokkhuddesānaṃ katthogadhaṃ kattha pariyāpannanti?**“In which of the four ways of reciting the Monastic Code is it immersed and included?”*";
P_HTM[5389]="*Nidānogadhaṃ nidānapariyāpannaṃ.**In the introduction.*";
P_HTM[5390]="*Katamena uddesena uddesaṃ āgacchatīti?**“In which recitation is it included?”*";
P_HTM[5391]="*Tatiyena uddesena uddesaṃ āgacchati.**In the third recitation.*";
P_HTM[5392]="*Catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ katamā vipattīti?**“To which of the four kinds of failure does it belong?”*";
P_HTM[5393]="*Sīlavipatti.**Failure in morality.*";
P_HTM[5394]="*Sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ katamo āpattikkhandhoti?**“To which of the seven classes of offenses does it belong?”*";
P_HTM[5395]="*Saṅghādisesāpattikkhandho.**The class of offenses entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[5396]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ katihi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhātīti?**“Through how many of the six kinds of origins of offenses does it originate?”*";
P_HTM[5397]="*Dvīhi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhāti—**It originates in two ways:*";
P_HTM[5398]="*siyā kāyato ca vācato ca samuṭṭhāti, na cittato;**from body and speech, not from mind; or*";
P_HTM[5399]="*siyā kāyato ca vācato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhāti …pe…**from body, speech, and mind. …*";
P_HTM[5400]="*kenābhatanti?**“Who handed it down?”*";
P_HTM[5401]="*Paramparābhataṃ—**The lineage:*";
P_HTM[5402]="*Upāli dāsako ceva,**“Upāli and Dāsaka,*";
P_HTM[5403]="*soṇako siggavo tathā;**Soṇaka and also Siggava;*";
P_HTM[5404]="*Moggaliputtena pañcamā,**With Moggaliputta as the fifth—*";
P_HTM[5405]="*ete jambusirivhaye.**these were in India, the land named after the glorious rose apple.*";
P_HTM[5406]="*…pe…**…*";
P_HTM[5407]="*Ete nāgā mahāpaññā,**These mighty beings of great wisdom,*";
P_HTM[5408]="*Vinayaññū maggakovidā;**Knowers of the Monastic Law and skilled in the path,*";
P_HTM[5409]="*Vinayaṃ dīpe pakāsesuṃ,**Proclaimed the Collection of Monastic Law*";
P_HTM[5410]="*Piṭakaṃ tambapaṇṇiyāti.**On the island of Sri Lanka.”*";
P_HTM[5411]="*Coriṃ vuṭṭhāpanapaccayā saṅghādiseso kattha paññattoti?**“The offense entailing suspension that is a result of giving the full admission to a female criminal—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[5412]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññatto.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5413]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[5414]="*Thullanandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ ārabbha.**The nun Thullanandā.*";
P_HTM[5415]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[5416]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī coriṃ vuṭṭhāpesi, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**The nun Thullanandā giving the full admission to a female criminal.*";
P_HTM[5417]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[5418]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ dvīhi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhāti—**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in two ways:*";
P_HTM[5419]="*siyā vācato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhāti, na kāyato;**from speech and mind, not from body; or*";
P_HTM[5420]="*siyā kāyato ca vācato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhāti …pe….**from body, speech, and mind. …*";
P_HTM[5421]="*Ekā gāmantaraṃ gamanapaccayā saṅghādiseso kattha paññattoti?**“The offense entailing suspension that is a result of walking to the next village by oneself—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[5422]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññatto.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5423]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[5424]="*Aññataraṃ bhikkhuniṃ ārabbha.**A certain nun.*";
P_HTM[5425]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[5426]="*Aññatarā bhikkhunī ekā gāmantaraṃ gacchi, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**A certain nun walking to the next village by herself.*";
P_HTM[5427]="*Ekā paññatti, tisso anupaññattiyo.**There is one rule. There are three additions to the rule.*";
P_HTM[5428]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhāti—**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in one way:*";
P_HTM[5429]="*paṭhamapārājike …pe….**(as in the first offense entailing expulsion) …*";
P_HTM[5430]="*Samaggena saṅghena ukkhittaṃ bhikkhuniṃ dhammena vinayena satthusāsanena anapaloketvā kārakasaṅghaṃ anaññāya gaṇassa chandaṃ osāraṇapaccayā saṅghādiseso kattha paññattoti?**“The offense entailing suspension that is a result of reinstating a nun who has been ejected by a unanimous Sangha in accordance with the rule, the Monastic Law, and the Teacher’s instruction, without getting permission from the Sangha that did the legal procedure and without the consent of the group—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[5431]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññatto.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5432]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[5433]="*Thullanandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ ārabbha.**The nun Thullanandā.*";
P_HTM[5434]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[5435]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī samaggena saṅghena ukkhittaṃ bhikkhuniṃ dhammena vinayena satthusāsanena anapaloketvā kārakasaṅghaṃ anaññāya gaṇassa chandaṃ osāresi, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**The nun Thullanandā reinstating a nun who has been ejected by a unanimous Sangha in accordance with the rule, the Monastic Law, and the Teacher’s instruction, without getting permission from the Sangha that did the legal procedure and without the consent of the group.*";
P_HTM[5436]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[5437]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhāti—**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in one way:*";
P_HTM[5438]="*dhuranikkhepe …pe….**through giving up one’s duty. …*";
P_HTM[5439]="*Avassutāya bhikkhuniyā avassutassa purisapuggalassa hatthato khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā sahatthā paṭiggahetvā bhuñjanapaccayā saṅghādiseso kattha paññattoti?**“The offense entailing suspension that is a result of a lustful nun eating fresh or cooked food after personally receiving it from the hands of a lustful man—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[5440]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññatto.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5441]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[5442]="*Sundarīnandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ ārabbha.**The nun Sundarīnandā.*";
P_HTM[5443]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[5444]="*Sundarīnandā bhikkhunī avassutā avassutassa purisapuggalassa hatthato āmisaṃ paṭiggahesi, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**The nun Sundarīnandā, being lustful, receiving food directly from a lustful man.*";
P_HTM[5445]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[5446]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhāti—**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in one way:*";
P_HTM[5447]="*paṭhamapārājike …pe….**(as in the first offense entailing expulsion) …*";
P_HTM[5448]="*“Kiṃ te, ayye, eso purisapuggalo karissati avassuto vā anavassuto vā, yato tvaṃ anavassutā. Iṅgha, ayye, yaṃ te eso purisapuggalo deti khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā taṃ tvaṃ sahatthā paṭiggahetvā khāda vā bhuñja vā”ti uyyojanapaccayā saṅghādiseso kattha paññattoti?**“The offense entailing suspension that is a result of urging a nun on, saying, “Venerable, what can this man do to you, whether he has lust or not, if you’re without? Go on, Venerable, receive it yourself and then eat whatever fresh or cooked food he gives to you”—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[5449]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññatto.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5450]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[5451]="*Aññataraṃ bhikkhuniṃ ārabbha.**A certain nun.*";
P_HTM[5452]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[5453]="*Aññatarā bhikkhunī—“kiṃ te, ayye, eso purisapuggalo karissati avassuto vā anavassuto vā, yato tvaṃ anavassutā. Iṅgha, ayye, yaṃ te eso purisapuggalo deti khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā taṃ tvaṃ sahatthā paṭiggahetvā khāda vā bhuñja vā”ti uyyojesi, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**A certain nun urging a nun on, saying, “Venerable, what can this man do to you, whether he has lust or not, if you’re without? Go on, Venerable, receive it yourself and then eat whatever fresh or cooked food he gives to you.”*";
P_HTM[5454]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[5455]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ tīhi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhāti …pe….**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in three ways: …*";
P_HTM[5456]="*Kupitāya anattamanāya bhikkhuniyā yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjanapaccayā saṅghādiseso kattha paññattoti?**“The offense entailing suspension that is a result of an angry nun not stopping when pressed up to the third time—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[5457]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññatto.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5458]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[5459]="*Caṇḍakāḷiṃ bhikkhuniṃ ārabbha.**The nun Caṇḍakālī.*";
P_HTM[5460]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[5461]="*Caṇḍakāḷī bhikkhunī kupitā anattamanā evaṃ avaca—“buddhaṃ paccācikkhāmi, dhammaṃ paccācikkhāmi, saṅghaṃ paccācikkhāmi, sikkhaṃ paccācikkhāmī”ti, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**The nun Caṇḍakālī saying in anger that, “I renounce the Buddha, I renounce the Teaching, I renounce the Sangha, I renounce the training.”*";
P_HTM[5462]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[5463]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhāti—**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in one way:*";
P_HTM[5464]="*dhuranikkhepe …pe….**through giving up one’s duty. …*";
P_HTM[5465]="*Kismiñcideva adhikaraṇe paccākatāya bhikkhuniyā yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjanapaccayā saṅghādiseso kattha paññattoti?**“The offense entailing suspension that is a result of a nun who has had a legal issue decided against her not stopping when pressed up to the third time—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[5466]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññatto.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5467]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[5468]="*Caṇḍakāḷiṃ bhikkhuniṃ ārabbha.**The nun Caṇḍakālī.*";
P_HTM[5469]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[5470]="*Caṇḍakāḷī bhikkhunī kismiñcideva adhikaraṇe paccākatā kupitā anattamanā evaṃ avaca—“chandagāminiyo ca bhikkhuniyo, dosagāminiyo ca bhikkhuniyo, mohagāminiyo ca bhikkhuniyo, bhayagāminiyo ca bhikkhuniyo”ti, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**The nun Caṇḍakālī, who had had a legal issue decided against her, saying that, “The nuns are acting out of desire, ill will, confusion, and fear.”*";
P_HTM[5471]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[5472]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhāti—**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in one way:*";
P_HTM[5473]="*dhuranikkhepe …pe….**through giving up one’s duty. …*";
P_HTM[5474]="*Saṃsaṭṭhānaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjanapaccayā saṅghādiseso kattha paññattoti?**“The offense entailing suspension that is a result of nuns who are socializing not stopping when pressed up to the third time—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[5475]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññatto.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5476]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[5477]="*Sambahulā bhikkhuniyo ārabbha.**A number of nuns.*";
P_HTM[5478]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[5479]="*Sambahulā bhikkhuniyo saṃsaṭṭhā vihariṃsu, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**A number of nuns socializing.*";
P_HTM[5480]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[5481]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhāti—**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in one way:*";
P_HTM[5482]="*dhuranikkhepe …pe….**through giving up one’s duty. …*";
P_HTM[5483]="*“Saṃsaṭṭhāva, ayye, tumhe viharatha. Mā tumhe nānā viharitthā”ti uyyojentiyā yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjanapaccayā saṅghādiseso kattha paññattoti?**“The offense entailing suspension that is a result of urging nuns in this way: “But, Venerables, you should socialize; don’t live separately;” and then not stopping when pressed up to the third time—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[5484]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññatto.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5485]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[5486]="*Thullanandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ ārabbha.**The nun Thullanandā.*";
P_HTM[5487]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[5488]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī—“saṃsaṭṭhāva, ayye, tumhe viharatha. Mā tumhe nānā viharitthā”ti uyyojesi, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**The nun Thullanandā urging nuns in this way: “But, Venerables, you should socialize. Don’t live separately.”*";
P_HTM[5489]="*Ekā paññatti.**There is one rule.*";
P_HTM[5490]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhāti—**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in one way:*";
P_HTM[5491]="*dhuranikkhepe …pe….**through giving up one’s duty. …*";
P_HTM[5492]="*Dadhiṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjanapaccayā pāṭidesanīyaṃ kattha paññattanti?**“The offense entailing acknowledgment that is a result of asking for curd and then eating it—where was it laid down?”*";
P_HTM[5493]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ paññattaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5494]="*Kaṃ ārabbhāti?**“Whom is it about?”*";
P_HTM[5495]="*Chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo ārabbha.**The nuns from the group of six.*";
P_HTM[5496]="*Kismiṃ vatthusminti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[5497]="*Chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo dadhiṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjiṃsu, tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ.**The nuns from the group of six asking for curd and then eating it.*";
P_HTM[5498]="*Ekā paññatti, ekā anupaññatti.**There is one rule. There is one addition to the rule.*";
P_HTM[5499]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ catūhi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhāti …pe….**Of the six kinds of origins of offenses, it originates in four ways: …*";
P_HTM[5500]="*Katthapaññattivāro niṭṭhito paṭhamo.**The first section on “where it was laid down” is finished.*";
P_HTM[5501]="*124. Dutiyabhāga **124.  Part two *";
P_HTM[5502]="*Katāpattivāra**The section on “how many offenses”*";
P_HTM[5503]="*1. Pārājikakaṇḍa**1. The chapter on offenses entailing expulsion*";
P_HTM[5504]="*Kāyasaṃsaggaṃ sādiyanapaccayā kati āpattiyo āpajjati?**How many kinds of offenses does one commit as a result of consenting to physical contact?*";
P_HTM[5505]="*Kāyasaṃsaggaṃ sādiyanapaccayā pañca āpattiyo āpajjati.**One commits five kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5506]="*Avassutā bhikkhunī avassutassa purisapuggalassa adhakkhakaṃ ubbhajāṇumaṇḍalaṃ gahaṇaṃ sādiyati, āpatti pārājikassa;**when a lustful nun consents to a lustful man taking hold of her anywhere below the collar bone but above the knees, she commits an offense entailing expulsion;*";
P_HTM[5507]="*bhikkhu kāyena kāyaṃ āmasati, āpatti saṅghādisesassa;**when a monk touches body with body, he commits an offense entailing suspension;*";
P_HTM[5508]="*kāyena kāyapaṭibaddhaṃ āmasati, āpatti thullaccayassa;**when one touches what is connected to the body with the body, one commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[5509]="*kāyapaṭibaddhena kāyapaṭibaddhaṃ āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when one touches what is connected to the body with what is connected to the body, one commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5510]="*aṅgulipatodake pācittiyaṃ—**for tickling, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5511]="*kāyasaṃsaggaṃ sādiyanapaccayā imā pañca āpattiyo āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[5512]="*Vajjappaṭicchādanapaccayā kati āpattiyo āpajjati?**How many kinds of offenses does one commit as a result of concealing an offenses?*";
P_HTM[5513]="*Vajjappaṭicchādanapaccayā catasso āpattiyo āpajjati.**One commits four kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5514]="*Bhikkhunī jānaṃ pārājikaṃ dhammaṃ paṭicchādeti, āpatti pārājikassa;**when a nun knowingly conceals an offense entailing expulsion, she commits an offense involving expulsion;*";
P_HTM[5515]="*vematikā paṭicchādeti, āpatti thullaccayassa;**when, being unsure, she conceals it, she commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[5516]="*bhikkhu saṅghādisesaṃ paṭicchādeti, āpatti pācittiyassa;**when a monk conceals an offense entailing suspension, he commits an offense entailing confession;*";
P_HTM[5517]="*ācāravipattiṃ paṭicchādeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa—**when one conceals a failure in conduct, one commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5518]="*vajjappaṭicchādanapaccayā imā catasso āpattiyo āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[5519]="*Yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjanapaccayā kati āpattiyo āpajjati?**“How many kinds of offenses does one commit as a result of not stopping when pressed up to the third time?”*";
P_HTM[5520]="*Yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjanapaccayā pañca āpattiyo āpajjati.**she commits five kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5521]="*Ukkhittānuvattikā bhikkhunī yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjati, ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ;**when a nun takes sides with one who has been ejected and she does not stop when pressed up to the third time, then after the motion, she commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5522]="*dvīhi kammavācāhi thullaccayā;**after each of the first two announcements, she commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[5523]="*kammavācāpariyosāne āpatti pārājikassa;**when the last announcement is finished, she commits an offense entailing expulsion;*";
P_HTM[5524]="*bhedakānuvattikā bhikkhunī yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjati, āpatti saṅghādisesassa;**when a nun sides with a monk who is pursuing schism and she does not stop when pressed up to the third time, she commits an offense entailing suspension;*";
P_HTM[5525]="*pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjati, āpatti pācittiyassa—**when not giving up a bad view after being pressed up to the third time, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5526]="*yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjanapaccayā imā pañca āpattiyo āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[5527]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ vatthuṃ paripūraṇapaccayā kati āpattiyo āpajjati?**How many kinds of offenses does she commit as a result of fulfilling the eight parts?*";
P_HTM[5528]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ vatthuṃ paripūraṇapaccayā tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.**She commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5529]="*Purisena—“itthannāmaṃ okāsaṃ āgacchā”ti vuttā gacchati, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when she goes to such-and-such a place when told by a man to do so, she commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5530]="*purisassa hatthapāsaṃ okkantamatte āpatti thullaccayassa;**when she enters within arm’s reach of the man, she commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[5531]="*aṭṭhamaṃ vatthuṃ paripūreti, āpatti pārājikassa—**when she fulfills the eight parts, she commits an offense entailing expulsion.*";
P_HTM[5532]="*aṭṭhamaṃ vatthuṃ paripūraṇapaccayā imā tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[5533]="*Pārājikā niṭṭhitā.**The offenses entailing expulsion are finished.*";
P_HTM[5534]="*2. Saṅghādisesakaṇḍādi**2. The chapter on offenses entailing suspension, etc.*";
P_HTM[5535]="*Ussayavādikā bhikkhunī aḍḍaṃ karaṇapaccayā tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.**As a result of initiating a lawsuit, a litigious nun commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5536]="*Ekassa āroceti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when she tells one other person, she commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5537]="*dutiyassa āroceti, āpatti thullaccayassa;**when she tells a second person, she commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[5538]="*aḍḍapariyosāne āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**when the lawsuit is finished, she commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[5539]="*Coriṃ vuṭṭhāpanapaccayā tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.**As a result of giving the full admission to a female criminal, she commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5540]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ;**after the motion, she commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5541]="*dvīhi kammavācāhi thullaccayā;**after each of the first two announcements, she commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[5542]="*kammavācāpariyosāne āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**when the last announcement is finished, she commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[5543]="*Ekā gāmantaraṃ gamanapaccayā tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.**As a result of walking alone to the next village, she commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5544]="*Gacchati, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when she is in the process of going, she commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5545]="*paṭhamaṃ pādaṃ parikkhepaṃ atikkāmeti, āpatti thullaccayassa;**when she crosses the boundary with her first foot, she commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[5546]="*dutiyaṃ pādaṃ atikkāmeti, āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**when she crosses with her second foot, she commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[5547]="*Samaggena saṅghena ukkhittaṃ bhikkhuniṃ dhammena vinayena satthusāsanena anapaloketvā kārakasaṅghaṃ anaññāya gaṇassa chandaṃ osāraṇapaccayā tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.**As a result of reinstating—without getting permission from the Sangha that did the legal procedure and without the consent of the group—a nun who has been ejected by a unanimous Sangha in accordance with the rule and the Monastic Law and the Teacher’s instruction, she commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5548]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ;**after the motion, she commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5549]="*dvīhi kammavācāhi thullaccayā;**after each of the first two announcements, she commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[5550]="*kammavācāpariyosāne āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**when the last announcement is finished, she commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[5551]="*Avassutā bhikkhunī avassutassa purisapuggalassa hatthato khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā sahatthā paṭiggahetvā bhuñjanapaccayā tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.**As a result of eating fresh or cooked food after receiving it directly from a lustful man, a lustful nun commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5552]="*“Khādissāmi bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti thullaccayassa;**when she receives fresh or cooked food with the intention of eating it, she commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[5553]="*ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti saṅghādisesassa;**for every mouthful, she commits an offense entailing suspension;*";
P_HTM[5554]="*udakadantaponaṃ paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**when she receives water or a tooth cleaner, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5555]="*“Kiṃ te, ayye, eso purisapuggalo karissati avassuto vā anavassuto vā, yato tvaṃ anavassutā. Iṅgha, ayye, yaṃ te eso purisapuggalo deti khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā taṃ tvaṃ sahatthā paṭiggahetvā khāda vā bhuñja vā”ti, uyyojanapaccayā tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.**As a result of urging a nun on, saying, “Venerable, what can this man do to you, whether he has lust or not, if you’re without? Go on, Venerable, receive it yourself and then eat whatever fresh or cooked food he gives to you,” she commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5556]="*Tassā vacanena khādissāmi bhuñjissāmīti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when, because of her statement, the other nun receives it with the intention of eating it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5557]="*ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti thullaccayassa;**for every mouthful, she commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[5558]="*bhojanapariyosāne āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**when the meal is finished, she commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[5559]="*Kupitā bhikkhunī yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjanapaccayā tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.**As a result of not stopping when pressed up to the third time, an angry nun commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5560]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ;**after the motion, she commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5561]="*dvīhi kammavācāhi thullaccayā;**after each of the first two announcements, she commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[5562]="*kammavācāpariyosāne āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**when the last announcement is finished, she commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[5563]="*Kismiñcideva adhikaraṇe paccākatā bhikkhunī yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjanapaccayā tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.**As a result of not stopping when pressed up to the third time, a nun who has had a legal issue decided against her commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5564]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ;**after the motion, she commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5565]="*dvīhi kammavācāhi thullaccayā;**after each of the first two announcements, she commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[5566]="*kammavācāpariyosāne āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**when the last announcement is finished, she commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[5567]="*Saṃsaṭṭhā bhikkhunī yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjanapaccayā tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.**As a result of not stopping when pressed up to the third time, a socializing nun commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5568]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ;**after the motion, she commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5569]="*dvīhi kammavācāhi thullaccayā;**after each of the first two announcements, she commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[5570]="*kammavācāpariyosāne āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**when the last announcement is finished, she commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[5571]="*“Saṃsaṭṭhāva, ayye, tumhe viharatha, mā tumhe nānā viharitthā”ti uyyojentī yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjanapaccayā tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.**As a result of urging a nun on, saying, “Venerables, you should socialize; don’t live separately;” and not stopping when pressed up to the third time, she commits three kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5572]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ;**after the motion, she commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5573]="*dvīhi kammavācāhi thullaccayā;**after each of the first two announcements, she commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[5574]="*kammavācāpariyosāne āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**when the last announcement is finished, she commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[5575]="*Dasa saṅghādisesā niṭṭhitā …pe… .**The ten rules entailing suspension are finished. …*";
P_HTM[5576]="*(Yathā heṭṭhā tathā vitthāretabbā paccayameva nānākaraṇaṃ)**(To be expanded as above, (pli-tv-pvr2.2.17.0) to (pli-tv-pvr2.2.141.3), with the only difference being “as a result of”.)*";
P_HTM[5577]="*Dadhiṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjanapaccayā kati āpattiyo āpajjati?**How many kinds of offenses does she commit as a result of asking for curd and then eating it?*";
P_HTM[5578]="*Dadhiṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjanapaccayā dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**she commits two kinds of offenses:*";
P_HTM[5579]="*Bhuñjissāmīti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when she receives it with the intention of eating it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5580]="*ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pāṭidesanīyassa—**for every mouthful, she commits an offense entailing acknowledgment.*";
P_HTM[5581]="*dadhiṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjanapaccayā imā dve āpattiyo āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[5582]="*Katāpattivāro niṭṭhito dutiyo.**The second section on “how many offenses” is finished.*";
P_HTM[5583]="*124. Dutiyabhāga **124.  Part two *";
P_HTM[5584]="*3. Vipattivāra**3. The section on failure*";
P_HTM[5585]="*Kāyasaṃsaggaṃ sādiyanapaccayā āpattiyo catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ kati vipattiyo bhajanti?**When it comes to the offenses that are a result of consenting to physical contact, to how many of the four kinds of failure do they belong?*";
P_HTM[5586]="*Kāyasaṃsaggaṃ sādiyanapaccayā āpattiyo catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ dve vipattiyo bhajanti—**They belong to two kinds of failure:*";
P_HTM[5587]="*siyā sīlavipattiṃ, siyā ācāravipattiṃ …pe….**they may be failure in morality; they may be failure in conduct. …*";
