P_HTM[5631]="*Kāyasaṃsaggaṃ sādiyanapaccayā kati āpattiyo āpajjati?**When it comes to the offenses that are a result of consenting to physical contact, how many kinds of offenses does one commit?*";
P_HTM[5632]="*Kāyasaṃsaggaṃ sādiyanapaccayā pañca āpattiyo āpajjati.**One commits five kinds of offenses :*";
P_HTM[5633]="*Avassutā bhikkhunī avassutassa purisapuggalassa adhakkhakaṃ ubbhajāṇumaṇḍalaṃ gahaṇaṃ sādiyati, āpatti pārājikassa;**when a lustful nun consents to a lustful man taking hold of her anywhere below the collar bone but above the knees, she commits an offense entailing expulsion;*";
P_HTM[5634]="*bhikkhu kāyena kāyaṃ āmasati, āpatti saṅghādisesassa;**when a monk touches body with body, he commits an offense entailing suspension;*";
P_HTM[5635]="*kāyena kāyapaṭibaddhaṃ āmasati, āpatti thullaccayassa;**when one touches what is connected to the body with the body, one commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[5636]="*kāyapaṭibaddhena kāyapaṭibaddhaṃ āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa;**when one touches what is connected to the body with what is connected to the body, one commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[5637]="*aṅgulipatodake pācittiyaṃ—**for tickling, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5638]="*kāyasaṃsaggaṃ sādiyanapaccayā imā pañca āpattiyo āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[5639]="*Tā āpattiyo catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ kati vipattiyo bhajanti?**When it comes to these offenses, to how many of the four kinds of failure do they belong?*";
P_HTM[5640]="*Sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ katihi āpattikkhandhehi saṅgahitā?**In how many of the seven classes of offenses are they found?*";
P_HTM[5641]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ katihi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhanti?**Through how many of the six kinds of origins of offenses do they originate?*";
P_HTM[5642]="*Catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ?**To which of the four kinds of legal issues do they belong?*";
P_HTM[5643]="*Sattannaṃ samathānaṃ katihi samathehi sammanti?**Through how many of the seven principles for settling legal issues are they settled?*";
P_HTM[5644]="*Tā āpattiyo catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ dve vipattiyo bhajanti—**They belong to two kinds of failure:*";
P_HTM[5645]="*siyā sīlavipattiṃ, siyā ācāravipattiṃ.**they may be failure in morality; they may be failure in conduct.*";
P_HTM[5646]="*Sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ pañcahi āpattikkhandhehi saṅgahitā—**They are found in five classes of offenses:*";
