P_HTM[6004]="*Tattha katamā pañca āpattiyo?**What are the five kinds of offenses?*";
P_HTM[6005]="*Pārājikāpatti, saṅghādisesāpatti, pācittiyāpatti, pāṭidesanīyāpatti, dukkaṭāpatti—**Offenses entailing expulsion; offenses entailing suspension; offenses entailing confession; offenses entailing acknowledgment; offenses of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6006]="*imā pañca āpattiyo.* **";
P_HTM[6007]="*Tattha katame pañca āpattikkhandhā?**What are the five classes of offenses?*";
P_HTM[6008]="*Pārājikāpattikkhandho, saṅghādisesāpattikkhandho, pācittiyāpattikkhandho, pāṭidesanīyāpattikkhandho, dukkaṭāpattikkhandho—**The class of offenses entailing expulsion; the class of offenses entailing suspension; the class of offenses entailing confession; the class of offenses entailing acknowledgment; the class of offenses of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6009]="*ime pañca āpattikkhandhā.* **";
P_HTM[6010]="*Tattha katamāni pañca vinītavatthūni?**What are the five grounds of training?*";
P_HTM[6011]="*Pañcahi āpattikkhandhehi ārati virati paṭivirati veramaṇī akiriyā akaraṇaṃ anajjhāpatti velāanatikkamo setughāto—**The refraining from, the keeping away from, the desisting from, the abstaining from, the non-doing of, the non-performing of, the non-committing of, the non-transgressing the boundary of, the incapability in respect of the five classes of offenses.*";
P_HTM[6012]="*imāni pañca vinītavatthūni.* **";
P_HTM[6013]="*Tattha katamā satta āpattiyo?**What are the seven kinds of offenses?*";
P_HTM[6014]="*Pārājikāpatti, saṅghādisesāpatti, thullaccayāpatti, pācittiyāpatti, pāṭidesanīyāpatti, dukkaṭāpatti, dubbhāsitāpatti—**The class of offenses entailing expulsion; the class of offenses entailing suspension; the class of serious offenses; the class of offenses entailing confession; the class of offenses entailing acknowledgment; the class of offenses of wrong conduct; the class of offenses of wrong speech.*";
P_HTM[6015]="*imā satta āpattiyo.* **";
P_HTM[6016]="*Tattha katame satta āpattikkhandhā?**What are the seven classes of offenses?*";
P_HTM[6017]="*Pārājikāpattikkhandho, saṅghādisesāpattikkhandho, thullaccayāpattikkhandho, pācittiyāpattikkhandho, pāṭidesanīyāpattikkhandho, dukkaṭāpattikkhandho, dubbhāsitāpattikkhandho—**The class of offenses entailing expulsion; the class of offenses entailing suspension; the class of serious offenses; the class of offenses entailing confession; the class of offenses entailing acknowledgment; the class of offenses of wrong conduct; the class of offenses of wrong speech.*";
P_HTM[6018]="*ime satta āpattikkhandhā.* **";
P_HTM[6019]="*Tattha katamāni satta vinītavatthūni?**What are the seven grounds of training?*";
P_HTM[6020]="*Sattahi āpattikkhandhehi ārati virati paṭivirati veramaṇī akiriyā akaraṇaṃ anajjhāpatti velāanatikkamo setughāto—**The refraining from, the keeping away from, the desisting from, the abstaining from, the non-doing of, the non-performing of, the non-committing of, the non-transgressing the boundary of, the incapability in respect of the seven classes of offenses.*";
P_HTM[6021]="*imāni satta vinītavatthūni.* **";
P_HTM[6022]="*Tattha katame cha agāravā?**What are the six kinds of disrespect?*";
P_HTM[6023]="*Buddhe agāravo, dhamme agāravo, saṅghe agāravo, sikkhāya agāravo, appamāde agāravo, paṭisandhāre agāravo—**Disrespect for the Buddha, disrespect for the Teaching, disrespect for the Sangha, disrespect for the training, disrespect for heedfulness, disrespect for hospitality.*";
P_HTM[6024]="*ime cha agāravā.* **";
P_HTM[6025]="*Tattha katame cha gāravā?**What are the six kinds of respect?*";
P_HTM[6026]="*Buddhe gāravo, dhamme gāravo, saṅghe gāravo, sikkhāya gāravo, appamāde gāravo, paṭisandhāre gāravo—**Respect for the Buddha, respect for the Teaching, respect for the Sangha, respect for the training, respect for heedfulness, respect for hospitality.*";
P_HTM[6027]="*ime cha gāravā.* **";
P_HTM[6028]="*Tattha katamāni cha vinītavatthūni?**What are the six grounds of training?*";
P_HTM[6029]="*Chahi agāravehi ārati virati paṭivirati veramaṇī akiriyā akaraṇaṃ anajjhāpatti velāanatikkamo setughāto—**The refraining from, the keeping away from, the desisting from, the abstaining from, the non-doing of, the non-performing of, the non-committing of, the non-transgressing the boundary of, the incapability in respect of the six kinds of disrespect.*";
P_HTM[6030]="*imāni cha vinītavatthūni.* **";
P_HTM[6031]="*Tattha katamā catasso vipattiyo?**What are four kinds of failure?*";
P_HTM[6032]="*Sīlavipatti, ācāravipatti, diṭṭhivipatti, ājīvavipatti—**Failure in morality, failure in conduct, failure in view, failure in livelihood.*";
P_HTM[6033]="*imā catasso vipattiyo.* **";
P_HTM[6034]="*Tattha katame cha āpattisamuṭṭhānā?**What are the six origins of offenses?*";
P_HTM[6035]="*Atthāpatti kāyato samuṭṭhāti, na vācato na cittato;**There are offenses that originate from body, but not from speech or mind;*";
P_HTM[6036]="*atthāpatti vācato samuṭṭhāti, na kāyato na cittato;**there are offenses that originate from speech, but not from body or mind;*";
P_HTM[6037]="*atthāpatti kāyato ca vācato ca samuṭṭhāti, na cittato;**there are offenses that originate from body and speech, but not from mind;*";
P_HTM[6038]="*atthāpatti kāyato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhāti, na vācato;**there are offenses that originate from body and mind, but not from speech;*";
P_HTM[6039]="*atthāpatti vācato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhāti, na kāyato;**there are offenses that originate from speech and mind, but not from body;*";
P_HTM[6040]="*atthāpatti kāyato ca vācato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhāti—**there are offenses that originate from body, speech, and mind;*";
P_HTM[6041]="*ime cha āpattisamuṭṭhānā.* **";
P_HTM[6042]="*Tattha katamāni cha vivādamūlāni?**What are the six sources of disputes?*";
P_HTM[6043]="*Idha bhikkhu kodhano hoti upanāhī.**It may be that a monk is angry and resentful.*";
P_HTM[6044]="*Yo so bhikkhu kodhano hoti upanāhī so sattharipi agāravo viharati appatisso, dhammepi agāravo viharati appatisso, saṅghepi agāravo viharati appatisso, sikkhāyapi na paripūrakārī hoti.**One who is angry and resentful is disrespectful and undeferential toward the Teacher, the Teaching, and the Sangha, and he doesn’t fulfill the training.*";
P_HTM[6045]="*Yo so bhikkhu satthari agāravo viharati appatisso, dhamme …pe…**Such a person*";
P_HTM[6046]="*saṅghe …pe…* **";
P_HTM[6047]="*sikkhāya na paripūrakārī, so saṅghe vivādaṃ janeti.**creates disputes in the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[6048]="*Yo hoti vivādo bahujanāhitāya bahujanāsukhāya bahuno janassa anatthāya ahitāya dukkhāya devamanussānaṃ.**Disputes are unbeneficial and a cause of unhappiness for humanity; they are harmful, detrimental, and a cause of suffering for gods and humans.*";
P_HTM[6049]="*Evarūpañce tumhe vivādamūlaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā samanupasseyyātha tatra tumhe tasseva pāpakassa vivādamūlassa pahānāya vāyameyyātha.**When you see such a source of disputes either in yourself or in others, you should make an effort to get rid of it.*";
P_HTM[6050]="*Evarūpañce tumhe vivādamūlaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā na samanupasseyyātha tatra tumhe tasseva pāpakassa vivādamūlassa āyatiṃ anavassavāya paṭipajjeyyātha.**If you don’t see such a source either in yourself or in others, you should practice so that it doesn’t reappear in the future.*";
P_HTM[6051]="*Evametassa pāpakassa vivādamūlassa pahānaṃ hoti.**In this way that bad source of disputes is abandoned.*";
P_HTM[6052]="*Evametassa pāpakassa vivādamūlassa āyatiṃ anavassavo hoti.**In this way that bad source of disputes has no future effect.*";
P_HTM[6053]="*Puna caparaṃ bhikkhu makkhī hoti paḷāsī …pe…**Or it may be that a monk is denigrating and controlling,*";
P_HTM[6054]="*issukī hoti maccharī, saṭho hoti māyāvī, pāpiccho hoti micchādiṭṭhi, sandiṭṭhiparāmāsī hoti ādhānaggāhī duppaṭinissaggī.**envious and stingy, treacherous and deceitful, one who has bad desires and wrong views, or one who obstinately grasps his own views and only gives them up with difficulty.*";
P_HTM[6055]="*Yo so bhikkhu sandiṭṭhiparāmāsī hoti ādhānaggāhī duppaṭinissaggī so sattharipi agāravo viharati appatisso, dhammepi agāravo viharati appatisso, saṅghepi agāravo viharati appatisso, sikkhāyapi na paripūrakārī hoti.**Any of these is disrespectful and undeferential toward the Teacher, the Teaching, and the Sangha, and he doesn’t fulfill the training.*";
P_HTM[6056]="*Yo so bhikkhu satthari agāravo viharati appatisso dhamme …pe…**Such a person*";
P_HTM[6057]="*saṅghe …pe…* **";
P_HTM[6058]="*sikkhāya na paripūrakārī, so saṅghe vivādaṃ janeti.**creates disputes in the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[6059]="*Yo so hoti vivādo bahujanāhitāya bahujanāsukhāya bahuno janassa anatthāya ahitāya dukkhāya devamanussānaṃ.**Disputes are unbeneficial and a cause of unhappiness for humanity; they are harmful, detrimental, and a cause of suffering for gods and humans.*";
