P_HTM[6329]="*Catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ, āpattādhikaraṇaṃ.**They are legal issues arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[6330]="*Sattannaṃ samathānaṃ tīhi samathehi sammanti—**They are settled in three ways:*";
P_HTM[6331]="*siyā sammukhāvinayena ca paṭiññātakaraṇena ca, siyā sammukhāvinayena ca tiṇavatthārakena cāti.**they may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by acting according to what has been admitted; or they may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[6332]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ katāpattivāro niṭṭhito dutiyo.**The second section on “how many offenses” for the six origins of offenses is finished.*";
P_HTM[6333]="*4.3. Āpattisamuṭṭhānagāthā**4.3 The verses on origins of offenses*";
