P_HTM[6383]="*4.4. Vipattipaccayavāra**4.4 The section on “as a result of failure”*";
P_HTM[6384]="*Sīlavipattipaccayā kati āpattiyo āpajjati?**How many offenses does one commit as a result of failure in morality?*";
P_HTM[6385]="*Sīlavipattipaccayā catasso āpattiyo āpajjati—**Four:*";
P_HTM[6386]="*bhikkhunī jānaṃ pārājikaṃ dhammaṃ paṭicchādeti, āpatti pārājikassa;**when a nun knowingly conceals an offense entailing expulsion, she commits an offense involving expulsion;*";
P_HTM[6387]="*vematikā paṭicchādeti, āpatti thullaccayassa;**when, being unsure, she conceals it, she commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[6388]="*bhikkhu saṅghādisesaṃ paṭicchādeti, āpatti pācittiyassa;**when a monk conceals an offense entailing suspension, he commits an offense entailing confession;*";
P_HTM[6389]="*attano duṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ paṭicchādeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa—**when he conceals a grave offense of his own, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6390]="*sīlavipattipaccayā imā catasso āpattiyo āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[6391]="*Tā āpattiyo catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ kati vipattiyo bhajanti …pe…**When it comes to these offenses, to how many of the four kinds of failure do they belong? …*";
P_HTM[6392]="*sattannaṃ samathānaṃ katihi samathehi sammanti?**Through how many of the seven principles for settling legal issues are they settled?*";
P_HTM[6393]="*Tā āpattiyo catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ dve vipattiyo bhajanti—**They belong to two kinds of failure:*";
P_HTM[6394]="*siyā sīlavipattiṃ, siyā ācāravipattiṃ.**they may be failure in morality; they may be failure in conduct.*";
P_HTM[6395]="*Sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ catūhi āpattikkhandhehi saṅgahitā—**They are found in four classes of offenses:*";
P_HTM[6396]="*siyā pārājikāpattikkhandhena, siyā thullaccayāpattikkhandhena, siyā pācittiyāpattikkhandhena, siyā dukkaṭāpattikkhandhena.**they may be in the class of offenses entailing expulsion; they may be in the class of serious offenses; they may be in the class of offenses entailing confession; they may be in the class of offenses of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6397]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhanti—**They originate in one way:*";
P_HTM[6398]="*kāyato ca vācato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhanti.**from body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[6399]="*Catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ, āpattādhikaraṇaṃ.**They are legal issues arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[6400]="*Sattannaṃ samathānaṃ tīhi samathehi sammanti—**They are settled in three ways:*";
P_HTM[6401]="*siyā sammukhāvinayena ca paṭiññātakaraṇena ca, siyā sammukhāvinayena ca tiṇavatthārakena ca.**they may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by acting according to what has been admitted; or they may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[6402]="*Ācāravipattipaccayā kati āpattiyo āpajjati?**How many offenses does one commit as a result of failure in conduct?*";
P_HTM[6403]="*Ācāravipattipaccayā ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati.**One:*";
P_HTM[6404]="*Ācāravipattiṃ paṭicchādeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa—**when one conceals a failure in conduct, one commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6405]="*ācāravipattipaccayā imaṃ ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[6406]="*Sā āpatti catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ kati vipattiyo bhajati …pe…**When it comes to this offense, to how many of the four kinds of failure does it belong? …*";
P_HTM[6407]="*sattannaṃ samathānaṃ katihi samathehi sammati?**Through how many of the seven principles for settling legal issues is it settled?*";
P_HTM[6408]="*Sā āpatti catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ ekaṃ vipattiṃ bhajati—**It belongs to one kind of failure:*";
P_HTM[6409]="*ācāravipattiṃ.**failure in conduct.*";
P_HTM[6410]="*Sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ ekena āpattikkhandhena saṅgahitā—**It is found in one class of offenses:*";
P_HTM[6411]="*dukkaṭāpattikkhandhena.**in the class of offenses of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6412]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhāti—**They originate in one way:*";
P_HTM[6413]="*kāyato ca vācato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhāti.**from body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[6414]="*Catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ āpattādhikaraṇaṃ.**It is a legal issue arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[6415]="*Sattannaṃ samathānaṃ tīhi samathehi sammati—**They are settled through three principles:*";
P_HTM[6416]="*siyā sammukhāvinayena ca paṭiññātakaraṇena ca, siyā sammukhāvinayena ca tiṇavatthārakena ca.**they may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by acting according to what has been admitted; or they may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[6417]="*Diṭṭhivipattipaccayā kati āpattiyo āpajjati?**How many offenses does one commit as a result of failure in view?*";
P_HTM[6418]="*Diṭṭhivipattipaccayā dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**Two:*";
P_HTM[6419]="*Pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjati, ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ;**when not giving up a bad view after being pressed up to the third time, one commits an offense entailing confession;*";
P_HTM[6420]="*kammavācāpariyosāne āpatti pācittiyassa—**when the last announcement is finished, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[6421]="*diṭṭhivipattipaccayā imā dve āpattiyo āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[6422]="*Tā āpattiyo catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ kati vipattiyo bhajanti …pe…**When it comes to these offenses, to how many of the four kinds of failure do they belong? …*";
P_HTM[6423]="*sattannaṃ samathānaṃ katihi samathehi sammanti?**Through how many of the seven principles for settling legal issues are they settled?*";
P_HTM[6424]="*Tā āpattiyo catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ ekaṃ vipattiṃ bhajanti—**They belong to one kind of failure:*";
P_HTM[6425]="*ācāravipattiṃ.**failure in conduct.*";
P_HTM[6426]="*Sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ dvīhi āpattikkhandhehi saṅgahitā—**They are found in two classes of offenses:*";
P_HTM[6427]="*siyā pācittiyāpattikkhandhena, siyā dukkaṭāpattikkhandhena.**they may be in the class of offenses entailing confession; they may be in the class of offenses of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6428]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhanti—**They originate in one way:*";
P_HTM[6429]="*kāyato ca vācato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhanti.**from body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[6430]="*Catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ, āpattādhikaraṇaṃ.**They are legal issues arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[6431]="*Sattannaṃ samathānaṃ tīhi samathehi sammanti—**They are settled in three ways:*";
P_HTM[6432]="*siyā sammukhāvinayena ca paṭiññātakaraṇena ca, siyā sammukhāvinayena ca tiṇavatthārakena ca.**they may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by acting according to what has been admitted; or they may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[6433]="*Ājīvavipattipaccayā kati āpattiyo āpajjati?**How many offenses does one commit as a result of failure in livelihood?*";
P_HTM[6434]="*Ājīvavipattipaccayā cha āpattiyo āpajjati—**Six:*";
P_HTM[6435]="*ājīvahetu ājīvakāraṇā pāpiccho icchāpakato asantaṃ abhūtaṃ uttarimanussadhammaṃ ullapati, āpatti pārājikassa;**when, to make a living—having bad desires, overcome by desire—one claims a non-existent, unreal superhuman quality, one commits an offense entailing expulsion;*";
P_HTM[6436]="*ājīvahetu ājīvakāraṇā sañcarittaṃ samāpajjati, āpatti saṅghādisesassa;**when, to make a living, one acts as a matchmaker, one commits an offense entailing suspension;*";
P_HTM[6437]="*ājīvahetu ājīvakāraṇā “yo te vihāre vasati, so bhikkhu arahā”ti bhaṇati, paṭivijānantassa āpatti thullaccayassa;**when, to make a living, one says, “Whatever monk lives in your dwelling is a perfected one,” and the listener understands, one commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[6438]="*ājīvahetu ājīvakāraṇā bhikkhu paṇītabhojanāni attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa;**when, to make a living, a monk eats fine foods that he himself has asked for, he commits an offense entailing confession;*";
P_HTM[6439]="*ājīvahetu ājīvakāraṇā bhikkhunī paṇītabhojanāni attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjati, āpatti pāṭidesanīyassa;**when, to make a living, a nun eats fine foods that she herself has asked for, she commits an offense entailing acknowledgment;*";
P_HTM[6440]="*ājīvahetu ājīvakāraṇā sūpaṃ vā odanaṃ vā agilāno attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa—**when, to make a living, one eats bean curry or rice that one has asked for oneself, one commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6441]="*ājīvavipattipaccayā imā cha āpattiyo āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[6442]="*Tā āpattiyo catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ kati vipattiyo bhajanti …pe…**When it comes to these offenses, to how many of the four kinds of failure do they belong? …*";
P_HTM[6443]="*sattannaṃ samathānaṃ katihi samathehi sammanti.**Through how many of the seven principles for settling legal issues are they settled?*";
P_HTM[6444]="*Tā āpattiyo catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ dve vipattiyo bhajanti—**They belong to two kinds of failure:*";
P_HTM[6445]="*siyā sīlavipattiṃ, siyā ācāravipattiṃ.**they may be failure in morality; they may be failure in conduct.*";
P_HTM[6446]="*Sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ chahi āpattikkhandhehi saṅgahitā—**They are found in six classes of offenses:*";
P_HTM[6447]="*siyā pārājikāpattikkhandhena, siyā saṅghādisesāpattikkhandhena, siyā thullaccayāpattikkhandhena, siyā pācittiyāpattikkhandhena, siyā pāṭidesanīyāpattikkhandhena, siyā dukkaṭāpattikkhandhena.**they may be in the class of offenses entailing expulsion; they may be in the class of offenses entailing suspension; they may be in the class of serious offenses; they may be in the class of offenses entailing confession; they may be in the class of offenses entailing acknowledgment; they may be in the class of offenses of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6448]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ chahi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhanti—**They originate in six ways:*";
P_HTM[6449]="*siyā kāyato samuṭṭhanti, na vācato na cittato;**from body, not from speech or mind; or*";
P_HTM[6450]="*siyā vācato samuṭṭhanti, na kāyato na cittato;**from speech, not from body or mind; or*";
P_HTM[6451]="*siyā kāyato ca vācato ca samuṭṭhanti, na cittato;**from body and speech, not from mind; or*";
P_HTM[6452]="*siyā kāyato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhanti, na vācato;**from body and mind, not from speech; or*";
P_HTM[6453]="*siyā vācato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhanti, na kāyato;**from speech and mind, not from body; or*";
P_HTM[6454]="*siyā kāyato ca vācato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhanti.**from body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[6455]="*Catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ, āpattādhikaraṇaṃ.**They are legal issues arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[6456]="*Sattannaṃ samathānaṃ tīhi samathehi sammanti—**They are settled in three ways:*";
P_HTM[6457]="*siyā sammukhāvinayena ca paṭiññātakaraṇena ca, siyā sammukhāvinayena ca tiṇavatthārakena ca.**they may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by acting according to what has been admitted; or they may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[6458]="*Vipattipaccayavāro niṭṭhito catuttho.**The fourth section on “as a result of failure” is finished.*";
P_HTM[6459]="*4.5. Adhikaraṇapaccayavāra**4.5 The section on “as a result of legal issues”*";
P_HTM[6460]="*Vivādādhikaraṇapaccayā kati āpattiyo āpajjati?**How many offenses does one commit as a result of legal issues arising from disputes?*";
P_HTM[6461]="*Vivādādhikaraṇapaccayā dve āpattiyo āpajjati—**Two:*";
P_HTM[6462]="*upasampannaṃ omasati, āpatti pācittiyassa;**when one speaks abusively to one who is fully ordained, one commits an offense entailing confession;*";
P_HTM[6463]="*anupasampannaṃ omasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa—**when one speaks abusively to one who is not fully ordained, one commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6464]="*vivādādhikaraṇapaccayā imā dve āpattiyo āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[6465]="*Tā āpattiyo catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ kati vipattiyo bhajanti …pe…**When it comes to these offenses, to how many of the four kinds of failure do they belong? …*";
P_HTM[6466]="*sattannaṃ samathānaṃ katihi samathehi sammanti?**Through how many of the seven principles for settling legal issues are they settled?*";
P_HTM[6467]="*Tā āpattiyo catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ ekaṃ vipattiṃ bhajanti—**They belong to one kind of failure:*";
P_HTM[6468]="*ācāravipattiṃ.**failure in conduct.*";
P_HTM[6469]="*Sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ dvīhi āpattikkhandhehi saṅgahitā—**They are found in two classes of offenses:*";
P_HTM[6470]="*siyā pācittiyāpattikkhandhena, siyā dukkaṭāpattikkhandhena.**they may be in the class of offenses entailing confession; they may be in the class of offenses of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6471]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ tīhi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhanti—**They originate in three ways:*";
P_HTM[6472]="*siyā kāyato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhanti, na vācato;**from body and mind, not from speech; or*";
P_HTM[6473]="*siyā vācato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhanti, na kāyato;**from speech and mind, not from body; or*";
P_HTM[6474]="*siyā kāyato ca vācato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhanti.**from body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[6475]="*Catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ, āpattādhikaraṇaṃ.**They are legal issues arising from an offense.*";
