P_HTM[6490]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ tīhi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhanti—**They originate in three ways:*";
P_HTM[6491]="*siyā kāyato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhanti, na vācato;**from body and mind, not from speech; or*";
P_HTM[6492]="*siyā vācato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhanti, na kāyato;**from speech and mind, not from body; or*";
P_HTM[6493]="*siyā kāyato ca vācato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhanti.**from body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[6494]="*Catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ, āpattādhikaraṇaṃ.**They are legal issues arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[6495]="*Sattannaṃ samathānaṃ tīhi samathehi sammanti—**They are settled in three ways:*";
P_HTM[6496]="*siyā sammukhāvinayena ca paṭiññātakaraṇena ca, siyā sammukhāvinayena ca tiṇavatthārakena ca.**they may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by acting according to what has been admitted; or they may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[6497]="*Āpattādhikaraṇapaccayā kati āpattiyo āpajjati?**How many offenses does one commit as a result of legal issues arising from offenses?*";
P_HTM[6498]="*Āpattādhikaraṇapaccayā catasso āpattiyo āpajjati.**Four:*";
P_HTM[6499]="*Bhikkhunī jānaṃ pārājikaṃ dhammaṃ paṭicchādeti, āpatti pārājikassa;**when a nun knowingly conceals an offense entailing expulsion, she commits an offense involving expulsion;*";
