P_HTM[6501]="*bhikkhu saṅghādisesaṃ paṭicchādeti, āpatti pācittiyassa;**when a monk conceals an offense entailing suspension, he commits an offense entailing confession;*";
P_HTM[6502]="*ācāravipattiṃ paṭicchādeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa—**when one conceals a failure in conduct, one commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6503]="*āpattādhikaraṇapaccayā imā catasso āpattiyo āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[6504]="*Tā āpattiyo catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ kati vipattiyo bhajanti …pe…**When it comes to these offenses, to how many of the four kinds of failure do they belong? …*";
P_HTM[6505]="*sattannaṃ samathānaṃ katihi samathehi sammanti?**Through how many of the seven principles for settling legal issues are they settled?*";
P_HTM[6506]="*Tā āpattiyo catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ dve vipattiyo bhajanti—**They belong to two kinds of failure:*";
P_HTM[6507]="*siyā sīlavipattiṃ, siyā ācāravipattiṃ.**they may be failure in morality; they may be failure in conduct.*";
P_HTM[6508]="*Sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ catūhi āpattikkhandhehi saṅgahitā—**They are found in four classes of offenses:*";
P_HTM[6509]="*siyā pārājikāpattikkhandhena, siyā thullaccayāpattikkhandhena, siyā pācittiyāpattikkhandhena, siyā dukkaṭāpattikkhandhena.**they may be in the class of offenses entailing expulsion; they may be in the class of serious offenses; they may be in the class of offenses entailing confession; they may be in the class of offenses of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6510]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhanti—**They originate in one way:*";
P_HTM[6511]="*kāyato ca vācato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhanti.**from body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[6512]="*Catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ, āpattādhikaraṇaṃ.**They are legal issues arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[6513]="*Sattannaṃ samathānaṃ tīhi samathehi sammanti—**They are settled in three ways:*";
P_HTM[6514]="*siyā sammukhāvinayena ca paṭiññātakaraṇena ca, siyā sammukhāvinayena ca tiṇavatthārakena ca.**they may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by acting according to what has been admitted; or they may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[6515]="*Kiccādhikaraṇapaccayā kati āpattiyo āpajjati?**How many offenses does one commit as a result of legal issues arising from business?*";
P_HTM[6516]="*Kiccādhikaraṇapaccayā pañca āpattiyo āpajjati.**Five:*";
P_HTM[6517]="*Ukkhittānuvattikā bhikkhunī yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjati, ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ;**when a nun takes sides with one who has been ejected and she does not stop when pressed up to the third time, then after the motion, she commits an offense of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[6518]="*dvīhi kammavācāhi thullaccayā;**after each of the first two announcements, she commits a serious offense;*";
P_HTM[6519]="*kammavācāpariyosāne āpatti pārājikassa.**when the last announcement is finished, she commits an offense entailing expulsion;*";
P_HTM[6520]="*Bhedakānuvattakā bhikkhū yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjanti, āpatti saṅghādisesassa;**when monks who side with a monk who is pursuing schism do not stop when pressed up to the third time, they commit an offense entailing suspension;*";
P_HTM[6521]="*pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjati, āpatti pācittiyassa—**when not giving up a bad view after being pressed up to the third time, one commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[6522]="*kiccādhikaraṇapaccayā imā pañca āpattiyo āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[6523]="*Tā āpattiyo catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ kati vipattiyo bhajanti …pe…**When it comes to these offenses, to how many of the four kinds of failure do they belong? …*";
P_HTM[6524]="*sattannaṃ samathānaṃ katihi samathehi sammanti?**Through how many of the seven principles for settling legal issues are they settled?*";
P_HTM[6525]="*Tā āpattiyo catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ dve vipattiyo bhajanti—**They belong to two kinds of failure:*";
P_HTM[6526]="*siyā sīlavipattiṃ, siyā ācāravipattiṃ.**they may be failure in morality; they may be failure in conduct.*";
P_HTM[6527]="*Sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ pañcahi āpattikkhandhehi saṅgahitā—**They are found in five classes of offenses:*";
P_HTM[6528]="*siyā pārājikāpattikkhandhena, siyā saṅghādisesāpattikkhandhena, siyā thullaccayāpattikkhandhena, siyā pācittiyāpattikkhandhena, siyā dukkaṭāpattikkhandhena.**they may be in the class of offenses entailing expulsion; they may be in the class of offenses entailing suspension; they may be in the class of serious offenses; they may be in the class of offenses entailing confession; they may be in the class of offenses of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6529]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhanti—**They originate in one way:*";
P_HTM[6530]="*kāyato ca vācato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhanti.**from body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[6531]="*Catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ, āpattādhikaraṇaṃ.**They are legal issues arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[6532]="*Sattannaṃ samathānaṃ tīhi samathehi sammanti—**They are settled in three ways:*";
P_HTM[6533]="*siyā sammukhāvinayena ca paṭiññātakaraṇena ca, siyā sammukhāvinayena ca tiṇavatthārakena ca.**they may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by acting according to what has been admitted; or they may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[6534]="*Ṭhapetvā satta āpattiyo satta āpattikkhandhe, avasesā āpattiyo catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ kati vipattiyo bhajanti?**Apart from the seven offenses and the seven classes of offenses, when it comes to the rest of the offenses, to how many of the four kinds of failure do they belong?*";
P_HTM[6535]="*Sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ katihi āpattikkhandhehi saṅgahitā?**In how many of the seven classes of offenses are they found?*";
P_HTM[6536]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ katihi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhanti?**Through how many of the six kinds of origins of offenses do they originate?*";
P_HTM[6537]="*Catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ?**To which of the four kinds of legal issues do they belong?*";
P_HTM[6538]="*Sattannaṃ samathānaṃ katihi samathehi sammanti?**Through how many of the seven principles for settling legal issues are they settled?*";
P_HTM[6539]="*Ṭhapetvā satta āpattiyo satta āpattikkhandhe avasesā āpattiyo catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ na katamaṃ vipattiṃ bhajanti?**Apart from the seven offenses and the seven classes of offenses, the rest of the offenses do not belong to any of the four kinds of failure.*";
P_HTM[6540]="*Sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ na katamena āpattikkhandhena saṅgahitā.**They are not found in any of the seven classes of offenses.*";
P_HTM[6541]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ na katamena āpattisamuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhanti.**They do not originate through any of the six kinds of origins of offenses.*";
P_HTM[6542]="*Catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ na katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ.**They do not belong to any of the four kinds of legal issues.*";
P_HTM[6543]="*Sattannaṃ samathānaṃ na katamena samathena sammanti.**They are not settled through any of the seven principles for settling legal issues?*";
P_HTM[6544]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[6545]="*Ṭhapetvā satta āpattiyo satta āpattikkhandhe, natthaññā āpattiyoti.**Apart from the seven offenses and the seven classes of offenses, there are no other offenses.*";
P_HTM[6546]="*Adhikaraṇapaccayavāro niṭṭhito pañcamo.**The fifth section on “as a result of legal issues” is finished.*";
P_HTM[6547]="*Antarapeyyālaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The middle repetition is finished.*";
P_HTM[6548]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[6549]="*Katipucchā samuṭṭhānā,**Questioning “how many”, origins,*";
P_HTM[6550]="*katāpatti tatheva ca;**And so “How many offenses;”*";
P_HTM[6551]="*Samuṭṭhānā vipatti ca,**Origins, and failure,*";
P_HTM[6552]="*tathādhikaraṇena cāti.**And so with legal issues.”*";
