P_HTM[6694]="*Tayo samathā āpattādhikaraṇassa sādhāraṇā—**They have three principles for settling legal issues arising from offenses in common:*";
P_HTM[6695]="*sammukhāvinayo, paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ, tiṇavatthārako.**resolution face-to-face, acting according to what has been admitted, and covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[6696]="*Cattāro samathā āpattādhikaraṇassa asādhāraṇā—**And they have three not in common:*";
P_HTM[6697]="*yebhuyyasikā, sativinayo, amūḷhavinayo, tassapāpiyasikā.**majority decision, resolution through recollection, resolution because of past insanity, and further penalty.*";
P_HTM[6698]="*Eko samatho kiccādhikaraṇassa sādhāraṇo—**They have one principles for settling legal issues arising from business in common:*";
P_HTM[6699]="*sammukhāvinayo.**resolution face-to-face.*";
P_HTM[6700]="*Cha samathā kiccādhikaraṇassa asādhāraṇā—**And they have six not in common:*";
P_HTM[6701]="*yebhuyyasikā, sativinayo, amūḷhavinayo, paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ, tassapāpiyasikā, tiṇavatthārako.**majority decision, resolution through recollection, resolution because of past insanity, acting according to what has been admitted, further penalty, and covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[6702]="*Sādhāraṇavāro niṭṭhito sattamo.**The seventh section on “in common” is finished.*";
P_HTM[6703]="*3. Tabbhāgiyavāra**3. The section on “belonging with that”*";
P_HTM[6704]="*Kati samathā vivādādhikaraṇassa tabbhāgiyā?**How many principles for settling are there that belong with legal issues arising from disputes?*";
P_HTM[6705]="*Kati samathā vivādādhikaraṇassa aññabhāgiyā?**How many belong with something else?*";
P_HTM[6706]="*Kati samathā anuvādādhikaraṇassa tabbhāgiyā?**How many principles for settling are there that belong with legal issues arising from accusations?*";
P_HTM[6707]="*Kati samathā anuvādādhikaraṇassa aññabhāgiyā?**How many belong with something else?*";
P_HTM[6708]="*Kati samathā āpattādhikaraṇassa tabbhāgiyā?**How many principles for settling are there that belong with legal issues arising from offenses?*";
P_HTM[6709]="*Kati samathā āpattādhikaraṇassa aññabhāgiyā?**How many belong with something else?*";
P_HTM[6710]="*Kati samathā kiccādhikaraṇassa tabbhāgiyā?**How many principles for settling are there that belong with legal issues arising from business?*";
P_HTM[6711]="*Kati samathā kiccādhikaraṇassa aññabhāgiyā?**How many belong with something else?*";
P_HTM[6712]="*Dve samathā vivādādhikaraṇassa tabbhāgiyā—**There are two principles for settling that belong with legal issues arising from disputes:*";
P_HTM[6713]="*sammukhāvinayo, yebhuyyasikā.**resolution face-to-face and majority decision.*";
P_HTM[6714]="*Pañca samathā vivādādhikaraṇassa aññabhāgiyā—**And there are five that belong with something else:*";
P_HTM[6715]="*sativinayo, amūḷhavinayo, paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ, tassapāpiyasikā, tiṇavatthārako.**resolution through recollection, resolution because of past insanity, acting according to what has been admitted, further penalty, and covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[6716]="*Cattāro samathā anuvādādhikaraṇassa tabbhāgiyā—**There are two principles for settling that belong with legal issues arising from accusations:*";
P_HTM[6717]="*sammukhāvinayo, sativinayo, amūḷhavinayo, tassapāpiyasikā.**resolution face-to-face, resolution through recollection, resolution because of past insanity, and further penalty.*";
P_HTM[6718]="*Tayo samathā anuvādādhikaraṇassa aññabhāgiyā—**And there are three that belong with something else:*";
P_HTM[6719]="*yebhuyyasikā, paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ, tiṇavatthārako.**majority decision, acting according to what has been admitted, and covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[6720]="*Tayo samathā āpattādhikaraṇassa tabbhāgiyā—**There are two principles for settling that belong with legal issues arising from offenses:*";
P_HTM[6721]="*sammukhāvinayo, paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ, tiṇavatthārako.**resolution face-to-face, acting according to what has been admitted, and covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[6722]="*Cattāro samathā āpattādhikaraṇassa aññabhāgiyā—**And there are four that belong with something else:*";
P_HTM[6723]="*yebhuyyasikā, sativinayo, amūḷhavinayo, tassapāpiyasikā.**majority decision, resolution through recollection, resolution because of past insanity, and further penalty.*";
P_HTM[6724]="*Eko samatho kiccādhikaraṇassa tabbhāgiyo—**There are two principles for settling that belong with legal issues arising from business:*";
P_HTM[6725]="*sammukhāvinayo.**resolution face-to-face.*";
P_HTM[6726]="*Cha samathā kiccādhikaraṇassa aññabhāgiyā—**And there are six that belong with something else:*";
P_HTM[6727]="*yebhuyyasikā, sativinayo, amūḷhavinayo, paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ, tassapāpiyasikā, tiṇavatthārako.**majority decision, resolution through recollection, resolution because of past insanity, acting according to what has been admitted, further penalty, and covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[6728]="*Tabbhāgiyavāro niṭṭhito aṭṭhamo.**The eighth section on “belonging to that” is finished*";
P_HTM[6729]="*4. Samathāsamathassasādhāraṇavāra**4. The section on different principles for settling used in common*";
P_HTM[6730]="*Samathā samathassa sādhāraṇā, samathā samathassa asādhāraṇā.**One way of settling used in common with another way of settling; one way of settling not used in common with another way of settling.*";
P_HTM[6731]="*Siyā samathā samathassa sādhāraṇā, siyā samathā samathassa asādhāraṇā.**It may be that one way of settling is in common with another way of settling; it may be that one way of settling is not in common with another way of settling.*";
P_HTM[6732]="*Kathaṃ siyā samathā samathassa sādhāraṇā?**How may it be that one way of settling is used in common with another way of settling?*";
P_HTM[6733]="*Kathaṃ siyā samathā samathassa asādhāraṇā?**How may it be that one way of settling is not used in common with another way of settling?*";
P_HTM[6734]="*Yebhuyyasikā sammukhāvinayassa sādhāraṇā, sativinayassa amūḷhavinayassa paṭiññātakaraṇassa tassapāpiyasikāya tiṇavatthārakassa asādhāraṇā.**[1] Majority decision is used in common with resolution face-to-face. It is not used in common with resolution through recollection, resolution because of past insanity, acting according to what has been admitted, further penalty, and covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[6735]="*Sativinayo sammukhāvinayassa sādhāraṇo, amūḷhavinayassa paṭiññātakaraṇassa tassapāpiyasikāya tiṇavatthārakassa yebhuyyasikāya asādhāraṇo.**Resolution through recollection is used in common with resolution face-to-face. It is not used in common with resolution because of past insanity, acting according to what has been admitted, further penalty, covering over as if with grass, and majority decision.*";
P_HTM[6736]="*Amūḷhavinayo sammukhāvinayassa sādhāraṇo, paṭiññātakaraṇassa tassapāpiyasikāya tiṇavatthārakassa yebhuyyasikāya sativinayassa asādhāraṇo.**Resolution because of past insanity is used in common with resolution face-to-face. It is not used in common with acting according to what has been admitted, further penalty, covering over as if with grass, majority decision, and resolution through recollection.*";
P_HTM[6737]="*Paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ sammukhāvinayassa sādhāraṇaṃ, tassapāpiyasikāya tiṇavatthārakassa yebhuyyasikāya sativinayassa amūḷhavinayassa asādhāraṇaṃ.**Acting according to what has been admitted is used in common with resolution face-to-face. It is not used in common with further penalty, covering over as if with grass, majority decision, resolution through recollection, and resolution because of past insanity.*";
P_HTM[6738]="*Tassapāpiyasikā sammukhāvinayassa sādhāraṇā, tiṇavatthārakassa yebhuyyasikāya sativinayassa amūḷhavinayassa paṭiññātakaraṇassa asādhāraṇā.**Further penalty is used in common with resolution face-to-face. It is not used in common with covering over as if with grass, majority decision, resolution through recollection, resolution because of past insanity, and acting according to what has been admitted.*";
P_HTM[6739]="*Tiṇavatthārako sammukhāvinayassa sādhāraṇo, yebhuyyasikāya sativinayassa amūḷhavinayassa paṭiññātakaraṇassa tassapāpiyasikāya asādhāraṇo.**Covering over as if with grass is used in common with resolution face-to-face. It is not used in common with majority decision, resolution through recollection, resolution because of past insanity, acting according to what has been admitted, and further penalty.*";
P_HTM[6740]="*Evaṃ siyā samathā samathassa sādhāraṇā;* **";
P_HTM[6741]="*evaṃ siyā samathā samathassa asādhāraṇā.* **";
P_HTM[6742]="*Samathā samathassa sādhāraṇavāro niṭṭhito navamo.**The ninth section on different principles for settling used in common is finished.*";
P_HTM[6743]="*5. Samathāsamathassatabbhāgiyavāra**5. The section on different principles for settling belonging with each other*";
P_HTM[6744]="*Samathā samathassa tabbhāgiyā, samathā samathassa aññabhāgiyā.**One way of settling belongs with another way of settling; one way of settling does not belong with another way of settling.*";
P_HTM[6745]="*Siyā samathā samathassa tabbhāgiyā, siyā samathā samathassa aññabhāgiyā.**It may be that one way of settling belongs with another way of settling; it may be that one way of settling does not belong with another way of settling.*";
P_HTM[6746]="*Kathaṃ siyā samathā samathassa tabbhāgiyā?**How may it be that one way of settling belongs with another way of settling?*";
P_HTM[6747]="*Kathaṃ siyā samathā samathassa aññabhāgiyā?**How may it be that one way of settling does not belong with another way of settling?*";
P_HTM[6748]="*Yebhuyyasikā sammukhāvinayassa tabbhāgiyā, sativinayassa amūḷhavinayassa paṭiññātakaraṇassa tassapāpiyasikāya tiṇavatthārakassa aññabhāgiyā.**[1] Majority decision belongs with resolution face-to-face. It does not belong with resolution through recollection, resolution because of past insanity, acting according to what has been admitted, further penalty, or covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[6749]="*Sativinayo sammukhāvinayassa tabbhāgiyo, amūḷhavinayassa paṭiññātakaraṇassa tassapāpiyasikāya tiṇavatthārakassa yebhuyyasikāya aññabhāgiyo.**Resolution through recollection belong with resolution face-to-face. It does not belong with resolution because of past insanity, acting according to what has been admitted, further penalty, covering over as if with grass, or majority decision.*";
P_HTM[6750]="*Amūḷhavinayo sammukhāvinayassa tabbhāgiyo, paṭiññātakaraṇassa tassapāpiyasikāya tiṇavatthārakassa yebhuyyasikāya sativinayassa aññabhāgiyo.**Resolution because of past insanity belong with resolution face-to-face. It does not belong with acting according to what has been admitted, further penalty, covering over as if with grass, majority decision, or resolution through recollection.*";
P_HTM[6751]="*Paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ sammukhāvinayassa tabbhāgiyaṃ, tassapāpiyasikāya tiṇavatthārakassa yebhuyyasikāya sativinayassa amūḷhavinayassa aññabhāgiyaṃ.**Acting according to what has been admitted belong with resolution face-to-face. It does not belong with further penalty, covering over as if with grass, majority decision, resolution through recollection, or resolution because of past insanity.*";
P_HTM[6752]="*Tassapāpiyasikā sammukhāvinayassa tabbhāgiyā, tiṇavatthārakassa yebhuyyasikāya sativinayassa amūḷhavinayassa paṭiññātakaraṇassa aññabhāgiyā.**Further penalty belong with resolution face-to-face. It does not belong with covering over as if with grass, majority decision, resolution through recollection, resolution because of past insanity, or acting according to what has been admitted.*";
P_HTM[6753]="*Tiṇavatthārako sammukhāvinayassa tabbhāgiyo, yebhuyyasikāya sativinayassa amūḷhavinayassa paṭiññātakaraṇassa tassapāpiyasikāya aññabhāgiyo.**Covering over as if with grass belongs with resolution face-to-face. It does not belong with majority decision, resolution through recollection, resolution because of past insanity, acting according to what has been admitted, or further penalty.*";
P_HTM[6754]="*Evaṃ siyā samathā samathassa tabbhāgiyā, evaṃ siyā samathā samathassa aññabhāgiyā.* **";
P_HTM[6755]="*Samathā samathassa tabbhāgiyavāro niṭṭhito dasamo.**The tenth section on different principles for settling belonging with each other is finished.*";
P_HTM[6756]="*6. Samathasammukhāvinayavāra**6. The section on “a way of settling is resolution face-to-face”*";
P_HTM[6757]="*Samatho sammukhāvinayo, sammukhāvinayo samatho?**Is one way of settling resolution face-to-face, and is resolution face-to-face one way of settling?*";
P_HTM[6758]="*Samatho yebhuyyasikā, yebhuyyasikā samatho?**Is one way of settling a majority decision, and is a majority decision one way of settling?*";
P_HTM[6759]="*Samatho sativinayo, sativinayo samatho?**Is one way of settling resolution through recollection, and is resolution through recollection one way of settling?*";
P_HTM[6760]="*Samatho amūḷhavinayo, amūḷhavinayo samatho?**Is one way of settling resolution because of past insanity, and is resolution because of past insanity one way of settling?*";
P_HTM[6761]="*Samatho paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ, paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ samatho?**Is one way of settling acting according to what has been admitted, and is acting according to what has been admitted one way of settling?*";
P_HTM[6762]="*Samatho tassapāpiyasikā, tassapāpiyasikā samatho?**Is one way of settling a further penalty, and is a further penalty one way of settling?*";
P_HTM[6763]="*Samatho tiṇavatthārako, tiṇavatthārako samatho?**Is one way of settling covering over as if with grass, and is covering over as if with grass one way of settling?*";
P_HTM[6764]="*Yebhuyyasikā sativinayo amūḷhavinayo paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ tassapāpiyasikā tiṇavatthārako—**Majority decision, resolution through recollection, resolution because of past insanity, acting according to what has been admitted, further penalty, and covering over as if with grass:*";
P_HTM[6765]="*ime samathā samathā, no sammukhāvinayo.**these principles for settling are principles for settling, but they are not resolution face-to-face.*";
P_HTM[6766]="*Sammukhāvinayo samatho ceva sammukhāvinayo ca.**Resolution face-to-face is both a way of settling and also resolution face-to-face.*";
P_HTM[6767]="*Sativinayo amūḷhavinayo paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ tassapāpiyasikā tiṇavatthārako sammukhāvinayo—**Resolution through recollection, resolution because of past insanity, acting according to what has been admitted, further penalty, covering over as if with grass, and resolution face-to-face:*";
P_HTM[6768]="*ime samathā samathā, no yebhuyyasikā.**these principles for settling are principles for settling, but they are not a majority decision.*";
P_HTM[6769]="*Yebhuyyasikā samatho ceva yebhuyyasikā ca.**A majority decision is both a way of settling and also a majority decision.*";
P_HTM[6770]="*Amūḷhavinayo paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ tassapāpiyasikā tiṇavatthārako sammukhāvinayo yebhuyyasikā—**Resolution because of past insanity, acting according to what has been admitted, further penalty, covering over as if with grass, resolution face-to-face, and majority decision:*";
P_HTM[6771]="*ime samathā samathā, no sativinayo.**these principles for settling are principles for settling, but they are not resolution through recollection.*";
P_HTM[6772]="*Sativinayo samatho ceva sativinayo ca.**Resolution through recollection is both a way of settling and also resolution through recollection.*";
P_HTM[6773]="*Paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ tassapāpiyasikā tiṇavatthārako sammukhāvinayo yebhuyyasikā sativinayo—**Acting according to what has been admitted, further penalty, covering over as if with grass, resolution face-to-face, majority decision, and resolution through recollection:*";
P_HTM[6774]="*ime samathā samathā, no amūḷhavinayo.**these principles for settling are principles for settling, but they are not resolution because of past insanity.*";
P_HTM[6775]="*Amūḷhavinayo samatho ceva amūḷhavinayo ca.**Resolution because of past insanity is both a way of settling and also resolution because of past insanity.*";
P_HTM[6776]="*Tassapāpiyasikā tiṇavatthārako sammukhāvinayo yebhuyyasikā sativinayo amūḷhavinayo—**Further penalty, covering over as if with grass, resolution face-to-face, majority decision, resolution through recollection, and resolution because of past insanity:*";
P_HTM[6777]="*ime samathā samathā, no paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ.**these principles for settling are principles for settling, but they are not acting according to what has been admitted.*";
P_HTM[6778]="*Paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ samatho ceva paṭiññātakaraṇañca.**Acting according to what has been admitted is both a way of settling and also acting according to what has been admitted.*";
P_HTM[6779]="*Tiṇavatthārako sammukhāvinayo yebhuyyasikā sativinayo amūḷhavinayo paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ—**Covering over as if with grass, resolution face-to-face, majority decision, resolution through recollection, resolution because of past insanity, and acting according to what has been admitted:*";
P_HTM[6780]="*ime samathā samathā, no tassapāpiyasikā.**these principles for settling are principles for settling, but they are not a further penalty.*";
P_HTM[6781]="*Tassapāpiyasikā samatho ceva tassapāpiyasikā ca.**A further penalty is both a way of settling and also a further penalty.*";
P_HTM[6782]="*Sammukhāvinayo yebhuyyasikā sativinayo amūḷhavinayo paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ tassapāpiyasikā—**Resolution face-to-face, majority decision, resolution through recollection, resolution because of past insanity, acting according to what has been admitted, and further penalty:*";
P_HTM[6783]="*ime samathā samathā, no tiṇavatthārako.**these principles for settling are principles for settling, but they are not covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[6784]="*Tiṇavatthārako samatho ceva tiṇavatthārako ca.**Covering over as if with grass is both a way of settling and also covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[6785]="*Samathasammukhāvinayavāro niṭṭhito ekādasamo.**The eleventh section on “a way of settling is resolution face-to-face” is finished.*";
P_HTM[6786]="*7. Vinayavāra**7. The section on resolution*";
P_HTM[6787]="*Vinayo sammukhāvinayo, sammukhāvinayo vinayo?**Is one way of resolution resolution face-to-face, and is resolution face-to-face one way of resolution?*";
P_HTM[6788]="*Vinayo yebhuyyasikā, yebhuyyasikā vinayo?**Is one way of resolution a majority decision, and is a majority decision one way of resolution?*";
P_HTM[6789]="*Vinayo sativinayo, sativinayo vinayo?**Is one way of resolution resolution through recollection, and is resolution through recollection one way of resolution?*";
P_HTM[6790]="*Vinayo amūḷhavinayo, amūḷhavinayo vinayo?**Is one way of resolution resolution because of past insanity, and is resolution because of past insanity one way of resolution?*";
P_HTM[6791]="*Vinayo paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ, paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ vinayo?**Is one way of resolution acting according to what has been admitted, and is acting according to what has been admitted one way of resolution?*";
P_HTM[6792]="*Vinayo tassapāpiyasikā, tassapāpiyasikā vinayo?**Is one way of resolution a further penalty, and is a further penalty one way of resolution?*";
P_HTM[6793]="*Vinayo tiṇavatthārako, tiṇavatthārako vinayo?**Is one way of resolution covering over as if with grass, and is covering over as if with grass one way of resolution?*";
P_HTM[6794]="*Vinayo siyā sammukhāvinayo siyā na sammukhāvinayo.**A resolution may be resolution face-to-face, or it may not be resolution face-to -face.*";
P_HTM[6795]="*Sammukhāvinayo vinayo ceva sammukhāvinayo ca.**Resolution face-to-face is both a resolution and also a resolution face-to-face.*";
P_HTM[6796]="*Vinayo siyā yebhuyyasikā, siyā na yebhuyyasikā.**A resolution may be a majority decision, or it may not be a majority decision.*";
P_HTM[6797]="*Yebhuyyasikā vinayo ceva yebhuyyasikā ca.**a majority decision is both a resolution and also a majority decision.*";
P_HTM[6798]="*Vinayo siyā sativinayo, siyā na sativinayo.**A resolution may be resolution through recollection, or it may not be resolution through recollection.*";
P_HTM[6799]="*Sativinayo vinayo ceva sativinayo ca.**Resolution through recollection is both a resolution and also a resolution through recollection.*";
P_HTM[6800]="*Vinayo siyā amūḷhavinayo, siyā na amūḷhavinayo.**A resolution may be resolution because of past insanity, or it may not be resolution because of past insanity.*";
P_HTM[6801]="*Amūḷhavinayo vinayo ceva amūḷhavinayo ca.**Resolution because of past insanity is both a resolution and also a resolution because of past insanity.*";
P_HTM[6802]="*Vinayo siyā paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ, siyā na paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ.**A resolution may be acting according to what has been admitted, or it may not be acting according to what has been admitted.*";
P_HTM[6803]="*Paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ vinayo ceva paṭiññātakaraṇañca.**Acting according to what has been admitted is both a resolution and also an acting according to what has been admitted.*";
P_HTM[6804]="*Vinayo siyā tassapāpiyasikā, siyā na tassapāpiyasikā.**A resolution may be a further penalty, or it may not be a further penalty.*";
P_HTM[6805]="*Tassapāpiyasikā vinayo ceva tassapāpiyasikā ca.**A further penalty is both a resolution and also a further penalty.*";
P_HTM[6806]="*Vinayo siyā tiṇavatthārako, siyā na tiṇavatthārako.**A resolution may be covering over as if with grass, or it may not be covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[6807]="*Tiṇavatthārako vinayo ceva tiṇavatthārako ca.**Covering over as if with grass is both a resolution and also a covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[6808]="*Vinayavāro niṭṭhito dvādasamo.**The twelfth section on resolution is finished.*";
P_HTM[6809]="*8. Kusalavāra**8. The section on the wholesome*";
P_HTM[6810]="*Sammukhāvinayo kusalo akusalo abyākato?**Is resolution face-to-face wholesome, unwholesome, or indeterminate?*";
P_HTM[6811]="*Yebhuyyasikā kusalā akusalā abyākatā?**Is a majority decision wholesome, unwholesome, or indeterminate?*";
P_HTM[6812]="*Sativinayo kusalo akusalo abyākato?**Is resolution through recollection wholesome, unwholesome, or indeterminate?*";
P_HTM[6813]="*Amūḷhavinayo kusalo akusalo abyākato?**Is resolution because of past insanity wholesome, unwholesome, or indeterminate?*";
P_HTM[6814]="*Paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ kusalaṃ akusalaṃ abyākataṃ?**Is acting according to what has been admitted wholesome, unwholesome, or indeterminate?*";
P_HTM[6815]="*Tassapāpiyasikā kusalā akusalā abyākatā?**Is a further penalty wholesome, unwholesome, or indeterminate?*";
P_HTM[6816]="*Tiṇavatthārako kusalo akusalo abyākato?**Is covering over as if with grass, wholesome, unwholesome, or indeterminate?*";
P_HTM[6817]="*Sammukhāvinayo siyā kusalo, siyā abyākato.**Resolution face-to-face may be wholesome or indeterminate.*";
P_HTM[6818]="*Natthi sammukhāvinayo akusalo.**Resolution face-to-face is never unwholesome.*";
P_HTM[6819]="*Yebhuyyasikā siyā kusalā, siyā akusalā, siyā abyākatā.**A majority decision may be wholesome, unwholesome, or indeterminate.*";
P_HTM[6820]="*Sativinayo siyā kusalo, siyā akusalo, siyā abyākato.**Resolution through recollection may be wholesome, unwholesome, or indeterminate.*";
P_HTM[6821]="*Amūḷhavinayo siyā kusalo, siyā akusalo, siyā abyākato.**Resolution because of past insanity may be wholesome, unwholesome, or indeterminate.*";
P_HTM[6822]="*Paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ siyā kusalaṃ, siyā akusalaṃ, siyā abyākataṃ.**Acting according to what has been admitted may be wholesome, unwholesome, or indeterminate.*";
P_HTM[6823]="*Tassapāpiyasikā siyā kusalā, siyā akusalā siyā abyākatā.**A further penalty may be wholesome, unwholesome, or indeterminate.*";
P_HTM[6824]="*Tiṇavatthārako siyā kusalo, siyā akusalo, siyā abyākato.**Covering over as if with grass, may be wholesome, unwholesome, or indeterminate.*";
P_HTM[6825]="*Vivādādhikaraṇaṃ kusalaṃ akusalaṃ abyākataṃ.**Is a legal issue arising from a dispute wholesome, unwholesome, or indeterminate?*";
P_HTM[6826]="*Anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ kusalaṃ akusalaṃ abyākataṃ.**Is a legal issue arising from an accusation wholesome, unwholesome, or indeterminate?*";
P_HTM[6827]="*Āpattādhikaraṇaṃ kusalaṃ akusalaṃ abyākataṃ.**Is a legal issue arising from an offense wholesome, unwholesome, or indeterminate?*";
P_HTM[6828]="*Kiccādhikaraṇaṃ kusalaṃ akusalaṃ abyākataṃ.**Is a legal issues arising from business wholesome, unwholesome, or indeterminate?*";
P_HTM[6829]="*Vivādādhikaraṇaṃ siyā kusalaṃ, siyā akusalaṃ, siyā abyākataṃ.**A legal issue arising from a dispute may be wholesome, unwholesome, or indeterminate.*";
P_HTM[6830]="*Anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ siyā kusalaṃ, siyā akusalaṃ, siyā abyākataṃ.**A legal issue arising from an accusation may be wholesome, unwholesome, or indeterminate.*";
P_HTM[6831]="*Āpattādhikaraṇaṃ siyā akusalaṃ, siyā abyākataṃ.**A legal issue arising from an accusation may be unwholesome or indeterminate.*";
P_HTM[6832]="*Natthi āpattādhikaraṇaṃ kusalaṃ.**A legal issue arising from an accusation is never wholesome.*";
P_HTM[6833]="*Kiccādhikaraṇaṃ siyā kusalaṃ, siyā akusalaṃ, siyā abyākataṃ.**A legal issue arising from business may be wholesome, unwholesome, or indeterminate.*";
P_HTM[6834]="*Kusalavāro niṭṭhito terasamo.**The thirteenth section on the wholesome is finished.*";
P_HTM[6835]="*9. Yatthavāra, pucchāvāra**9. The section on “where”, the section on questioning*";
P_HTM[6836]="*Yattha yebhuyyasikā labbhati, tattha sammukhāvinayo labbhati;**Where a majority decision is appropriate, there resolution face-to-face is appropriate.*";
P_HTM[6837]="*yattha sammukhāvinayo labbhati, tattha yebhuyyasikā labbhati.**Where resolution face-to-face is appropriate, there a majority decision is appropriate.*";
P_HTM[6838]="*Na tattha sativinayo labbhati, na tattha amūḷhavinayo labbhati, na tattha paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ labbhati, na tattha tassapāpiyasikā labbhati, na tattha tiṇavatthārako labbhati.**But there resolution through recollection is not appropriate, nor is resolution because of past insanity, acting according to what has been admitted, a further penalty, or covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[6839]="*Yattha sativinayo labbhati, tattha sammukhāvinayo labbhati;**Where resolution through recollection is appropriate, there resolution face-to-face is appropriate.*";
P_HTM[6840]="*yattha sammukhāvinayo labbhati, tattha sativinayo labbhati.**Where resolution face-to-face is appropriate, there resolution through recollection is appropriate.*";
P_HTM[6841]="*Na tattha amūḷhavinayo labbhati, na tattha paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ labbhati, na tattha tassapāpiyasikā labbhati, na tattha tiṇavatthārako labbhati, na tattha yebhuyyasikā labbhati.**But there resolution because of past insanity is not appropriate, nor is acting according to what has been admitted, a further penalty, covering over as if with grass, or a majority decision.*";
P_HTM[6842]="*Yattha amūḷhavinayo labbhati, tattha sammukhāvinayo labbhati;**Where resolution because of past insanity is appropriate, there resolution face-to-face is appropriate.*";
P_HTM[6843]="*yattha sammukhāvinayo labbhati, tattha amūḷhavinayo labbhati.**Where resolution face-to-face is appropriate, there resolution because of past insanity is appropriate.*";
P_HTM[6844]="*Na tattha paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ labbhati, na tattha tassapāpiyasikā labbhati, na tattha tiṇavatthārako labbhati, na tattha yebhuyyasikā labbhati, na tattha sativinayo labbhati.**But there acting according to what has been admitted is not appropriate, nor a further penalty, covering over as if with grass, a majority decision, or resolution through recollection.*";
P_HTM[6845]="*Yattha paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ labbhati, tattha sammukhāvinayo labbhati;**Where acting according to what has been admitted is appropriate, there resolution face-to-face is appropriate.*";
P_HTM[6846]="*yattha sammukhāvinayo labbhati, tattha paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ labbhati.**Where resolution face-to-face is appropriate, there acting according to what has been admitted is appropriate.*";
P_HTM[6847]="*Na tattha tassapāpiyasikā labbhati, na tattha tiṇavatthārako labbhati, na tattha yebhuyyasikā labbhati, na tattha sativinayo labbhati, na tattha amūḷhavinayo labbhati.**But there a further penalty is not appropriate, nor is covering over as if with grass, a majority decision, resolution through recollection, or resolution because of past insanity.*";
P_HTM[6848]="*Yattha tassapāpiyasikā labbhati, tattha sammukhāvinayo labbhati;**Where a further penalty is appropriate, there resolution face-to-face is appropriate.*";
P_HTM[6849]="*yattha sammukhāvinayo labbhati, tattha tassapāpiyasikā labbhati.**Where resolution face-to-face is appropriate, there a further penalty is appropriate.*";
P_HTM[6850]="*Na tattha tiṇavatthārako labbhati, na tattha yebhuyyasikā labbhati, na tattha sativinayo labbhati, na tattha amūḷhavinayo labbhati, na tattha paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ labbhati.**But there covering over as if with grass is not appropriate, nor is a majority decision, resolution through recollection, resolution because of past insanity, or acting according to what has been admitted.*";
P_HTM[6851]="*Yattha tiṇavatthārako labbhati, tattha sammukhāvinayo labbhati;**Where covering over as if with grass is appropriate, there resolution face-to-face is appropriate.*";
P_HTM[6852]="*yattha sammukhāvinayo labbhati, tattha tiṇavatthārako labbhati.**Where resolution face-to-face is appropriate, there covering over as if with grass, is appropriate.*";
P_HTM[6853]="*Na tattha yebhuyyasikā labbhati, na tattha sativinayo labbhati, na tattha amūḷhavinayo labbhati, na tattha paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ labbhati, na tattha tassapāpiyasikā labbhati.**But there a majority decision is not appropriate, nor is resolution through recollection, resolution because of past insanity, acting according to what has been admitted, or a further penalty.*";
P_HTM[6854]="*Yattha yebhuyyasikā tattha sammukhāvinayo;**Where there is a majority decision, there is resolution face-to-face.*";
P_HTM[6855]="*yattha sammukhāvinayo tattha yebhuyyasikā.**Where there is resolution face-to-face, there is a majority decision.*";
P_HTM[6856]="*Na tattha sativinayo, na tattha amūḷhavinayo, na tattha paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ, na tattha tassapāpiyasikā, na tattha tiṇavatthārako.**But there resolution through recollection is not appropriate, nor is resolution because of past insanity, acting according to what has been admitted, a further penalty, or covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[6857]="*Yattha sativinayo tattha sammukhāvinayo;**Where there is resolution through recollection, there is resolution face-to-face.*";
P_HTM[6858]="*yattha sammukhāvinayo tattha sativinayo.**Where there is resolution face-to-face, there is resolution through recollection.*";
P_HTM[6859]="*Na tattha amūḷhavinayo, na tattha paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ, na tattha tassapāpiyasikā, na tattha tiṇavatthārako, na tattha yebhuyyasikā.**But there resolution because of past insanity is not appropriate, nor is acting according to what has been admitted, a further penalty, covering over as if with grass, or majority decision.*";
P_HTM[6860]="*Sammukhāvinayaṃ kātuna mūlaṃ …pe….**Resolution face-to-face to be done as the basis …*";
P_HTM[6861]="*Yattha tiṇavatthārako tattha sammukhāvinayo;**Where there is covering over as if with grass, there is resolution face-to-face.*";
P_HTM[6862]="*yattha sammukhāvinayo tattha tiṇavatthārako.**Where there is resolution face-to-face, there is covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[6863]="*Na tattha yebhuyyasikā, na tattha sativinayo, na tattha amūḷhavinayo, na tattha paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ, na tattha tassapāpiyasikā.**But there a majority decision is not appropriate, nor is resolution because of past insanity, acting according to what has been admitted, or a further penalty.*";
P_HTM[6864]="*Cakkapeyyālaṃ.**Permutation series repetition.*";
P_HTM[6865]="*Yatthavāro niṭṭhito cuddasamo.**The fourteenth section on “where” is finished.*";
P_HTM[6866]="*10. Samathavāra, vissajjanāvāra**10. The section on settling, the section on responding*";
P_HTM[6867]="*Yasmiṃ samaye sammukhāvinayena ca yebhuyyasikāya ca adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasammati, yattha yebhuyyasikā labbhati tattha sammukhāvinayo labbhati, yattha sammukhāvinayo labbhati tattha yebhuyyasikā labbhati.**On an occasion when a legal issue is being resolved through resolution face-to-face and majority decision, then, where a majority decision is appropriate, there resolution face-to-face is appropriate, and where resolution face-to-face is appropriate, there a majority decision is appropriate.*";
P_HTM[6868]="*Na tattha sativinayo labbhati, na tattha amūḷhavinayo labbhati, na tattha paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ labbhati, na tattha tassapāpiyasikā labbhati, na tattha tiṇavatthārako labbhati.**But there resolution through recollection is not appropriate, nor is resolution because of past insanity, acting according to what has been admitted, a further penalty, or covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[6869]="*Yasmiṃ samaye sammukhāvinayena ca sativinayena ca adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasammati, yattha sativinayo labbhati tattha sammukhāvinayo labbhati, yattha sammukhāvinayo labbhati tattha sativinayo labbhati.**On an occasion when a legal issue is being resolved through resolution face-to-face and resolution through recollection, then, where resolution through recollection is appropriate, there resolution face-to-face is appropriate, and where resolution face-to-face is appropriate, there resolution through recollection is appropriate.*";
P_HTM[6870]="*Na tattha amūḷhavinayo labbhati, na tattha paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ labbhati, na tattha tassapāpiyasikā labbhati, na tattha tiṇavatthārako labbhati, na tattha yebhuyyasikā labbhati.**But there resolution because of past insanity is not appropriate, nor is acting according to what has been admitted, a further penalty, covering over as if with grass, or a majority decision.*";
P_HTM[6871]="*Yasmiṃ samaye sammukhāvinayena ca amūḷhavinayena ca adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasammati, yattha amūḷhavinayo labbhati tattha sammukhāvinayo labbhati, yattha sammukhāvinayo labbhati tattha amūḷhavinayo labbhati.**On an occasion when a legal issue is being resolved through resolution face-to-face and resolution because of past insanity, then, where resolution because of past insanity is appropriate, there resolution face-to-face is appropriate, and where resolution face-to-face is appropriate, there resolution because of past insanity is appropriate.*";
P_HTM[6872]="*Na tattha paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ labbhati, na tattha tassapāpiyasikā labbhati, na tattha tiṇavatthārako labbhati, na tattha yebhuyyasikā labbhati, na tattha sativinayo labbhati.**But there acting according to what has been admitted is not appropriate, nor is a further penalty, covering over as if with grass, a majority decision, or resolution through recollection.*";
P_HTM[6873]="*Yasmiṃ samaye sammukhāvinayena ca paṭiññātakaraṇena ca adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasammati, yattha paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ labbhati tattha sammukhāvinayo labbhati, yattha sammukhāvinayo labbhati tattha paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ labbhati.**On an occasion when a legal issue is being resolved through resolution face-to-face and acting according to what has been admitted, then, where acting according to what has been admitted is appropriate, there resolution face-to-face is appropriate, and where resolution face-to-face is appropriate, there acting according to what has been admitted is appropriate.*";
P_HTM[6874]="*Na tattha tassapāpiyasikā labbhati, na tattha tiṇavatthārako labbhati, na tattha yebhuyyasikā labbhati, na tattha sativinayo labbhati, na tattha amūḷhavinayo labbhati.**But there a further penalty is not appropriate, nor is covering over as if with grass, a majority decision, resolution through recollection, or resolution because of past insanity.*";
P_HTM[6875]="*Yasmiṃ samaye sammukhāvinayena ca tassapāpiyasikāya ca adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasammati, yattha tassapāpiyasikā labbhati tattha sammukhāvinayo labbhati, yattha sammukhāvinayo labbhati tattha tassapāpiyasikā labbhati.**On an occasion when a legal issue is being resolved through resolution face-to-face and a further penalty, then, where a further penalty is appropriate, there resolution face-to-face is appropriate, and where resolution face-to-face is appropriate, there a further penalty is appropriate.*";
P_HTM[6876]="*Na tattha tiṇavatthārako labbhati, na tattha yebhuyyasikā labbhati, na tattha sativinayo labbhati, na tattha amūḷhavinayo labbhati, na tattha paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ labbhati.**But there covering over as if with grass is not appropriate, nor is a majority decision, resolution through recollection, resolution because of past insanity, or acting according to what has been admitted.*";
P_HTM[6877]="*Yasmiṃ samaye sammukhāvinayena ca tiṇavatthārakena ca adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasammati, yattha tiṇavatthārako labbhati tattha sammukhāvinayo labbhati, yattha sammukhāvinayo labbhati tattha tiṇavatthārako labbhati.**On an occasion when a legal issue is being resolved through resolution face-to-face and covering over as if with grass, then, where covering over as if with grass is appropriate, there resolution face-to-face is appropriate, and where resolution face-to-face is appropriate, there covering over as if with grass is appropriate.*";
P_HTM[6878]="*Na tattha yebhuyyasikā labbhati, na tattha sativinayo labbhati, na tattha amūḷhavinayo labbhati, na tattha paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ labbhati, na tattha tassapāpiyasikā labbhati.**But there a majority decision is not appropriate, nor is resolution through recollection, resolution because of past insanity, acting according to what has been admitted, or a further penalty.*";
P_HTM[6879]="*Samathavāro niṭṭhito pannarasamo.**The fifteenth section on settling is finished.*";
P_HTM[6880]="*11. Saṃsaṭṭhavāra**11. The section on connection*";
P_HTM[6881]="*Adhikaraṇanti vā samathāti vā ime dhammā saṃsaṭṭhā udāhu visaṃsaṭṭhā?**“Are ‘legal issue’ and ‘settling’ connected or disconnected?*";
P_HTM[6882]="*Labbhā ca panimesaṃ dhammānaṃ vinibbhujitvā vinibbhujitvā nānākaraṇaṃ paññāpetunti?**Is it possible to completely separate them and point to their difference?”*";
P_HTM[6883]="*Adhikaraṇanti vā samathāti vā ime dhammā visaṃsaṭṭhā, no saṃsaṭṭhā.**“‘Legal issue’ and ‘settling’ are disconnected, not connected.*";
P_HTM[6884]="*Labbhā ca panimesaṃ dhammānaṃ vinibbhujitvā vinibbhujitvā nānākaraṇaṃ paññāpetunti.**It is possible to completely separate them and point to their difference.”*";
P_HTM[6885]="*So—“mā hevan”tissa vacanīyo.**They should be told not to say so.*";
P_HTM[6886]="*Adhikaraṇanti vā samathāti vā ime dhammā saṃsaṭṭhā, no visaṃsaṭṭhā.**“‘Legal issue’ and ‘settling’ are connected, not disconnected.*";
P_HTM[6887]="*No ca labbhā imesaṃ dhammānaṃ vinibbhujitvā vinibbhujitvā nānākaraṇaṃ paññāpetuṃ.**It is not possible to completely separate them and point to their difference.*";
P_HTM[6888]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[6889]="*Nanu vuttaṃ bhagavatā—**Did not the Buddha say that*";
P_HTM[6890]="*“cattārimāni, bhikkhave, adhikaraṇāni, satta samathā.**there are four kinds of legal issues and seven principles for settling.*";
P_HTM[6891]="*Adhikaraṇā samathehi sammanti, samathā adhikaraṇehi sammanti.**Legal issues are settled through the principles for settling; the principles for settling are settled through legal issues.*";
P_HTM[6892]="*Evaṃ, ime dhammā saṃsaṭṭhā no visaṃsaṭṭhā;**In this way they are connected, not disconnected.*";
P_HTM[6893]="*no ca labbhā imesaṃ dhammānaṃ vinibbhujitvā vinibbhujitvā nānākaraṇaṃ paññāpetun”ti.**It is not possible to completely separate them and point to their difference.”*";
P_HTM[6894]="*Saṃsaṭṭhavāro niṭṭhito soḷasamo.**The sixteenth section on connection is finished.*";
P_HTM[6895]="*12. Sammativāra**12. The section on settling*";
P_HTM[6896]="*Vivādādhikaraṇaṃ katihi samathehi sammati?**Through how many principles is a legal issue arising from a dispute settled?*";
P_HTM[6897]="*Anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ katihi samathehi sammati?**Through how many principles is a legal issue arising from an accusation settled?*";
P_HTM[6898]="*Āpattādhikaraṇaṃ katihi samathehi sammati?**Through how many principles is a legal issue arising from an offense settled?*";
P_HTM[6899]="*Kiccādhikaraṇaṃ katihi samathehi sammati?**Through how many principles is a legal issue arising from business settled?*";
P_HTM[6900]="*Vivādādhikaraṇaṃ dvīhi samathehi sammati—**A legal issue arising from a dispute is settled through two principles:*";
P_HTM[6901]="*sammukhāvinayena ca yebhuyyasikāya ca.**through resolution face-to-face and through a majority decision.*";
P_HTM[6902]="*Anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ catūhi samathehi sammati—**A legal issue arising from an accusation is settled is settled through four principles:*";
P_HTM[6903]="*sammukhāvinayena ca sativinayena ca amūḷhavinayena ca tassapāpiyasikāya ca.**through resolution face-to-face, through resolution through recollection, through resolution because of past insanity, and through a further penalty.*";
P_HTM[6904]="*Āpattādhikaraṇaṃ tīhi samathehi sammati—**A legal issue arising from an offense is settled is settled through three principles:*";
P_HTM[6905]="*sammukhāvinayena ca paṭiññātakaraṇena ca tiṇavatthārakena ca.**through resolution face-to-face, through acting according to what has been admitted, and through covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[6906]="*Kiccādhikaraṇaṃ ekena samathena sammati—**A legal issue arising from business is settled is settled in one way:*";
P_HTM[6907]="*sammukhāvinayena.**through resolution face-to-face.*";
P_HTM[6908]="*Vivādādhikaraṇañca anuvādādhikaraṇañca katihi samathehi sammanti?**In how many ways is a legal issue arising from a dispute and a legal issue arising from an accusation settled?*";
P_HTM[6909]="*Vivādādhikaraṇañca anuvādādhikaraṇañca pañcahi samathehi sammanti—**In five ways:*";
P_HTM[6910]="*sammukhāvinayena ca yebhuyyasikāya ca sativinayena ca amūḷhavinayena ca tassapāpiyasikāya ca.**through resolution face-to-face, through majority decision, through resolution through recollection, through resolution because of past insanity, and through further penalty.*";
P_HTM[6911]="*Vivādādhikaraṇañca āpattādhikaraṇañca katihi samathehi sammanti?**In how many ways is a legal issue arising from a dispute and a legal issue arising from an offense settled?*";
P_HTM[6912]="*Vivādādhikaraṇañca āpattādhikaraṇañca catūhi samathehi sammanti—**In four ways:*";
P_HTM[6913]="*sammukhāvinayena ca yebhuyyasikāya ca paṭiññātakaraṇena ca tiṇavatthārakena ca.**through resolution face-to-face, through majority decision, through acting according to what has been admitted, and through covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[6914]="*Vivādādhikaraṇañca kiccādhikaraṇañca katihi samathehi sammanti?**In how many ways is a legal issue arising from a dispute and a legal issue arising from business settled?*";
P_HTM[6915]="*Vivādādhikaraṇañca kiccādhikaraṇañca dvīhi samathehi sammanti—**In two ways:*";
P_HTM[6916]="*sammukhāvinayena ca yebhuyyasikāya ca.**through resolution face-to-face, and through majority decision.*";
P_HTM[6917]="*Anuvādādhikaraṇañca āpattādhikaraṇañca katihi samathehi sammanti?**In how many ways is a legal issue arising from an accusation and a legal issue arising from an offense settled?*";
P_HTM[6918]="*Anuvādādhikaraṇañca āpattādhikaraṇañca chahi samathehi sammanti—**In six ways:*";
P_HTM[6919]="*sammukhāvinayena ca sativinayena ca amūḷhavinayena ca paṭiññātakaraṇena ca tassapāpiyasikāya ca tiṇavatthārakena ca.**through resolution face-to-face, through resolution through recollection, through resolution because of past insanity, through acting according to what has been admitted, through further penalty, and through covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[6920]="*Anuvādādhikaraṇañca kiccādhikaraṇañca katihi samathehi sammanti?**In how many ways is a legal issue arising from an accusation and a legal issue arising from business settled?*";
P_HTM[6921]="*Anuvādādhikaraṇañca kiccādhikaraṇañca catūhi samathehi sammanti—**In four ways:*";
P_HTM[6922]="*sammukhāvinayena ca sativinayena ca amūḷhavinayena ca tassapāpiyasikāya ca.**through resolution face-to-face, through resolution through recollection, through resolution because of past insanity, and through further penalty.*";
P_HTM[6923]="*Āpattādhikaraṇañca kiccādhikaraṇañca katihi samathehi sammanti?**In how many ways is a legal issue arising from an offense and a legal issue arising from business settled?*";
P_HTM[6924]="*Āpattādhikaraṇañca kiccādhikaraṇañca tīhi samathehi sammanti—**In three ways:*";
