P_HTM[7046]="*Sativinayo vivādādhikaraṇena na sammati, anuvādādhikaraṇena na sammati, āpattādhikaraṇena na sammati;**(c) Resolution through recollection is not settled through a legal issue arising from a dispute, a legal issue arising from an accusation, or a legal issue arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[7047]="*kiccādhikaraṇena sammati.**It is settled through a legal issue arising from business.*";
P_HTM[7048]="*Amūḷhavinayo vivādādhikaraṇena na sammati, anuvādādhikaraṇena na sammati, āpattādhikaraṇena na sammati;**(d) Resolution because of past insanity is not settled through a legal issue arising from a dispute, a legal issue arising from an accusation, or a legal issue arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[7049]="*kiccādhikaraṇena sammati.**It is settled through a legal issue arising from business.*";
P_HTM[7050]="*Paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ vivādādhikaraṇena na sammati, anuvādādhikaraṇena na sammati, āpattādhikaraṇena na sammati;**(e) Acting according to what has been admitted is not settled through a legal issue arising from a dispute, a legal issue arising from an accusation, or a legal issue arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[7051]="*kiccādhikaraṇena sammati.**It is settled through a legal issue arising from business.*";
P_HTM[7052]="*Tassapāpiyasikā vivādādhikaraṇena na sammati, anuvādādhikaraṇena na sammati, āpattādhikaraṇena na sammati;**(f) A further penalty is not settled through a legal issue arising from a dispute, a legal issue arising from an accusation, or a legal issue arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[7053]="*kiccādhikaraṇena sammati.**It is settled through a legal issue arising from business.*";
P_HTM[7054]="*Tiṇavatthārako vivādādhikaraṇena na sammati, anuvādādhikaraṇena na sammati, āpattādhikaraṇena na sammati;**(g) Covering over as if with grass is not settled through a legal issue arising from a dispute, a legal issue arising from an accusation, or a legal issue arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[7055]="*kiccādhikaraṇena sammati.**It is settled through a legal issue arising from business.*";
P_HTM[7056]="*Evaṃ siyā samathā adhikaraṇehi sammanti.* **";
P_HTM[7057]="*Evaṃ siyā samathā adhikaraṇehi na sammanti.* **";
P_HTM[7058]="*Kathaṃ siyā adhikaraṇā samathehi sammanti, kathaṃ siyā adhikaraṇā samathehi na sammanti?**How may it be that legal issues are settled through principles for settling? How may it be that legal issues are not settled through principles for settling?*";
P_HTM[7059]="*Vivādādhikaraṇaṃ sammukhāvinayena ca yebhuyyasikāya ca sammati;**(a) A legal issue arising from a dispute is settled though resolution face-to-face and through majority decision.*";
P_HTM[7060]="*sativinayena ca amūḷhavinayena ca paṭiññātakaraṇena ca tassapāpiyasikāya ca tiṇavatthārakena ca na sammati.**It is not settled through resolution through recollection, through resolution because of past insanity, through acting according to what has been admitted, through further penalty, or through covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[7061]="*Anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ sammukhāvinayena ca sativinayena ca amūḷhavinayena ca tassapāpiyasikāya ca sammati;**(b) A legal issue arising from an accusation is settled though resolution face-to-face, though resolution through recollection, though resolution because of past insanity, and though further penalty.*";
P_HTM[7062]="*yebhuyyasikāya ca paṭiññātakaraṇena ca tiṇavatthārakena ca na sammati.**It is not settled through majority decision, through acting according to what has been admitted, or through covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[7063]="*Āpattādhikaraṇaṃ sammukhāvinayena ca paṭiññātakaraṇena ca tiṇavatthārakena ca sammati;**(c) A legal issue arising from an offense is settled though resolution face-to-face, through acting according to what has been admitted, and through covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[7064]="*yebhuyyasikāya ca sativinayena ca amūḷhavinayena ca tassapāpiyasikāya ca na sammati.**It is not settled through majority decision, though resolution through recollection, though resolution because of past insanity, or though further penalty.*";
P_HTM[7065]="*Kiccādhikaraṇaṃ sammukhāvinayena sammati;**(d) A legal issue arising from business is settled though resolution face-to-face.*";
P_HTM[7066]="*yebhuyyasikāya ca sativinayena ca amūḷhavinayena ca paṭiññātakaraṇena ca tassapāpiyasikāya ca tiṇavatthārakena ca na sammati.**It is not settled through majority decision, through resolution through recollection, through resolution because of past insanity, through acting according to what has been admitted, through further penalty, or through covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[7067]="*Evaṃ siyā adhikaraṇā samathehi sammanti.* **";
P_HTM[7068]="*Evaṃ siyā adhikaraṇā samathehi na sammanti.* **";
P_HTM[7069]="*Kathaṃ siyā adhikaraṇā adhikaraṇehi sammanti? Kathaṃ siyā adhikaraṇā adhikaraṇehi na sammanti?**How may it be that legal issues are settled through legal issues? How may it be that legal issues are not settled through legal issues?*";
P_HTM[7070]="*Vivādādhikaraṇaṃ vivādādhikaraṇena na sammati, anuvādādhikaraṇena na sammati, āpattādhikaraṇena na sammati;**(a) A legal issue arising from a dispute is not settled through a legal issue arising from a dispute, through a legal issue arising from an accusation, or through a legal issue arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[7071]="*kiccādhikaraṇena sammati.**It is settled through a legal issue arising from business.*";
P_HTM[7072]="*Anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ vivādādhikaraṇena na sammati, anuvādādhikaraṇena na sammati, āpattādhikaraṇena na sammati;**(b) A legal issue arising from an accusation is not settled through a legal issue arising from a dispute, through a legal issue arising from an accusation, or through a legal issue arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[7073]="*kiccādhikaraṇena sammati.**It is settled through a legal issue arising from business.*";
P_HTM[7074]="*Āpattādhikaraṇaṃ vivādādhikaraṇena na sammati, anuvādādhikaraṇena na sammati, āpattādhikaraṇena na sammati;**(c) A legal issue arising from an offense is not settled through a legal issue arising from a dispute, through a legal issue arising from an accusation, or through a legal issue arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[7075]="*kiccādhikaraṇena sammati.**It is settled through a legal issue arising from business.*";
P_HTM[7076]="*Kiccādhikaraṇaṃ vivādādhikaraṇena na sammati, anuvādādhikaraṇena na sammati, āpattādhikaraṇena na sammati;**(d) A legal issue arising from business is not settled through a legal issue arising from a dispute, through a legal issue arising from an accusation, or through a legal issue arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[7077]="*kiccādhikaraṇena sammati.**It is settled through a legal issue arising from business.*";
P_HTM[7078]="*Evaṃ siyā adhikaraṇā adhikaraṇehi sammanti.* **";
P_HTM[7079]="*Evaṃ siyā adhikaraṇā adhikaraṇehi na sammanti.* **";
P_HTM[7080]="*Chāpi samathā cattāropi adhikaraṇā sammukhāvinayena sammanti;**Six principles for settling and the four legal issues are settled through resolution face-to-face.*";
P_HTM[7081]="*sammukhāvinayo na kenaci sammati.**Resolution face-to-face is not settled through anything.*";
P_HTM[7082]="*Samathādhikaraṇavāro niṭṭhito ekūnavīsatimo.**The nineteenth section on principles for settling and legal issues is finished.*";
P_HTM[7083]="*15. Samuṭṭhāpanavāra**15. The section on causing to originate*";
P_HTM[7084]="*Vivādādhikaraṇaṃ catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ samuṭṭhāpeti?**Which of the four legal issues cause the legal issue arising from a dispute to originate?*";
P_HTM[7085]="*Vivādādhikaraṇaṃ catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ na katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ samuṭṭhāpeti;**None of them.*";
P_HTM[7086]="*api ca vivādādhikaraṇapaccayā cattāro adhikaraṇā jāyanti.**Nevertheless, the four legal issues are produced from the legal issue arising from a dispute.*";
P_HTM[7087]="*Yathā kathaṃ viya?**How is that?*";
P_HTM[7088]="*Idha bhikkhū vivadanti—**It may be that monks are disputing, saying,*";
P_HTM[7089]="*“dhammo”ti vā, “adhammo”ti vā, “vinayo”ti vā, “avinayo”ti vā, “abhāsitaṃ alapitaṃ tathāgatenā”ti vā, “bhāsitaṃ lapitaṃ tathāgatenā”ti vā, “anāciṇṇaṃ tathāgatenā”ti vā, “āciṇṇaṃ tathāgatenā”ti vā, “apaññattaṃ tathāgatenā”ti vā, “paññattaṃ tathāgatenā”ti vā, “āpattī”ti vā, “anāpattī”ti vā, “lahukā āpattī”ti vā, “garukā āpattī”ti vā, “sāvasesā āpattī”ti vā, “anavasesā āpattī”ti vā, “duṭṭhullā āpattī”ti vā “aduṭṭhullā āpattī”ti vā.**‘This is the Teaching’, ‘This is contrary to the Teaching’, ‘This is the Monastic Law’, ‘This is contrary to the Monastic Law’, ‘This was spoken by the Buddha’, ‘This was not spoken by the Buddha’, ‘This was practiced by the Buddha’, ‘This was not practiced by the Buddha’, ‘This was laid down by the Buddha’, ‘This was not laid down by the Buddha’, ‘This is an offense’, ‘This is not an offense’, ‘This is a light offense’, ‘This is a heavy offense’, ‘This is a curable offense’, ‘This is an incurable offense’, ‘This is a grave offense’, or ‘This is a minor offense.’*";
P_HTM[7090]="*Yaṃ tattha bhaṇḍanaṃ kalaho viggaho vivādo nānāvādo aññathāvādo vipaccatāya vohāro medhakaṃ, idaṃ vuccati vivādādhikaraṇaṃ.**In regard to this, whatever quarreling, arguing, conflict, disputing, variety in opinion, difference in opinion, heated speech, or strife there is, this called a legal issue arising from a dispute.*";
P_HTM[7091]="*Vivādādhikaraṇe saṅgho vivadati.**When, during a legal issue arising from a dispute, the Sangha disputes, there is a legal issue arising from a dispute.*";
P_HTM[7092]="*Vivādādhikaraṇaṃ vivadamāno anuvadati.**When one who is disputing makes an accusation, there is an legal issue arising from an accusation.*";
P_HTM[7093]="*Anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ anuvadamāno āpattiṃ āpajjati āpattādhikaraṇaṃ.**When one who is accusing commits an offense, there is a legal issue arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[7094]="*Tāya āpattiyā saṅgho kammaṃ karoti kiccādhikaraṇaṃ.**When the Sangha does a legal procedure because of that offense, there is a legal issue arising from business.*";
P_HTM[7095]="*Evaṃ vivādādhikaraṇapaccayā cattāro adhikaraṇā jāyanti.* **";
P_HTM[7096]="*Anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ samuṭṭhāpeti?**Which of the four legal issues cause the legal issue arising from an accusation to originate?*";
P_HTM[7097]="*Anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ na katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ samuṭṭhāpeti;**None of them.*";
P_HTM[7098]="*api ca anuvādādhikaraṇapaccayā cattāro adhikaraṇā jāyanti.**Nevertheless, the four legal issues are produced from the legal issue arising from an accusation.*";
P_HTM[7099]="*Yathā kathaṃ viya?**How is that?*";
P_HTM[7100]="*Idha bhikkhū bhikkhuṃ anuvadanti sīlavipattiyā vā ācāravipattiyā vā diṭṭhivipattiyā vā ājīvavipattiyā vā.**It may be that the monks accuse a monk of failure in morality, failure in conduct, failure in view, or failure in livelihood.*";
P_HTM[7101]="*Yo tattha anuvādo anuvadanā anullapanā anubhaṇanā anusampavaṅkatā abbhussahanatā anubalappadānaṃ, idaṃ vuccati anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ.**In regard to this, whatever accusation, accusing, allegation, blame, taking sides because of friendship, taking part in the accusation, or supporting the accusation there is, this is called a legal issue arising from an accusation.*";
P_HTM[7102]="*Anuvādādhikaraṇe saṅgho vivadati.**When, during a legal issue arising from an accusation, the Sangha disputes, there is a legal issue arising from a dispute.*";
P_HTM[7103]="*Vivādādhikaraṇaṃ vivadamāno anuvadati.**When one who is disputing makes an accusation, there is an legal issue arising from an accusation.*";
P_HTM[7104]="*Anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ anuvadamāno āpattiṃ āpajjati āpattādhikaraṇaṃ.**When one who is accusing commits an offense, there is a legal issue arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[7105]="*Tāya āpattiyā saṅgho kammaṃ karoti kiccādhikaraṇaṃ.**When the Sangha does a legal procedure because of that offense, there is a legal issue arising from business.*";
P_HTM[7106]="*Evaṃ anuvādādhikaraṇapaccayā cattāro adhikaraṇā jāyanti.* **";
P_HTM[7107]="*Āpattādhikaraṇaṃ catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ samuṭṭhāpeti?**Which of the four legal issues cause the legal issue arising from an offense to originate?*";
P_HTM[7108]="*Āpattādhikaraṇaṃ catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ na katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ samuṭṭhāpeti;**None of them.*";
P_HTM[7109]="*api ca āpattādhikaraṇapaccayā cattāro adhikaraṇā jāyanti.**Nevertheless, the four legal issues are produced from the legal issue arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[7110]="*Yathā kathaṃ viya?**How is that?*";
P_HTM[7111]="*Pañcapi āpattikkhandhā āpattādhikaraṇaṃ, sattapi āpattikkhandhā āpattādhikaraṇaṃ, idaṃ vuccati āpattādhikaraṇaṃ.**There are legal issues arising from offenses because of the five classes of offenses, and there are legal issues arising from offenses because of the seven classes of offenses—these are called legal issues arising from offenses.*";
P_HTM[7112]="*Āpattādhikaraṇe saṅgho vivadati.**When, during a legal issue arising from an offense, the Sangha disputes, there is a legal issue arising from a dispute.*";
P_HTM[7113]="*Vivādādhikaraṇaṃ vivadamāno anuvadati.**When one who is disputing makes an accusation, there is an legal issue arising from an accusation.*";
P_HTM[7114]="*Anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ anuvadamāno āpattiṃ āpajjati āpattādhikaraṇaṃ.**When one who is accusing commits an offense, there is a legal issue arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[7115]="*Tāya āpattiyā saṅgho kammaṃ karoti kiccādhikaraṇaṃ.**When the Sangha does a legal procedure because of that offense, there is a legal issue arising from business.*";
P_HTM[7116]="*Evaṃ āpattādhikaraṇapaccayā cattāro adhikaraṇā jāyanti.* **";
P_HTM[7117]="*Kiccādhikaraṇaṃ catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ samuṭṭhāpeti?**Which of the four legal issues cause the legal issue arising from business to originate?*";
P_HTM[7118]="*Kiccādhikaraṇaṃ catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ na katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ samuṭṭhāpeti,**None of them.*";
P_HTM[7119]="*api ca kiccādhikaraṇapaccayā cattāro adhikaraṇā jāyanti.**Nevertheless, the four legal issues are produced from the legal issue arising from business.*";
P_HTM[7120]="*Yathā kathaṃ viya?**How is that?*";
P_HTM[7121]="*Yā saṅghassa kiccayatā karaṇīyatā apalokanakammaṃ ñattikammaṃ ñattidutiyakammaṃ ñatticatutthakammaṃ, idaṃ vuccati kiccādhikaraṇaṃ.**Whatever is the duty or the business of the Sangha—a legal procedure consisting of getting permission, a legal procedure consisting of one motion, a legal procedure consisting of one motion and one announcement, a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements—this is called a legal issue arising from business.*";
P_HTM[7122]="*Kiccādhikaraṇe saṅgho vivadati.**When, during a legal issue arising from business, the Sangha disputes, there is a legal issue arising from a dispute.*";
P_HTM[7123]="*Vivādādhikaraṇaṃ vivadamāno anuvadati.**When one who is disputing makes an accusation, there is an legal issue arising from an accusation.*";
P_HTM[7124]="*Anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ anuvadamāno āpattiṃ āpajjati āpattādhikaraṇaṃ.**When one who is accusing commits an offense, there is a legal issue arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[7125]="*Tāya āpattiyā saṅgho kammaṃ karoti kiccādhikaraṇaṃ.**When the Sangha does a legal procedure because of that offense, there is a legal issue arising from business.*";
P_HTM[7126]="*Evaṃ kiccādhikaraṇapaccayā cattāro adhikaraṇā jāyanti.* **";
P_HTM[7127]="*Samuṭṭhāpanavāro niṭṭhito vīsatimo.**The twentieth section on causing to originate is finished.*";
P_HTM[7128]="*16. Bhajativāra**16. The section on “belonging to”*";
P_HTM[7129]="*Vivādādhikaraṇaṃ catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ bhajati?**To which of the four legal issues does a legal issue arising from a dispute belong?*";
P_HTM[7130]="*Katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ upanissitaṃ?**Which legal issue does it depend on?*";
P_HTM[7131]="*Katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ pariyāpannaṃ?**Which legal issue is it included in?*";
P_HTM[7132]="*Katamena adhikaraṇena saṅgahitaṃ?**Which legal issue is it grouped with?*";
P_HTM[7133]="*Anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ bhajati?**To which of the four legal issues does a legal issue arising from an accusation dispute belong?*";
P_HTM[7134]="*Katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ upanissitaṃ?**Which legal issue does it depend on?*";
P_HTM[7135]="*Katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ pariyāpannaṃ?**Which legal issue is it included in?*";
P_HTM[7136]="*Katamena adhikaraṇena saṅgahitaṃ?**Which legal issue is it grouped with?*";
P_HTM[7137]="*Āpattādhikaraṇaṃ catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ bhajati?**To which of the four legal issues does a legal issue arising from an offense belong?*";
P_HTM[7138]="*Katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ upanissitaṃ?**Which legal issue does it depend on?*";
P_HTM[7139]="*Katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ pariyāpannaṃ?**Which legal issue is it included in?*";
P_HTM[7140]="*Katamena adhikaraṇena saṅgahitaṃ?**Which legal issue is it grouped with?*";
P_HTM[7141]="*Kiccādhikaraṇaṃ catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ bhajati?**To which of the four legal issues does a legal issue arising from business belong?*";
P_HTM[7142]="*Katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ upanissitaṃ?**Which legal issue does it depend on?*";
P_HTM[7143]="*Katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ pariyāpannaṃ?**Which legal issue is it included in?*";
P_HTM[7144]="*Katamena adhikaraṇena saṅgahitaṃ?**Which legal issue is it grouped with?*";
P_HTM[7145]="*Vivādādhikaraṇaṃ catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ vivādādhikaraṇaṃ bhajati, vivādādhikaraṇaṃ upanissitaṃ, vivādādhikaraṇaṃ pariyāpannaṃ, vivādādhikaraṇena saṅgahitaṃ.**A legal issue arising from a dispute belongs to legal issues arising from disputes; it depends on legal issues arising from disputes; it is included in legal issues arising from disputes; it is grouped with legal issues arising from disputes.*";
P_HTM[7146]="*Anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ bhajati, anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ upanissitaṃ, anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ pariyāpannaṃ, anuvādādhikaraṇena saṅgahitaṃ.**A legal issue arising from an accusation belongs to legal issues arising from accusations; it depends on legal issues arising from accusations; it is included in legal issues arising from accusations; it is grouped with legal issues arising from accusations.*";
P_HTM[7147]="*Āpattādhikaraṇaṃ catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ āpattādhikaraṇaṃ bhajati, āpattādhikaraṇaṃ upanissitaṃ, āpattādhikaraṇaṃ pariyāpannaṃ, āpattādhikaraṇena saṅgahitaṃ.**A legal issue arising from an offense belongs to legal issues arising from offenses; it depends on legal issues arising from offenses; it is included in legal issues arising from offenses; it is grouped with legal issues arising from offenses.*";
P_HTM[7148]="*Kiccādhikaraṇaṃ catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ kiccādhikaraṇaṃ bhajati, kiccādhikaraṇaṃ upanissitaṃ, kiccādhikaraṇaṃ pariyāpannaṃ, kiccādhikaraṇena saṅgahitaṃ.**A legal issue arising from business belongs to legal issues arising from business; it depends on legal issues arising from business; it is included in legal issues arising from business; it is grouped with legal issues arising from business.*";
P_HTM[7149]="*Vivādādhikaraṇaṃ sattannaṃ samathānaṃ kati samathe bhajati, kati samathe upanissitaṃ, kati samathe pariyāpannaṃ, katihi samathehi saṅgahitaṃ, katihi samathehi sammati?**To how many of the seven principles for settling does a legal issue arising from a dispute belong? On how many principles for settling does it depend? In how many principles for settling is it included? With how many principles for settling is it grouped? Through how many principles for settling is it settled?*";
P_HTM[7150]="*Anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ sattannaṃ samathānaṃ kati samathe bhajati, kati samathe upanissitaṃ, kati samathe pariyāpannaṃ, katihi samathehi saṅgahitaṃ, katihi samathehi sammati?**To how many of the seven principles for settling does a legal issue arising from an accusation belong? On how many principles for settling does it depend? In how many principles for settling is it included? With how many principles for settling is it grouped? Through how many principles for settling is it settled?*";
P_HTM[7151]="*Āpattādhikaraṇaṃ sattannaṃ samathānaṃ kati samathe bhajati, kati samathe upanissitaṃ, kati samathe pariyāpannaṃ, katihi samathehi saṅgahitaṃ, katihi samathehi sammati?**To how many of the seven principles for settling does a legal issue arising from an offense belong? On how many principles for settling does it depend? In how many principles for settling is it included? With how many principles for settling is it grouped? Through how many principles for settling is it settled?*";
P_HTM[7152]="*Kiccādhikaraṇaṃ sattannaṃ samathānaṃ kati samathe bhajati, kati samathe upanissitaṃ, kati samathe pariyāpannaṃ, katihi samathehi saṅgahitaṃ, katihi samathehi sammati?**To how many of the seven principles for settling does a legal issue arising from business belong? On how many principles for settling does it depend? In how many principles for settling is it included? With how many principles for settling is it grouped? Through how many principles for settling is it settled?*";
P_HTM[7153]="*Vivādādhikaraṇaṃ sattannaṃ samathānaṃ dve samathe bhajati, dve samathe upanissitaṃ, dve samathe pariyāpannaṃ, dvīhi samathehi saṅgahitaṃ, dvīhi samathehi sammati—**A legal issue arising from a dispute belongs to two principles for settling; it depends on two principles for settling; it is included in two principles for settling; it is grouped with two principles for settling; it is settled through two principles for settling:*";
P_HTM[7154]="*sammukhāvinayena ca yebhuyyasikāya ca.**through resolution face-to-face and through majority decision.*";
P_HTM[7155]="*Anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ sattannaṃ samathānaṃ cattāro samathe bhajati, cattāro samathe upanissitaṃ, cattāro samathe pariyāpannaṃ, catūhi samathehi saṅgahitaṃ, catūhi samathehi sammati—**A legal issue arising from an accusation belongs to four principles for settling; it depends on four principles for settling; it is included in four principles for settling; it is grouped with four principles for settling; it is settled through four principles for settling:*";
P_HTM[7156]="*sammukhāvinayena ca sativinayena ca amūḷhavinayena ca tassapāpiyasikāya ca.**through resolution face-to-face, through resolution through recollection, through resolution because of past insanity, and through further penalty.*";
P_HTM[7157]="*Āpattādhikaraṇaṃ sattannaṃ samathānaṃ tayo samathe bhajati, tayo samathe upanissitaṃ, tayo samathe pariyāpannaṃ, tīhi samathehi saṅgahitaṃ tīhi samathehi sammati—**A legal issue arising from an offense belongs to three principles for settling; it depends on three principles for settling; it is included in three principles for settling; it is grouped with three principles for settling; it is settled through three principles for settling:*";
P_HTM[7158]="*sammukhāvinayena ca paṭiññātakaraṇena ca tiṇavatthārakena ca.**through resolution face-to-face, through acting according to what has been admitted, and through covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[7159]="*Kiccādhikaraṇaṃ sattannaṃ samathānaṃ ekaṃ samathaṃ bhajati, ekaṃ samathaṃ upanissitaṃ, ekaṃ samathaṃ pariyāpannaṃ, ekena samathena saṅgahitaṃ, ekena samathena sammati—**A legal issue arising from business belongs to one way of settling; it depends on one way of settling; it is included in one way of settling; it is grouped with one way of settling; it is settled through one way of settling:*";
P_HTM[7160]="*sammukhāvinayenāti.**through resolution face-to-face.*";
P_HTM[7161]="*Bhajativāro niṭṭhito ekavīsatimo.**The twenty-first section on “belonging to” is finished.*";
P_HTM[7162]="*Samathabhedo niṭṭhito.**The sub-division on settling is finished.*";
