P_HTM[7311]="*Thullavajjā āpatti jānitabbā.**Heavy offenses should be known.*";
P_HTM[7312]="*Athullavajjā āpatti jānitabbā.**Light offenses should be known.*";
P_HTM[7313]="*Gihipaṭisaṃyuttā āpatti jānitabbā.**Offenses connected with householders should be known.*";
P_HTM[7314]="*Na gihipaṭisaṃyuttā āpatti jānitabbā.**Offenses not connected with householders should be known.*";
P_HTM[7315]="*Niyatā āpatti jānitabbā.**Offenses with a fixed rebirth should be known.*";
P_HTM[7316]="*Aniyatā āpatti jānitabbā.**Offenses with an indeterminate rebirth should be known.*";
P_HTM[7317]="*Ādikaro puggalo jānitabbo.**The person who is the first offender should be known.*";
P_HTM[7318]="*Anādikaro puggalo jānitabbo.**The subsequent offenders should be known.*";
P_HTM[7319]="*Adhiccāpattiko puggalo jānitabbo.**The occasional offender should be known.*";
P_HTM[7320]="*Abhiṇhāpattiko puggalo jānitabbo.**The frequent offender should be known.*";
P_HTM[7321]="*Codako puggalo jānitabbo.**The accusing person should be known.*";
P_HTM[7322]="*Cuditako puggalo jānitabbo.**The accused person should be known.*";
P_HTM[7323]="*Adhammacodako puggalo jānitabbo.**The person who accuses illegitimately should be known.*";
P_HTM[7324]="*Adhammacuditako puggalo jānitabbo.**The person who is accused illegitimately should be known.*";
P_HTM[7325]="*Dhammacodako puggalo jānitabbo.**The person who accuses legitimately should be known.*";
P_HTM[7326]="*Dhammacuditako puggalo jānitabbo.**The person who is accused legitimately should be known.*";
P_HTM[7327]="*Niyato puggalo jānitabbo.**The person with a fixed future should be known.*";
P_HTM[7328]="*Aniyato puggalo jānitabbo.**The person with an indeterminate future should be known.*";
P_HTM[7329]="*Abhabbāpattiko puggalo jānitabbo.**The person incapable of an offense should be known.*";
P_HTM[7330]="*Bhabbāpattiko puggalo jānitabbo.**The person capable of an offense should be known.*";
P_HTM[7331]="*Ukkhittako puggalo jānitabbo.**The ejected person should be known.*";
P_HTM[7332]="*Anukkhittako puggalo jānitabbo.**The unejected person should be known.*";
P_HTM[7333]="*Nāsitako puggalo jānitabbo.**The expelled person should be known.*";
P_HTM[7334]="*Anāsitako puggalo jānitabbo.**The unexpelled person should be known.*";
P_HTM[7335]="*Samānasaṃvāsako puggalo jānitabbo.**The person who belongs to the same Buddhist sect should be known.*";
P_HTM[7336]="*Asamānasaṃvāsako puggalo jānitabbo.**The person who belongs to a different Buddhist sect should be known.*";
P_HTM[7337]="*Ṭhapanaṃ jānitabbanti.**Cancellation should be known.”*";
P_HTM[7338]="*Ekakaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The section on ones is finished.*";
P_HTM[7339]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[7340]="*Karā āpatti lahukā,**“That produce, offense, light,*";
P_HTM[7341]="*sāvasesā ca duṭṭhullā;**And curable, grave;*";
P_HTM[7342]="*Paṭikammadesanā ca,**Making amends, and confession,*";
P_HTM[7343]="*antarā vajjakiriyaṃ.**Obstructive, blameworthy, action.*";
P_HTM[7344]="*Kiriyākiriyaṃ pubbā,**Both an action and a non-action, initial,*";
P_HTM[7345]="*Antarā gaṇanūpagā;**While making amends, fit to be counted;*";
P_HTM[7346]="*Paññatti anānuppanna,**Rule, unprompted,*";
P_HTM[7347]="*Sabbasādhāraṇā ca ekato.**Everywhere, and in common, for one Sangha.*";
P_HTM[7348]="*Thullagihiniyatā ca,**Heavy, householder, and fixed,*";
P_HTM[7349]="*ādi adhiccacodako;**First, occasional, accusing;*";
P_HTM[7350]="*Adhammadhammaniyato,**Illegitimately, legitimately, fixed,*";
P_HTM[7351]="*abhabbokkhittanāsitā;**Incapable, ejected, expelled;*";
P_HTM[7352]="*Samānaṃ ṭhapanañceva,**The same, and cancellation:*";
P_HTM[7353]="*uddānaṃ ekake idanti.**This is the summary of the ones.”*";
P_HTM[7354]="*2. Dukavāra**2. The section on twos*";
P_HTM[7355]="*Atthāpatti saññā vimokkhā, atthāpatti no saññāvimokkhā.**There are offenses for which perception is a factor, and offenses for which it is not.*";
P_HTM[7356]="*Atthāpatti laddhasamāpattikassa, atthāpatti na laddhasamāpattikassa.**There are offenses for which the attainment has been achieved, and offenses for which it has not.*";
P_HTM[7357]="*Atthāpatti saddhammapaṭisaññuttā, atthāpatti asaddhammapaṭisaññuttā.**There are offenses that are connected with the true Teaching, and offenses that are not.*";
P_HTM[7358]="*Atthāpatti saparikkhārapaṭisaññuttā, atthāpatti paraparikkhārapaṭisaññuttā.**There are offenses that are connected with one’s own requisites, and offenses that are connected with someone else’s requisites.*";
P_HTM[7359]="*Atthāpatti sapuggalapaṭisaññuttā, atthāpatti parapuggalapaṭisaññuttā.**There are offenses that are connected with oneself, and offenses that are connected others.*";
P_HTM[7360]="*Atthi saccaṃ bhaṇanto garukaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati, musā bhaṇanto lahukaṃ.**There are heavy offenses committed by one speaking the truth, and light offenses committed by one speaking falsely.*";
P_HTM[7361]="*Atthi musā bhaṇanto garukaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati, saccaṃ bhaṇanto lahukaṃ.**There are heavy offenses committed by one speaking falsely, and light offenses committed by one speaking the truth.*";
P_HTM[7362]="*Atthāpatti bhūmigato āpajjati, no vehāsagato.**There are offenses committed by one on the ground, not by one above ground.*";
P_HTM[7363]="*Atthāpatti vehāsagato āpajjati, no bhūmigato.**There are offenses committed by one above ground, not by one on the ground.*";
P_HTM[7364]="*Atthāpatti nikkhamanto āpajjati, no pavisanto.**There are offenses committed by one who is leaving, not by one who is entering.*";
P_HTM[7365]="*Atthāpatti pavisanto āpajjati, no nikkhamanto.**There are offenses committed by one who is entering, not by one who is leaving.*";
P_HTM[7366]="*Atthāpatti ādiyanto āpajjati, atthāpatti anādiyanto āpajjati.**There are offenses committed by applying, and offenses committed by not applying.*";
P_HTM[7367]="*Atthāpatti samādiyanto āpajjati, atthāpatti na samādiyanto āpajjati.**There are offenses committed by undertaking, and offenses committed by not undertaking.*";
P_HTM[7368]="*Atthāpatti karonto āpajjati, atthāpatti na karonto āpajjati.**There are offenses committed by doing, and offenses committed by not doing.*";
P_HTM[7369]="*Atthāpatti dento āpajjati, atthāpatti na dento āpajjati.**There are offenses committed by giving, and offenses committed by not giving.*";
P_HTM[7370]="*Atthāpatti desento āpajjati, atthāpatti na desento āpajjati.**There are offenses committed by teaching, and offenses committed by not teaching.*";
P_HTM[7371]="*Atthāpatti paṭiggaṇhanto āpajjati, atthāpatti na paṭiggaṇhanto āpajjati.**There are offenses committed by receiving, and offenses committed by not receiving.*";
P_HTM[7372]="*Atthāpatti paribhogena āpajjati, atthāpatti na paribhogena āpajjati.**There are offenses committed by means of equipment, and offenses committed not by means of equipment.*";
P_HTM[7373]="*Atthāpatti rattiṃ āpajjati, no divā.**There are offenses committed at night, not by day.*";
P_HTM[7374]="*Atthāpatti divā āpajjati, no rattiṃ.**There are offenses committed by day, not at night.*";
P_HTM[7375]="*Atthāpatti aruṇugge āpajjati, atthāpatti na aruṇugge āpajjati.**There are offenses committed at dawn, and offenses committed not at dawn.*";
P_HTM[7376]="*Atthāpatti chindanto āpajjati, atthāpatti na chindanto āpajjati.**There are offenses committed by cutting, and offenses committed by not cutting.*";
P_HTM[7377]="*Atthāpatti chādento āpajjati, atthāpatti na chādento āpajjati.**There are offenses committed by covering, and offenses committed by not covering.*";
P_HTM[7378]="*Atthāpatti dhārento āpajjati, atthāpatti na dhārento āpajjati.**There are offenses committed by wearing, and offenses committed by not wearing.*";
P_HTM[7379]="*Dve uposathā—**There are two observance days:*";
P_HTM[7380]="*cātuddasiko ca pannarasiko ca.**the fourteenth and the fifteenth.*";
P_HTM[7381]="*Dve pavāraṇā—**There are two invitation days:*";
P_HTM[7382]="*cātuddasikā ca pannarasikā ca.**the fourteenth and the fifteenth.*";
P_HTM[7383]="*Dve kammāni—**There are two legal procedures:*";
P_HTM[7384]="*apalokanakammaṃ, ñattikammaṃ.**the procedure consisting of getting permission, and the procedure consisting of one motion.*";
P_HTM[7385]="*Aparānipi dve kammāni—**There are two other legal procedures:*";
P_HTM[7386]="*ñattidutiyakammaṃ, ñatticatutthakammaṃ.**the procedure consisting of one motion and one announcement, and the procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements.*";
P_HTM[7387]="*Dve kammavatthūni—**There are two bases for legal procedures:*";
P_HTM[7388]="*apalokanakammassa vatthu, ñattikammassa vatthu.**the basis for the procedure consisting of getting permission, and the basis for the procedure consisting of one motion.*";
P_HTM[7389]="*Aparānipi dve kammavatthūni—**There are two other bases for legal procedures:*";
P_HTM[7390]="*ñattidutiyakammassa vatthu, ñatticatutthakammassa vatthu.**the basis for the procedure consisting of one motion and one announcement, and the basis for the procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements.*";
P_HTM[7391]="*Dve kammadosā—**There are two kinds of flaws in legal procedures:*";
P_HTM[7392]="*apalokanakammassa doso, ñattikammassa doso.**the flaw in a procedure consisting of getting permission, and the flaw in a procedure consisting of one motion.*";
P_HTM[7393]="*Aparepi dve kammadosā—**There are two other kinds of flaws in legal procedures:*";
P_HTM[7394]="*ñattidutiyakammassa doso, ñatticatutthakammassa doso.**the flaw in a procedure consisting of one motion and one announcement, and the flaw in a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements.*";
P_HTM[7395]="*Dve kammasampattiyo—**There are two kinds of successes in legal procedures:*";
P_HTM[7396]="*apalokanakammassa sampatti, ñattikammassa sampatti.**the success of a procedure consisting of getting permission, and the success of a procedure consisting of one motion.*";
P_HTM[7397]="*Aparāpi dve kammasampattiyo—**There are two other kinds of successes in legal procedures:*";
P_HTM[7398]="*ñattidutiyakammassa sampatti, ñatticatutthakammassa sampatti.**the success of a procedure consisting of one motion and one announcement, and the success of a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements.*";
P_HTM[7399]="*Dve nānāsaṃvāsakabhūmiyo—**There are two grounds for belonging to a different Buddhist sect:*";
P_HTM[7400]="*attanā vā attānaṃ nānāsaṃvāsakaṃ karoti, samaggo vā naṃ saṅgho ukkhipati adassane vā appaṭikamme vā appaṭinissagge vā.**either one makes oneself belong to a different Buddhist sect, or a unanimous assembly ejects one for not recognizing an offense, for not making amends for an offense, or for not giving up a bad view.*";
P_HTM[7401]="*Dve samānasaṃvāsakabhūmiyo—**There are two grounds for belonging to the same Buddhist sect:*";
P_HTM[7402]="*attanā vā attānaṃ samānasaṃvāsakaṃ karoti, samaggo vā naṃ saṅgho ukkhittaṃ osāreti dassane vā paṭikamme vā paṭinissagge vā.**Either one makes oneself belong to the same Buddhist sect; or, in regard to one who had been ejected, a unanimous assembly re-admits them for recognizing an offense, for making amends for an offense, or for giving up a bad view.*";
P_HTM[7403]="*Dve pārājikā—**There are two kinds of offenses entailing expulsion:*";
P_HTM[7404]="*bhikkhūnañca bhikkhunīnañca.**for monks and for nuns.*";
P_HTM[7405]="*Dve saṅghādisesā, dve thullaccayā, dve pācittiyā, dve pāṭidesanīyā, dve dukkaṭā, dve dubbhāsitā—**There are two kinds of offenses entailing suspension, two kinds of serious offenses, two kinds of offenses entailing confession, two kinds of offenses entailing acknowledgment, two kinds of offenses of wrong conduct, two kinds of offenses of wrong speech:*";
P_HTM[7406]="*bhikkhūnañca bhikkhunīnañca.**for monks and for nuns.*";
P_HTM[7407]="*Satta āpattiyo, satta āpattikkhandhā.**There are seven kinds of offenses and seven classes of offenses.*";
P_HTM[7408]="*Dvīhākārehi saṅgho bhijjati—**Schism in the Sangha occurs in two ways:*";
P_HTM[7409]="*kammena vā salākaggāhena vā.**though a legal procedure or through a vote.*";
P_HTM[7410]="*Dve puggalā na upasampādetabbā—**Two kinds of people should not be given the full ordination:*";
P_HTM[7411]="*addhānahīno, aṅgahīno.**one lacking in age, and one lacking in limbs.*";
P_HTM[7412]="*Aparepi dve puggalā na upasampādetabbā—**Another two kinds of people should not be given the full ordination:*";
P_HTM[7413]="*vatthuvipanno, karaṇadukkaṭako.**one who is deficient as subject, and one who has acted wrongly.*";
P_HTM[7414]="*Aparepi dve puggalā na upasampādetabbā—**Another two kinds of people should not be given the full ordination:*";
P_HTM[7415]="*aparipūro paripūro no ca yācati.**one who is incomplete, and one is complete but has not asked.*";
P_HTM[7416]="*Dvinnaṃ puggalānaṃ nissāya na vatthabbaṃ—**One should not live with formal support from two kinds of persons:*";
P_HTM[7417]="*alajjissa ca bālassa ca.**one who is shameless, and on who is ignorant.*";
P_HTM[7418]="*Dvinnaṃ puggalānaṃ nissayo na dātabbo—**One should not give formal support to two kinds of people:*";
P_HTM[7419]="*alajjissa ca lajjino ca na yācati.**one who is shameless, and one who has a sense of conscience but who has not asked.*";
P_HTM[7420]="*Dvinnaṃ puggalānaṃ nissayo dātabbo—**One should give formal support to two kinds of people:*";
P_HTM[7421]="*bālassa ca lajjissa ca yācati.**one who is ignorant, and one who has a sense of conscience and who has asked.*";
P_HTM[7422]="*Dve puggalā abhabbā āpattiṃ āpajjituṃ—**Two kinds of people are incapable of committing an offense:*";
P_HTM[7423]="*buddhā ca paccekabuddhā ca.**Buddhas and solitary Buddhas.*";
P_HTM[7424]="*Dve puggalā bhabbā, āpattiṃ āpajjituṃ—**Two kinds of people are capable of committing an offense:*";
P_HTM[7425]="*bhikkhū ca bhikkhuniyo ca.**monks and nuns.*";
P_HTM[7426]="*Dve puggalā abhabbā sañcicca āpattiṃ āpajjituṃ—**Two kinds of people are incapable of intentionally committing an offense:*";
P_HTM[7427]="*bhikkhū ca bhikkhuniyo ca ariyapuggalā.**monks and nuns who are noble persons.*";
P_HTM[7428]="*Dve puggalā bhabbā sañcicca āpattiṃ āpajjituṃ—**Two kinds of people are capable of intentionally committing an offense:*";
P_HTM[7429]="*bhikkhū ca bhikkhuniyo ca puthujjanā.**monks and nuns who are ordinary persons.*";
P_HTM[7430]="*Dve puggalā abhabbā sañcicca sātisāraṃ vatthuṃ ajjhācarituṃ—**Two kinds of people are incapable of intentionally committing an action that goes too far:*";
P_HTM[7431]="*bhikkhū ca bhikkhuniyo ca ariyapuggalā.**monks and nuns who are noble persons.*";
P_HTM[7432]="*Dve puggalā bhabbā sañcicca sātisāraṃ vatthuṃ ajjhācarituṃ—**Two kinds of people are capable of intentionally committing an action that goes too far:*";
P_HTM[7433]="*bhikkhū ca bhikkhuniyo ca puthujjanā.**monks and nuns who are ordinary persons.*";
P_HTM[7434]="*Dve paṭikkosā—**There are two kinds of objections:*";
P_HTM[7435]="*kāyena vā paṭikkosati vācāya vā paṭikkosati.**one objects by body, or one objects by speech.*";
P_HTM[7436]="*Dve nissāraṇā—**There are two kinds of sending away:*";
P_HTM[7437]="*atthi puggalo appatto nissāraṇaṃ tañce saṅgho nissāreti ekacco sunissārito, ekacco dunnissārito.**if the Sangha sends away those who don’t have the attributes needed for being sent away, the sending away of some succeeds, while the sending away of others fails.*";
P_HTM[7438]="*Dve osāraṇā—**“There are two kinds of admittance:*";
P_HTM[7439]="*atthi puggalo appatto osāraṇaṃ tañce saṅgho osāreti ekacco sosārito, ekacco dosārito.**if the Sangha admits those who don’t have the attributes needed for being admitted, the admittance of some succeeds, while the admittance of others fails.*";
P_HTM[7440]="*Dve paṭiññā—**There are two kinds of admitting:*";
P_HTM[7441]="*kāyena vā paṭijānāti vācāya vā paṭijānāti.**one admits by body, or one admits by speech.*";
P_HTM[7442]="*Dve paṭiggahā—**There are two kinds of receiving:*";
P_HTM[7443]="*kāyena vā paṭiggaṇhāti kāyapaṭibaddhena vā paṭiggaṇhāti.**one receives by body, or one receives by what is connected to the body.*";
P_HTM[7444]="*Dve paṭikkhepā—**There are two kinds of prohibitions:*";
P_HTM[7445]="*kāyena vā paṭikkhipati vācāya vā paṭikkhipati.**one prohibits by body, or one prohibits by speech.*";
P_HTM[7446]="*Dve upaghātikā—**There are two kinds of harming:*";
P_HTM[7447]="*sikkhūpaghātikā ca bhogūpaghātikā ca.**harming of the training, and harming of possessions.*";
P_HTM[7448]="*Dve codanā—**There are two kinds of accusing:*";
P_HTM[7449]="*kāyena vā codeti vācāya vā codeti.**one accuses by body, or one accuses by speech.*";
P_HTM[7450]="*Dve kathinassa palibodhā—**There are two obstacles for the ending of the robe-making season:*";
P_HTM[7451]="*āvāsapalibodho ca cīvarapalibodho ca.**the monastery obstacle, and the robe obstacle.*";
P_HTM[7452]="*Dve kathinassa apalibodhā—**There are two removals of obstacles for the ending of the robe-making season:*";
P_HTM[7453]="*āvāsaapalibodho ca cīvaraapalibodho ca.**the removal of the monastery obstacle, and the removal of the robe obstacle.*";
P_HTM[7454]="*Dve cīvarāni—**There are two kinds of robes:*";
P_HTM[7455]="*gahapatikañca paṃsukūlañca.**from householders, and from rags.*";
P_HTM[7456]="*Dve pattā—**There are two kinds of almsbowls:*";
P_HTM[7457]="*ayopatto mattikāpatto.**iron bowls, and ceramic bowls.*";
P_HTM[7458]="*Dve maṇḍalāni—**There are two kinds of bowl stands:*";
P_HTM[7459]="*tipumayaṃ, sīsamayaṃ.**bowl stands made of tin, and a bowl stands made of lead.*";
P_HTM[7460]="*Dve pattassa adhiṭṭhānā—**There are two ways of determining an almsbowl:*";
P_HTM[7461]="*kāyena vā adhiṭṭheti vācāya vā adhiṭṭheti.**one determines it by body, or one determines it by speech.*";
P_HTM[7462]="*Dve cīvarassa adhiṭṭhānā—**There are two ways of determining a robe:*";
P_HTM[7463]="*kāyena vā adhiṭṭheti vācāya vā adhiṭṭheti.**one determines it by body, or one determines it by speech.*";
P_HTM[7464]="*Dve vikappanā—**There are two kinds of transfers:*";
P_HTM[7465]="*sammukhāvikappanā ca parammukhāvikappanā ca.**transfer face-to-face, and transfer in the absence of.*";
P_HTM[7466]="*Dve vinayā—**There are two Monastic Laws:*";
P_HTM[7467]="*bhikkhūnañca bhikkhunīnañca.**for the monks, and for the nuns.*";
P_HTM[7468]="*Dve venayikā—**There are two things that belong to the Monastic Law:*";
P_HTM[7469]="*paññattañca paññattānulomañca.**the rules, and what accords with the rules.*";
P_HTM[7470]="*Dve vinayassa sallekhā—**There are two kinds of eliminations of the Monastic Law:*";
P_HTM[7471]="*akappiye setughāto, kappiye mattakāritā.**ending access to what is unallowable, and moderation in what is allowable.*";
P_HTM[7472]="*Dvīhākārehi āpattiṃ āpajjati—**One commits an offense in two ways:*";
P_HTM[7473]="*kāyena vā āpajjati vācāya vā āpajjati.**one commits it by body, or one commits it by speech.*";
P_HTM[7474]="*Dvīhākārehi āpattiyā vuṭṭhāti—**One is cleared of an offense in two ways:*";
P_HTM[7475]="*kāyena vā vuṭṭhāti vācāya vā vuṭṭhāti.**one is cleared by body, or one is cleared by speech.*";
P_HTM[7476]="*Dve parivāsā—**There are two kinds of probation:*";
P_HTM[7477]="*paṭicchannaparivāso, appaṭicchannaparivāso.**probation for concealed offenses, and probation for unconcealed offenses.*";
P_HTM[7478]="*Aparepi dve parivāsā—**There are two other kinds of probation:*";
P_HTM[7479]="*suddhantaparivāso samodhānaparivāso.**purifying probation, and simultaneous probation.*";
P_HTM[7480]="*Dve mānattā—**There are two kinds of trial periods:*";
P_HTM[7481]="*paṭicchannamānattaṃ, appaṭicchannamānattaṃ.**trial periods for concealed offenses, and trial periods for unconcealed offenses.*";
P_HTM[7482]="*Aparepi dve mānattā—**There are two other kinds of trial periods:*";
P_HTM[7483]="*pakkhamānattaṃ, samodhānamānattaṃ.**trial periods for a half-month, and simultaneous trial periods.*";
P_HTM[7484]="*Dvinnaṃ puggalānaṃ ratticchedo—**Not counting a day is for two kinds of people:*";
P_HTM[7485]="*pārivāsikassa ca mānattacārikassa ca.**for one on probation, and for one undertaking the trial period.*";
P_HTM[7486]="*Dve anādariyāni—**There are two kinds of disrespect:*";
P_HTM[7487]="*puggalānādariyañca dhammānādariyañca.**disrespect for the person, and disrespect for the rule.*";
P_HTM[7488]="*Dve loṇāni—**There are two kinds of salt:*";
P_HTM[7489]="*jātimañca kārimañca.**natural, and produced.*";
P_HTM[7490]="*Aparānipi dve loṇāni—**There are two other kinds of salt:*";
P_HTM[7491]="*sāmuddaṃ kāḷaloṇaṃ.**sea salt, and black salt.*";
P_HTM[7492]="*Aparānipi dve loṇāni—**There are two other kinds of salt:*";
P_HTM[7493]="*sindhavaṃ, ubbhidaṃ.**hill salt, and soil salt.*";
P_HTM[7494]="*Aparānipi dve loṇāni—**There are two other kinds of salt:*";
P_HTM[7495]="*romakaṃ, pakkālakaṃ.**salt from the Roma country, and salty grain.*";
P_HTM[7496]="*Dve paribhogā—**There are two kinds of useful things:*";
P_HTM[7497]="*abbhantaraparibhogo ca bāhiraparibhogo ca.**internally useful things, and externally useful things.*";
P_HTM[7498]="*Dve akkosā—**There are two kinds of name-calling:*";
P_HTM[7499]="*hīno ca akkoso ukkaṭṭho ca akkoso.**low name-calling, and high name-calling.*";
P_HTM[7500]="*Dvīhākārehi pesuññaṃ hoti—**There is malicious talebearing in two ways:*";
P_HTM[7501]="*piyakamyassa vā bhedādhippāyassa vā.**for one wanting to endear himself or for one aiming at division.*";
P_HTM[7502]="*Dvīhākārehi gaṇabhojanaṃ pasavati—**Eating in a group comes about in two ways:*";
P_HTM[7503]="*nimantanato vā viññattito vā.**through an invitation, or through asking.*";
P_HTM[7504]="*Dve vassūpanāyikā—**There are two entries to the rainy-season residence:*";
P_HTM[7505]="*purimikā, pacchimikā.**the first and the second.*";
P_HTM[7506]="*Dve adhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni.**There are two kinds of illegitimate cancellations of the Monastic Code.*";
P_HTM[7507]="*Dve dhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni.**There are two kinds of legitimate cancellations of the Monastic Code.*";
P_HTM[7508]="*Dve puggalā bālā—**There are two kinds of fools:*";
P_HTM[7509]="*yo ca anāgataṃ bhāraṃ vahati, yo ca āgataṃ bhāraṃ na vahati.**one who takes on future responsibilities, and one who does not take on current responsibilities.*";
P_HTM[7510]="*Dve puggalā paṇḍitā—**There are two kinds of wise persons:*";
P_HTM[7511]="*yo ca anāgataṃ bhāraṃ na vahati, yo ca āgataṃ bhāraṃ vahati.**one who does not take on future responsibilities, and one who takes on current responsibilities.*";
P_HTM[7512]="*Aparepi dve puggalā bālā—**There are two other kinds of fools:*";
P_HTM[7513]="*yo ca akappiye kappiyasaññī, yo ca kappiye akappiyasaññī.**one who perceives what is unallowable as allowable, and one who perceives what is allowable as unallowable.*";
P_HTM[7514]="*Dve puggalā paṇḍitā—**There are two kinds of wise persons:*";
P_HTM[7515]="*yo ca akappiye akappiyasaññī, yo ca kappiye kappiyasaññī.**one who perceives what is unallowable as unallowable, and one who perceives what is allowable as allowable.*";
P_HTM[7516]="*Aparepi dve puggalā bālā—**There are two other kinds of fools:*";
P_HTM[7517]="*yo ca anāpattiyā āpattisaññī, yo ca āpattiyā anāpattisaññī.**one who perceives a non-offense as an offense, and one who perceives an offense as a non-offense.*";
P_HTM[7518]="*Dve puggalā paṇḍitā—**There are two kinds of wise persons:*";
P_HTM[7519]="*yo ca āpattiyā āpattisaññī, yo ca anāpattiyā anāpattisaññī.**one who perceives an offense as an offense, and one who perceives a non-offense as a non-offense.*";
P_HTM[7520]="*Aparepi dve puggalā bālā—**There are two other kinds of fools:*";
P_HTM[7521]="*yo ca adhamme dhammasaññī, yo ca dhamme adhammasaññī.**one who perceives what is contrary to the Teaching as the Teaching, and one who perceives what is the Teaching as contrary to the Teaching.*";
P_HTM[7522]="*Dve puggalā paṇḍitā—**There are two kinds of wise persons:*";
P_HTM[7523]="*yo ca adhamme adhammasaññī, yo ca dhamme dhammasaññī.**one who perceives what is contrary to the Teaching as contrary to the Teaching, and one who perceives what is the Teaching as the Teaching.*";
P_HTM[7524]="*Aparepi dve puggalā bālā—**There are two other kinds of fools:*";
P_HTM[7525]="*yo ca avinaye vinayasaññī, yo ca vinaye avinayasaññī.**one who perceives what is contrary to the Monastic Law as the Monastic Law, and one who perceives what is the Monastic Law as contrary to the Monastic Law.*";
P_HTM[7526]="*Dve puggalā paṇḍitā—**There are two kinds of wise persons:*";
P_HTM[7527]="*yo ca avinaye avinayasaññī, yo ca vinaye vinayasaññī.**one who perceives what is contrary to the Monastic Law as contrary to the Monastic Law, and one who perceives what is the Monastic Law as the Monastic Law.*";
P_HTM[7528]="*Dvinnaṃ puggalānaṃ āsavā vaḍḍhanti—**The corruptions increase for two kinds of persons:*";
P_HTM[7529]="*yo ca na kukkuccāyitabbaṃ kukkuccāyati, yo ca kukkuccāyitabbaṃ na kukkuccāyati.**one who is afraid of wrongdoing when one should not be, and one who is not afraid of wrongdoing when one should be.*";
P_HTM[7530]="*Dvinnaṃ puggalānaṃ āsavā na vaḍḍhanti—**The corruptions do not increase for two kinds of persons:*";
P_HTM[7531]="*yo ca na kukkuccāyitabbaṃ na kukkuccāyati, yo ca kukkuccāyitabbaṃ kukkuccāyati.**one who is not afraid of wrongdoing when one should not be, and one who is afraid of wrongdoing when one should be.*";
P_HTM[7532]="*Aparesampi dvinnaṃ puggalānaṃ āsavā vaḍḍhanti—**The corruptions increase for two other kinds of persons:*";
P_HTM[7533]="*yo ca akappiye kappiyasaññī, yo ca kappiye akappiyasaññī.**one who perceives what is unallowable as allowable, and one who perceives what is allowable as unallowable.*";
P_HTM[7534]="*Dvinnaṃ puggalānaṃ āsavā na vaḍḍhanti—**The corruptions do not increase for two other kinds of persons:*";
P_HTM[7535]="*yo ca akappiye akappiyasaññī, yo ca kappiye kappiyasaññī.**one who perceives what is unallowable as unallowable, and one who perceives what is allowable as allowable.*";
P_HTM[7536]="*Aparesampi dvinnaṃ puggalānaṃ āsavā vaḍḍhanti—**The corruptions increase for two other kinds of persons:*";
P_HTM[7537]="*yo ca anāpattiyā āpattisaññī, yo ca āpattiyā anāpattisaññī.**one who perceives a non-offense as an offense, and one who perceives an offense as a non-offense.*";
P_HTM[7538]="*Dvinnaṃ puggalānaṃ āsavā na vaḍḍhanti—**The corruptions do not increase for two other kinds of persons:*";
P_HTM[7539]="*yo ca anāpattiyā anāpattisaññī, yo ca āpattiyā āpattisaññī.**one who perceives a non-offense as a non-offense, and one who perceives an offense as an offense.*";
P_HTM[7540]="*Aparesampi dvinnaṃ puggalānaṃ āsavā vaḍḍhanti—**The corruptions increase for two other kinds of persons:*";
P_HTM[7541]="*yo ca adhamme dhammasaññī, yo ca dhamme adhammasaññī.**one who perceives what is contrary to the Teaching as the Teaching, and one who perceives what is the Teaching as contrary to the Teaching.*";
P_HTM[7542]="*Dvinnaṃ puggalānaṃ āsavā na vaḍḍhanti—**The corruptions do not increase for two other kinds of persons:*";
P_HTM[7543]="*yo ca adhamme adhammasaññī, yo ca dhamme dhammasaññī.**one who perceives what is contrary to the Teaching as contrary to the Teaching, and one who perceives what is the Teaching as the Teaching.*";
P_HTM[7544]="*Aparesampi dvinnaṃ puggalānaṃ āsavā vaḍḍhanti—**The corruptions increase for two other kinds of persons:*";
P_HTM[7545]="*yo ca avinaye vinayasaññī, yo ca vinaye avinayasaññī.**one who perceives what is contrary to the Monastic Law as the Monastic Law, and one who perceives what is the Monastic Law as contrary to the Monastic Law.*";
P_HTM[7546]="*Dvinnaṃ puggalānaṃ āsavā na vaḍḍhanti—**The corruptions do not increase for two other kinds of persons:*";
P_HTM[7547]="*yo ca avinaye avinayasaññī, yo ca vinaye vinayasaññī.**one who perceives what is contrary to the Monastic Law as contrary to the Monastic Law, and one who perceives what is the Monastic Law as the Monastic Law.*";
P_HTM[7548]="*Dukā niṭṭhitā.**The section on twos is finished.*";
P_HTM[7549]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[7550]="*Saññā laddhā ca saddhammā,**“Perception, and achieved, the true Teaching,*";
P_HTM[7551]="*parikkhārā ca puggalā;**And requisites, persons;*";
P_HTM[7552]="*Saccaṃ bhūmi nikkhamanto,**Truth, ground, leaving,*";
P_HTM[7553]="*ādiyanto samādiyaṃ.**Applying, undertaking.*";
P_HTM[7554]="*Karonto dento gaṇhanto,**Doing, giving, receiving,*";
P_HTM[7555]="*paribhogena ratti ca;**By equipment, and at night;*";
P_HTM[7556]="*Aruṇāchindaṃ chādento,**Dawn, cutting, covering,*";
P_HTM[7557]="*dhārento ca uposathā.**And wearing, observance days.*";
P_HTM[7558]="*Pavāraṇā kammāparā,**Invitation days, legal procedure, other,*";
P_HTM[7559]="*vatthu aparā dosā ca;**Basis, other, and flaw;*";
P_HTM[7560]="*Aparā dve ca sampatti,**Other, and two on success,*";
P_HTM[7561]="*nānā samānameva ca.**Different, and the same.*";
P_HTM[7562]="*Pārājisaṅghathullaccaya,**Expulsion, suspension, serious offense,*";
P_HTM[7563]="*pācitti pāṭidesanā;**Confession, acknowledgment;*";
P_HTM[7564]="*Dukkaṭā dubbhāsitā ceva,**Wrong conduct, and wrong speech,*";
P_HTM[7565]="*satta āpattikkhandhā ca.**Seven, and classes of offenses.*";
P_HTM[7566]="*Bhijjati upasampadā,**Schism, full ordination,*";
P_HTM[7567]="*tatheva apare duve;**And two other;*";
P_HTM[7568]="*Na vatthabbaṃ na dātabbaṃ,**Should not live, should not give,*";
P_HTM[7569]="*abhabbābhabbameva ca.**Incapable, and capable.*";
P_HTM[7570]="*Sañcicca sātisārā ca,**Intentionally, and goes too far,*";
P_HTM[7571]="*paṭikkosā nissāraṇā;**Objections, sending away;*";
P_HTM[7572]="*Osāraṇā paṭiññā ca,**Admittance, and admitting,*";
P_HTM[7573]="*paṭiggahā paṭikkhipā.**Receiving, prohibition.*";
P_HTM[7574]="*Upaghāti codanā ca,**Harming, and accusing,*";
P_HTM[7575]="*kathinā ca duve tathā;**And so two on the robe-making season;*";
P_HTM[7576]="*Cīvarā pattamaṇḍalā,**Robes, bowls, bowl stands,*";
P_HTM[7577]="*adhiṭṭhānā tatheva dve.**And so two on determining.*";
P_HTM[7578]="*Vikappanā ca vinayā,**And transfer, Monastic Laws,*";
P_HTM[7579]="*venayikā ca sallekhā;**And belong to the Monastic Law, elimination;*";
P_HTM[7580]="*Āpajjati ca vuṭṭhāti,**And commits, is cleared,*";
P_HTM[7581]="*parivāsāpare duve.**Probations, two others.*";
P_HTM[7582]="*Dve mānattā apare ca,**Two trial periods, others,*";
P_HTM[7583]="*ratticchedo anādari;**Not counting a day, disrespect;*";
P_HTM[7584]="*Dve loṇā tayo apare,**Two salts, three others,*";
P_HTM[7585]="*paribhogakkosena ca.**Useful thing, and with abuse.*";
P_HTM[7586]="*Pesuñño ca gaṇāvassa,**And malicious talebearing, group, rainy-season residence,*";
P_HTM[7587]="*ṭhapanā bhārakappiyaṃ;**Cancellations, responsibility, allowable;*";
P_HTM[7588]="*Anāpatti adhammadhammā,**Non-offense, contrary to the Teaching as the Teaching,*";
P_HTM[7589]="*vinaye āsave tathāti.**Contrary to the Monastic Law, and so corruptions.”*";
P_HTM[7590]="*3. Tikavāra**3. The section on threes*";
P_HTM[7591]="*Atthāpatti tiṭṭhante bhagavati āpajjati, no parinibbute;**“There are offenses that one commits while the Buddha is alive, not after his extinguishment.*";
P_HTM[7592]="*atthāpatti parinibbute bhagavati āpajjati, no tiṭṭhante;**There are offenses that one commits after the Buddha’s extinguishment, not while he is alive.*";
P_HTM[7593]="*atthāpatti tiṭṭhantepi bhagavati āpajjati parinibbutepi.**There are offenses that one commits both while the Buddha is alive and also after his extinguishment.*";
P_HTM[7594]="*Atthāpatti kāle āpajjati, no vikāle;**There are offenses that one commits at the right time, not at the wrong time.*";
P_HTM[7595]="*atthāpatti vikāle āpajjati, no kāle;**There are offenses that one commits at the wrong time, not at the right time.*";
P_HTM[7596]="*atthāpatti kāle ceva āpajjati vikāle ca.**There are offenses that one commits both at the right time and also at the wrong time.*";
P_HTM[7597]="*Atthāpatti rattiṃ āpajjati, no divā;**There are offenses that one commits at night, not by day.*";
P_HTM[7598]="*atthāpatti divā āpajjati, no rattiṃ;**There are offenses that one commits by day, not at night.*";
P_HTM[7599]="*atthāpatti rattiñceva āpajjati divā ca.**There are offenses that one commits both at night and also by day.*";
P_HTM[7600]="*Atthāpatti dasavasso āpajjati, no ūnadasavasso;**There are offenses that one commits when one has ten or more years of seniority, not less.*";
P_HTM[7601]="*atthāpatti ūnadasavasso āpajjati, no dasavasso;**There are offenses that one commits when one has less than ten years of seniority, not ten or more.*";
P_HTM[7602]="*atthāpatti dasavasso ceva āpajjati ūnadasavasso ca.**There are offenses that one commits both when one has ten or more years of seniority and also when one has less.*";
P_HTM[7603]="*Atthāpatti pañcavasso āpajjati, no ūnapañcavasso;**There are offenses that one commits when one has five or more years of seniority, not less.*";
P_HTM[7604]="*atthāpatti ūnapañcavasso āpajjati, no pañcavasso;**There are offenses that one commits when one has less than five years of seniority, not five or more.*";
P_HTM[7605]="*atthāpatti pañcavasso ceva āpajjati ūnapañcavasso ca.**There are offenses that one commits both when one has five or more years of seniority and also when one has less.*";
P_HTM[7606]="*Atthāpatti kusalacitto āpajjati;**There are offenses that one commits with a wholesome mind.*";
P_HTM[7607]="*atthāpatti akusalacitto āpajjati;**There are offenses that one commits with an unwholesome mind.*";
P_HTM[7608]="*atthāpatti abyākatacitto āpajjati.**There are offenses that one commits with a indeterminate mind.*";
P_HTM[7609]="*Atthāpatti sukhavedanāsamaṅgī āpajjati;**There are offenses that one commits while experiencing pleasant feelings.*";
P_HTM[7610]="*atthāpatti dukkhavedanāsamaṅgī āpajjati;**There are offenses that one commits while experiencing unpleasant feelings.*";
P_HTM[7611]="*atthāpatti adukkhamasukhavedanāsamaṅgī āpajjati.**There are offenses that one commits while experiencing neither pleasant nor unpleasant feelings.*";
P_HTM[7612]="*Tīṇi codanāvatthūni—**There are three grounds for an accusation:*";
P_HTM[7613]="*diṭṭhena, sutena, parisaṅkāya.**what is seen, what is heard, and what is suspected.*";
P_HTM[7614]="*Tayo salākaggāhā—**There are three ways of voting:*";
P_HTM[7615]="*guḷhako, vivaṭako, sakaṇṇajappako.**in secret, openly, and by whispering in the ear.*";
P_HTM[7616]="*Tayo paṭikkhepā—**Three things are prohibited:*";
P_HTM[7617]="*mahicchatā, asantuṭṭhitā, asallekhatā.**great desires, discontent, and self-inflation.*";
P_HTM[7618]="*Tayo anuññātā—**Three things are allowed:*";
P_HTM[7619]="*appicchatā, santuṭṭhitā, sallekhatā.**fewness of wishes, contentment, and self-elimination.*";
P_HTM[7620]="*Aparepi tayo paṭikkhepā—**Three other things are prohibited:*";
P_HTM[7621]="*mahicchatā, asantuṭṭhitā, amattaññutā.**great desires, discontent, and lacking a sense of moderation.*";
P_HTM[7622]="*Tayo anuññātā—**Three things are allowed:*";
P_HTM[7623]="*appicchatā, santuṭṭhitā, mattaññutā.**fewness of wishes, contentment, and having a sense of moderation.*";
P_HTM[7624]="*Tisso paññattiyo—**There are three kinds of rules:*";
P_HTM[7625]="*paññatti, anupaññatti, anuppannapaññatti.**a rule, an addition to a rule, and an unprompted rule.*";
P_HTM[7626]="*Aparāpi tisso paññattiyo—**There are three other kinds of rules:*";
P_HTM[7627]="*sabbatthapaññatti, padesapaññatti, sādhāraṇapaññatti.**a rule that applies everywhere, a rule that applies in a particular place, and a rule that the monks and nuns have in common.*";
P_HTM[7628]="*Aparāpi tisso paññattiyo—**There are three other kinds of rules:*";
P_HTM[7629]="*asādhāraṇapaññatti, ekatopaññatti, ubhatopaññatti.**a rule the monks and nuns do not have in common, a rule for one Sangha, and a rule for both Sanghas.*";
P_HTM[7630]="*Atthāpatti bālo āpajjati, no paṇḍito;**There are offenses committed by fools, not by the wise.*";
P_HTM[7631]="*atthāpatti paṇḍito āpajjati, no bālo;**There are offenses committed by the wise, not by fools.*";
P_HTM[7632]="*atthāpatti bālo ceva āpajjati paṇḍito ca.**There are offenses committed by both by fools and the wise.*";
P_HTM[7633]="*Atthāpatti kāḷe āpajjati, no juṇhe;**There are offenses committed when the moon is new, not when it’s full.*";
P_HTM[7634]="*atthāpatti juṇhe āpajjati, no kāḷe;**There are offenses committed when the moon is full, not when it’s new.*";
P_HTM[7635]="*atthāpatti kāḷe ceva āpajjati juṇhe ca.**There are offenses committed both when the moon is new and when it’s full.*";
P_HTM[7636]="*Atthi kāḷe kappati, no juṇhe;**There are things that are allowable when the moon is new, not when it’s full.*";
P_HTM[7637]="*atthi juṇhe kappati, no kāḷe;**There are things that are allowable when the moon is full, not when it’s new.*";
P_HTM[7638]="*atthi kāḷe ceva kappati juṇhe ca.**There are things that are allowable both when the moon is new and when it’s full.*";
P_HTM[7639]="*Atthāpatti hemante āpajjati, no gimhe no vasse;**There are offenses committed during winter, not during summer or the rainy season.*";
P_HTM[7640]="*atthāpatti gimhe āpajjati, no hemante no vasse;**There are offenses committed during summer, not during winter or the rainy season.*";
P_HTM[7641]="*atthāpatti vasse āpajjati, no hemante no gimhe.**There are offenses committed during the rainy season, not during winter or summer.*";
P_HTM[7642]="*Atthāpatti saṅgho āpajjati, na gaṇo na puggalo;**There are offenses committed by a sangha, not by several monks or an individual.*";
P_HTM[7643]="*atthāpatti gaṇo āpajjati, na saṅgho na puggalo;**There are offenses committed by several monks, not by a sangha or an individual.*";
P_HTM[7644]="*atthāpatti puggalo āpajjati, na saṅgho na gaṇo.**There are offenses committed by an individual, not by a sangha or several monks.*";
P_HTM[7645]="*Atthi saṅghassa kappati, na gaṇassa na puggalassa;**There are things allowable for a sangha, not for several monks or an individual.*";
P_HTM[7646]="*atthi gaṇassa kappati, na saṅghassa na puggalassa;**There are things allowable for several monks, not for a sangha or an individual.*";
P_HTM[7647]="*atthi puggalassa kappati, na saṅghassa na gaṇassa.**There are things allowable for an individual, not for a sangha or several monks.*";
P_HTM[7648]="*Tisso chādanā—**Three kinds of concealing:*";
P_HTM[7649]="*vatthuṃ chādeti, no āpattiṃ;**one conceals the action that was the basis for the offense, not the offense.*";
P_HTM[7650]="*āpattiṃ chādeti, no vatthuṃ;**one conceals the offense, not the action that was the basis for the offense.*";
P_HTM[7651]="*vatthuñceva chādeti āpattiñca.**one conceals both the action that was the basis for the offense and also the offense.*";
P_HTM[7652]="*Tisso paṭicchādiyo—**There are three coverings:*";
P_HTM[7653]="*jantāgharapaṭicchādi, udakapaṭicchādi, vatthapaṭicchādi.**a sauna, water, and a cloth.*";
P_HTM[7654]="*Tīṇi paṭicchannāni vahanti, no vivaṭāni—**Three things happen concealed, not openly:*";
P_HTM[7655]="*mātugāmo paṭicchanno vahati, no vivaṭo;**Women are married with a veil, not unveiled.*";
P_HTM[7656]="*brāhmaṇānaṃ mantā paṭicchannā vahanti, no vivaṭā;**The mantras of the brahmins are transmitted in secret, not openly.*";
P_HTM[7657]="*micchādiṭṭhi paṭicchannā vahati, no vivaṭā.**Wrong view is transmitted in secret, not openly.*";
P_HTM[7658]="*Tīṇi vivaṭāni virocanti, no paṭicchannāni—**Three things shine in the open, not when concealed:*";
P_HTM[7659]="*candamaṇḍalaṃ vivaṭaṃ virocati, no paṭicchannaṃ;**The moon shines in the open, not when concealed.*";
P_HTM[7660]="*sūriyamaṇḍalaṃ vivaṭaṃ virocati, no paṭicchannaṃ;**The sun shines in the open, not when concealed.*";
P_HTM[7661]="*tathāgatappavedito dhammavinayo vivaṭo virocati, no paṭicchanno.**The spiritual path made known by the Buddha shines in the open, not when concealed.*";
P_HTM[7662]="*Tayo senāsanaggāhā—**There are three times for the allocation of dwellings:*";
P_HTM[7663]="*purimako, pacchimako, antarāmuttako.**the first, the second, and when given up in between.*";
P_HTM[7664]="*Atthāpatti gilāno āpajjati, no agilāno;**There are offenses that one commits when sick, not when not sick.*";
P_HTM[7665]="*atthāpatti agilāno āpajjati, no gilāno;**There are offenses that one commits when not sick, not when sick.*";
P_HTM[7666]="*atthāpatti gilāno ceva āpajjati agilāno ca.**There are offenses that one commits both when sick and when not sick.*";
P_HTM[7667]="*Tīṇi adhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni.**There are three kinds of illegitimate cancellations of the Monastic Code .*";
P_HTM[7668]="*Tīṇi dhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni.**There are three kinds of legitimate cancellations of the Monastic Code.*";
P_HTM[7669]="*Tayo parivāsā—**There are three kinds of probation:*";
P_HTM[7670]="*paṭicchannaparivāso, appaṭicchannaparivāso, suddhantaparivāso.**probation for concealed offenses, probation for unconcealed offenses, and purifying probation.*";
P_HTM[7671]="*Tayo mānattā—**There are three kinds of trial periods:*";
P_HTM[7672]="*paṭicchannamānattaṃ, appaṭicchannamānattaṃ, pakkhamānattaṃ.**trial period for concealed offenses, trial period for unconcealed offenses, and trial period for a half-month.*";
P_HTM[7673]="*Tayo pārivāsikassa bhikkhuno ratticchedā—**There are three things that stop a monk on probation from counting a particular day toward his probationary period:*";
P_HTM[7674]="*sahavāso, vippavāso, anārocanā.**he stays in the same room as a regular monk; he stays apart from other monks; he doesn’t inform other monks of his status.*";
P_HTM[7675]="*Atthāpatti anto āpajjati, no bahi;**There are offenses that one commits inside, not outside.*";
P_HTM[7676]="*atthāpatti bahi āpajjati, no anto;**There are offenses that one commits outside, not inside.*";
P_HTM[7677]="*atthāpatti anto ceva āpajjati bahi ca.**There are offenses that one commits both inside and outside.*";
P_HTM[7678]="*Atthāpatti antosīmāya āpajjati, no bahisīmāya;**There are offenses that one commits inside the monastic boundary, not outside.*";
P_HTM[7679]="*atthāpatti bahisīmāya āpajjati, no antosīmāya;**There are offenses that one commits outside the monastic boundary, not inside.*";
P_HTM[7680]="*atthāpatti antosīmāya ceva āpajjati bahisīmāya ca.**There are offenses that one commits both inside and outside the monastic boundary.*";
P_HTM[7681]="*Tīhākārehi āpattiṃ āpajjati—**One commits an offense in three ways:*";
P_HTM[7682]="*kāyena āpajjati, vācāya āpajjati, kāyena vācāya āpajjati.**one commits an offense by body, by speech, or by body and speech.*";
P_HTM[7683]="*Aparehipi tīhākārehi āpattiṃ āpajjati—**One commits an offense in three other ways:*";
P_HTM[7684]="*saṅghamajjhe, gaṇamajjhe, puggalassa santike.**in the midst of the Sangha, in the midst of a group, or in the presence of an individual.*";
P_HTM[7685]="*Tīhākārehi āpattiyā vuṭṭhāti—**One clears an offense in three ways:*";
P_HTM[7686]="*kāyena vuṭṭhāti, vācāya vuṭṭhāti, kāyena vācāya vuṭṭhāti.**one clears an offense by body, by speech, or by body and speech.*";
P_HTM[7687]="*Aparehipi tīhākārehi āpattiyā vuṭṭhāti—**One clears an offense in three other ways:*";
P_HTM[7688]="*saṅghamajjhe, gaṇamajjhe, puggalassa santike.**in the midst of the Sangha, in the midst of a group, or in the presence of an individual.*";
P_HTM[7689]="*Tīṇi adhammikāni amūḷhavinayassa dānāni.**There are three illegitimate grantings of resolution because of past insanity.*";
P_HTM[7690]="*Tīṇi dhammikāni amūḷhavinayassa dānāni.**There are three legitimate grantings of resolution because of past insanity.*";
P_HTM[7691]="*Tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho tajjanīyakammaṃ kareyya—**When a monk has three qualities, the Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of condemnation against him:*";
P_HTM[7692]="*bhaṇḍanakārako hoti kalahakārako vivādakārako bhassakārako saṅghe adhikaraṇakārako, bālo hoti abyatto, āpattibahulo anapadāno gihisaṃsaṭṭho viharati ananulomikehi gihisaṃsaggehi.**he is quarrelsome, argumentative, and a creator of legal issues in the Sangha; he is ignorant and incompetent, often committing offenses, incapable of determining whether he has committed an offense; he is constantly and improperly socializing with householders.*";
P_HTM[7693]="*Tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho niyassakammaṃ kareyya—**When a monk has three qualities, the Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of demotion against him:*";
P_HTM[7694]="*bhaṇḍanakārako hoti …pe… saṅghe adhikaraṇakārako, bālo hoti abyatto, āpattibahulo anapadāno gihisaṃsaṭṭho viharati ananulomikehi gihisaṃsaggehi.**he is quarrelsome, argumentative, and a creator of legal issues in the Sangha; he is ignorant and incompetent, often committing offenses, incapable of determining whether he has committed an offense; he is constantly and improperly socializing with householders.*";
P_HTM[7695]="*Tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho pabbājanīyakammaṃ kareyya—**When a monk has three qualities, the Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of banishing him:*";
P_HTM[7696]="*bhaṇḍanakārako hoti …pe… saṅghe adhikaraṇakārako, bālo hoti abyatto, āpattibahulo anapadāno kuladūsako hoti pāpasamācāro pāpasamācārā dissanti ceva suyyanti ca.**he is quarrelsome, argumentative, and a creator of legal issues in the Sangha; he is ignorant and incompetent, often committing offenses, incapable of determining whether he has committed an offense; he is a corrupter of families and badly behaved, and his bad behavior has been seen and heard about.*";
P_HTM[7697]="*Tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ kareyya—**When a monk has three qualities, the Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of reconciliation against him:*";
P_HTM[7698]="*bhaṇḍanakārako hoti …pe… saṅghe adhikaraṇakārako, bālo hoti abyatto, āpattibahulo anapadāno gihī akkosati paribhāsati.**he is quarrelsome, argumentative, and a creator of legal issues in the Sangha; he is ignorant and incompetent, often committing offenses, incapable of determining whether he has committed an offense; he abuses and reviles householders.*";
P_HTM[7699]="*Tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho āpattiyā adassane ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kareyya—**When a monk has three qualities, the Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of ejecting him for not recognizing an offense:*";
P_HTM[7700]="*bhaṇḍanakārako hoti …pe… saṅghe adhikaraṇakārako, bālo hoti abyatto, āpattibahulo anapadāno āpattiṃ āpajjitvā na icchati āpattiṃ passituṃ.**he is quarrelsome, argumentative, and a creator of legal issues in the Sangha; he is ignorant and incompetent, often committing offenses, incapable of determining whether he has committed an offense; after committing an offense, he refuses to recognize it.*";
P_HTM[7701]="*Tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho āpattiyā appaṭikamme ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kareyya—**When a monk has three qualities, the Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of ejecting him for not making amends for an offense:*";
P_HTM[7702]="*bhaṇḍanakārako hoti …pe… saṅghe adhikaraṇakārako, bālo hoti abyatto, āpattibahulo anapadāno āpattiṃ āpajjitvā na icchati āpattiṃ paṭikātuṃ.**he is quarrelsome, argumentative, and a creator of legal issues in the Sangha; he is ignorant and incompetent, often committing offenses, incapable of determining whether he has committed an offense; after committing an offense, he refuses to make amends for it.*";
P_HTM[7703]="*Tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kareyya—**When a monk has three qualities, the Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of ejecting him for not giving up a bad view:*";
P_HTM[7704]="*bhaṇḍanakārako hoti …pe… saṅghe adhikaraṇakārako, bālo hoti abyatto, āpattibahulo anapadāno na icchati pāpikaṃ diṭṭhiṃ paṭinissajjituṃ.**he is quarrelsome, argumentative, and a creator of legal issues in the Sangha; he is ignorant and incompetent, often committing offenses, incapable of determining whether he has committed an offense; he refuses to give up a bad view.*";
P_HTM[7705]="*Tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho āgāḷhāya ceteyya—**When a monk has three qualities, the Sangha may, if it wishes, plan a strong action against him:*";
P_HTM[7706]="*bhaṇḍanakārako hoti kalahakārako vivādakārako bhassakārako saṅghe adhikaraṇakārako, bālo hoti abyatto āpattibahulo anapadāno, gihisaṃsaṭṭho viharati ananulomikehi gihisaṃsaggehi.**he is quarrelsome, argumentative, and a creator of legal issues in the Sangha; he is ignorant and incompetent, often committing offenses, incapable of determining whether he has committed an offense; he is constantly and improperly socializing with householders.*";
P_HTM[7707]="*Tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno kammaṃ kātabbaṃ—**When a monk has three qualities a legal procedure may be done against him:*";
P_HTM[7708]="*alajjī ca hoti, bālo ca, apakatatto ca.**he is shameless, ignorant, and not a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[7709]="*Aparehipi tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno kammaṃ kātabbaṃ—**When a monk has three other qualities a legal procedure may be done against him:*";
P_HTM[7710]="*adhisīle sīlavipanno hoti, ajjhācāre ācāravipanno hoti, atidiṭṭhiyā diṭṭhivipanno hoti.**he has failed in the higher morality; he has failed in conduct; he has failed in view.*";
P_HTM[7711]="*Aparehipi tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno kammaṃ kātabbaṃ—**When a monk has three other qualities a legal procedure may be done against him:*";
P_HTM[7712]="*kāyikena davena samannāgato hoti, vācasikena davena samannāgato hoti, kāyikavācasikena davena samannāgato hoti.**his bodily conduct is frivolous; his verbal conduct is frivolous; his bodily and verbal conduct are frivolous.*";
P_HTM[7713]="*Aparehipi tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno kammaṃ kātabbaṃ—**When a monk has three other qualities a legal procedure may be done against him:*";
P_HTM[7714]="*kāyikena anācārena samannāgato hoti, vācasikena anācārena samannāgato hoti, kāyikavācasikena anācārena samannāgato hoti.**he is improperly behaved by body; he is improperly behaved by speech; he is improperly behaved by body and speech.*";
P_HTM[7715]="*Aparehipi tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno kammaṃ kātabbaṃ—**When a monk has three other qualities a legal procedure may be done against him:*";
P_HTM[7716]="*kāyikena upaghātikena samannāgato hoti, vācasikena upaghātikena samannāgato hoti, kāyikavācasikena upaghātikena samannāgato hoti.**his bodily conduct is harmful; his verbal conduct is harmful; his bodily and verbal conduct are harmful.*";
P_HTM[7717]="*Aparehipi tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno kammaṃ kātabbaṃ—**When a monk has three other qualities a legal procedure may be done against him:*";
P_HTM[7718]="*kāyikena micchājīvena samannāgato hoti, vācasikena micchājīvena samannāgato hoti, kāyikavācasikena micchājīvena samannāgato hoti.**he has wrong livelihood by body; he has wrong livelihood by speech; he has wrong livelihood by body and speech.*";
P_HTM[7719]="*Aparehipi tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno kammaṃ kātabbaṃ—**When a monk has three other qualities a legal procedure may be done against him:*";
P_HTM[7720]="*āpattiṃ āpanno kammakato upasampādeti, nissayaṃ deti, sāmaṇeraṃ upaṭṭhāpeti.**if, after committing an offense and having a legal procedure done against him, he: gives the full ordination, gives formal support, has a novice monk attend on him.*";
P_HTM[7721]="*Aparehipi tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno kammaṃ kātabbaṃ—**When a monk has three other qualities a legal procedure may be done against him:*";
P_HTM[7722]="*yāya āpattiyā saṅghena kammaṃ kataṃ hoti taṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati, aññaṃ vā tādisikaṃ, tato vā pāpiṭṭhataraṃ.**he commits the same offense for which the Sangha did the legal procedure against him; he commits an offense similar to the one for which the Sangha did the legal procedure against him; he commits an offense worse than the one for which the Sangha did the legal procedure against him.*";
P_HTM[7723]="*Aparehipi tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno kammaṃ kātabbaṃ—**When a monk has three other qualities a legal procedure may be done against him:*";
P_HTM[7724]="*buddhassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, dhammassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, saṅghassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati.**he disparages the Buddha; he disparages the Teaching; he disparages the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[7725]="*Tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno saṅghamajjhe uposathaṃ ṭhapentassa—“alaṃ, bhikkhu, mā bhaṇḍanaṃ mā kalahaṃ mā viggahaṃ mā vivādan”ti omadditvā saṅghena uposatho kātabbo—**When a monk has three qualities and is having the observance-day procedure cancelled in the midst of the Sangha, then, after pressing him by saying, “Enough. No more arguing and disputing,” the Sangha should do the observance-day procedure. These are the three qualities:*";
P_HTM[7726]="*alajjī ca hoti, bālo ca, apakatatto ca.**he is shameless, ignorant, and not a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[7727]="*Tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno saṅghamajjhe pavāraṇaṃ ṭhapentassa—“alaṃ, bhikkhu, mā bhaṇḍanaṃ mā kalahaṃ mā viggahaṃ mā vivādan”ti omadditvā saṅghena pavāretabbaṃ—**When a monk has three qualities and is having the invitation-day procedure cancelled in the midst of the Sangha, then, after pressing him by saying, “Enough. No more arguing and disputing,” the Sangha should do the invitation-day procedure. These are the three qualities:*";
P_HTM[7728]="*alajjī ca hoti, bālo ca, apakatatto ca.**he is shameless, ignorant, and not a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[7729]="*Tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno na kāci saṅghasammuti dātabbā—**The Sangha should not give any approval to a monk has three qualities:*";
P_HTM[7730]="*alajjī ca hoti, bālo ca, apakatatto ca.**he is shameless, ignorant, and not a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[7731]="*Tīhaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe na voharitabbaṃ—**When a monk has three qualities, he should not speak in the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[7732]="*alajjī ca hoti, bālo ca, apakatatto ca.**he is shameless, ignorant, and not a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[7733]="*Tīhaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu na kismiñci paccekaṭṭhāne ṭhapetabbo—**When a monk has three qualities, he should not be put in a position of leadership:*";
P_HTM[7734]="*alajjī ca hoti, bālo ca, apakatatto ca.**he is shameless, ignorant, and not a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[7735]="*Tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno nissāya na vatthabbaṃ—**When a monk has three qualities, one should not live with formal support from him:*";
P_HTM[7736]="*alajjī ca hoti, bālo ca, apakatatto ca.**he is shameless, ignorant, and not a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[7737]="*Tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno nissayo na dātabbo—**When a monk has three qualities, he should not give formal support:*";
P_HTM[7738]="*alajjī ca hoti, bālo ca, apakatatto ca.**he is shameless, ignorant, and not a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[7739]="*Tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno okāsakammaṃ kārāpentassa nālaṃ okāsakammaṃ kātuṃ—**When a monk has three qualities, he is not qualified to ask for permission to accuse another:*";
P_HTM[7740]="*alajjī ca hoti, bālo ca, apakatatto ca.**he is shameless, ignorant, and not a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[7741]="*Tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno savacanīyaṃ nādātabbaṃ—**When a monk has three qualities, he should not be allowed to speak to initiate a legal process:*";
P_HTM[7742]="*alajjī ca hoti, bālo ca, apakatatto ca.**he is shameless, ignorant, and not a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[7743]="*Tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno vinayo na pucchitabbo—**When a monk has three qualities, he should not be asked about the Monastic Law:*";
P_HTM[7744]="*alajjī ca hoti, bālo ca, apakatatto ca.**he is shameless, ignorant, and not a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[7745]="*Tīhaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā vinayo na pucchitabbo—**When a monk has three qualities, he should not ask about the Monastic Law:*";
P_HTM[7746]="*alajjī ca hoti, bālo ca, apakatatto ca.**he is shameless, ignorant, and not a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[7747]="*Tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno vinayo na vissajjetabbo—**When a monk has three qualities, his questions about the Monastic Law should not be replied to:*";
P_HTM[7748]="*alajjī ca hoti, bālo ca, apakatatto ca.**he is shameless, ignorant, and not a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[7749]="*Tīhaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā vinayo na vissajjetabbo—**When a monk has three qualities, he should not reply to questions about the Monastic Law:*";
P_HTM[7750]="*alajjī ca hoti, bālo ca, apakatatto ca.**he is shameless, ignorant, and not a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[7751]="*Tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno anuyogo na dātabbo—**When a monk has three qualities, he should not be allowed to question:*";
P_HTM[7752]="*alajjī ca hoti, bālo ca, apakatatto ca.**he is shameless, ignorant, and not a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[7753]="*Tīhaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ vinayo na sākacchitabbo—**When a monk has three qualities, one should not discuss the Monastic Law with him:*";
P_HTM[7754]="*alajjī ca hoti, bālo ca, apakatatto ca.**he is shameless, ignorant, and not a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[7755]="*Tīhaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā na upasampādetabbaṃ na nissayo dātabbo na sāmaṇero upaṭṭhāpetabbo—**When a monk has three qualities, he should not give the full ordination, give formal support, or have a novice monk attend on him:*";
P_HTM[7756]="*alajjī ca hoti, bālo ca, apakatatto ca.**he is shameless, ignorant, and not a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[7757]="*Tayo uposathā—**There are three observance-day procedures:*";
P_HTM[7758]="*cātuddasiko, pannarasiko, sāmaggiuposatho.**on the fourteenth, on the fifteenth, and the observance-day procedures for the sake of unity.*";
P_HTM[7759]="*Aparepi tayo uposathā—**There are three other observance-day procedures:*";
P_HTM[7760]="*saṅgheuposatho, gaṇeuposatho, puggaleuposatho.**the observance-day procedure for a Sangha, the observance-day procedure for a group, and thee observance-day procedure for an individual.*";
P_HTM[7761]="*Aparepi tayo uposathā—**There are three other observance-day procedures:*";
P_HTM[7762]="*suttuddesouposatho, pārisuddhiuposatho, adhiṭṭhānuposatho.**the observance-day procedure which consists of reciting the Monastic Code, the observance-day procedure which consists of declaring purity, and the observance-day procedure which consists of a determination.*";
P_HTM[7763]="*Tisso pavāraṇā—**There are three invitation-day procedures:*";
P_HTM[7764]="*cātuddasikā, pannarasikā, sāmaggipavāraṇā.**on the fourteenth, on the fifteenth, and the invitation-day procedure for the sake of unity.*";
P_HTM[7765]="*Aparāpi tisso pavāraṇā—**There are three other invitation-day procedures:*";
P_HTM[7766]="*saṅghepavāraṇā, gaṇepavāraṇā, puggalepavāraṇā.**the invitation-day procedures for a Sangha, the invitation-day procedures for a group, and the invitation-day procedures for an individual.*";
P_HTM[7767]="*Aparāpi tisso pavāraṇā—**There are three other invitation-day procedures:*";
P_HTM[7768]="*tevācikāpavāraṇā, dvevācikāpavāraṇā, samānavassikāpavāraṇā.**the invitation-day procedure done by means of three statements, the invitation-day procedure done by means of two statements, the invitation-day procedure done by means of groups according to year of seniority.*";
P_HTM[7769]="*Tayo āpāyikā nerayikā—**There are three kinds of persons bound for a hell:*";
P_HTM[7770]="*idamappahāya, yo ca abrahmacārī brahmacāripaṭiñño, yo ca suddhaṃ brahmacāriṃ parisuddhabrahmacariyaṃ carantaṃ amūlakena abrahmacariyena anuddhaṃseti, yo cāyaṃ evaṃvādī evaṃdiṭṭhi—“natthi kāmesu doso”ti so kāmesu pātabyataṃ āpajjati.**one who does not abandon and abstain from sexuality, while claiming to do so; one who groundlessly charges someone who lives the spiritual life in purity with not abstaining from sexuality; one who has a view such as this: “There is no fault in worldly pleasures,” and then indulges in them.*";
P_HTM[7771]="*Tīṇi akusalamūlāni—**There are three unwholesome sources:*";
P_HTM[7772]="*lobho akusalamūlaṃ, doso akusalamūlaṃ, moho akusalamūlaṃ.**greed, ill will, and delusion.*";
P_HTM[7773]="*Tīṇi kusalamūlāni—**There are three wholesome sources:*";
P_HTM[7774]="*alobho kusalamūlaṃ, adoso kusalamūlaṃ, amoho kusalamūlaṃ.**non-greed, non-ill will, and non-delusion.*";
P_HTM[7775]="*Tīṇi duccaritāni—**There are three kinds of misconduct:*";
P_HTM[7776]="*kāyaduccaritaṃ, vacīduccaritaṃ, manoduccaritaṃ.**misconduct by body, misconduct by speech, and misconduct by mind.*";
P_HTM[7777]="*Tīṇi sucaritāni—**There are three kinds of good conduct:*";
P_HTM[7778]="*kāyasucaritaṃ, vacīsucaritaṃ, manosucaritaṃ.**good conduct by body, good conduct by speech, and good conduct by mind.*";
P_HTM[7779]="*Tayo atthavase paṭicca bhagavatā kulesu tikabhojanaṃ paññattaṃ—**There are three reasons why the Buddha laid down the rule against eating in groups of more than three:*";
P_HTM[7780]="*dummaṅkūnaṃ puggalānaṃ niggahāya, pesalānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ phāsuvihārāya, “mā pāpicchā pakkhaṃ nissāya saṅghaṃ bhindeyyun”ti kulānuddayatāya ca.**for the restraint of bad people; for the ease of good monks, stopping those with bad desires from creating a faction and then splitting the Sangha; and out of compassion for families.*";
P_HTM[7781]="*Tīhi asaddhammehi abhibhūto pariyādinnacitto devadatto āpāyiko nerayiko kappaṭṭho atekiccho pāpicchatā pāpamittatā oramattakena visesādhigamena antarā vosānaṃ āpādi.**Because he was overcome by and immersed in three bad qualities, Devadatta was irredeemably destined to an eon in hell: bad desires; bad friends; and after minor success, he stopped short of the goal.*";
P_HTM[7782]="*Tisso sammutiyo—**There are three permissions:*";
P_HTM[7783]="*daṇḍasammuti, sikkāsammuti, daṇḍasikkāsammuti.**approval to use a staff, approval to use a carrying net, and approval to use both a staff and a carrying net.*";
P_HTM[7784]="*Tisso pādukā dhuvaṭṭhānikā asaṅkamanīyā—**There are three kinds of foot-stands that are fixed in place and immobile:*";
P_HTM[7785]="*vaccapādukā, passāvapādukā, ācamanapādukā.**foot-stands for defecating, foot-stands for urinating, foot-stands for restroom rinsing.*";
P_HTM[7786]="*Tisso pādaghaṃsaniyo—**There are three kinds of foot scrubbers:*";
P_HTM[7787]="*sakkharaṃ, kathalā, samuddapheṇakoti.**stones, pebbles, and pumice.”*";
P_HTM[7788]="*Tikaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The section on threes is finished.*";
P_HTM[7789]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[7790]="*Tiṭṭhante kāle rattiñca,**“While he is alive, at the right time, and at night,*";
P_HTM[7791]="*dasa pañca kusalena;**ten, five, with wholesome;*";
P_HTM[7792]="*Vedanā codanā vatthu,**Feeling, grounds for accusation,*";
P_HTM[7793]="*salākā dve paṭikkhipā.**Voting, two on prohibited.*";
P_HTM[7794]="*Paññatti apare dve ca,**Rule, and two others,*";
P_HTM[7795]="*bālo kāḷe ca kappati;**Fools, and at the new moon, allowable;*";
P_HTM[7796]="*Hemante saṅgho saṅghassa,**During winter, a sangha, for a sangha,*";
P_HTM[7797]="*chādanā ca paṭicchādi.**And concealings, a covering.*";
P_HTM[7798]="*Paṭicchannā vivaṭā ca,**Concealed, and in the open,*";
P_HTM[7799]="*senāsanagilāyanā;**Dwelling, sick;*";
P_HTM[7800]="*Pātimokkhaṃ parivāsaṃ,**Monastic Code, probation,*";
P_HTM[7801]="*mānattā pārivāsikā.**Trial period, those on probation.*";
P_HTM[7802]="*Anto anto ca sīmāya,**Inside, and inside the boundary,*";
P_HTM[7803]="*āpajjati punāpare;**One commits, and another;*";
P_HTM[7804]="*Vuṭṭhāti apare ceva,**One clears, and another,*";
P_HTM[7805]="*amūḷhavinayā duve.**Two on resolution because of past insanity.*";
P_HTM[7806]="*Tajjanīyā niyassā ca,**Condemnation, and demotion,*";
P_HTM[7807]="*pabbājapaṭisāraṇī;**Banishing, reconciliation;*";
P_HTM[7808]="*Adassanā paṭikamme,**Not recognizing, making amends,*";
P_HTM[7809]="*anissagge ca diṭṭhiyā.**And not giving up a bad view.*";
P_HTM[7810]="*Āgāḷhakammādhisīle,**Strong, formal procedure, in the higher morality,*";
P_HTM[7811]="*davānācāraghātikā;**Frivolous, improperly behaved, harmful;*";
P_HTM[7812]="*Ājīvāpannā tādisikā,**Livelihood, committed, similar,*";
P_HTM[7813]="*avaṇṇuposathena ca.**Disparages, and observance-day procedure.*";
P_HTM[7814]="*Pavāraṇā sammuti ca,**Invitation-day procedure, and approval,*";
P_HTM[7815]="*vohārapaccekena ca;**Speak, and with in a leadership;*";
P_HTM[7816]="*Na vatthabbaṃ na dātabbaṃ,**Should not live, should not give,*";
P_HTM[7817]="*okāsaṃ na kare tathā.**And should not ask for permission.*";
P_HTM[7818]="*Na kare savacanīyaṃ,**Should not initiate a legal process,*";
P_HTM[7819]="*na pucchitabbakā duve;**Two on those who should not be asked;*";
P_HTM[7820]="*Na vissajje duve ceva,**And two on should not reply,*";
P_HTM[7821]="*anuyogampi no dade.**And one should not answer.*";
P_HTM[7822]="*Sākacchā upasampadā,**Discussion, full ordination,*";
P_HTM[7823]="*nissayasāmaṇerā ca;**Formal support, and novice monks;*";
P_HTM[7824]="*Uposathatikā tīṇi,**Three on three observance-day procedures,*";
P_HTM[7825]="*pavāraṇatikā tayo.**Three on three invitation-day procedures.*";
P_HTM[7826]="*Āpāyikā akusalā,**Bound for the lower, unwholesome,*";
P_HTM[7827]="*kusalā caritā duve;**Wholesome, two on conduct;*";
P_HTM[7828]="*Tikabhojanasaddhamme,**Eating in groups of more than three, in bad qualities,*";
P_HTM[7829]="*sammuti pādukena ca;**Permission, and with foot-stands;*";
P_HTM[7830]="*Pādaghaṃsanikā ceva,**And foot scrubbers—*";
P_HTM[7831]="*uddānaṃ tikake idanti.**This is the summary for the threes.”*";
P_HTM[7832]="*4. Catukkavāra**4. The section on fours*";
P_HTM[7833]="*Atthāpatti sakavācāya āpajjati, paravācāya vuṭṭhāti;**There are offenses that one commits through one’s own speech, but clears through someone else’s speech.*";
P_HTM[7834]="*atthāpatti paravācāya āpajjati, sakavācāya vuṭṭhāti;**There are offenses that one commits through someone else’s speech, but clears through one’s own speech.*";
P_HTM[7835]="*atthāpatti sakavācāya āpajjati, sakavācāya vuṭṭhāti;**There are offenses that one commits through one’s own speech, but clears through one’s own speech.*";
P_HTM[7836]="*atthāpatti paravācāya āpajjati, paravācāya vuṭṭhāti.**There are offenses that one commits through someone else’s speech, but clears through someone else’s speech.*";
P_HTM[7837]="*Atthāpatti kāyena āpajjati, vācāya vuṭṭhāti;**There are offenses that one commits by body, but clears by speech.*";
P_HTM[7838]="*atthāpatti vācāya āpajjati, kāyena vuṭṭhāti;**There are offenses that one commits by speech, but clears by body.*";
P_HTM[7839]="*atthāpatti kāyena āpajjati, kāyena vuṭṭhāti;**There are offenses that one commits by body and clears by body.*";
P_HTM[7840]="*atthāpatti vācāya āpajjati, vācāya vuṭṭhāti.**There are offenses that one commits by speech and clears by speech.*";
P_HTM[7841]="*Atthāpatti pasutto āpajjati, paṭibuddho vuṭṭhāti;**There are offenses that one commits while sleeping, but clears while awake.*";
P_HTM[7842]="*atthāpatti paṭibuddho āpajjati, pasutto vuṭṭhāti;**There are offenses that one commits while awake, but clears while sleeping.*";
P_HTM[7843]="*atthāpatti pasutto āpajjati, pasutto vuṭṭhāti;**There are offenses that one commits while sleeping and clears while sleeping.*";
P_HTM[7844]="*atthāpatti paṭibuddho āpajjati, paṭibuddho vuṭṭhāti.**There are offenses that one commits while awake and clears while awake.*";
P_HTM[7845]="*Atthāpatti acittako āpajjati, sacittako vuṭṭhāti;**There are offenses that one commits unintentionally, but clears intentionally.*";
P_HTM[7846]="*atthāpatti sacittako āpajjati, acittako vuṭṭhāti;**There are offenses that one commits intentionally, but clears unintentionally.*";
P_HTM[7847]="*atthāpatti acittako āpajjati, acittako vuṭṭhāti;**There are offenses that one commits unintentionally and clears unintentionally.*";
P_HTM[7848]="*atthāpatti sacittako āpajjati, sacittako vuṭṭhāti.**There are offenses that one commits intentionally and clears intentionally.*";
P_HTM[7849]="*Atthāpatti āpajjanto deseti;**There are offenses where the confession is an offense.*";
P_HTM[7850]="*desento āpajjati;**There are offenses where the offense is a confession.*";
P_HTM[7851]="*atthāpatti āpajjanto vuṭṭhāti;**There are offenses where the clearing is an offense.*";
P_HTM[7852]="*vuṭṭhahanto āpajjati.**There are offenses where the offense is a clearing.*";
P_HTM[7853]="*Atthāpatti kammena āpajjati, akammena vuṭṭhāti;**There are offenses that one commits through action, but clears through non-action.*";
P_HTM[7854]="*atthāpatti akammena āpajjati, kammena vuṭṭhāti;**There are offenses that one commits through non-action, but clears through action.*";
P_HTM[7855]="*atthāpatti kammena āpajjati, kammena vuṭṭhāti;**There are offenses that one commits through action and clears through action.*";
P_HTM[7856]="*atthāpatti akammena āpajjati, akammena vuṭṭhāti.**There are offenses that one commits through non-action and clears through non-action.*";
P_HTM[7857]="*Cattāro anariyavohārā—**There are four kinds of ignoble speech:*";
P_HTM[7858]="*adiṭṭhe diṭṭhavāditā, assute sutavāditā, amute mutavāditā, aviññāte viññātavāditā.**saying that one has seen what one has not seen; saying that one has heard what one has not heard; saying that one has sensed what one has not sensed; saying that one has known what one has not known.*";
P_HTM[7859]="*Cattāro ariyavohārā—**There are four kinds of noble speech:*";
P_HTM[7860]="*adiṭṭhe adiṭṭhavāditā, assute assutavāditā, amute amutavāditā, aviññāte aviññātavāditā.**saying that one has not seen what one has not seen; saying that one has not heard what one has not heard; saying that one has not sensed what one has not sensed; saying that one has not known what one has not known.*";
P_HTM[7861]="*Aparepi cattāro anariyavohārā—**There are four other kinds of ignoble speech:*";
P_HTM[7862]="*diṭṭhe adiṭṭhavāditā, sute assutavāditā, mute amutavāditā, viññāte aviññātavāditā.**saying that one has not seen what one has seen; saying that one has not heard what one has heard; saying that one has not sensed what one has sensed; saying that one has not known what one has known.*";
P_HTM[7863]="*Cattāro ariyavohārā—**There are four other kinds of noble speech:*";
P_HTM[7864]="*diṭṭhe diṭṭhavāditā, sute sutavāditā, mute mutavāditā, viññāte viññātavāditā.**saying that one has seen what one has seen; saying that one has heard what one has heard; saying that one has sensed what one has sensed; saying that one has known what one has known.*";
P_HTM[7865]="*Cattāro pārājikā bhikkhūnaṃ bhikkhunīhi sādhāraṇā;**The monks have four offenses entailing expulsion in common with the nuns.*";
P_HTM[7866]="*cattāro pārājikā bhikkhunīnaṃ bhikkhūhi asādhāraṇā.**The nuns have four offenses entailing expulsion not in common with the monks.*";
P_HTM[7867]="*Cattāro parikkhārā—**There are four kinds of requisites:*";
P_HTM[7868]="*atthi parikkhāro rakkhitabbo gopetabbo mamāyitabbo paribhuñjitabbo;**There are requisites that should be guarded, taken as a personal possession, and made use of.*";
P_HTM[7869]="*atthi parikkhāro rakkhitabbo gopetabbo mamāyitabbo, na paribhuñjitabbo;**There are requisites that should be guarded and taken as a personal possession, but not be made use of.*";
P_HTM[7870]="*atthi parikkhāro rakkhitabbo gopetabbo, na mamāyitabbo na paribhuñjitabbo;**There are requisites that should be guarded, but not taken as a personal possession or made use of.*";
P_HTM[7871]="*atthi parikkhāro na rakkhitabbo na gopetabbo, na mamāyitabbo na paribhuñjitabbo.**There are requisites that should neither be guarded, nor taken as a personal possession or made use of.*";
P_HTM[7872]="*Atthāpatti sammukhā āpajjati, parammukhā vuṭṭhāti;**There are offenses one commits in the presence of someone, but clears in their absence.*";
P_HTM[7873]="*atthāpatti parammukhā āpajjati, sammukhā vuṭṭhāti;**There are offenses one commits in the absence of someone, but clears in their presence.*";
P_HTM[7874]="*atthāpatti sammukhā āpajjati, sammukhā vuṭṭhāti;**There are offenses one commits in the presence of someone, and clears in their presence.*";
P_HTM[7875]="*atthāpatti parammukhā āpajjati, parammukhā vuṭṭhāti.**There are offenses one commits in the absence of someone, and clears in their absence.*";
P_HTM[7876]="*Atthāpatti ajānanto āpajjati, jānanto vuṭṭhāti;**There are offenses one commits unknowingly, but clears knowingly.*";
P_HTM[7877]="*atthāpatti jānanto āpajjati, ajānanto vuṭṭhāti;**There are offenses one commits knowingly, but clears unknowingly.*";
P_HTM[7878]="*atthāpatti ajānanto āpajjati, ajānanto vuṭṭhāti;**There are offenses one commits unknowingly, but clears unknowingly.*";
P_HTM[7879]="*atthāpatti jānanto āpajjati, jānanto vuṭṭhāti.**There are offenses one commits knowingly, but clears knowingly.*";
P_HTM[7880]="*Catūhākārehi āpattiṃ āpajjati—**One commits offenses in four ways:*";
P_HTM[7881]="*kāyena āpajjati, vācāya āpajjati, kāyena vācāya āpajjati, kammavācāya āpajjati.**by body, by speech, by body and speech, through a legal procedure.*";
P_HTM[7882]="*Aparehipi catūhākārehi āpattiṃ āpajjati—**One commits offenses in four other ways:*";
P_HTM[7883]="*saṅghamajjhe, gaṇamajjhe, puggalassa santike, liṅgapātubhāvena.**in the midst of the Sangha, in the midst of a group, in the presence of an individual, through the appearance of sexual characteristics.*";
P_HTM[7884]="*Catūhākārehi āpattiyā vuṭṭhāti—**One clears offenses in four ways:*";
P_HTM[7885]="*kāyena vuṭṭhāti, vācāya vuṭṭhāti, kāyena vācāya vuṭṭhāti, kammavācāya vuṭṭhāti.**by body, by speech, by body and speech, through a legal procedure.*";
P_HTM[7886]="*Aparehipi catūhākārehi āpattiyā vuṭṭhāti—**One clears offenses in four other ways:*";
P_HTM[7887]="*saṅghamajjhe, gaṇamajjhe, puggalassa santike, liṅgapātubhāvena.**in the midst of the Sangha, in the midst of a group, in the presence of an individual, through the appearance of sexual characteristics.*";
P_HTM[7888]="*Saha paṭilābhena purimaṃ jahati, pacchime patiṭṭhāti, viññattiyo paṭippassambhanti, paṇṇattiyo nirujjhanti.**When one gets it: one abandons the former, one is established in the latter, asking for things comes to an end, rules cease.*";
P_HTM[7889]="*Saha paṭilābhena pacchimaṃ jahati, purime patiṭṭhāti, viññattiyo paṭippassambhanti, paṇṇattiyo nirujjhanti.**When one gets it: one abandons the latter, one is established in the former, asking for things comes to an end, rules cease.*";
P_HTM[7890]="*Catasso codanā—**There are four kinds of accusing:*";
P_HTM[7891]="*sīlavipattiyā codeti, ācāravipattiyā codeti, diṭṭhivipattiyā codeti, ājīvavipattiyā codeti.**one accuses someone for failure in morality, one accuses someone for failure in conduct, one accuses someone for failure in view, one accuses someone for failure in livelihood.*";
P_HTM[7892]="*Cattāro parivāsā—**There are four kinds of probation:*";
P_HTM[7893]="*paṭicchannaparivāso, appaṭicchannaparivāso, suddhantaparivāso, samodhānaparivāso.**probations for concealed offenses, probations for unconcealed offenses, purifying probations, and simultaneous probations.*";
P_HTM[7894]="*Cattāro mānattā—**There are four kinds of trial periods:*";
P_HTM[7895]="*paṭicchannamānattaṃ, appaṭicchannamānattaṃ, pakkhamānattaṃ, samodhānamānattaṃ.**trial periods for concealed offenses, trial periods for unconcealed offenses, trial periods for a half-month, and simultaneous trial periods.*";
P_HTM[7896]="*Cattāro mānattacārikassa bhikkhuno ratticchedā—**There are four things that stop a monk undertaking the trial period from counting a particular day toward his trial period:*";
P_HTM[7897]="*sahavāso, vippavāso, anārocanā, ūne gaṇe carati.**he stays in the same room as a regular monk; he stays apart from other monks; he doesn’t inform other monks of his status; he travels without a group.*";
P_HTM[7898]="*Cattāro sāmukkaṃsā.**There are four unique things.*";
P_HTM[7899]="*Cattāro paṭiggahitaparibhogā—**There are four kinds of equipment that need to be received:*";
P_HTM[7900]="*yāvakālikaṃ, yāmakālikaṃ, sattāhakālikaṃ, yāvajīvikaṃ.**ordinary food, post-midday tonics, seven-day tonics, and lifetime tonics.*";
P_HTM[7901]="*Cattāri mahāvikaṭāni—**There are four filthy edibles:*";
P_HTM[7902]="*gūtho, muttaṃ, chārikā, mattikā.**feces, urine, ash, and clay.*";
P_HTM[7903]="*Cattāri kammāni—**There are four kinds of legal procedures:*";
P_HTM[7904]="*apalokanakammaṃ, ñattikammaṃ, ñattidutiyakammaṃ, ñatticatutthakammaṃ.**a procedure consisting of getting permission, a procedure consisting of one motion, a procedure consisting of one motion and one announcement, or a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements.*";
P_HTM[7905]="*Aparānipi cattāri kammāni—**There are four other kinds of legal procedures:*";
P_HTM[7906]="*adhammena vaggakammaṃ, adhammena samaggakammaṃ, dhammena vaggakammaṃ, dhammena samaggakammaṃ.**an illegitimate legal procedure done by an incomplete assembly, an illegitimate legal procedure done unanimously, a legitimate legal procedure done by an incomplete assembly, and a legitimate legal procedure done unanimously.*";
P_HTM[7907]="*Catasso vipattiyo—**There are four kinds of failure:*";
P_HTM[7908]="*sīlavipatti, ācāravipatti, diṭṭhivipatti, ājīvavipatti.**Failure in morality, failure in conduct, failure in view, and failure in livelihood.*";
P_HTM[7909]="*Cattāri adhikaraṇāni—**There are four kinds of legal issues:*";
P_HTM[7910]="*vivādādhikaraṇaṃ, anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ, āpattādhikaraṇaṃ, kiccādhikaraṇaṃ.**legal issues arising from disputes, legal issues arising from accusations, legal issues arising from offenses, and legal issues arising from business.*";
P_HTM[7911]="*Cattāro parisadūsanā—**There are four kinds of people that corrupt a gathering:*";
P_HTM[7912]="*bhikkhu dussīlo pāpadhammo parisadūsano, bhikkhunī dussīlā pāpadhammā parisadūsanā, upāsako dussīlo pāpadhammo parisadūsano, upāsikā dussīlā pāpadhammā parisadūsanā.**an immoral monk with bad qualities, an immoral nun with bad qualities, an immoral male lay follower with bad qualities, an immoral female lay follower with bad qualities.*";
P_HTM[7913]="*Cattāro parisasobhanā—**There are four kinds of people that make a gathering shine:*";
P_HTM[7914]="*bhikkhu sīlavā kalyāṇadhammo parisasobhano, bhikkhunī sīlavatī kalyāṇadhammā parisasobhanā, upāsako sīlavā kalyāṇadhammo parisasobhano, upāsikā sīlavatī kalyāṇadhammā parisasobhanā.**a moral monk with good qualities, a moral nun with good qualities, a moral male lay follower with good qualities, a moral female lay follower with good qualities.*";
P_HTM[7915]="*Atthāpatti āgantuko āpajjati, no āvāsiko;**There are offenses committed by new arrivals, not by residents.*";
P_HTM[7916]="*atthāpatti āvāsiko āpajjati, no āgantuko;**There are offenses committed by residents, not by new arrivals.*";
P_HTM[7917]="*atthāpatti āgantuko ceva āpajjati āvāsiko ca;**There are offenses committed both by new arrivals and by residents.*";
P_HTM[7918]="*atthāpatti neva āgantuko āpajjati, no āvāsiko.**There are offenses committed neither by new arrivals nor by residents.*";
P_HTM[7919]="*Atthāpatti gamiko āpajjati, no āvāsiko;**There are offenses committed by those departing, not by residents.*";
P_HTM[7920]="*atthāpatti āvāsiko āpajjati, no gamiko;**There are offenses committed by residents, not by those departing.*";
P_HTM[7921]="*atthāpatti gamiko ceva āpajjati āvāsiko ca;**There are offenses committed both by those departing and by residents.*";
P_HTM[7922]="*atthāpatti neva gamiko āpajjati no āvāsiko.**There are offenses committed neither by those departing nor by residents.*";
P_HTM[7923]="*Atthi vatthunānattatā no āpattinānattatā, atthi āpattinānattatā no vatthunānattatā, atthi vatthunānattatā ceva āpattinānattatā ca, atthi neva vatthunānattatā no āpattinānattatā.**There are rules that have variety in the action that is the basis for the offense, but not in the offense; there are rules that have variety in the offense, but not in the action that is the basis for the offense; there are rules that have variety both in the action that is the basis for the offense and in the offense; there are rules that have variety neither in the action that is the basis for the offense nor in the offense.*";
P_HTM[7924]="*Atthi vatthusabhāgatā no āpattisabhāgatā, atthi āpattisabhāgatā no vatthusabhāgatā, atthi vatthusabhāgatā ceva āpattisabhāgatā ca atthi neva vatthusabhāgatā no āpattisabhāgatā.**There are rules where the action that is the basis for the offense is shared, but not the offense; there are rules where the offense is shared, but not the action that is the basis for the offense; there are rules where both the action that is the basis for the offense and the offense are shared; there are rules where neither the action that is the basis for the offense nor the offense is shared.*";
P_HTM[7925]="*Atthāpatti upajjhāyo āpajjati no saddhivihāriko, atthāpatti saddhivihāriko āpajjati no upajjhāyo, atthāpatti upajjhāyo ceva āpajjati saddhivihāriko ca, atthāpatti neva upajjhāyo āpajjati no saddhivihāriko.**There are offenses committed by the preceptor, but not the student; there are offenses committed by the student, but not the preceptor; there are offenses committed by both the preceptor and the student; there are offenses committed by neither the preceptor nor the student.*";
P_HTM[7926]="*Atthāpatti ācariyo āpajjati no antevāsiko, atthāpatti antevāsiko āpajjati no ācariyo, atthāpatti ācariyo ceva āpajjati antevāsiko ca, atthāpatti neva ācariyo āpajjati no antevāsiko.**There are offenses committed by the teacher, but not the pupil; there are offenses committed by the pupil, but not the teacher; there are offenses committed by both the teacher and the pupil; there are offenses committed by neither the teacher nor the pupil.*";
P_HTM[7927]="*Cattāro paccayā anāpatti vassacchedassa—**There is no offense for breaking the rainy-season residence for these four reasons:*";
P_HTM[7928]="*saṅgho vā bhinno hoti, saṅghaṃ vā bhinditukāmā honti, jīvitantarāyo vā hoti, brahmacariyantarāyo vā hoti.**there is a schism in the Sangha; there are some some who wants to create a schism in the Sangha; there is a danger to life; there is a danger to living the spiritual life.*";
P_HTM[7929]="*Cattāri vacīduccaritāni—**There are four kinds of bad conduct by speech:*";
P_HTM[7930]="*musāvādo, pisuṇā vācā, pharusā vācā, samphappalāpo.**lying, divisive speech, harsh speech, and idle speech.*";
P_HTM[7931]="*Cattāri vacīsucaritāni—**There are four kinds of good conduct by speech:*";
P_HTM[7932]="*saccavācā, apisuṇā vācā, saṇhā vācā, mantā bhāsā.**truthful speech, non-divisive speech, gentle speech, and meaningful speech.*";
P_HTM[7933]="*Atthi ādiyanto garukaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati, payojento lahukaṃ;**There are offenses that are serious when doing them oneself, but light when inciting someone else.*";
P_HTM[7934]="*atthi ādiyanto lahukaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati, payojento garukaṃ;**There are offenses that are light when doing them oneself, but serious when inciting someone else.*";
P_HTM[7935]="*atthi ādiyantopi payojentopi garukaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati;**There are offenses that are serious both when doing them oneself and when inciting someone else.*";
P_HTM[7936]="*atthi ādiyantopi payojentopi lahukaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati.**There are offenses that are light both when doing them oneself and when inciting someone else.*";
P_HTM[7937]="*Atthi puggalo abhivādanāraho, no paccuṭṭhānāraho;**There are people who deserve being bowed down to, but not being stood up for.*";
P_HTM[7938]="*atthi puggalo paccuṭṭhānāraho, no abhivādanāraho;**There are people who deserve being stood up for, but not to being bowed down to.*";
P_HTM[7939]="*atthi puggalo abhivādanāraho ceva paccuṭṭhānāraho ca;**There are people who deserve both being bowed down to and being stood up for.*";
P_HTM[7940]="*atthi puggalo neva abhivādanāraho no paccuṭṭhānāraho.**There are people who deserve neither being bowed down to nor being stood up for.*";
P_HTM[7941]="*Atthi puggalo āsanāraho, no abhivādanāraho;**There are people who deserve a seat, but not being bowed down to.*";
P_HTM[7942]="*atthi puggalo abhivādanāraho, no āsanāraho;**There are people who deserve being bowed down to, but not a seat.*";
P_HTM[7943]="*atthi puggalo āsanāraho ceva abhivādanāraho ca;**There are people who deserve both a seat and being bowed down to.*";
P_HTM[7944]="*atthi puggalo neva āsanāraho no abhivādanāraho.**There are people who deserve neither a seat nor being bowed down to.*";
P_HTM[7945]="*Atthāpatti kāle āpajjati, no vikāle;**There are offenses that one commits at the right time, not at the wrong time.*";
P_HTM[7946]="*atthāpatti vikāle āpajjati, no kāle;**There are offenses that one commits at the wrong time, not at the right time.*";
P_HTM[7947]="*atthāpatti kāle ceva āpajjati vikāle ca;**There are offenses that one commits at both the right time and at the wrong time.*";
P_HTM[7948]="*atthāpatti neva kāle āpajjati no vikāle.**There are offenses that one commits neither at the right time nor at the wrong time.*";
P_HTM[7949]="*Atthi paṭiggahitaṃ kāle kappati, no vikāle;**There are things that are allowable to receive at the right time, but not at the wrong time.*";
P_HTM[7950]="*atthi paṭiggahitaṃ vikāle kappati, no kāle;**There are things that are allowable to receive at the wrong time, but not at the right time.*";
P_HTM[7951]="*atthi paṭiggahitaṃ kāle ceva kappati vikāle ca;**There are things that are allowable to receive both at the right time and at the wrong time.*";
P_HTM[7952]="*atthi paṭiggahitaṃ neva kāle kappati no vikāle.**There are things that are allowable to receive neither at the right time nor at the wrong time.*";
P_HTM[7953]="*Atthāpatti paccantimesu janapadesu āpajjati, no majjhimesu;**There are offenses that one commits in outlying countries, but not in the central Ganges plain.*";
P_HTM[7954]="*atthāpatti majjhimesu janapadesu āpajjati, no paccantimesu;**There are offenses that one commits in the central Ganges plain, but not in outlying countries.*";
P_HTM[7955]="*atthāpatti paccantimesu ceva janapadesu āpajjati majjhimesu ca;**There are offenses that one commits both in outlying countries and in the central Ganges plain.*";
P_HTM[7956]="*atthāpatti neva paccantimesu janapadesu āpajjati no majjhimesu.**There are offenses that one commits neither in outlying countries nor in the central Ganges plain.*";
P_HTM[7957]="*Atthi paccantimesu janapadesu kappati, no majjhimesu;**There are things that are allowable in outlying countries, but not in the central Ganges plain.*";
P_HTM[7958]="*atthi majjhimesu janapadesu kappati, no paccantimesu;**There are things that are allowable in the central Ganges plain, but not in outlying countries.*";
P_HTM[7959]="*atthi paccantimesu ceva janapadesu kappati majjhimesu ca;**There are things that are allowable both in outlying countries and in the central Ganges plain.*";
P_HTM[7960]="*atthi neva paccantimesu janapadesu kappati no majjhimesu.**There are things that are allowable neither in outlying countries nor in the central Ganges plain.*";
P_HTM[7961]="*Atthāpatti anto āpajjati, no bahi;**There are offenses that one commits inside, but not outside.*";
P_HTM[7962]="*atthāpatti bahi āpajjati, no anto;**There are offenses that one commits outside, but not inside.*";
P_HTM[7963]="*atthāpatti anto ceva āpajjati bahi ca;**There are offenses that one commits both inside and outside.*";
P_HTM[7964]="*atthāpatti neva anto āpajjati no bahi.**There are offenses that one commits neither inside nor outside.*";
P_HTM[7965]="*Atthāpatti antosīmāya āpajjati, no bahisīmāya;**There are offenses that one commits inside the monastic boundary, not outside.*";
P_HTM[7966]="*atthāpatti bahisīmāya āpajjati, no antosīmāya;**There are offenses that one commits outside the monastic boundary, not inside.*";
P_HTM[7967]="*atthāpatti antosīmāya ceva āpajjati bahisīmāya ca;**There are offenses that one commits both inside and outside the the monastic boundary.*";
P_HTM[7968]="*atthāpatti neva antosīmāya āpajjati no bahisīmāya.**There are offenses that one commits neither inside nor outside the monastic boundary.*";
P_HTM[7969]="*Atthāpatti gāme āpajjati, no araññe;**There are offenses that one commits in inhabited areas, not in the wilderness.*";
P_HTM[7970]="*atthāpatti araññe āpajjati, no gāme;**There are offenses that one commits in the wilderness, not in inhabited areas.*";
P_HTM[7971]="*atthāpatti gāme ceva āpajjati araññe ca;**There are offenses that one commits both in inhabited areas and in the wilderness.*";
P_HTM[7972]="*atthāpatti neva gāme āpajjati no araññe.**There are offenses that one commits neither in inhabited areas nor in the wilderness.*";
P_HTM[7973]="*Catasso codanā—**There are four kinds of accusing:*";
P_HTM[7974]="*vatthusandassanā, āpattisandassanā, saṃvāsapaṭikkhepo, sāmīcipaṭikkhepo.**pointing out the action that is the basis for an offense, pointing out the offense, prohibiting living together, prohibiting acts of respect.*";
P_HTM[7975]="*Cattāro pubbakiccā.**There are four kinds of preliminary actions.*";
P_HTM[7976]="*Cattāro pattakallā.**There are four kinds of seeming appropriate to.*";
P_HTM[7977]="*Cattāri anaññapācittiyāni.**There are four offenses entailing confession concerning “no other”.*";
P_HTM[7978]="*Catasso bhikkhusammutiyo.**There are four kinds of approval from the monks.*";
P_HTM[7979]="*Cattāri agatigamanāni—**There are four ways of acting that are wrong:*";
P_HTM[7980]="*chandāgatiṃ gacchati, dosāgatiṃ gacchati, mohāgatiṃ gacchati, bhayāgatiṃ gacchati.**one is swayed by desire, ill will, confusion, and fear.*";
P_HTM[7981]="*Cattāri nāgatigamanāni—**There are four ways of acting that are not wrong:*";
P_HTM[7982]="*na chandāgatiṃ gacchati, na dosāgatiṃ gacchati, na mohāgatiṃ gacchati, na bhayāgatiṃ gacchati.**one is not swayed by desire, ill will, confusion, or fear.*";
P_HTM[7983]="*Catūhaṅgehi samannāgato alajjī bhikkhu saṅghaṃ bhindati—**When a shameless monk who has four qualities, he causes a schism in the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[7984]="*chandāgatiṃ gacchanto, dosāgatiṃ gacchanto, mohāgatiṃ gacchanto, bhayāgatiṃ gacchanto.**he is swayed by desire, ill will, confusion, and he fear.*";
P_HTM[7985]="*Catūhaṅgehi samannāgato pesalo bhikkhu bhinnaṃ saṅghaṃ samaggaṃ karoti—**When a good monk who has four qualities, he unites a divided Sangha:*";
P_HTM[7986]="*na chandāgatiṃ gacchanto, na dosāgatiṃ gacchanto, na mohāgatiṃ gacchanto, na bhayāgatiṃ gacchanto.**he is not swayed by desire, ill will, confusion, or fear.*";
P_HTM[7987]="*Catūhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno vinayo na pucchitabbo—**When a monk has four qualities, he should not be asked about the Monastic Law:*";
P_HTM[7988]="*chandāgatiṃ gacchati, dosāgatiṃ gacchati, mohāgatiṃ gacchati, bhayāgatiṃ gacchati.**he is swayed by desire, ill will, confusion, and fear.*";
P_HTM[7989]="*Catūhaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā vinayo na pucchitabbo—**When a monk has four qualities, he should not ask about the Monastic Law:*";
P_HTM[7990]="*chandāgatiṃ gacchati, dosāgatiṃ gacchati, mohāgatiṃ gacchati, bhayāgatiṃ gacchati.**he is swayed by desire, ill will, confusion, and fear.*";
P_HTM[7991]="*Catūhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno vinayo na vissajjetabbo—**When a monk has four qualities, he should not reply to questions about the Monastic Law:*";
P_HTM[7992]="*chandāgatiṃ gacchati, dosāgatiṃ gacchati, mohāgatiṃ gacchati, bhayāgatiṃ gacchati.**he is swayed by desire, ill will, confusion, and fear.*";
P_HTM[7993]="*Catūhaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā vinayo na vissajjetabbo—**When a monk has three qualities, his questions about the Monastic Law should not be replied to:*";
P_HTM[7994]="*chandāgatiṃ gacchati, dosāgatiṃ gacchati, mohāgatiṃ gacchati, bhayāgatiṃ gacchati.**he is swayed by desire, ill will, confusion, and fear.*";
P_HTM[7995]="*Catūhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno anuyogo na dātabbo—**When a monk has four qualities, he should not be allowed to question:*";
P_HTM[7996]="*chandāgatiṃ gacchati, dosāgatiṃ gacchati, mohāgatiṃ gacchati, bhayāgatiṃ gacchati.**he is swayed by desire, ill will, confusion, and fear.*";
P_HTM[7997]="*Catūhaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ vinayo na sākacchitabbo—**When a monk has four qualities, one should not discuss the Monastic Law with him:*";
P_HTM[7998]="*chandāgatiṃ gacchati, dosāgatiṃ gacchati, mohāgatiṃ gacchati, bhayāgatiṃ gacchati.**he is swayed by desire, ill will, confusion, and fear.*";
P_HTM[7999]="*Atthāpatti gilāno āpajjati, no agilāno;**There are offenses that one commits when sick, not when not sick.*";
P_HTM[8000]="*atthāpatti agilāno āpajjati, no gilāno;**There are offenses that one commits when not sick, not when sick.*";
P_HTM[8001]="*atthāpatti gilāno ceva āpajjati agilāno ca;**There are offenses that one commits both when sick and when not sick.*";
P_HTM[8002]="*atthāpatti neva gilāno āpajjati no agilāno.**There are offenses that one commits neither when sick nor when not sick.*";
P_HTM[8003]="*Cattāri adhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni.**There are four kinds of illegitimate cancellations of the Monastic Code.*";
P_HTM[8004]="*Cattāri dhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni.**There are four kinds of legitimate cancellations of the Monastic Code.*";
P_HTM[8005]="*Catukkaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The section on fours is finished.*";
P_HTM[8006]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[8007]="*Sakavācāya kāyena,**“Through one’s own speech, by body,*";
P_HTM[8008]="*pasutto ca acittako;**While sleeping, unintentionally;*";
P_HTM[8009]="*Āpajjanto ca kammena,**And committing, through action,*";
P_HTM[8010]="*vohārā caturo tathā.**And so four on speech.*";
P_HTM[8011]="*Bhikkhūnaṃ bhikkhunīnañca,**The monks have, and the nuns have,*";
P_HTM[8012]="*parikkhāro ca sammukhā;**And requisite, in the presence of;*";
P_HTM[8013]="*Ajānakāye majjhe ca,**Unknowingly, by body, and in the midst of,*";
P_HTM[8014]="*vuṭṭhāti duvidhā tathā.**And so twofold on clears.*";
P_HTM[8015]="*Paṭilābhena codanā,**When one gets it, accusing,*";
P_HTM[8016]="*parivāsā ca vuccati;**And it is called probations;*";
P_HTM[8017]="*Mānattacārikā cāpi,**Trial period, and also undertaking,*";
P_HTM[8018]="*sāmukkaṃsā paṭiggahi.**Unique things, received.*";
P_HTM[8019]="*Mahāvikaṭakammāni,**filthy edibles, legal procedures,*";
P_HTM[8020]="*puna kamme vipattiyo;**Again legal procedures, failures;*";
P_HTM[8021]="*Adhikaraṇā dussīlā ca,**Legal issues, and immoral,*";
P_HTM[8022]="*sobhanāgantukena ca.**Shining, and by new arrivals.*";
P_HTM[8023]="*Gamiko vatthunānattā,**Those departing, variety in the action,*";
P_HTM[8024]="*sabhāgupajjhāyena ca;**Shared, similarity, and with preceptor;*";
P_HTM[8025]="*Ācariyo paccayā vā,**Teacher, reasons,*";
P_HTM[8026]="*duccaritaṃ sucaritaṃ.**Bad conduct, good conduct.*";
P_HTM[8027]="*Ādiyanto puggalo ca,**Doing them oneself, and people,*";
P_HTM[8028]="*araho āsanena ca;**Deserving, and with a seat;*";
P_HTM[8029]="*Kāle ca kappati ceva,**And at the right time, and allowable,*";
P_HTM[8030]="*paccantimesu kappati.**In outlying, allowable.*";
P_HTM[8031]="*Anto anto ca sīmāya,**Inside, and inside the boundary,*";
P_HTM[8032]="*gāme ca codanāya ca;**And in an inhabited area, and accusings;*";
P_HTM[8033]="*Pubbakiccaṃ pattakallaṃ,**Preliminary action, seeming appropriate to,*";
P_HTM[8034]="*anaññā sammutiyo ca.**“No other”, and approval.*";
P_HTM[8035]="*Agati nāgati ceva,**Wrong acting, and not wrong acting,*";
P_HTM[8036]="*alajjī pesalena ca;**Shameless, and good;*";
P_HTM[8037]="*Pucchitabbā duve ceva,**And two on should be asked,*";
P_HTM[8038]="*vissajjeyyā tathā duve;**And another two on should reply;*";
P_HTM[8039]="*Anuyogo ca sākacchā,**And question, discussion,*";
P_HTM[8040]="*gilāno ṭhapanena cāti.**Sick, and with cancellation.”*";
P_HTM[8041]="*5. Pañcakavāra**5. The section on fives*";
P_HTM[8042]="*Pañca āpattiyo.**There are five kinds of offenses.*";
P_HTM[8043]="*Pañca āpattikkhandhā.**There are five classes of offenses.*";
P_HTM[8044]="*Pañca vinītavatthūni.**There are five grounds of training.*";
P_HTM[8045]="*Pañca kammāni ānantarikāni.**There are five kinds of actions with results in the next life.*";
P_HTM[8046]="*Pañca puggalā niyatā.**There are five kinds of people with fixed rebirth.*";
P_HTM[8047]="*Pañca chedanakā āpattiyo.**There are five offenses involving cutting.*";
P_HTM[8048]="*Pañcahākārehi āpattiṃ āpajjati.**There are five reasons for committing an offense.*";
P_HTM[8049]="*Pañca āpattiyo.**There are five kinds of offenses because of lying.*";
P_HTM[8050]="*Musāvādapaccayā pañcahākārehi kammaṃ na upeti—**There are five reasons why a legal procedure is invalid:*";
P_HTM[8051]="*sayaṃ vā kammaṃ na karoti, paraṃ vā na ajjhesati, chandaṃ vā pārisuddhiṃ vā na deti, kayiramāne kamme paṭikkosati, kate vā pana kamme adhammadiṭṭhi hoti.**one does not do the legal procedure oneself; or one does not request someone else; one does not give one’s consent or declare one’s purity; one objects while the legal procedure is being carried out; or one has the view that the completed legal procedure is illegitimate.*";
P_HTM[8052]="*Pañcahākārehi kammaṃ upeti—**There are five reasons why a legal procedure is valid:*";
P_HTM[8053]="*sayaṃ vā kammaṃ karoti, paraṃ vā ajjhesati, chandaṃ vā pārisuddhiṃ vā deti, kayiramāne kamme nappaṭikkosati, kate vā pana kamme dhammadiṭṭhi hoti.**one does the legal procedure oneself; or one requests someone else; one gives one’s consent or declares one’s purity; one does not object while the legal procedure is being carried out; or one has the view that the completed legal procedure is legitimate.*";
P_HTM[8054]="*Pañca piṇḍapātikassa bhikkhuno kappanti—**There are five things that are allowable for a monk who is eating almsfood:*";
P_HTM[8055]="*anāmantacāro, gaṇabhojanaṃ, paramparabhojanaṃ, anadhiṭṭhānaṃ, avikappanā.**visiting families before or after a meal invitation, eating in a group, eating a meal before another, non-determination, non-transfer.*";
P_HTM[8056]="*Pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu ussaṅkitaparisaṅkito hoti—**When a monk has five qualities—whether he is bad or firm in morality—he is suspected and mistrusted:*";
P_HTM[8057]="*pāpabhikkhupi akuppadhammopi vesiyāgocaro vā hoti, vidhavāgocaro vā hoti, thullakumārigocaro vā hoti, paṇḍakagocaro vā hoti, bhikkhunigocaro vā hoti.**he regularly associates with sex workers, widows, single women, _paṇḍakas_, or nuns.*";
P_HTM[8058]="*Pañca telāni—**There are five kinds of oil:*";
P_HTM[8059]="*tilatelaṃ, sāsapatelaṃ, madhukatelaṃ, eraṇḍakatelaṃ, vasātelaṃ.**sesame oil, mustard-seed oil, honey-tree oil, castor oil, and oil from fat.*";
P_HTM[8060]="*Pañca vasāni—**There are five kinds of fat:*";
P_HTM[8061]="*acchavasaṃ, macchavasaṃ, susukāvasaṃ, sūkaravasaṃ, gadrabhavasaṃ.**bear fat, fish fat, alligator fat, pig fat, and donkey fat.*";
P_HTM[8062]="*Pañca byasanāni—**There are five kinds of losses:*";
P_HTM[8063]="*ñātibyasanaṃ, bhogabyasanaṃ, rogabyasanaṃ, sīlabyasanaṃ, diṭṭhibyasanaṃ.**loss of relatives, loss of property, loss of health, loss in morality, and loss of view.*";
P_HTM[8064]="*Pañca sampadā—**There are five kinds of successes:*";
P_HTM[8065]="*ñātisampadā, bhogasampadā, arogasampadā, sīlasampadā, diṭṭhisampadā.**success in relatives, success in property, success in health, success in morality, and success in view.*";
P_HTM[8066]="*Pañca nissayapaṭippassaddhiyo upajjhāyamhā—**There are five reasons why the formal support from a preceptor comes to an end:*";
P_HTM[8067]="*upajjhāyo pakkanto vā hoti, vibbhanto vā, kālaṅkato vā, pakkhasaṅkanto vā, āṇattiyeva pañcamī.**the preceptor goes away; the preceptor disrobes; the preceptor dies; the preceptor joins another faction; or the preceptor orders it.*";
P_HTM[8068]="*Pañca puggalā na upasampādetabbā—**There are five kinds of people who should not be given the full ordination:*";
P_HTM[8069]="*addhānahīno, aṅgahīno, vatthuvipanno, karaṇadukkaṭako, aparipūro.**one lacking in age, one lacking in limbs, one who is deficient as subject, one who has acted wrongly, and one who is incomplete.*";
P_HTM[8070]="*Pañca paṃsukūlāni—**There are five kinds of rags:*";
P_HTM[8071]="*sosānikaṃ, pāpaṇikaṃ, undūrakkhāyikaṃ, upacikakkhāyikaṃ, aggidaḍḍhaṃ.**those from a charnel ground, those from a shop, those eaten by rats, those eaten by termites, those burnt by fire.*";
P_HTM[8072]="*Aparānipi pañca paṃsukūlāni—**There are five other kinds of rags:*";
P_HTM[8073]="*gokhāyikaṃ, ajakkhāyikaṃ, thūpacīvaraṃ, ābhisekikaṃ, gatapaṭiyāgataṃ.**those chewed by cattle, those chewed by goats, those left at a stupa, those discarded from a kingʼs consecration, those taken to and then brought back from a charnel ground.*";
P_HTM[8074]="*Pañca avahārā—**There are five kinds of removing:*";
P_HTM[8075]="*theyyāvahāro, pasayhāvahāro, parikappāvahāro, paṭicchannāvahāro, kusāvahāro.**removing by theft, removing by force, removing dependent on conditions, removing by concealing, removing by drawing lots.*";
P_HTM[8076]="*Pañca mahācorā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**There are five great gangsters to be found in the world.*";
P_HTM[8077]="*Pañca avissajjaniyāni.**There are five things not to be given away.*";
P_HTM[8078]="*Pañca avebhaṅgiyāni.**There are five things not to be shared out.*";
P_HTM[8079]="*Pañcāpattiyo kāyato samuṭṭhanti, na vācato na cittato.**There are five kinds of offenses that originate from body, not from speech and mind.*";
P_HTM[8080]="*Pañcāpattiyo kāyato ca vācato ca samuṭṭhanti, na cittato.**There are five kinds of offenses that originate from body and speech, not from mind.*";
P_HTM[8081]="*Pañcāpattiyo desanāgāminiyo.**There are five kinds of offenses that are confessable.*";
P_HTM[8082]="*Pañca saṅghā.**There are five kinds of Sanghas.*";
P_HTM[8083]="*Pañca pātimokkhuddesā.**There are five ways of reciting the Monastic Code.*";
P_HTM[8084]="*Sabbapaccantimesu janapadesu vinayadharapañcamena gaṇena upasampādetabbaṃ.**In all outlying countries, the full ordination is to be given by a group of five, including one expert on the Monastic Law.*";
P_HTM[8085]="*Pañcānisaṃsā kathinatthāre.**There are five benefits of doing the robe-making procedure.*";
P_HTM[8086]="*Pañca kammāni.**There are five kinds of legal procedures.*";
P_HTM[8087]="*Yāvatatiyake pañca āpattiyo.**There are five “up to three times” offenses.*";
P_HTM[8088]="*Pañcahākārehi adinnaṃ ādiyantassa āpatti pārājikassa.**When five factors are fulfilled, there is an offense entailing expulsion for one who steals.*";
P_HTM[8089]="*Pañcahākārehi adinnaṃ ādiyantassa āpatti thullaccayassa.**When five factors are fulfilled, there is a serious offense for one who steals.*";
P_HTM[8090]="*Pañcahākārehi adinnaṃ ādiyantassa āpatti dukkaṭassa.**When five factors are fulfilled, there is an offense of wrong conduct for one who steals.*";
P_HTM[8091]="*Pañca akappiyāni na paribhuñjitabbāni—**There are five unallowable things that should not be used:*";
P_HTM[8092]="*adinnañca hoti, aviditañca hoti, akappiyañca hoti, appaṭiggahitañca hoti, akatātirittañca hoti.**what has not been given, what is not known about, what is not allowable, what has not been received, and what has not been “made leftover”.*";
P_HTM[8093]="*Pañca kappiyāni paribhuñjitabbāni—**There are five allowable things that may be used:*";
P_HTM[8094]="*dinnañca hoti, viditañca hoti, kappiyañca hoti, paṭiggahitañca hoti, katātirittañca hoti.**what has been given, what is known about, what is allowable, what has been received, and what has been “made leftover”.*";
P_HTM[8095]="*Pañca dānāni apuññāni puññasammatāni lokasmiṃ—**There are five gifts without merit that are considered meritorious in the world:*";
P_HTM[8096]="*majjadānaṃ, samajjadānaṃ, itthidānaṃ, usabhadānaṃ, cittakammadānaṃ.**alcohol, entertainment, a woman, a bull, and a picture.*";
P_HTM[8097]="*Pañca uppannā duppaṭivinodayā—**There are five things that are hard to remove:*";
P_HTM[8098]="*uppanno rāgo duppaṭivinodayo, uppanno doso duppaṭivinodayo, uppanno moho duppaṭivinodayo, uppannaṃ paṭibhānaṃ duppaṭivinodayaṃ, uppannaṃ gamiyacittaṃ duppaṭivinodayaṃ.**desire, ill will, confusion, the desire to speak, and the thought of departing.*";
P_HTM[8099]="*Pañcānisaṃsā sammajjaniyā—**There are five benefits of sweeping:*";
P_HTM[8100]="*sakacittaṃ pasīdati, paracittaṃ pasīdati, devatā attamanā honti, pāsādikasaṃvattanikakammaṃ upacinati, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati.**one’s own mind becomes serene, the minds of others become serene, the gods are pleased, one accumulates actions that lead to being inspiring, at the break-up of the body after death one is reborn in heaven.*";
P_HTM[8101]="*Aparepi pañcānisaṃsā sammajjaniyā—**There are five other benefits of sweeping:*";
P_HTM[8102]="*sakacittaṃ pasīdati, paracittaṃ pasīdati, devatā attamanā honti, satthusāsanaṃ kataṃ hoti, pacchimā janatā diṭṭhānugatiṃ āpajjati.**one’s own mind becomes serene, the minds of others become serene, the gods are pleased, one carries out the Teacher’s instruction, later generations follow one’s example.*";
P_HTM[8103]="*Pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato vinayadharo “bālo” tveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati—**When an expert on the Monastic Law has five qualities, he is reckoned as ignorant:*";
P_HTM[8104]="*attano bhāsapariyantaṃ na uggaṇhāti, parassa bhāsapariyantaṃ na uggaṇhāti, attano bhāsapariyantaṃ na uggahetvā parassa bhāsapariyantaṃ na uggahetvā adhammena kāreti appaṭiññāya.**he does not grasp what is proper for himself to say; he does not grasp what is proper for others to say; not grasping either, he makes them act illegitimately, without their admission.*";
P_HTM[8105]="*Pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato vinayadharo “paṇḍito” tveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati—**When an expert on the Monastic Law has five qualities, he is reckoned as wise:*";
P_HTM[8106]="*attano bhāsapariyantaṃ uggaṇhāti, parassa bhāsapariyantaṃ uggaṇhāti, attano bhāsapariyantaṃ uggahetvā parassa bhāsapariyantaṃ uggahetvā dhammena kāreti paṭiññāya.**he grasps what is proper for himself to say; he grasps what is proper for others to say; grasping both, he makes them act legitimately, in accordance with their admission.*";
P_HTM[8107]="*Aparehipi pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato vinayadharo “bālo” tveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati—**When an expert on the Monastic Law has five other qualities, he is reckoned as ignorant:*";
P_HTM[8108]="*āpattiṃ na jānāti, āpattiyā mūlaṃ na jānāti, āpattisamudayaṃ na jānāti, āpattinirodhaṃ na jānāti, āpattinirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ na jānāti.**he does not know the offenses; he does not know the sources of offenses; he does not know the origin of offenses; he does not know the ending of offenses; he does not know the path leading to the ending of offenses.*";
P_HTM[8109]="*Pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato vinayadharo “paṇḍito” tveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati—**When an expert on the Monastic Law has five qualities, he is reckoned as wise:*";
P_HTM[8110]="*āpattiṃ jānāti, āpattiyā mūlaṃ jānāti, āpattisamudayaṃ jānāti, āpattinirodhaṃ jānāti, āpattinirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ jānāti.**he knows the offenses; he knows the sources of offenses; he knows the origin of offenses; he knows the ending of offenses; he knows the path leading to the ending of offenses.*";
P_HTM[8111]="*Aparehipi pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato vinayadharo “bālo” tveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati—**When an expert on the Monastic Law has five other qualities, he is reckoned as ignorant:*";
P_HTM[8112]="*adhikaraṇaṃ na jānāti, adhikaraṇassa mūlaṃ na jānāti, adhikaraṇasamudayaṃ na jānāti, adhikaraṇanirodhaṃ na jānāti, adhikaraṇanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ na jānāti.**he does not know the legal issues; he does not know the source of the legal issues; he does not know the origin of the legal issues; he does not know the ending of the legal issues; he does not know the path leading to the ending of the legal issues.*";
P_HTM[8113]="*Pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato vinayadharo “paṇḍito” tveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati—**When an expert on the Monastic Law has five qualities, he is reckoned as wise:*";
P_HTM[8114]="*adhikaraṇaṃ jānāti, adhikaraṇassa mūlaṃ jānāti, adhikaraṇasamudayaṃ jānāti, adhikaraṇanirodhaṃ jānāti, adhikaraṇanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ jānāti.**he knows legal issues; he knows the source of legal issues; he knows the origin of legal issues; he knows the ending of legal issues; he knows the path leading to the ending of legal issues.*";
P_HTM[8115]="*Aparehipi pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato vinayadharo “bālo” tveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati—**When an expert on the Monastic Law has five other qualities, he is reckoned as ignorant:*";
P_HTM[8116]="*vatthuṃ na jānāti, nidānaṃ na jānāti, paññattiṃ na jānāti, anupaññattiṃ na jānāti, anusandhivacanapathaṃ na jānāti.**he does not know the actions that are the basis for offenses; he does not know the origin stories; he does not know the rules; he does not know the additions to the rules; he does not know the sequence of statements.*";
P_HTM[8117]="*Pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato vinayadharo “paṇḍito” tveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati—**When an expert on the Monastic Law has five qualities, he is reckoned as wise:*";
P_HTM[8118]="*vatthuṃ jānāti, nidānaṃ jānāti, paññattiṃ jānāti, anupaññattiṃ jānāti, anusandhivacanapathaṃ jānāti.**he knows the actions that are the basis for offenses; he knows the origin stories; he knows the rules; he knows the additions to the rules; he knows the sequence of statements.*";
P_HTM[8119]="*Aparehipi pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato vinayadharo “bālo” tveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati—**When an expert on the Monastic Law has five other qualities, he is reckoned as ignorant:*";
P_HTM[8120]="*ñattiṃ na jānāti, ñattiyā karaṇaṃ na jānāti, na pubbakusalo hoti, na aparakusalo hoti, akālaññū ca hoti.**he does not know the motion; he does not know how the motion is done; he is not skilled in what comes first; he is not skilled in what comes afterwards; he does not know the right time.*";
P_HTM[8121]="*Pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato vinayadharo “paṇḍito” tveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati—**When an expert on the Monastic Law has five qualities, he is reckoned as wise:*";
P_HTM[8122]="*ñattiṃ jānāti, ñattiyā karaṇaṃ jānāti, pubbakusalo hoti, aparakusalo hoti, kālaññū ca hoti.**he knows the motion; he knows how the motion is done; he is skilled in what comes first; he is skilled in what comes afterwards; he knows the right time.*";
P_HTM[8123]="*Aparehipi pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato vinayadharo “bālo” tveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati—**When an expert on the Monastic Law has five other qualities, he is reckoned as ignorant:*";
P_HTM[8124]="*āpattānāpattiṃ na jānāti, lahukagarukaṃ āpattiṃ na jānāti, sāvasesānavasesaṃ āpattiṃ na jānāti, duṭṭhullāduṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ na jānāti, ācariyaparamparā kho panassa na suggahitā hoti na sumanasikatā na sūpadhāritā.**he does not know the offenses and non-offenses; he does not know the light and heavy offenses; he does not know the curable and incurable offenses; he does not know the grave and minor offenses; he has not well-learned or well-remembered his teachers’ tradition.*";
P_HTM[8125]="*Pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato vinayadharo “paṇḍito” tveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati—**When an expert on the Monastic Law has five qualities, he is reckoned as wise:*";
P_HTM[8126]="*āpattānāpattiṃ jānāti, lahukagarukaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, sāvasesānavasesaṃ āpattiṃ jānati, duṭṭhullāduṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, ācariyaparamparā kho panassa suggahitā hoti sumanasikatā sūpadhāritā.**he knows the offenses and non-offenses; he knows the light and heavy offenses; he knows the curable and incurable offenses; he knows the grave and minor offenses; he has well-learned and well-remembered his teachers’ tradition.*";
P_HTM[8127]="*Aparehipi pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato vinayadharo “bālo” tveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati—**When an expert on the Monastic Law has five other qualities, he is reckoned as ignorant:*";
P_HTM[8128]="*āpattānāpattiṃ na jānāti, lahukagarukaṃ āpattiṃ na jānāti, sāvasesānavasesaṃ āpattiṃ na jānāti, duṭṭhullāduṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, ubhayāni kho panassa pātimokkhāni na vitthārena svāgatāni honti na suvibhattāni na suppavattīni na suvinicchitāni suttaso anubyañjanaso.**he does not know the offenses and non-offenses; he does not know the light and heavy offenses; he does not know the curable and incurable offenses; he does not know the grave and minor offenses; he has not properly learned both Monastic Codes in detail, not having analyzed them well, thoroughly mastered them, or investigated them well, both in terms of the rules and their detailed exposition.*";
P_HTM[8129]="*Pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato vinayadharo “paṇḍito” tveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati—**When an expert on the Monastic Law has five qualities, he is reckoned as wise:*";
P_HTM[8130]="*āpattānāpattiṃ jānāti, lahukagarukaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, sāvasesānavasesaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, duṭṭhullāduṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, ubhayāni kho panassa pātimokkhāni vitthārena svāgatāni honti suvibhattāni suppavattīni suvinicchitāni suttaso anubyañjanaso.**he knows the offenses and non-offenses; he knows the light and heavy offenses; he knows the curable and incurable offenses; he knows the grave and minor offenses; he has properly learned both Monastic Codes in detail, having analyzed them well, thoroughly mastered them, and investigated them well, both in terms of the rules and their detailed exposition.*";
P_HTM[8131]="*Aparehipi pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato vinayadharo “bālo” tveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati—**When an expert on the Monastic Law has five other qualities, he is reckoned as ignorant:*";
P_HTM[8132]="*āpattānāpattiṃ na jānāti, lahukagarukaṃ āpattiṃ na jānāti, sāvasesānavasesaṃ āpattiṃ na jānāti, duṭṭhullāduṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ na jānāti, adhikaraṇe ca na vinicchayakusalo hoti.**he does not know the offenses and non-offenses; he does not know the light and heavy offenses; he does not know the curable and incurable offenses; he does not know the grave and minor offenses; he is not skilled in legal issues and deliberations.*";
P_HTM[8133]="*Pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato vinayadharo “paṇḍito” tveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati—**When an expert on the Monastic Law has five qualities, he is reckoned as wise:*";
P_HTM[8134]="*āpattānāpattiṃ jānāti, lahukagarukaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, sāvasesānavasesaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, duṭṭhullāduṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, adhikaraṇe ca vinicchayakusalo hoti.**he knows the offenses and non-offenses; he knows the light and heavy offenses; he knows the curable and incurable offenses; he knows the grave and minor offenses; he is skilled in legal issues and deliberations.*";
P_HTM[8135]="*Pañca āraññikā—**There are five kinds of wilderness dwellers:*";
P_HTM[8136]="*mandattā momūhattā āraññiko hoti, pāpiccho icchāpakato āraññiko hoti, ummādā cittakkhepā āraññiko hoti, “vaṇṇitaṃ buddhehi buddhasāvakehī”ti āraññiko hoti, api ca appicchaññeva nissāya santuṭṭhiññeva nissāya sallekhaññeva nissāya pavivekaññeva nissāya idamatthitaññeva nissāya āraññiko hoti.**one may be a wilderness dweller because of stupidity and folly; because one is overcome by bad desires; because of insanity and derangement; because it is praised by the Buddhas and their disciples; or because of fewness of wishes, contentment, self-elimination, seclusion, and wanting it.*";
P_HTM[8137]="*Pañca piṇḍapātikā …pe…**There are five kinds of people who only eat almsfood …*";
P_HTM[8138]="*pañca paṃsukūlikā …pe…**There are five kinds of rag-robe wearers …*";
P_HTM[8139]="*pañca rukkhamūlikā …pe…**There are these five kinds of people who live at the foot of a tree …*";
P_HTM[8140]="*pañca sosānikā …pe…**There are five kinds of people who live in charnel grounds …*";
P_HTM[8141]="*pañca abbhokāsikā …pe…**There are five kinds of people who live out in the open …*";
P_HTM[8142]="*pañca tecīvarikā …pe…**There are five kinds of people who only have three robes …*";
P_HTM[8143]="*pañca sapadānacārikā …pe…**There are five kinds of people who go on continuous almsround …*";
P_HTM[8144]="*pañca nesajjikā …pe…**There are five kinds of people who never lie down …*";
P_HTM[8145]="*pañca yathāsanthatikā …pe…**There are five kinds of people who accept any resting place …*";
P_HTM[8146]="*pañca ekāsanikā …pe…**There are five kinds of people who eat in one sitting per day …*";
P_HTM[8147]="*pañca khalupacchābhattikā …pe…**There are five kinds of people who refuse to accept food offered after the meal has begun …*";
P_HTM[8148]="*pañca pattapiṇḍikā—**There are five kinds of people who eat only from the almsbowl:*";
P_HTM[8149]="*mandattā momūhattā pattapiṇḍiko hoti, pāpiccho icchāpakato pattapiṇḍiko hoti, ummādā cittakkhepā pattapiṇḍiko hoti, “vaṇṇitaṃ buddhehi buddhasāvakehī”ti pattapiṇḍiko hoti, api ca appicchaññeva nissāya santuṭṭhiññeva nissāya sallekhaññeva nissāya pavivekaññeva nissāya idamatthitaññeva nissāya pattapiṇḍiko hoti.**one may be someone who eats only from the almsbowl because of stupidity and folly; because one is overcome by bad desires; because of insanity and derangement; because it is praised by the Buddhas and their disciples; or because of fewness of wishes, contentment, self-elimination, seclusion, and wanting it.*";
P_HTM[8150]="*Pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā nānissitena vatthabbaṃ—**When a monk has five qualities, he should not live without formal support:*";
P_HTM[8151]="*uposathaṃ na jānāti, uposathakammaṃ na jānāti, pātimokkhaṃ na jānāti, pātimokkhuddesaṃ na jānāti, ūnapañcavasso hoti.**he does not know about the observance day; he does not know the observance-day procedure; he does not know the Monastic Code; he does not know the recitation of the Monastic Code; he has less than five years of seniority.*";
P_HTM[8152]="*Pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā anissitena vatthabbaṃ—**When a monk has five qualities, he may live without formal support:*";
P_HTM[8153]="*uposathaṃ jānāti, uposathakammaṃ jānāti, pātimokkhaṃ jānāti, pātimokkhuddesaṃ jānāti, pañcavasso vā hoti atirekapañcavasso vā.**he knows about the observance day; he knows the observance-day procedure; he knows the Monastic Code; he knows the recitation of the Monastic Code; he has five or more years of seniority.*";
P_HTM[8154]="*Aparehipi pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā nānissitena vatthabbaṃ—**When a monk has five other qualities, he should not live without formal support:*";
P_HTM[8155]="*pavāraṇaṃ na jānāti, pavāraṇākammaṃ na jānāti, pātimokkhaṃ na jānāti, pātimokkhuddesaṃ na jānāti, ūnapañcavasso hoti.**he does not know about the invitation day; he does not know the invitation-day procedure; he does not know the Monastic Code; he does not know the recitation of the Monastic Code; he has less than five years of seniority.*";
P_HTM[8156]="*Pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā anissitena vatthabbaṃ—**When a monk has five qualities, he may live without formal support:*";
P_HTM[8157]="*pavāraṇaṃ jānāti, pavāraṇākammaṃ jānāti, pātimokkhaṃ jānāti, pātimokkhuddesaṃ jānāti, pañcavasso vā hoti atirekapañcavasso vā.**he knows about the invitation day; he knows the invitation-day procedure; he knows the Monastic Code; he knows the recitation of the Monastic Code; he has five or more years of seniority.*";
P_HTM[8158]="*Aparehipi pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā nānissitena vatthabbaṃ—**When a monk has five other qualities, he should not live without formal support:*";
P_HTM[8159]="*āpattānāpattiṃ na jānāti, lahukagarukaṃ āpattiṃ na jānāti, sāvasesānavasesaṃ āpattiṃ na jānāti, duṭṭhullāduṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ na jānāti, ūnapañcavasso hoti.**he does not know the offenses and non-offenses; he does not know the light and heavy offenses; he does not know the curable and incurable offenses; he does not know the grave and minor offenses; he has less than five years of seniority.*";
P_HTM[8160]="*Pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā anissitena vatthabbaṃ—**When a monk has five qualities, he may live without formal support:*";
P_HTM[8161]="*āpattānāpattiṃ jānāti, lahukagarukaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, sāvasesānavasesaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, duṭṭhullāduṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, pañcavasso vā hoti atirekapañcavasso vā.**he knows the offenses and non-offenses; he knows the light and heavy offenses; he knows the curable and incurable offenses; he knows the grave and minor offenses; he has five or more years of seniority.*";
P_HTM[8162]="*Pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatāya bhikkhuniyā nānissitāya vatthabbaṃ—**A nun who is possessed of five qualities should not live independently:*";
P_HTM[8163]="*uposathaṃ na jānāti, uposathakammaṃ na jānāti, pātimokkhaṃ na jānāti, pātimokkhuddesaṃ na jānāti, ūnapañcavassā hoti.**she does not know about the observance day; she does not know the observance-day procedure; she does not know the Monastic Code; she does not know the recitation of the Monastic Code; she has less than five years of seniority.*";
P_HTM[8164]="*Pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatāya bhikkhuniyā anissitāya vatthabbaṃ—**When a nun has five qualities, she may live without formal support:*";
P_HTM[8165]="*uposathaṃ jānāti, uposathakammaṃ jānāti, pātimokkhaṃ jānāti, pātimokkhuddesaṃ jānāti, pañcavassā vā hoti atirekapañcavassā vā.**she knows about the observance day; she knows the observance-day procedure; she knows the Monastic Code; she knows the recitation of the Monastic Code; she has five or more years of seniority.*";
P_HTM[8166]="*Aparehipi pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatāya bhikkhuniyā nānissitāya vatthabbaṃ—**When a nun has five other qualities, she should not live without formal support:*";
P_HTM[8167]="*pavāraṇaṃ na jānāti, pavāraṇākammaṃ na jānāti, pātimokkhaṃ na jānāti, pātimokkhuddesaṃ na jānāti, ūnapañcavassā hoti.**she does not know about the invitation day; she does not know the invitation-day procedure; she does not know the Monastic Code; she does not know the recitation of the Monastic Code; she has less than five years of seniority.*";
P_HTM[8168]="*Pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatāya bhikkhuniyā anissitāya vatthabbaṃ—**When a nun has five qualities, she may live without formal support:*";
P_HTM[8169]="*pavāraṇaṃ jānāti, pavāraṇākammaṃ jānāti, pātimokkhaṃ jānāti, pātimokkhuddesaṃ jānāti, pañcavassā vā hoti atirekapañcavassā vā.**she knows about the invitation day; she knows the invitation-day procedure; she knows the Monastic Code; she knows the recitation of the Monastic Code; she has five or more years of seniority.*";
P_HTM[8170]="*Aparehipi pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatāya bhikkhuniyā nānissitāya vatthabbaṃ—**When a nun has five other qualities, she should not live without formal support:*";
P_HTM[8171]="*āpattānāpattiṃ na jānāti, lahukagarukaṃ āpattiṃ na jānāti, sāvasesānavasesaṃ āpattiṃ na jānāti, duṭṭhullāduṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ na jānāti, ūnapañcavassā hoti.**she does not know the offenses and non-offenses; she does not know the light and heavy offenses; she does not know the curable and incurable offenses; she does not know the grave and minor offenses; she has less than five years of seniority.*";
P_HTM[8172]="*Pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatāya bhikkhuniyā anissitāya vatthabbaṃ—**When a nun has five qualities, she may live without formal support:*";
P_HTM[8173]="*āpattānāpattiṃ jānāti, lahukagarukaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, sāvasesānavasesaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, duṭṭhullāduṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, pañcavassā vā hoti atirekapañcavassā vā.**she knows the offenses and non-offenses; she knows the light and heavy offenses; she knows the curable and incurable offenses; she knows the grave and minor offenses; she has five or more years of seniority.*";
P_HTM[8174]="*Pañca ādīnavā apāsādike—**There are five dangers in being uninspiring:*";
P_HTM[8175]="*attāpi attānaṃ upavadati, anuviccapi viññū garahanti, pāpako kittisaddo abbhuggacchati, sammūḷho kālaṃ karoti, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati.**You criticize yourself; after investigating, wise people condemn you; you get a bad reputation; you die confused; after death, you are reborn in a lower realm.*";
P_HTM[8176]="*Pañcānisaṃsā pāsādike—**There are five benefits in being inspiring:*";
P_HTM[8177]="*attāpi attānaṃ na upavadati, anuviccapi viññū pasaṃsanti, kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggacchati, asammūḷho kālaṃ karoti, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati.**You do not criticize yourself; after investigating, wise people praise you; you get a good reputation; you die unconfused; after death, you are reborn in heaven.*";
P_HTM[8178]="*Aparepi pañca ādīnavā apāsādike—**There are five other dangers in being uninspiring:*";
P_HTM[8179]="*appasannā na pasīdanti, pasannānaṃ ekaccānaṃ aññathattaṃ hoti, satthusāsanaṃ akataṃ hoti, pacchimā janatā diṭṭhānugatiṃ nāpajjati, cittamassa na pasīdati.**you hinder confidence in those without it; you cause some to lose their confidence; you don’t carry out the Teacher’s instructions; later generations follow your example; your mind doesn’t become serene.*";
P_HTM[8180]="*Pañcānisaṃsā pāsādike—**There are five benefits in being inspiring:*";
P_HTM[8181]="*appasannā pasīdanti, pasannānaṃ bhiyyobhāvāya hoti, satthusāsanaṃ kataṃ hoti, pacchimā janatā diṭṭhānugatiṃ āpajjati, cittamassa pasīdati.**you give rise confidence in those without it; you increase the confidence of those who have it; you carry out the Teacher’s instructions; later generations follow your example; your mind becomes serene.*";
P_HTM[8182]="*Pañca ādīnavā kulūpake—**There are five dangers in associating with families:*";
P_HTM[8183]="*anāmantacāre āpajjati, raho nisajjāya āpajjati, paṭicchanne āsane āpajjati, mātugāmassa uttarichappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ desento āpajjati, kāmasaṅkappabahulo ca viharati.**he commits the offense of visiting families before or after a meal invitation; he commits the offense of sitting in private with a woman; he commits the offense of sitting on a concealed seat with a woman; he commits the offense of teaching more than five or six sentences to a woman; he has a lot of sensual thoughts.*";
P_HTM[8184]="*Pañca ādīnavā kulūpakassa bhikkhuno—**There are five dangers for a monk who associates with families:*";
P_HTM[8185]="*ativelaṃ kulesu saṃsaṭṭhassa viharato mātugāmassa abhiṇhadassanaṃ, dassane sati saṃsaggo, saṃsagge sati vissāso, vissāse sati otāro, otiṇṇacittassetaṃ bhikkhuno pāṭikaṅkhaṃ anabhirato vā brahmacariyaṃ carissati aññataraṃ vā saṅkiliṭṭhaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjissati sikkhaṃ vā paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattissati.**when he associates too much with families, he often sees women; because of seeings them, he associates with them; because of associating with them, there is intimacy; because of intimacy, there is weakness; because his mind is overcome by lust, it is to be expected that he will be dissatisfied with the spiritual life, that he commits a certain defiled offense, or that he will renounce the training and return to the lower life.*";
P_HTM[8186]="*Pañca bījajātāni—**There are five kinds of propagation:*";
P_HTM[8187]="*mūlabījaṃ, khandhabījaṃ, phaḷubījaṃ, aggabījaṃ, bījabījaññeva pañcamaṃ.**propagation from roots, propagation from stems, propagation from joints, propagation from cuttings, and propagation from regular seeds as the fifth.*";
P_HTM[8188]="*Pañcahi samaṇakappehi phalaṃ paribhuñjitabbaṃ—**When fruit is allowable for monastics for any of five reasons, it may be eaten:*";
P_HTM[8189]="*aggiparijitaṃ, satthaparijitaṃ, nakhaparijitaṃ, abījaṃ, nibbattabījaññeva pañcamaṃ.**it has been damaged by fire, it has been damaged by a knife, it has been damaged by a nail, it’s seedless, the seeds have been removed.*";
P_HTM[8190]="*Pañca visuddhiyo—**There are five kinds of purification:*";
P_HTM[8191]="*nidānaṃ uddisitvā avasesaṃ sutena sāvetabbaṃ, ayaṃ paṭhamā visuddhi;**After reciting the introduction, the rest is announced as if heard.*";
P_HTM[8192]="*nidānaṃ uddisitvā cattāri pārājikāni uddisitvā avasesaṃ sutena sāvetabbaṃ, ayaṃ dutiyā visuddhi;**After reciting the introduction and the four rules entailing expulsion, the rest is announced as if heard.*";
P_HTM[8193]="*nidānaṃ uddisitvā cattāri pārājikāni uddisitvā terasa saṅghādisese uddisitvā avasesaṃ sutena sāvetabbaṃ, ayaṃ tatiyā visuddhi;**After reciting the introduction, the four rules entailing expulsion, and the thirteen rules entailing suspension, the rest is announced as if heard.*";
P_HTM[8194]="*nidānaṃ uddisitvā cattāri pārājikāni uddisitvā terasa saṅghādisese uddisitvā dve aniyate uddisitvā avasesaṃ sutena sāvetabbaṃ, ayaṃ catutthā visuddhi;**After reciting the introduction, the four rules entailing expulsion, the thirteen rules entailing suspension, and the two undetermined rules, the rest is announced as if heard.*";
P_HTM[8195]="*vitthāreneva pañcamī.**In full is the fifth.*";
P_HTM[8196]="*Aparāpi pañca visuddhiyo—**There are five other kinds of purification:*";
P_HTM[8197]="*suttuddeso, pārisuddhiuposatho, adhiṭṭhānuposatho, pavāraṇā, sāmaggīuposathoyeva pañcamo.**the observance-day procedure which consists of reciting the Monastic Code, the observance-day procedure which consists of declaring purity, the observance-day procedure which consists of a determination, the invitation procedure, and the unity observance day as the fifth.*";
P_HTM[8198]="*Pañcānisaṃsā vinayadhare—**There are five benefits of being an expert on the Monastic Law:*";
P_HTM[8199]="*attano sīlakkhandho sugutto hoti surakkhito, kukkuccapakatānaṃ paṭisaraṇaṃ hoti, visārado saṅghamajjhe voharati, paccatthike sahadhammena suniggahitaṃ niggaṇhāti, saddhammaṭṭhitiyā paṭipanno hoti.**your own morality is well guarded; you are a refuge for those who are habitually anxious; you speak with confidence in the midst of the Sangha; you can legitimately and properly refute an opponent; you are practicing for the longevity of the true Teaching.*";
P_HTM[8200]="*Pañca adhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni.**There are five kinds of illegitimate cancellations of the Monastic Code:*";
P_HTM[8201]="*Pañca dhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanānīti.**There are five kinds of legitimate cancellations of the Monastic Code:*";
P_HTM[8202]="*Pañcakaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The section on fives is finished.*";
P_HTM[8203]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[8204]="*Āpatti āpattikkhandhā,**“Offense, classes of offenses,*";
P_HTM[8205]="*vinītānantarena ca;**Training, and with the next life;*";
P_HTM[8206]="*Puggalā chedanā ceva,**People, and also cutting,*";
P_HTM[8207]="*āpajjati ca paccayā.**And committing, reasons.*";
P_HTM[8208]="*Na upeti upeti ca,**Invalid, and valid,*";
P_HTM[8209]="*kappantusaṅkitelañca;**Allowable, suspected, and oil;*";
P_HTM[8210]="*Vasaṃ byasanā sampadā,**Fat, loss, success,*";
P_HTM[8211]="*passaddhi puggalena ca.**Comes to an end, and with people.*";
P_HTM[8212]="*Sosānikaṃ khāyitañca,**Charnel ground, and chewed,*";
P_HTM[8213]="*theyyaṃ coro ca vuccati;**Theft, and one called a gangster;*";
P_HTM[8214]="*Avissajji avebhaṅgi,**Not to be given away, not to be shared out,*";
P_HTM[8215]="*kāyato kāyavācato.**From body, from body and speech.*";
P_HTM[8216]="*Desanā saṅghaṃ uddesaṃ,**Confessable, Sangha, recitating,*";
P_HTM[8217]="*paccantikathinena ca;**Outlying, and with the robe-making procedure;*";
P_HTM[8218]="*Kammāni yāvatatiyaṃ,**Legal procedures, up to three times,*";
P_HTM[8219]="*pārājithulladukkaṭaṃ.**An offense entailing expulsion, a serious offense, wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[8220]="*Akappiyaṃ kappiyañca,**Unallowable, and allowable,*";
P_HTM[8221]="*apuññaduvinodayā;**Without merit, hard to remove;*";
P_HTM[8222]="*Sammajjanī apare ca,**Sweeping, and other,*";
P_HTM[8223]="*bhāsaṃ āpattimeva ca.**To say, and also offenses.*";
P_HTM[8224]="*Adhikaraṇaṃ vatthu ñatti,**Legal issues, the actions that are the basis for offenses, motion,*";
P_HTM[8225]="*āpattā ubhayāni ca;**And both offenses and non-offenses;*";
P_HTM[8226]="*Lahukaṭṭhamakā ete,**These are light and strong,*";
P_HTM[8227]="*kaṇhasukkā vijānatha.**Understanding dark and bright.*";
P_HTM[8228]="*Araññaṃ piṇḍapātañca,**Wilderness, and almsfood,*";
P_HTM[8229]="*paṃsurukkhasusānikā;**Rag-robe, tree, people who live in charnel grounds;*";
P_HTM[8230]="*Abbhokāso cīvarañca,**Out in the open, and robe,*";
P_HTM[8231]="*sapadāno nisajjiko.**Continuous, people who never lie down.*";
P_HTM[8232]="*Santhati khalu pacchāpi,**Resting place, also after,*";
P_HTM[8233]="*pattapiṇḍikameva ca;**And people who eat only from the bowl;*";
P_HTM[8234]="*Uposathaṃ pavāraṇaṃ,**Observance day, invitation day,*";
P_HTM[8235]="*āpattānāpattipi ca.**And also offenses and non-offenses.*";
P_HTM[8236]="*Kaṇhasukkapadā ete,**These verses on dark and bright,*";
P_HTM[8237]="*bhikkhunīnampi te tathā;**And so they are for the nuns;*";
P_HTM[8238]="*Apāsādikapāsādi,**Being uninspiring, being inspiring,*";
P_HTM[8239]="*tatheva apare duve.**And so two others.*";
P_HTM[8240]="*Kulūpake ativelaṃ,**Associating with families, too much,*";
P_HTM[8241]="*bījaṃ samaṇakappi ca;**Propagation, and allowable for monastics;*";
P_HTM[8242]="*Visuddhi apare ceva,**Purification, and a another,*";
P_HTM[8243]="*vinayādhammikena ca;**Monastic Law, and with illegitimate;*";
P_HTM[8244]="*Dhammikā ca tathā vuttā,**And so legitimate is spoken of.*";
P_HTM[8245]="*niṭṭhitā suddhipañcakāti.**The basic section on fives is finished.”*";
P_HTM[8246]="*6. Chakkavāra**6. The section on sixes*";
P_HTM[8247]="*Cha agāravā.**“There are six kinds of disrespect.*";
P_HTM[8248]="*Cha gāravā.**There are six kinds of respect.*";
P_HTM[8249]="*Cha vinītavatthūni.**There are six grounds of training.*";
P_HTM[8250]="*Cha sāmīciyo.**There are six proper ways.*";
P_HTM[8251]="*Cha āpattisamuṭṭhānā.**There are six origins of offenses.*";
P_HTM[8252]="*Chacchedanakā āpattiyo.**There are six offenses involving cutting.*";
P_HTM[8253]="*Chahākārehi āpattiṃ āpajjati.**There are six ways of committing an offense.*";
P_HTM[8254]="*Chānisaṃsā vinayadhare.**There are six benefits of being an expert on the Monastic Law.*";
P_HTM[8255]="*Cha paramāni.**There are six rules about ‘at the most’.*";
P_HTM[8256]="*Chārattaṃ ticīvarena vippavasitabbaṃ.**One may be stay apart from one’s three robes for six days.*";
P_HTM[8257]="*Cha cīvarāni.**There are six kinds of robe-cloth.*";
P_HTM[8258]="*Cha rajanāni.**There are six kinds of dye.*";
P_HTM[8259]="*Cha āpattiyo kāyato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhanti na vācato.**There are six offenses that originate from body and mind, not from speech.*";
P_HTM[8260]="*Cha āpattiyo vācato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhanti na kāyato.**There are six offenses that originate from speech and mind, not from body.*";
P_HTM[8261]="*Cha āpattiyo kāyato ca vācato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhanti.**There are six offenses that originate from body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[8262]="*Cha kammāni.**There are six kinds of legal procedures.*";
P_HTM[8263]="*Cha vivādamūlāni.**There are six sources of disputes.*";
P_HTM[8264]="*Cha anuvādamūlāni.**There are six sources of accusations.*";
P_HTM[8265]="*Cha sāraṇīyā dhammā.**There are six aspects of friendliness.*";
P_HTM[8266]="*Dīghaso cha vidatthiyo, sugatavidatthiyā.**Six standard handspans in length.*";
P_HTM[8267]="*Tiriyaṃ cha vidatthiyo.**Six handspans wide.*";
P_HTM[8268]="*Cha nissayapaṭippassaddhiyo ācariyamhā.**There are six reasons why the formal support from a teacher comes to an end.*";
P_HTM[8269]="*Cha nahāne anupaññattiyo.**There are six additions to the rule on bathing.*";
P_HTM[8270]="*Vippakatacīvaraṃ ādāya pakkamati.**Takes an unfinished robe and leaves the monastery.*";
P_HTM[8271]="*Vippakatacīvaraṃ samādāya pakkamati.**Leaves the monastery with an unfinished robe.*";
P_HTM[8272]="*Chahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā upasampādetabbaṃ nissayo dātabbo sāmaṇero upaṭṭhāpetabbo—**When a monk who has six qualities, he may give the full ordination, give formal support, and have a novice monk attend on him:*";
P_HTM[8273]="*asekkhena sīlakkhandhena samannāgato hoti, asekkhena samādhikkhandhena samannāgato hoti, asekkhena paññakkhandhena samannāgato hoti, asekkhena vimuttikkhandhena samannāgato hoti, asekkhena vimuttiñāṇadassanakkhandhena samannāgato hoti, dasavasso vā hoti atirekadasavasso vā.**he has the virtue, stillness, wisdom, freedom, and knowledge and vision of freedom of one who is fully trained, and he has ten or more years of seniority.*";
P_HTM[8274]="*Aparehipi chahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā upasampādetabbaṃ nissayo dātabbo sāmaṇero upaṭṭhāpetabbo—**When a monk who has six other qualities, he may give the full ordination, give formal support, and have a novice monk attend on him:*";
P_HTM[8275]="*attanā asekkhena sīlakkhandhena samannāgato hoti, paraṃ asekkhe sīlakkhandhe samādapetā;**He both has it himself and encourages others in the virtue of one who is fully trained;*";
P_HTM[8276]="*attanā asekkhena samādhikkhandhena samannāgato hoti, paraṃ asekkhe samādhikkhandhe samādapetā;**He both has it himself and encourages others in the stillness of one who is fully trained;*";
P_HTM[8277]="*attanā asekkhena paññakkhandhena samannāgato hoti, paraṃ asekkhe paññakkhandhe samādapetā;**He both has it himself and encourages others in the wisdom of one who is fully trained;*";
P_HTM[8278]="*attanā asekkhena vimuttikkhandhena samannāgato hoti, paraṃ asekkhe vimuttikkhandhe samādapetā;**He both has it himself and encourages others in the freedom of one who is fully trained;*";
P_HTM[8279]="*attanā asekkhena vimuttiñāṇadassanakkhandhena samannāgato hoti, paraṃ asekkhe vimuttiñāṇadassanakkhandhe samādapetā;**He both has it himself and encourages others in the knowledge and vision of freedom of one who is fully trained;*";
P_HTM[8280]="*dasavasso vā hoti atirekadasavasso vā.**he has ten or more years of seniority.*";
P_HTM[8281]="*Aparehipi chahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā upasampādetabbaṃ nissayo dātabbo sāmaṇero upaṭṭhāpetabbo—**When a monk who has six other qualities, he may give the full ordination, give formal support, and have a novice monk attend on him:*";
P_HTM[8282]="*saddho hoti, hirimā hoti, ottappī hoti, āraddhavīriyo hoti, upaṭṭhitassati hoti, dasavasso vā hoti atirekadasavasso vā.**he has faith, conscience, moral prudence, energy, mindfulness, and ten or more years of seniority.*";
P_HTM[8283]="*Aparehipi chahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā upasampādetabbaṃ nissayo dātabbo sāmaṇero upaṭṭhāpetabbo—**When a monk who has six other qualities, he may give the full ordination, give formal support, and have a novice monk attend on him:*";
P_HTM[8284]="*na adhisīle sīlavipanno hoti, na ajjhācāre ācāravipanno hoti, na atidiṭṭhiyā diṭṭhivipanno hoti, bahussuto hoti, paññavā hoti, dasavasso vā hoti atirekadasavasso vā.**he has not failed in the higher morality; he has not failed in conduct; he has not failed in view; he’s learned; he’s wise; he has ten or more years of seniority.*";
P_HTM[8285]="*Aparehipi chahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā upasampādetabbaṃ nissayo dātabbo sāmaṇero upaṭṭhāpetabbo—**When a monk who has six other qualities, he may give the full ordination, give formal support, and have a novice monk attend on him:*";
P_HTM[8286]="*paṭibalo hoti antevāsiṃ vā saddhivihāriṃ vā gilānaṃ upaṭṭhātuṃ vā upaṭṭhāpetuṃ vā, anabhirataṃ vūpakāsetuṃ vā vūpakāsāpetuṃ vā, uppannaṃ kukkuccaṃ dhammato vinodetuṃ, āpattiṃ jānāti, āpattivuṭṭhānaṃ jānāti, dasavasso vā hoti atirekadasavasso vā.**He’s capable of three things in regard to a student: to nurse him or have him nursed when he’s sick; to send him away or have him sent away when he’s discontent with the spiritual life; to use the Teaching to dispel anxiety. And he knows the offenses; he knows how offenses are cleared; and he has ten or more years of seniority.*";
P_HTM[8287]="*Aparehipi chahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā upasampādetabbaṃ nissayo dātabbo sāmaṇero upaṭṭhāpetabbo—**When a monk who has six other qualities, he may give the full ordination, give formal support, and have a novice monk attend on him:*";
P_HTM[8288]="*paṭibalo hoti antevāsiṃ vā saddhivihāriṃ vā ābhisamācārikāya sikkhāya sikkhāpetuṃ, ādibrahmacāriyakāya sikkhāya vinetuṃ, abhidhamme vinetuṃ, abhivinaye vinetuṃ, uppannaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ dhammato vivecetuṃ, dasavasso vā hoti atirekadasavasso vā.**He’s capable of five things in regard to a student: to train him in good conduct; to train him in the basics of the spiritual life; to train him in the Teaching; to train him in the Monastic Law; and to use the Teaching to make him give up wrong views. And he has ten or more years of seniority.*";
P_HTM[8289]="*Aparehipi chahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā upasampādetabbaṃ nissayo dātabbo sāmaṇero upaṭṭhāpetabbo—**When a monk who has six other qualities, he may give the full ordination, give formal support, and have a novice monk attend on him:*";
P_HTM[8290]="*āpattiṃ jānāti, anāpattiṃ jānāti, lahukaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, garukaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, ubhayāni kho panassa pātimokkhāni vitthārena svāgatāni honti suvibhattāni suppavattīni suvinicchitāni suttaso anubyañjanaso, dasavasso vā hoti atirekadasavasso vā.**he knows the offenses; he knows the non-offense; he knows the light offenses; he knows the heavy offenses; he has properly learned both Monastic Codes in detail, and he has analyzed them well, thoroughly mastered them, and investigated them well, both in terms of the rules and their detailed exposition; he has ten or more years of seniority.*";
P_HTM[8291]="*Cha adhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni.**There are six kinds of illegitimate cancellations of the Monastic Code.*";
P_HTM[8292]="*Cha dhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanānīti.**There are six kinds of legitimate cancellations of the Monastic Code.”*";
P_HTM[8293]="*Chakkaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The section on sixes is finished.*";
P_HTM[8294]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[8295]="*Agāravā gāravā ca,**“Disrespect, and respect,*";
P_HTM[8296]="*vinītā sāmīcipi ca;**Training, and proper ways;*";
P_HTM[8297]="*Samuṭṭhānā chedanā ceva,**Origins, and cutting,*";
P_HTM[8298]="*ākārānisaṃsena ca.**Ways, and with benefit.*";
P_HTM[8299]="*Paramāni ca chārattaṃ,**And at the most, six days,*";
P_HTM[8300]="*cīvaraṃ rajanāni ca;**Robe-cloth, and kinds of dye;*";
P_HTM[8301]="*Kāyato cittato cāpi,**And from body and mind,*";
P_HTM[8302]="*vācato cittatopi ca.**And from speech and mind.*";
P_HTM[8303]="*Kāyavācācittato ca,**And from body, speech and mind,*";
P_HTM[8304]="*kammavivādameva ca;**Legal procedure, and dispute;*";
P_HTM[8305]="*Anuvādā dīghaso ca,**Accusations, and in length,*";
P_HTM[8306]="*tiriyaṃ nissayena ca.**Wide, and with formal support.*";
P_HTM[8307]="*Anupaññatti ādāya,**Additions to the rule, takes,*";
P_HTM[8308]="*samādāya tatheva ca;**And so with;*";
P_HTM[8309]="*Asekkhe samādapetā,**Fully trained, one who encourages,*";
P_HTM[8310]="*saddho adhisīlena ca;**Faith, and with higher morality;*";
P_HTM[8311]="*Gilānābhisamācārī,**Sick, good conduct,*";
P_HTM[8312]="*āpattādhammadhammikāti.**Offense, illegitimate, legitimate.”*";
P_HTM[8313]="*7. Sattakavāra**7. The section on sevens*";
P_HTM[8314]="*Sattāpattiyo.**“There are seven kinds of offenses.*";
P_HTM[8315]="*Sattāpattikkhandhā.**There are seven classes of offenses.*";
P_HTM[8316]="*Satta vinītavatthūni.**There are seven grounds of training.*";
P_HTM[8317]="*Satta sāmīciyo.**There are seven proper ways.*";
P_HTM[8318]="*Satta adhammikā paṭiññātakaraṇā.**There are seven illegitimate ways of acting according to what has been admitted.*";
P_HTM[8319]="*Satta dhammikā paṭiññātakaraṇā.**There are seven legitimate ways of acting according to what has been admitted.*";
P_HTM[8320]="*Sattannaṃ anāpatti sattāhakaraṇīyena gantuṃ.**There is no offense in going for seven days to seven kinds of people.*";
P_HTM[8321]="*Sattānisaṃsā vinayadhare.**There are seven benefits of being an expert on the Monastic Law.*";
P_HTM[8322]="*Satta paramāni.**There are seven rules about ‘at the most’.*";
P_HTM[8323]="*Sattame aruṇuggamane nissaggiyaṃ hoti.**Becoming subject to relinquishment at dawn on the seventh day.*";
P_HTM[8324]="*Satta samathā.**There are seven principles for settling legal issues.*";
P_HTM[8325]="*Satta kammāni.**There are seven kinds of legal procedures.*";
P_HTM[8326]="*Satta āmakadhaññāni.**There are seven kinds of raw grain.*";
P_HTM[8327]="*Tiriyaṃ sattantarā.**The rule on seven wide inside.*";
P_HTM[8328]="*Gaṇabhojane satta anupaññattiyo.**There are seven additions to the rule on eating in a group.*";
P_HTM[8329]="*Bhesajjāni paṭiggahetvā sattāhaparamaṃ sannidhikārakaṃ paribhuñjitabbāni.**After being received, the tonics should be used from storage for at most seven days.*";
P_HTM[8330]="*Katacīvaraṃ ādāya pakkamati.**Takes a finished robe and leaves the monastery.*";
P_HTM[8331]="*Katacīvaraṃ samādāya pakkamati.**Leaves the monastery with a finished robe.*";
P_HTM[8332]="*Bhikkhussa na hoti āpatti daṭṭhabbā.**A monk doesn’t have any offense he needs to recognize.*";
P_HTM[8333]="*Bhikkhussa hoti āpatti daṭṭhabbā.**A monk does have an offense he needs to recognize.*";
P_HTM[8334]="*Bhikkhussa hoti āpatti daṭṭhabbā.**A monk has an offense he needs to make amends for.*";
P_HTM[8335]="*Satta adhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni.**There are seven kinds of illegitimate cancellations of the Monastic Code.*";
P_HTM[8336]="*Satta dhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni.**There are seven kinds of legitimate cancellations of the Monastic Code.*";
P_HTM[8337]="*Sattahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu vinayadharo hoti—**When a monk has seven qualities, he is an expert on the Monastic Law:*";
P_HTM[8338]="*āpattiṃ jānāti, anāpattiṃ jānāti, lahukaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, garukaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, sīlavā hoti, pātimokkhasaṃvarasaṃvuto viharati ācāragocarasampanno aṇumattesu vajjesu bhayadassāvī samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu, catunnaṃ jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī hoti akicchalābhī akasiralābhī, āsavānañca khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati.**He knows the offenses. [2] He knows the non-offenses. [3] He knows the light offenses. [4] He knows the heavy offenses. [5] He is virtuous and restrained by the Monastic Code. His conduct is good, he associates with the right people, and he sees danger in minor faults. And he undertakes and trains in the training rules. [6] Whenever he wants, he accesses the four absorptions, those pleasant higher-mind meditations of the present life. [7] And because of the ending of the corruptions, he has realized with his own insight, in this very life, the liberation by mind and the liberation by wisdom.*";
P_HTM[8339]="*Aparehipi sattahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu vinayadharo hoti—**When a monk has seven other qualities, he is an expert on the Monastic Law:*";
P_HTM[8340]="*āpattiṃ jānāti, anāpattiṃ jānāti, lahukaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, garukaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, bahussuto hoti sutadharo sutasannicayo ye te dhammā ādikalyāṇā majjhekalyāṇā pariyosānakalyāṇā sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ abhivadanti tathārūpassa dhammā bahussutā honti dhātā vacasā paricitā manasānupekkhitā diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā, catunnaṃ jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī hoti akicchalābhī akasiralābhī, āsavānañca khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati.**He knows the offenses. [2] He knows the non-offenses. [3] He knows the light offenses. [4] He knows the heavy offenses. [5] He has learned much, and he retains and accumulates what he has learned. Those teachings that are good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, that have a true goal and are well articulated, and that set out the perfectly complete and pure spiritual life—he has learned many such teachings, retained them in mind, recited them verbally, mentally investigated them, and penetrated them well by view. [6] Whenever he wants, he accesses the four absorptions, those pleasant higher-mind meditations of the present life. [7] And because of the ending of the corruptions, he has realized with his own insight, in this very life, the liberation by mind and the liberation by wisdom.*";
P_HTM[8341]="*Aparehipi sattahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu vinayadharo hoti—**When a monk has seven other qualities, he is an expert on the Monastic Law:*";
P_HTM[8342]="*āpattiṃ jānāti, anāpattiṃ jānāti, lahukaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, garukaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, ubhayāni kho panassa pātimokkhāni vitthārena svāgatāni honti suvibhattāni suppavattīni suvinicchitāni suttaso anubyañjanaso, catunnaṃ jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī hoti akicchalābhī akasiralābhī, āsavānañca khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati.**He knows the offenses. [2] He knows the non-offenses. [3] He knows the light offenses. [4] He knows the heavy offenses. [5] He has properly learned both Monastic Codes in detail; he has analyzed them well, thoroughly mastered them, and investigated them well, both in terms of the rules and their detailed exposition. [6] Whenever he wants, he accesses the four absorptions, those pleasant higher-mind meditations of the present life. [7] And because of the ending of the corruptions, he has realized with his own insight, in this very life, the liberation by mind and the liberation by wisdom.*";
P_HTM[8343]="*Aparehipi sattahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu vinayadharo hoti—**When a monk has seven other qualities, he is an expert on the Monastic Law:*";
P_HTM[8344]="*āpattiṃ jānāti; anāpattiṃ jānāti; lahukaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti; garukaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti; anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati, seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ dvepi jātiyo tissopi jātiyo catassopi jātiyo pañcapi jātiyo dasapi jātiyo vīsampi jātiyo tiṃsampi jātiyo cattālīsampi jātiyo paññāsampi jātiyo jātisatampi jātisahassampi jātisatasahassampi anekepi saṃvaṭṭakappe anekepi vivaṭṭakappe anekepi saṃvaṭṭavivaṭṭakappe—“amutrāsiṃ evaṃnāmo evaṅgotto evaṃvaṇṇo evamāhāro evaṃsukhadukkhappaṭisaṃvedī evamāyupariyanto, so tato cuto amutra udapādiṃ; tatrāpāsiṃ evaṃnāmo evaṅgotto evaṃvaṇṇo evamāhāro evaṃsukhadukkhappaṭisaṃvedī evamāyupariyanto, so tato cuto idhūpapanno”ti iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati; dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passati cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe, sugate duggate yathākammūpage satte pajānāti—“ime vata bhonto sattā kāyaduccaritena samannāgatā, vacīduccaritena samannāgatā, manoduccaritena samannāgatā, ariyānaṃ upavādakā, micchādiṭṭhikā, micchādiṭṭhikammasamādānā, te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapannā, ime vā pana bhonto sattā kāyasucaritena samannāgatā, vacīsucaritena samannāgatā, manosucaritena samannāgatā, ariyānaṃ anupavādakā, sammādiṭṭhikā, sammādiṭṭhikammasamādānā, te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapannā”ti iti dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passati cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe sugate duggate yathākammūpage satte pajānāti; āsavānañca khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati.**He knows the offenses. [2] He knows the non-offenses. [3] He knows the light offenses. [4] He knows the heavy offenses. [5] He recollects many past lives, that is, one birth, two births, three births, four births, five births, ten births, twenty births, thirty births, forty births, fifty births, a hundred births, a thousand births, a hundred thousand births; many eons of world dissolution, many eons of world evolution, many eons of both dissolution and evolution; and he knows: ʻThere I had such name, such family, such appearance, such food, such experience of pleasure and pain, and such a lifespan. Passing away from there, I was reborn elsewhere, and there I had such name, such family, such appearance, such food, such experience of pleasure and pain, and such a lifespan. Passing away from there, I was reborn here.’ In this way he recollects many past lives with their characteristics and particulars. [6] With superhuman and purified clairvoyance, he sees beings passing away and getting reborn, inferior and superior, beautiful and ugly, gone to good destinations and to bad destinations, and he understands how beings pass on according to their actions: ‘These beings who engaged in misconduct by body, speech, and mind, who abused the noble ones, who had wrong views and acted accordingly, at the breaking up of the body after death, have been reborn in a lower realm, a bad destination, a world of misery, hell. But these beings who engaged in good conduct of body, speech, and mind, who did not abuse the noble ones, who held right view and acted accordingly, at the breaking up of the body after death, have been reborn in a good destination, a heaven world.’ In this way, with superhuman and purified clairvoyance, he sees beings passing away and getting reborn, inferior and superior, beautiful and ugly, gone to good destinations and to bad destinations, and he understands how beings pass on according to their actions. [7] And because of the ending of the corruptions, he has realized with his own insight, in this very life, the liberation by mind and the liberation by wisdom.*";
P_HTM[8345]="*Sattahaṅgehi samannāgato vinayadharo sobhati—**When an expert on the Monastic Law has seven qualities, he shines:*";
P_HTM[8346]="*āpattiṃ jānāti, anāpattiṃ jānāti, lahukaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, garukaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, sīlavā hoti …pe… samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu, catunnaṃ jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī hoti akicchalābhī akasiralābhī, āsavānañca khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati.**He knows the offenses. [2] He knows the non-offenses. [3] He knows the light offenses. [4] He knows the heavy offenses. [5] He is virtuous and restrained by the Monastic Code. His conduct is good, he associates with the right people, and he sees danger in minor faults. And he undertakes and trains in the training rules. [6] Whenever he wants, he accesses the four absorptions, those pleasant higher-mind meditations of the present life. [7] And because of the ending of the corruptions, he has realized with his own insight, in this very life, the liberation by mind and the liberation by wisdom.*";
P_HTM[8347]="*Aparehipi sattahaṅgehi samannāgato vinayadharo sobhati—**When an expert on the Monastic Law has seven qualities, he shines:*";
P_HTM[8348]="*āpattiṃ jānāti, anāpattiṃ jānāti, lahukaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, garukaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, bahussuto hoti …pe… diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdho catunnaṃ jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī hoti akicchalābhī akasiralābhī, āsavānañca khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati.**He knows the offenses. [2] He knows the non-offenses. [3] He knows the light offenses. [4] He knows the heavy offenses. [5] He has learned much, and he retains and accumulates what he has learned. Those teachings that are good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, that have a true goal and are well articulated, and that set out the perfectly complete and pure spiritual life—he has learned many such teachings, retained them in mind, recited them verbally, mentally investigated them, and penetrated them well by view. [6] Whenever he wants, he accesses the four absorptions, those pleasant higher-mind meditations of the present life. [7] And because of the ending of the corruptions, he has realized with his own insight, in this very life, the liberation by mind and the liberation by wisdom.*";
P_HTM[8349]="*Aparehipi sattahaṅgehi samannāgato vinayadharo sobhati—**When an expert on the Monastic Law has seven qualities, he shines:*";
P_HTM[8350]="*āpattiṃ jānāti, anāpattiṃ jānāti, lahukaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, garukaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, ubhayāni kho panassa pātimokkhāni vitthārena svāgatāni honti suvibhattāni suppavattīni suvinicchitāni suttaso anubyañjanaso, catunnaṃ jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī hoti akicchalābhī akasiralābhī, āsavānañca khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati.**He knows the offenses. [2] He knows the non-offenses. [3] He knows the light offenses. [4] He knows the heavy offenses. [5] He has properly learned both Monastic Codes in detail; he has analyzed them well, thoroughly mastered them, and investigated them well, both in terms of the rules and their detailed exposition. [6] Whenever he wants, he accesses the four absorptions, those pleasant higher-mind meditations of the present life. [7] And because of the ending of the corruptions, he has realized with his own insight, in this very life, the liberation by mind and the liberation by wisdom.*";
P_HTM[8351]="*Aparehipi sattahaṅgehi samannāgato vinayadharo sobhati—**When an expert on the Monastic Law has seven qualities, he shines:*";
P_HTM[8352]="*āpattiṃ jānāti; anāpattiṃ jānāti; lahukaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti; garukaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti; anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati, seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ dvepi jātiyo …pe… iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati, dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passati cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe sugate duggate yathākammūpage satte pajānāti …pe… iti dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passati cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe sugate duggate yathākammūpage satte pajānāti; āsavānañca khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati.**He knows the offenses. [2] He knows the non-offenses. [3] He knows the light offenses. [4] He knows the heavy offenses. [5] He recollects many past lives, that is, one birth, two births, three births, four births, five births, ten births, twenty births, thirty births, forty births, fifty births, a hundred births, a thousand births, a hundred thousand births; many eons of world dissolution, many eons of world evolution, many eons of both dissolution and evolution; and he knows: ʻThere I had such name, such family, such appearance, such food, such experience of pleasure and pain, and such a lifespan. Passing away from there, I was reborn elsewhere, and there I had such name, such family, such appearance, such food, such experience of pleasure and pain, and such a lifespan. Passing away from there, I was reborn here.’ In this way he recollects many past lives with their characteristics and particulars. [6] With superhuman and purified clairvoyance, he sees beings passing away and getting reborn, inferior and superior, beautiful and ugly, gone to good destinations and to bad destinations, and he understands how beings pass on according to their actions: ‘These beings who engaged in misconduct by body, speech, and mind, who abused the noble ones, who had wrong views and acted accordingly, at the breaking up of the body after death, have been reborn in a lower realm, a bad destination, a world of misery, hell. But these beings who engaged in good conduct of body, speech, and mind, who did not abuse the noble ones, who held right view and acted accordingly, at the breaking up of the body after death, have been reborn in a good destination, a heaven world.’ In this way, with superhuman and purified clairvoyance, he sees beings passing away and getting reborn, inferior and superior, beautiful and ugly, gone to good destinations and to bad destinations, and he understands how beings pass on according to their actions. [7] And because of the ending of the corruptions, he has realized with his own insight, in this very life, the liberation by mind and the liberation by wisdom.*";
P_HTM[8353]="*Satta asaddhammā—**There are seven bad qualities:*";
P_HTM[8354]="*assaddho hoti, ahiriko hoti, anottappī hoti, appassuto hoti, kusīto hoti, muṭṭhassati hoti, duppañño hoti.**one has no faith, conscience, or moral prudence; and one is ignorant, lazy, absentminded, and foolish.*";
P_HTM[8355]="*Satta saddhammā—**There are seven good qualities:*";
P_HTM[8356]="*saddho hoti, hirimā hoti, ottappī hoti, bahussuto hoti, āraddhavīriyo hoti, upaṭṭhitassati hoti, paññavā hotīti.**one has faith, conscience, and moral prudence; and one is learned, energetic, mindful, and wise.”*";
P_HTM[8357]="*Sattakaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The section on sevens is finished.*";
P_HTM[8358]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[8359]="*Āpatti āpattikkhandhā,**“Offense, classes of offenses,*";
P_HTM[8360]="*vinītā sāmīcipi ca;**Training, and proper ways;*";
P_HTM[8361]="*Adhammikā dhammikā ca,**Illegitimate, and legitimate,*";
P_HTM[8362]="*anāpatti ca sattāhaṃ.**And seven days is no offense.*";
P_HTM[8363]="*Ānisaṃsā paramāni,**Benefits, ‘at the most’,*";
P_HTM[8364]="*aruṇasamathena ca;**Dawn, and with settling;*";
P_HTM[8365]="*Kammā āmakadhaññā ca,**Legal procedures, and kinds of raw grain,*";
P_HTM[8366]="*tiriyaṃ gaṇabhojane.**Wide, eating in a group.*";
P_HTM[8367]="*Sattāhaparamaṃ ādāya,**At most seven days, takes,*";
P_HTM[8368]="*samādāya tatheva ca;**And so with;*";
P_HTM[8369]="*Na hoti hoti hoti ca,**Doesn’t, does, and does,*";
P_HTM[8370]="*adhammā dhammikāni ca.**Illegitimate and legitimate.*";
P_HTM[8371]="*Caturo vinayadharā,**Four about experts on the Monastic Law,*";
P_HTM[8372]="*catubhikkhū ca sobhane;**And four about monks who shine;*";
P_HTM[8373]="*Satta ceva asaddhammā,**And seven bad qualities,*";
P_HTM[8374]="*satta saddhammā desitāti.**Seven good qualities have been taught.”*";
P_HTM[8375]="*8. Aṭṭhakavāra**8. The section on eights*";
P_HTM[8376]="*Aṭṭhānisaṃse sampassamānena na so bhikkhu āpattiyā adassane ukkhipitabbo.**“When you see eight benefits, you should not eject a monk for not recognizing an offense.*";
P_HTM[8377]="*Aṭṭhānisaṃse sampassamānena paresampi saddhāya sā āpatti desetabbā.**When you see eight benefits, you should confess an offense even for the sake of the faith of others.*";
P_HTM[8378]="*Aṭṭha yāvatatiyakā.**There are eight “after the third”.*";
P_HTM[8379]="*Aṭṭhahākārehi kulāni dūseti.**There are eight ways of corrupting families.*";
P_HTM[8380]="*Aṭṭha mātikā cīvarassa uppādāya.**There are eight summaries for the giving of a robe.*";
P_HTM[8381]="*Aṭṭha mātikā kathinassa ubbhārāya.**There are eight summaries for when the robe-making season comes to an end.*";
P_HTM[8382]="*Aṭṭha pānāni.**There are eight kinds of drinks.*";
P_HTM[8383]="*Aṭṭhahi asaddhammehi abhibhūto pariyādinnacitto devadatto āpāyiko nerayiko kappaṭṭho atekiccho.**Because he is overcome by and immersed in eight bad qualities, Devadatta is irredeemably destined to an eon in hell.*";
P_HTM[8384]="*Aṭṭha lokadhammā.**There are eight worldly phenomena.*";
P_HTM[8385]="*Aṭṭha garudhammā.**There are eight important principles.*";
P_HTM[8386]="*Aṭṭha pāṭidesanīyā.**There are eight offenses entailing acknowledgment.*";
P_HTM[8387]="*Aṭṭhaṅgiko musāvādo.**Lying has eight factors.*";
P_HTM[8388]="*Aṭṭha uposathaṅgāni.**The observance day has eight factors.*";
P_HTM[8389]="*Aṭṭha dūteyyaṅgāni.**There are eight qualities of a qualified messenger.*";
P_HTM[8390]="*Aṭṭha titthiyavattāni.**There are eight practices of monastics of other religions.*";
P_HTM[8391]="*Aṭṭha acchariyā abbhutadhammā mahāsamudde.**There are eight amazing qualities in the great ocean.*";
P_HTM[8392]="*Aṭṭha acchariyā abbhutadhammā imasmiṃ dhammavinaye.**There are eight amazing qualities in this spiritual path.*";
P_HTM[8393]="*Aṭṭha anatirittā.**There are eight “not left overs”.*";
P_HTM[8394]="*Aṭṭha atirittā.**There are eight “left overs”.*";
P_HTM[8395]="*Aṭṭhame aruṇuggamane nissaggiyaṃ hoti.**Becoming subject to relinquishment at dawn on the eighth day.*";
P_HTM[8396]="*Aṭṭha pārājikā.**There are eight offenses entailing expulsion.*";
P_HTM[8397]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ vatthuṃ paripūrentī nāsetabbā.**When she fulfills the eight parts, she should be expelled.*";
P_HTM[8398]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ vatthuṃ paripūrentiyā desitāpi adesitā hoti.**When she fulfills the eight parts, even if she confesses, it is not actually confessed.*";
P_HTM[8399]="*Aṭṭhavācikā upasampadā.**There is full ordination with eight announcements.*";
P_HTM[8400]="*Aṭṭhannaṃ paccuṭṭhātabbaṃ.**One should stand up for eight people.*";
P_HTM[8401]="*Aṭṭhannaṃ āsanaṃ dātabbaṃ.**One should offer a seat to eight people.*";
P_HTM[8402]="*Upāsikā aṭṭha varāni yācati.**The female lay follower who asked for eight favors.*";
P_HTM[8403]="*Aṭṭhahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu bhikkhunovādako sammannitabbo.**When a monk has eight qualities, he may be appointed as an instructor of the nuns.*";
P_HTM[8404]="*Aṭṭhānisaṃsā vinayadhare.**There are eight benefits of being an expert on the Monastic Law.*";
P_HTM[8405]="*Aṭṭha paramāni.**There are eight rules about ‘at the most’.*";
P_HTM[8406]="*Tassapāpiyasikākammakatena bhikkhunā aṭṭhasu dhammesu sammā vattitabbaṃ.**A monk who has had a legal procedure of further penalty done against himself should behave properly in eight respects.*";
P_HTM[8407]="*Aṭṭha adhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni.**There are eight kinds of illegitimate cancellations of the Monastic Code.*";
P_HTM[8408]="*Aṭṭha dhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanānīti.**There are eight kinds of legitimate cancellations of the Monastic Code.”*";
P_HTM[8409]="*Aṭṭhakaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The section on eights is finished.*";
P_HTM[8410]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[8411]="*Na so bhikkhu paresampi,**“Not that monk, even in others,*";
P_HTM[8412]="*yāvatatiyadūsanā;**Up to the three times, corrupting;*";
P_HTM[8413]="*Mātikā kathinubbhārā,**Summaries, the robe-making season coming to an end,*";
P_HTM[8414]="*pānā abhibhūtena ca.**Drinks, and with overcome by.*";
P_HTM[8415]="*Lokadhammā garudhammā,**Worldly phenomena, important principles,*";
P_HTM[8416]="*pāṭidesanīyā musā;**Offenses entailing acknowledgment, lying;*";
P_HTM[8417]="*Uposathā ca dūtaṅgā,**And observance days, qualities of a qualified messenger,*";
P_HTM[8418]="*titthiyā samuddepi ca.**Monastics of other religions, and also in the ocean.*";
P_HTM[8419]="*Abbhutā anatirittaṃ,**Amazing, not left over,*";
P_HTM[8420]="*atirittaṃ nissaggiyaṃ;**Left over, subject to relinquishment;*";
P_HTM[8421]="*Pārājikaṭṭhamaṃ vatthu,**Offenses entailing expulsion, eight parts,*";
P_HTM[8422]="*adesitūpasampadā.**Not actually confessed, full ordination.*";
P_HTM[8423]="*Paccuṭṭhānāsanañceva,**One should stand up for, and seat,*";
P_HTM[8424]="*varaṃ ovādakena ca;**Favor, and with an instructor;*";
P_HTM[8425]="*Ānisaṃsā paramāni,**Benefits, at the most,*";
P_HTM[8426]="*aṭṭhadhammesu vattanā;**Behaving in eight respects;*";
P_HTM[8427]="*Adhammikā dhammikā ca,**Illegitimate, and legitimate:*";
P_HTM[8428]="*aṭṭhakā suppakāsitāti.**The section on eights has been well proclaimed.”*";
P_HTM[8429]="*9. Navakavāra**9. The section on nines*";
P_HTM[8430]="*Nava āghātavatthūni.**“There are nine grounds for resentment.*";
P_HTM[8431]="*Nava āghātapaṭivinayā.**There are nine ways of getting rid of resentment.*";
P_HTM[8432]="*Nava vinītavatthūni.**There are nine grounds of training.*";
P_HTM[8433]="*Nava paṭhamāpattikā.**There are nine immediate offenses.*";
P_HTM[8434]="*Navahi saṅgho bhijjati.**The Sangha is split by a group of nine.*";
P_HTM[8435]="*Nava paṇītabhojanāni.**There are nine fine foods.*";
P_HTM[8436]="*Navamaṃsehi dukkaṭaṃ.**There is an offense of wrong conduct for eating nine kinds of meat.*";
P_HTM[8437]="*Nava pātimokkhuddesā.**There are nine ways of reciting the Monastic Code.*";
P_HTM[8438]="*Nava paramāni.**There are nine rules about ‘at the most’.*";
P_HTM[8439]="*Nava taṇhāmūlakā dhammā.**There are nine things rooted in craving.*";
P_HTM[8440]="*Nava vidhamānā.**There are nine kinds of conceit.*";
P_HTM[8441]="*Nava cīvarāni adhiṭṭhātabbāni.**There are nine kinds of robe-cloth that should be determined.*";
P_HTM[8442]="*Nava cīvarāni na vikappetabbāni.**There are nine kinds of robe-cloth that should not be transferred.*";
P_HTM[8443]="*Dīghaso nava vidatthiyo sugatavidatthiyā.**Nine standard handspans long.*";
P_HTM[8444]="*Nava adhammikāni dānāni.**There are nine illegitimate kinds of gifts.*";
P_HTM[8445]="*Nava adhammikā paṭiggahā.**There are nine illegitimate kinds of receiving.*";
P_HTM[8446]="*Nava adhammikā paribhogā—**There are nine illegitimate kinds of possessions.*";
P_HTM[8447]="*tīṇi dhammikāni dānāni, tayo dhammikā paṭiggahā, tayo dhammikā paribhogā.**There are three legitimate kinds of gifts, three legitimate kinds of receiving, and three legitimate kinds of possessions.*";
P_HTM[8448]="*Nava adhammikā saññattiyo.**There are nine illegitimate ways of winning over.*";
P_HTM[8449]="*Nava dhammikā saññattiyo.**There are nine legitimate ways of winning over.*";
P_HTM[8450]="*Adhammakamme dve navakāni.**There are two groups of nine on illegitimate legal procedures.*";
P_HTM[8451]="*Dhammakamme dve navakāni.**There are two groups of nine on legitimate legal procedures.*";
P_HTM[8452]="*Nava adhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni.**There are nine kinds of illegitimate cancellations of the Monastic Code.*";
P_HTM[8453]="*Nava dhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanānīti.**There are nine kinds of legitimate cancellations of the Monastic Code.”*";
P_HTM[8454]="*Navakaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The section on nines is finished.*";
P_HTM[8455]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[8456]="*Āghātavatthuvinayā,**“Grounds for resentment, getting rid of,*";
P_HTM[8457]="*vinītā paṭhamena ca;**Training, and with immediate;*";
P_HTM[8458]="*Bhijjati ca paṇītañca,**And split, and fine,*";
P_HTM[8459]="*maṃsuddesaparamāni ca.**Meat, reciting, and at the most.*";
P_HTM[8460]="*Taṇhā mānā adhiṭṭhānā,**Craving, conceit, should be determined,*";
P_HTM[8461]="*vikappe ca vidatthiyo;**And should transfer, handspans;*";
P_HTM[8462]="*Dānā paṭiggahā bhogā,**Gifts, kinds of receiving, kinds of possessions,*";
P_HTM[8463]="*tividhā puna dhammikā.**And again threefold legitimate kinds.*";
P_HTM[8464]="*Adhammadhammasaññatti,**Illegitimate ways of winning over, and legitimate ways of winning over,*";
P_HTM[8465]="*duve dve navakāni ca;**And twice two groups of nine;*";
P_HTM[8466]="*Pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni,**Cancellations of the Monastic Code—*";
P_HTM[8467]="*adhammadhammikāni cāti.**Illegitimate, and legitimate.”*";
P_HTM[8468]="*10. Dasakavāra**10. The section on tens*";
P_HTM[8469]="*Dasa āghātavatthūni.**“There are ten grounds for resentment.*";
P_HTM[8470]="*Dasa āghātapaṭivinayā.**There are ten ways of getting rid of resentment.*";
P_HTM[8471]="*Dasa vinītavatthūni.**There are ten grounds of training.*";
P_HTM[8472]="*Dasavatthukā micchādiṭṭhi.**There are ten subject matters of wrong view.*";
P_HTM[8473]="*Dasavatthukā sammādiṭṭhi.**There are ten subject matters of right view.*";
P_HTM[8474]="*Dasa antaggāhikā diṭṭhi.**There are ten side views.*";
P_HTM[8475]="*Dasa micchattā.**There are ten kinds wrongness.*";
P_HTM[8476]="*Dasa sammattā.**There are ten kinds of rightness.*";
P_HTM[8477]="*Dasa akusalakammapathā.**There are ten ways of doing unskillful deeds.*";
P_HTM[8478]="*Dasa kusalakammapathā.**There are ten ways of doing skillful deeds.*";
P_HTM[8479]="*Dasa adhammikā salākaggāhā.**There are ten reasons why a vote is illegitimate.*";
P_HTM[8480]="*Dasa dhammikā salākaggāhā.**There are ten reasons why a vote is legitimate.*";
P_HTM[8481]="*Sāmaṇerānaṃ dasa sikkhāpadāni.**There are ten training rules for the novice monks.*";
P_HTM[8482]="*Dasahaṅgehi samannāgato sāmaṇero nāsetabbo.**A novice monk who has ten qualities should be expelled.*";
P_HTM[8483]="*Dasahaṅgehi samannāgato vinayadharo “bālo” tveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati—**When an expert on the Monastic Law has ten qualities, he is reckoned as ignorant:*";
P_HTM[8484]="*attano bhāsapariyantaṃ na uggaṇhāti, parassa bhāsapariyantaṃ na uggaṇhāti, attano bhāsapariyantaṃ anuggahetvā parassa bhāsapariyantaṃ anuggahetvā adhammena kāreti, appaṭiññāya āpattiṃ na jānāti, āpattiyā mūlaṃ na jānāti, āpattisamudayaṃ na jānāti, āpattinirodhaṃ na jānāti, āpattinirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ na jānāti.**he does not grasp what is proper for himself to say; he does not grasp what is proper for others to say; not grasping either, he makes them act illegitimately, without their admission; he does not know the offenses; he does not know the sources of offenses; he does not know the origin of offenses; he does not know the ending of offenses; he does not know the path leading to the ending of offenses.*";
P_HTM[8485]="*Dasahaṅgehi samannāgato vinayadharo “paṇḍito” tveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati—**When an expert on the Monastic Law has ten other qualities, he is reckoned as wise:*";
P_HTM[8486]="*attano bhāsapariyantaṃ uggaṇhāti, parassa bhāsapariyantaṃ uggaṇhāti, attano bhāsapariyantaṃ uggahetvā parassa bhāsapariyantaṃ uggahetvā dhammena kāreti, paṭiññāya āpattiṃ jānāti, āpattiyā mūlaṃ jānāti, āpattisamudayaṃ jānāti, āpattinirodhaṃ jānāti, āpattinirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ jānāti.**he grasps what is proper for himself to say; he grasps what is proper for others to say; grasping both, he makes them act legitimately, in accordance with their admission; he knows the offenses; he knows the sources of offenses; he knows the origin of offenses; he knows the ending of offenses; he knows the path leading to the ending of offenses.*";
P_HTM[8487]="*Aparehipi dasahaṅgehi samannāgato vinayadharo “bālo” tveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati—**When an expert on the Monastic Law has ten other qualities, he is reckoned as ignorant:*";
P_HTM[8488]="*adhikaraṇaṃ na jānāti, adhikaraṇassa mūlaṃ na jānāti, adhikaraṇasamudayaṃ na jānāti, adhikaraṇanirodhaṃ na jānāti, adhikaraṇanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ na jānāti, vatthuṃ na jānāti, nidānaṃ na jānāti, paññattiṃ na jānāti, anupaññattiṃ na jānāti, anusandhivacanapathaṃ na jānāti.**he does not know the legal issues; he does not know the sources of the legal issues; he does not know the origin of the legal issues; he does not know the ending of the legal issues; he does not know the path leading to the ending of the legal issues; he does not know the actions that are the basis for offenses; he does not know the origin stories; he does not know the rules; he does not know the additions to the rules; he does not know the sequence of statements.*";
P_HTM[8489]="*Dasahaṅgehi samannāgato vinayadharo “paṇḍito” tveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati—**When an expert on the Monastic Law has ten other qualities, he is reckoned as wise:*";
P_HTM[8490]="*adhikaraṇaṃ jānāti, adhikaraṇassa mūlaṃ jānāti, adhikaraṇasamudayaṃ jānāti, adhikaraṇanirodhaṃ jānāti, adhikaraṇanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ jānāti, vatthuṃ jānāti, nidānaṃ jānāti, paññattiṃ jānāti, anupaññattiṃ jānāti, anusandhivacanapathaṃ jānāti.**he knows legal issues; he knows the sources of legal issues; he knows the origin of legal issues; he knows the ending of legal issues; he knows the path leading to the ending of legal issues; he knows the actions that are the basis for offenses; he knows the origin stories; he knows the rules; he knows the additions to the rules; he knows the sequence of statements.*";
P_HTM[8491]="*Aparehipi dasahaṅgehi samannāgato vinayadharo “bālo” tveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati—**When an expert on the Monastic Law has ten other qualities, he is reckoned as ignorant:*";
P_HTM[8492]="*ñattiṃ na jānāti, ñattiyā karaṇaṃ na jānāti, na pubbakusalo hoti, na aparakusalo hoti, akālaññū ca hoti, āpattānāpattiṃ na jānāti, lahukagarukaṃ āpattiṃ na jānāti, sāvasesānavasesaṃ āpattiṃ na jānāti, duṭṭhullāduṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ na jānāti, ācariyaparamparā kho panassa na suggahitā hoti na sumanasikatā na sūpadhāritā.**he does not know the motion; he does not know how the motion is done; he is not skilled in what comes first; he is not skilled in what comes afterwards; he does not know the right time; he does not know the offenses and non-offenses; he does not know the light and heavy offenses; he does not know the curable and incurable offenses; he does not know the grave and minor offenses; he has not well-learned or well-remembered his teachers’ tradition.*";
P_HTM[8493]="*Dasahaṅgehi samannāgato vinayadharo “paṇḍito” tveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati—**When an expert on the Monastic Law has ten other qualities, he is reckoned as wise:*";
P_HTM[8494]="*ñattiṃ jānāti, ñattiyā karaṇaṃ jānāti, pubbakusalo hoti, aparakusalo hoti, kālaññū ca hoti, āpattānāpattiṃ jānāti, lahukagarukaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, sāvasesānavasesaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, duṭṭhullāduṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, ācariyaparamparā kho panassa suggahitā hoti sumanasikatā sūpadhāritā.**he knows the motion; he knows how the motion is done; he is skilled in what comes first; he is skilled in what comes afterwards; he knows the right time; he knows the offenses and non-offenses; he knows the light and heavy offenses; he knows the curable and incurable offenses; he knows the grave and minor offenses; he has well-learned and well-remembered his teachers’ tradition.*";
P_HTM[8495]="*Aparehipi dasahaṅgehi samannāgato vinayadharo “bālo” tveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati—**When an expert on the Monastic Law has ten other qualities, he is reckoned as ignorant:*";
P_HTM[8496]="*āpattānāpattiṃ na jānāti, lahukagarukaṃ āpattiṃ na jānāti, sāvasesānavasesaṃ āpattiṃ na jānāti, duṭṭhullāduṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ na jānāti, ubhayāni kho panassa pātimokkhāni vitthārena na svāgatāni honti na suvibhattāni na suppavattīni na suvinicchitāni suttaso anubyañjanaso, āpattānāpattiṃ na jānāti, lahukagarukaṃ āpattiṃ na jānāti, sāvasesānavasesaṃ āpattiṃ na jānāti, duṭṭhullāduṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ na jānāti, adhikaraṇe ca na vinicchayakusalo hoti.**he does not know the offenses and non-offenses; he does not know the light and heavy offenses; he does not know the curable and incurable offenses; he does not know the grave and minor offenses; he has not properly learned both Monastic Codes in detail, not having analyzed them well, thoroughly mastered them, and investigated them well, both in terms of the rules and their detailed exposition; he does not know the offenses and non-offenses; he does not know the light and heavy offenses; he does not know the curable and incurable offenses; he does not know the grave and minor offenses; he is not skilled in legal issues and deliberations.*";
P_HTM[8497]="*Dasahaṅgehi samannāgato vinayadharo “paṇḍito” tveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati—**When an expert on the Monastic Law has ten other qualities, he is reckoned as wise:*";
P_HTM[8498]="*āpattānāpattiṃ jānāti, lahukagarukaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, sāvasesānavasesaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, duṭṭhullāduṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, ubhayāni kho panassa pātimokkhāni vitthārena svāgatāni honti suvibhattāni suppavattīni suvinicchitāni suttaso anubyañjanaso, āpattānāpattiṃ jānāti, lahukagarukaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, sāvasesānavasesaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, duṭṭhullāduṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, adhikaraṇe ca vinicchayakusalo hoti.**he knows the offenses and non-offenses; he knows the light and heavy offenses; he knows the curable and incurable offenses; he knows the grave and minor offenses; he has properly learned both Monastic Codes in detail, having analyzed them well, thoroughly mastered them, and investigated them well, both in terms of the rules and their detailed exposition; he knows the offenses and non-offenses; he knows the light and heavy offenses; he knows the curable and incurable offenses; he knows the grave and minor offenses; he is skilled in legal issues and deliberations.*";
P_HTM[8499]="*Dasahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu ubbāhikāya sammannitabbo.**A monk who has ten qualities may be appointed to a committee.*";
P_HTM[8500]="*Dasa atthavase paṭicca tathāgatena sāvakānaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ.**The Buddha laid down the training rules for his disciples for ten reasons.*";
P_HTM[8501]="*Dasa ādīnavā rājantepurappavesane.**There are ten dangers in entering a royal compound.*";
P_HTM[8502]="*Dasa dānavatthūni.**There are ten reasons for giving.*";
P_HTM[8503]="*Dasa ratanāni.**There are ten treasures.*";
P_HTM[8504]="*Dasavaggo bhikkhusaṅgho.**There is a sangha of monks consisting of a group of ten.*";
P_HTM[8505]="*Dasavaggena gaṇena upasampādetabbaṃ.**A group of ten may give the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[8506]="*Dasa paṃsukūlāni.**There are ten kinds of rags.*";
P_HTM[8507]="*Dasa cīvaradhāraṇā.**There are ten kinds of robe wearing.*";
P_HTM[8508]="*Dasāhaparamaṃ atirekacīvaraṃ dhāretabbaṃ.**One should keep an extra robe for ten days at the most.*";
P_HTM[8509]="*Dasa sukkāni.**There are ten kinds semen.*";
P_HTM[8510]="*Dasa itthiyo.**There are ten kinds women.*";
P_HTM[8511]="*Dasa bhariyāyo.**There are ten kinds of wives.*";
P_HTM[8512]="*Vesāliyā dasa vatthūni dīpenti.**The ten practices proclaim as allowable at Vesālī.*";
P_HTM[8513]="*Dasa puggalā avandiyā.**There are ten kinds of people a monk should not pay respect to.*";
P_HTM[8514]="*Dasa akkosavatthūni.**There are ten kinds of abuse.*";
P_HTM[8515]="*Dasahākārehi pesuññaṃ upasaṃharati.**There are ten ways of engaging in malicious talebearing.*";
P_HTM[8516]="*Dasa senāsanāni.**There are ten kinds of furniture.*";
P_HTM[8517]="*Dasa varāni yāciṃsu.**They asked for ten favors.*";
P_HTM[8518]="*Dasa adhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni.**There are ten kinds of illegitimate cancellations of the Monastic Code.*";
P_HTM[8519]="*Dasa dhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni.**These are the ten legitimate cancellations of the Monastic Code.*";
P_HTM[8520]="*Dasānisaṃsā yāguyā.**These are the ten benefits of rice porridge.*";
P_HTM[8521]="*Dasa maṃsā akappiyā.**There are ten kinds of unallowable meat.*";
P_HTM[8522]="*Dasa paramāni.**There are ten rules about ‘at the most’.*";
P_HTM[8523]="*Dasavassena bhikkhunā byattena paṭibalena pabbājetabbaṃ upasampādetabbaṃ nissayo dātabbo sāmaṇero upaṭṭhāpetabbo.**A competent and capable monk who has ten years of seniority may give the going forth, the full ordination, and formal support, and may have a novice monk attend on him.*";
P_HTM[8524]="*Dasavassāya bhikkhuniyā byattāya paṭibalāya pabbājetabbaṃ upasampādetabbaṃ nissayo dātabbo sāmaṇerī upaṭṭhāpetabbā.**A competent and capable nun who has ten years of seniority may give the going forth, the full ordination, and formal support, and may have a novice nun attend on her.*";
P_HTM[8525]="*Dasavassāya bhikkhuniyā byattāya paṭibalāya vuṭṭhāpanasammuti sāditabbā.**A competent and capable nun who has ten years of seniority may agree to be approved to give the full admission.*";
P_HTM[8526]="*Dasavassāya gihigatāya sikkhā dātabbāti.**The training may be given to a married girl who is ten years old.”*";
P_HTM[8527]="*Dasakaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The section on tens is finished.*";
P_HTM[8528]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[8529]="*Āghātaṃ vinayaṃ vatthu,**“Resentment, getting rid of, grounds,*";
P_HTM[8530]="*micchā sammā ca antagā;**Wrong, and right, off;*";
P_HTM[8531]="*Micchattā ceva sammattā,**And kinds of wrongness, kinds of rightnesses,*";
P_HTM[8532]="*akusalā kusalāpi ca.**Unskillful, and also skillful.*";
P_HTM[8533]="*Salākā adhammā dhammā,**A vote: illegitimate, legitimate,*";
P_HTM[8534]="*sāmaṇerā ca nāsanā;**Novice monks, and expelling;*";
P_HTM[8535]="*Bhāsādhikaraṇañceva,**To say, and legal issues,*";
P_HTM[8536]="*ñattilahukameva ca.**Motion, and light.*";
P_HTM[8537]="*Lahukā garukā ete,**These light and heavy:*";
P_HTM[8538]="*kaṇhasukkā vijānatha;**Understand the dark and bright;*";
P_HTM[8539]="*Ubbāhikā ca sikkhā ca,**And committee, and training,*";
P_HTM[8540]="*antepure ca vatthūni.**And compound, reasons.*";
P_HTM[8541]="*Ratanaṃ dasavaggo ca,**Treasure, and a group of ten,*";
P_HTM[8542]="*tatheva upasampadā;**And so the full ordination;*";
P_HTM[8543]="*Paṃsukūladhāraṇā ca,**Rag, and wearing,*";
P_HTM[8544]="*dasāhasukkaitthiyo.**Ten days, semen, women.*";
P_HTM[8545]="*Bhariyā dasa vatthūni,**Wives, ten practices,*";
P_HTM[8546]="*avandiyakkosena ca;**Should not pay respect to, and abuse;*";
P_HTM[8547]="*Pesuññañceva senāni,**And malicious talebearing, kinds of furniture,*";
P_HTM[8548]="*varāni ca adhammikā.**And favors, illegitimate.*";
P_HTM[8549]="*Dhammikā yāgumaṃsā ca,**Legitimate, rice porridge, and meat,*";
P_HTM[8550]="*paramā bhikkhu bhikkhunī;**‘At the most’, monk, nun;*";
P_HTM[8551]="*Vuṭṭhāpanā gihigatā,**Full admission, married girl—*";
P_HTM[8552]="*dasakā suppakāsitāti.**The section on tens has been well proclaimed.”*";
P_HTM[8553]="*11. Ekādasakavāra**11. The section on elevens*";
P_HTM[8554]="*Ekādasa puggalā anupasampannā na upasampādetabbā, upasampannā nāsetabbā.**There are eleven kinds of people who should not be ordained, and if they have been ordained, they should be expelled.*";
P_HTM[8555]="*Ekādasa pādukā akappiyā.**There are eleven kinds of unallowable shoes.*";
P_HTM[8556]="*Ekādasa pattā akappiyā.**There are eleven kinds of unallowable almsbowls.*";
P_HTM[8557]="*Ekādasa cīvarāni akappiyāni.**There are eleven kinds of unallowable robes.*";
P_HTM[8558]="*Ekādasa yāvatatiyakā.**There are eleven “after the third”.*";
P_HTM[8559]="*Bhikkhunīnaṃ ekādasa antarāyikā dhammā pucchitabbā.**The nuns should be asked about the eleven obstructions.*";
P_HTM[8560]="*Ekādasa cīvarāni adhiṭṭhātabbāni.**There are eleven kinds of robe-cloth that should be determined.*";
P_HTM[8561]="*Ekādasa cīvarāni na vikappetabbāni.**There are eleven kinds of robe-cloth that should not be transferred.*";
P_HTM[8562]="*Ekādase aruṇuggamane nissaggiyaṃ hoti.**Becoming subject to relinquishment at dawn on the eleventh day.*";
P_HTM[8563]="*Ekādasa gaṇṭhikā kappiyā.**There are eleven kinds of allowable toggles.*";
P_HTM[8564]="*Ekādasa vidhā kappiyā.**There are eleven kinds of allowable buckles.*";
P_HTM[8565]="*Ekādasa pathavī akappiyā.**There are eleven kinds of unallowable earth.*";
P_HTM[8566]="*Ekādasa pathavī kappiyā.**There are eleven kinds of allowable earth.*";
P_HTM[8567]="*Ekādasa nissayapaṭippassaddhiyo.**There are eleven reasons why formal support comes to an end.*";
P_HTM[8568]="*Ekādasa puggalā avandiyā.**There are eleven kinds of people a monk should not pay respect to.*";
P_HTM[8569]="*Ekādasa paramāni.**There are eleven rules about ‘at the most’.*";
P_HTM[8570]="*Ekādasa varāni yāciṃsu.**They asked for eleven favors.*";
P_HTM[8571]="*Ekādasa sīmādosā.**There are eleven kinds of flaws in monastic boundaries.*";
P_HTM[8572]="*Akkosakaparibhāsake puggale ekādasādīnavā pāṭikaṅkhā.**There are eleven dangers to be expected for people who abuse and revile.*";
P_HTM[8573]="*Mettāya cetovimuttiyā āsevitāya bhāvitāya bahulīkatāya yānīkatāya vatthukatāya anuṭṭhitāya paricitāya susamāraddhāya ekādasānisaṃsā pāṭikaṅkhā.**There are eleven benefits to be expected for one who practices the liberation of mind through love, who develops, cultivates, and makes it a vehicle and basis, who keeps it up, accumulates, and properly implements it:*";
P_HTM[8574]="*Sukhaṃ supati, sukhaṃ paṭibujjhati, na pāpakaṃ supinaṃ passati, manussānaṃ piyo hoti, amanussānaṃ piyo hoti, devatā rakkhanti, nāssa aggi vā visaṃ vā satthaṃ vā kamati, tuvaṭṭaṃ cittaṃ samādhiyati, mukhavaṇṇo vippasīdati, asammūḷho kālaṃ karoti, uttari appaṭivijjhanto brahmalokūpago hoti—**you sleep well, wake up rested, and have no nightmares; you are loved by humans and spirits; you are protected by the gods; you cannot be harmed by fire, poison, or weapons; your mind is quickly stilled; your face is serene; you dies unconfused; and if you do not go any further, you are reborn in the world of the supreme beings.”*";
P_HTM[8575]="*mettāya cetovimuttiyā āsevitāya bhāvitāya bahulīkatāya yānīkatāya vatthukatāya anuṭṭhitāya paricitāya susamāraddhāya ime ekādasānisaṃsā pāṭikaṅkhāti.* **";
P_HTM[8576]="*Ekādasakaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The section on elevens is finished.*";
P_HTM[8577]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[8578]="*Nāsetabbā pādukā ca,**“Should be expelled, and shoes,*";
P_HTM[8579]="*pattā ca cīvarāni ca;**And bowls, and robes;*";
P_HTM[8580]="*Tatiyā pucchitabbā ca,**Three, and should be asked about,*";
P_HTM[8581]="*adhiṭṭhānavikappanā.**Determination, transferring.*";
P_HTM[8582]="*Aruṇā gaṇṭhikā vidhā,**Dawn, toggles, buckles,*";
P_HTM[8583]="*akappiyā ca kappiyaṃ;**And unallowable, allowable;*";
P_HTM[8584]="*Nissayāvandiyā ceva,**Formal support, and pay respect to,*";
P_HTM[8585]="*paramāni varāni ca;**‘At the most’, and favors;*";
P_HTM[8586]="*Sīmādosā ca akkosā,**And flaws in boundaries, abuse,*";
P_HTM[8587]="*mettāyekādasā katāti.**With love—the section on elevens is done.”*";
P_HTM[8588]="*Ekuttarikaṃ.**The increasing by one is finished.*";
P_HTM[8589]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[8590]="*Ekakā ca dukā ceva,**“The ones, and twos,*";
P_HTM[8591]="*tikā ca catupañcakā;**And the threes, fours, fives;*";
P_HTM[8592]="*Chasattaṭṭhanavakā ca,**And the sixes, sevens, eights, nines,*";
P_HTM[8593]="*dasa ekādasāni ca.**The tens, and the elevens.*";
P_HTM[8594]="*Hitāya sabbasattānaṃ,**The stainless increasing by one,*";
P_HTM[8595]="*ñātadhammena tādinā;**Taught by the Unwavering One,*";
P_HTM[8596]="*Ekuttarikā vimalā,**The Great Hero who knows the Teaching,*";
P_HTM[8597]="*mahāvīrena desitāti.**For the welfare of all beings.”*";
P_HTM[8598]="*Ekuttarikaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The increasing by one is finished.*";
P_HTM[8599]="*124. 1 Ādimajjhantapucchana **124.  1. Questions on the beginning, the middle, and the end *";
P_HTM[8600]="*Uposathakammassa ko ādi, kiṃ majjhe, kiṃ pariyosānaṃ?**What is the beginning, the middle, and the end of the observance-day procedure?*";
