P_HTM[8774]="*te suṇohi yathātathaṃ;**Listen to them as they truly are:*";
P_HTM[8775]="*Methunaviggahuttari,**Sexual intercourse, person, super,*";
P_HTM[8776]="*atirekañca kāḷakaṃ.**And extra, black.*";
P_HTM[8777]="*Bhūtaṃ paramparabhattaṃ,**True, a meal before another,*";
P_HTM[8778]="*dantaponena acelako;**With tooth cleaner, naked ascetic;*";
P_HTM[8779]="*Bhikkhunīsu ca akkoso,**And abuse among the nuns—*";
P_HTM[8780]="*dasete vesāliyaṃ katā.**These ten were pronounced at Vesālī.*";
P_HTM[8781]="*Ye rājagahe paññattā,**Those laid down at Rājagaha,*";
P_HTM[8782]="*Te suṇohi yathātathaṃ;**Listen to them as they truly are:*";
P_HTM[8783]="*Adinnādānaṃ rājagahe,**Stealing at Rājagaha,*";
P_HTM[8784]="*Dve anuddhaṃsanā dvepi ca bhedā.**Two on charging, and also two on schism.*";
P_HTM[8785]="*Antaravāsakaṃ rūpiyaṃ suttaṃ,**Sarong, money, thread,*";
P_HTM[8786]="*Ujjhāpanena ca pācitapiṇḍaṃ;**And with complaining, having almsfood prepared;*";
P_HTM[8787]="*Gaṇabhojanaṃ vikāle ca,**A group meal, and at the wrong time,*";
P_HTM[8788]="*Cārittaṃ nahānaṃ ūnavīsati.**Visiting, bathing, less than twenty.*";
P_HTM[8789]="*Cīvaraṃ datvā vosāsanti,**Gives out a robe, giving directions—*";
P_HTM[8790]="*Ete rājagahe katā;**These were pronounced at Rājagaha;*";
P_HTM[8791]="*Giraggacariyā tattheva,**Hilltop, wandering, right there,*";
P_HTM[8792]="*Chandadānena ekavīsati.**With given consent it is twenty-one.*";
P_HTM[8793]="*Ye sāvatthiyaṃ paññattā,**Those laid down at Sāvatthī,*";
P_HTM[8794]="*Te suṇohi yathātathaṃ;**Listen to them as they truly are:*";
P_HTM[8795]="*Pārājikāni cattāri,**Four offenses entailing expulsion,*";
P_HTM[8796]="*Saṅghādisesā bhavanti soḷasa.**And sixteen offenses entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[8797]="*Aniyatā ca dve honti,**And the two undetermined offenses,*";
P_HTM[8798]="*nissaggiyā catuvīsati;**Twenty-four offenses entailing relinquishment;*";
P_HTM[8799]="*Chapaññāsasatañceva,**And one hundred and fifty-six*";
P_HTM[8800]="*khuddakāni pavuccanti.**Minor offenses were spoken.*";
P_HTM[8801]="*Dasayeva ca gārayhā,**And ten on blameworthy,*";
P_HTM[8802]="*dvesattati ca sekhiyā;**And seventy-two on training—*";
P_HTM[8803]="*Chaūna tīṇisatāni,**Two hundred and ninety-four,*";
P_HTM[8804]="*sabbe sāvatthiyaṃ katā.**All pronounced at Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[8805]="*Ye āḷaviyaṃ paññattā,**Those laid down at Āḷavī,*";
P_HTM[8806]="*te suṇohi yathātathaṃ;**Listen to them as they truly are:*";
P_HTM[8807]="*Kuṭikosiyaseyyā ca,**Hut, silk, and sleeping place,*";
P_HTM[8808]="*khaṇane gaccha devate;**On digging, go deity;*";
P_HTM[8809]="*Sappāṇakañca siñcanti,**And they pour water that contains living beings—*";
P_HTM[8810]="*cha ete āḷaviyaṃ katā.**These six were pronounced at Āḷavī.*";
P_HTM[8811]="*Ye kosambiyaṃ paññattā,**Those laid down at Kosambī,*";
P_HTM[8812]="*te suṇohi yathātathaṃ;**Listen to them as they truly are:*";
P_HTM[8813]="*Mahāvihāro dovacassaṃ,**A large dwelling, difficult to correct,*";
P_HTM[8814]="*aññaṃ dvāraṃ surāya ca;**Evasive, door, and with alcohol;*";
P_HTM[8815]="*Anādariyaṃ sahadhammo,**Disrespect, legitimately,*";
P_HTM[8816]="*payopānena aṭṭhamaṃ.**And the eighth is with a milk drink.*";
P_HTM[8817]="*Ye sakkesu paññattā,**Those laid down among the Sakyans,*";
P_HTM[8818]="*te suṇohi yathātathaṃ;**Listen to them as they truly are:*";
P_HTM[8819]="*Eḷakalomāni patto ca,**Wool, and bowl,*";
P_HTM[8820]="*ovādo ceva bhesajjaṃ.**And instruction, medicine.*";
P_HTM[8821]="*Sūci āraññiko ceva,**Needle, and wilderness:*";
P_HTM[8822]="*aṭṭhete kāpilavatthave;**The eight at Kapilavatthu;*";
P_HTM[8823]="*Udakasuddhiyā ovādo,**With cleaning with water, and instruction,*";
P_HTM[8824]="*bhikkhunīsu pavuccanti.**Spoken among the nuns.*";
P_HTM[8825]="*Ye bhaggesu paññattā,**Those laid down among the Bhaggas,*";
P_HTM[8826]="*te suṇohi yathātathaṃ;**Listen to them as they truly are:*";
P_HTM[8827]="*Samādahitvā visibbenti,**They lit a fire to warm themselves,*";
P_HTM[8828]="*sāmisena sasitthakaṃ.**Soiled with food, containing rice.*";
P_HTM[8829]="*Pārājikāni cattāri,**The four offenses entailing expulsion,*";
P_HTM[8830]="*saṅghādisesāni bhavanti;**Seven offenses entailing suspension;*";
P_HTM[8831]="*Satta ca nissaggiyāni,**Eight offenses entailing relinquishment,*";
P_HTM[8832]="*aṭṭha dvattiṃsa khuddakā.**And thirty-two minor offenses.*";
P_HTM[8833]="*Dve gārayhā tayo sekkhā,**Two blameworthy offenses, and three on training—*";
P_HTM[8834]="*chappaññāsa sikkhāpadā;**Fifty-six training rules,*";
P_HTM[8835]="*Chasu nagaresu paññattā,**Laid down at six towns,*";
P_HTM[8836]="*buddhenādiccabandhunā.**By the Buddha, the Kinsman of the Sun.*";
P_HTM[8837]="*Chaūna tīṇisatāni,**Two hundred and ninety-four,*";
P_HTM[8838]="*sabbe sāvatthiyaṃ katā;**All pronounced at Sāvatthī,*";
P_HTM[8839]="*Kāruṇikena buddhena,**By the compassionate Buddha,*";
P_HTM[8840]="*gotamena yasassinā”.**The famous Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[8841]="*2. Catuvipatti**2. The four kinds of failure*";
P_HTM[8842]="*“Yaṃ taṃ pucchimha akittayi no,**“What we have asked, you have answered;*";
P_HTM[8843]="*Taṃ taṃ byākataṃ anaññathā;**All is explained, not otherwise.*";
P_HTM[8844]="*Aññaṃ taṃ pucchāmi tadiṅgha brūhi,**I wish to ask you another question. Please tell me this:*";
P_HTM[8845]="*Garuka lahukañcāpi sāvasesaṃ;**Serious, and light, curable;*";
P_HTM[8846]="*Anavasesaṃ duṭṭhullañca aduṭṭhullaṃ,**Incurable, and grave, minor,*";
P_HTM[8847]="*Ye ca yāvatatiyakā.**And those that are ‘after the third’.*";
P_HTM[8848]="*Sādhāraṇaṃ asādhāraṇaṃ,**In common, not in common,*";
P_HTM[8849]="*Vibhattiyo ca yehi samathehi sammanti;**The ways that failures are settled—*";
P_HTM[8850]="*Sabbānipetāni viyākarohi,**Please explain all these too,*";
P_HTM[8851]="*Handa vākyaṃ suṇoma te”.**And we will listen to you.”*";
P_HTM[8852]="*“Ekatiṃsā ye garukā,**“There are thirty-one serious ones,*";
P_HTM[8853]="*Aṭṭhettha anavasesā;**And eight here that are incurable;*";
P_HTM[8854]="*Ye garukā te duṭṭhullā,**Those that are serious are grave,*";
P_HTM[8855]="*Ye duṭṭhullā sā sīlavipatti;**Those that are grave are failures in morality;*";
P_HTM[8856]="*Pārājikaṃ saṅghādiseso,**Offenses entailing expulsion, offenses entailing suspension—*";
P_HTM[8857]="*‘Sīlavipattī’ti vuccati.**they are called ‘failure in morality’.*";
P_HTM[8858]="*Thullaccayaṃ pācittiyā,**Serious offenses, offenses entailing confession,*";
P_HTM[8859]="*Pāṭidesanīyaṃ dukkaṭaṃ;**Offenses entailing acknowledgment, offenses of wrong conduct;*";
P_HTM[8860]="*Dubbhāsitaṃ yo cāyaṃ,**Offenses of wrong speech,*";
P_HTM[8861]="*Akkosati hasādhippāyo;**And whoever calls another names for fun—*";
P_HTM[8862]="*Ayaṃ sā ācāravipattisammatā.**this is considered failure in conduct.*";
P_HTM[8863]="*Viparītadiṭṭhiṃ gaṇhanti,**Holding on to distorted views,*";
P_HTM[8864]="*Asaddhammehi purakkhatā;**Aiming at what is contrary to the true Dhamma;*";
P_HTM[8865]="*Abbhācikkhanti sambuddhaṃ,**Misrepresenting the Awakened One,*";
P_HTM[8866]="*Duppaññā mohapārutā;**Being foolish, enveloped in delusion—*";
P_HTM[8867]="*Ayaṃ sā diṭṭhivipattisammatā.**this is considered failure in view.*";
P_HTM[8868]="*Ājīvahetu ājīvakāraṇā pāpiccho icchāpakato asantaṃ abhūtaṃ uttarimanussadhammaṃ ullapati, ājīvahetu ājīvakāraṇā sañcarittaṃ samāpajjati, ājīvahetu ājīvakāraṇā ‘yo te vihāre vasati, so bhikkhu arahā’ti bhaṇati, ājīvahetu ājīvakāraṇā bhikkhu paṇītabhojanāni attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjati, ājīvahetu ājīvakāraṇā bhikkhunī paṇītabhojanāni attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjati, ājīvahetu ājīvakāraṇā sūpaṃ vā odanaṃ vā agilāno attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjati.**When, to make a living—having bad desires, overcome by desire—one claims a non-existent, unreal superhuman quality; when, to make a living, one acts as a matchmaker; when, to make a living, one says, ‘Whatever monk lives in your dwelling is a perfected one;’ when, to make a living, a monk eats fine foods that he himself has asked for; when, to make a living, a nun eats fine foods that she herself has asked for; when, to make a living, one eats bean curry or rice that one has asked for oneself—*";
P_HTM[8869]="*Ayaṃ sā ājīvavipatti sammatā.**this is considered failure in livelihood.*";
P_HTM[8870]="*Ekādasa yāvatatiyakā,**There are eleven ‘after the third’;*";
P_HTM[8871]="*Te suṇohi yathātathaṃ;**Listen to them as they truly are:*";
P_HTM[8872]="*Ukkhittānuvattikā,**A nun who takes sides with one who has been ejected,*";
P_HTM[8873]="*Aṭṭha yāvatatiyakā;**Eight ‘after the third’,*";
P_HTM[8874]="*Ariṭṭho caṇḍakāḷī ca,**Ariṭṭha, and Caṇḍakālī—*";
P_HTM[8875]="*Ime te yāvatatiyakā”.**These are those ‘after the third’.”*";
P_HTM[8876]="*3. Chedanakādi**3. To be cut down, etc.*";
P_HTM[8877]="*“Kati chedanakāni?**“How many on ‘to be cut down’?*";
P_HTM[8878]="*Kati bhedanakāni?**How many on ‘to be destroyed’?*";
P_HTM[8879]="*Kati uddālanakāni?**How many on ‘to be stripped’?*";
P_HTM[8880]="*Kati anaññapācittiyāni?**How many on ‘no other, he commits an offense entailing confession’?*";
P_HTM[8881]="*Kati bhikkhusammutiyo?**How many on ‘the monks have agreed’?*";
P_HTM[8882]="*Kati sāmīciyo?**How many on ‘what is proper’?*";
P_HTM[8883]="*Kati paramāni?**How many on ‘at the most’?*";
P_HTM[8884]="*Kati jānanti paññattā,**How many on ‘knowing’?*";
P_HTM[8885]="*buddhenādiccabandhunā”.**Were laid down by the Buddha, the Kinsman of the Sun?”*";
P_HTM[8886]="*“Cha chedanakāni.**“There are six on ‘to be cut down’.*";
P_HTM[8887]="*Ekaṃ bhedanakaṃ.**There is one on ‘to be destroyed’.*";
P_HTM[8888]="*Ekaṃ uddālanakaṃ.**There is one on ‘to be stripped’.*";
P_HTM[8889]="*Cattāri anaññapācittiyāni.**There are four on ‘no other, he commits an offense entailing confession’.*";
P_HTM[8890]="*Catasso bhikkhusammutiyo.**There are four on ‘the monks have agreed’.*";
P_HTM[8891]="*Satta sāmīciyo.**There are seven on ‘what is proper’.*";
P_HTM[8892]="*Cuddasa paramāni.**There are fourteen on ‘at the most’.*";
P_HTM[8893]="*Sodasa jānanti paññattā,**There are sixteen on ‘knowing’.*";
P_HTM[8894]="*buddhenādiccabandhunā”.**They were laid down by the Buddha, the Kinsman of the Sun.”*";
P_HTM[8895]="*4. Asādhāraṇādi**4. Not in common, etc.*";
P_HTM[8896]="*“Vīsaṃ dve satāni,**“Two hundred and twenty*";
P_HTM[8897]="*Bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadāni;**Training rules for the monks*";
P_HTM[8898]="*Uddesaṃ āgacchanti uposathesu,**Come up for recitation on the Observance days;*";
P_HTM[8899]="*Tīṇi satāni cattāri;**Three hundred and four*";
P_HTM[8900]="*Bhikkhunīnaṃ sikkhāpadāni,**Training rules for the nuns*";
P_HTM[8901]="*Uddesaṃ āgacchanti uposathesu.**Come up for recitation on the Observance days.*";
P_HTM[8902]="*Chacattārīsā bhikkhūnaṃ,**Forty-six of the monks’ rules*";
P_HTM[8903]="*bhikkhunīhi asādhāraṇā;**Are not in common with the nuns.*";
P_HTM[8904]="*Sataṃ tiṃsā ca bhikkhunīnaṃ,**One hundred and thirty of the nuns’ rules*";
P_HTM[8905]="*bhikkhūhi asādhāraṇā.**Are not in common with the monks.*";
P_HTM[8906]="*Sataṃ sattati chacceva,**So one hundred and seventy-six in total*";
P_HTM[8907]="*ubhinnaṃ asādhāraṇā;**Are not in common.*";
P_HTM[8908]="*Sataṃ sattati cattāri,**One hundred and seventy-four*";
P_HTM[8909]="*ubhinnaṃ samasikkhatā.**Are trained in by both.*";
P_HTM[8910]="*Vīsaṃ dve satāni,**Two hundred and twenty*";
P_HTM[8911]="*Bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadāni;**Training rules for the monks*";
P_HTM[8912]="*Uddesaṃ āgacchanti uposathesu,**Come up for recitation on the Observance days.*";
P_HTM[8913]="*Te suṇohi yathātathaṃ.**Listen to them as they truly are:*";
P_HTM[8914]="*Pārājikāni cattāri,**The four offenses entailing expulsion;*";
P_HTM[8915]="*Saṅghādisesāni bhavanti terasa;**There are thirteen offenses entailing suspension;*";
P_HTM[8916]="*Aniyatā dve honti.**There are two undetermined offenses;*";
P_HTM[8917]="*Nissaggiyāni tiṃseva,**The thirty offenses entailing relinquishment;*";
P_HTM[8918]="*dvenavuti ca khuddakā;**And ninety-two minor offenses;*";
P_HTM[8919]="*Cattāro pāṭidesanīyā,**The four offenses entailing acknowledgment;*";
P_HTM[8920]="*pañcasattati sekhiyā.**The seventy-five rules to be trained in.*";
P_HTM[8921]="*Vīsaṃ dve satāni cime honti,**These are the two hundred and twenty*";
P_HTM[8922]="*Bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadāni;**Training rules for the monks*";
P_HTM[8923]="*Uddesaṃ āgacchanti uposathesu.**That comes up for recitation on the observance days.*";
P_HTM[8924]="*Tīṇi satāni cattāri,**Three hundred and four*";
P_HTM[8925]="*Bhikkhunīnaṃ sikkhāpadāni;**Training rules for the nuns*";
P_HTM[8926]="*Uddesaṃ āgacchanti uposathesu,**Come up for recitation on the Observance days.*";
P_HTM[8927]="*Te suṇohi yathātathaṃ.**Listen to them as they truly are:*";
P_HTM[8928]="*Pārājikāni aṭṭha,**The eight offenses entailing expulsion;*";
P_HTM[8929]="*Saṅghādisesāni bhavanti sattarasa;**There are seventeen offenses entailing suspension;*";
P_HTM[8930]="*Nissaggiyāni tiṃseva,**The thirty offenses entailing relinquishment;*";
P_HTM[8931]="*Sataṃ saṭṭhi cha ceva;**And one hundred and sixty-six*";
P_HTM[8932]="*Khuddakāni pavuccanti.**Are called minor offenses;*";
P_HTM[8933]="*Aṭṭha pāṭidesanīyā,**The eight offenses entailing acknowledgment;*";
P_HTM[8934]="*Pañcasattati sekhiyā;**The seventy-five rules to be trained in.*";
P_HTM[8935]="*Tīṇi satāni cattāri cime honti,**These are the three hundred and four*";
P_HTM[8936]="*Bhikkhunīnaṃ sikkhāpadāni;**Training rules for the nuns*";
P_HTM[8937]="*Uddesaṃ āgacchanti uposathesu.**That comes up for recitation on the observance days.*";
P_HTM[8938]="*Chacattārīsā bhikkhūnaṃ,**Forty-six of the monks’ rules*";
P_HTM[8939]="*bhikkhunīhi asādhāraṇā;**Are not in common with the nuns—*";
P_HTM[8940]="*Te suṇohi yathātathaṃ.**Listen to them as they truly are:*";
P_HTM[8941]="*Cha saṅghādisesā,**Six offenses entailing suspension*";
P_HTM[8942]="*dve aniyatehi aṭṭha;**With the two undetermined offenses are eight.*";
P_HTM[8943]="*Nissaggiyāni dvādasa,**Twelve offenses entailing relinquishment;*";
P_HTM[8944]="*tehi te honti vīsati.**With these there are twenty.*";
P_HTM[8945]="*Dvevīsati khuddakā,**Twenty-two minor offenses,*";
P_HTM[8946]="*Caturo pāṭidesanīyā;**Four offenses entailing acknowledgment—*";
P_HTM[8947]="*Chacattārīsā cime honti,**These are the forty-six*";
P_HTM[8948]="*Bhikkhūnaṃ bhikkhunīhi asādhāraṇā.**That the monks do not have in common with the nuns.*";
P_HTM[8949]="*Sataṃ tiṃsā ca bhikkhunīnaṃ,**One hundred and thirty of the nuns’ rules*";
P_HTM[8950]="*bhikkhūhi asādhāraṇā;**Are not in common with the monks—*";
P_HTM[8951]="*Te suṇohi yathātathaṃ.**Listen to them as they truly are:*";
P_HTM[8952]="*Pārājikāni cattāri,**Four offenses entailing expulsion,*";
P_HTM[8953]="*saṅghamhā dasa nissare;**Ten offenses where one is sent away from the Sangha,*";
P_HTM[8954]="*Nissaggiyāni dvādasa,**Twelve offenses entailing relinquishment,*";
P_HTM[8955]="*channavuti ca khuddakā;**And ninety-six minor offenses;*";
P_HTM[8956]="*Aṭṭha pāṭidesanīyā.**Eight offenses entailing acknowledgment—*";
P_HTM[8957]="*Sataṃ tiṃsā cime honti,**These are the one hundred and thirty*";
P_HTM[8958]="*Bhikkhunīnaṃ bhikkhūhi asādhāraṇā;**That the nuns do not have in common with the monks.*";
P_HTM[8959]="*Sataṃ sattati chacceva,**The one hundred and seventy-six*";
P_HTM[8960]="*Ubhinnaṃ asādhāraṇā;**That are not in common—*";
P_HTM[8961]="*Te suṇohi yathātathaṃ.**Listen to them as they truly are:*";
P_HTM[8962]="*Pārājikāni cattāri,**Four offenses entailing expulsion;*";
P_HTM[8963]="*Saṅghādisesāni bhavanti soḷasa;**There are sixteen offenses entailing suspension;*";
P_HTM[8964]="*Aniyatā dve honti,**There are the two undetermined offenses;*";
P_HTM[8965]="*Nissaggiyāni catuvīsati;**The twenty-four offenses entailing relinquishment;*";
P_HTM[8966]="*Sataṃ aṭṭhārasā ceva,**And one hundred and eighteen*";
P_HTM[8967]="*Khuddakāni pavuccanti;**Are called minor offenses;*";
P_HTM[8968]="*Dvādasa pāṭidesanīyā.**The twelve offenses entailing acknowledgment.*";
P_HTM[8969]="*Sataṃ sattati chaccevime honti,**These are the hundred and seventy-six*";
P_HTM[8970]="*Ubhinnaṃ asādhāraṇā;**That the two do not have in common.*";
P_HTM[8971]="*Sataṃ sattati cattāri,**One hundred and seventy-four*";
P_HTM[8972]="*Ubhinnaṃ samasikkhatā;**Are trained in by both—*";
P_HTM[8973]="*Te suṇohi yathātathaṃ.**Listen to them as they truly are:*";
P_HTM[8974]="*Pārājikāni cattāri,**Four offenses entailing expulsion;*";
P_HTM[8975]="*Saṅghādisesāni bhavanti satta;**There are seven offenses entailing suspension;*";
P_HTM[8976]="*Nissaggiyāni aṭṭhārasa,**Eighteen offenses entailing relinquishment;*";
P_HTM[8977]="*Samasattati khuddakā;**Seventy minor offenses;*";
P_HTM[8978]="*Pañcasattati sekhiyāni.**Seventy-five rules to be trained in.*";
P_HTM[8979]="*Sataṃ sattati cattāri cime honti,**These are the hundred and seventy-four*";
P_HTM[8980]="*Ubhinnaṃ samasikkhatā;**That are trained in by both.*";
P_HTM[8981]="*Aṭṭheva pārājikā ye durāsadā,**The eight offenses entailing expulsion that are dangerous to approach,*";
P_HTM[8982]="*Tālavatthusamūpamā.**Like the simile of a palm stump.*";
P_HTM[8983]="*Paṇḍupalāso puthusilā,**That person is like a withered leaf, like an ordinary stone that has broken in half,*";
P_HTM[8984]="*sīsacchinnova so naro;**Like someone with their head cut off.*";
P_HTM[8985]="*Tālova matthakacchinno,**Like a palm-tree with its top cut off,*";
P_HTM[8986]="*aviruḷhī bhavanti te.**They are incapable of growth.*";
P_HTM[8987]="*Tevīsati saṅghādisesā,**Twenty-three offenses entailing suspension,*";
P_HTM[8988]="*Dve aniyatā;**Two undetermined offenses,*";
P_HTM[8989]="*Dve cattārīsa nissaggiyā,**Forty-two offenses entailing relinquishment,*";
P_HTM[8990]="*Aṭṭhāsītisataṃ pācittiyā;**One hundred and eighty-eight offenses entailing confession,*";
P_HTM[8991]="*Dvādasa pāṭidesanīyā.**Twelve offenses entailing acknowledgment,*";
P_HTM[8992]="*Pañcasattati sekhiyā,**Seventy-five rules to be trained in.*";
P_HTM[8993]="*tīhi samathehi sammanti;**They are settled in three ways:*";
P_HTM[8994]="*Sammukhā ca paṭiññāya,**In the presence of, and with the admission of,*";
P_HTM[8995]="*tiṇavatthārakena ca.**And through covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[8996]="*Dve uposathā dve pavāraṇā,**There are two observance days, two Invitation days,*";
P_HTM[8997]="*Cattāri kammāni jinena desitā;**And four legal procedures taught by the Victor.*";
P_HTM[8998]="*Pañceva uddesā caturo bhavanti,**There are five recitations, and four: it is not different;*";
P_HTM[8999]="*Anaññathā āpattikkhandhā ca bhavanti satta.**And there are seven classes of offenses.*";
P_HTM[9000]="*Adhikaraṇāni cattāri,**The four kinds of legal issues*";
P_HTM[9001]="*Sattahi samathehi sammanti;**Are settled through seven principles:*";
P_HTM[9002]="*Dvīhi catūhi tīhi,**Through two of them, through four, through three,*";
P_HTM[9003]="*Kiccaṃ ekena sammati”.**And business is settled through one.”*";
P_HTM[9004]="*5. Pārājikādiāpatti**5. The offenses entailing expulsion, etc.*";
P_HTM[9005]="*“Pārājikan”ti yaṃ vuttaṃ,**“It is called, ‘An offense entailing expulsion’.*";
P_HTM[9006]="*taṃ suṇohi yathātathaṃ;**Listen to it as it really is:*";
P_HTM[9007]="*Cuto paraddho bhaṭṭho ca,**When one has fallen away, offended, and fallen down,*";
P_HTM[9008]="*saddhammā hi niraṅkato;**Rejected the true Teaching,*";
P_HTM[9009]="*Saṃvāsopi tahiṃ natthi,**One is also excluded from the community.*";
P_HTM[9010]="*tenetaṃ iti vuccati.**This it why it is called that.*";
P_HTM[9011]="*“Saṅghādiseso”ti yaṃ vuttaṃ,**It is called, ‘An offense entailing suspension’.*";
P_HTM[9012]="*taṃ suṇohi yathātathaṃ;**Listen to it as it really is:*";
P_HTM[9013]="*Saṅghova deti parivāsaṃ,**Only the Sangha gives probation,*";
P_HTM[9014]="*mūlāya paṭikassati;**Sends back to the beginning,*";
P_HTM[9015]="*Mānattaṃ deti abbheti,**Gives the trial period, and rehabilitates.*";
P_HTM[9016]="*tenetaṃ iti vuccati.**This it why it is called that.*";
P_HTM[9017]="*“Aniyato”ti yaṃ vuttaṃ,**It is called, ‘An undetermined offense’.*";
P_HTM[9018]="*taṃ suṇohi yathātathaṃ;**Listen to it as it really is:*";
P_HTM[9019]="*Aniyato na niyato,**Undetermined, not determined,*";
P_HTM[9020]="*anekaṃsikataṃ padaṃ;**An undecided rule,*";
P_HTM[9021]="*Tiṇṇamaññataraṃ ṭhānaṃ,**It is one of three cases.*";
P_HTM[9022]="*“aniyato”ti pavuccati.**It is called, ‘An undetermined offense’.*";
P_HTM[9023]="*“Thullaccayan”ti yaṃ vuttaṃ,**It is called, ‘A serious offense’.*";
P_HTM[9024]="*taṃ suṇohi yathātathaṃ;**Listen to it as it really is:*";
P_HTM[9025]="*Ekassa mūle yo deseti,**The one who confesses to instigating another,*";
P_HTM[9026]="*yo ca taṃ paṭigaṇhati;**And the one who agrees to it—*";
P_HTM[9027]="*Accayo tena samo natthi,**There is no offense that fits with that.*";
P_HTM[9028]="*tenetaṃ iti vuccati.**This it why it is called that.*";
P_HTM[9029]="*“Nissaggiyan”ti yaṃ vuttaṃ,**It is called, ‘An offense entailing relinquishment’.*";
P_HTM[9030]="*taṃ suṇohi yathātathaṃ;**Listen to it as it really is:*";
P_HTM[9031]="*Saṅghamajjhe gaṇamajjhe,**In the midst of the Sangha, in the midst of a group,*";
P_HTM[9032]="*ekasseva ca ekato;**Or just one with one,*";
P_HTM[9033]="*Nissajjitvāna deseti,**One relinquishes and then confesses.*";
P_HTM[9034]="*tenetaṃ iti vuccati.**This it why it is called that.*";
P_HTM[9035]="*“Pācittiyan”ti yaṃ vuttaṃ,**It is called, ‘An offense entailing confession’.*";
P_HTM[9036]="*Taṃ suṇohi yathātathaṃ;**Listen to it as it really is:*";
P_HTM[9037]="*Pāteti kusalaṃ dhammaṃ,**One lets go of a wholesome state,*";
P_HTM[9038]="*Ariyamaggaṃ aparajjhati;**Goes against the noble path,*";
P_HTM[9039]="*Cittasammohanaṭṭhānaṃ,**Having a deluded mind.*";
P_HTM[9040]="*Tenetaṃ iti vuccati.**This it why it is called that.*";
P_HTM[9041]="*“Pāṭidesanīyan”ti yaṃ vuttaṃ,**It is called, ‘An offense entailing acknowledgment’.*";
P_HTM[9042]="*Taṃ suṇohi yathātathaṃ;**Listen to it as it really is:*";
P_HTM[9043]="*Bhikkhu aññātako santo,**An unrelated monk,*";
P_HTM[9044]="*Kicchā laddhāya bhojanaṃ;**Whatever food she has obtained with difficulty,*";
P_HTM[9045]="*Sāmaṃ gahetvā bhuñjeyya,**Should he receive it himself and eat it,*";
P_HTM[9046]="*“Gārayhan”ti pavuccati.**It is called blameworthy.*";
P_HTM[9047]="*Nimantanāsu bhuñjantā chandāya,**When eating at an invitation,*";
P_HTM[9048]="*Vosāsati tattha bhikkhuniṃ;**And a nun there gives directions based on favouritism,*";
P_HTM[9049]="*Anivāretvā tahiṃ bhuñje,**If they eat without having stopped her,*";
P_HTM[9050]="*“Gārayhan”ti pavuccati.**It is called blameworthy.*";
P_HTM[9051]="*Saddhācittaṃ kulaṃ gantvā,**Going to a family that has faith,*";
P_HTM[9052]="*appabhogaṃ anāḷiyaṃ;**But is poor with little wealth,*";
P_HTM[9053]="*Agilāno tahiṃ bhuñje,**If one eats there without being sick,*";
P_HTM[9054]="*“gārayhan”ti pavuccati.**It is called blameworthy.*";
P_HTM[9055]="*Yo ce araññe viharanto,**If anyone stays in a wilderness,*";
P_HTM[9056]="*sāsaṅke sabhayānake;**That is risky and dangerous,*";
P_HTM[9057]="*Aviditaṃ tahiṃ bhuñje,**And they eat there without making an announcement,*";
P_HTM[9058]="*“gārayhan”ti pavuccati.**It is called blameworthy.*";
P_HTM[9059]="*Bhikkhunī aññātikā santā,**An unrelated nun,*";
P_HTM[9060]="*Yaṃ paresaṃ mamāyitaṃ;**Whatever belongs to others—*";
P_HTM[9061]="*Sappi telaṃ madhuṃ phāṇitaṃ,**Ghee, oil, honey, syrup,*";
P_HTM[9062]="*Macchamaṃsaṃ atho khīraṃ;**Fish, meat, milk, and curd—*";
P_HTM[9063]="*Dadhiṃ sayaṃ viññāpeyya bhikkhunī,**If she herself asks for them,*";
P_HTM[9064]="*Gārayhapattā sugatassa sāsane.**She has committed a blameworthy act in the instruction of the Accomplished One.*";
P_HTM[9065]="*“Dukkaṭan”ti yaṃ vuttaṃ,**It is called, ‘An offense of wrong conduct’.*";
P_HTM[9066]="*taṃ suṇohi yathātathaṃ;**Listen to it as it really is:*";
P_HTM[9067]="*Aparaddhaṃ viraddhañca,**Offended, and failed,*";
P_HTM[9068]="*khalitaṃ yañca dukkaṭaṃ.**Faltered, and what is badly done,*";
P_HTM[9069]="*Yaṃ manusso kare pāpaṃ,**Whatever people do that is bad,*";
P_HTM[9070]="*āvi vā yadi vā raho;**Whether in public or in private,*";
P_HTM[9071]="*“Dukkaṭan”ti pavedenti,**They declare to be wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9072]="*tenetaṃ iti vuccati.**This it why it is called that.*";
P_HTM[9073]="*“Dubbhāsitan”ti yaṃ vuttaṃ,**“It is called, ‘An offense of wrong speech’.*";
P_HTM[9074]="*taṃ suṇohi yathātathaṃ;**Listen to it as it really is:*";
P_HTM[9075]="*Dubbhāsitaṃ durābhaṭṭhaṃ,**Wrong speech, wrong utterance,*";
P_HTM[9076]="*saṅkiliṭṭhañca yaṃ padaṃ;**Whatever sentence is defiled,*";
P_HTM[9077]="*Yañca viññū garahanti,**And condemned by the wise.*";
P_HTM[9078]="*tenetaṃ iti vuccati.**This it why it is called that.*";
P_HTM[9079]="*“Sekhiyan”ti yaṃ vuttaṃ,**It is called, ‘To be trained in’.*";
P_HTM[9080]="*taṃ suṇohi yathātathaṃ;**Listen to it as it really is:*";
P_HTM[9081]="*Sekkhassa sikkhamānassa,**For one who is a trainee, training,*";
P_HTM[9082]="*ujumaggānusārino.**Following the straight path,*";
P_HTM[9083]="*Ādi cetaṃ caraṇañca,**This is the beginning and the right conduct,*";
P_HTM[9084]="*mukhaṃ saññamasaṃvaro;**With controlled mouth and restraint—*";
P_HTM[9085]="*Sikkhā etādisī natthi,**There is no training like this.*";
P_HTM[9086]="*tenetaṃ iti vuccati.**This it why it is called that.*";
P_HTM[9087]="*Channamativassati,**It rains on what’s concealed,*";
P_HTM[9088]="*vivaṭaṃ nātivassati;**Not on what’s revealed.*";
P_HTM[9089]="*Tasmā channaṃ vivaretha,**Therefore, reveal the concealed,*";
P_HTM[9090]="*evaṃ taṃ nātivassati.**And it will not be rained upon.*";
P_HTM[9091]="*Gati migānaṃ pavanaṃ,**The forest is the destination of deer,*";
P_HTM[9092]="*Ākāso pakkhinaṃ gati;**The air is the destination of birds,*";
P_HTM[9093]="*Vibhavo gati dhammānaṃ,**Non-existence is the destination of phenomena,*";
P_HTM[9094]="*Nibbānaṃ arahato gatīti.**Extinguishment is the destination of a Perfected One.”*";
P_HTM[9095]="*Gāthāsaṅgaṇikaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The collection of verses is finished.*";
