P_HTM[9103]="*Gāthāsaṅgaṇikaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The collection of verses is finished*";
P_HTM[9104]="*124. 1. Ukkoṭanabhedādi **124.  1. The sub*";
P_HTM[9105]="*Cattāri adhikaraṇāni.**There are four kinds of legal issues:*";
P_HTM[9106]="*Vivādādhikaraṇaṃ, anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ, āpattādhikaraṇaṃ, kiccādhikaraṇaṃ—**legal issues arising from disputes, legal issues arising from accusations, legal issues arising from offenses, legal issues arising from business.*";
P_HTM[9107]="*imāni cattāri adhikaraṇāni.* **";
P_HTM[9108]="*Imesaṃ catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ kati ukkoṭā?**How many reopenings are there of these four legal issues?*";
P_HTM[9109]="*Imesaṃ catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ dasa ukkoṭā.**Ten.*";
P_HTM[9110]="*Vivādādhikaraṇassa dve ukkoṭā, anuvādādhikaraṇassa cattāro ukkoṭā, āpattādhikaraṇassa tayo ukkoṭā, kiccādhikaraṇassa eko ukkoṭo—**There are two reopenings of legal issues arising from disputes, four of legal issues arising from accusations, three of legal issues arising from offenses, and one of legal issues arising from business.*";
P_HTM[9111]="*imesaṃ catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ ime dasa ukkoṭā.* **";
P_HTM[9112]="*Vivādādhikaraṇaṃ ukkoṭento kati samathe ukkoṭeti?**When reopening a legal issue arising from a dispute, how many principles for settling it does one reopen?*";
P_HTM[9113]="*Anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ ukkoṭento kati samathe ukkoṭeti?**When reopening a legal issue arising from an accusation, how many principles for settling it does one reopen?*";
P_HTM[9114]="*Āpattādhikaraṇaṃ ukkoṭento kati samathe ukkoṭeti?**When reopening a legal issue arising from an offense, how many principles for settling it does one reopen?*";
P_HTM[9115]="*Kiccādhikaraṇaṃ ukkoṭento kati samathe ukkoṭeti?**When reopening a legal issue arising from business, how many principles for settling it does one reopen?*";
P_HTM[9116]="*Vivādādhikaraṇaṃ ukkoṭento dve samathe ukkoṭeti.**When reopening a legal issue arising from a dispute, one reopens two principles for settling it.*";
P_HTM[9117]="*Anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ ukkoṭento cattāro samathe ukkoṭeti.**When reopening a legal issue arising from an accusation, one reopens two principles for settling it.*";
P_HTM[9118]="*Āpattādhikaraṇaṃ ukkoṭento tayo samathe ukkoṭeti.**When reopening a legal issue arising from an offense, one reopens two principles for settling it.*";
P_HTM[9119]="*Kiccādhikaraṇaṃ ukkoṭento ekaṃ samathaṃ ukkoṭeti.**When reopening a legal issue arising from business, one reopens two principles for settling it.*";
P_HTM[9120]="*Kati ukkoṭā?**How many kinds of reopening are there?*";
P_HTM[9121]="*Katihākārehi ukkoṭanaṃ pasavati?**In how many ways does a reopening come about?*";
P_HTM[9122]="*Katihaṅgehi samannāgato puggalo adhikaraṇaṃ ukkoṭeti?**How many qualities do people who reopen legal issues have?*";
P_HTM[9123]="*Kati puggalā adhikaraṇaṃ ukkoṭentā āpattiṃ āpajjanti?**How many kinds of people commit an offense when they reopen a legal issue?*";
P_HTM[9124]="*Dvādasa ukkoṭā.**There are twelve kinds of reopening.*";
P_HTM[9125]="*Dasahākārehi ukkoṭanaṃ pasavati.**A reopening comes about in ten ways.*";
P_HTM[9126]="*Catūhaṅgehi samannāgato puggalo adhikaraṇaṃ ukkoṭeti.**People who have four qualities reopen legal issues.*";
P_HTM[9127]="*Cattāro puggalā adhikaraṇaṃ ukkoṭentā āpattiṃ āpajjanti?**There are four kinds of people who commit an offense when they reopen legal issues.*";
P_HTM[9128]="*Katame dvādasa ukkoṭā?**What are the twelve kinds of reopening?*";
P_HTM[9129]="*Akataṃ kammaṃ, dukkaṭaṃ kammaṃ, puna kātabbaṃ kammaṃ, anihataṃ, dunnihataṃ, puna nihanitabbaṃ, avinicchitaṃ, duvinicchitaṃ, puna vinicchitabbaṃ, avūpasantaṃ, duvūpasantaṃ, puna vūpasametabbanti—**The legal procedure hasn’t been done; it’s been done badly; it should be done again; it’s not been settled; it’s been badly settled; it should be settled again; it’s not been decided; it’s been badly decided; it should be decided again; it’s not been resolved; it’s been badly resolved; it should be resolved again.*";
P_HTM[9130]="*ime dvādasa ukkoṭā.* **";
P_HTM[9131]="*Katamehi dasahākārehi ukkoṭanaṃ pasavati?**What are the ten ways that a reopening comes about?*";
P_HTM[9132]="*Tattha jātakaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ ukkoṭeti, tattha jātakaṃ vūpasantaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ ukkoṭeti, antarāmagge adhikaraṇaṃ ukkoṭeti, antarāmagge vūpasantaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ ukkoṭeti, tattha gataṃ adhikaraṇaṃ ukkoṭeti, tattha gataṃ vūpasantaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ ukkoṭeti, sativinayaṃ ukkoṭeti, amūḷhavinayaṃ ukkoṭeti, tassapāpiyasikaṃ ukkoṭeti, tiṇavatthārakaṃ ukkoṭeti—**One reopens a legal issue where it arose; one reopens a legal issue where it arose and was resolved; one reopens a legal issue while traveling; one reopens a legal issue that was resolved while traveling; one reopens a legal issue after going there; one reopens a legal issue that was resolved after going there; one reopens a resolution by recollection; one reopens a resolution because of past insanity; one reopens a decision on giving a further penalty; one reopens a decision of covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[9133]="*imehi dasahākārehi ukkoṭanaṃ pasavati.* **";
P_HTM[9134]="*Katamehi catūhaṅgehi samannāgato puggalo adhikaraṇaṃ ukkoṭeti?**What are the four qualities that people who reopen legal issues have?*";
P_HTM[9135]="*Chandāgatiṃ gacchanto adhikaraṇaṃ ukkoṭeti, dosāgatiṃ gacchanto adhikaraṇaṃ ukkoṭeti, mohāgatiṃ gacchanto adhikaraṇaṃ ukkoṭeti, bhayāgatiṃ gacchanto adhikaraṇaṃ ukkoṭeti—**they reopen legal issues swayed by desire, ill will, confusion, or fear.*";
P_HTM[9136]="*imehi catūhaṅgehi samannāgato puggalo adhikaraṇaṃ ukkoṭeti.* **";
P_HTM[9137]="*Katame cattāro puggalā adhikaraṇaṃ ukkoṭentā āpattiṃ āpajjanti?**Who are the four kinds of people who commit an offense when they reopen a legal issue?*";
P_HTM[9138]="*Tadahupasampanno ukkoṭeti ukkoṭanakaṃ pācittiyaṃ, āgantuko ukkoṭeti ukkoṭanakaṃ pācittiyaṃ, kārako ukkoṭeti ukkoṭanakaṃ pācittiyaṃ, chandadāyako ukkoṭeti ukkoṭanakaṃ pācittiyaṃ—**If one who was ordained on that very day does the reopening, they commit an offense entailing confession; if one who has newly arrived does the reopening, they commit an offense entailing confession; if the original doer does the reopening, they commit an offense entailing confession; if one who has given their consent does the reopening, they commit an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[9139]="*ime cattāro puggalā adhikaraṇaṃ ukkoṭentā āpattiṃ āpajjanti.* **";
P_HTM[9140]="*2. Adhikaraṇanidānādi**2. The sources of the legal issues, etc.*";
P_HTM[9141]="*Vivādādhikaraṇaṃ kiṃnidānaṃ, kiṃsamudayaṃ, kiṃjātikaṃ, kiṃpabhavaṃ, kiṃsambhāraṃ, kiṃsamuṭṭhānaṃ?**What is the source, the origin, the birth, the arising, the production, the origination of legal issues arising from disputes?*";
P_HTM[9142]="*Anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ kiṃnidānaṃ, kiṃsamudayaṃ, kiṃjātikaṃ, kiṃpabhavaṃ, kiṃsambhāraṃ, kiṃsamuṭṭhānaṃ?**What is the source, the origin, the birth, the arising, the production, the origination of legal issues arising from accusations?*";
P_HTM[9143]="*Āpattādhikaraṇaṃ kiṃnidānaṃ, kiṃsamudayaṃ, kiṃjātikaṃ, kiṃpabhavaṃ, kiṃsambhāraṃ, kiṃsamuṭṭhānaṃ?**What is the source, the origin, the birth, the arising, the production, the origination of legal issues arising from offenses?*";
P_HTM[9144]="*Kiccādhikaraṇaṃ kiṃnidānaṃ, kiṃsamudayaṃ, kiṃjātikaṃ, kiṃpabhavaṃ, kiṃsambhāraṃ, kiṃsamuṭṭhānaṃ?**What is the source, the origin, the birth, the arising, the production, the origination of legal issues arising from business?*";
P_HTM[9145]="*Vivādādhikaraṇaṃ vivādanidānaṃ vivādasamudayaṃ vivādajātikaṃ vivādapabhavaṃ vivādasambhāraṃ vivādasamuṭṭhānaṃ.**Legal issues arising from disputes have disputes as their source, their origin, their birth, their arising, their production, their origination.*";
P_HTM[9146]="*Anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ anuvādanidānaṃ anuvādasamudayaṃ anuvādajātikaṃ anuvādapabhavaṃ anuvādasambhāraṃ anuvādasamuṭṭhānaṃ.**Legal issues arising from accusations have accusations as their source, their origin, their birth, their arising, their production, their origination.*";
P_HTM[9147]="*Āpattādhikaraṇaṃ āpattinidānaṃ āpattisamudayaṃ āpattijātikaṃ āpattipabhavaṃ āpattisambhāraṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānaṃ.**Legal issues arising from offenses have offenses as their source, their origin, their birth, their arising, their production, their origination.*";
P_HTM[9148]="*Kiccādhikaraṇaṃ kiccayanidānaṃ kiccayasamudayaṃ kiccayajātikaṃ kiccayapabhavaṃ kiccayasambhāraṃ kiccayasamuṭṭhānaṃ.**Legal issues arising from business have business as their source, their origin, their birth, their arising, their production, their origination.*";
P_HTM[9149]="*Vivādādhikaraṇaṃ kiṃnidānaṃ, kiṃsamudayaṃ, kiṃjātikaṃ, kiṃpabhavaṃ, kiṃsambhāraṃ, kiṃsamuṭṭhānaṃ?**What is the source, the origin, the birth, the arising, the production, the origination of legal issues arising from disputes?*";
P_HTM[9150]="*Anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ …pe…**… of legal issues arising from accusations?*";
P_HTM[9151]="*āpattādhikaraṇaṃ …pe…**… of legal issues arising from offenses?*";
P_HTM[9152]="*kiccādhikaraṇaṃ kiṃnidānaṃ, kiṃsamudayaṃ, kiṃjātikaṃ, kiṃpabhavaṃ, kiṃsambhāraṃ, kiṃsamuṭṭhānaṃ?**What is the source, the origin, the birth, the arising, the production, the origination of legal issues arising from business?*";
P_HTM[9153]="*Vivādādhikaraṇaṃ hetunidānaṃ, hetusamudayaṃ, hetujātikaṃ, hetupabhavaṃ, hetusambhāraṃ, hetusamuṭṭhānaṃ.**Legal issues arising from disputes have causes as their source, their origin, their birth, their arising, their production, their origination.*";
P_HTM[9154]="*Anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ …pe…**Legal issues arising from accusations …*";
P_HTM[9155]="*āpattādhikaraṇaṃ …pe…**Legal issues arising from offenses …*";
P_HTM[9156]="*kiccādhikaraṇaṃ hetunidānaṃ, hetusamudayaṃ, hetujātikaṃ, hetupabhavaṃ, hetusambhāraṃ, hetusamuṭṭhānaṃ.**Legal issues arising from business have causes as their source, their origin, their birth, their arising, their production, their origination.*";
P_HTM[9157]="*Vivādādhikaraṇaṃ kiṃnidānaṃ, kiṃsamudayaṃ, kiṃjātikaṃ, kiṃpabhavaṃ, kiṃsambhāraṃ, kiṃsamuṭṭhānaṃ?**What is the source, the origin, the birth, the arising, the production, the origination of legal issues arising from disputes?*";
P_HTM[9158]="*Anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ …pe…**… of legal issues arising from accusations?*";
P_HTM[9159]="*āpattādhikaraṇaṃ …pe…**… of legal issues arising from offenses?*";
P_HTM[9160]="*kiccādhikaraṇaṃ kiṃnidānaṃ, kiṃsamudayaṃ, kiṃjātikaṃ, kiṃpabhavaṃ, kiṃsambhāraṃ, kiṃsamuṭṭhānaṃ?**What is the source, the origin, the birth, the arising, the production, the origination of legal issues arising from business?*";
P_HTM[9161]="*Vivādādhikaraṇaṃ paccayanidānaṃ, paccayasamudayaṃ, paccayajātikaṃ, paccayapabhavaṃ, paccayasambhāraṃ, paccayasamuṭṭhānaṃ.**Legal issues arising from disputes have conditions as their source, their origin, their birth, their arising, their production, their origination.*";
P_HTM[9162]="*Anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ …pe…**Legal issues arising from accusations …*";
P_HTM[9163]="*āpattādhikaraṇaṃ …pe…**Legal issues arising from offenses …*";
P_HTM[9164]="*kiccādhikaraṇaṃ paccayanidānaṃ, paccayasamudayaṃ, paccayajātikaṃ, paccayapabhavaṃ, paccayasambhāraṃ, paccayasamuṭṭhānaṃ.**Legal issues arising from business have conditions as their source, their origin, their birth, their arising, their production, their origination.*";
P_HTM[9165]="*3. Adhikaraṇamūlādi**3. The roots of legal issues, etc.*";
P_HTM[9166]="*Catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ kati mūlāni, kati samuṭṭhānā?**How many roots do the four kinds of legal issues have, how many origins?*";
P_HTM[9167]="*Catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ tettiṃsa mūlāni, tettiṃsa samuṭṭhānā.**They have thirty-three roots, thirty-three origins.*";
P_HTM[9168]="*Catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ katamāni tettiṃsa mūlāni?**What are the thirty-three roots?*";
P_HTM[9169]="*Vivādādhikaraṇassa dvādasa mūlāni, anuvādādhikaraṇassa cuddasa mūlāni, āpattādhikaraṇassa cha mūlāni, kiccādhikaraṇassa ekaṃ mūlaṃ, saṅgho—**Legal issues arising from disputes have twelve roots; legal issues arising from accusations have fourteen roots; legal issues arising from offenses have six roots; legal issues arising from business have one root, the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[9170]="*catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ imāni tettiṃsa mūlāni.* **";
P_HTM[9171]="*Catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ katame tettiṃsa samuṭṭhānā?**What are the thirty-three origins?*";
P_HTM[9172]="*Vivādādhikaraṇassa aṭṭhārasabhedakaravatthūni samuṭṭhānā, anuvādādhikaraṇassa catasso vipattiyo samuṭṭhānā, āpattādhikaraṇassa sattāpattikkhandhā samuṭṭhānā, kiccādhikaraṇassa cattāri kammāni samuṭṭhānā—**Legal issues arising from disputes originate from the eighteen bases for schism; legal issues arising from accusations originate from the four kinds of failure; legal issues arising from offenses originate from the seven classes of offenses; legal issues arising from business originate from the four kinds of legal procedures.*";
P_HTM[9173]="*catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ ime tettiṃsa samuṭṭhānā.* **";
P_HTM[9174]="*4. Adhikaraṇapaccayāpatti**4. Offenses because of legal issues*";
P_HTM[9175]="*Vivādādhikaraṇaṃ āpattānāpattīti?**Is a legal issue arising from a dispute an offense or not an offense?*";
P_HTM[9176]="*Vivādādhikaraṇaṃ na āpatti.**It is not an offense.*";
P_HTM[9177]="*Kiṃ pana vivādādhikaraṇapaccayā āpattiṃ āpajjeyyāti?**Is it possible to commit an offense because of a legal issue arising from a dispute?*";
P_HTM[9178]="*Āma, vivādādhikaraṇapaccayā āpattiṃ āpajjeyya.**Yes.*";
P_HTM[9179]="*Vivādādhikaraṇapaccayā kati āpattiyo āpajjati?**How many offenses does one commit because of legal issues arising from disputes?*";
P_HTM[9180]="*Vivādādhikaraṇapaccayā dve āpattiyo āpajjati.**Two:*";
P_HTM[9181]="*Upasampannaṃ omasati, āpatti pācittiyassa;**there is an offense entailing confession for abusing one who is fully ordained;*";
P_HTM[9182]="*anupasampannaṃ omasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa—**there is an offense of wrong conduct for abusing one who is not fully ordained.*";
P_HTM[9183]="*vivādādhikaraṇapaccayā imā dve āpattiyo āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[9184]="*Tā āpattiyo catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ kati vipattiyo bhajanti?**When it comes to these offenses, to how many of the four kinds of failure do they belong?*";
P_HTM[9185]="*Catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ?**To which of the four kinds of legal issues do they belong?*";
P_HTM[9186]="*Sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ katihi āpattikkhandhehi saṅgahitā?**In how many of the seven classes of offenses are they found?*";
P_HTM[9187]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ katihi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhanti?**Through how many of the six kinds of origins of offenses do they originate?*";
P_HTM[9188]="*Katihi adhikaraṇehi, katisu ṭhānesu, katihi samathehi sammanti?**Through how many kinds of legal issues, in how many places, and through how many of the principles for settling legal issues are they settled?*";
P_HTM[9189]="*Tā āpattiyo catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ ekaṃ vipattiṃ bhajanti—**They belong to one kind of failure:*";
P_HTM[9190]="*ācāravipattiṃ.**failure in conduct.*";
P_HTM[9191]="*Catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ, āpattādhikaraṇaṃ.**They are legal issues arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[9192]="*Sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ dvīhi āpattikkhandhehi saṅgahitā—**They are found in two classes of offenses:*";
P_HTM[9193]="*siyā pācittiyāpattikkhandhena, siyā dukkaṭāpattikkhandhena.**they may be in the class of offenses entailing confession; they may be in the class of offenses of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9194]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ tīhi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhanti.**They originate in three ways.*";
P_HTM[9195]="*Ekena adhikaraṇena—**They are settled through one kind of legal issues:*";
P_HTM[9196]="*kiccādhikaraṇena;**legal issues arising from business.*";
P_HTM[9197]="*tīsu ṭhānesu—**They are settled in three places:*";
P_HTM[9198]="*saṅghamajjhe, gaṇamajjhe, puggalassa santike;**in the midst of the Sangha, in the midst of a group, or in the presence of an individual.*";
P_HTM[9199]="*tīhi samathehi sammanti—**They are settled through three principles:*";
P_HTM[9200]="*siyā sammukhāvinayena ca paṭiññātakaraṇena ca, siyā sammukhāvinayena ca tiṇavatthārakena ca.**they may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by acting according to what has been admitted; or they may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[9201]="*Anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ āpattānāpattīti?**Is a legal issue arising from an accusation an offense or not an offense?*";
P_HTM[9202]="*Anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ na āpatti.**It is not an offense.*";
P_HTM[9203]="*Kiṃ pana anuvādādhikaraṇapaccayā āpattiṃ āpajjeyyāti?**Is it possible to commit an offense because of a legal issue arising from an accusation?*";
P_HTM[9204]="*Āma, anuvādādhikaraṇapaccayā āpattiṃ āpajjeyya.**Yes.*";
P_HTM[9205]="*Anuvādādhikaraṇapaccayā, kati āpattiyo āpajjati?**How many offenses does one commit because of legal issues arising from accusation?*";
P_HTM[9206]="*Anuvādādhikaraṇapaccayā tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.**Three:*";
P_HTM[9207]="*Bhikkhuṃ amūlakena pārājikena dhammena anuddhaṃseti, āpatti saṅghādisesassa;**there is an offense entailing suspension for groundlessly charging a monk with an offense entailing expulsion;*";
P_HTM[9208]="*amūlakena saṅghādisesena anuddhaṃseti, āpatti pācittiyassa;**there is an offense entailing confession for groundlessly charging someone with an offense entailing suspension;*";
P_HTM[9209]="*amūlikāya ācāravipattiyā anuddhaṃseti, āpatti dukkaṭassa—**there is an offense of wrong conduct for groundlessly charging someone with failure in conduct.*";
P_HTM[9210]="*anuvādādhikaraṇapaccayā imā tisso āpattiyo āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[9211]="*Tā āpattiyo catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ kati vipattiyo bhajanti?**When it comes to these offenses, to how many of the four kinds of failure do they belong?*";
P_HTM[9212]="*Catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ?**To which of the four kinds of legal issues do they belong?*";
P_HTM[9213]="*Sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ katihi āpattikkhandhehi saṅgahitā?**In how many of the seven classes of offenses are they found?*";
P_HTM[9214]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ katihi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhanti?**Through how many of the six kinds of origins of offenses do they originate?*";
P_HTM[9215]="*Katihi adhikaraṇehi, katisu ṭhānesu, katihi samathehi sammanti?**Through how many kinds of legal issues, in how many places, and through how many of the principles for settling legal issues are they settled?*";
P_HTM[9216]="*Tā āpattiyo catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ dve vipattiyo bhajanti—**They belong to two kinds of failure:*";
P_HTM[9217]="*siyā sīlavipattiṃ, siyā ācāravipattiṃ.**they may be failure in morality; they may be failure in conduct.*";
P_HTM[9218]="*Catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ, āpattādhikaraṇaṃ.**They are legal issues arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[9219]="*Sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ tīhi āpattikkhandhehi saṅgahitā—**They are found in three classes of offenses:*";
P_HTM[9220]="*siyā saṅghādisesāpattikkhandhena, siyā pācittiyāpattikkhandhena, siyā dukkaṭāpattikkhandhena.**they may be in the class of offenses entailing suspension; they may be in the class of offenses entailing confession; they may be in the class of offenses of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9221]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ tīhi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhanti.**They originate in three ways.*";
P_HTM[9222]="*Yā tā āpattiyo garukā tā āpattiyo ekena adhikaraṇena—**The heavy offenses are settled through one kind of legal issues:*";
P_HTM[9223]="*kiccādhikaraṇena;**legal issues arising from business.*";
P_HTM[9224]="*ekamhi ṭhāne—**They are settled in one way:*";
P_HTM[9225]="*saṅghamajjhe;**in the midst of the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[9226]="*dvīhi samathehi sammanti—**They are settled through two principles:*";
P_HTM[9227]="*sammukhāvinayena ca paṭiññātakaraṇena ca.**by resolution face-to-face and by acting according to what has been admitted.*";
P_HTM[9228]="*Yā tā āpattiyo lahukā tā āpattiyo ekena adhikaraṇena—**The light offenses are settled through one kind of legal issues:*";
P_HTM[9229]="*kiccādhikaraṇena;**legal issues arising from business.*";
P_HTM[9230]="*tīsu ṭhānesu—**They are settled in three places:*";
P_HTM[9231]="*saṅghamajjhe gaṇamajjhe puggalassa santike;**in the midst of the Sangha, in the midst of a group, or in the presence of an individual.*";
P_HTM[9232]="*tīhi samathehi sammanti—**They are settled through three principles:*";
P_HTM[9233]="*siyā sammukhāvinayena ca paṭiññātakaraṇena ca, siyā sammukhāvinayena ca tiṇavatthārakena ca.**they may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by acting according to what has been admitted; or they may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[9234]="*Āpattādhikaraṇaṃ āpattānāpattīti?**Is a legal issue arising from an offense an offense or not an offense?*";
P_HTM[9235]="*Āpattādhikaraṇaṃ āpatti.**It is an offense.*";
P_HTM[9236]="*Kiṃ pana āpattādhikaraṇapaccayā āpattiṃ āpajjeyyāti?**Is it possible to commit an offense because of a legal issue arising from an offense?*";
P_HTM[9237]="*Āma, āpattādhikaraṇapaccayā āpattiṃ āpajjeyya.**Yes.*";
P_HTM[9238]="*Āpattādhikaraṇapaccayā kati āpattiyo āpajjati?**How many offenses does one commit because of legal issues arising from offenses?*";
P_HTM[9239]="*Āpattādhikaraṇapaccayā catasso āpattiyo āpajjati.**Four:*";
P_HTM[9240]="*Bhikkhunī jānaṃ pārājikaṃ dhammaṃ paṭicchādeti, āpatti pārājikassa;**there is an offense involving expulsion for a nun who knowingly conceals an offense entailing expulsion;*";
P_HTM[9241]="*vematikā paṭicchādeti, āpatti thullaccayassa;**there is a serious offense for concealing it if she is unsure;*";
P_HTM[9242]="*bhikkhu saṅghādisesaṃ paṭicchādeti, āpatti pācittiyassa;**there is an offense entailing confession for a monk who conceals an offense entailing suspension;*";
P_HTM[9243]="*ācāravipattiṃ paṭicchādeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa—**there is an offense of wrong conduct for concealing a failure in conduct.*";
P_HTM[9244]="*āpattādhikaraṇapaccayā imā catasso āpattiyo āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[9245]="*Tā āpattiyo catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ kati vipattiyo bhajanti?**When it comes to these offenses, to how many of the four kinds of failure do they belong?*";
P_HTM[9246]="*Catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ?**To which of the four kinds of legal issues do they belong?*";
P_HTM[9247]="*Sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ katihi āpattikkhandhehi saṅgahitā?**In how many of the seven classes of offenses are they found?*";
P_HTM[9248]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ katihi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhanti?**Through how many of the six kinds of origins of offenses do they originate?*";
P_HTM[9249]="*Katihi adhikaraṇehi, katisu ṭhānesu, katihi samathehi sammanti?**Through how many kinds of legal issues, in how many places, and through how many of the principles for settling legal issues are they settled?*";
P_HTM[9250]="*Tā āpattiyo catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ dve vipattiyo bhajanti—**They belong to two kinds of failure:*";
P_HTM[9251]="*siyā sīlavipattiṃ siyā ācāravipattiṃ.**they may be failure in morality; they may be failure in conduct.*";
P_HTM[9252]="*Catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ āpattādhikaraṇaṃ.**They are legal issues arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[9253]="*Sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ catūhi āpattikkhandhehi saṅgahitā—**They are found in four classes of offenses:*";
P_HTM[9254]="*siyā pārājikāpattikkhandhena, siyā thullaccayāpattikkhandhena, siyā pācittiyāpattikkhandhena, siyā dukkaṭāpattikkhandhena.**they may be in the class of offenses entailing expulsion; they may be in the class of serious offenses; they may be in the class of offenses entailing confession; they may be in the class of offenses of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9255]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhanti—**They originate in one way:*";
P_HTM[9256]="*kāyato ca vācato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhanti.**from body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[9257]="*Yā sā āpatti anavasesā sā āpatti na katamena adhikaraṇena, na katamamhi ṭhāne, na katamena samathena sammati.**The incurable offenses are not settled by any kind of legal issue, in any place, or through any of the principles for settling legal issues.*";
P_HTM[9258]="*Yā tā āpattiyo lahukā tā āpattiyo ekena adhikaraṇena—**The light offenses are settled through one kind of legal issues:*";
P_HTM[9259]="*kiccādhikaraṇena;**legal issues arising from business.*";
P_HTM[9260]="*tīsu ṭhānesu—**They are settled in three places:*";
P_HTM[9261]="*saṅghamajjhe, gaṇamajjhe, puggalassa santike;**in the midst of the Sangha, in the midst of a group, or in the presence of an individual.*";
P_HTM[9262]="*tīhi samathehi sammanti—**They are settled through three principles:*";
P_HTM[9263]="*siyā sammukhāvinayena ca paṭiññātakaraṇena ca, siyā sammukhāvinayena ca tiṇavatthārakena ca.**they may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by acting according to what has been admitted; or they may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[9264]="*Kiccādhikaraṇaṃ āpattānāpattīti?**Is a legal issue arising from business an offense or not an offense?*";
P_HTM[9265]="*Kiccādhikaraṇaṃ na āpatti.**It is not an offense.*";
P_HTM[9266]="*Kiṃ pana kiccādhikaraṇapaccayā āpattiṃ āpajjeyyāti?**Is it possible to commit an offense because of a legal issue arising from an accusation?*";
P_HTM[9267]="*Āma, kiccādhikaraṇapaccayā āpattiṃ āpajjeyya.**Yes.*";
P_HTM[9268]="*Kiccādhikaraṇapaccayā kati āpattiyo āpajjati?**How many offenses does one commit because of legal issues arising from business?*";
P_HTM[9269]="*Kiccādhikaraṇapaccayā pañca āpattiyo āpajjati.**Five:*";
P_HTM[9270]="*Ukkhittānuvattikā bhikkhunī yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjati, ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ;**there is an offense of wrong conduct after the motion when a nun takes sides with one who has been ejected and she does not stop when pressed up to the third time;*";
P_HTM[9271]="*dvīhi kammavācāhi thullaccayā;**there is a serious offense after each of the first two announcements;*";
P_HTM[9272]="*kammavācāpariyosāne āpatti pārājikassa;**there is an offense entailing expulsion when the last announcement is finished;*";
P_HTM[9273]="*bhedakānuvattakā bhikkhū yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjanti, āpatti saṅghādisesassa;**there is an offense entailing suspension when monks who side with a monk who is pursuing schism do not stop when pressed up to the third time;*";
P_HTM[9274]="*pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjanti, āpatti pācittiyassa—**there is an offense entailing confession when not giving up a bad view after being pressed up to the third time.*";
P_HTM[9275]="*kiccādhikaraṇapaccayā imā pañca āpattiyo āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[9276]="*Tā āpattiyo catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ kati vipattiyo bhajanti?**When it comes to these offenses, to how many of the four kinds of failure do they belong?*";
P_HTM[9277]="*Catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ?**To which of the four kinds of legal issues do they belong?*";
P_HTM[9278]="*Sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ katihi āpattikkhandhehi saṅgahitā?**In how many of the seven classes of offenses are they found?*";
P_HTM[9279]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ katihi samuṭṭhānehi samuṭṭhanti?**Through how many of the six kinds of origins of offenses do they originate?*";
P_HTM[9280]="*Katihi adhikaraṇehi, katisu ṭhānesu, katihi samathehi sammanti?**Through how many kinds of legal issues, in how many places, and through how many of the principles for settling legal issues are they settled?*";
P_HTM[9281]="*Tā āpattiyo catunnaṃ vipattīnaṃ dve vipattiyo bhajanti—**They belong to two kinds of failure:*";
P_HTM[9282]="*siyā sīlavipattiṃ siyā ācāravipattiṃ.**they may be failure in morality; they may be failure in conduct.*";
P_HTM[9283]="*Catunnaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ āpattādhikaraṇaṃ.**They are legal issues arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[9284]="*Sattannaṃ āpattikkhandhānaṃ pañcahi āpattikkhandhehi saṅgahitā—**They are found in five classes of offenses:*";
P_HTM[9285]="*siyā pārājikāpattikkhandhena, siyā saṅghādisesāpattikkhandhena, siyā thullaccayāpattikkhandhena, siyā pācittiyāpattikkhandhena, siyā dukkaṭāpattikkhandhena.**they may be in the class of offenses entailing expulsion; they may be in the class of offenses entailing suspension; they may be in the class of serious offenses; they may be in the class of offenses entailing confession; they may be in the class of offenses of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9286]="*Channaṃ āpattisamuṭṭhānānaṃ ekena samuṭṭhānena samuṭṭhanti—**They originate in one way:*";
P_HTM[9287]="*kāyato ca vācato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhanti.**from body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[9288]="*Yā sā āpatti anavasesā sā āpatti na katamena adhikaraṇena, na katamamhi ṭhāne, na katamena samathena sammati.**The incurable offenses are not settled by any kind of legal issue, in any place, or through any of the principles for settling legal issues.*";
P_HTM[9289]="*Yā sā āpatti garukā sā āpatti ekena adhikaraṇena—**The heavy offense is settled through one kind of legal issue:*";
P_HTM[9290]="*kiccādhikaraṇena;**a legal issue arising from business.*";
P_HTM[9291]="*ekamhi ṭhāne—**It is settled in one place:*";
P_HTM[9292]="*saṅghamajjhe;**in the midst of the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[9293]="*dvīhi samathehi sammati—**They are settled through two principles:*";
P_HTM[9294]="*sammukhāvinayena ca paṭiññātakaraṇena ca.**by resolution face-to-face and by acting according to what has been admitted.*";
P_HTM[9295]="*Yā tā āpattiyo lahukā tā āpattiyo ekena adhikaraṇena—**The light offenses are settled through one kind of legal issues:*";
P_HTM[9296]="*kiccādhikaraṇena;**legal issues arising from business.*";
P_HTM[9297]="*tīsu ṭhānesu—**They are settled in three places:*";
P_HTM[9298]="*saṅghamajjhe, gaṇamajjhe, puggalassa santike;**in the midst of the Sangha, in the midst of a group, or in the presence of an individual.*";
P_HTM[9299]="*tīhi samathehi sammanti—**They are settled through three principles:*";
P_HTM[9300]="*siyā sammukhāvinayena ca paṭiññātakaraṇena ca, siyā sammukhāvinayena ca tiṇavatthārakena ca.**they may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by acting according to what has been admitted; or they may be settled by resolution face-to-face and by covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[9301]="*5. Adhikaraṇādhippāya**5. The difference between legal issues*";
P_HTM[9302]="*Vivādādhikaraṇaṃ hoti anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ, hoti āpattādhikaraṇaṃ, hoti kiccādhikaraṇaṃ.**Is a legal issue arising from a dispute a legal issue arising from an accusation, a legal issue arising from an offense, or a legal issue arising from business?*";
P_HTM[9303]="*Vivādādhikaraṇaṃ na hoti anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ, na hoti āpattādhikaraṇaṃ, na hoti kiccādhikaraṇaṃ;**A legal issue arising from a dispute is neither a legal issue arising from an accusation, nor a legal issue arising from an offense, nor a legal issue arising from business.*";
P_HTM[9304]="*api ca, vivādādhikaraṇapaccayā hoti anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ, hoti āpattādhikaraṇaṃ, hoti kiccādhikaraṇaṃ.**Nevertheless, because of a legal issue arising from a dispute, there is legal issue arising from an accusation, a legal issue arising from an offense, and a legal issue arising from business.*";
P_HTM[9305]="*Yathā kathaṃ viya?**How is this?*";
P_HTM[9306]="*Idha bhikkhū vivadanti—**It may be that monks are disputing, saying,*";
P_HTM[9307]="*dhammoti vā adhammoti vā …pe…**‘This is the Teaching’, ‘This is contrary to the Teaching’ …*";
P_HTM[9308]="*duṭṭhullāpattīti vā aduṭṭhullāpattīti vā.**‘This is a grave offense’, or ‘This is a minor offense.’*";
P_HTM[9309]="*Yaṃ tattha bhaṇḍanaṃ kalaho viggaho vivādo nānāvādo aññathāvādo vipaccatāya vohāro medhakaṃ, idaṃ vuccati vivādādhikaraṇaṃ.**In regard to this, whatever quarreling, arguing, conflict, disputing, variety in opinion, difference in opinion, heated speech, or strife there is, this called a legal issue arising from a dispute.*";
P_HTM[9310]="*Vivādādhikaraṇe saṅgho vivadati vivādādhikaraṇaṃ.**When, during a legal issue arising from a dispute, the Sangha disputes, there is a legal issue arising from a dispute.*";
P_HTM[9311]="*Vivadamāno anuvadati anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ.**When one who is disputing makes an accusation, there is an legal issue arising from an accusation.*";
P_HTM[9312]="*Anuvadamāno āpattiṃ āpajjati āpattādhikaraṇaṃ.**When one who is accusing commits an offense, there is a legal issue arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[9313]="*Tāya āpattiyā saṅgho kammaṃ karoti kiccādhikaraṇaṃ.**When the Sangha does a legal procedure because of that offense, there is a legal issue arising from business.*";
P_HTM[9314]="*Evaṃ vivādādhikaraṇapaccayā hoti anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ, hoti āpattādhikaraṇaṃ, hoti kiccādhikaraṇaṃ.**In this way, a legal issue arising from a dispute is a legal issue arising from an accusation, a legal issue arising from an offense, and a legal issue arising from business.*";
P_HTM[9315]="*Anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ hoti āpattādhikaraṇaṃ, hoti kiccādhikaraṇaṃ, hoti vivādādhikaraṇaṃ.**Is a legal issue arising from an accusation a legal issue arising from an offense, a legal issue arising from business, or legal issue arising from a dispute?*";
P_HTM[9316]="*Anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ na hoti āpattādhikaraṇaṃ, na hoti kiccādhikaraṇaṃ, na hoti vivādādhikaraṇaṃ;**A legal issue arising from an accusation is neither a legal issue arising from an offense, nor a legal issue arising from business, nor a legal issue arising from a dispute.*";
P_HTM[9317]="*api ca anuvādādhikaraṇapaccayā hoti āpattādhikaraṇaṃ, hoti kiccādhikaraṇaṃ, hoti vivādādhikaraṇaṃ.**Nevertheless, because of a legal issue arising from an accusation, there is a legal issue arising from an offense, a legal issue arising from business, and a legal issue arising from a dispute.*";
P_HTM[9318]="*Yathā kathaṃ viya?**How is this?*";
P_HTM[9319]="*Idha bhikkhū bhikkhuṃ anuvadanti sīlavipattiyā vā ācāravipattiyā vā diṭṭhivipattiyā vā ājīvavipattiyā vā.**It may be that the monks accuse a monk of failure in morality, failure in conduct, failure in view, or failure in livelihood.*";
P_HTM[9320]="*Yo tattha anuvādo anuvadanā anullapanā anubhaṇanā anusampavaṅkatā abbhussahanatā anubalappadānaṃ, idaṃ vuccati anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ.**In regard to this, whatever accusation, accusing, allegation, blame, taking sides because of friendship, taking part in the accusation, or supporting the accusation there is, this is called a legal issue arising from an accusation.*";
P_HTM[9321]="*Anuvādādhikaraṇe saṅgho vivadati, vivādādhikaraṇaṃ.**When, during a legal issue arising from an accusation, the Sangha disputes, there is a legal issue arising from a dispute.*";
P_HTM[9322]="*Vivadamāno anuvadati, anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ.**When one who is disputing makes an accusation, there is an legal issue arising from an accusation.*";
P_HTM[9323]="*Anuvadamāno āpattiṃ āpajjati, āpattādhikaraṇaṃ.**When one who is accusing commits an offense, there is a legal issue arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[9324]="*Tāya āpattiyā saṅgho kammaṃ karoti, kiccādhikaraṇaṃ.**When the Sangha does a legal procedure because of that offense, there is a legal issue arising from business.*";
P_HTM[9325]="*Evaṃ anuvādādhikaraṇapaccayā hoti āpattādhikaraṇaṃ, hoti kiccādhikaraṇaṃ, hoti vivādādhikaraṇaṃ.**In this way, a legal issue arising from an accusation is a legal issue arising from an offense, a legal issue arising from business, and a legal issue arising from a dispute.*";
P_HTM[9326]="*Āpattādhikaraṇaṃ hoti kiccādhikaraṇaṃ, hoti vivādādhikaraṇaṃ, hoti anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ.**Is a legal issue arising from an offense a legal issue arising from business, a legal issue arising from a dispute, or a legal issue arising from an accusation?*";
P_HTM[9327]="*Āpattādhikaraṇaṃ na hoti kiccādhikaraṇaṃ, na hoti vivādādhikaraṇaṃ, na hoti anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ;**A legal issue arising from an offense is neither a legal issue arising from business, nor a legal issue arising from a dispute, nor a legal issue arising from an accusation.*";
P_HTM[9328]="*api ca āpattādhikaraṇapaccayā hoti kiccādhikaraṇaṃ, hoti vivādādhikaraṇaṃ, hoti anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ.**Nevertheless, because of a legal issue arising from an offense, there is a legal issue arising from business, a legal issue arising from a dispute, and a legal issue arising from an accusation.*";
P_HTM[9329]="*Yathā kathaṃ viya?**How is this?*";
P_HTM[9330]="*Pañcapi āpattikkhandhā āpattādhikaraṇaṃ, sattapi āpattikkhandhā āpattādhikaraṇaṃ, idaṃ vuccati āpattādhikaraṇaṃ.**There are legal issues arising from offenses because of the five classes of offenses, and there are legal issues arising from offenses because of the seven classes of offenses—these are called legal issues arising from offenses.*";
P_HTM[9331]="*Āpattādhikaraṇe saṅgho vivadati vivādādhikaraṇaṃ.**When, during a legal issue arising from an offense, the Sangha disputes, there is a legal issue arising from a dispute.*";
P_HTM[9332]="*Vivadamāno anuvadati anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ.**When one who is disputing makes an accusation, there is an legal issue arising from an accusation.*";
P_HTM[9333]="*Anuvadamāno āpattiṃ āpajjati āpattādhikaraṇaṃ.**When one who is accusing commits an offense, there is a legal issue arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[9334]="*Tāya āpattiyā saṅgho kammaṃ karoti kiccādhikaraṇaṃ.**When the Sangha does a legal procedure because of that offense, there is a legal issue arising from business.*";
P_HTM[9335]="*Evaṃ āpattādhikaraṇapaccayā hoti kiccādhikaraṇaṃ, hoti vivādādhikaraṇaṃ, hoti anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ.**In this way, a legal issue arising from an offense is a legal issue arising from business, a legal issue arising from a dispute, and a legal issue arising from an accusation.*";
P_HTM[9336]="*Kiccādhikaraṇaṃ hoti vivādādhikaraṇaṃ, hoti anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ, hoti āpattādhikaraṇaṃ.**Is a legal issue arising from business a legal issue arising from a dispute, a legal issue arising from an accusation, or a legal issue arising from an offense?*";
P_HTM[9337]="*Kiccādhikaraṇaṃ na hoti vivādādhikaraṇaṃ, na hoti anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ, na hoti āpattādhikaraṇaṃ;**A legal issue arising from business is neither a legal issue arising from a dispute, nor a legal issue arising from an accusation, nor a legal issue arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[9338]="*api ca kiccādhikaraṇapaccayā hoti vivādādhikaraṇaṃ, hoti anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ, hoti āpattādhikaraṇaṃ.**Nevertheless, because of a legal issue arising from business, there is a legal issue arising from a dispute, a legal issue arising from an accusation, and a legal issue arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[9339]="*Yathā kathaṃ viya?**How is this?*";
P_HTM[9340]="*Yā saṅghassa kiccayatā karaṇīyatā apalokanakammaṃ ñattikammaṃ ñattidutiyakammaṃ ñatticatutthakammaṃ, idaṃ vuccati kiccādhikaraṇaṃ.**Whatever is the duty or the business of the Sangha—a legal procedure consisting of getting permission, a legal procedure consisting of one motion, a legal procedure consisting of one motion and one announcement, a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements—this is called a legal issue arising from business.*";
P_HTM[9341]="*Kiccādhikaraṇe saṅgho vivadati vivādādhikaraṇaṃ.**When, during a legal issue arising from business, the Sangha disputes, there is a legal issue arising from a dispute.*";
P_HTM[9342]="*Vivadamāno anuvadati anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ.**When one who is disputing makes an accusation, there is an legal issue arising from an accusation.*";
P_HTM[9343]="*Anuvadamāno āpattiṃ āpajjati āpattādhikaraṇaṃ.**When one who is accusing commits an offense, there is a legal issue arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[9344]="*Tāya āpattiyā saṅgho kammaṃ karoti kiccādhikaraṇaṃ.**When the Sangha does a legal procedure because of that offense, there is a legal issue arising from business.*";
P_HTM[9345]="*Evaṃ kiccādhikaraṇapaccayā hoti vivādādhikaraṇaṃ, hoti anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ, hoti āpattādhikaraṇaṃ.**In this way, a legal issue arising from business is a legal issue arising from a dispute, a legal issue arising from an accusation, and a legal issue arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[9346]="*6. Pucchāvāra**6. The section on questioning*";
P_HTM[9347]="*Yattha sativinayo tattha sammukhāvinayo?**When there is resolution by recollection, is there also resolution face-to-face?*";
P_HTM[9348]="*Yattha sammukhāvinayo tattha sativinayo?**When there is resolution face-to-face, is there also resolution by recollection?*";
P_HTM[9349]="*Yattha amūḷhavinayo tattha sammukhāvinayo?**When there is resolution because of past insanity, is there also resolution face-to-face?*";
