P_HTM[9456]="*sammukhāvinayoti vā yebhuyyasikāti vā …**Are resolution face-to-face and majority decision …*";
P_HTM[9457]="*sammukhāvinayoti vā tassapāpiyasikāti vā …**Are resolution face-to-face and a further penalty …*";
P_HTM[9458]="*sammukhāvinayoti vā tiṇavatthārakoti vā—ime dhammā nānatthā nānābyañjanā, udāhu ekatthā byañjanameva nānaṃ?**Are resolution face-to-face and covering over as if with grass different in meaning and different in phrasing, or the same in meaning and just different in wording?*";
P_HTM[9459]="*Sammukhāvinayoti vā sativinayoti vā—ime dhammā nānatthā ceva nānābyañjanā ca.**Resolution face-to-face and resolution by recollection are different in meaning and different in wording.*";
P_HTM[9460]="*Sammukhāvinayoti vā amūḷhavinayoti vā …pe…**Resolution face-to-face and resolution because of past insanity …*";
P_HTM[9461]="*sammukhāvinayoti vā paṭiññātakaraṇanti vā …**Resolution face-to-face and acting according to what has been admitted …*";
P_HTM[9462]="*sammukhāvinayoti vā yebhuyyasikāti vā …**Resolution face-to-face and majority decision …*";
P_HTM[9463]="*sammukhāvinayoti vā tassapāpiyasikāti vā …**Resolution face-to-face and a further penalty …*";
P_HTM[9464]="*sammukhāvinayoti vā tiṇavatthārakoti vā—ime dhammā nānatthā ceva nānābyañjanā ca.**Resolution face-to-face and covering over as if with grass are different in meaning and different in wording.*";
P_HTM[9465]="*Vivādo vivādādhikaraṇaṃ, vivādo no adhikaraṇaṃ, adhikaraṇaṃ no vivādo, adhikaraṇañceva vivādo ca?**Are there disputes that are a legal issue arising from a dispute? Are there disputes that are not a legal issue? Are there legal issues that are not a dispute? Are there legal issues that are also a dispute?*";
P_HTM[9466]="*Siyā vivādo vivādādhikaraṇaṃ, siyā vivādo no adhikaraṇaṃ, siyā adhikaraṇaṃ no vivādo, siyā adhikaraṇañceva vivādo ca.**There may be disputes that are a legal issue arising from a dispute; there may be disputes that are not a legal issue; there may legal issues that are not a dispute; there may be legal issues that are also a dispute.*";
P_HTM[9467]="*Tattha katamo vivādo vivādādhikaraṇaṃ?**How is there a dispute that is a legal issue arising from a dispute?*";
P_HTM[9468]="*Idha bhikkhū vivadanti dhammoti vā adhammoti vā …pe…**It may be that the monks are disputing, saying, ‘This is the Teaching’, ‘This is contrary to the Teaching’ …*";
P_HTM[9469]="*duṭṭhullā āpattīti vā aduṭṭhullā āpattīti vā.**‘This is a grave offense’, or ‘This is a minor offense.’*";
P_HTM[9470]="*Yaṃ tattha bhaṇḍanaṃ, kalaho, viggaho, vivādo, nānāvādo, aññathāvādo, vipaccatāya vohāro, medhakaṃ—**In regard to this, whatever quarreling, arguing, conflict, disputing, variety in opinion, difference in opinion, heated speech, or strife there is—*";
P_HTM[9471]="*ayaṃ vivādo vivādādhikaraṇaṃ.**this is a dispute that is a legal issue arising from a dispute.*";
P_HTM[9472]="*Tattha katamo vivādo no adhikaraṇaṃ?**How is there a dispute that is not a legal issue?*";
P_HTM[9473]="*Mātāpi puttena vivadati, puttopi mātarā vivadati, pitāpi puttena vivadati, puttopi pitarā vivadati, bhātāpi bhātarā vivadati, bhātāpi bhaginiyā vivadati, bhaginīpi bhātarā vivadati, sahāyopi sahāyena vivadati—**A mother disputes with her child; a child with their mother; a father with his child; a child with their father; a brother with his brother; a brother with his sister; a sister with her brother; a friend with their friend—*";
P_HTM[9474]="*ayaṃ vivādo no adhikaraṇaṃ.**this is a dispute that is not a legal issue.*";
P_HTM[9475]="*Tattha katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ no vivādo?**How is there a legal issue that is not a dispute?*";
P_HTM[9476]="*Anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ, āpattādhikaraṇaṃ, kiccādhikaraṇaṃ—**A legal issue arising from an accusation, a legal issue arising from an offense, a legal issue arising from business—*";
P_HTM[9477]="*idaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ no vivādo.**this is a legal issue that is not a dispute.*";
P_HTM[9478]="*Tattha katamaṃ adhikaraṇañceva vivādo ca?**How is there a legal issue that is also a dispute?*";
P_HTM[9479]="*Vivādādhikaraṇaṃ adhikaraṇañceva vivādo ca.**A legal issue arising from a dispute is a legal issue and also a dispute.*";
P_HTM[9480]="*Anuvādo anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ, anuvādo no adhikaraṇaṃ, adhikaraṇaṃ no anuvādo, adhikaraṇañceva anuvādo ca?**Are there accusations that are a legal issue arising from an accusation? Are there accusations that are not a legal issue? Are there legal issues that are not an accusation? Are there legal issues that are also an accusation?*";
P_HTM[9481]="*Siyā anuvādo anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ, siyā anuvādo no adhikaraṇaṃ, siyā adhikaraṇaṃ no anuvādo, siyā adhikaraṇañceva anuvādo ca.**There may be accusations that are a legal issue arising from an accusation; there may be accusations that are not a legal issue; there may be legal issues that are not an accusation; there may legal issues that are also an accusation.*";
P_HTM[9482]="*Tattha katamo anuvādo anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ?**How is there an accusation that is a legal issue arising from an accusation?*";
P_HTM[9483]="*Idha bhikkhū bhikkhuṃ anuvadanti sīlavipattiyā vā ācāravipattiyā vā diṭṭhivipattiyā vā ājīvavipattiyā vā.**It may be that the monks accuse a monk of failure in morality, failure in conduct, failure in view, or failure in livelihood.*";
P_HTM[9484]="*Yo tattha anuvādo, anuvadanā anullapanā anubhaṇanā anusampavaṅkatā abbhussahanatā anubalappadānaṃ—**In regard to this, whatever accusation, accusing, allegation, blame, taking sides because of friendship, taking part in the accusation, or supporting the accusation there is—*";
P_HTM[9485]="*ayaṃ anuvādo anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ.**this is an accusation that is a legal issue arising from an accusation.*";
P_HTM[9486]="*Tattha katamo anuvādo no adhikaraṇaṃ?**How is there an accusation that is not a legal issue?*";
P_HTM[9487]="*Mātāpi puttaṃ anuvadati, puttopi mātaraṃ anuvadati, pitāpi puttaṃ anuvadati, puttopi pitaraṃ anuvadati, bhātāpi bhātaraṃ anuvadati, bhātāpi bhaginiṃ anuvadati, bhaginīpi bhātaraṃ anuvadati, sahāyopi sahāyaṃ anuvadati—**A mother accuses her child; a child their mother; a father his child; a child their father; a brother his brother; a brother his sister; a sister her brother; a friend their friend—*";
P_HTM[9488]="*ayaṃ anuvādo no adhikaraṇaṃ.**this is an accusation that is not a legal issue.*";
P_HTM[9489]="*Tattha katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ no anuvādo?**How is there a legal issue that is not an accusation?*";
P_HTM[9490]="*Āpattādhikaraṇaṃ kiccādhikaraṇaṃ vivādādhikaraṇaṃ—**A legal issue arising from an offense, a legal issue arising from business, a legal issue arising from a dispute—*";
P_HTM[9491]="*idaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ no anuvādo.**this is a legal issue that is not an accusation.*";
P_HTM[9492]="*Tattha katamaṃ adhikaraṇañceva anuvādo ca?**How is there a legal issue that is also an accusation?*";
P_HTM[9493]="*Anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ adhikaraṇañceva anuvādo ca.**A legal issue arising from an accusation is a legal issue and also an accusation.*";
P_HTM[9494]="*Āpatti āpattādhikaraṇaṃ, āpatti no adhikaraṇaṃ, adhikaraṇaṃ no āpatti, adhikaraṇañceva āpatti ca?**Are there offenses that are a legal issue arising from an offense? Are there offenses that are not a legal issue? Are there legal issues that are not an offense? Are there legal issues that are also an offense?*";
P_HTM[9495]="*Siyā āpatti āpattādhikaraṇaṃ, siyā āpatti no adhikaraṇaṃ, siyā adhikaraṇaṃ no āpatti, siyā adhikaraṇañceva āpatti ca.**There may be offenses that are a legal issue arising from an offense; there may be offenses that are not a legal issue; there may be legal issues that are not an offense; there may be legal issues that are also an offense.*";
P_HTM[9496]="*Tattha katamā āpatti āpattādhikaraṇaṃ?**How is there an offense that is a legal issue arising from an offense?*";
P_HTM[9497]="*Pañcapi āpattikkhandhā āpattādhikaraṇaṃ.**There are legal issues arising from offenses because of the five classes of offenses;*";
P_HTM[9498]="*Sattapi āpattikkhandhā āpattādhikaraṇaṃ.**there are legal issues arising from offenses because of the seven classes of offenses—*";
P_HTM[9499]="*Ayaṃ āpatti āpattādhikaraṇaṃ.**this is an offense that is a legal issue arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[9500]="*Tattha katamā āpatti no adhikaraṇaṃ?**How is there an offense that is not a legal issue?*";
P_HTM[9501]="*Sotāpatti samāpatti—**The attainment of stream-entry—*";
P_HTM[9502]="*ayaṃ āpatti no adhikaraṇaṃ.**this is an attainment/offense that is not a legal issue.*";
P_HTM[9503]="*Tattha katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ no āpatti?**How is there a legal issue that is not an offense?*";
P_HTM[9504]="*Kiccādhikaraṇaṃ vivādādhikaraṇaṃ anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ—**A legal issue arising from business, a legal issue arising from a dispute, a legal issue arising from an accusation—*";
P_HTM[9505]="*idaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ no āpatti.**this is a legal issue that is not an offense.*";
P_HTM[9506]="*Tattha katamaṃ adhikaraṇañceva āpatti ca?**How is there a legal issue that is also an offense?*";
P_HTM[9507]="*Āpattādhikaraṇaṃ adhikaraṇañceva āpatti ca.**A legal issue arising from an offense is a legal issue and also an offense.*";
P_HTM[9508]="*Kiccaṃ kiccādhikaraṇaṃ, kiccaṃ no adhikaraṇaṃ, adhikaraṇaṃ no kiccaṃ, adhikaraṇañceva kiccañca?**Is there business that is a legal issue arising from business? Is there business that is not a legal issue? Are there legal issues that are not business? Are there legal issues that are also business?*";
P_HTM[9509]="*Siyā kiccaṃ kiccādhikaraṇaṃ, siyā kiccaṃ no adhikaraṇaṃ, siyā adhikaraṇaṃ no kiccaṃ, siyā adhikaraṇañceva kiccañca.**There may be business that is a legal issue arising from business; there may be business that is not a legal issue; there may be legal issues that are not business; there may be legal issues that are also business.*";
P_HTM[9510]="*Tattha katamaṃ kiccaṃ kiccādhikaraṇaṃ?**How is there business that is a legal issue arising from business?*";
P_HTM[9511]="*Yā saṅghassa kiccayatā karaṇīyatā apalokanakammaṃ ñattikammaṃ ñattidutiyakammaṃ ñatticatutthakammaṃ—**Whatever is the duty or the business of the Sangha—a legal procedure consisting of getting permission, a legal procedure consisting of one motion, a legal procedure consisting of one motion and one announcement, a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements—*";
P_HTM[9512]="*idaṃ kiccaṃ kiccādhikaraṇaṃ.**this is business that is a legal issue arising from business.*";
P_HTM[9513]="*Tattha katamaṃ kiccaṃ no adhikaraṇaṃ?**How is there business that is not a legal issue?*";
P_HTM[9514]="*Ācariyakiccaṃ upajjhāyakiccaṃ samānupajjhāyakiccaṃ samānācariyakiccaṃ—**The duty to teacher, the duty to a preceptor, the duty to a co-student, the duty to a co-pupil—*";
P_HTM[9515]="*idaṃ kiccaṃ no adhikaraṇaṃ.**this is business that is not a legal issue.*";
P_HTM[9516]="*Tattha katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ no kiccaṃ?**How is there a legal issue that is not business?*";
P_HTM[9517]="*Vivādādhikaraṇaṃ anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ āpattādhikaraṇaṃ—**A legal issue arising from a dispute, a legal issue arising from an accusation, a legal issue arising from an offense—*";
P_HTM[9518]="*idaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ no kiccaṃ.**this is a legal issue that is not business.*";
P_HTM[9519]="*Tattha katamaṃ adhikaraṇañceva kiccañca?**How is there a legal issue that is also business?*";
P_HTM[9520]="*Kiccādhikaraṇaṃ adhikaraṇañceva kiccaṃ cāti.**A legal issue arising from business is a legal issue and also business.”*";
P_HTM[9521]="*Adhikaraṇabhedaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The sub-division on legal issues is finished.*";
P_HTM[9522]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[9523]="*Adhikaraṇaṃ ukkoṭā,**Legal issue, reopenings,*";
P_HTM[9524]="*ākārā puggalena ca;**Ways, and with people;*";
P_HTM[9525]="*Nidānahetupaccayā,**Sources, causes, conditions,*";
P_HTM[9526]="*mūlaṃ samuṭṭhānena ca.**Roots, and with origin.*";
P_HTM[9527]="*Āpatti hoti yattha ca,**Offense, is, and when,*";
P_HTM[9528]="*saṃsaṭṭhā nidānena ca;**Connected, and with source;*";
P_HTM[9529]="*Hetupaccayamūlāni,**Cause, condition, roots,*";
P_HTM[9530]="*samuṭṭhānena byañjanā;**With origin, wording;*";
P_HTM[9531]="*Vivādo adhikaraṇanti,**Dispute, legal issue.*";
P_HTM[9532]="*bhedādhikaraṇe idanti.**This is in the sub-division on legal issues.*";
P_HTM[9533]="*124. 1. Codanādipucchāvissajjanā **124.  1. Questions and responses on accusing, etc. *";
P_HTM[9534]="*Codanā kimatthāya,**“‘What is the purpose of accusing?*";
P_HTM[9535]="*Sāraṇā kissa kāraṇā;**Why is there reminding?*";
P_HTM[9536]="*Saṅgho kimatthāya,**What is the purpose of the Sangha?*";
P_HTM[9537]="*Matikammaṃ pana kissa kāraṇā.**Why is there the taking of advice?’*";
P_HTM[9538]="*Codanā sāraṇatthāya,**‘The purpose of accusing is reminding,*";
P_HTM[9539]="*Niggahatthāya sāraṇā;**The purpose of reminding is restraint;*";
P_HTM[9540]="*Saṅgho pariggahatthāya,**The purpose of the Sangha is scrutiny,*";
P_HTM[9541]="*Matikammaṃ pana pāṭiyekkaṃ.**But taking advice is individual.*";
P_HTM[9542]="*Mā kho turito abhaṇi,**Don’t speak hastily,*";
P_HTM[9543]="*mā kho caṇḍikato bhaṇi;**Don’t speak fiercely;*";
P_HTM[9544]="*Mā kho paṭighaṃ janayi,**Don’t be hostile—*";
P_HTM[9545]="*sace anuvijjako tuvaṃ.**If you are an investigator.*";
P_HTM[9546]="*Mā kho sahasā abhaṇi,**Don’t speak fast,*";
P_HTM[9547]="*Kathaṃ viggāhikaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ;**Argumentative speech is not beneficial.*";
P_HTM[9548]="*Sutte vinaye anulome,**In line with the discourses and the Monastic Law,*";
P_HTM[9549]="*Paññatte anulomike.**In line with what has been laid down,*";
P_HTM[9550]="*Anuyogavattaṃ nisāmaya,**Consider carefully the proper procedure of examination,*";
P_HTM[9551]="*Kusalena buddhimatā kataṃ;**As formulated by the skilled Awakened One,*";
P_HTM[9552]="*Suvuttaṃ sikkhāpadānulomikaṃ,**Well-spoken in line with the training rules—*";
P_HTM[9553]="*Gatiṃ na nāsento samparāyikaṃ;**Do not ruin your future rebirth.*";
P_HTM[9554]="*Hitesī anuyuñjassu,**You should seek what is beneficial,*";
P_HTM[9555]="*Kālenatthūpasaṃhitaṃ.**At the right time, what is connected with the goal.*";
P_HTM[9556]="*Cuditassa ca codakassa ca,**The statements of the accuser and the accused,*";
P_HTM[9557]="*Sahasā vohāraṃ mā padhāresi;**Do not consider them hastily:*";
P_HTM[9558]="*Codako āha āpannoti,**If the accuser says the accused has offended,*";
P_HTM[9559]="*Cuditako āha anāpannoti.**But the accused says he has not,*";
P_HTM[9560]="*Ubho anukkhipanto,**Then, both moving along,*";
P_HTM[9561]="*Paṭiññānusandhitena kāraye;**Should be dealt with in line with their admission.*";
P_HTM[9562]="*Paṭiññā lajjīsu katā,**The conscientious admit their faults,*";
P_HTM[9563]="*Alajjīsu evaṃ na vijjati;**But there is no such things among the shameless;*";
P_HTM[9564]="*Bahumpi alajjī bhāseyya,**For even if the shameless should speak a lot,*";
P_HTM[9565]="*Vattānusandhitena kāraye.**They should be dealt with in line with their conduct.’*";
P_HTM[9566]="*Alajjī kīdiso hoti,**What are the shameless like,*";
P_HTM[9567]="*Paṭiññā yassa na rūhati;**In that an admission is not effective?*";
P_HTM[9568]="*Etañca tāhaṃ pucchāmi,**I ask you this:*";
P_HTM[9569]="*Kīdiso vuccati alajjī puggalo.**What are they like, the people called shameless?*";
P_HTM[9570]="*Sañcicca āpattiṃ āpajjati,**‘They intentionally commit offenses,*";
P_HTM[9571]="*Āpattiṃ parigūhati;**Hide their offense,*";
P_HTM[9572]="*Agatigamanañca gacchati,**And go to a bad rebirth—*";
P_HTM[9573]="*Ediso vuccati alajjīpuggalo.**Such people are called shameless.’*";
P_HTM[9574]="*Saccaṃ ahampi jānāmi,**‘I too know the truth—*";
P_HTM[9575]="*Ediso vuccati alajjīpuggalo;**Such people are called shameless.*";
P_HTM[9576]="*Aññañca tāhaṃ pucchāmi,**And may I ask you something else:*";
P_HTM[9577]="*Kīdiso vuccati lajjīpuggalo.**What are they like, the people called conscientious?’*";
P_HTM[9578]="*Sañcicca āpattiṃ nāpajjati,**‘They do not intentionally commit offenses,*";
P_HTM[9579]="*Āpattiṃ na parigūhati;**Nor do they hide them,*";
P_HTM[9580]="*Agatigamanaṃ na gacchati,**And they do not go to a bad rebirth—*";
P_HTM[9581]="*Ediso vuccati lajjīpuggalo.**Such people are called conscientious.’*";
P_HTM[9582]="*Saccaṃ ahampi jānāmi,**‘I too know the truth—*";
P_HTM[9583]="*Ediso vuccati lajjīpuggalo;**Such people are called conscientious.*";
P_HTM[9584]="*Aññañca tāhaṃ pucchāmi,**And may I ask you something else:*";
P_HTM[9585]="*Kīdiso vuccati adhammacodako.**What are they like, those who accuse illegitimately?’*";
P_HTM[9586]="*Akālena codeti abhūtena,**‘They accuse at the wrong time, untruthfully,*";
P_HTM[9587]="*Pharusena anatthasaṃhitena;**Harshly, without benefit;*";
P_HTM[9588]="*Dosantaro codeti no mettācitto,**They accuse with a mind of ill will, not a mind of good will—*";
P_HTM[9589]="*Ediso vuccati adhammacodako.**Such a person is called one who accuses illegitimately.’*";
P_HTM[9590]="*Saccaṃ ahampi jānāmi,**‘I too know the truth—*";
P_HTM[9591]="*Ediso vuccati adhammacodako;**Such a person is called one who accuses illegitimately.*";
P_HTM[9592]="*Aññañca tāhaṃ pucchāmi,**And may I ask you something else:*";
P_HTM[9593]="*Kīdiso vuccati dhammacodako.**What are they like, those who accuse legitimately?’*";
P_HTM[9594]="*Kālena codeti bhūtena,**‘They accuse at the right time, truthfully,*";
P_HTM[9595]="*Saṇhena atthasaṃhitena;**Gently, beneficially;*";
P_HTM[9596]="*Mettācitto codeti no dosantaro,**They accuse with a mind of good will, not a mind of ill will—*";
P_HTM[9597]="*Ediso vuccati dhammacodako.**Such a person is called one who accuses legitimately.’*";
P_HTM[9598]="*Saccaṃ ahampi jānāmi,**‘I too know the truth—*";
P_HTM[9599]="*Ediso vuccati dhammacodako;**Such a person is called one who accuses legitimately.*";
P_HTM[9600]="*Aññañca tāhaṃ pucchāmi,**And may I ask you something else:*";
P_HTM[9601]="*Kīdiso vuccati bālacodako.**What are they like, the people called ignorant accusers?’*";
P_HTM[9602]="*Pubbāparaṃ na jānāti,**‘They do not know the sequence;*";
P_HTM[9603]="*Pubbāparassa akovido;**They are ignorant about it.*";
P_HTM[9604]="*Anusandhivacanapathaṃ na jānāti,**They do not know the sequence of statements;*";
P_HTM[9605]="*Anusandhivacanapathassa akovido;**They are ignorant about it—*";
P_HTM[9606]="*Ediso vuccati bālacodako.**Such people are called ignorant accusers.’*";
P_HTM[9607]="*Saccaṃ ahampi jānāmi,**‘I too know the truth—*";
P_HTM[9608]="*Ediso vuccati bālacodako;**Such people are called ignorant accusers.*";
P_HTM[9609]="*Aññañca tāhaṃ pucchāmi,**And may I ask you something else:*";
P_HTM[9610]="*Kīdiso vuccati paṇḍitacodako.**What are they like, the people called learned accusers?’*";
P_HTM[9611]="*Pubbāparampi jānāti,**‘They know the sequence;*";
P_HTM[9612]="*Pubbāparassa kovido;**They are knowledgeable about it.*";
P_HTM[9613]="*Anusandhivacanapathaṃ jānāti,**They know the sequence of statements;*";
P_HTM[9614]="*Anusandhivacanapathassa kovido;**They are knowledgeable about it—*";
P_HTM[9615]="*Ediso vuccati paṇḍitacodako.**Such people are called learned accusers.’*";
P_HTM[9616]="*Saccaṃ ahampi jānāmi,**‘I too know the truth—*";
P_HTM[9617]="*Ediso vuccati paṇḍitacodako;**Such people are called learned accusers.*";
P_HTM[9618]="*Aññañca tāhaṃ pucchāmi,**And may I ask you something else:*";
P_HTM[9619]="*Codanā kinti vuccati.**What is meant by accusing?’*";
P_HTM[9620]="*Sīlavipattiyā codeti,**‘One accuses because of failure in morality,*";
P_HTM[9621]="*atho ācāradiṭṭhiyā;**And for failure in conduct and view;*";
P_HTM[9622]="*Ājīvenapi codeti,**Also one accuses for failure in livelihood—*";
P_HTM[9623]="*codanā tena vuccatīti.**Because of this it is called accusing.’”*";
P_HTM[9624]="*Aparaṃ gāthāsaṅgaṇikaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**Another collection of verses is finished.*";
P_HTM[9625]="*124. 1. Anuvijjakaanuyoga **124.  1. Investigation *";
P_HTM[9626]="*Anuvijjakena codako pucchitabbo—**The investigator should ask the accuser:*";
P_HTM[9627]="*“yaṃ kho tvaṃ, āvuso, imaṃ bhikkhuṃ codesi, kimhi naṃ codesi, sīlavipattiyā vā codesi, ācāravipattiyā vā codesi, diṭṭhivipattiyā vā codesī”ti?**“Do you accuse this monk for failure in morality, failure in conduct, failure in view, or failure in livelihood?”*";
P_HTM[9628]="*So ce evaṃ vadeyya—**If he says,*";
P_HTM[9629]="*“sīlavipattiyā vā codemi, ācāravipattiyā vā codemi, diṭṭhivipattiyā vā codemī”ti, so evamassa vacanīyo—**“I am accusing him of failure in morality,” or “I am accusing him of failure in conduct,” or “I am accusing him of failure in view,” he should be asked,*";
P_HTM[9630]="*“jānāsi panāyasmā sīlavipattiṃ, jānāsi ācāravipattiṃ, jānāsi diṭṭhivipattin”ti?**“‘Do you know what failure in morality is?” “Do you know what failure in conduct is?” “Do you know what failure in view is?”*";
P_HTM[9631]="*So ce evaṃ vadeyya—**If he says,*";
P_HTM[9632]="*“jānāmi kho ahaṃ, āvuso, sīlavipattiṃ, jānāmi ācāravipattiṃ, jānāmi diṭṭhivipattin”ti, so evamassa vacanīyo—**“I do,” he should be asked what they are.*";
P_HTM[9633]="*“katamā panāvuso, sīlavipatti?* **";
P_HTM[9634]="*Katamā ācāravipatti?* **";
P_HTM[9635]="*Katamā diṭṭhivipattī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[9636]="*So ce evaṃ vadeyya—**If he says,*";
P_HTM[9637]="*“cattāri ca pārājikāni, terasa ca saṅghādisesā, ayaṃ sīlavipatti.**“The four offenses entailing expulsion and the thirteen entailing suspension are failure in morality,”*";
P_HTM[9638]="*Thullaccayaṃ, pācittiyaṃ, pāṭidesanīyaṃ, dukkaṭaṃ, dubbhāsitaṃ, ayaṃ ācāravipatti.**“The serious offenses, the offenses entailing confession, the offenses entailing acknowledgment, the offenses of wrong conduct, and the offenses of wrong speech are failure in conduct,”*";
P_HTM[9639]="*Micchādiṭṭhi, antaggāhikā diṭṭhi, ayaṃ diṭṭhivipattī”ti, so evamassa vacanīyo—**“Wrong views and side views are failure in view,” he should be asked,*";
P_HTM[9640]="*“yaṃ kho tvaṃ, āvuso, imaṃ bhikkhuṃ codesi, diṭṭhena vā codesi sutena vā codesi parisaṅkāya vā codesī”ti?**“Are you accusing this monk because of what you have seen, because of what you have heard, or because of suspicion?”*";
P_HTM[9641]="*So ce evaṃ vadeyya—**If he says,*";
P_HTM[9642]="*“diṭṭhena vā codemi sutena vā codemi parisaṅkāya vā codemī”ti, so evamassa vacanīyo—**“I’m accusing him because of what I have seen,” “I’m accusing him because of what I have heard,” “I’m accusing him because of suspicion,” he should be asked,*";
P_HTM[9643]="*“yaṃ kho tvaṃ, āvuso, imaṃ bhikkhuṃ diṭṭhena codesi, kiṃ te diṭṭhaṃ kinti te diṭṭhaṃ, kadā te diṭṭhaṃ, kattha te diṭṭhaṃ pārājikaṃ ajjhāpajjanto diṭṭho, saṅghādisesaṃ ajjhāpajjanto diṭṭho, thullaccayaṃ …**“Since you’re accusing this monk because of what you have seen, what have you seen? How did you see it? When did you see it? Where did you see it? Did you see him commit an offense entailing expulsion? Did you see him commit an offense entailing suspension? Did you see him commit a serious offense?*";
P_HTM[9644]="*pācittiyaṃ …**… an offense entailing confession?*";
P_HTM[9645]="*pāṭidesanīyaṃ …**… an offense entailing acknowledgment?*";
P_HTM[9646]="*dukkaṭaṃ …**… an offense of wrong conduct?*";
P_HTM[9647]="*dubbhāsitaṃ ajjhāpajjanto diṭṭho, kattha ca tvaṃ ahosi, kattha cāyaṃ bhikkhu ahosi, kiñca tvaṃ karosi, kiṃ cāyaṃ bhikkhu karotī”ti?**… an offense of wrong speech? Where were you? Where was this monk? What were you doing? What was this monk doing?”*";
P_HTM[9648]="*So ce evaṃ vadeyya—**If he says,*";
P_HTM[9649]="*“na kho ahaṃ, āvuso, imaṃ bhikkhuṃ diṭṭhena codemi, api ca sutena codemī”ti, so evamassa vacanīyo—**“I didn’t accuse this monk because of what I have seen, but because of what I have heard,” he should be asked,*";
P_HTM[9650]="*“yaṃ kho tvaṃ, āvuso, imaṃ bhikkhuṃ sutena codesi, kiṃ te sutaṃ, kinti te sutaṃ, kadā te sutaṃ, kattha te sutaṃ, pārājikaṃ ajjhāpannoti sutaṃ, saṅghādisesaṃ …**“Since you’re accusing this monk because of what you have heard, what have you heard? How did you hear it? When did you hear it? Where did you hear it? Did you hear that he has committed an offense entailing expulsion? Did you hear that he has committed an offense entailing suspension?*";
P_HTM[9651]="*thullaccayaṃ …**… a serious offense?*";
P_HTM[9652]="*pācittiyaṃ …**… an offense entailing confession?*";
P_HTM[9653]="*pāṭidesanīyaṃ …**… an offense entailing acknowledgment?*";
P_HTM[9654]="*dukkaṭaṃ …**… an offense of wrong conduct?*";
P_HTM[9655]="*dubbhāsitaṃ ajjhāpannoti sutaṃ, bhikkhussa sutaṃ, bhikkhuniyā sutaṃ, sikkhamānāya sutaṃ, sāmaṇerassa sutaṃ, sāmaṇeriyā sutaṃ, upāsakassa sutaṃ, upāsikāya sutaṃ, rājūnaṃ sutaṃ, rājamahāmattānaṃ sutaṃ, titthiyānaṃ sutaṃ, titthiyasāvakānaṃ sutan”ti?**Did you hear that he has committed an offense of wrong speech? Did you hear it from a monk? Did you hear it from a nun? Did you hear it from a trainee nun? Did you hear it from a novice monk? Did you hear it from a novice nun? Did you hear it from a male lay follower? Did you hear it from a female lay follower? Did you hear it from kings? Did you hear it from a king’s officials? Did you hear it from the monastics of another religion? Did you hear it from the lay followers of another religion?”*";
P_HTM[9656]="*So ce evaṃ vadeyya—**If he says,*";
P_HTM[9657]="*“na kho ahaṃ, āvuso, imaṃ bhikkhuṃ sutena codemi, api ca parisaṅkāya codemī”ti, so evamassa vacanīyo—**If he says, “I didn’t accuse this monk because of what I have heard, but because of suspicion,” he should be asked,*";
P_HTM[9658]="*“yaṃ kho tvaṃ, āvuso, imaṃ bhikkhuṃ parisaṅkāya codesi, kiṃ parisaṅkasi, kinti parisaṅkasi, kadā parisaṅkasi, kattha parisaṅkasi, pārājikaṃ ajjhāpannoti parisaṅkasi, saṅghādisesaṃ ajjhāpannoti parisaṅkasi, thullaccayaṃ …**“Since you’re accusing this monk because of suspicion, what do you suspect? How do you suspect it? When did you suspect it? Where did you suspect it? Do you suspect that he has committed an offense entailing expulsion? Do you suspect that he has committed an offense entailing suspension? Do you suspect that he has committed a serious offense?*";
P_HTM[9659]="*pācittiyaṃ …**… an offense entailing confession?*";
P_HTM[9660]="*pāṭidesanīyaṃ …**… an offense entailing acknowledgment?*";
P_HTM[9661]="*dukkaṭaṃ …**… an offense of wrong conduct?*";
P_HTM[9662]="*dubbhāsitaṃ ajjhāpannoti parisaṅkasi, bhikkhussa sutvā parisaṅkasi, bhikkhuniyā sutvā parisaṅkasi, sikkhamānāya sutvā parisaṅkasi, sāmaṇerassa sutvā parisaṅkasi, sāmaṇeriyā sutvā parisaṅkasi, upāsakassa sutvā parisaṅkasi, upāsikāya sutvā parisaṅkasi, rājūnaṃ sutvā parisaṅkasi, rājamahāmattānaṃ sutvā parisaṅkasi, titthiyānaṃ sutvā parisaṅkasi, titthiyasāvakānaṃ sutvā parisaṅkasī”ti?**Do you suspect that he has committed an offense of wrong speech? Do you suspect it after hearing about it from a monk? Do you suspect it after hearing about it from a nun? Do you suspect it after hearing about it from a trainee nun? Do you suspect it after hearing about it from a novice monk? Do you suspect it after hearing about it from a novice nun? Do you suspect it after hearing about it from a male lay follower? Do you suspect it after hearing about it from a female lay follower? Do you suspect it after hearing about it from kings? Do you suspect it after hearing about it from a king’s officials? Do you suspect it after hearing about it from the monastics of another religion? Do you suspect it after hearing about it from the lay followers of another religion?”*";
P_HTM[9663]="*Diṭṭhaṃ diṭṭhena sameti,**If what he saw agrees with what he says he saw,*";
P_HTM[9664]="*diṭṭhena saṃsandate diṭṭhaṃ;**If they correspond with each other,*";
P_HTM[9665]="*Diṭṭhaṃ paṭicca na upeti,**But what was seen is not adequate to prove the accusation,*";
P_HTM[9666]="*asuddhaparisaṅkito;**Then the one suspecting impurity*";
P_HTM[9667]="*So puggalo paṭiññāya,**Should admit it,*";
P_HTM[9668]="*kātabbo tenuposatho.**And they should then do the observance-day procedure with him.*";
P_HTM[9669]="*Sutaṃ sutena sameti,**If what he heard agrees with what he says he heard,*";
P_HTM[9670]="*sutena saṃsandate sutaṃ;**If they correspond with each other,*";
P_HTM[9671]="*Sutaṃ paṭicca na upeti,**But what was heard is not adequate to prove the accusation,*";
P_HTM[9672]="*asuddhaparisaṅkito;**Then the one suspecting impurity*";
P_HTM[9673]="*So puggalo paṭiññāya,**Should admit it,*";
P_HTM[9674]="*kātabbo tenuposatho.**And they should then do the observance-day procedure with him.*";
P_HTM[9675]="*Mutaṃ mutena sameti,**If what he sensed agrees with what he says he sensed,*";
P_HTM[9676]="*mutena saṃsandate mutaṃ;**If they correspond with each other,*";
P_HTM[9677]="*Mutaṃ paṭicca na upeti,**But what was sensed is not adequate to prove the accusation,*";
P_HTM[9678]="*asuddhaparisaṅkito;**Then the one suspecting impurity*";
P_HTM[9679]="*So puggalo paṭiññāya,**Should admit it,*";
P_HTM[9680]="*kātabbo tenuposatho.**And they should then do the observance-day procedure with him.*";
P_HTM[9681]="*Codanāya ko ādi, kiṃ majjhe, kiṃ pariyosānaṃ?**What is the beginning, the middle, and the end of an accusation?*";
P_HTM[9682]="*Codanāya okāsakammaṃ ādi, kiriyā majjhe, samatho pariyosānaṃ.**Getting permission is the beginning of an accusation, doing it is the middle, settling it is the end.*";
P_HTM[9683]="*Codanāya kati mūlāni, kati vatthūni, kati bhūmiyo, katihākārehi codeti?**How many roots does accusing have, how many bases, and how many grounds? And in how many ways does one accuse?*";
P_HTM[9684]="*Codanāya dve mūlāni, tīṇi vatthūni, pañca bhūmiyo, dvīhākārehi codeti.**It has two roots, three bases, and five grounds. And one accuses in two ways.*";
P_HTM[9685]="*Codanāya katamāni dve mūlāni?**What are the two roots?*";
P_HTM[9686]="*Samūlikā vā amūlikā vā—**With a root and without a root.*";
P_HTM[9687]="*codanāya imāni dve mūlāni.* **";
P_HTM[9688]="*Codanāya katamāni tīṇi vatthūni?**What are the three bases?*";
P_HTM[9689]="*Diṭṭhena sutena parisaṅkāya—**The seen, the heard, and the suspected.*";
P_HTM[9690]="*codanāya imāni tīṇi vatthūni.* **";
P_HTM[9691]="*Codanāya katamā pañca bhūmiyo?**What are the five grounds?*";
P_HTM[9692]="*Kālena vakkhāmi no akālena, bhūtena vakkhāmi no abhūtena, saṇhena vakkhāmi no pharusena, atthasaṃhitena vakkhāmi no anatthasaṃhitena, mettācitto vakkhāmi no dosantaroti—**“I’ll speak at an appropriate time, not at an inappropriate one; I’ll speak the truth, not falsehood; I’ll speak gently, not harshly; I’ll speak what’s beneficial, not what’s unbeneficial; I’ll speak with a mind of good will, not with ill will.”*";
P_HTM[9693]="*codanāya imā pañca bhūmiyo.* **";
P_HTM[9694]="*Katamehi dvīhākārehi codeti?**What are the two ways of accusing?*";
P_HTM[9695]="*Kāyena vā codeti vācāya vā codeti—**One accuses by body or by speech.*";
P_HTM[9696]="*imehi dvīhākārehi codeti.* **";
P_HTM[9697]="*2. Codakādipaṭipatti**2. The actions of an accuser, etc.*";
P_HTM[9698]="*Codakena kathaṃ paṭipajjitabbaṃ?**How should the accuser act?*";
P_HTM[9699]="*Cuditakena kathaṃ paṭipajjitabbaṃ?**How should the accused act?*";
P_HTM[9700]="*Saṅghena kathaṃ paṭipajjitabbaṃ?**How should the Sangha act?*";
P_HTM[9701]="*Anuvijjakena kathaṃ paṭipajjitabbaṃ?**How should the investigator act?*";
P_HTM[9702]="*Codakena kathaṃ paṭipajjitabbanti?**“How should the accuser act?”*";
P_HTM[9703]="*Codakena pañcasu dhammesu patiṭṭhāya paro codetabbo.**The accuser should set up five qualities before accusing another:*";
P_HTM[9704]="*Kālena vakkhāmi no akālena, bhūtena vakkhāmi no abhūtena, saṇhena vakkhāmi no pharusena, atthasaṃhitena vakkhāmi no anatthasaṃhitena, mettācitto vakkhāmi no dosantaroti—**“I’ll speak at an appropriate time, not at an inappropriate one; I’ll speak the truth, not falsehood; I’ll speak gently, not harshly; I’ll speak what’s beneficial, not what’s unbeneficial; I’ll speak with a mind of good will, not with ill will.”*";
P_HTM[9705]="*codakena evaṃ paṭipajjitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9706]="*Cuditakena kathaṃ paṭipajjitabbanti?**“How should the accused act?”*";
P_HTM[9707]="*Cuditakena dvīsu dhammesu paṭipajjitabbaṃ.**The accused should set up two qualities:*";
P_HTM[9708]="*Sacce ca akuppe ca—**truth and composure.*";
P_HTM[9709]="*cuditakena evaṃ paṭipajjitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9710]="*Saṅghena kathaṃ paṭipajjitabbanti?**“How should the Sangha act?”*";
P_HTM[9711]="*Saṅghena otiṇṇānotiṇṇaṃ jānitabbaṃ.**The Sangha should know what has been brought before it and what is not.*";
P_HTM[9712]="*Saṅghena evaṃ paṭipajjitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9713]="*Anuvijjakena kathaṃ paṭipajjitabbanti?**“How should the investigator act?”*";
P_HTM[9714]="*Anuvijjakena yena dhammena yena vinayena yena satthusāsanena taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasammati tathā taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametabbaṃ.**The investigator resolves that legal issue in accordance with the Teaching, the Monastic Law, and the Teacher’s instruction.*";
P_HTM[9715]="*Anuvijjakena evaṃ paṭipajjitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9716]="*Uposatho kimatthāya,**What is the purpose of the observance-day procedure?*";
P_HTM[9717]="*Pavāraṇā kissa kāraṇā;**Why is there an invitation-day procedure?*";
P_HTM[9718]="*Parivāso kimatthāya,**What is the purpose of probation?*";
P_HTM[9719]="*Mūlāyapaṭikassanā kissa kāraṇā;**Why is there a sending back to the beginning?*";
P_HTM[9720]="*Mānattaṃ kimatthāya,**What is the purpose of the trial period?*";
P_HTM[9721]="*Abbhānaṃ kissa kāraṇā.**Why is there rehabilitation?*";
P_HTM[9722]="*Uposatho sāmaggatthāya,**The purpose of the observance-day procedure is unity.*";
P_HTM[9723]="*Visuddhatthāya pavāraṇā;**The purpose of the invitation-day procedure is purity.*";
P_HTM[9724]="*Parivāso mānattatthāya,**The purpose of probation is purity is the trial period.*";
P_HTM[9725]="*Mūlāyapaṭikassanā niggahatthāya;**The purpose of sending back to the beginning is restraint.*";
P_HTM[9726]="*Mānattaṃ abbhānatthāya,**The purpose of the trial period is rehabilitation.*";
P_HTM[9727]="*Visuddhatthāya abbhānaṃ.**The purpose of rehabilitation is purity.*";
P_HTM[9728]="*Chandā dosā bhayā mohā,**If, because of desire, ill will, fear or confusion,*";
P_HTM[9729]="*there ca paribhāsati;**A senior monk reviles someone,*";
P_HTM[9730]="*Kāyassa bhedā duppañño,**Then, when the body breaks up, that foolish person,*";
P_HTM[9731]="*khato upahatindriyo;**Damaged, with impaired faculties,*";
P_HTM[9732]="*Nirayaṃ gacchati dummedho,**Being stupid, goes to hell,*";
P_HTM[9733]="*na ca sikkhāya gāravo.**Not respecting the training.*";
P_HTM[9734]="*Na ca āmisaṃ nissāya,**But not depending worldly gain,*";
P_HTM[9735]="*na ca nissāya puggalaṃ;**Not depending on individual people,*";
P_HTM[9736]="*Ubho ete vivajjetvā,**Giving up both of these,*";
P_HTM[9737]="*yathādhammo tathā kare.**One should act according to the Teaching.*";
P_HTM[9738]="*3. Codakassaattajhāpana**3. The accuser burning himself*";
P_HTM[9739]="*Kodhano upanāhī ca,**“Angry and resentful,*";
P_HTM[9740]="*Caṇḍo ca paribhāsako;**Fierce and reviling,*";
P_HTM[9741]="*Anāpattiyā āpattīti ropeti,**He charges someone innocent with an offense—*";
P_HTM[9742]="*Tādiso codako jhāpeti attānaṃ.**Such an accuser burns himself.*";
P_HTM[9743]="*Upakaṇṇakaṃ jappati jimhaṃ pekkhati,**Whispering in the ear, looking for flaws,*";
P_HTM[9744]="*Vītiharati kummaggaṃ paṭisevati;**Reciprocating, following the wrong path,*";
P_HTM[9745]="*Anāpattiyā āpattīti ropeti,**He charges someone innocent with an offense—*";
P_HTM[9746]="*Tādiso codako jhāpeti attānaṃ.**Such an accuser burns himself.*";
P_HTM[9747]="*Akālena codeti abhūtena,**Accusing at the wrong time, untruthfully,*";
P_HTM[9748]="*Pharusena anatthasaṃhitena;**Harshly, without benefit,*";
P_HTM[9749]="*Dosantaro codeti no mettācitto,**With a mind of ill will, not a mind of good will,*";
P_HTM[9750]="*Anāpattiyā āpattīti ropeti;**He charges someone innocent with an offense—*";
P_HTM[9751]="*Tādiso codako jhāpeti attānaṃ.**Such an accuser burns himself.*";
P_HTM[9752]="*Dhammādhammaṃ na jānāti,**Not knowing the Teaching or what is contrary to the Teaching,*";
P_HTM[9753]="*Dhammādhammassa akovido;**Ignorant about both,*";
P_HTM[9754]="*Anāpattiyā āpattīti ropeti,**He charges someone innocent with an offense—*";
P_HTM[9755]="*Tādiso codako jhāpeti attānaṃ.**Such an accuser burns himself.*";
P_HTM[9756]="*Vinayāvinayaṃ na jānāti,**Not knowing the Monastic Law or what is contrary to the Monastic Law,*";
P_HTM[9757]="*Vinayāvinayassa akovido;**Ignorant about both,*";
P_HTM[9758]="*Anāpattiyā āpattīti ropeti,**He charges someone innocent with an offense—*";
P_HTM[9759]="*Tādiso codako jhāpeti attānaṃ.**Such an accuser burns himself.*";
P_HTM[9760]="*Bhāsitābhāsitaṃ na jānāti,**Not knowing what was spoken or what was not spoken,*";
P_HTM[9761]="*Bhāsitābhāsitassa akovido;**Ignorant about both,*";
P_HTM[9762]="*Anāpattiyā āpattīti ropeti,**He charges someone innocent with an offense—*";
P_HTM[9763]="*Tādiso codako jhāpeti attānaṃ.**Such an accuser burns himself.*";
P_HTM[9764]="*Āciṇṇānāciṇṇaṃ na jānāti,**Not knowing what was practiced or what was not practiced,*";
P_HTM[9765]="*Āciṇṇānāciṇṇassa akovido;**Ignorant about both,*";
P_HTM[9766]="*Anāpattiyā āpattīti ropeti,**He charges someone innocent with an offense—*";
P_HTM[9767]="*Tādiso codako jhāpeti attānaṃ.**Such an accuser burns himself.*";
P_HTM[9768]="*Paññattāpaññattaṃ na jānāti,**Not knowing what was laid down or what was not laid down,*";
P_HTM[9769]="*Paññattāpaññattassa akovido;**Ignorant about both,*";
P_HTM[9770]="*Anāpattiyā āpattīti ropeti,**He charges someone innocent with an offense—*";
P_HTM[9771]="*Tādiso codako jhāpeti attānaṃ.**Such an accuser burns himself.*";
P_HTM[9772]="*Āpattānāpattiṃ na jānāti,**Not knowing the offenses or the non-offenses,*";
P_HTM[9773]="*Āpattānāpattiyā akovido;**Ignorant about both,*";
P_HTM[9774]="*Anāpattiyā āpattīti ropeti,**He charges someone innocent with an offense—*";
P_HTM[9775]="*Tādiso codako jhāpeti attānaṃ.**Such an accuser burns himself.*";
P_HTM[9776]="*Lahukagarukaṃ na jānāti,**Not knowing light offenses or heavy offenses,*";
P_HTM[9777]="*Lahukagarukassa akovido;**Ignorant about both,*";
P_HTM[9778]="*Anāpattiyā āpattīti ropeti,**He charges someone innocent with an offense—*";
P_HTM[9779]="*Tādiso codako jhāpeti attānaṃ.**Such an accuser burns himself.*";
P_HTM[9780]="*Sāvasesānavasesaṃ na jānāti,**Not knowing curable offenses or incurable offenses,*";
P_HTM[9781]="*Sāvasesānavasesassa akovido;**Ignorant about both,*";
P_HTM[9782]="*Anāpattiyā āpattīti ropeti,**He charges someone innocent with an offense—*";
P_HTM[9783]="*Tādiso codako jhāpeti attānaṃ.**Such an accuser burns himself.*";
P_HTM[9784]="*Duṭṭhullāduṭṭhullaṃ na jānāti,**Not knowing grave offenses or minor offenses,*";
P_HTM[9785]="*Duṭṭhullāduṭṭhullassa akovido;**Ignorant about both,*";
P_HTM[9786]="*Anāpattiyā āpattīti ropeti,**He charges someone innocent with an offense—*";
P_HTM[9787]="*Tādiso codako jhāpeti attānaṃ.**Such an accuser burns himself.*";
P_HTM[9788]="*Pubbāparaṃ na jānāti,**Not knowing what comes before or what comes afterwards,*";
P_HTM[9789]="*Pubbāparassa akovido;**Ignorant about both,*";
P_HTM[9790]="*Anāpattiyā āpattīti ropeti,**He charges someone innocent with an offense—*";
P_HTM[9791]="*Tādiso codako jhāpeti attānaṃ.**Such an accuser burns himself.*";
P_HTM[9792]="*Anusandhivacanapathaṃ na jānāti,**Not knowing the sequence of statements,*";
P_HTM[9793]="*Anusandhivacanapathassa akovido;**Ignorant about it,*";
P_HTM[9794]="*Anāpattiyā āpattīti ropeti,**He charges someone innocent with an offense—*";
P_HTM[9795]="*Tādiso codako jhāpeti attānanti.**Such an accuser burns himself.”*";
P_HTM[9796]="*Codanākaṇḍaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The chapter on accusing is finished.*";
P_HTM[9797]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[9798]="*Codanā anuvijjā ca,**“Accusing, and investigating,*";
P_HTM[9799]="*ādi mūlenuposatho;**Beginning, at root, observance day,*";
P_HTM[9800]="*Gati codanakaṇḍamhi,**Destiny. In the chapter on accusing,*";
P_HTM[9801]="*sāsanaṃ patiṭṭhāpayanti.**The instruction is placed.”*";
P_HTM[9802]="*124. 1. Anuvijjakassapaṭipatti **124.  1. The procedure for an investigator *";
P_HTM[9803]="*Saṅgāmāvacarena bhikkhunā saṅghaṃ upasaṅkamantena:**When a monk who is involved in a conflict is about to approach the Sangha, he should:*";
P_HTM[9804]="*nīcacittena saṅgho upasaṅkamitabbo;**be humble;*";
P_HTM[9805]="*rajoharaṇasamena cittena;**be intent on removing defilements;*";
P_HTM[9806]="*āsanakusalena bhavitabbaṃ nisajjakusalena; there bhikkhū anupakhajjantena, nave bhikkhū āsanena appaṭibāhantena, yathāpatirūpe āsane nisīditabbaṃ;**be skilled in appropriate seats and where to sit down, taking a seat without encroaching on the senior monks and without blocking the junior monks;*";
P_HTM[9807]="*anānākathikena bhavitabbaṃ atiracchānakathikena; sāmaṃ vā dhammo bhāsitabbo paro vā ajjhesitabbo ariyo vā tuṇhībhāvo nātimaññitabbo.**not ramble or talk pointlessly, but speak according to the Teaching or invite others to speak or value noble silence.*";
P_HTM[9808]="*Saṅghena anumatena puggalena anuvijjakena anuvijjitukāmena na upajjhāyo pucchitabbo, na ācariyo pucchitabbo, na saddhivihāriko pucchitabbo, na antevāsiko pucchitabbo, na samānupajjhāyako pucchitabbo, na samānācariyako pucchitabbo, na jāti pucchitabbā, na nāmaṃ pucchitabbaṃ, na gottaṃ pucchitabbaṃ, na āgamo pucchitabbo, na kulapadeso pucchitabbo, na jātibhūmi pucchitabbā.**An investigator—who has been approved by the Sangha and who wishes to investigate—should not ask about preceptor, teacher, student, pupil, co-student, co-pupil, caste, name, family, reciter tradition, home address, or nationality.*";
P_HTM[9809]="*Taṃ kiṃ kāraṇā?**What is the reason for that?*";
P_HTM[9810]="*Atrassa pemaṃ vā doso vā.**“In these cases there would be affection or ill will.*";
P_HTM[9811]="*Peme vā sati dose vā, chandāpi gaccheyya, dosāpi gaccheyya, mohāpi gaccheyya, bhayāpi gaccheyya.**When there is affection or ill will, one might be swayed by favoritism, ill will, confusion, or fear.*";
P_HTM[9812]="*Saṅghena anumatena puggalena anuvijjakena anuvijjitukāmena saṅghagarukena bhavitabbaṃ no puggalagarukena, saddhammagarukena bhavitabbaṃ no āmisagarukena, atthavasikena bhavitabbaṃ no parisakappikena, kālena anuvijjitabbaṃ no akālena, bhūtena anuvijjitabbaṃ no abhūtena, saṇhena anuvijjitabbaṃ no pharusena, atthasaṃhitena anuvijjitabbaṃ no anatthasaṃhitena, mettācittena anuvijjitabbaṃ no dosantarena, na upakaṇṇakajappinā bhavitabbaṃ, na jimhaṃ pekkhitabbaṃ, na akkhi nikhaṇitabbaṃ, na bhamukaṃ ukkhipitabbaṃ, na sīsaṃ ukkhipitabbaṃ, na hatthavikāro kātabbo, na hatthamuddā dassetabbā.**An investigator—who has been approved by the Sangha and who wishes to investigate—should respect the Sangha, not individuals; should value the true Dhamma, not worldly things; should value the goal, not conformity with a gathering; should investigate at an appropriate time, not at an inappropriate one; should investigate truthfully, not falsely; should investigate gently, not harshly; should investigate beneficially, not unbeneficially; should investigate with a mind of good will, not with ill will; should not whisper in the ear; should not look for flaws; should not wink; should not raise an eyebrow; should not nod; should not signal with the hand; should not gesture with the hand.*";
P_HTM[9813]="*Āsanakusalena bhavitabbaṃ nisajjakusalena, yugamattaṃ pekkhantena atthaṃ anuvidhiyantena sake āsane nisīditabbaṃ, na ca āsanā vuṭṭhātabbaṃ, na vītihātabbaṃ, na kummaggo sevitabbo, na bāhāvikkhepakaṃ bhaṇitabbaṃ, aturitena bhavitabbaṃ asāhasikena, acaṇḍikatena bhavitabbaṃ vacanakkhamena, mettācittena bhavitabbaṃ hitānukampinā, kāruṇikena bhavitabbaṃ hitaparisakkinā, asamphappalāpinā bhavitabbaṃ pariyantabhāṇinā, averavasikena bhavitabbaṃ anasuruttena, attā pariggahetabbo, paro pariggahetabbo, codako pariggahetabbo, cuditako pariggahetabbo, adhammacodako pariggahetabbo, adhammacuditako pariggahetabbo, dhammacodako pariggahetabbo, dhammacuditako pariggahetabbo, vuttaṃ ahāpentena avuttaṃ apakāsentena otiṇṇāni padabyañjanāni sādhukaṃ pariggahetvā paro paṭipucchitvā yathā paṭiññāya kāretabbo, mando hāsetabbo, bhīrū assāsetabbo, caṇḍo nisedhetabbo, asuci vibhāvetabbo, ujumaddavena na chandāgatiṃ gantabbaṃ, na dosāgatiṃ gantabbaṃ, na mohāgatiṃ gantabbaṃ, na bhayāgatiṃ gantabbaṃ, majjhattena bhavitabbaṃ dhammesu ca puggalesu ca.**One should be skilled in appropriate seats and where to sit down. Looking a plow’s length in front, acting in line with one’s aim, one should sit down on one’s own seat. One should not get up from one’s seat, mangle the investigation, take a wrong path, gesticulate, proceed hastily with force, or speak fiercely without patience. One should have mind of loving kindness with compassion and empathy, and be concerned and work for the welfare of the parties involved. One should speak succinctly and to the point, without being angry or argumentative. He should assess himself, the others, the accuser, the accused, one who accuses illegitimately, one who is accused illegitimately, one who accuses legitimately, and one who is accused legitimately. Not mangling what has been said, nor proclaiming what has not been said, he should carefully scrutinize the sentences and words under consideration, question the others, and deal with them according to what they have admitted. He should gladden those who are confused, relax those who are frightened, restrain those who are fierce, and expose those who are impure. Being moral and gentle, one should not be swayed by favoritism, anger, confusion, or fear. One should be impartial in regard to the Teaching and the people involved.*";
P_HTM[9814]="*Evañca pana anuvijjako anuvijjamāno satthu ceva sāsanakaro hoti, viññūnañca sabrahmacārīnaṃ piyo ca hoti manāpo ca garu ca bhāvanīyo ca.**In this way an investigator is acting in accordance with the instruction of the Teacher. And they are dear, agreeable, respected, and esteemed by their discerning fellow monastics.*";
P_HTM[9815]="*Suttaṃ saṃsandanatthāya, opammaṃ nidassanatthāya, attho viññāpanatthāya, paṭipucchā ṭhapanatthāya, okāsakammaṃ codanatthāya, codanā sāraṇatthāya, sāraṇā savacanīyatthāya, savacanīyaṃ palibodhatthāya, palibodho vinicchayatthāya, vinicchayo santīraṇatthāya, santīraṇaṃ ṭhānāṭhānagamanatthāya, ṭhānāṭhānagamanaṃ dummaṅkūnaṃ puggalānaṃ niggahatthāya, pesalānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ sampaggahatthāya, saṅgho sampariggahasampaṭicchanatthāya, saṅghena anumatā puggalā paccekaṭṭhāyino avisaṃvādakaṭṭhāyino.**The Monastic Code is for the sake of direction, the similes for the sake of illustration, the goal is to be made known, and questioning is for sake of establishing. Asking for permission is for the sake of accusing, accusing for reminding, reminding for initiating a legal process, initiating a legal process for obstructing, obstructing for investigating, investigating for weighing up, weighing up for deciding what is and is not the case, and deciding what is and is not the case is for the sake of restraining bad people and to support the good monks. The Sangha has the purpose of examining and accepting the decision. The Sangha should appoint people who are leaders and who are trustworthy.*";
P_HTM[9816]="*Vinayo saṃvaratthāya, saṃvaro avippaṭisāratthāya, avippaṭisāro pāmujjatthāya, pāmujjaṃ pītatthāya, pīti passaddhatthāya, passaddhi sukhatthāya, sukhaṃ samādhatthāya, samādhi yathābhūtañāṇadassanatthāya, yathābhūtañāṇadassanaṃ nibbidatthāya, nibbidā virāgatthāya, virāgo vimuttatthāya, vimutti vimuttiñāṇadassanatthāya, vimuttiñāṇadassanaṃ anupādāparinibbānatthāya.**The Monastic Law is for the sake of restraint, restraint for non-regret, non-regret for joy, joy for rapture, rapture for tranquility, tranquility for bliss, bliss for stillness, stillness for seeing things according to reality, seeing things according to reality for repulsion, repulsion for dispassion, dispassion for liberation, liberation for knowledge and vision of liberation, and knowledge and vision of liberation is for the sake of extinguishment without grasping.*";
P_HTM[9817]="*Etadatthā kathā, etadatthā mantanā, etadatthā upanisā, etadatthaṃ sotāvadhānaṃ—**This is the purpose of discussion, this is the purpose of consultation, this is the purpose of vital conditions, this is the purpose of listening,*";
P_HTM[9818]="*yadidaṃ anupādācittassa vimokkhoti.**that is, the release of mind without grasping.”*";
P_HTM[9819]="*Anuyogavattaṃ nisāmaya,**“Consider carefully the proper procedure of examination,*";
P_HTM[9820]="*Kusalena buddhimatā kataṃ;**As formulated by the skilled Awakened One,*";
P_HTM[9821]="*Suvuttaṃ sikkhāpadānulomikaṃ,**Well-spoken in line with the training rules—*";
P_HTM[9822]="*Gatiṃ na nāsento samparāyikaṃ.**Do not ruin your future rebirth.*";
P_HTM[9823]="*Vatthuṃ vipattiṃ āpattiṃ,**Ignorant about basis, failure, and offense,*";
P_HTM[9824]="*Nidānaṃ ākāraakovido;**As well as source and ways;*";
P_HTM[9825]="*Pubbāparaṃ na jānāti,**Not knowing the sequence,*";
P_HTM[9826]="*Katākataṃ samena ca.**And the same with what has and has not been done.*";
P_HTM[9827]="*Kammañca adhikaraṇañca,**Ignorant about legal procedures and legal issues,*";
P_HTM[9828]="*samathe cāpi akovido;**As well as their settling.*";
P_HTM[9829]="*Ratto duṭṭho ca mūḷho ca,**Greedy, angry, and confused,*";
P_HTM[9830]="*bhayā mohā ca gacchati.**Swayed by fear and confusion,*";
P_HTM[9831]="*Na ca saññattikusalo,**Not skilled in persuasion,*";
P_HTM[9832]="*nijjhattiyā ca akovido;**Nor in making others understand;*";
P_HTM[9833]="*Laddhapakkho ahiriko,**A shameless one who has obtained a faction,*";
P_HTM[9834]="*kaṇhakammo anādaro;**Disrespectful and doing dark deeds—*";
P_HTM[9835]="*Sa ve tādisako bhikkhu,**A monk such as this*";
P_HTM[9836]="*appaṭikkhoti vuccati.**Should be deferred to.*";
P_HTM[9837]="*Vatthuṃ vipattiṃ āpattiṃ,**Understanding basis, failure, and offense,*";
P_HTM[9838]="*nidānaṃ ākārakovido;**As well as source and ways;*";
P_HTM[9839]="*Pubbāparañca jānāti,**Knowing the sequence,*";
P_HTM[9840]="*katākataṃ samena ca.**And the same with what has and has not been done.*";
P_HTM[9841]="*Kammañca adhikaraṇañca,**Understanding legal procedures and legal issues,*";
P_HTM[9842]="*samathe cāpi kovido;**As well as their settling.*";
P_HTM[9843]="*Aratto aduṭṭho amūḷho,**Not greedy, angry, or confused,*";
P_HTM[9844]="*bhayā mohā na gacchati.**Swayed neither by fear nor confusion,*";
P_HTM[9845]="*Saññattiyā ca kusalo,**Skilled in persuasion,*";
P_HTM[9846]="*nijjhattiyā ca kovido;**And in making others understand;*";
P_HTM[9847]="*Laddhapakkho hirimano,**A conscientious one who has obtained a faction,*";
P_HTM[9848]="*sukkakammo sagāravo;**Respectful and doing bright deeds—*";
P_HTM[9849]="*Sa ve tādisako bhikkhu,**A monk such as this*";
P_HTM[9850]="*sappaṭikkhoti vuccatīti.**Should be deferred to.”*";
P_HTM[9851]="*Cūḷasaṅgāmaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The shorter section on conflict is finished*";
P_HTM[9852]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[9853]="*Nīcacittena puccheyya,**“Humble, one may ask,*";
P_HTM[9854]="*garu saṅghe na puggale;**Respect for the Sangha, not individuals;*";
P_HTM[9855]="*Suttaṃ saṃsandanatthāya,**The Monastic Code is for the sake of direction,*";
P_HTM[9856]="*vinayānuggahena ca;**And with supporting the training—*";
P_HTM[9857]="*uddānaṃ cūḷasaṅgāme,**The summary of the shorter section,*";
P_HTM[9858]="*ekuddeso idaṃ katanti.**Made into one recitation.”*";
P_HTM[9859]="*124. 1. Voharantenajānitabbādi **124.  1. What is to be known by one who is speaking, etc. *";
P_HTM[9860]="*Saṅgāmāvacarena bhikkhunā saṅghe voharantena vatthu jānitabbaṃ, vipatti jānitabbā, āpatti jānitabbā, nidānaṃ jānitabbaṃ, ākāro jānitabbo, pubbāparaṃ jānitabbaṃ, katākataṃ jānitabbaṃ, kammaṃ jānitabbaṃ, adhikaraṇaṃ jānitabbaṃ, samatho jānitabbo, na chandāgati gantabbā, na dosāgati gantabbā, na mohāgati gantabbā, na bhayāgati gantabbā, saññāpanīye ṭhāne saññāpetabbaṃ, nijjhāpanīye ṭhāne nijjhāpetabbaṃ, pekkhanīye ṭhāne pekkhitabbaṃ, pasādanīye ṭhāne pasādetabbaṃ, “laddhapakkhomhī”ti parapakkho nāvajānitabbo, bahussutomhīti appassuto nāvajānitabbo, therataromhīti navakataro nāvajānitabbo, asampattaṃ na byāhātabbaṃ, sampattaṃ dhammato vinayato na parihāpetabbaṃ, yena dhammena yena vinayena yena satthusāsanena taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasammati, tathā taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametabbaṃ.**When a monk who is involved in a conflict is speaking in the Sangha, he should know the actions that are the bases for offenses, as well as the failures, the offenses, the origin stories, the attributes, the sequence, what has and has not been done, the legal procedures, the legal issues, and their settling. He should not be swayed by desire, ill will, confusion or fear. He should persuade when persuasion is appropriate, should make others understand when making understand is appropriate, should look on when looking on is appropriate, and should inspire when inspiration is appropriate. Thinking, “I have obtained a faction,” he should not despise the factions of others. Thinking, “I am learned,” he should not despise those who are ignorant. Thinking, “I am more senior,” he should not despise those who are junior. He should not speak about what has not been reached, and he should not, based on the Teaching and the Monastic Law, neglect what has been reached. He should resolve that legal issue in accordance with the Teaching, the Monastic Law, and the Teacher’s instruction.*";
P_HTM[9861]="*Vatthu jānitabbanti**“He should know the actions that are the bases for offenses”:*";
P_HTM[9862]="*aṭṭhapārājikānaṃ vatthu jānitabbaṃ, tevīsasaṅghādisesānaṃ vatthu jānitabbaṃ, dveaniyatānaṃ vatthu jānitabbaṃ, dvecattārīsanissaggiyānaṃ vatthu jānitabbaṃ, aṭṭhāsītisatapācittiyānaṃ vatthu jānitabbaṃ, dvādasapāṭidesanīyānaṃ vatthu jānitabbaṃ, dukkaṭānaṃ vatthu jānitabbaṃ, dubbhāsitānaṃ vatthu jānitabbaṃ.**he should know the actions that are the bases for the eight offenses entailing expulsion, for the twenty-three offenses entailing suspension, for the two undetermined offenses, for the forty-two offenses entailing relinquishment, for the one hundred and eighty-eight offenses entailing confession, for the twelve offenses entailing acknowledgment, for the offenses of wrong conduct, and for the offenses of wrong speech.*";
P_HTM[9863]="*Vipatti jānitabbāti**“He should know the failures”:*";
P_HTM[9864]="*sīlavipatti jānitabbā, ācāravipatti jānitabbā, diṭṭhivipatti jānitabbā, ājīvavipatti jānitabbā.**he should know failure in morality, failure in conduct, failure in view, and failure in livelihood.*";
P_HTM[9865]="*Āpatti jānitabbāti**“He should know the offenses”:*";
P_HTM[9866]="*pārājikāpatti jānitabbā, saṅghādisesāpatti jānitabbā, thullaccayāpatti jānitabbā, pācittiyāpatti jānitabbā, pāṭidesanīyāpatti jānitabbā, dukkaṭāpatti jānitabbā, dubbhāsitāpatti jānitabbā.**he should know the offenses entailing expulsion, the offenses entailing suspension, the serious offenses, the offenses entailing confession, the offenses entailing acknowledgement, the offenses of wrong conduct, and the offenses of wrong speech.*";
P_HTM[9867]="*Nidānaṃ jānitabbanti**“He should know the origin stories”:*";
P_HTM[9868]="*aṭṭhapārājikānaṃ nidānaṃ jānitabbaṃ, tevīsasaṅghādisesānaṃ nidānaṃ jānitabbaṃ, dveaniyatānaṃ nidānaṃ jānitabbaṃ, dvecattārīsanissaggiyānaṃ nidānaṃ jānitabbaṃ, aṭṭhāsītisatapācittiyānaṃ nidānaṃ jānitabbaṃ, dvādasapāṭidesanīyānaṃ nidānaṃ jānitabbaṃ, dukkaṭānaṃ nidānaṃ jānitabbaṃ, dubbhāsitānaṃ nidānaṃ jānitabbaṃ.**he should know the origin stories to the eight offenses entailing expulsion, to the twenty-three offenses entailing suspension, to the two undetermined offenses, to the forty-two offenses entailing relinquishment, to the one hundred and eighty-eight offenses entailing confession, to the twelve offenses entailing acknowledgment, to the offenses of wrong conduct, to the offenses of wrong speech.*";
P_HTM[9869]="*Ākāro jānitabboti**“He should know the attributes”:*";
P_HTM[9870]="*saṅgho ākārato jānitabbo, gaṇo ākārato jānitabbo, puggalo ākārato jānitabbo, codako ākārato jānitabbo, cuditako ākārato jānitabbo.**he should know the attributes of a Sangha, of a group, of an individual, of an accuser, of an accused.*";
P_HTM[9871]="*Saṅgho ākārato jānitabboti**“He should know the attributes of a Sangha”:*";
P_HTM[9872]="*paṭibalo nu kho ayaṃ saṅgho imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ dhammena vinayena satthusāsanena udāhu noti, evaṃ saṅgho ākārato jānitabbo.**“Is this Sangha capable of resolving this legal issue according to the Teaching, the Monastic law, and the Teacherʼs instruction, or is it not?”*";
P_HTM[9873]="*Gaṇo ākārato jānitabboti**“He should know the attributes of a group”:*";
P_HTM[9874]="*paṭibalo nu kho ayaṃ gaṇo imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ dhammena vinayena satthusāsanena udāhu noti, evaṃ gaṇo ākārato jānitabbo.**“Is this group capable of resolving this legal issue according to the Teaching, the Monastic law, and the Teacherʼs instruction, or is it not?”*";
P_HTM[9875]="*Puggalo ākārato jānitabboti**“He should know the attributes of an individual”:*";
P_HTM[9876]="*paṭibalo nu kho ayaṃ puggalo imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ dhammena vinayena satthusāsanena udāhu noti, evaṃ puggalo ākārato jānitabbo.**“Is this individual capable of resolving this legal issue according to the Teaching, the Monastic law, and the Teacherʼs instruction, or is he not?”*";
P_HTM[9877]="*Codako ākārato jānitabboti**“He should know the attributes of an accuser”:*";
P_HTM[9878]="*kacci nu kho ayamāyasmā pañcasu dhammesu patiṭṭhāya paraṃ codeti udāhu noti, evaṃ codako ākārato jānitabbo.**“Is this Venerable established in the five qualities before accusing another, or is he not?”*";
P_HTM[9879]="*Cuditako ākārato jānitabboti**“He should know the attributes of an accused”:*";
P_HTM[9880]="*kacci nu kho ayamāyasmā dvīsu dhammesu patiṭṭhito sacce ca akuppe ca udāhu noti, evaṃ cuditako ākārato jānitabbo.**“Is this Venerable established in the two qualities of truth and composure, or is he not?”*";
P_HTM[9881]="*Pubbāparaṃ jānitabbanti**“He should know the sequence”:*";
P_HTM[9882]="*kacci nu kho ayamāyasmā vatthuto vā vatthuṃ saṅkamati, vipattito vā vipattiṃ saṅkamati, āpattito vā āpattiṃ saṅkamati, avajānitvā vā paṭijānāti, paṭijānitvā vā avajānāti, aññena vā aññaṃ paṭicarati, udāhu noti, evaṃ pubbāparaṃ jānitabbaṃ.**“Does this Venerable move from one action that is the basis for an offense to another action, from one failure to another, from one offense to another? Does he assert things after denying them, deny things after asserting them, or evade the issue? Or does he not?”*";
P_HTM[9883]="*Katākataṃ jānitabbanti**“He should know what has and has not been done”:*";
P_HTM[9884]="*methunadhammo jānitabbo, methunadhammassa anulomaṃ jānitabbaṃ, methunadhammassa pubbabhāgo jānitabbo.**he should know sexual intercourse, he should know what amounts to sexual intercourse, he should know the preliminaries of sexual intercourse.*";
P_HTM[9885]="*Methunadhammo jānitabboti**“He should know sexual intercourse”:*";
P_HTM[9886]="*dvayaṃdvayasamāpatti jānitabbā.**he should know that which is done wherever there are couples.*";
P_HTM[9887]="*Methunadhammassa anulomaṃ jānitabbanti**“He should know what amounts to sexual intercourse”:*";
P_HTM[9888]="*bhikkhu attano mukhena parassa aṅgajātaṃ gaṇhāti.**a monk taking the genitals of another in his mouth.*";
P_HTM[9889]="*Methunadhammassa pubbabhāgo jānitabboti**“He should know the preliminaries of sexual intercourse”:*";
P_HTM[9890]="*vaṇṇāvaṇṇo, kāyasaṃsaggo, duṭṭhullavācā, attakāmapāricariyā, vacanamanuppadānaṃ.**the various colors of semen, physical contact, indecent speech, satisfying one’s own desires, and matchmaking.*";
P_HTM[9891]="*Kammaṃ jānitabbanti**“He should know the legal procedures”:*";
P_HTM[9892]="*soḷasakammāni jānitabbāni—**he should know the sixteen legal procedures:*";
P_HTM[9893]="*cattāri apalokanakammāni jānitabbāni, cattāri ñattikammāni jānitabbāni, cattāri ñattidutiyakammāni jānitabbāni, cattāri ñatticatutthakammāni jānitabbāni.**he should know the four kinds of legal procedures consisting of getting permission, the four kinds of legal procedures consisting of one motion, the four kinds of legal procedures consisting one motion and one announcement, and the four kinds of legal procedures consisting of one motion and three announcements.*";
P_HTM[9894]="*Adhikaraṇaṃ jānitabbanti**“He should know the legal issues”:*";
P_HTM[9895]="*cattāri adhikaraṇāni jānitabbāni—**he should know the four kinds of legal issues:*";
P_HTM[9896]="*vivādādhikaraṇaṃ jānitabbaṃ, anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ jānitabbaṃ, āpattādhikaraṇaṃ jānitabbaṃ, kiccādhikaraṇaṃ jānitabbaṃ.**he should know the legal issues arising from disputes, the legal issues arising from accusations, the legal issues arising from offenses, and the legal issues arising from business.*";
P_HTM[9897]="*Samatho jānitabboti**“He should know settling”:*";
P_HTM[9898]="*satta samathā jānitabbā—**he should know the seven principles of settling:*";
P_HTM[9899]="*sammukhāvinayo jānitabbo, sativinayo jānitabbo, amūḷhavinayo jānitabbo, paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ jānitabbaṃ, yebhuyyasikā jānitabbā, tassapāpiyasikā jānitabbā, tiṇavatthārako jānitabbo.**he should know resolution face-to-face, resolution through recollection, resolution because of past insanity, acting according to what has been admitted, majority decision, further penalty, and covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[9900]="*2. Agatiagantabba**2. Not to be swayed*";
P_HTM[9901]="*Na chandāgati gantabbāti**“He should not be swayed by desire”:*";
P_HTM[9902]="*chandāgatiṃ gacchanto kathaṃ chandāgatiṃ gacchati?**How is one swayed by desire?*";
P_HTM[9903]="*Idhekacco—“ayaṃ me upajjhāyo vā ācariyo vā saddhivihāriko vā antevāsiko vā samānupajjhāyako vā samānācariyako vā sandiṭṭho vā sambhatto vā ñātisālohito vā”ti, tassānukampāya tassānurakkhāya adhammaṃ dhammoti dīpeti, dhammaṃ adhammoti dīpeti, avinayaṃ vinayoti dīpeti, vinayaṃ avinayoti dīpeti, abhāsitaṃ alapitaṃ tathāgatena bhāsitaṃ lapitaṃ tathāgatenāti dīpeti, bhāsitaṃ lapitaṃ tathāgatena abhāsitaṃ alapitaṃ tathāgatenāti dīpeti, anāciṇṇaṃ tathāgatena āciṇṇaṃ tathāgatenāti dīpeti, āciṇṇaṃ tathāgatena anāciṇṇaṃ tathāgatenāti dīpeti, apaññattaṃ tathāgatena paññattaṃ tathāgatenāti dīpeti, paññattaṃ tathāgatena apaññattaṃ tathāgatenāti dīpeti, anāpattiṃ āpattīti dīpeti, āpattiṃ anāpattīti dīpeti, lahukaṃ āpattiṃ garukā āpattīti dīpeti, garukaṃ āpattiṃ lahukā āpattīti dīpeti, sāvasesaṃ āpattiṃ anavasesā āpattīti dīpeti, anavasesaṃ āpattiṃ sāvasesā āpattīti dīpeti, duṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ aduṭṭhullā āpattīti dīpeti, aduṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ duṭṭhullā āpattīti dīpeti.**It may be that someone thinks, “This is my preceptor, teacher, student, pupil, co-student, co-pupil, friend, companion, or relative.” To be compassionate toward and protect this person, he proclaims what is contrary to the Teaching as the Teaching and what is the Teaching as contrary to the Teaching. He proclaims what is contrary to the Monastic Law as the Monastic Law, and what is the Monastic Law as contrary to the Monastic Law. He proclaims what hasn’t been spoken by the Buddha as spoken by the Buddha, and what has been spoken by the Buddha as not spoken by the Buddha. He proclaims what was not practiced by the Buddha as practiced by the Buddha, and what was practiced by the Buddha as not practiced by the Buddha. He proclaims what was not laid down by the Buddha as laid down by the Buddha, and what was laid down by the Buddha as not laid down by the Buddha. He proclaims a non-offense as an offense, and an offense as a non-offense. He proclaims a light offense as heavy, and a heavy offense as light. He proclaims a curable offense as incurable, and an incurable offense as curable. He proclaims a grave offense as minor, and a minor offense as grave.*";
P_HTM[9904]="*Imehi aṭṭhārasahi vatthūhi chandāgatiṃ gacchanto bahujanāhitāya paṭipanno hoti bahujanāsukhāya bahuno janassa anatthāya ahitāya dukkhāya devamanussānaṃ.**If he is swayed by desire by way of these eighteen grounds, then his behaviour is unbeneficial and a cause of unhappiness for humanity; it is harmful, detrimental, and a cause of suffering for gods and humans.*";
P_HTM[9905]="*Imehi aṭṭhārasahi vatthūhi chandāgatiṃ gacchanto khataṃ upahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati, sāvajjo ca hoti sānuvajjo ca viññūnaṃ, bahuñca apuññaṃ pasavati.**If he is swayed by desire by way of these eighteen grounds, then he is damaged and impaired, blamed and criticized by sensible people, and makes much demerit.*";
P_HTM[9906]="*Chandāgatiṃ gacchanto evaṃ chandāgatiṃ gacchati.* **";
P_HTM[9907]="*Na dosāgati gantabbāti**“He should not be swayed by ill will”:*";
P_HTM[9908]="*dosāgatiṃ gacchanto kathaṃ dosāgatiṃ gacchati?**How is one swayed by ill will?*";
P_HTM[9909]="*Idhekacco anatthaṃ me acarīti āghātaṃ bandhati, anatthaṃ me caratīti āghātaṃ bandhati, anatthaṃ me carissatīti āghātaṃ bandhati, piyassa me manāpassa anatthaṃ acari … anatthaṃ carati … anatthaṃ carissatīti āghātaṃ bandhati, appiyassa me amanāpassa atthaṃ acari … atthaṃ carati … atthaṃ carissatīti āghātaṃ bandhati.**It may be that someone thinks, “They have harmed me,” and he gives rise to resentment. Or he thinks, “They are harming me,” and he gives rise to resentment. Or he thinks, “They will harm me,” and he gives rise to resentment. Or he thinks, “They have harmed someone who is dear to me” … “They are harming someone who is dear to me” … “They will harm someone who is dear to me” … “They have benefited someone I dislike” … “They are benefiting someone I dislike” … “They will benefit someone I dislike,” and he gives rise to resentment.*";
P_HTM[9910]="*Imehi navahi āghātavatthūhi āghāto paṭighāto kuddho kodhābhibhūto adhammaṃ dhammoti dīpeti, dhammaṃ adhammoti dīpeti …pe…**Because of these nine grounds for resentment, he is resentful, hostile, angry, and overcome by anger, and then proclaims what is contrary to the Teaching as the Teaching and what is the Teaching as contrary to the Teaching …*";
P_HTM[9911]="*duṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ aduṭṭhullā āpattīti dīpeti, aduṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ duṭṭhullā āpattīti dīpeti.**He proclaims a grave offense as minor, and a minor offense as grave.*";
P_HTM[9912]="*Imehi aṭṭhārasahi vatthūhi dosāgatiṃ gacchanto bahujanāhitāya paṭipanno hoti bahujanāsukhāya bahuno janassa anatthāya ahitāya dukkhāya devamanussānaṃ.**If he is swayed by ill will by way of these eighteen grounds, then his behaviour is unbeneficial and a cause of unhappiness for humanity; it is harmful, detrimental, and a cause of suffering for gods and humans.*";
P_HTM[9913]="*Imehi aṭṭhārasahi vatthūhi dosāgatiṃ gacchanto khataṃ upahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati, sāvajjo ca hoti sānuvajjo ca viññūnaṃ bahuñca apuññaṃ pasavati.**If he is swayed by ill will by way of these eighteen grounds, then he is damaged and impaired, blamed and criticized by sensible people, and makes much demerit.*";
P_HTM[9914]="*Dosāgatiṃ gacchanto evaṃ dosāgatiṃ gacchati.* **";
P_HTM[9915]="*Na mohāgati gantabbāti**“He should not be swayed by confusion”:*";
P_HTM[9916]="*mohāgatiṃ gacchanto kathaṃ mohāgatiṃ gacchati?**How is one swayed by confusion?*";
P_HTM[9917]="*Ratto rāgavasena gacchati, duṭṭho dosavasena gacchati, mūḷho mohavasena gacchati, parāmaṭṭho diṭṭhivasena gacchati, mūḷho sammūḷho mohābhibhūto adhammaṃ dhammoti dīpeti, dhammaṃ adhammoti dīpeti …pe…**Swayed by desire, ill will, or confusion, or grasping a view, he is confused, deluded, and overcome by confusion, and then proclaims what is contrary to the Teaching as the Teaching and what is the Teaching as contrary to the Teaching …*";
P_HTM[9918]="*duṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ aduṭṭhullā āpattīti dīpeti, aduṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ duṭṭhullā āpattīti dīpeti.**He proclaims a grave offense as minor, and a minor offense as grave.*";
P_HTM[9919]="*Imehi aṭṭhārasahi vatthūhi mohāgatiṃ gacchanto bahujanāhitāya paṭipanno hoti bahujanāsukhāya bahuno janassa anatthāya ahitāya dukkhāya devamanussānaṃ.**If he is swayed by confusion by way of these eighteen grounds, then his behaviour is unbeneficial and a cause of unhappiness for humanity; it is harmful, detrimental, and a cause of suffering for gods and humans.*";
P_HTM[9920]="*Imehi aṭṭhārasahi vatthūhi mohāgatiṃ gacchanto khataṃ upahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati, sāvajjo ca hoti sānuvajjo ca viññūnaṃ, bahuñca apuññaṃ pasavati.**If he is swayed by confusion by way of these eighteen grounds, then he is damaged and impaired, blamed and criticized by sensible people, and makes much demerit.*";
P_HTM[9921]="*Mohāgatiṃ gacchanto evaṃ mohāgatiṃ gacchati.* **";
P_HTM[9922]="*Na bhayāgati gantabbāti**“He should not be swayed by fear”:*";
P_HTM[9923]="*bhayāgatiṃ gacchanto kathaṃ bhayāgatiṃ gacchati?**How is one swayed by fear?*";
P_HTM[9924]="*Idhekacco—“ayaṃ visamanissito vā gahananissito vā balavanissito vā kakkhaḷo pharuso jīvitantarāyaṃ vā brahmacariyantarāyaṃ vā karissatī”ti, tassa bhayā bhīto adhammaṃ dhammoti dīpeti, dhammaṃ adhammoti dīpeti, avinayaṃ vinayoti dīpeti, vinayaṃ avinayoti dīpeti, abhāsitaṃ alapitaṃ tathāgatena bhāsitaṃ lapitaṃ tathāgatenāti dīpeti, bhāsitaṃ lapitaṃ tathāgatena abhāsitaṃ alapitaṃ tathāgatenāti dīpeti, anāciṇṇaṃ tathāgatena āciṇṇaṃ tathāgatenāti dīpeti, āciṇṇaṃ tathāgatena anāciṇṇaṃ tathāgatenāti dīpeti, apaññattaṃ tathāgatena paññattaṃ tathāgatenāti dīpeti, paññattaṃ tathāgatena apaññattaṃ tathāgatenāti dīpeti, anāpattiṃ āpattīti dīpeti, āpattiṃ anāpattīti dīpeti, lahukaṃ āpattiṃ garukā āpattīti dīpeti, garukaṃ āpattiṃ lahukā āpattīti dīpeti, sāvasesaṃ āpattiṃ anavasesā āpattīti dīpeti, anavasesaṃ āpattiṃ sāvasesā āpattīti dīpeti, duṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ aduṭṭhullā āpattīti dīpeti, aduṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ duṭṭhullā āpattīti dīpeti.**It may be that someone thinks, “This one relies on uneven ground, thick cover, and powerful individuals; he is cruel and harsh, and will be a danger to life or to living the spiritual life.” Fearful or frightened of him, he proclaims what is contrary to the Teaching as the Teaching and what is the Teaching as contrary to the Teaching. He proclaims what is contrary to the Monastic Law as the Monastic Law, and what is the Monastic Law as contrary to the Monastic Law. He proclaims what hasn’t been spoken by the Buddha as spoken by the Buddha, and what has been spoken by the Buddha as not spoken by the Buddha. He proclaims what was not practiced by the Buddha as practiced by the Buddha, and what was practiced by the Buddha as not practiced by the Buddha. He proclaims what was not laid down by the Buddha as laid down by the Buddha, and what was laid down by the Buddha as not laid down by the Buddha. He proclaims a non-offense as an offense, and an offense as a non-offense. He proclaims a light offense as heavy, and a heavy offense as light. He proclaims a curable offense as incurable, and an incurable offense as curable. He proclaims a grave offense as minor, and a minor offense as grave.*";
P_HTM[9925]="*Imehi aṭṭhārasahi vatthūhi bhayāgatiṃ gacchanto bahujanāhitāya paṭipanno hoti bahujanāsukhāya bahuno janassa anatthāya ahitāya dukkhāya devamanussānaṃ.**If he is swayed by fear by way of these eighteen grounds, then his behaviour is unbeneficial and a cause of unhappiness for humanity; it is harmful, detrimental, and a cause of suffering for gods and humans.*";
P_HTM[9926]="*Imehi aṭṭhārasahi vatthūhi bhayāgatiṃ gacchanto khataṃ upahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati, sāvajjo ca hoti, sānuvajjo ca viññūnaṃ, bahuñca apuññaṃ pasavati.**If he is swayed by fear by way of these eighteen grounds, then he is damaged and impaired, blamed and criticized by sensible people, and makes much demerit.*";
P_HTM[9927]="*Bhayāgatiṃ gacchanto evaṃ bhayāgatiṃ gacchati.* **";
P_HTM[9928]="*Chandā dosā bhayā mohā,**“If, because of desire, ill will, fear, or confusion,*";
P_HTM[9929]="*yo dhammaṃ ativattati;**He goes beyond the Teaching,*";
P_HTM[9930]="*Nihīyati tassa yaso,**Then his reputation is harmed,*";
P_HTM[9931]="*kāḷapakkheva candimāti.**Like the moon during the waning fortnight.”*";
P_HTM[9932]="*3. Agatiagamana**3. Not being swayed*";
P_HTM[9933]="*Kathaṃ na chandāgatiṃ gacchati?**How is one not swayed by desire?*";
P_HTM[9934]="*Adhammaṃ adhammoti dīpento na chandāgatiṃ gacchati, dhammaṃ dhammoti dīpento na chandāgatiṃ gacchati, avinayaṃ avinayoti dīpento na chandāgatiṃ gacchati, vinayaṃ vinayoti dīpento na chandāgatiṃ gacchati, abhāsitaṃ alapitaṃ tathāgatena abhāsitaṃ alapitaṃ tathāgatenāti dīpento na chandāgatiṃ gacchati, bhāsitaṃ lapitaṃ tathāgatena bhāsitaṃ lapitaṃ tathāgatenāti dīpento na chandāgatiṃ gacchati, anāciṇṇaṃ tathāgatena anāciṇṇaṃ tathāgatenāti dīpento na chandāgatiṃ gacchati, āciṇṇaṃ tathāgatena āciṇṇaṃ tathāgatenāti dīpento na chandāgatiṃ gacchati, apaññattaṃ tathāgatena apaññattaṃ tathāgatenāti dīpento na chandāgatiṃ gacchati, paññattaṃ tathāgatena paññattaṃ tathāgatenāti dīpento na chandāgatiṃ gacchati, anāpattiṃ anāpattīti dīpento na chandāgatiṃ gacchati, āpattiṃ āpattīti dīpento na chandāgatiṃ gacchati, lahukaṃ āpattiṃ lahukā āpattīti dīpento na chandāgatiṃ gacchati, garukaṃ āpattiṃ garukā āpattīti dīpento na chandāgatiṃ gacchati, sāvasesaṃ āpattiṃ sāvasesā āpattīti dīpento na chandāgatiṃ gacchati, anavasesaṃ āpattiṃ anavasesā āpattīti dīpento na chandāgatiṃ gacchati, duṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ duṭṭhullā āpattīti dīpento na chandāgatiṃ gacchati, aduṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ aduṭṭhullā āpattīti dīpento na chandāgatiṃ gacchati.**One is not swayed by desire if one proclaims what is contrary to the Teaching as contrary to the Teaching, and what the Teaching as the Teaching; if one proclaims what is contrary to the Monastic Law as contrary to the Monastic Law, and what is the Monastic Law as the Monastic Law; if one proclaims what hasn’t been spoken by the Buddha as not spoken by the Buddha, and what has been spoken by the Buddha as spoken by the Buddha; if one proclaims what was not practiced by the Buddha as not practiced by the Buddha, and what was practiced by the Buddha as practiced by the Buddha; if one proclaims what was not laid down by the Buddha as not laid down by the Buddha, and what was laid down by the Buddha as laid down by the Buddha; if one proclaims a non-offense as a non-offense, and an offense as an offense; if one proclaims a light offense as light, and a heavy offense as heavy; if one proclaims a curable offense as curable, and an incurable offense as incurable; if one proclaims a grave offense as grave, and a minor offense as minor.*";
P_HTM[9935]="*Evaṃ na chandāgatiṃ gacchati.* **";
P_HTM[9936]="*Kathaṃ na dosāgatiṃ gacchati?**How is one not swayed by ill will?*";
P_HTM[9937]="*Adhammaṃ adhammoti dīpento na dosāgatiṃ gacchati, dhammaṃ dhammoti dīpento na dosāgatiṃ gacchati …pe…**One is not swayed by ill will if one proclaims what is contrary to the Teaching as contrary to the Teaching, and what the Teaching as the Teaching …*";
P_HTM[9938]="*duṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ duṭṭhullā āpattīti dīpento na dosāgatiṃ gacchati, aduṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ aduṭṭhullā āpattīti dīpento na dosāgatiṃ gacchati.**if one proclaims a grave offense as grave, and a minor offense as minor.*";
P_HTM[9939]="*Evaṃ na dosāgatiṃ gacchati.* **";
P_HTM[9940]="*Kathaṃ na mohāgatiṃ gacchati?**How is one not swayed by confusion?*";
P_HTM[9941]="*Adhammaṃ adhammoti dīpento na mohāgatiṃ gacchati, dhammaṃ dhammoti dīpento na mohāgatiṃ gacchati …pe…**One is not swayed by confusion if one proclaims what is contrary to the Teaching as contrary to the Teaching, and what the Teaching as the Teaching …*";
P_HTM[9942]="*duṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ duṭṭhullā āpattīti dīpento na mohāgatiṃ gacchati, aduṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ aduṭṭhullā āpattīti dīpento na mohāgatiṃ gacchati.**if one proclaims a grave offense as grave, and a minor offense as minor.*";
P_HTM[9943]="*Evaṃ na mohāgatiṃ gacchati.* **";
P_HTM[9944]="*Kathaṃ na bhayāgatiṃ gacchati?**How is one not swayed by fear?*";
P_HTM[9945]="*Adhammaṃ adhammoti dīpento na bhayāgatiṃ gacchati, dhammaṃ dhammoti dīpento na bhayāgatiṃ gacchati, avinayaṃ avinayoti dīpento na bhayāgatiṃ gacchati, vinayaṃ vinayoti dīpento na bhayāgatiṃ gacchati, abhāsitaṃ alapitaṃ tathāgatena abhāsitaṃ alapitaṃ tathāgatenāti dīpento na bhayāgatiṃ gacchati, bhāsitaṃ lapitaṃ tathāgatena bhāsitaṃ lapitaṃ tathāgatenāti dīpento na bhayāgatiṃ gacchati, anāciṇṇaṃ tathāgatena anāciṇṇaṃ tathāgatenāti dīpento na bhayāgatiṃ gacchati, āciṇṇaṃ tathāgatena āciṇṇaṃ tathāgatenāti dīpento na bhayāgatiṃ gacchati, apaññattaṃ tathāgatena apaññattaṃ tathāgatenāti dīpento na bhayāgatiṃ gacchati, paññattaṃ tathāgatena paññattaṃ tathāgatenāti dīpento na bhayāgatiṃ gacchati, anāpattiṃ anāpattīti dīpento na bhayāgatiṃ gacchati, āpattiṃ āpattīti dīpento na bhayāgatiṃ gacchati, lahukaṃ āpattiṃ lahukā āpattīti dīpento na bhayāgatiṃ gacchati, garukaṃ āpattiṃ garukā āpattīti dīpento na bhayāgatiṃ gacchati, sāvasesaṃ āpattiṃ sāvasesā āpattīti dīpento na bhayāgatiṃ gacchati, anavasesaṃ āpattiṃ anavasesā āpattīti dīpento na bhayāgatiṃ gacchati, duṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ duṭṭhullā āpattīti dīpento na bhayāgatiṃ gacchati, aduṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ aduṭṭhullā āpattīti dīpento na bhayāgatiṃ gacchati.**One is not swayed by fear if one proclaims what is contrary to the Teaching as contrary to the Teaching, and what the Teaching as the Teaching; if one proclaims what is contrary to the Monastic Law as contrary to the Monastic Law, and what is the Monastic Law as the Monastic Law; if one proclaims what hasn’t been spoken by the Buddha as not spoken by the Buddha, and what has been spoken by the Buddha as spoken by the Buddha; if one proclaims what was not practiced by the Buddha as not practiced by the Buddha, and what was practiced by the Buddha as practiced by the Buddha; if one proclaims what was not laid down by the Buddha as not laid down by the Buddha, and what was laid down by the Buddha as laid down by the Buddha; if one proclaims a non-offense as a non-offense, and an offense as an offense; if one proclaims a light offense as light, and a heavy offense as heavy; if one proclaims a curable offense as curable, and an incurable offense as incurable; if one proclaims a grave offense as grave, and a minor offense as minor.*";
P_HTM[9946]="*Evaṃ na bhayāgatiṃ gacchati.* **";
P_HTM[9947]="*Chandā dosā bhayā mohā,**“If, because of desire, ill will, fear, or confusion,*";
P_HTM[9948]="*yo dhammaṃ nātivattati;**He does not go beyond the Teaching,*";
P_HTM[9949]="*Āpūrati tassa yaso,**Then his reputation grows,*";
P_HTM[9950]="*sukkapakkheva candimāti.**Like the moon during the waxing fortnight.”*";
P_HTM[9951]="*4. Saññāpanīyādi**4. To be persuaded, etc.*";
P_HTM[9952]="*Kathaṃ saññāpanīye ṭhāne saññāpeti?**How does one persuade when persuasion is appropriate?*";
P_HTM[9953]="*Adhammaṃ adhammoti dīpento saññāpanīye ṭhāne saññāpeti, dhammaṃ dhammoti dīpento saññāpanīye ṭhāne saññāpeti …pe…**Proclaiming what is contrary to the Teaching as contrary to the Teaching and what is the Teaching as the Teaching, he persuades others when persuasion is appropriate. …*";
P_HTM[9954]="*duṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ duṭṭhullā āpattīti dīpento saññāpanīye ṭhāne saññāpeti, aduṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ aduṭṭhullā āpattīti dīpento saññāpanīye ṭhāne saññāpeti.**Proclaiming a grave offense as grave and a minor offense as minor, he persuades others when persuasion is appropriate.*";
P_HTM[9955]="*Evaṃ saññāpanīye ṭhāne saññāpeti.* **";
P_HTM[9956]="*Kathaṃ nijjhāpanīye ṭhāne nijjhāpeti?**How does one make others understand when making understand is appropriate?*";
P_HTM[9957]="*Adhammaṃ adhammoti dīpento nijjhāpanīye ṭhāne nijjhāpeti, dhammaṃ dhammoti dīpento nijjhāpanīye ṭhāne nijjhāpeti …pe…**Proclaiming what is contrary to the Teaching as contrary to the Teaching and what is the Teaching as the Teaching, he makes others understand when making understand is appropriate. …*";
P_HTM[9958]="*duṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ duṭṭhullā āpattīti dīpento nijjhāpanīye ṭhāne nijjhāpeti, aduṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ aduṭṭhullā āpattīti dīpento nijjhāpanīye ṭhāne nijjhāpeti.**Proclaiming a grave offense as grave and a minor offense as minor, he makes others understand when making understand is appropriate.*";
P_HTM[9959]="*Evaṃ nijjhāpanīye ṭhāne nijjhāpeti.* **";
P_HTM[9960]="*Kathaṃ pekkhanīye ṭhāne pekkhati?**How does one look on when looking on is appropriate?*";
P_HTM[9961]="*Adhammaṃ adhammoti dīpento pekkhanīye ṭhāne pekkhati, dhammaṃ dhammoti dīpento pekkhanīye ṭhāne pekkhati …pe…**Proclaiming what is contrary to the Teaching as contrary to the Teaching and what is the Teaching as the Teaching, he looks on when looking on is appropriate. …*";
P_HTM[9962]="*duṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ duṭṭhullā āpattīti dīpento pekkhanīye ṭhāne pekkhati, aduṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ aduṭṭhullā āpattīti dīpento pekkhanīye ṭhāne pekkhati.**Proclaiming a grave offense as grave and a minor offense as minor, he looks on when looking on is appropriate.*";
P_HTM[9963]="*Evaṃ pekkhanīye ṭhāne pekkhati.* **";
P_HTM[9964]="*Kathaṃ pasādanīye ṭhāne pasādeti?**How does one inspire when inspiration is appropriate?*";
P_HTM[9965]="*Adhammaṃ adhammoti dīpento pasādanīye ṭhāne pasādeti, dhammaṃ dhammoti dīpento pasādanīye ṭhāne pasādeti …pe…**Proclaiming what is contrary to the Teaching as contrary to the Teaching and what is the Teaching as the Teaching, he inspires when inspiration is appropriate. …*";
P_HTM[9966]="*duṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ duṭṭhullā āpattīti dīpento pasādanīye ṭhāne pasādeti, aduṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ aduṭṭhullā āpattīti dīpento pasādanīye ṭhāne pasādeti.**Proclaiming a grave offense as grave and a minor offense as minor, he inspires when inspiration is appropriate.*";
P_HTM[9967]="*Evaṃ pasādanīye ṭhāne pasādeti.* **";
P_HTM[9968]="*5. Parapakkhādiavajānana**5. Despising the factions of others, etc.*";
P_HTM[9969]="*Kathaṃ laddhapakkhomhīti parapakkhaṃ avajānāti?**Thinking, “I have obtained a faction,” how does one despise the factions of others?*";
P_HTM[9970]="*Idhekacco laddhapakkho hoti laddhaparivāro pakkhavā ñātimā.**It may be that someone has obtained a faction, a group of followers, and has relatives.*";
P_HTM[9971]="*“Ayaṃ aladdhapakkho aladdhaparivāro na pakkhavā na ñātimā”ti tassa avajānanto adhammaṃ dhammoti dīpeti, dhammaṃ adhammoti dīpeti …pe…**He thinks, “This one does not have a faction or a group of followers, and does not have relatives,” and despising him, he proclaims what is contrary to the Teaching as the Teaching and what is the Teaching as contrary to the Teaching. …*";
P_HTM[9972]="*duṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ aduṭṭhullā āpattīti dīpeti, aduṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ duṭṭhullā āpattīti dīpeti.**He proclaims a grave offense as minor, and a minor offense as grave.*";
P_HTM[9973]="*Evaṃ laddhapakkhomhīti parapakkhaṃ avajānāti.* **";
P_HTM[9974]="*Kathaṃ bahussutomhīti appassutaṃ avajānāti?**Thinking, “I am learned,” how does one despise those who are ignorant?*";
P_HTM[9975]="*Idhekacco bahussuto hoti sutadharo sutasannicayo.**It may be that someone is learned, one who has retained and accumulated what he has learned.*";
P_HTM[9976]="*“Ayaṃ appassuto appāgamo appadharo”ti tassa avajānanto adhammaṃ dhammoti dīpeti, dhammaṃ adhammoti dīpeti …pe…**He thinks, “This one is ignorant; he has learned little and remembers little,” and despising him, he proclaims what is contrary to the Teaching as the Teaching and what is the Teaching as contrary to the Teaching. …*";
P_HTM[9977]="*duṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ aduṭṭhullā āpattīti dīpeti, aduṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ duṭṭhullā āpattīti dīpeti.**He proclaims a grave offense as minor, and a minor offense as grave.*";
P_HTM[9978]="*Evaṃ bahussutomhīti appassutaṃ avajānāti.* **";
P_HTM[9979]="*Kathaṃ therataromhīti navakataraṃ avajānāti?**Thinking, “I am more senior,” how does one despise those who are junior?*";
P_HTM[9980]="*Idhekacco thero hoti rattaññū cirapabbajito “ayaṃ navako appaññāto appakataññū imassa vacanaṃ akataṃ bhavissatī”ti tassa avajānanto adhammaṃ dhammoti dīpeti, dhammaṃ adhammoti dīpeti …pe…**It may be that someone is a senior monk of long standing. He thinks, “This is an unknown and ignorant junior monk; one should not do as he asks,” and despising him, he proclaims what is contrary to the Teaching as the Teaching and what is the Teaching as contrary to the Teaching. …*";
P_HTM[9981]="*duṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ aduṭṭhullā āpattīti dīpeti, aduṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ duṭṭhullā āpattīti dīpeti.**He proclaims a grave offense as minor, and a minor offense as grave.*";
P_HTM[9982]="*Evaṃ therataromhīti navakataraṃ avajānāti.* **";
P_HTM[9983]="*Asampattaṃ na byāharitabbanti**“He should not speak about what has not been reached”:*";
P_HTM[9984]="*anotiṇṇaṃ bhāraṃ na otāretabbaṃ.**he should not bring up an issue not under consideration.*";
P_HTM[9985]="*Sampattaṃ dhammato vinayato na parihāpetabbanti**“He should not, based on the Teaching and the Monastic Law, neglect what has been reached”:*";
P_HTM[9986]="*yaṃatthāya saṅgho sannipatito hoti, taṃ atthaṃ dhammato vinayato na parihāpetabbaṃ.**the purpose for which the Sangha has gathered should not be neglected based on the Teaching or the Monastic Law.*";
P_HTM[9987]="*Yena dhammenāti**“In accordance with the Teaching”:*";
P_HTM[9988]="*bhūtena vatthunā.**in according with truth, in accordance with the action that was the basis for the offense.*";
P_HTM[9989]="*Yena vinayenāti**“In accordance with the Monastic Law”:*";
P_HTM[9990]="*codetvā sāretvā.**having accused and having reminded.*";
P_HTM[9991]="*Yena satthusāsanenāti**“In accordance with the Teacher’s instruction”:*";
P_HTM[9992]="*ñattisampadāya anussāvanasampadāya, yena dhammena yena vinayena yena satthusāsanena taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasammati, tathā taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametabbanti.**he resolves that legal issue, complete in motion and complete in announcement, in accordance with the Teaching, the Monastic Law, and the Teacher’s instruction.*";
P_HTM[9993]="*6. Anuvijjakassaanuyoga**6. The questioning of the investigator*";
P_HTM[9994]="*Anuvijjakena codako pucchitabbo—**The investigator should ask the accuser,*";
P_HTM[9995]="*“yaṃ kho tvaṃ, āvuso, imassa bhikkhuno pavāraṇaṃ ṭhapesi, kimhi naṃ ṭhapesi, sīlavipattiyā vā ṭhapesi, ācāravipattiyā vā ṭhapesi, diṭṭhivipattiyā vā ṭhapesī”ti?**“Are you canceling this monk’s invitation because he has failed in morality, in conduct, or in view?”*";
P_HTM[9996]="*So ce evaṃ vadeyya—**If he says,*";
P_HTM[9997]="*“sīlavipattiyā vā ṭhapemi, ācāravipattiyā vā ṭhapemi, diṭṭhivipattiyā vā ṭhapemī”ti, so evamassa vacanīyo—**“I’m canceling it because he has failed in morality,” “I’m canceling it because he has failed in conduct,” “I’m canceling it because he has failed in view,” he should be asked,*";
P_HTM[9998]="*“jānāti panāyasmā sīlavipattiṃ, jānāti ācāravipattiṃ, jānāti diṭṭhivipattin”ti?**“Do you know what failure in morality is?” “Do you know what failure in conduct is?” “Do you know what failure in view is?”*";
P_HTM[9999]="*So ce evaṃ vadeyya—**If he says,*";
P_HTM[10000]="*“jānāmi kho ahaṃ, āvuso, sīlavipattiṃ, jānāmi ācāravipattiṃ, jānāmi diṭṭhivipattin”ti, so evamassa vacanīyo—**“I do,” he should be asked what they are.*";
P_HTM[10001]="*“katamā panāvuso, sīlavipatti, katamā ācāravipatti, katamā diṭṭhivipattī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[10002]="*So ce evaṃ vadeyya—**If he says,*";
P_HTM[10003]="*“cattāri pārājikāni terasa saṅghādisesā—ayaṃ sīlavipatti.**“The four offenses entailing expulsion and the thirteen entailing suspension are failure in morality,”*";
P_HTM[10004]="*Thullaccayaṃ pācittiyaṃ pāṭidesanīyaṃ dukkaṭaṃ dubbhāsitaṃ—ayaṃ ācāravipatti.**“The serious offenses, the offenses entailing confession, the offenses entailing acknowledgment, the offenses of wrong conduct, and the offenses of wrong speech are failure in conduct,”*";
P_HTM[10005]="*Micchādiṭṭhi antaggāhikādiṭṭhi—ayaṃ diṭṭhivipattī”ti, so evamassa vacanīyo—**“Wrong views and side views are failure in view,” he should be asked,*";
P_HTM[10006]="*“yaṃ kho tvaṃ, āvuso, imassa bhikkhuno pavāraṇaṃ ṭhapesi, diṭṭhena vā ṭhapesi, sutena vā ṭhapesi, parisaṅkāya vā ṭhapesī”ti?**“Are you canceling this monk’s invitation because of what you have seen, because of what you have heard, or because of suspicion?”*";
P_HTM[10007]="*So ce evaṃ vadeyya—**If he says,*";
P_HTM[10008]="*“diṭṭhena vā ṭhapemi, sutena vā ṭhapemi, parisaṅkāya vā ṭhapemī”ti, so evamassa vacanīyo—**“I’m canceling it because of what I have seen,” “I’m canceling it because of what I have heard,” “I’m canceling it because of suspicion,” he should be asked,*";
P_HTM[10009]="*“yaṃ kho tvaṃ, āvuso, imassa bhikkhuno diṭṭhena pavāraṇaṃ ṭhapesi, kiṃ te diṭṭhaṃ, kinti te diṭṭhaṃ, kadā te diṭṭhaṃ, kattha te diṭṭhaṃ, pārājikaṃ ajjhāpajjanto diṭṭho, saṅghādisesaṃ ajjhāpajjanto diṭṭho, thullaccayaṃ …**“Since you’re canceling this monk’s invitation because of what you have seen, what have you seen? How did you see it? When did you see it? Where did you see it? Did you see him commit an offense entailing expulsion? Did you see him commit an offense entailing suspension? Did you see him commit a serious offense? …*";
P_HTM[10010]="*pācittiyaṃ …**… an offense entailing confession?*";
P_HTM[10011]="*pāṭidesanīyaṃ …**… an offense entailing acknowledgment?*";
P_HTM[10012]="*dukkaṭaṃ …**… an offense of wrong conduct?*";
P_HTM[10013]="*dubbhāsitaṃ ajjhāpajjanto diṭṭho, kattha ca tvaṃ ahosi, kattha cāyaṃ bhikkhu ahosi, kiñca tvaṃ karosi, kiṃ cāyaṃ bhikkhu karotī”ti?**… an offense of wrong speech? Where were you? Where was this monk? What were you doing? What was this monk doing?”*";
P_HTM[10014]="*So ce evaṃ vadeyya—**If he says,*";
P_HTM[10015]="*“na kho ahaṃ, āvuso, imassa bhikkhuno diṭṭhena pavāraṇaṃ ṭhapemi, api ca sutena pavāraṇaṃ ṭhapemī”ti, so evamassa vacanīyo—**“I didn’t cancel this monk’s invitation because of what I have seen, but because of what I have heard,” he should be asked,*";
P_HTM[10016]="*“yaṃ kho tvaṃ, āvuso, imassa bhikkhuno sutena pavāraṇaṃ ṭhapesi, kiṃ te sutaṃ, kinti te sutaṃ, kadā te sutaṃ, kattha te sutaṃ, pārājikaṃ ajjhāpannoti sutaṃ, saṅghādisesaṃ ajjhāpannoti sutaṃ, thullaccayaṃ …**“Since you’re canceling this monk’s invitation because of what you have heard, what have you heard? How did you hear it? When did you hear it? Where did you hear it? Did you hear that he has committed an offense entailing expulsion? Did you hear that he has committed an offense entailing suspension? Did you hear that he has committed a serious offense?*";
P_HTM[10017]="*pācittiyaṃ …**… an offense entailing confession?*";
P_HTM[10018]="*pāṭidesanīyaṃ …**… an offense entailing acknowledgment?*";
P_HTM[10019]="*dukkaṭaṃ …**… an offense of wrong conduct?*";
P_HTM[10020]="*dubbhāsitaṃ ajjhāpannoti sutaṃ, bhikkhussa sutaṃ, bhikkhuniyā sutaṃ, sikkhamānāya sutaṃ, sāmaṇerassa sutaṃ, sāmaṇeriyā sutaṃ, upāsakassa sutaṃ, upāsikāya sutaṃ, rājūnaṃ sutaṃ, rājamahāmattānaṃ sutaṃ, titthiyānaṃ sutaṃ, titthiyasāvakānaṃ sutan”ti?**Did you hear that he has committed an offense of wrong speech? Did you hear it from a monk? Did you hear it from a nun? Did you hear it from a trainee nun? Did you hear it from a novice monk? Did you hear it from a novice nun? Did you hear it from a male lay follower? Did you hear it from a female lay follower? Did you hear it from kings? Did you hear it from a king’s officials? Did you hear it from the monastics of another religion? Did you hear it from the lay followers of another religion?”*";
P_HTM[10021]="*So ce evaṃ vadeyya—**If he says,*";
P_HTM[10022]="*“na kho ahaṃ, āvuso, imassa bhikkhuno sutena pavāraṇaṃ ṭhapemi, api ca parisaṅkāya pavāraṇaṃ ṭhapemī”ti, so evamassa vacanīyo—**If he says, “I didn’t cancel this monk’s invitation because of what I have heard, but because of suspicion,” he should be asked,*";
P_HTM[10023]="*“yaṃ kho tvaṃ, āvuso, imassa bhikkhuno parisaṅkāya pavāraṇaṃ ṭhapesi, kiṃ parisaṅkasi, kinti parisaṅkasi, kadā parisaṅkasi, kattha parisaṅkasi, pārājikaṃ ajjhāpannoti parisaṅkasi, saṅghādisesaṃ ajjhāpannoti parisaṅkasi, thullaccayaṃ …**“Since you’re canceling this monk’s invitation because of suspicion, what do you suspect? How do you suspect it? When did you suspect it? Where did you suspect it? Do you suspect that he has committed an offense entailing expulsion? Do you suspect that he has committed an offense entailing suspension? Do you suspect that he has committed a serious offense?*";
P_HTM[10024]="*pācittiyaṃ …**… an offense entailing confession?*";
P_HTM[10025]="*pāṭidesanīyaṃ …**… an offense entailing acknowledgment?*";
P_HTM[10026]="*dukkaṭaṃ …**… an offense of wrong conduct?*";
P_HTM[10027]="*dubbhāsitaṃ ajjhāpannoti parisaṅkasi, bhikkhussa sutvā parisaṅkasi, bhikkhuniyā sutvā parisaṅkasi, sikkhamānāya sutvā parisaṅkasi, sāmaṇerassa sutvā parisaṅkasi, sāmaṇeriyā sutvā parisaṅkasi, upāsakassa sutvā parisaṅkasi, upāsikāya sutvā parisaṅkasi, rājūnaṃ sutvā parisaṅkasi, rājamahāmattānaṃ sutvā parisaṅkasi, titthiyānaṃ sutvā parisaṅkasi, titthiyasāvakānaṃ sutvā parisaṅkasī”ti?**Do you suspect that he has committed an offense of wrong speech? Do you suspect it after hearing about it from a monk? Do you suspect it after hearing about it from a nun? Do you suspect it after hearing about it from a trainee nun? Do you suspect it after hearing about it from a novice monk? Do you suspect it after hearing about it from a novice nun? Do you suspect it after hearing about it from a male lay follower? Do you suspect it after hearing about it from a female lay follower? Do you suspect it after hearing about it from kings? Do you suspect it after hearing about it from a king’s officials? Do you suspect it after hearing about it from the monastics of another religion? Do you suspect it after hearing about it from the lay followers of another religion?”*";
P_HTM[10028]="*Diṭṭhaṃ diṭṭhena sameti,**“If what he saw agrees with what he says he saw,*";
P_HTM[10029]="*diṭṭhena saṃsandate diṭṭhaṃ;**If they correspond with each other,*";
P_HTM[10030]="*Diṭṭhaṃ paṭicca na upeti,**But what was seen is not adequate to prove the accusation,*";
P_HTM[10031]="*asuddhaparisaṅkito;**Then the one suspecting impurity*";
P_HTM[10032]="*So puggalo paṭiññāya,**Should admit it,*";
P_HTM[10033]="*kātabbā tena pavāraṇā.**And they should then do the invitation-day procedure with him.*";
P_HTM[10034]="*Sutaṃ sutena sameti,**If what he heard agrees with what he says he heard,*";
P_HTM[10035]="*sutena saṃsandate sutaṃ;**If they correspond with each other,*";
P_HTM[10036]="*Sutaṃ paṭicca na upeti,**But what was heard is not adequate to prove the accusation,*";
P_HTM[10037]="*asuddhaparisaṅkito;**Then the one suspecting impurity*";
P_HTM[10038]="*So puggalo paṭiññāya,**Should admit it,*";
P_HTM[10039]="*kātabbā tena pavāraṇā.**And they should then do the invitation-day procedure with him.*";
P_HTM[10040]="*Mutaṃ mutena sameti,**If what he sensed agrees with what he says he sensed,*";
P_HTM[10041]="*Mutena saṃsandate mutaṃ;**If they correspond with each other,*";
P_HTM[10042]="*Mutaṃ paṭicca na upeti,**But what was sensed is not adequate to prove the accusation,*";
P_HTM[10043]="*Asuddhaparisaṅkito;**Then the one suspecting impurity*";
P_HTM[10044]="*So puggalo paṭiññāya,**Should admit it,*";
P_HTM[10045]="*Kātabbā tena pavāraṇāti.**And they should then do the invitation-day procedure with him.”*";
P_HTM[10046]="*7. Pucchāvibhāga**7. The details of asking*";
P_HTM[10047]="*Kiṃ te diṭṭhanti katamā pucchā?**In regard to “What have you seen?”, what are the questions?*";
P_HTM[10048]="*Kinti te diṭṭhanti katamā pucchā?**In regard to “How did you see it?”, what are the questions?*";
P_HTM[10049]="*Kadā te diṭṭhanti katamā pucchā?**In regard to “When did you see it?”, what are the questions?*";
P_HTM[10050]="*Kattha te diṭṭhanti katamā pucchā?**In regard to “Where did you see it?”, what are the questions?*";
P_HTM[10051]="*Kiṃ te diṭṭhanti**“In regard to ‘What have you seen?’,*";
P_HTM[10052]="*vatthupucchā, vipattipucchā, āpattipucchā, ajjhācārapucchā.**there are questions on the actions that is the basis for offenses, there are questions on failure, there are questions on offenses, and there are questions on misconduct.*";
P_HTM[10053]="*Vatthupucchāti—**‘Questions on the action that is the basis for the offense’:*";
P_HTM[10054]="*aṭṭhapārājikānaṃ vatthupucchā, tevīsasaṅghādisesānaṃ vatthupucchā, dveaniyatānaṃ vatthupucchā, dvecattārīsanissaggiyānaṃ vatthupucchā, aṭṭhāsītisatapācittiyānaṃ vatthupucchā, dvādasapāṭidesanīyānaṃ vatthupucchā, dukkaṭānaṃ vatthupucchā, dubbhāsitānaṃ vatthupucchā.**there are questions on the actions that are the bases for the eight offenses entailing expulsion, on the actions that are the bases for the twenty-three offenses entailing suspension, for the two undetermined offenses, for the forty-two offenses entailing relinquishment, for the one hundred and eighty-eight offenses entailing confession, for the twelve offenses entailing acknowledgment, for the offenses of wrong conduct, and for the offenses of wrong speech.*";
P_HTM[10055]="*Vipattipucchāti—**‘Questions on failure’:*";
P_HTM[10056]="*sīlavipattipucchā, ācāravipattipucchā, diṭṭhivipattipucchā, ājīvavipattipucchā.**there are questions on failure in morality, on failure in conduct, on failure in view, and on failure in livelihood.*";
P_HTM[10057]="*Āpattipucchāti—**‘Questions on the offenses’:*";
P_HTM[10058]="*pārājikāpattipucchā, saṅghādisesāpattipucchā, thullaccayāpattipucchā, pācittiyāpattipucchā, pāṭidesanīyāpattipucchā, dukkaṭāpattipucchā, dubbhāsitāpattipucchā.**there are questions on the offenses entailing expulsion, on the offenses entailing suspension, on the serious offenses, on the offenses entailing confession, on the offenses entailing acknowledgement, on the offenses of wrong conduct, and on the offenses of wrong speech.*";
P_HTM[10059]="*Ajjhācārapucchāti—**‘Questions on misconduct’:*";
P_HTM[10060]="*dvayaṃdvayasamāpattipucchā.**questions on that which is done wherever there are couples.*";
P_HTM[10061]="*Kinti te diṭṭhanti**In regard to ‘How did you see it?’,*";
P_HTM[10062]="*liṅgapucchā, iriyāpathapucchā, ākārapucchā, vippakārapucchā.**there are questions on characteristics, on deportment, on ways, and on movement.*";
P_HTM[10063]="*Liṅgapucchāti—dīghaṃ vā rassaṃ vā kaṇhaṃ vā odātaṃ vā.**‘Questions on characteristics’: tall, short, dark-skinned, or light-skinned.*";
P_HTM[10064]="*Iriyāpathapucchāti gacchantaṃ vā ṭhitaṃ vā nisinnaṃ vā nipannaṃ vā.**‘Questions on deportment’: walking, standing, sitting, or lying down.*";
P_HTM[10065]="*Ākārapucchāti gihiliṅge vā titthiyaliṅge vā pabbajitaliṅge vā.**‘Questions on ways’: the characteristics of a householder, of a monastic of another religion, or of one gone forth.*";
P_HTM[10066]="*Vippakārapucchāti gacchantaṃ vā ṭhitaṃ vā nisinnaṃ vā nipannaṃ vā.**‘Questions on movement’: walking, standing, sitting, or lying down.*";
P_HTM[10067]="*Kadā te diṭṭhanti**In regard to ‘When did you see it?’,*";
P_HTM[10068]="*kālapucchā, samayapucchā, divasapucchā, utupucchā.**there are questions on time, on occasion, on day, and on season.*";
P_HTM[10069]="*Kālapucchāti pubbaṇhakāle vā majjhanhikakāle vā sāyanhakāle vā.**‘Questions on time’: in the morning, at midday, or in the evening.*";
P_HTM[10070]="*Samayapucchāti pubbaṇhasamaye vā majjhanhikasamaye vā sāyanhasamaye vā.**‘Questions on occasion’: in the morning, at midday, or in the evening.*";
P_HTM[10071]="*Divasapucchāti purebhattaṃ vā pacchābhattaṃ vā rattiṃ vā divā vā kāḷe vā juṇhe vā.**‘Questions on day’: before the meal, after the meal, at night, by day, at new moon, or at full moon.*";
P_HTM[10072]="*Utupucchāti hemante vā gimhe vā vasse vā.**‘Questions on season’: in winter, in summer, or during the rainy season.*";
P_HTM[10073]="*Kattha te diṭṭhanti**In regard to ‘Where did you see it?’,*";
P_HTM[10074]="*ṭhānapucchā, bhūmipucchā, okāsapucchā, padesapucchā.**there are questions about place, about elevation, about location, and about region.*";
P_HTM[10075]="*Ṭhānapucchāti bhūmiyā vā pathaviyā vā dharaṇiyā vā jagatiyā vā.**‘Questions about place’: on the ground, on the earth, on the planet, or in the world.*";
P_HTM[10076]="*Bhūmipucchāti bhūmiyā vā pathaviyā vā pabbate vā pāsāṇe vā pāsāde vā.**‘Questions about elevation’: on the ground, on the earth, on a mountain, on a rock, or in a stilt house.*";
P_HTM[10077]="*Okāsapucchāti puratthime vā okāse pacchime vā okāse uttare vā okāse dakkhiṇe vā okāse.**‘Questions about location’: to the east, to the west, to the north, and to the south.*";
P_HTM[10078]="*Padesapucchāti puratthime vā padese pacchime vā padese uttare vā padese dakkhiṇe vā padeseti.**‘Questions about region’: to the east, to the west, to the north, and to the south.”*";
P_HTM[10079]="*Mahāsaṅgāmaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The great section on conflict is finished.*";
P_HTM[10080]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[10081]="*Vatthu nidānaṃ ākāro,**“Basis for an offense, origin story, attribute,*";
P_HTM[10082]="*pubbāparaṃ katākataṃ;**Sequence, what has and has not been done;*";
P_HTM[10083]="*Kammādhikaraṇañceva,**Legal procedure and legal issue,*";
P_HTM[10084]="*samatho chandagāmi ca.**Settling, and swayed by desire.*";
P_HTM[10085]="*Dosā mohā bhayā ceva,**By ill will, confusion, and fear,*";
P_HTM[10086]="*saññā nijjhāpanena ca;**Persuasion, and by making understand;*";
P_HTM[10087]="*Pekkhā pasāde pakkhomhi,**Looking on, inspiration, I have a faction,*";
P_HTM[10088]="*sutatheratarena ca.**Learned, and with more senior.*";
P_HTM[10089]="*Asampattañca sampattaṃ,**And not reached, reached,*";
P_HTM[10090]="*dhammena vinayena ca;**According to the Teaching, and the Monastic Law;*";
P_HTM[10091]="*Satthussa sāsanenāpi,**Also according to the Teacher’s instruction—*";
P_HTM[10092]="*mahāsaṅgāmañāpanāti.**The explanation in the great section on conflict.”*";
P_HTM[10093]="*124. 1. Kathinaatthatādi **124.  1. The robe*";
P_HTM[10094]="*Kassa kathinaṃ anatthataṃ?**Who has not participated in the robe-making procedure?*";
P_HTM[10095]="*Kassa kathinaṃ atthataṃ?**Who has participated in the robe-making procedure?*";
P_HTM[10096]="*Kinti kathinaṃ anatthataṃ?**How is the robe-making procedure not done?*";
P_HTM[10097]="*Kinti kathinaṃ atthataṃ?**How is the robe-making procedure done?*";
P_HTM[10098]="*Kassa kathinaṃ anatthatanti?**“Who has not participated in the robe-making procedure?”*";
P_HTM[10099]="*Dvinnaṃ puggalānaṃ anatthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ—**Two kinds of people:*";
P_HTM[10100]="*anatthārakassa ca ananumodakassa ca.**those who have not performed the robe-making procedure and those who have not expressed their appreciation.*";
P_HTM[10101]="*Imesaṃ dvinnaṃ puggalānaṃ anatthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10102]="*Kassa kathinaṃ atthatanti?**“Who has participated in the robe-making procedure?”*";
P_HTM[10103]="*Dvinnaṃ puggalānaṃ atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ—**Two kinds of people:*";
P_HTM[10104]="*atthārakassa ca anumodakassa ca.**those who have performed the robe-making procedure and those who have expressed their appreciation.*";
P_HTM[10105]="*Imesaṃ dvinnaṃ puggalānaṃ atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10106]="*Kinti kathinaṃ anatthatanti?**“How is the robe-making procedure not done?”*";
P_HTM[10107]="*Catuvīsatiyā ākārehi anatthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ,**There are twenty-four ways in which the robe-making procedure has not been done:*";
P_HTM[10108]="*na ullikhitamattena atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ,**The robe-making procedure hasn’t been done merely by marking the cloth,*";
P_HTM[10109]="*na dhovanamattena atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ,**merely by washing the cloth,*";
P_HTM[10110]="*na cīvaravicāraṇamattena atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ,**merely by planning the robe,*";
P_HTM[10111]="*na chedanamattena atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ,**merely by cutting the cloth,*";
P_HTM[10112]="*na bandhanamattena atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ,**merely by a tacking the cloth,*";
P_HTM[10113]="*na ovaṭṭiyakaraṇamattena atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ,**merely by sewing a seam,*";
P_HTM[10114]="*na kaṇḍusakaraṇamattena atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ,**merely by marking with a strip of cloth,*";
P_HTM[10115]="*na daḷhīkammakaraṇamattena atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ,**merely by strengthening,*";
P_HTM[10116]="*na anuvātakaraṇamattena atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ,**merely by adding a border lengthwise,*";
P_HTM[10117]="*na paribhaṇḍakaraṇamattena atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ,**merely by adding a border crosswise,*";
P_HTM[10118]="*na ovaddheyyakaraṇamattena atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ,**merely by adding a patch,*";
P_HTM[10119]="*na kambalamaddanamattena atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ,**merely by partial dyeing;*";
P_HTM[10120]="*na nimittakatena atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ,**nor has it been done if a monk has made an indication,*";
P_HTM[10121]="*na parikathākatena atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ,**if a monk has given a hint,*";
P_HTM[10122]="*na kukkukatena atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ,**if the robe has been borrowed,*";
P_HTM[10123]="*na sannidhikatena atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ,**if it has been stored,*";
P_HTM[10124]="*na nissaggiyena atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ,**if it is to be relinquished,*";
P_HTM[10125]="*na akappakatena atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ,**if it hasn’t been marked,*";
P_HTM[10126]="*na aññatra saṅghāṭiyā atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ,**if it’s not an outer robe*";
P_HTM[10127]="*na aññatra uttarāsaṅgena atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ,**or an upper robe*";
P_HTM[10128]="*na aññatra antaravāsakena atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ,**or a sarong;*";
P_HTM[10129]="*na aññatra pañcakena vā atirekapañcakena vā tadaheva sañchinnena samaṇḍalīkatena atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ,**nor has it been done if the robe hasn’t been made on that very day with five or more cut sections with panels,*";
P_HTM[10130]="*na aññatra puggalassa atthārā atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ,**if the robe-making procedure isn’t done by an individual,*";
P_HTM[10131]="*sammā ce atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ, tañce nissīmaṭṭho anumodati.**or if the appreciation for the procedure is expressed by someone outside the monastic boundary.*";
P_HTM[10132]="*Evampi anatthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10133]="*Nimittakammaṃ nāma nimittaṃ karoti—**Making an indication: one makes an indication, thinking,*";
P_HTM[10134]="*“iminā dussena kathinaṃ attharissāmī”ti.**“I will do the robe-making procedure with this cloth.”*";
P_HTM[10135]="*Parikathā nāma parikathaṃ karoti—**Hinting: one gives a hint, thinking,*";
P_HTM[10136]="*“imāya parikathāya kathinadussaṃ nibbattessāmī”ti.**“With this hint, I will make a cloth for the robe-making procedure appear.”*";
P_HTM[10137]="*Kukkukataṃ nāma anādiyadānaṃ vuccati.**Borrowed: taking what has not been given is so called.*";
P_HTM[10138]="*Sannidhi nāma dve sannidhiyo—**Stored: there are two kinds of storing:*";
P_HTM[10139]="*karaṇasannidhi vā nicayasannidhi vā.**storing for the purpose of making and storing for the purpose of accumulation.*";
P_HTM[10140]="*Nissaggiyaṃ nāma kayiramāne aruṇaṃ uṭṭhahati.**To be relinquished: dawn arrives while it is being made.*";
P_HTM[10141]="*Imehi catuvīsatiyā ākārehi anatthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10142]="*Kinti kathinaṃ atthatanti?**“How is the robe-making procedure done?”*";
P_HTM[10143]="*Sattarasahi ākārehi atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ.**The robe-making procedure is done through seventeen aspects:*";
P_HTM[10144]="*Ahatena atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ, ahatakappena atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ, pilotikāya atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ, paṃsukūlena atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ, pāpaṇikena atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ, animittakatena atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ, aparikathākatena atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ, akukkukatena atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ, asannidhikatena atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ, anissaggiyena atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ, kappakatena atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ, saṅghāṭiyā atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ, uttarāsaṅgena atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ, antaravāsakena atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ, pañcakena vā atirekapañcakena vā tadaheva sañchinnena samaṇḍalīkatena atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ, puggalassa atthārā atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ, sammā ce atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ, tañce sīmaṭṭho anumodati, evampi atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ.**The robe-making procedure has been done if the cloth is brand new, if it’s nearly new, if it’s old, if it’s a rag, if it’s from a shop; it has been done if a monk hasn’t given a sign, if a monk hasn’t given a hint, if the robe hasn’t been borrowed, if it hasn’t been stored, if it’s not to be relinquished, if it has been marked, if it’s an outer robe or an upper robe or a sarong; it has been done if the robe has been made on that very day with five or more cut sections with panels, if the robe-making procedure is done by an individual, and if the appreciation for the procedure is expressed by someone inside the monastic boundary.*";
P_HTM[10145]="*Imehi sattarasahi ākārehi atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10146]="*Saha kathinassa atthārā kati dhammā jāyanti?**How many things are produced together with the doing of the robe-making procedure?*";
P_HTM[10147]="*Saha kathinassa atthārā pannarasa dhammā jāyanti—**Fifteen things:*";
P_HTM[10148]="*aṭṭha mātikā, dve palibodhā, pañcānisaṃsā.**eight summaries, two obstacles, and five benefits.*";
P_HTM[10149]="*Saha kathinassa atthārā ime pannarasa dhammā jāyanti.* **";
P_HTM[10150]="*2. Kathinaanantarapaccayādi**2. The immediately preceding condition for the robe-making procedure, etc.*";
P_HTM[10151]="*Payogassa katame dhammā anantarapaccayena paccayo, samanantarapaccayena paccayo, nissayapaccayena paccayo, upanissayapaccayena paccayo, purejātapaccayena paccayo, pacchājātapaccayena paccayo, sahajātapaccayena paccayo?**Which things are a condition for effort—by being an immediately preceding condition, by being an immediately prior condition, by being a support condition, by being a decisive support condition, by being a pre-arising condition, by being a post-arising condition, by being a co-arising condition?*";
P_HTM[10152]="*Pubbakaraṇassa katame dhammā anantarapaccayena paccayo …pe…**Which things are a condition for the prior duties—by being an immediately preceding condition …*";
P_HTM[10153]="*paccuddhārassa katame dhammā …**Which things are a condition for relinquishment …*";
P_HTM[10154]="*adhiṭṭhānassa katame dhammā …**Which things are a condition for determining …*";
P_HTM[10155]="*atthārassa katame dhammā …**Which things are a condition for doing the robe-making procedure …*";
P_HTM[10156]="*mātikānañca palibodhānañca katame dhammā …**Which things are a condition for the summaries and the obstacles …*";
P_HTM[10157]="*vatthussa katame dhammā anantarapaccayena paccayo, samanantarapaccayena paccayo, nissayapaccayena paccayo, upanissayapaccayena paccayo, purejātapaccayena paccayo, pacchājātapaccayena paccayo, sahajātapaccayena paccayo?**Which things are a condition for the subject—by being an immediately preceding condition, by being an immediately prior condition, by being a support condition, by being a decisive support condition, by being a pre-arising condition, by being a post-arising condition, by being a co-arising condition?*";
P_HTM[10158]="*Pubbakaraṇaṃ payogassa anantarapaccayena paccayo, samanantarapaccayena paccayo, nissayapaccayena paccayo, upanissayapaccayena paccayo.**The prior duties are an immediately preceding condition for effort, and an immediately prior condition, a support condition, and a decisive support condition.*";
P_HTM[10159]="*Payogo pubbakaraṇassa purejātapaccayena paccayo.**Effort is a pre-arising condition for the prior duties.*";
P_HTM[10160]="*Pubbakaraṇaṃ payogassa pacchājātapaccayena paccayo.**The prior duties are a post-arising condition for effort.*";
P_HTM[10161]="*Pannarasa dhammā sahajātapaccayena paccayo.**The fifteen things are a co-arising condition.*";
P_HTM[10162]="*Paccuddhāro pubbakaraṇassa anantarapaccayena paccayo, samanantarapaccayena paccayo, nissayapaccayena paccayo, upanissayapaccayena paccayo.**Relinquishment is an immediately preceding condition for the prior duties, and an immediately prior condition, a support condition, and a decisive support condition.*";
P_HTM[10163]="*Pubbakaraṇaṃ paccuddhārassa purejātapaccayena paccayo.**The prior duties are a pre-arising condition for relinquishment.*";
P_HTM[10164]="*Paccuddhāro pubbakaraṇassa pacchājātapaccayena paccayo.**Relinquishment is a pre-arising condition for the prior duties.*";
P_HTM[10165]="*Pannarasa dhammā sahajātapaccayena paccayo.**The fifteen things are a co-arising condition.*";
P_HTM[10166]="*Adhiṭṭhānaṃ paccuddhārassa anantarapaccayena paccayo, samanantarapaccayena paccayo, nissayapaccayena paccayo, upanissayapaccayena paccayo.**Determining is an immediately preceding condition for relinquishment, and an immediately prior condition, a support condition, and a decisive support condition.*";
P_HTM[10167]="*Paccuddhāro adhiṭṭhānassa purejātapaccayena paccayo.**Relinquishment is a pre-arising condition for determining.*";
P_HTM[10168]="*Adhiṭṭhānaṃ paccuddhārassa pacchājātapaccayena paccayo.**Determining is a pre-arising condition for relinquishment.*";
P_HTM[10169]="*Pannarasa dhammā sahajātapaccayena paccayo.**The fifteen things are a co-arising condition.*";
P_HTM[10170]="*Atthāro adhiṭṭhānassa anantarapaccayena paccayo, samanantarapaccayena paccayo, nissayapaccayena paccayo, upanissayapaccayena paccayo.**Doing the robe-making procedure is an immediately preceding condition for determining, and an immediately prior condition, a support condition, and a decisive support condition.*";
P_HTM[10171]="*Adhiṭṭhānaṃ atthārassa purejātapaccayena paccayo.**Determining is a pre-arising condition for doing the robe-making procedure.*";
P_HTM[10172]="*Atthāro adhiṭṭhānassa pacchājātapaccayena paccayo.**Doing the robe-making procedure is a pre-arising condition for determining.*";
P_HTM[10173]="*Pannarasa dhammā sahajātapaccayena paccayo.**The fifteen things are a co-arising condition.*";
P_HTM[10174]="*Mātikā ca palibodhā ca atthārassa anantarapaccayena paccayo, samanantarapaccayena paccayo, nissayapaccayena paccayo, upanissayapaccayena paccayo.**The summaries and the obstacles are an immediately preceding condition for doing the robe-making procedure, and an immediately prior condition, a support condition, and a decisive support condition.*";
P_HTM[10175]="*Atthāro mātikānañca palibodhānañca purejātapaccayena paccayo.**Doing the robe-making procedure is a pre-arising condition for the summaries and the obstacles.*";
P_HTM[10176]="*Mātikā ca palibodhā ca atthārassa pacchājātapaccayena paccayo.**The summaries and the obstacles are a pre-arising condition for doing the robe-making procedure.*";
P_HTM[10177]="*Pannarasa dhammā sahajātapaccayena paccayo.**The fifteen things are a co-arising condition.*";
P_HTM[10178]="*Āsā ca anāsā ca vatthussa anantarapaccayena paccayo, samanantarapaccayena paccayo, nissayapaccayena paccayo, upanissayapaccayena paccayo.**Expectation and non-expectation are an immediately preceding condition for the subject, and an immediately prior condition, a support condition, and a decisive support condition.*";
P_HTM[10179]="*Vatthu āsānañca anāsānañca purejātapaccayena paccayo.**The subject is a pre-arising condition for expectation and non-expectation.*";
P_HTM[10180]="*Āsā ca anāsā ca vatthussa pacchājātapaccayena paccayo.**Expectation and non-expectation are a pre-arising condition for the subject.*";
P_HTM[10181]="*Pannarasa dhammā sahajātapaccayena paccayo.**The fifteen things are a co-arising condition.*";
P_HTM[10182]="*3. Pubbakaraṇanidānādivibhāga**3. The details on the source of the prior duties, etc.*";
P_HTM[10183]="*Pubbakaraṇaṃ kiṃnidānaṃ, kiṃsamudayaṃ, kiṃjātikaṃ, kiṃpabhavaṃ, kiṃsambhāraṃ, kiṃsamuṭṭhānaṃ?**What is the source, the origin, the birth, the arising, the production, the origination of the prior duties?*";
P_HTM[10184]="*Paccuddhāro kiṃnidāno, kiṃsamudayo, kiṃjātiko, kiṃpabhavo, kiṃsambhāro, kiṃsamuṭṭhāno?**What is the source, the origin, the birth, the arising, the production, the origination of relinquishment?*";
P_HTM[10185]="*Adhiṭṭhānaṃ kiṃnidānaṃ, kiṃsamudayaṃ, kiṃjātikaṃ, kiṃpabhavaṃ, kiṃsambhāraṃ, kiṃsamuṭṭhānaṃ?**What is the source, the origin, the birth, the arising, the production, the origination of determining?*";
P_HTM[10186]="*Atthāro kiṃnidāno, kiṃsamudayo, kiṃjātiko, kiṃpabhavo, kiṃsambhāro, kiṃsamuṭṭhāno?**What is the source, the origin, the birth, the arising, the production, the origination of doing the robe-making procedure?*";
P_HTM[10187]="*Mātikā ca palibodhā ca kiṃnidānā, kiṃsamudayā, kiṃjātikā, kiṃpabhavā, kiṃsambhārā kiṃsamuṭṭhānā?**What is the source, the origin, the birth, the arising, the production, the origination of the summaries and the obstacles?*";
P_HTM[10188]="*Āsā ca anāsā ca kiṃnidānā, kiṃsamudayā, kiṃjātikā, kiṃpabhavā, kiṃsambhārā, kiṃsamuṭṭhānā?**What is the source, the origin, the birth, the arising, the production, the origination of expectation and non-expectation?*";
P_HTM[10189]="*Pubbakaraṇaṃ payoganidānaṃ, payogasamudayaṃ, payogajātikaṃ, payogapabhavaṃ, payogasambhāraṃ, payogasamuṭṭhānaṃ.**The prior duties have effort as their source, origin, birth, arising, production, and origination.*";
P_HTM[10190]="*Paccuddhāro pubbakaraṇanidāno, pubbakaraṇasamudayo, pubbakaraṇajātiko, pubbakaraṇapabhavo, pubbakaraṇasambhāro, pubbakaraṇasamuṭṭhāno.**Relinquishment have the prior duties as its source, origin, birth, arising, production, and origination.*";
P_HTM[10191]="*Adhiṭṭhānaṃ paccuddhāranidānaṃ, paccuddhārasamudayaṃ, paccuddhārajātikaṃ, paccuddhārapabhavaṃ, paccuddhārasambhāraṃ, paccuddhārasamuṭṭhānaṃ.**Determining has relinquishment as its source, origin, birth, arising, production, and origination.*";
P_HTM[10192]="*Atthāro adhiṭṭhānanidāno, adhiṭṭhānasamudayo, adhiṭṭhānajātiko, adhiṭṭhānapabhavo, adhiṭṭhānasambhāro, adhiṭṭhānasamuṭṭhāno.**Doing the robe-making procedure has determining as its source, origin, birth, arising, production, and origination.*";
P_HTM[10193]="*Mātikā ca palibodhā ca atthāranidānā, atthārasamudayā, atthārajātikā, atthārapabhavā, atthārasambhārā, atthārasamuṭṭhānā.**The summaries and the obstacles has doing the robe-making procedure as its source, origin, birth, arising, production, and origination.*";
P_HTM[10194]="*Āsā ca anāsā ca vatthunidānā, vatthusamudayā, vatthujātikā, vatthupabhavā, vatthusambhārā, vatthusamuṭṭhānā.**Expectation and non-expectation have the summaries and the obstacles as their source, origin, birth, arising, production, and origination.*";
P_HTM[10195]="*Payogo kiṃnidāno, kiṃsamudayo, kiṃjātiko, kiṃpabhavo, kiṃsambhāro, kiṃsamuṭṭhāno,**What is the source, the origin, the birth, the arising, the production, the origination of effort?*";
P_HTM[10196]="*pubbakaraṇaṃ …pe…**… of the prior duties?*";
P_HTM[10197]="*paccuddhāro …**… of relinquishment?*";
P_HTM[10198]="*adhiṭṭhānaṃ …**… of determining?*";
P_HTM[10199]="*atthāro …**… of doing the robe-making procedure?*";
P_HTM[10200]="*mātikā ca palibodhā ca …**… of the summaries and the obstacles?*";
P_HTM[10201]="*vatthu …**… of the subject?*";
