P_HTM[10227]="*Pubbakaraṇaṃ katihi dhammehi saṅgahitaṃ?**How many things are the prior duties grouped with?*";
P_HTM[10228]="*Pubbakaraṇaṃ sattahi dhammehi saṅgahitaṃ.**With seven things:*";
P_HTM[10229]="*Dhovanena, vicāraṇena, chedanena, bandhanena, sibbanena, rajanena, kappakaraṇena—**washing, planning, cutting, tacking, sewing, dyeing, and making.*";
P_HTM[10230]="*pubbakaraṇaṃ imehi sattahi dhammehi saṅgahitaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10231]="*Paccuddhāro katihi dhammehi saṅgahito?**How many things is relinquishment grouped with?*";
P_HTM[10232]="*Paccuddhāro tīhi dhammehi saṅgahito—**With three things:*";
P_HTM[10233]="*saṅghāṭiyā, uttarāsaṅgena, antaravāsakena.**the outer robe, the upper robe, and the sarong.*";
P_HTM[10234]="*Adhiṭṭhānaṃ katihi dhammehi saṅgahitaṃ?**How many things is determining grouped with?*";
P_HTM[10235]="*Adhiṭṭhānaṃ tīhi dhammehi saṅgahitaṃ—**With three things:*";
P_HTM[10236]="*saṅghāṭiyā, uttarāsaṅgena, antaravāsakena.**the outer robe, the upper robe, and the sarong.*";
P_HTM[10237]="*Atthāro katihi dhammehi saṅgahito?**How many things is doing the robe-making procedure grouped with?*";
P_HTM[10238]="*Atthāro ekena dhammena saṅgahito—**With one thing:*";
P_HTM[10239]="*vacībhedena.**breaking into speech.*";
P_HTM[10240]="*Kathinassa kati mūlāni, kati vatthūni, kati bhūmiyo?**How many roots does the robe-making procedure have, how many bases, and how many grounds?*";
P_HTM[10241]="*Kathinassa ekaṃ mūlaṃ—**The robe-making procedure has one root:*";
P_HTM[10242]="*saṅgho;**the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[10243]="*tīṇi vatthūni—**It has three subjects:*";
P_HTM[10244]="*saṅghāṭi, uttarāsaṅgo, antaravāsako;**the outer robe, the upper robe, and the sarong.*";
P_HTM[10245]="*cha bhūmiyo—**It has six grounds:*";
P_HTM[10246]="*khomaṃ, kappāsikaṃ, koseyyaṃ, kambalaṃ, sāṇaṃ, bhaṅgaṃ.**linen, cotton, silk, wool, sunn hemp, and hemp.*";
P_HTM[10247]="*Kathinassa ko ādi, kiṃ majjhe, kiṃ pariyosānaṃ?**What is the beginning, the middle, and the end of the robe-making procedure?*";
P_HTM[10248]="*Kathinassa pubbakaraṇaṃ ādi, kriyā majjhe, atthāro pariyosānaṃ.**The prior duties are the beginning, doing it is the middle, the robe-making procedure is the end.*";
P_HTM[10249]="*Katihaṅgehi samannāgato puggalo abhabbo kathinaṃ attharituṃ?**When a person has how many qualities, are they unable to do the robe-making procedure?*";
P_HTM[10250]="*Katihaṅgehi samannāgato puggalo bhabbo kathinaṃ attharituṃ?**When a person has how many qualities, are they able to do the robe-making procedure?*";
P_HTM[10251]="*Aṭṭhahaṅgehi samannāgato puggalo abhabbo kathinaṃ attharituṃ.**A person who has eight qualities is unable to do the robe-making procedure.*";
P_HTM[10252]="*Aṭṭhahaṅgehi samannāgato puggalo bhabbo kathinaṃ attharituṃ.**A person who has eight qualities is able to do the robe-making procedure.*";
P_HTM[10253]="*Katamehi aṭṭhahaṅgehi samannāgato puggalo abhabbo kathinaṃ attharituṃ?**What are the eight qualities of a person who is unable to do the robe-making procedure?*";
P_HTM[10254]="*Pubbakaraṇaṃ na jānāti, paccuddhāraṃ na jānāti, adhiṭṭhānaṃ na jānāti, atthāraṃ na jānāti, mātikaṃ na jānāti, palibodhaṃ na jānāti, uddhāraṃ na jānāti, ānisaṃsaṃ na jānāti—**They do not know the prior duties, relinquishment, determining, the robe-making procedure, the summaries, the obstacles, the ending of the robe-making season, or the benefits.*";
P_HTM[10255]="*imehi aṭṭhahaṅgehi samannāgato puggalo abhabbo kathinaṃ attharituṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10256]="*Katamehi aṭṭhahaṅgehi samannāgato puggalo bhabbo kathinaṃ attharituṃ?**What are the eight qualities of a person who is able to do the robe-making procedure?*";
P_HTM[10257]="*Pubbakaraṇaṃ jānāti, paccuddhāraṃ jānāti, adhiṭṭhānaṃ jānāti, atthāraṃ jānāti, mātikaṃ jānāti, palibodhaṃ jānāti, uddhāraṃ jānāti, ānisaṃsaṃ jānāti—**They know the prior duties, relinquishment, determining, the robe-making procedure, the summaries, the obstacles, the ending of the robe-making season, and the benefits.*";
P_HTM[10258]="*imehi aṭṭhahaṅgehi samannāgato puggalo bhabbo kathinaṃ attharituṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10259]="*Katinaṃ puggalānaṃ kathinatthārā na ruhanti?**For how many kinds of people is the robe-making procedure not effective?*";
P_HTM[10260]="*Katinaṃ puggalānaṃ kathinatthārā ruhanti?**For how many kinds of people is the robe-making procedure effective?*";
P_HTM[10261]="*Tiṇṇaṃ puggalānaṃ kathinatthārā na ruhanti.**It is not effective for three kinds of people.*";
P_HTM[10262]="*Tiṇṇaṃ puggalānaṃ kathinatthārā ruhanti.**It is effective for three kinds of people.*";
P_HTM[10263]="*Katamesaṃ tiṇṇaṃ puggalānaṃ kathinatthārā na ruhanti?**For which three kinds of people is it not effective?*";
P_HTM[10264]="*Nissīmaṭṭho anumodati, anumodento na vācaṃ bhindati, vācaṃ bhindanto na paraṃ viññāpeti—**For one who expresses their appreciation outside the monastic boundary; for one who does not express their appreciation verbally; for one who expresses it verbally, but no one hears it.*";
P_HTM[10265]="*imesaṃ tiṇṇaṃ puggalānaṃ kathinatthārā na ruhanti.* **";
P_HTM[10266]="*Katamesaṃ tiṇṇaṃ puggalānaṃ kathinatthārā ruhanti?**For which three kinds of people is it effective?*";
P_HTM[10267]="*Sīmaṭṭho anumodati, anumodento vācaṃ bhindati, vācaṃ bhindanto paraṃ viññāpeti—**For one who expresses their appreciation within the monastic boundary; for one who expresses their appreciation verbally; for one who expresses it verbally and another hears it.*";
P_HTM[10268]="*imesaṃ tiṇṇaṃ puggalānaṃ kathinatthārā ruhanti.* **";
P_HTM[10269]="*Kati kathinatthārā na ruhanti?**How many kinds of robe-making procedures are invalid?*";
P_HTM[10270]="*Kati kathinatthārā ruhanti?**How many kinds of robe-making procedures are valid?*";
P_HTM[10271]="*Tayo kathinatthārā na ruhanti.**Three kinds of robe-making procedures are invalid.*";
P_HTM[10272]="*Tayo kathinatthārā ruhanti.**Three kinds of robe-making procedures are valid.*";
P_HTM[10273]="*Katame tayo kathinatthārā na ruhanti?**What are the three kinds of robe-making procedures that are invalid?*";
P_HTM[10274]="*Vatthuvipannañceva hoti, kālavipannañca, karaṇavipannañca—**The subject fails; the timing fails; the making fails.*";
P_HTM[10275]="*ime tayo kathinatthārā na ruhanti.* **";
P_HTM[10276]="*Katame tayo kathinatthārā ruhanti?**What are the three kinds of robe-making procedures that are valid?*";
P_HTM[10277]="*Vatthusampannañceva hoti, kālasampannañca, karaṇasampannañca—**The subject succeeds; the timing succeeds; the making succeeds.*";
P_HTM[10278]="*ime tayo kathinatthārā ruhanti.* **";
P_HTM[10279]="*4. Kathinādijānitabbavibhāga**4. The details on what is to be known about the robe-making procedure, etc.*";
P_HTM[10280]="*Kathinaṃ jānitabbaṃ, kathinatthāro jānitabbo, kathinassa atthāramāso jānitabbo, kathinassa atthāravipatti jānitabbā, kathinassa atthārasampatti jānitabbā, nimittakammaṃ jānitabbaṃ, parikathā jānitabbā, kukkukataṃ jānitabbaṃ, sannidhi jānitabbā, nissaggiyaṃ jānitabbaṃ.**The robe-making ceremony is to be known; the robe-making procedure is to be known; the month of the robe-making procedure is to be known; failure of the robe-making procedure is to be known; success of the robe-making procedure is to be known; the giving of an indication is to be known; a hint is to be known; borrowing is to be known; storing is to be known; relinquishment is to be known.*";
P_HTM[10281]="*Kathinaṃ jānitabbanti**“The robe-making ceremony is to be known”:*";
P_HTM[10282]="*tesaññeva dhammānaṃ saṅgaho samavāyo nāmaṃ nāmakammaṃ nāmadheyyaṃ nirutti byañjanaṃ abhilāpo yadidaṃ kathinanti.**the robe-making ceremony is the grouping and coming together of those things, their name, appellation, label, expression, wording, designation.*";
P_HTM[10283]="*Kathinassa atthāramāso jānitabboti**“The month of the robe-making procedure is to be known”:*";
P_HTM[10284]="*vassānassa pacchimo māso jānitabbo.**the last month of the rainy season.*";
P_HTM[10285]="*Kathinassa atthāravipatti jānitabbāti**“Failure of the robe-making procedure is to be known”:*";
P_HTM[10286]="*catuvīsatiyā ākārehi kathinassa atthāravipatti jānitabbā.**the robe-making procedure fails in twenty-four ways.*";
P_HTM[10287]="*Kathinassa atthārasampatti jānitabbāti**“Success of the robe-making procedure is to be known”:*";
P_HTM[10288]="*sattarasahi ākārehi kathinassa atthārasampatti jānitabbā.**The robe-making procedure is successful through seventeen aspects.*";
P_HTM[10289]="*Nimittakammaṃ jānitabbanti**“The giving of an indication is to be known”:*";
P_HTM[10290]="*nimittaṃ karoti iminā dussena kathinaṃ attharissāmīti.**one makes an indication, thinking, “I will do the robe-making procedure with this cloth.”*";
P_HTM[10291]="*Parikathā jānitabbāti**“A hint is to be known”:*";
P_HTM[10292]="*parikathaṃ karoti imāya parikathāya kathinadussaṃ nibbattessāmīti.**one gives a hint, thinking, “With this hint, I will make a cloth for the robe-making procedure appear.”*";
P_HTM[10293]="*Kukkukataṃ jānitabbanti**“Borrowing is to be known”:*";
P_HTM[10294]="*anādiyadānaṃ jānitabbaṃ.**taking what has not been given.*";
P_HTM[10295]="*Sannidhi jānitabbāti**“Storing is to be known”:*";
P_HTM[10296]="*dve sannidhiyo jānitabbā—karaṇasannidhi vā nicayasannidhi vā.**there is storing for the purpose of making and storing for the purpose of accumulation.*";
P_HTM[10297]="*Nissaggiyaṃ jānitabbanti**“Relinquishment is to be known”:*";
P_HTM[10298]="*kariyamāne aruṇaṃ uṭṭhahati.**dawn arrives while it is being made.*";
P_HTM[10299]="*Kathinatthāro jānitabboti**“The robe-making procedure is to be known”:*";
P_HTM[10300]="*sace saṅghassa kathinadussaṃ uppannaṃ hoti, saṅghena kathaṃ paṭipajjitabbaṃ, atthārakena kathaṃ paṭipajjitabbaṃ, anumodakena kathaṃ paṭipajjitabbaṃ.**If cloth has been given to the Sangha for the robe-making procedure, what should the Sangha do? What should the one who performs the robe-making procedure do? What should one who expresses their appreciation do?*";
P_HTM[10301]="*Saṅghena ñattidutiyena kammena kathinatthārakassa bhikkhuno dātabbaṃ, tena kathinatthārakena bhikkhunā tadaheva dhovitvā vimajjitvā vicāretvā chinditvā sibbetvā rajitvā kappaṃ katvā kathinaṃ attharitabbaṃ.**The Sangha should give the cloth, through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and one announcement, to the monk who is performing the robe-making procedure. The monk who is performing the robe-making procedure should wash the cloth, iron it, plan it, cut it, sew it, dye it, mark it, and then do the robe-making procedure.*";
P_HTM[10302]="*Sace saṅghāṭiyā kathinaṃ attharitukāmo hoti, porāṇikā saṅghāṭi paccuddharitabbā, navā saṅghāṭi adhiṭṭhātabbā.**If he wishes to do the robe-making procedure with an outer robe, he should relinquish his old outer robe and then determine the new outer robe.*";
P_HTM[10303]="*Imāya saṅghāṭiyā kathinaṃ attharāmīti vācā bhinditabbā.**He should then say, “I do the robe-making procedure with this outer robe.”*";
P_HTM[10304]="*Sace uttarāsaṅgena kathinaṃ attharitukāmo hoti, porāṇako uttarāsaṅgo paccuddharitabbo, navo uttarāsaṅgo adhiṭṭhātabbo.**If he wishes to do the robe-making procedure with an upper robe, he should relinquish his old outer robe and then determine the new outer robe.*";
P_HTM[10305]="*Iminā uttarāsaṅgena kathinaṃ attharāmīti vācā bhinditabbā.**He should then say, “I do the robe-making procedure with this upper robe.”*";
P_HTM[10306]="*Sace antaravāsakena kathinaṃ attharitukāmo hoti, porāṇako antaravāsako paccuddharitabbo, navo antaravāsako adhiṭṭhātabbo.**If he wishes to do the robe-making procedure with a sarong, he should relinquish his old outer robe and then determine the new outer robe.*";
P_HTM[10307]="*Iminā antaravāsakena kathinaṃ attharāmīti vācā bhinditabbā.**He should then say, “I do the robe-making procedure with this sarong.”*";
P_HTM[10308]="*Tena kathinatthārakena bhikkhunā saṅghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—**After approaching the Sangha, that monk who is performing the robe-making procedure should put his upper robe over one shoulder, raise his joined palms, and say:*";
P_HTM[10309]="*“atthataṃ, bhante, saṅghassa kathinaṃ, dhammiko kathinatthāro, anumodathā”ti.**“Venerable Sir, the Sangha’s robe-making procedure has been done. The robe-making procedure is legitimate. Please express your appreciation.”*";
P_HTM[10310]="*Tehi anumodakehi bhikkhūhi ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—**The monks who are expressing their appreciation should put their upper robe over one shoulder, raise their joined palms, and say:*";
P_HTM[10311]="*“atthataṃ, āvuso, saṅghassa kathinaṃ, dhammiko kathinatthāro, anumodāmā”ti.**“The Sangha’s robe-making procedure has been done. The robe-making procedure is legitimate. We express our appreciation.”*";
P_HTM[10312]="*Tena kathinatthārakena bhikkhunā sambahule bhikkhū upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassu vacanīyā—**After approaching several monks, that monk who is performing the robe-making procedure should put his upper robe over one shoulder, raise his joined palms, and say:*";
P_HTM[10313]="*“atthataṃ, bhante, saṅghassa kathinaṃ, dhammiko kathinatthāro, anumodathā”ti.**“Venerable Sir, the Sangha’s robe-making procedure has been done. The robe-making procedure is legitimate. Please express your appreciation.”*";
P_HTM[10314]="*Tehi anumodakehi bhikkhūhi ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—**The monks who are expressing their appreciation should put their upper robe over one shoulder, raise their joined palms, and say:*";
P_HTM[10315]="*“atthataṃ, āvuso, saṅghassa kathinaṃ, dhammiko kathinatthāro anumodāmā”ti.**“The Sangha’s robe-making procedure has been done. The robe-making procedure is legitimate. We express our appreciation.”*";
P_HTM[10316]="*Tena kathinatthārakena bhikkhunā ekaṃ bhikkhuṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—**After approaching a single monk, that monk who is performing the robe-making procedure should put his upper robe over one shoulder, raise his joined palms, and say:*";
P_HTM[10317]="*“atthataṃ, āvuso, saṅghassa kathinaṃ, dhammiko kathinatthāro, anumodāhī”ti.**“The Sangha’s robe-making procedure has been done. The robe-making procedure is legitimate. Please express your appreciation.”*";
P_HTM[10318]="*Tena anumodakena bhikkhunā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—**The monk who is expressing his appreciation should put his upper robe over one shoulder, raise his joined palms, and say:*";
P_HTM[10319]="*“atthataṃ, āvuso, saṅghassa kathinaṃ, dhammiko kathinatthāro, anumodāmī”ti.**“The Sangha’s robe-making procedure has been done. The robe-making procedure is legitimate. I express my appreciation.”*";
P_HTM[10320]="*5. Puggalassevakathinatthāra**5. The robe-making procedure for an individual*";
P_HTM[10321]="*Saṅgho kathinaṃ attharati, gaṇo kathinaṃ attharati, puggalo kathinaṃ attharatīti?**“Does the Sangha do the robe-making ceremony; does a group do the robe-making ceremony; does an individual do the robe-making ceremony?”*";
P_HTM[10322]="*Na saṅgho kathinaṃ attharati, na gaṇo kathinaṃ attharati, puggalo kathinaṃ attharatīti.**“The Sangha does not do the robe-making ceremony, a group does not do the robe-making ceremony, but an individual does the robe-making ceremony.”*";
P_HTM[10323]="*Hañci na saṅgho kathinaṃ attharati, na gaṇo kathinaṃ attharati, puggalo kathinaṃ attharati.**If the Sangha does not do the robe-making ceremony, nor a group, but an individual does, then,*";
P_HTM[10324]="*Saṅghassa anatthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ, gaṇassa anatthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ, puggalassa atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ.**the Sangha has not done the robe-making ceremony, a group has not done the robe-making ceremony, but an individual has done the robe-making ceremony.*";
P_HTM[10325]="*Saṅgho pātimokkhaṃ uddisati gaṇo pātimokkhaṃ uddisati puggalo pātimokkhaṃ uddisatīti?**“Does the Sangha recite the Monastic Code; does a group recite the Monastic Code; does an individual recites the Monastic Code?”*";
P_HTM[10326]="*Na saṅgho pātimokkhaṃ uddisati, na gaṇo pātimokkhaṃ uddisati, puggalo pātimokkhaṃ uddisatīti.**“The Sangha does not recite the Monastic Code, a group does not recite the Monastic Code, but an individual recites the Monastic Code.”*";
P_HTM[10327]="*Hañci na saṅgho pātimokkhaṃ uddisati, na gaṇo pātimokkhaṃ uddisati, puggalo pātimokkhaṃ uddisati.**If the Sangha does not recite the Monastic Code, nor a group, but an individual does, then,*";
P_HTM[10328]="*Saṅghassa anuddiṭṭhaṃ hoti pātimokkhaṃ, gaṇassa anuddiṭṭhaṃ hoti pātimokkhaṃ, puggalassa uddiṭṭhaṃ hoti pātimokkhaṃ.**the Sangha has not recited the Monastic Code, a group has not recited it, but an individual has.*";
P_HTM[10329]="*Saṅghassa sāmaggiyā gaṇassa sāmaggiyā puggalassa uddesā saṅghassa uddiṭṭhaṃ hoti pātimokkhaṃ, gaṇassa uddiṭṭhaṃ hoti pātimokkhaṃ, puggalassa uddiṭṭhaṃ hoti pātimokkhaṃ.**“When an individual recites to a united Sangha, to a united group, then the Monastic Code has been recited by the Sangha, by the group, and by the individual.*";
P_HTM[10330]="*Evameva na saṅgho kathinaṃ attharati, na gaṇo kathinaṃ attharati, puggalo kathinaṃ attharati.**It is in this way that the Sangha does not do the robe-making ceremony, nor a group, but an individual does.*";
P_HTM[10331]="*Saṅghassa anumodanāya gaṇassa anumodanāya puggalassa atthārā saṅghassa atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ, gaṇassa atthataṃ hoti kathinaṃ, puggalassa atthataṃ hoti kathinanti.**When an individual does the robe-making procedure, and the Sangha expresses its appreciation, the group expresses its appreciation, then the robe-making procedure has been done by the Sangha, by the group, and by the individual.”*";
P_HTM[10332]="*6. Palibodhapañhābyākaraṇa**6. Questions and answers regarding the obstacles*";
P_HTM[10333]="*Pakkamanantiko kathinuddhāro,**“The robe-making season comes to an end when one departs from the monastery.*";
P_HTM[10334]="*Vutto ādiccabandhunā;**So said the Kinsman of the Sun.*";
P_HTM[10335]="*Etañca tāhaṃ pucchāmi,**And about this I ask you:*";
P_HTM[10336]="*Katamo palibodho paṭhamaṃ chijjati.**Which obstacle is removed first?”*";
P_HTM[10337]="*Pakkamanantiko kathinuddhāro,**“The robe-making season comes to an end when one departs from the monastery.*";
P_HTM[10338]="*Vutto ādiccabandhunā;**So said the Kinsman of the Sun.*";
P_HTM[10339]="*Etañca tāhaṃ vissajjissaṃ,**And about this I answer you:*";
P_HTM[10340]="*Cīvarapalibodho paṭhamaṃ chijjati;**The robe obstacle is removed first.*";
P_HTM[10341]="*Tassa saha bahisīmagamanā,**The monastery obstacle is removed when one is outside the monastic boundary.”*";
P_HTM[10342]="*Āvāsapalibodho chijjati.* **";
P_HTM[10343]="*Niṭṭhānantiko kathinuddhāro,**“The robe-making season comes to an end when the robe is finished.*";
P_HTM[10344]="*Vutto ādiccabandhunā;**So said the Kinsman of the Sun.*";
P_HTM[10345]="*Etañca tāhaṃ pucchāmi,**And about this I ask you:*";
P_HTM[10346]="*Katamo palibodho paṭhamaṃ chijjati.**Which obstacle is removed first?”*";
P_HTM[10347]="*Niṭṭhānantiko kathinuddhāro,**“The Sun that the robe-making season comes to an end when the robe is finished.*";
P_HTM[10348]="*Vutto ādiccabandhunā;**So said the Kinsman of the Sun.*";
P_HTM[10349]="*Etañca tāhaṃ vissajjissaṃ,**And about this I answer you:*";
P_HTM[10350]="*Āvāsapalibodho paṭhamaṃ chijjati;**The monastery obstacle is removed first.*";
P_HTM[10351]="*Cīvare niṭṭhite cīvarapalibodho chijjati.**The robe obstacle is removed when the robe is finished.”*";
P_HTM[10352]="*Sanniṭṭhānantiko kathinuddhāro,**“The robe-making season comes to an end when he makes that decision.*";
P_HTM[10353]="*Vutto ādiccabandhunā;**So said the Kinsman of the Sun.*";
P_HTM[10354]="*Etañca tāhaṃ pucchāmi,**And about this I ask you:*";
P_HTM[10355]="*Katamo palibodho paṭhamaṃ chijjati.**Which obstacle is removed first?”*";
P_HTM[10356]="*Sanniṭṭhānantiko kathinuddhāro,**“The robe-making season comes to an end when he makes that decision.*";
P_HTM[10357]="*Vutto ādiccabandhunā;**So said the Kinsman of the Sun.*";
P_HTM[10358]="*Etañca tāhaṃ vissajjissaṃ,**And about this I answer you:*";
P_HTM[10359]="*Dve palibodhā apubbaṃ acarimaṃ chijjanti.**The two obstacles are removed simultaneously.”*";
P_HTM[10360]="*Nāsanantiko kathinuddhāro,**“The robe-making season comes to an end when the robe-cloth is lost.*";
P_HTM[10361]="*Vutto ādiccabandhunā;**So said the Kinsman of the Sun.*";
P_HTM[10362]="*Etañca tāhaṃ pucchāmi,**And about this I ask you:*";
P_HTM[10363]="*Katamo palibodho paṭhamaṃ chijjati.**Which obstacle is removed first?”*";
P_HTM[10364]="*Nāsanantiko kathinuddhāro,**“The robe-making season comes to an end when the robe-cloth is lost.*";
P_HTM[10365]="*Vutto ādiccabandhunā;**So said the Kinsman of the Sun.*";
P_HTM[10366]="*Etañca tāhaṃ vissajjissaṃ,**And about this I answer you:*";
P_HTM[10367]="*Āvāsapalibodho paṭhamaṃ chijjati;**The monastery obstacle is removed first.*";
P_HTM[10368]="*Cīvare naṭṭhe cīvarapalibodho chijjati.**The robe obstacle is removed when the robe is lost.”*";
P_HTM[10369]="*Savanantiko kathinuddhāro,**“The robe-making season comes to an end when he hears about the end of the robe-making season.*";
P_HTM[10370]="*Vutto ādiccabandhunā;**So said the Kinsman of the Sun.*";
P_HTM[10371]="*Etañca tāhaṃ pucchāmi,**And about this I ask you:*";
P_HTM[10372]="*Katamo palibodho paṭhamaṃ chijjati.**Which obstacle is removed first?”*";
P_HTM[10373]="*Savanantiko kathinuddhāro,**“The robe-making season comes to an end when he hears about the end of the robe-making season.*";
P_HTM[10374]="*Vutto ādiccabandhunā;**So said the Kinsman of the Sun.*";
P_HTM[10375]="*Etañca tāhaṃ vissajjissaṃ,**And about this I answer you:*";
P_HTM[10376]="*Cīvarapalibodho paṭhamaṃ chijjati;**The robe obstacle is removed first.*";
P_HTM[10377]="*Tassa saha savanena,**The monastery obstacle is removed when one hears about the end of the robe-making season.”*";
P_HTM[10378]="*Āvāsapalibodho chijjati.* **";
P_HTM[10379]="*Āsāvacchediko kathinuddhāro,**“The robe-making season comes to an end when the expectation is thwarted.*";
P_HTM[10380]="*Vutto ādiccabandhunā;**So said the Kinsman of the Sun.*";
P_HTM[10381]="*Etañca tāhaṃ pucchāmi,**And about this I ask you:*";
P_HTM[10382]="*Katamo palibodho paṭhamaṃ chijjati.**Which obstacle is removed first?”*";
P_HTM[10383]="*Āsāvacchediko kathinuddhāro,**“The robe-making season comes to an end when the expectation is thwarted.*";
P_HTM[10384]="*Vutto ādiccabandhunā;**So said the Kinsman of the Sun.*";
P_HTM[10385]="*Etañca tāhaṃ vissajjissaṃ,**And about this I answer you:*";
P_HTM[10386]="*Āvāsapalibodho paṭhamaṃ chijjati;**The monastery obstacle is removed first.*";
P_HTM[10387]="*Cīvarāsāya upacchinnāya cīvarapalibodho chijjati.**The robe obstacle is removed when the expectation of more robe-cloth is thwarted.”*";
P_HTM[10388]="*Sīmātikkamanantiko kathinuddhāro,**“The robe-making season comes to an end while he is outside the monastic boundary.*";
P_HTM[10389]="*Vutto ādiccabandhunā;**So said the Kinsman of the Sun.*";
P_HTM[10390]="*Etañca tāhaṃ pucchāmi,**And about this I ask you:*";
P_HTM[10391]="*Katamo palibodho paṭhamaṃ chijjati.**Which obstacle is removed first?”*";
P_HTM[10392]="*Sīmātikkamanantiko kathinuddhāro,**“The robe-making season comes to an end while he is outside the monastic boundary.*";
P_HTM[10393]="*Vutto ādiccabandhunā;**So said the Kinsman of the Sun.*";
P_HTM[10394]="*Etañca tāhaṃ vissajjissaṃ,**And about this I answer you:*";
P_HTM[10395]="*Cīvarapalibodho paṭhamaṃ chijjati;**The robe obstacle is removed first.*";
P_HTM[10396]="*Tassa bahisīme āvāsapalibodho chijjati.**The monastery obstacle is removed when one is outside the monastic boundary.”*";
P_HTM[10397]="*Sahubbhāro kathinuddhāro,**“The robe-making season comes to an end together.*";
P_HTM[10398]="*Vutto ādiccabandhunā;**So said the Kinsman of the Sun.*";
P_HTM[10399]="*Etañca tāhaṃ pucchāmi,**And about this I ask you:*";
P_HTM[10400]="*Katamo palibodho paṭhamaṃ chijjati.**Which obstacle is removed first?”*";
P_HTM[10401]="*Sahubbhāro kathinuddhāro,**“The robe-making season comes to an end together.*";
P_HTM[10402]="*Vutto ādiccabandhunā;**So said the Kinsman of the Sun.*";
P_HTM[10403]="*Etañca tāhaṃ vissajjissaṃ,**And about this I answer you:*";
P_HTM[10404]="*Dve palibodhā apubbaṃ acarimaṃ chijjantīti.**The two obstacles are removed simultaneously.”*";
P_HTM[10405]="*Kati kathinuddhārā saṅghādhīnā?**How many kinds of endings of the robe-making season are dependent on the Sangha?*";
P_HTM[10406]="*Kati kathinuddhārā puggalādhīnā?**How many kinds of endings of the robe-making season are dependent on an individual?*";
P_HTM[10407]="*Kati kathinuddhārā neva saṅghādhīnā na puggalādhīnā?**How many kinds of endings of the robe-making season are dependent neither on the Sangha nor on an individual?*";
P_HTM[10408]="*Eko kathinuddhāro saṅghādhīno—**One kind of ending of the robe-making season is dependent on the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[10409]="*antarubbhāro.**when the robe-making season comes to an end midway.*";
P_HTM[10410]="*Cattāro kathinuddhārā puggalādhīnā—**Four kinds of endings of the robe-making season are dependent on an individual:*";
P_HTM[10411]="*pakkamanantiko, niṭṭhānantiko, sanniṭṭhānantiko, sīmātikkamanantiko.**when one departs from the monastery, when the robe is finished, when one makes a decision, and when one is outside the monastic boundary.*";
P_HTM[10412]="*Cattāro kathinuddhārā neva saṅghādhīnā na puggalādhīnā—**Four kinds of endings of the robe-making season are dependent neither on the Sangha nor on an individual:*";
P_HTM[10413]="*nāsanantiko, savanantiko, āsāvacchediko, sahubbhāro.**when the robe-cloth is lost, when he hears about the end of the robe-making season, when an expectation of more robe-cloth is thwarted, and when the robe-making season comes to an end together.*";
P_HTM[10414]="*Kati kathinuddhārā antosīmāya uddhariyyanti?**How many kinds of endings of the robe-making season happen within the monastic boundary?*";
P_HTM[10415]="*Kati kathinuddhārā bahisīmāya uddhariyyanti?**How many kinds of endings of the robe-making season happen outside the monastery boundary?*";
P_HTM[10416]="*Kati kathinuddhārā siyā antosīmāya uddhariyyanti siyā bahisīmāya uddhariyyanti?**How many kinds of endings of the robe-making season may happen within or outside the monastic boundary?*";
P_HTM[10417]="*Dve kathinuddhārā antosīmāya uddhariyyanti—**Two kinds of endings of the robe-making season happen within the monastic boundary:*";
P_HTM[10418]="*antarubbhāro, sahubbhāro.**when the robe-making season comes to an end midway, and when the robe-making season comes to an end together.*";
P_HTM[10419]="*Tayo kathinuddhārā bahisīmāya uddhariyyanti—**Three kinds of endings of the robe-making season happen outside the monastic boundary:*";
P_HTM[10420]="*pakkamanantiko, savanantiko, sīmātikkamanantiko.**when one departs from the monastery, when one hears about the end of the robe-making season, and when one is outside the monastic boundary.*";
P_HTM[10421]="*Cattāro kathinuddhārā siyā antosīmāya uddhariyyanti siyā bahisīmāya uddhariyyanti—**Four kinds of endings of the robe-making season may happen within or outside the monastic boundary?*";
P_HTM[10422]="*niṭṭhānantiko, sanniṭṭhānantiko, nāsanantiko, āsāvacchediko.**when the robe is finished, when he makes a decision, when the robe-cloth is lost, and when an expectation of more robe-cloth is thwarted.*";
P_HTM[10423]="*Kati kathinuddhārā ekuppādā ekanirodhā?**How many kinds of endings of the robe-making season arise together and end together?*";
P_HTM[10424]="*Kati kathinuddhārā ekuppādā nānānirodhā?**How many kinds of endings of the robe-making season arise together and end separately?*";
P_HTM[10425]="*Dve kathinuddhārā ekuppādā ekanirodhā—**“Two kinds of endings of the robe-making season arise together and end together:*";
P_HTM[10426]="*antarubbhāro, sahubbhāro.**when the robe-making season comes to an end midway, and when the robe-making season comes to an end together.*";
P_HTM[10427]="*Avasesā kathinuddhārā ekuppādā nānānirodhāti.**The rest of endings of the robe-making season arise together but end separately.”*";
P_HTM[10428]="*Kathinabhedo niṭṭhito.**The sub-division on the robe-making procedure is finished.*";
P_HTM[10429]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[10430]="*Kassa kinti pannarasa,**“Who has, how, fifteen,*";
P_HTM[10431]="*dhammā nidānahetu ca;**Things, source, and cause;*";
P_HTM[10432]="*Paccayasaṅgahamūlā,**Condition, grouped with, roots,*";
P_HTM[10433]="*ādi ca atthārapuggalā.**And beginning, persons who do the robe-making procedure.*";
P_HTM[10434]="*Tiṇṇaṃ tayo jānitabbaṃ,**For three, three, to be known,*";
P_HTM[10435]="*atthāraṃ uddesena ca;**The robe-making procedure, and with recitation;*";
P_HTM[10436]="*Palibodhādhinā sīmāya,**Obstacles, dependent on, with boundary,*";
P_HTM[10437]="*uppādanirodhena cāti.**And with arise and end.”*";
P_HTM[10438]="*124. 1. Anissitavagga **124.  1. The sub*";
P_HTM[10439]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[10440]="*Atha kho āyasmā upāli yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**Venerable Upāli went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down,*";
P_HTM[10441]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā upāli bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**and said,*";
P_HTM[10442]="*“katihi nu kho, bhante, aṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā yāvajīvaṃ nānissitena vatthabban”ti?**“Venerable Sir, when a monk has how many qualities, should he live with formal support for life?”*";
P_HTM[10443]="*“Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā yāvajīvaṃ nānissitena vatthabbaṃ.**“When he has five qualities, Upāli:*";
P_HTM[10444]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10445]="*Uposathaṃ na jānāti, uposathakammaṃ na jānāti, pātimokkhaṃ na jānāti, pātimokkhuddesaṃ na jānāti, ūnapañcavasso hoti—**he does not know about the observance day; he does not know the observance-day procedure; he does not know the Monastic Code; he does not know the recitation of the Monastic Code; he has less than five years of seniority.*";
P_HTM[10446]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā yāvajīvaṃ nānissitena vatthabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10447]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā yāvajīvaṃ anissitena vatthabbaṃ.**But when a monk has five qualities, he may live without formal support for life:*";
P_HTM[10448]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10449]="*Uposathaṃ jānāti, uposathakammaṃ jānāti, pātimokkhaṃ jānāti, pātimokkhuddesaṃ jānāti, pañcavasso vā hoti atirekapañcavasso vā—**he knows about the observance day; he knows the observance-day procedure; he knows the Monastic Code; he knows the recitation of the Monastic Code; he has five or more years of seniority.*";
P_HTM[10450]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā yāvajīvaṃ anissitena vatthabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10451]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā yāvajīvaṃ nānissitena vatthabbaṃ.**When a monk has five other qualities, he should live with formal support for life:*";
P_HTM[10452]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10453]="*Pavāraṇaṃ na jānāti, pavāraṇākammaṃ na jānāti, pātimokkhaṃ na jānāti, pātimokkhuddesaṃ na jānāti, ūnapañcavasso hoti—**he does not know about the invitation day; he does not know the invitation-day procedure; he does not know the Monastic Code; he does not know the recitation of the Monastic Code; he has less than five years of seniority.*";
P_HTM[10454]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā yāvajīvaṃ nānissitena vatthabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10455]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā yāvajīvaṃ anissitena vatthabbaṃ.**But when a monk has five qualities, he may live without formal support for life:*";
P_HTM[10456]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10457]="*Pavāraṇaṃ jānāti, pavāraṇākammaṃ jānāti, pātimokkhaṃ jānāti, pātimokkhuddesaṃ jānāti, pañcavasso vā hoti atirekapañcavasso vā—**he knows about the invitation day; he knows the invitation-day procedure; he knows the Monastic Code; he knows the recitation of the Monastic Code; he has five or more years of seniority.*";
P_HTM[10458]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā yāvajīvaṃ anissitena vatthabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10459]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā yāvajīvaṃ nānissitena vatthabbaṃ.**When a monk has five other qualities, he should live with formal support for life:*";
P_HTM[10460]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10461]="*Āpattānāpattiṃ na jānāti, lahukagarukaṃ āpattiṃ na jānāti, sāvasesānavasesaṃ āpattiṃ na jānāti, duṭṭhullāduṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ na jānāti, ūnapañcavasso hoti—**he does not know the offenses and non-offenses; he does not know the light and heavy offenses; he does not know the curable and incurable offenses; he does not know the grave and minor offenses; he has less than five years of seniority.*";
P_HTM[10462]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā yāvajīvaṃ nānissitena vatthabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10463]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā yāvajīvaṃ anissitena vatthabbaṃ.**But when a monk has five qualities, he may live without formal support for life:*";
P_HTM[10464]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10465]="*Āpattānāpattiṃ jānāti, lahukagarukaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, sāvasesānavasesaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, duṭṭhullāduṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, pañcavasso vā hoti atirekapañcavasso vā—**he knows the offenses and non-offenses; he knows the light and heavy offenses; he knows the curable and incurable offenses; he knows the grave and minor offenses; he has five or more years of seniority.”*";
P_HTM[10466]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā yāvajīvaṃ anissitena vatthabbaṃ”.* **";
P_HTM[10467]="*“Katihi nu kho, bhante, aṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā na upasampādetabbaṃ, na nissayo dātabbo, na sāmaṇero upaṭṭhāpetabbo”ti?**“Sir, when a monk has how many qualities, should he not give the full ordination or formal support, nor have a novice monk attend on him?”*";
P_HTM[10468]="*“Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā na upasampādetabbaṃ, na nissayo dātabbo, na sāmaṇero upaṭṭhāpetabbo.**“When he has five qualities:*";
P_HTM[10469]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10470]="*Na paṭibalo hoti antevāsiṃ vā saddhivihāriṃ vā gilānaṃ upaṭṭhātuṃ vā upaṭṭhāpetuṃ vā, anabhirataṃ vūpakāsetuṃ vā vūpakāsāpetuṃ vā, uppannaṃ kukkuccaṃ dhammato vinodetuṃ, abhidhamme vinetuṃ, abhivinaye vinetuṃ—**He’s not capable of three things in regard to a student: to nurse him or have him nursed when he’s sick; to send him away or have him sent away when he’s discontent with the spiritual life; and to use the Teaching to dispel anxiety. And he is not capable of training him in the Teaching; and he is not capable of training him in the Monastic Law.*";
P_HTM[10471]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā na upasampādetabbaṃ, na nissayo dātabbo, na sāmaṇero upaṭṭhāpetabbo.* **";
P_HTM[10472]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā upasampādetabbaṃ, nissayo dātabbo, sāmaṇero upaṭṭhāpetabbo.**But when a monk has five qualities, he may give the full ordination and formal support, and he may have a novice monk attend on him:*";
P_HTM[10473]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10474]="*Paṭibalo hoti antevāsiṃ vā saddhivihāriṃ vā gilānaṃ upaṭṭhātuṃ vā upaṭṭhāpetuṃ vā, anabhirataṃ vūpakāsetuṃ vā vūpakāsāpetuṃ vā, uppannaṃ kukkuccaṃ dhammato vinodetuṃ, abhidhamme vinetuṃ, abhivinaye vinetuṃ—**He’s capable of three things in regard to a student: to nurse him or have him nursed when he’s sick; to send him away or have him sent away when he’s discontent with the spiritual life; and to use the Teaching to dispel anxiety. And he is capable of training him in the Teaching; and he is capable of training him in the Monastic Law.*";
P_HTM[10475]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā upasampādetabbaṃ, nissayo dātabbo, sāmaṇero upaṭṭhāpetabbo.* **";
P_HTM[10476]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā na upasampādetabbaṃ, na nissayo dātabbo, na sāmaṇero upaṭṭhāpetabbo.**When a monk has five other qualities, he should not give the full ordination or formal support, nor have a novice monk attend on him:*";
P_HTM[10477]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10478]="*Na paṭibalo hoti antevāsiṃ vā saddhivihāriṃ vā abhisamācārikāya sikkhāya sikkhāpetuṃ, ādibrahmacāriyakāya sikkhāya vinetuṃ, adhisīle vinetuṃ, adhicitte vinetuṃ, adhipaññāya vinetuṃ—**He’s not capable of five things in regard to a student: to train him in good conduct; to train him in the basics of the spiritual life; to train him in the higher morality; to train him in the higher mind; to train him in the higher wisdom.*";
P_HTM[10479]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā na upasampādetabbaṃ, na nissayo dātabbo, na sāmaṇero upaṭṭhāpetabbo.* **";
P_HTM[10480]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā upasampādetabbaṃ, nissayo dātabbo, sāmaṇero upaṭṭhāpetabbo.**But when a monk has five qualities, he may give the full ordination and formal support, and he may have a novice monk attend on him:*";
P_HTM[10481]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10482]="*Paṭibalo hoti antevāsiṃ vā saddhivihāriṃ vā abhisamācārikāya sikkhāya sikkhāpetuṃ, ādibrahmacāriyakāya sikkhāya vinetuṃ, adhisīle vinetuṃ, adhicitte vinetuṃ, adhipaññāya vinetuṃ—**He’s capable of five things in regard to a student: to train him in good conduct; to train him in the basics of the spiritual life; to train him in the higher morality; to train him in the higher mind; to train him in the higher wisdom.”*";
P_HTM[10483]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā upasampādetabbaṃ, nissayo dātabbo, sāmaṇero upaṭṭhāpetabbo”ti.* **";
P_HTM[10484]="*“Katihi nu kho, bhante, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno kammaṃ kātabban”ti?**“Sir, when a monk has how many qualities, should a legal procedure be done against him?”*";
P_HTM[10485]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno kammaṃ kātabbaṃ.**“When he has five qualities:*";
P_HTM[10486]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10487]="*Alajjī ca hoti, bālo ca, apakatatto ca, micchādiṭṭhiko ca hoti, ājīvavipanno ca—**he is shameless, ignorant, and not a regular monk, and he has wrong view, and he has failed in livelihood.*";
P_HTM[10488]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno kammaṃ kātabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10489]="*“Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno kammaṃ kātabbaṃ.**When a monk has five other qualities, should a legal procedure be done against him:*";
P_HTM[10490]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10491]="*Adhisīle sīlavipanno hoti, ajjhācāre ācāravipanno hoti, atidiṭṭhiyā diṭṭhivipanno hoti, micchādiṭṭhiko ca hoti, ājīvavipanno ca—**he has failed in the higher morality; he has failed in conduct; he has failed in view; he has wrong view; and he has failed in livelihood.*";
P_HTM[10492]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno kammaṃ kātabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10493]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno kammaṃ kātabbaṃ.**When a monk has five other qualities, should a legal procedure be done against him:*";
P_HTM[10494]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10495]="*Kāyikena davena samannāgato hoti, vācasikena davena samannāgato hoti, kāyikavācasikena davena samannāgato hoti, micchādiṭṭhiko ca hoti, ājīvavipanno ca—**he is frivolous in bodily conduct; he is frivolous in verbal conduct; he is frivolous in bodily and verbal conduct; he has wrong view; and he has failed in livelihood.*";
P_HTM[10496]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno kammaṃ kātabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10497]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno kammaṃ kātabbaṃ.**When a monk has five other qualities, should a legal procedure be done against him:*";
P_HTM[10498]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10499]="*Kāyikena anācārena samannāgato hoti, vācasikena anācārena samannāgato hoti, kāyikavācasikena anācārena samannāgato hoti, micchādiṭṭhiko ca hoti, ājīvavipanno ca—**he is improperly behaved by body; he is improperly behaved by speech; he is improperly behaved by body and speech; he has wrong view; and he has failed in livelihood.*";
P_HTM[10500]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno kammaṃ kātabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10501]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno kammaṃ kātabbaṃ.**When a monk has five other qualities, should a legal procedure be done against him:*";
P_HTM[10502]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10503]="*Kāyikena upaghātikena samannāgato hoti, vācasikena upaghātikena samannāgato hoti, kāyikavācasikena upaghātikena samannāgato hoti, micchādiṭṭhiko ca hoti, ājīvavipanno ca—**his bodily conduct is harmful; his verbal conduct is harmful; his bodily and verbal conduct are harmful; he has wrong view; and he has failed in livelihood.*";
P_HTM[10504]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno kammaṃ kātabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10505]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno kammaṃ kātabbaṃ.**When a monk has five other qualities, should a legal procedure be done against him:*";
P_HTM[10506]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10507]="*Kāyikena micchājīvena samannāgato hoti, vācasikena micchājīvena samannāgato hoti, kāyikavācasikena micchājīvena samannāgato hoti, micchādiṭṭhiko ca hoti, ājīvavipanno ca—**he has wrong livelihood by body; he has wrong livelihood by speech; he has wrong livelihood by body and speech; he has wrong view; and he has failed in livelihood.*";
P_HTM[10508]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno kammaṃ kātabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10509]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno kammaṃ kātabbaṃ.**When a monk has five other qualities, should a legal procedure be done against him:*";
P_HTM[10510]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10511]="*Āpattiṃ āpanno kammakato upasampādeti, nissayaṃ deti, sāmaṇeraṃ upaṭṭhāpeti, bhikkhunovādakasammutiṃ sādiyati, sammatopi bhikkhuniyo ovadati—**if, after committing an offense and having a legal procedure done against him, he: gives the full ordination, [2] gives formal support, [3] has a novice monk attend on him, [4] he accepts being appointed as an instructor of the nuns; [5] he instructs the nuns, whether appointed or not.*";
P_HTM[10512]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno kammaṃ kātabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10513]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno kammaṃ kātabbaṃ.**When a monk has five other qualities, should a legal procedure be done against him:*";
P_HTM[10514]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10515]="*Yāya āpattiyā saṅghena kammaṃ kataṃ hoti taṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati, aññaṃ vā tādisikaṃ, tato vā pāpiṭṭhataraṃ, kammaṃ garahati, kammike garahati—**he commits the same offense for which the Sangha did the legal procedure against him; he commits an offense similar to the one for which the Sangha did the legal procedure against him; he commits an offense worse than the one for which the Sangha did the legal procedure against him; he criticizes the procedure; he criticizes those who did the procedure.*";
P_HTM[10516]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno kammaṃ kātabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10517]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno kammaṃ kātabbaṃ.**When a monk has five other qualities, should a legal procedure be done against him:*";
P_HTM[10518]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10519]="*Buddhassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, dhammassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, saṅghassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, micchādiṭṭhiko ca hoti, ājīvavipanno ca—**he disparages the Buddha; he disparages the Teaching; he disparages the Sangha; he has wrong view; and he has failed in livelihood.”*";
P_HTM[10520]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno kammaṃ kātabban”ti.* **";
P_HTM[10521]="*Anissitavaggo niṭṭhito paṭhamo.**The first sub-chapter on “without formal” support is finished.*";
P_HTM[10522]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[10523]="*Uposathaṃ pavāraṇaṃ,**“Observance day, invitation day,*";
P_HTM[10524]="*āpatti ca gilānakaṃ;**And offense, one who is sick;*";
P_HTM[10525]="*Abhisamācāralajjī ca,**Good conduct, and shameless,*";
P_HTM[10526]="*adhisīle davena ca.**Higher morality, and with frivolity.*";
P_HTM[10527]="*Anācāraṃ upaghāti,**Improperly behaved, harmful,*";
P_HTM[10528]="*micchā āpattimeva ca;**Wrong, and offense;*";
P_HTM[10529]="*Yāyāpattiyā buddhassa,**Offense for which, of the Buddha—*";
P_HTM[10530]="*paṭhamo vaggasaṅgahoti.**The compilation of the first sub-chapter is finished.”*";
P_HTM[10531]="*2. Nappaṭippassambhanavagga**2. The sub-chapter on not lifting*";
P_HTM[10532]="*“Katihi nu kho, bhante, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno kammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabban”ti?**“Sir, when a monk has how many qualities, should a legal procedure done against him not be lifted?”*";
P_HTM[10533]="*“Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno kammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**“When he has five qualities, Upāli:*";
P_HTM[10534]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10535]="*Āpattiṃ āpanno kammakato upasampādeti, nissayaṃ deti, sāmaṇeraṃ upaṭṭhāpeti, bhikkhunovādakasammutiṃ sādiyati, sammatopi bhikkhuniyo ovadati—**if, after committing an offense and having a legal procedure done against him, he: gives the full ordination, [2] gives formal support, [3] has a novice monk attend on him, [4] he accepts being appointed as an instructor of the nuns; [5] he instructs the nuns, whether appointed or not.*";
P_HTM[10536]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno kammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10537]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno kammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**When a monk has five other qualities, should a legal procedure done against him not be lifted:*";
P_HTM[10538]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10539]="*Yāya āpattiyā saṅghena kammaṃ kataṃ hoti taṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati, aññaṃ vā tādisikaṃ, tato vā pāpiṭṭhataraṃ, kammaṃ garahati, kammike garahati—**he commits the same offense for which the Sangha did the legal procedure against him; he commits an offense similar to the one for which the Sangha did the legal procedure against him; he commits an offense worse than the one for which the Sangha did the legal procedure against him; he criticizes the procedure; he criticizes those who did the procedure.*";
P_HTM[10540]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno kammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10541]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno kammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**When a monk has five other qualities, should a legal procedure done against him not be lifted:*";
P_HTM[10542]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10543]="*Buddhassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, dhammassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, saṅghassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, micchādiṭṭhiko ca hoti, ājīvavipanno ca—**he disparages the Buddha; he disparages the Teaching; he disparages the Sangha; he has wrong view; and he has failed in livelihood.*";
P_HTM[10544]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno kammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10545]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno kammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**When a monk has five other qualities, should a legal procedure done against him not be lifted:*";
P_HTM[10546]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10547]="*Alajjī ca hoti, bālo ca, apakatatto ca, omaddakārako ca hoti, vattesu sikkhāya ca na paripūrakārī—**he is shameless, ignorant, and not a regular monk, and he oppresses others, and he does not fulfil the training in proper conduct.”*";
P_HTM[10548]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno kammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabban”ti.* **";
P_HTM[10549]="*“Saṅgāmāvacarena, bhante, bhikkhunā saṅghaṃ upasaṅkamantena kati dhamme ajjhattaṃ upaṭṭhāpetvā saṅgho upasaṅkamitabbo”ti?**“Sir, when a monk is involved in a conflict and is about to approach the Sangha, how many qualities should he first set up in himself?”*";
P_HTM[10550]="*“Saṅgāmāvacarena, upāli, bhikkhunā saṅghaṃ upasaṅkamantena pañca dhamme ajjhattaṃ upaṭṭhāpetvā saṅgho upasaṅkamitabbo.**“He should set up five qualities in himself:*";
P_HTM[10551]="*Katame pañca?* **";
P_HTM[10552]="*Saṅgāmāvacarena, upāli, bhikkhunā saṅghaṃ upasaṅkamantena nīcacittena saṅgho upasaṅkamitabbo, rajoharaṇasamena cittena, āsanakusalena bhavitabbaṃ nissajjakusalena, there bhikkhū anupakhajjantena, nave bhikkhū āsanena appaṭibāhantena yathāpatirūpe āsane nisīditabbaṃ, anānākathikena bhavitabbaṃ atiracchānakathikena, sāmaṃ vā dhammo bhāsitabbo, paro vā ajjhesitabbo, ariyo vā tuṇhībhāvo nātimaññitabbo, sace, upāli, saṅgho samaggakaraṇīyāni kammāni karoti;**he should be humble; he should be intent on removing defilements; he should be skilled in appropriate seats and where to sit down, taking a seat without encroaching on the senior monks and without blocking the junior monks; he should not ramble or talk pointlessly, but should speak according to the Teaching or invite others to speak or value noble silence; if the Sangha is doing procedures requiring unity, but the monk does not approve of it, then he should reveal his view but think ‘I should not be at variance with the Sangha,’ and then the unity will not be lost.*";
P_HTM[10553]="*tatra ce, upāli, bhikkhuno nakkhamati, api diṭṭhāvikammaṃ katvā ñāpetabbā sāmaggī.* **";
P_HTM[10554]="*Taṃ kissahetu?* **";
P_HTM[10555]="*Māhaṃ saṅghena nānatto assanti.* **";
P_HTM[10556]="*Saṅgāmāvacarenupāli, bhikkhunā saṅghaṃ upasaṅkamantena ime pañca dhamme ajjhattaṃ upaṭṭhāpetvā saṅgho upasaṅkamitabbo”ti.* **";
P_HTM[10557]="*“Katihi nu kho, bhante, aṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu saṅghe voharanto bahujanaakanto ca hoti bahujanaamanāpo ca bahujanaarucito cā”ti?**“When a monk has how many qualities, does the majority dislike and disapprove of him when he speaks in the Sangha?”*";
P_HTM[10558]="*“Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu saṅghe voharanto bahujanaakanto ca hoti bahujanaamanāpo ca bahujanarucito ca.**“When he has five qualities:*";
P_HTM[10559]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10560]="*Ussitamantī ca hoti, nissitajappī ca, na ca bhāsānusandhikusalo hoti, na yathādhamme yathāvinaye yathāpattiyā codetā hoti, na yathādhamme yathāvinaye yathāpattiyā kāretā hoti—**he is condescending; he repeats what others say; he is bad at keeping to the topic; he does not accuse others according to the Teaching, the Monastic Law, or their offense; he does not make amends according to the Teaching, the Monastic Law, or his offense.*";
P_HTM[10561]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu saṅghe voharanto bahujanaakanto ca hoti bahujanaamanāpo ca bahujanaarucito ca.* **";
P_HTM[10562]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu saṅghe voharanto bahujanakanto ca hoti bahujanamanāpo ca bahujanarucito ca.**But when a monk has five qualities, the majority likes and approves of him when he speaks in the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[10563]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10564]="*Na ussitamantī ca hoti, na nissitajappī ca, bhāsānusandhikusalo ca hoti, yathādhamme yathāvinaye yathāpattiyā codetā hoti, yathādhamme yathāvinaye yathāpattiyā kāretā hoti—**he is not condescending; he does not repeat what others say; he is good at keeping to the topic; he accuses others according to the Teaching, the Monastic Law, and their offense; he makes amends according to the Teaching, the Monastic Law, and his offense.*";
P_HTM[10565]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu saṅghe voharanto bahujanakanto ca hoti bahujanamanāpo ca bahujanarucito ca.* **";
P_HTM[10566]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu saṅghe voharanto bahujanaakanto ca hoti bahujanaamanāpo ca bahujanaarucito ca.**When a monk has five other qualities, the majority dislikes and disapproves of him when he speaks in the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[10567]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10568]="*Ussādetā ca hoti, apasādetā ca, adhammaṃ gaṇhāti, dhammaṃ paṭibāhati, samphañca bahuṃ bhāsati—**he praises; and he blames; he maintains what is contrary to the Teaching; he obstructs what is in accordance with the Teaching; he often speaks frivolously.*";
P_HTM[10569]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu saṅghe voharanto bahujanaakanto ca hoti bahujanaamanāpo ca bahujanaarucito ca.* **";
P_HTM[10570]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu saṅghe voharanto bahujanakanto ca hoti bahujanamanāpo ca bahujanarucito ca.**But when a monk has five qualities, the majority likes and approves of him when he speaks in the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[10571]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10572]="*Na ussādetā ca hoti, na apasādetā ca, dhammaṃ gaṇhāti, adhammaṃ paṭibāhati, samphañca na bahuṃ bhāsati—**he doesn’t praise; and he doesn’t blame; he maintains what is in accordance with the Teaching; he obstructs what is contrary to the Teaching; he rarely speaks frivolously.*";
P_HTM[10573]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu saṅghe voharanto bahujanakanto ca hoti bahujanamanāpo ca bahujanarucito ca.* **";
P_HTM[10574]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu saṅghe voharanto bahujanaakanto ca hoti bahujanaamanāpo ca bahujanaarucito ca.**When a monk has five other qualities, the majority dislikes and disapproves of him when he speaks in the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[10575]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10576]="*Pasayhapavattā hoti, anokāsakammaṃ kāretvā pavattā hoti, na yathādhamme yathāvinaye yathāpattiyā codetā hoti, na yathādhamme yathāvinaye yathāpattiyā kāretā hoti, na yathādiṭṭhiyā byākatā hoti—**he speaks forcefully; he speaks without having obtained permission; he does not accuse others according to the Teaching, the Monastic Law, or their offense; he does not make amends according to the Teaching, the Monastic Law, or his offense; he does not explain things according to his own view.*";
P_HTM[10577]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu saṅghe voharanto bahujanaakanto ca hoti bahujanaamanāpo ca bahujanaarucito ca.* **";
P_HTM[10578]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu saṅghe voharanto bahujanakanto ca hoti bahujanamanāpo ca bahujanarucito ca.**But when a monk has five qualities, the majority likes and approves of him when he speaks in the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[10579]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10580]="*Na pasayhapavattā hoti, okāsakammaṃ kāretvā pavattā hoti, yathādhamme yathāvinaye yathāpattiyā codetā hoti, yathādhamme yathāvinaye yathāpattiyā kāretā hoti, yathādiṭṭhiyā byākatā hoti—**he does not speak forcefully; he does not speak without having obtained permission; he accuses others according to the Teaching, the Monastic Law, and their offense; he makes amends according to the Teaching, the Monastic Law, and his offense; he explains things according to his own view.*";
P_HTM[10581]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu saṅghe voharanto bahujanakanto ca hoti bahujanamanāpo ca bahujanarucito cā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[10582]="*“Kati nu kho, bhante, ānisaṃsā vinayapariyattiyā”ti?**“Sir, how many benefits are there of studying the Monastics Law?”*";
P_HTM[10583]="*“Pañcime, upāli, ānisaṃsā vinayapariyattiyā.**“There are these five benefits:*";
P_HTM[10584]="*Katame pañca?* **";
P_HTM[10585]="*Attano sīlakkhandho sugutto hoti surakkhito, kukkuccapakatānaṃ paṭisaraṇaṃ hoti, visārado saṅghamajjhe voharati, paccatthike sahadhammena suniggahitaṃ niggaṇhāti, saddhammaṭṭhitiyā paṭipanno hoti—**your own morality is well guarded; you are a refuge for those who are habitually anxious; you speak with confidence in the midst of the Sangha; you can legitimately and properly refute an opponent; you are practicing for the longevity of the true Teaching.”*";
P_HTM[10586]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcānisaṃsā vinayapariyattiyā”.* **";
P_HTM[10587]="*Nappaṭippassambhanavaggo niṭṭhito dutiyo.**The second sub-chapter on not lifting is finished.*";
P_HTM[10588]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[10589]="*Āpanno yāyavaṇṇañca,**“Committing, for which, and praise,*";
P_HTM[10590]="*alajjī saṅgāmena ca;**Shameless, and with conflict;*";
P_HTM[10591]="*Ussitā ussādetā ca,**Condescending, and praises,*";
P_HTM[10592]="*pasayha pariyattiyāti.**Forcefully, studying.”*";
P_HTM[10593]="*Paṭhamayamakapaññatti.**The first pairs have been laid down.*";
P_HTM[10594]="*3. Vohāravagga**3. The sub-chapter on speech*";
P_HTM[10595]="*“Katihi nu kho, bhante, aṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe na voharitabban”ti**“Sir, when a monk has how many qualities, should he not speak in the Sangha?”*";
P_HTM[10596]="*“Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe na voharitabbaṃ.**“When he has five qualities, Upāli:*";
P_HTM[10597]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10598]="*Āpattiṃ na jānāti, āpattisamuṭṭhānaṃ na jānāti, āpattiyā payogaṃ na jānāti, āpattiyā vūpasamaṃ na jānāti, āpattiyā na vinicchayakusalo hoti—**he does not know the offenses; he does not know the origin of the offenses; he does not know the kind of effort required to commit the offenses; he does not know the settling of offenses; he is not skilled in deciding on offenses.*";
P_HTM[10599]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe na voharitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10600]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe voharitabbaṃ.**But when a monk has five qualities, he may speak in the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[10601]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10602]="*Āpattiṃ jānāti, āpattisamuṭṭhānaṃ jānāti, āpattiyā payogaṃ jānāti, āpattiyā vūpasamaṃ jānāti, āpattiyā vinicchayakusalo hoti—**he knows the offenses; he know the origin of the offenses; he knows the kind of effort required to commit the offenses; he knows the settling of offenses; he is skilled in deciding on offenses.*";
P_HTM[10603]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe voharitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10604]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe na voharitabbaṃ.**When a monk has five other qualities, he should not speak in the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[10605]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10606]="*Adhikaraṇaṃ na jānāti, adhikaraṇasamuṭṭhānaṃ na jānāti, adhikaraṇassa payogaṃ na jānāti, adhikaraṇassa vūpasamaṃ na jānāti, adhikaraṇassa na vinicchayakusalo hoti—**he does not know the legal issues; he does not know the origin of the legal issues; he does not know the kind of effort that is the source of the legal issues; he does not know the settling of legal issues; he is not skilled in deciding legal issues.*";
P_HTM[10607]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe na voharitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10608]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe voharitabbaṃ.**But when a monk has five qualities, he may speak in the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[10609]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10610]="*Adhikaraṇaṃ jānāti, adhikaraṇasamuṭṭhānaṃ jānāti, adhikaraṇassa payogaṃ jānāti, adhikaraṇassa vūpasamaṃ jānāti, adhikaraṇassa vinicchayakusalo hoti—**he knows the legal issues; he knows the origin of the legal issues; he knows the kind of effort that is the source of the legal issues; he knows the settling of legal issues; he is skilled in deciding legal issues.*";
P_HTM[10611]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe voharitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10612]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe na voharitabbaṃ.**When a monk has five other qualities, he should not speak in the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[10613]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10614]="*Pasayhapavattā hoti, anokāsakammaṃ kāretvā pavattā hoti, na yathādhamme yathāvinaye yathāpattiyā codetā hoti, na yathādhamme yathāvinaye yathāpattiyā kāretā hoti, na yathādiṭṭhiyā byākatā hoti—**he speaks forcefully; he speaks without having obtained permission; he does not accuse others according to the Teaching, the Monastic Law, or their offense; he does not make amends according to the Teaching, the Monastic Law, or his offense; he does not explain things according to his own view.*";
P_HTM[10615]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe na voharitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10616]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe voharitabbaṃ.**But when a monk has five qualities, he may speak in the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[10617]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10618]="*Na pasayhapavattā hoti, okāsakammaṃ kāretvā pavattā hoti, yathādhamme yathāvinaye yathāpattiyā codetā hoti, yathādhamme yathāvinaye yathāpattiyā kāretā hoti, yathādiṭṭhiyā byākatā hoti—**he does not speak forcefully; he does not speak without having obtained permission; he accuses others according to the Teaching, the Monastic Law, and their offense; he makes amends according to the Teaching, the Monastic Law, and his offense; he explains things according to his own view.*";
P_HTM[10619]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe voharitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10620]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe na voharitabbaṃ.**When a monk has five other qualities, he should not speak in the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[10621]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10622]="*Āpattānāpattiṃ na jānāti, lahukagarukaṃ āpattiṃ na jānāti, sāvasesānavasesaṃ āpattiṃ na jānāti, duṭṭhullāduṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ na jānāti, sappaṭikammaṃ appaṭikammaṃ āpattiṃ na jānāti—**he does not know the offenses and non-offenses; he does not know the light and heavy offenses; he does not know the curable and incurable offenses; he does not know the grave and minor offenses; he does not know the offenses that are clearable by making amends and the offenses that are not clearable by making amends.*";
P_HTM[10623]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe na voharitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10624]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe voharitabbaṃ.**But when a monk has five qualities, he may speak in the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[10625]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10626]="*Āpattānāpattiṃ jānāti, lahukagarukaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, sāvasesānavasesaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, duṭṭhullāduṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, sappaṭikammaṃ appaṭikammaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti—**he knows the offenses and non-offenses; he knows the light and heavy offenses; he knows the curable and incurable offenses; he knows the grave and minor offenses; he knows the offenses that are clearable by making amends and the offenses that are not clearable by making amends.*";
P_HTM[10627]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe voharitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10628]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe na voharitabbaṃ.**When a monk has five other qualities, he should not speak in the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[10629]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10630]="*Kammaṃ na jānāti, kammassa karaṇaṃ na jānāti, kammassa vatthuṃ na jānāti, kammassa vattaṃ na jānāti, kammassa vūpasamaṃ na jānāti—**he does not know the legal procedures; he does not know how the legal procedures are done; he does not know the actions that are the basis for the legal procedures; he does not know the proper conduct in relation to legal procedures; he does not know the settling of legal procedures.*";
P_HTM[10631]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe na voharitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10632]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe voharitabbaṃ.**But when a monk has five qualities, he may speak in the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[10633]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10634]="*Kammaṃ jānāti, kammassa karaṇaṃ jānāti, kammassa vatthuṃ jānāti, kammassa vattaṃ jānāti, kammassa vūpasamaṃ jānāti—**he knows the legal procedures; he knows how the legal procedures are done; he knows the actions that are the basis for the legal procedures; he knows the proper conduct in relation to legal procedures; he knows the settling of legal procedures.*";
P_HTM[10635]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe voharitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10636]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe na voharitabbaṃ.**When a monk has five other qualities, he should not speak in the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[10637]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10638]="*Vatthuṃ na jānāti, nidānaṃ na jānāti, paññattiṃ na jānāti, padapaccābhaṭṭhaṃ na jānāti, anusandhivacanapathaṃ na jānāti—**he does not know the actions that are the basis for offenses; he does not know the origin stories; he does not know the rules; he does not know the right order of words; he does not know the sequence of statements.*";
P_HTM[10639]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe na voharitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10640]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe voharitabbaṃ.**But when a monk has five qualities, he may speak in the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[10641]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10642]="*Vatthuṃ jānāti, nidānaṃ jānāti, paññattiṃ jānāti, padapaccābhaṭṭhaṃ jānāti, anusandhivacanapathaṃ jānāti—**he knows the actions that are the basis for offenses; he knows the origin stories; he knows the rules; he knows the right order of words; he knows the sequence of statements.*";
P_HTM[10643]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe voharitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10644]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe na voharitabbaṃ.**When a monk has five other qualities, he should not speak in the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[10645]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10646]="*Chandāgatiṃ gacchati, dosāgatiṃ gacchati, mohāgatiṃ gacchati, bhayāgatiṃ gacchati, alajjī ca hoti—**he is swayed by desire, ill will, confusion, and fear, and he is shameless.*";
P_HTM[10647]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe na voharitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10648]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe voharitabbaṃ.**But when a monk has five qualities, he may speak in the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[10649]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10650]="*Na chandāgatiṃ gacchati, na dosāgatiṃ gacchati, na mohāgatiṃ gacchati, na bhayāgatiṃ gacchati, lajjī ca hoti—**he is not swayed by desire, ill will, confusion, or fear, and he has a sense of conscience.*";
P_HTM[10651]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe voharitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10652]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe na voharitabbaṃ.**When a monk has five other qualities, he should not speak in the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[10653]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10654]="*Chandāgatiṃ gacchati, dosāgatiṃ gacchati, mohāgatiṃ gacchati, bhayāgatiṃ gacchati, akusalo ca hoti vinaye—**he is swayed by desire, ill will, confusion, and fear, and he is unskilled in the Monastic Law.*";
P_HTM[10655]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe na voharitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10656]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe voharitabbaṃ.**But when a monk has five qualities, he may speak in the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[10657]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10658]="*Na chandāgatiṃ gacchati, na dosāgatiṃ gacchati, na mohāgatiṃ gacchati, na bhayāgatiṃ gacchati, kusalo ca hoti vinaye—**he is not swayed by desire, ill will, confusion, or fear, and he is skilled in the Monastic Law.*";
P_HTM[10659]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe voharitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10660]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe na voharitabbaṃ.**When a monk has five other qualities, he should not speak in the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[10661]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10662]="*Ñattiṃ na jānāti, ñattiyā karaṇaṃ na jānāti, ñattiyā anussāvanaṃ na jānāti, ñattiyā samathaṃ na jānāti, ñattiyā vūpasamaṃ na jānāti—**he does not know the motion; he does not know how the motion is done; he does not know the proclamation of the motion; he does not know the settling of the motion; he does not know the resolution of the motion.*";
P_HTM[10663]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe na voharitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10664]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe voharitabbaṃ.**But when a monk has five qualities, he may speak in the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[10665]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10666]="*Ñattiṃ jānāti, ñattiyā karaṇaṃ jānāti, ñattiyā anussāvanaṃ jānāti, ñattiyā samathaṃ jānāti, ñattiyā vūpasamaṃ jānāti—**he knows the motion; he knows how the motion is done; he knows the proclamation of the motion; he knows the settling of the motion; he know the resolution of the motion.*";
P_HTM[10667]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe voharitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10668]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe na voharitabbaṃ.**When a monk has five other qualities, he should not speak in the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[10669]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10670]="*Suttaṃ na jānāti, suttānulomaṃ na jānāti, vinayaṃ na jānāti, vinayānulomaṃ na jānāti, na ca ṭhānāṭhānakusalo hoti—**he does not know the Monastic Code; he does not know what is in accordance with the Monastic Code; he does not know the Monastic Law; he does not know what is in accordance with the Monastic Law; he is not skilled in what is and what is not possible.*";
P_HTM[10671]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe na voharitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10672]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe voharitabbaṃ.**But when a monk has five qualities, he may speak in the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[10673]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10674]="*Suttaṃ jānāti, suttānulomaṃ jānāti, vinayaṃ jānāti, vinayānulomaṃ jānāti, ṭhānāṭhānakusalo ca hoti—**he knows the Monastic Code; he knows what is in accordance with the Monastic Code; he knows the Monastic Law; he knows what is in accordance with the Monastic Law; he is skilled in what is and what is not possible.*";
P_HTM[10675]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe voharitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10676]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe na voharitabbaṃ.**When a monk has five other qualities, he should not speak in the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[10677]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10678]="*Dhammaṃ na jānāti, dhammānulomaṃ na jānāti, vinayaṃ na jānāti, vinayānulomaṃ na jānāti, na ca pubbāparakusalo hoti—**he does not know the Teaching; he does not know what is in accordance with the Teaching; he does not know the Monastic Law; he does not know what is in accordance with the Monastic Law; he is not skilled in sequence.*";
P_HTM[10679]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe na voharitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10680]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe voharitabbaṃ.**But when a monk has five qualities, he may speak in the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[10681]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10682]="*Dhammaṃ jānāti, dhammānulomaṃ jānāti, vinayaṃ jānāti, vinayānulomaṃ jānāti, pubbāparakusalo ca hoti—**he knows the Teaching; he knows what is in accordance with the Teaching; he knows the Monastic Law; he knows what is in accordance with the Monastic Law; he is skilled in sequence.*";
P_HTM[10683]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saṅghe voharitabban”ti.* **";
P_HTM[10684]="*Vohāravaggo niṭṭhito tatiyo.**The third sub-chapter on speech is finished.*";
P_HTM[10685]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[10686]="*Āpatti adhikaraṇaṃ,**“Offenses, legal issues,*";
P_HTM[10687]="*pasayhāpatti jānanā;**Forcefully, knowing offenses;*";
P_HTM[10688]="*Kammaṃ vatthuṃ alajjī ca,**Legal procedures, the actions that are the basis, and shameless,*";
P_HTM[10689]="*akusalo ca ñattiyā;**Unskilled, of the motion;*";
P_HTM[10690]="*Suttaṃ na jānāti dhammaṃ,**He does not know the Monastic Code, or the Teaching—*";
P_HTM[10691]="*tatiyo vaggasaṅgahoti.**The compilation of the third sub-chapter is finished.”*";
P_HTM[10692]="*4. Diṭṭhāvikammavagga**4. The sub-chapter on revealing one’s view*";
P_HTM[10693]="*“Kati nu kho, bhante, adhammikā diṭṭhāvikammā”ti?**“Sir, how many illegitimate kinds of revealing one’s view are there?”*";
P_HTM[10694]="*“Pañcime, upāli, adhammikā diṭṭhāvikammā.**“There are five, Upāli:*";
P_HTM[10695]="*Katame pañca?* **";
P_HTM[10696]="*Anāpattiyā diṭṭhiṃ āvi karoti, adesanāgāminiyā āpattiyā diṭṭhiṃ āvi karoti, desitāya āpattiyā diṭṭhiṃ āvi karoti, catūhi pañcahi diṭṭhiṃ āvi karoti, mano mānasena diṭṭhiṃ āvi karoti—**one reveals a view about a non-offense; one reveals a view about an offense that is not clearable by confession; one reveals a view about an offense that has been confessed; one reveals a view to four or five people; one reveals a view mind to mind.*";
P_HTM[10697]="*ime kho, upāli, pañca adhammikā diṭṭhāvikammā.* **";
P_HTM[10698]="*Pañcime, upāli, dhammikā diṭṭhāvikammā.**But there are five legitimate kinds of revealing one’s view:*";
P_HTM[10699]="*Katame pañca?* **";
P_HTM[10700]="*Āpattiyā diṭṭhiṃ āvi karoti, desanāgāminiyā āpattiyā diṭṭhiṃ āvi karoti, adesitāya āpattiyā diṭṭhiṃ āvi karoti, na catūhi pañcahi diṭṭhiṃ āvi karoti, na mano mānasena diṭṭhiṃ āvi karoti—**one reveals a view about an offense; one reveals a view about an offense that is clearable by confession; one reveals a view about an offense that has not been confessed; one does not reveal a view to four or five people; one does not reveal a view mind to mind.*";
P_HTM[10701]="*ime kho, upāli, pañca dhammikā diṭṭhāvikammā.* **";
P_HTM[10702]="*Aparepi, upāli, pañca adhammikā diṭṭhāvikammā.**There are five other illegitimate kinds of revealing one’s view:*";
P_HTM[10703]="*Katame pañca?* **";
P_HTM[10704]="*Nānāsaṃvāsakassa santike diṭṭhiṃ āvi karoti, nānāsīmāya ṭhitassa santike diṭṭhiṃ āvi karoti, apakatattassa santike diṭṭhiṃ āvi karoti, catūhi pañcahi diṭṭhiṃ āvi karoti, mano mānasena diṭṭhiṃ āvi karoti—**one reveals a view in the presence of someone who belongs to a different Buddhist sect; one reveals a view in the presence of someone who is within a different monastic boundary; one reveals a view in the presence of someone who is not a regular monk; one reveals a view to four or five people; one reveals a view mind to mind.*";
P_HTM[10705]="*ime kho, upāli, pañca adhammikā diṭṭhāvikammā.* **";
P_HTM[10706]="*Pañcime, upāli, dhammikā diṭṭhāvikammā.**But there are five legitimate kinds of revealing one’s view:*";
P_HTM[10707]="*Katame pañca?* **";
P_HTM[10708]="*Samānasaṃvāsakassa santike diṭṭhiṃ āvi karoti, samānasīmāya ṭhitassa santike diṭṭhiṃ āvi karoti, pakatattassa santike diṭṭhiṃ āvi karoti, na catūhi pañcahi diṭṭhiṃ āvi karoti, na mano mānasena diṭṭhiṃ āvi karoti—**one reveals a view in the presence of someone who belongs to the same Buddhist sect; one reveals a view in the presence of someone who is within the same monastic boundary; one reveals a view in the presence of someone who is a regular monk; one does not reveal a view to four or five people; one does not reveal a view mind to mind.”*";
P_HTM[10709]="*ime kho, upāli, pañca dhammikā diṭṭhāvikammā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[10710]="*“Kati nu kho, bhante, adhammikā paṭiggahā”ti?**“How many illegitimate kinds of receiving are there?”*";
P_HTM[10711]="*“Pañcime, upāli, adhammikā paṭiggahā.**“There are five:*";
P_HTM[10712]="*Katame pañca?* **";
P_HTM[10713]="*Kāyena diyyamānaṃ kāyena appaṭiggahitaṃ, kāyena diyyamānaṃ kāyappaṭibaddhena appaṭiggahitaṃ, kāyappaṭibaddhena diyyamānaṃ kāyena appaṭiggahitaṃ, kāyappaṭibaddhena diyyamānaṃ kāyappaṭibaddhena appaṭiggahitaṃ, nissaggiyena diyyamānaṃ kāyena vā kāyappaṭibaddhena vā appaṭiggahitaṃ—**when someone gives by body and one does not receive by body; when someone gives by body and one does not receive with something connected to the body; when someone gives with something connected to the body and one does not receive by body; when someone gives with something connected to the body and one does not receive with something connected to the body; when someone gives by releasing and one does not receive by body or with something connected to the body.*";
P_HTM[10714]="*ime kho, upāli, pañca adhammikā paṭiggahā.* **";
P_HTM[10715]="*Pañcime, upāli, dhammikā paṭiggahā.**But there are five legitimate kinds of receiving:*";
P_HTM[10716]="*Katame pañca?* **";
P_HTM[10717]="*Kāyena diyyamānaṃ kāyena paṭiggahitaṃ, kāyena diyyamānaṃ kāyappaṭibaddhena paṭiggahitaṃ, kāyappaṭibaddhena diyyamānaṃ kāyena paṭiggahitaṃ, kāyappaṭibaddhena diyyamānaṃ kāyappaṭibaddhena paṭiggahitaṃ, nissaggiyena diyyamānaṃ kāyena vā kāyappaṭibaddhena vā paṭiggahitaṃ—**when someone gives by body and one receives by body; when someone gives by body and one receives with something connected to the body; when someone gives with something connected to the body and one receives by body; when someone gives with something connected to the body and one receives with something connected to the body; when someone gives by releasing and one receives by body or with something connected to the body.”*";
P_HTM[10718]="*ime kho, upāli, pañca dhammikā paṭiggahā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[10719]="*“Kati nu kho, bhante, anatirittā”ti?**“In how many ways is something considered as not leftover?”*";
P_HTM[10720]="*“Pañcime, upāli, anatirittā.**“In five ways:*";
P_HTM[10721]="*Katame pañca?* **";
P_HTM[10722]="*Akappiyakataṃ hoti, appaṭiggahitakataṃ hoti anuccāritakataṃ hoti, ahatthapāse kataṃ hoti, alametaṃ sabbanti avuttaṃ hoti—**the making it leftover is done with food that is not allowable; it is done with food that has not been received; it is done with food that is not held in hand; it is done by one who is not within arm’s reach; “I’ve had enough,” has not been said.*";
P_HTM[10723]="*ime kho, upāli, pañca anatirittā.* **";
P_HTM[10724]="*Pañcime, upāli, atirittā.**There are five ways that something is considered as leftover:*";
P_HTM[10725]="*Katame pañca?* **";
P_HTM[10726]="*Kappiyakataṃ hoti, paṭiggahitakataṃ hoti, uccāritakataṃ hoti, hatthapāse kataṃ hoti, alametaṃ sabbanti vuttaṃ hoti—**the making it leftover is done with food that is allowable; it is done with food that has been received; it is done with food that is held in hand; it is done by one who is within arm’s reach; “I’ve had enough,” has been said.*";
P_HTM[10727]="*ime kho, upāli, pañca atirittā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[10728]="*“Katihi nu kho, bhante, ākārehi pavāraṇā paññāyatī”ti?**“In how many ways is there a refusal of an invitation to eat more?”*";
P_HTM[10729]="*“Pañcahupāli, ākārehi pavāraṇā paññāyati.**“In five ways:*";
P_HTM[10730]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10731]="*Asanaṃ paññāyati, bhojanaṃ paññāyati, hatthapāse ṭhito abhiharati, paṭikkhepo paññāyati—**there is eating; there is cooked food; it is offered by one standing within arm’s reach; there is a refusal.*";
P_HTM[10732]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahākārehi pavāraṇā paññāyatī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[10733]="*“Kati nu kho, bhante, adhammikā paṭiññātakaraṇā”ti?**“How many illegitimately ways are there of acting according to what has been admitted?”*";
P_HTM[10734]="*“Pañcime, upāli, adhammikā paṭiññātakaraṇā.**“There are five ways:*";
P_HTM[10735]="*Katame pañca?* **";
P_HTM[10736]="*Bhikkhu pārājikaṃ ajjhāpanno hoti, pārājikena codiyamāno saṅghādisesaṃ ajjhāpanno paṭijānāti, taṃ saṅgho saṅghādisesena kāreti, adhammikaṃ paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ.**A monk has committed an offense entailing expulsion. When he is accused of having committed such an offense, he admits to committing an offense entailing suspension. The Sangha deals with him for an offense entailing suspension. That acting according to what has been admitted is illegitimate.*";
P_HTM[10737]="*Bhikkhu pārājikaṃ ajjhāpanno hoti, pārājikena codiyamāno pācittiyaṃ …pe…**A monk has committed an offense entailing expulsion. When he is accused of having committed such an offense, he admits to committing an offense entailing confession …*";
P_HTM[10738]="*pāṭidesanīyaṃ …**an offense entailing acknowledgment …*";
P_HTM[10739]="*dukkaṭaṃ ajjhāpanno paṭijānāti, taṃ saṅgho dukkaṭena kāreti, adhammikaṃ paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ.**an offense of wrong conduct. The Sangha deals with him for an offense of wrong conduct. That acting according to what has been admitted is illegitimate.*";
P_HTM[10740]="*Bhikkhu saṅghādisesaṃ …pe…**A monk has committed an offense entailing suspension …*";
P_HTM[10741]="*pācittiyaṃ …**A monk has committed an offense entailing confession …*";
P_HTM[10742]="*pāṭidesanīyaṃ …**A monk has committed an offense entailing acknowledgment …*";
P_HTM[10743]="*dukkaṭaṃ ajjhāpanno hoti. Dukkaṭena codiyamāno pārājikaṃ ajjhāpanno paṭijānāti, taṃ saṅgho pārājikena kāreti, adhammikaṃ paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ.**A monk has committed an offense of wrong conduct. When he is accused of having committed such an offense, he admits to committing an offense entailing expulsion. The Sangha deals with him for an offense entailing expulsion. That acting according to what has been admitted is illegitimate.*";
P_HTM[10744]="*Bhikkhu dukkaṭaṃ ajjhāpanno hoti, dukkaṭena codiyamāno saṅghādisesaṃ …pe…**A monk has committed an offense of wrong conduct. When he is accused of having committed such an offense, he admits to committing an offense entailing suspension. …*";
P_HTM[10745]="*pācittiyaṃ …**an offense entailing confession …*";
P_HTM[10746]="*pāṭidesanīyaṃ ajjhāpanno paṭijānāti, taṃ saṅgho pāṭidesanīyena kāreti, adhammikaṃ paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ.**an offense entailing acknowledgment. The Sangha deals with him for an offense entailing acknowledgment. That acting according to what has been admitted is illegitimate.*";
P_HTM[10747]="*Ime kho, upāli, pañca adhammikā paṭiññātakaraṇā.* **";
P_HTM[10748]="*Pañcime, upāli, dhammikā paṭiññātakaraṇā.**There are five ways of legitimately acting according to what has been admitted:*";
P_HTM[10749]="*Katame pañca?* **";
P_HTM[10750]="*Bhikkhu pārājikaṃ ajjhāpanno hoti, pārājikena codiyamāno pārājikaṃ ajjhāpanno paṭijānāti, taṃ saṅgho pārājikena kāreti, dhammikaṃ paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ.**A monk has committed an offense entailing expulsion. When he is accused of having committed such an offense, he admits it. The Sangha deals with him for an offense entailing expulsion. That acting according to what has been admitted is legitimate.*";
P_HTM[10751]="*Bhikkhu saṅghādisesaṃ …pe…**A monk has committed an offense entailing suspension …*";
P_HTM[10752]="*pācittiyaṃ …**A monk has committed an offense entailing confession …*";
P_HTM[10753]="*pāṭidesanīyaṃ …**A monk has committed an offense entailing acknowledgment …*";
P_HTM[10754]="*dukkaṭaṃ ajjhāpanno hoti, dukkaṭena codiyamāno dukkaṭaṃ ajjhāpanno paṭijānāti, taṃ saṅgho dukkaṭena kāreti, dhammikaṃ paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ.**A monk has committed an offense of wrong conduct. When he is accused of having committed such an offense, he admits it. The Sangha deals with him for an offense of wrong conduct. That acting according to what has been admitted is legitimate.”*";
P_HTM[10755]="*Ime kho, upāli, pañca dhammikā paṭiññātakaraṇā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[10756]="*“Katihi nu kho, bhante, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno okāsakammaṃ kārāpentassa nālaṃ okāsakammaṃ kātun”ti?**“Sir, when a monk has how many qualities, is he unqualified to ask for permission to admonish someone?”*";
P_HTM[10757]="*“Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno okāsakammaṃ kārāpentassa nālaṃ okāsakammaṃ kātuṃ.**“When he has five qualities:*";
P_HTM[10758]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10759]="*Alajjī ca hoti, bālo ca, apakatatto ca, cāvanādhippāyo vattā hoti, no vuṭṭhānādhippāyo—**he is shameless; he is ignorant; he is not a regular monk; he speaks to make someone disrobe; he is not aiming to clear someone’s offense.*";
P_HTM[10760]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno okāsakammaṃ kārāpentassa nālaṃ okāsakammaṃ kātuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10761]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno okāsakammaṃ kārāpentassa alaṃ okāsakammaṃ kātuṃ.**“But when a monk has five qualities, he is qualified to ask for permission to admonish someone:*";
P_HTM[10762]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10763]="*Lajjī ca hoti, paṇḍito ca, pakatatto ca, vuṭṭhānādhippāyo vattā hoti, no cāvanādhippāyo—**he has a sense of conscience; he is knowledgeable; he is a regular monk; he is aiming to clear someone’s offense; he is not speaking to make someone disrobe.*";
P_HTM[10764]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno okāsakammaṃ kārāpentassa alaṃ okāsakammaṃ kātun”ti.* **";
P_HTM[10765]="*“Katihi nu kho, bhante, aṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ vinayo na sākacchitabbo”ti?**“When a monk has how many qualities, should the Monastic Law not be discussed with him?”*";
P_HTM[10766]="*“Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ vinayo na sākacchitabbo.**“When he has five qualities:*";
P_HTM[10767]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10768]="*Vatthuṃ na jānāti, nidānaṃ na jānāti, paññattiṃ na jānāti, padapaccābhaṭṭhaṃ na jānāti, anusandhivacanapathaṃ na jānāti—**he does not know the actions that are the basis for offenses; he does not know the origin stories; he does not know the rules; he does not know the right order of words; he does not know the sequence of statements.*";
P_HTM[10769]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ vinayo na sākacchitabbo.* **";
P_HTM[10770]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ vinayo sākacchitabbo.**But when a monk has five qualities, the Monastic Law may be discussed with him:*";
P_HTM[10771]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10772]="*Vatthuṃ jānāti, nidānaṃ jānāti, paññattiṃ jānāti, padapaccābhaṭṭhaṃ jānāti, anusandhivacanapathaṃ jānāti—**he knows the actions that are the basis for offenses; he knows the origin stories; he knows the rules; he knows the right order of words; he knows the sequence of statements.”*";
P_HTM[10773]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ vinayo sākacchitabbo”ti.* **";
P_HTM[10774]="*“Kati nu kho, bhante, pañhāpucchā”ti?**“How many kinds of questions and enquiries are there?”*";
P_HTM[10775]="*“Pañcimā, upāli, pañhāpucchā.**“There are five:*";
P_HTM[10776]="*Katamā pañca?* **";
P_HTM[10777]="*Mandattā momūhattā pañhaṃ pucchati, pāpiccho icchāpakato pañhaṃ pucchati, paribhavā pañhaṃ pucchati, aññātukāmo pañhaṃ pucchati, sace me pañhaṃ puṭṭho sammadeva byākarissati iccetaṃ kusalaṃ no ce pañhaṃ puṭṭho sammadeva byākarissati ahamassa sammadeva byākarissāmīti pañhaṃ pucchati—**one asks because of stupidity and folly; because one is overcome by bad desires; because of contempt; because one desires to know; because of the thought, ‘If he replies correctly when I ask him, all is well, but if he doesnʼt, I will correctly reply for him.’”*";
P_HTM[10778]="*imā kho, upāli, pañca pañhāpucchā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[10779]="*“Kati nu kho, bhante, aññabyākaraṇā”ti?**“How many kinds of declaration of perfect insight are there?”*";
P_HTM[10780]="*“Pañcime, upāli, aññabyākaraṇā.**“There are five:*";
P_HTM[10781]="*Katame pañca?* **";
P_HTM[10782]="*Mandattā momūhattā aññaṃ byākaroti, pāpiccho icchāpakato aññaṃ byākaroti, ummādā cittakkhepā aññaṃ byākaroti, adhimānena aññaṃ byākaroti, bhūtaṃ aññaṃ byākaroti—**one declares perfect insight because of stupidity and folly; because one is overcome by bad desires; because of insanity and derangement; because of overestimation; because it is true.”*";
P_HTM[10783]="*ime kho, upāli, pañca aññabyākaraṇā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[10784]="*“Kati nu kho, bhante, visuddhiyo”ti?**“How many kinds of purification are there?”*";
P_HTM[10785]="*“Pañcimā, upāli, visuddhiyo.**“There are five:*";
P_HTM[10786]="*Katamā pañca?* **";
P_HTM[10787]="*Nidānaṃ uddisitvā avasesaṃ sutena sāvetabbaṃ ayaṃ paṭhamā visuddhi, nidānaṃ uddisitvā cattāri pārājikāni uddisitvā avasesaṃ sutena sāvetabbaṃ ayaṃ dutiyā visuddhi, nidānaṃ uddisitvā cattāri pārājikāni uddisitvā terasa saṅghādisese uddisitvā avasesaṃ sutena sāvetabbaṃ ayaṃ tatiyā visuddhi, nidānaṃ uddisitvā cattāri pārājikāni uddisitvā terasa saṅghādisese uddisitvā dve aniyate uddisitvā avasesaṃ sutena sāvetabbaṃ ayaṃ catutthā visuddhi, vitthāreneva pañcamī—**After reciting the introduction, the rest is announced as if heard. [2] After reciting the introduction and the four rules entailing expulsion, the rest is announced as if heard. [3] After reciting the introduction, the four rules entailing expulsion, and the thirteen rules entailing suspension, the rest is announced as if heard. [4] After reciting the introduction, the four rules entailing expulsion, the thirteen rules entailing suspension, and the two undetermined rules, the rest is announced as if heard. [5] In full is the fifth.”*";
P_HTM[10788]="*imā kho, upāli, pañca visuddhiyo”ti.* **";
P_HTM[10789]="*“Kati nu kho, bhante, bhojanā”ti?**“How many kinds of cooked food are there?”*";
P_HTM[10790]="*“Pañcime, upāli, bhojanā.**“There are five:*";
P_HTM[10791]="*Katame pañca?* **";
P_HTM[10792]="*Odano, kummāso, sattu, maccho, maṃsaṃ—**cooked grain, porridge, flour products, fish, and meat.”*";
P_HTM[10793]="*ime kho, upāli, pañca bhojanā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[10794]="*Diṭṭhāvikammavaggo niṭṭhito catuttho.**The fourth sub-chapter on revealing one’s view is finished.*";
P_HTM[10795]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[10796]="*Diṭṭhāvikammā apare,**“Revealing one’s view, other,*";
P_HTM[10797]="*paṭiggahānatirittā;**Receiving, not leftover;*";
P_HTM[10798]="*Pavāraṇā paṭiññātaṃ,**Refusal of an invitation to eat more, according to what has been admitted,*";
P_HTM[10799]="*okāsaṃ sākacchena ca;**Permission, and with discussion;*";
P_HTM[10800]="*Pañhaṃ aññabyākaraṇā,**Question, declarations of perfect insight,*";
P_HTM[10801]="*visuddhi cāpi bhojanāti.**And also purification, cooked food.”*";
P_HTM[10802]="*5. Attādānavagga**5. The sub-chapter on raising an issue*";
P_HTM[10803]="*“Codakena, bhante, bhikkhunā paraṃ codetukāmena kati dhamme ajjhattaṃ paccavekkhitvā paro codetabbo”ti?**“Sir, how many qualities should a monk see in himself before accusing another?”*";
P_HTM[10804]="*“Codakenupāli, bhikkhunā paraṃ codetukāmena pañca dhamme ajjhattaṃ paccavekkhitvā paro codetabbo.**“He should see five qualities in himself:*";
P_HTM[10805]="*Katame pañca?* **";
P_HTM[10806]="*Codakenupāli, bhikkhunā paraṃ codetukāmena evaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ—**He should reflect:*";
P_HTM[10807]="*‘Parisuddhakāyasamācāro nu khomhi, parisuddhenamhi kāyasamācārena samannāgato acchiddena appaṭimaṃsena, saṃvijjati nu kho me eso dhammo udāhu no’ti.**‘Is my bodily conduct pure and faultless? Is this quality found in me or not?’*";
P_HTM[10808]="*No ce, upāli, bhikkhu parisuddhakāyasamācāro hoti, parisuddhena kāyasamācārena samannāgato acchiddena appaṭimaṃsena, tassa bhavanti vattāro—**If it’s not, there will be those who say,*";
P_HTM[10809]="*‘iṅgha tāva āyasmā kāyikaṃ sikkhassū’ti itissa bhavanti vattāro.**‘Please train your own bodily conduct first.’*";
P_HTM[10810]="*Puna caparaṃ, upāli, codakena bhikkhunā paraṃ codetukāmena evaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ—**He should reflect:*";
P_HTM[10811]="*‘parisuddhavacīsamācāro nu khomhi, parisuddhenamhi vacīsamācārena samannāgato acchiddena appaṭimaṃsena, saṃvijjati nu kho me eso dhammo udāhu no’ti.**‘Is my verbal conduct pure and faultless? Is this quality found in me or not?’*";
P_HTM[10812]="*No ce, upāli, bhikkhu parisuddhavacīsamācāro hoti, parisuddhena vacīsamācārena samannāgato acchiddena appaṭimaṃsena, tassa bhavanti vattāro—**If it’s not, there will be those who say,*";
P_HTM[10813]="*‘iṅgha tāva āyasmā vācasikaṃ sikkhassū’ti itissa bhavanti vattāro.**‘Please train your own verbal conduct first.’*";
P_HTM[10814]="*Puna caparaṃ, upāli, codakena bhikkhunā paraṃ codetukāmena evaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ—**He should reflect:*";
P_HTM[10815]="*‘mettaṃ nu kho me cittaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ sabrahmacārīsu anāghātaṃ, saṃvijjati nu kho me eso dhammo udāhu no’ti.**‘Do I have a mind of good will toward my fellow monastics? Am I free from ill will toward them? Is this quality found in me or not?’*";
P_HTM[10816]="*No ce, upāli, bhikkhuno mettaṃ cittaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ hoti sabrahmacārīsu anāghātaṃ, tassa bhavanti vattāro—**If it’s not, there will be those who say,*";
P_HTM[10817]="*‘iṅgha tāva āyasmā sabrahmacārīsu mettaṃ cittaṃ upaṭṭhāpehī’ti itissa bhavanti vattāro.**‘Please set up a mind of good will toward your fellow monastics first.’*";
P_HTM[10818]="*Puna caparaṃ, upāli, codakena bhikkhunā paraṃ codetukāmena evaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ—**He should reflect:*";
P_HTM[10819]="*‘bahussuto nu khomhi sutadharo sutasannicayo, ye te dhammā ādikalyāṇā majjhekalyāṇā pariyosānakalyāṇā sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ abhivadanti, tathārūpā me dhammā bahussutā honti dhātā vacasā paricitā manasānupekkhitā diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā, saṃvijjati nu kho me eso dhammo udāhu no’ti.**‘Have I learned much and do I retain and accumulate what I’ve learned? Those teachings that are good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, that have a true goal and are well articulated, and that set out the perfectly complete and pure spiritual life—have I learned many such teachings, retained them in mind, recited them verbally, mentally investigated them, and penetrated them well by view? Is this quality found in me or not?’*";
P_HTM[10820]="*No ce, upāli, bhikkhu bahussuto hoti sutadharo sutasannicayo, ye te dhammā ādikalyāṇā majjhekalyāṇā pariyosānakalyāṇā sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ abhivadanti, tathārūpassa dhammā na bahussutā honti dhātā vacasā paricitā manasānupekkhitā diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā, tassa bhavanti vattāro—**If it’s not, there will be those who say,*";
P_HTM[10821]="*‘iṅgha tāva āyasmā āgamaṃ pariyāpuṇassū’ti itissa bhavanti vattāro.**‘Please learn the tradition first.’*";
P_HTM[10822]="*Puna caparaṃ, upāli, codakena bhikkhunā paraṃ codetukāmena evaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ—**He should reflect:*";
P_HTM[10823]="*‘ubhayāni kho me pātimokkhāni vitthārena svāgatāni honti suvibhattāni suppavattīni suvinicchitāni suttaso anubyañjanaso, saṃvijjati nu kho me eso dhammo udāhu no’ti.**‘Have I properly learned both Monastic Codes in detail; have I analyzed them well, thoroughly mastered them, and investigated them well, both in terms of the rules and their detailed exposition? Is this quality found in me or not?’*";
P_HTM[10824]="*No ce, upāli, bhikkhuno ubhayāni pātimokkhāni vitthārena svāgatāni honti suvibhattāni suppavattīni suvinicchitāni suttaso anubyañjanaso, ‘idaṃ panāvuso kattha vuttaṃ bhagavatā’ti iti puṭṭho na sampāyati, (…) tassa bhavanti vattāro—**If it’s not, there will be those who say,*";
P_HTM[10825]="*‘iṅgha tāva āyasmā vinayaṃ pariyāpuṇassū’ti itissa bhavanti vattāro.**‘Please learn the Monastic Law first.’”*";
P_HTM[10826]="*Codakenupāli, bhikkhunā paraṃ codetukāmena ime pañca dhamme ajjhattaṃ paccavekkhitvā paro codetabbo”ti.* **";
P_HTM[10827]="*“Codakena, bhante, bhikkhunā paraṃ codetukāmena kati dhamme ajjhattaṃ upaṭṭhāpetvā paro codetabbo”ti?**“Sir, how many qualities should a monk set up in himself before accusing another?”*";
P_HTM[10828]="*“Codakenupāli, bhikkhunā paraṃ codetukāmena pañca dhamme ajjhattaṃ upaṭṭhāpetvā paro codetabbo.**“He should set up five qualities in himself:*";
P_HTM[10829]="*Katame pañca?* **";
P_HTM[10830]="*Kālena vakkhāmi no akālena, bhūtena vakkhāmi no abhūtena, saṇhena vakkhāmi no pharusena, atthasaṃhitena vakkhāmi no anatthasaṃhitena, mettācitto vakkhāmi no dosantaroti—**‘I’ll speak at an appropriate time, not at an inappropriate one; I’ll speak the truth, not falsehood; I’ll speak gently, not harshly; I’ll speak what’s beneficial, not what’s unbeneficial; I’ll speak with a mind of good will, not with internal ill will.’”*";
P_HTM[10831]="*codakenupāli, bhikkhunā paraṃ codetukāmena ime pañca dhamme ajjhattaṃ upaṭṭhāpetvā paro codetabbo”ti.* **";
P_HTM[10832]="*“Codakena, bhante, bhikkhunā paraṃ codetukāmena kati dhamme ajjhattaṃ manasi karitvā paro codetabbo”ti?**“How many qualities should a monk attend to in himself before accusing another?”*";
P_HTM[10833]="*“Codakenupāli, bhikkhunā paraṃ codetukāmena pañca dhamme ajjhattaṃ manasi karitvā paro codetabbo.**“He should attend to five qualities in himself:*";
P_HTM[10834]="*Katame pañca?* **";
P_HTM[10835]="*Kāruññatā, hitesitā, anukampatā, āpattivuṭṭhānatā, vinayapurekkhāratā—**compassion, being of benefit, sympathy, the idea of clearing offenses, and the idea of giving priority to the training.”*";
P_HTM[10836]="*codakenupāli, bhikkhunā paraṃ codetukāmena ime pañca dhamme ajjhattaṃ manasi karitvā paro codetabbo”ti.* **";
P_HTM[10837]="*“Katihi nu kho, bhante, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno okāsakammaṃ kārāpentassa nālaṃ okāsakammaṃ kātun”ti?**“When a monk has how many qualities, is he unqualified to ask for permission to admonish someone?”*";
P_HTM[10838]="*“Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno okāsakammaṃ kārāpentassa nālaṃ okāsakammaṃ kātuṃ.**“When he has five qualities:*";
P_HTM[10839]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10840]="*Aparisuddhakāyasamācāro hoti, aparisuddhavacīsamācāro hoti, aparisuddhājīvo hoti, bālo hoti abyatto, na paṭibalo anuyuñjiyamāno anuyogaṃ dātuṃ—**he is impure in bodily conduct; he is impure in verbal conduct; he is impure in livelihood; he is ignorant and incompetent; he is incapable of answering properly when questioned.”*";
P_HTM[10841]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno okāsakammaṃ kārāpentassa nālaṃ okāsakammaṃ kātuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10842]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno okāsakammaṃ kārāpentassa alaṃ okāsakammaṃ kātuṃ.**But when a monk has five qualities, he is qualified to ask for permission to admonish someone:*";
P_HTM[10843]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10844]="*Parisuddhakāyasamācāro hoti, parisuddhavacīsamācāro hoti, parisuddhājīvo hoti, paṇḍito hoti byatto paṭibalo anuyuñjiyamāno anuyogaṃ dātuṃ—**he is pure in bodily conduct; he is pure in verbal conduct; he is pure in livelihood; he is knowledgeable and competent; he is capable of answering properly when questioned.*";
P_HTM[10845]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno okāsakammaṃ kārāpentassa alaṃ okāsakammaṃ kātun”ti.* **";
P_HTM[10846]="*“Attādānaṃ ādātukāmena, bhante, bhikkhunā katihaṅgehi samannāgataṃ attādānaṃ ādātabban”ti?**“Sir, if a monk wishes to raise an issue, how many factors should be fulfilled?”*";
P_HTM[10847]="*“Attādānaṃ ādātukāmenupāli, bhikkhunā pañcaṅgasamannāgataṃ attādānaṃ ādātabbaṃ.**“Five factors should be fulfilled:*";
P_HTM[10848]="*Katame pañca?* **";
P_HTM[10849]="*Attādānaṃ ādātukāmena, upāli, bhikkhunā evaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ—**He should reflect*";
P_HTM[10850]="*‘yaṃ kho ahaṃ imaṃ attādānaṃ ādātukāmo, kālo nu kho imaṃ attādānaṃ ādātuṃ udāhu no’ti.**whether or not it’s the right time to raise the issue.*";
P_HTM[10851]="*Sace, upāli, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti—**If he knows*";
P_HTM[10852]="*‘akālo imaṃ attādānaṃ ādātuṃ no kālo’ti, na taṃ, upāli, attādānaṃ ādātabbaṃ.**it’s the wrong time, he shouldn’t raise it.*";
P_HTM[10853]="*Sace panupāli, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti—**But if he knows*";
P_HTM[10854]="*‘kālo imaṃ attādānaṃ ādātuṃ no akālo’ti, tenupāli, bhikkhunā uttari paccavekkhitabbaṃ—**it’s the right time, he should reflect further*";
P_HTM[10855]="*‘yaṃ kho ahaṃ imaṃ attādānaṃ ādātukāmo bhūtaṃ nu kho idaṃ attādānaṃ udāhu no’ti.**whether or not it’s a real issue.*";
P_HTM[10856]="*Sace, upāli, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti—**If he knows*";
P_HTM[10857]="*‘abhūtaṃ idaṃ attādānaṃ no bhūtan’ti, na taṃ, upāli, attādānaṃ ādātabbaṃ.**it’s not, he shouldn’t raise it.*";
P_HTM[10858]="*Sace panupāli, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti—**But if he knows*";
P_HTM[10859]="*‘bhūtaṃ idaṃ attādānaṃ no abhūtan’ti, tenupāli, bhikkhunā uttari paccavekkhitabbaṃ—**it’s real, he should reflect further*";
P_HTM[10860]="*‘yaṃ kho ahaṃ imaṃ attādānaṃ ādātukāmo, atthasaṃhitaṃ nu kho idaṃ attādānaṃ udāhu no’ti.**whether or not raising the issue will be beneficial.*";
P_HTM[10861]="*Sace, upāli, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti—**If he knows*";
P_HTM[10862]="*‘anatthasaṃhitaṃ idaṃ attādānaṃ no atthasaṃhitan’ti, na taṃ, upāli, attādānaṃ ādātabbaṃ.**it won’t, he shouldn’t raise it.*";
P_HTM[10863]="*Sace panupāli, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti—**But if he knows*";
P_HTM[10864]="*‘atthasaṃhitaṃ idaṃ attādānaṃ no anatthasaṃhitan’ti, tenupāli, bhikkhunā uttari paccavekkhitabbaṃ—**it will be beneficial, he should reflect further*";
P_HTM[10865]="*‘imaṃ kho ahaṃ attādānaṃ ādiyamāno labhissāmi sandiṭṭhe sambhatte bhikkhū dhammato vinayato pakkhe udāhu no’ti.**whether or not the monks who are on the side of the Teaching and the Monastic Law will take his side.*";
P_HTM[10866]="*Sace, upāli, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti—**If he knows*";
P_HTM[10867]="*‘imaṃ kho ahaṃ attādānaṃ ādiyamāno na labhissāmi sandiṭṭhe sambhatte bhikkhū dhammato vinayato pakkhe’ti, na taṃ, upāli, attādānaṃ ādātabbaṃ.**that they won’t, he shouldn’t raise it.*";
P_HTM[10868]="*Sace panupāli, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti—**But if he knows*";
P_HTM[10869]="*‘idaṃ kho ahaṃ attādānaṃ ādiyamāno labhissāmi sandiṭṭhe sambhatte bhikkhū dhammato vinayato pakkhe’ti, tenupāli, bhikkhunā uttari paccavekkhitabbaṃ—**they will take his side, he should reflect further*";
P_HTM[10870]="*‘imaṃ kho me attādānaṃ ādiyato bhavissati saṅghassa tatonidānaṃ bhaṇḍanaṃ kalaho viggaho vivādo saṅghabhedo saṅgharāji saṅghavavatthānaṃ saṅghanānākaraṇaṃ udāhu no’ti.**whether or not raising the issue will lead to arguments and disputes, to fracture and schism in the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[10871]="*Sace, upāli, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti—**If he knows*";
P_HTM[10872]="*‘imaṃ kho me attādānaṃ ādiyato bhavissati saṅghassa tatonidānaṃ bhaṇḍanaṃ kalaho viggaho vivādo saṅghabhedo saṅgharāji saṅghavavatthānaṃ saṅghanānākaraṇan’ti, na taṃ, upāli, attādānaṃ ādātabbaṃ.**it will, he shouldn’t raise it.*";
P_HTM[10873]="*Sace panupāli, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti—**But if he knows*";
P_HTM[10874]="*‘imaṃ kho me attādānaṃ ādiyato na bhavissati saṅghassa tatonidānaṃ bhaṇḍanaṃ kalaho viggaho vivādo saṅghabhedo saṅgharāji saṅghavavatthānaṃ saṅghanānākaraṇan’ti, taṃ ādātabbaṃ, upāli, attādānaṃ.**it won’t, he may raise the issue.*";
P_HTM[10875]="*Evaṃ pañcaṅgasamannāgataṃ kho, upāli, attādānaṃ ādinnaṃ pacchāpi avippaṭisārakaraṃ bhavissatī”ti.**In this way, when five factors are fulfilled, he won’t regret raising it.”*";
P_HTM[10876]="*“Katihi nu kho, bhante, aṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu adhikaraṇajātānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ bahūpakāro hotī”ti?**“How many qualities should a monk have to be of great help to monks who are involved in a legal issue?”*";
P_HTM[10877]="*“Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu adhikaraṇajātānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ bahūpakāro hoti.**“He should have five qualities:*";
P_HTM[10878]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10879]="*Sīlavā hoti, pātimokkhasaṃvarasaṃvuto viharati ācāragocarasampanno aṇumattesu vajjesu bhayadassāvī, samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu;**(a) He is virtuous and restrained by the Monastic Code. His conduct is good, he associates with the right people, and he sees danger in minor faults. He undertakes and trains in the training rules.*";
P_HTM[10880]="*bahussuto hoti sutadharo sutasannicayo;**(b) He has learned much, and he retains and accumulates what he has learned.*";
P_HTM[10881]="*ye te dhammā ādikalyāṇā majjhekalyāṇā pariyosānakalyāṇā sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ abhivadanti tathārūpassa dhammā bahussutā honti dhātā vacasā paricitā manasānupekkhitā diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā, ubhayāni kho panassa pātimokkhāni vitthārena svāgatāni honti suvibhattāni suppavattīni suvinicchitāni suttaso anubyañjanaso;**(c) Those teachings that are good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, that have a true goal and are well articulated, and that set out the perfectly complete and pure spiritual life—he has learned many such teachings, retained them in mind, recited them verbally, mentally investigated them, and penetrated them well by view.*";
P_HTM[10882]="*vinaye kho pana ṭhito hoti asaṃhīro;**(d) He is firmly committed to the Monastic Law.*";
P_HTM[10883]="*paṭibalo hoti ubho atthapaccatthike assāsetuṃ saññāpetuṃ nijjhāpetuṃ pekkhetuṃ pasādetuṃ—**(e) He is capable of making both sides relax, of persuading them, of convincing them, of making them see, of reconciling them.*";
P_HTM[10884]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu adhikaraṇajātānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ bahūpakāro hoti.* **";
P_HTM[10885]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu adhikaraṇajātānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ bahūpakāro hoti.**A monk who has five other qualities is also of great help to monks who are involved in a legal issue:*";
P_HTM[10886]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10887]="*Parisuddhakāyasamācāro hoti, parisuddhavacīsamācāro hoti, parisuddhājīvo hoti, paṇḍito hoti byatto, paṭibalo anuyuñjiyamāno anuyogaṃ dātuṃ—**he is pure in bodily conduct; he is pure in verbal conduct; he is pure in livelihood; he is knowledgeable and competent; he is capable of answering properly when questioned.*";
P_HTM[10888]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu adhikaraṇajātānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ bahūpakāro hoti.* **";
P_HTM[10889]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu adhikaraṇajātānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ bahūpakāro hoti.**A monk who has five other qualities is also of great help to monks who are involved in a legal issue:*";
P_HTM[10890]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10891]="*Vatthuṃ jānāti, nidānaṃ jānāti, paññattiṃ jānāti, padapaccābhaṭṭhaṃ jānāti, anusandhivacanapathaṃ jānāti—**he knows the actions that are the basis for offenses; he knows the origin stories; he knows the rules; he knows the right order of words; he knows the sequence of statements.*";
P_HTM[10892]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu adhikaraṇajātānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ bahūpakāro hotī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[10893]="*“Katihi nu kho, bhante, aṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā nānuyuñjitabban”ti?**“Sir, when a monk has how many qualities, should he not be examined?”*";
P_HTM[10894]="*“Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā nānuyuñjitabbaṃ.**“When he has five qualities:*";
P_HTM[10895]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10896]="*Suttaṃ na jānāti, suttānulomaṃ na jānāti, vinayaṃ na jānāti, vinayānulomaṃ na jānāti, na ca ṭhānāṭhānakusalo hoti—**he does not know the Monastic Code; he does not know what is in accordance with the Monastic Code; he does not know the Monastic Law; he does not know what is in accordance with the Monastic Law; he is not skilled in what is and what is not possible.*";
P_HTM[10897]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā nānuyuñjitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10898]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā anuyuñjitabbaṃ.**But when a monk has five qualities, he may be examined:*";
P_HTM[10899]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10900]="*Suttaṃ jānāti, suttānulomaṃ jānāti, vinayaṃ jānāti, vinayānulomaṃ jānāti, ṭhānāṭhānakusalo ca hoti—**he knows the Monastic Code; he knows what is in accordance with the Monastic Code; he knows the Monastic Law; he knows what is in accordance with the Monastic Law; he is skilled in what is and what is not possible.*";
P_HTM[10901]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā anuyuñjitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10902]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā nānuyuñjitabbaṃ.**When a monk has five other qualities, he should not be examined:*";
P_HTM[10903]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10904]="*Dhammaṃ na jānāti, dhammānulomaṃ na jānāti, vinayaṃ na jānāti, vinayānulomaṃ na jānāti, na ca pubbāparakusalo hoti—**he does not know the Teaching; he does not know what is in accordance with the Teaching; he does not know the Monastic Law; he does not know what is in accordance with the Monastic Law; he is not skilled in sequence.*";
P_HTM[10905]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā nānuyuñjitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10906]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā anuyuñjitabbaṃ.**But when a monk has five qualities, he may be examined:*";
P_HTM[10907]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10908]="*Dhammaṃ jānāti, dhammānulomaṃ jānāti, vinayaṃ jānāti, vinayānulomaṃ jānāti, pubbāparakusalo ca hoti—**he knows the Teaching; he knows what is in accordance with the Teaching; he knows the Monastic Law; he knows what is in accordance with the Monastic Law; he is skilled in sequence.*";
P_HTM[10909]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā anuyuñjitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10910]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā nānuyuñjitabbaṃ.**When a monk has five other qualities, he should not be examined:*";
P_HTM[10911]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10912]="*Vatthuṃ na jānāti, nidānaṃ na jānāti, paññattiṃ na jānāti, padapaccābhaṭṭhaṃ na jānāti, anusandhivacanapathaṃ na jānāti—**he does not know the actions that are the basis for offenses; he does not know the origin stories; he does not know the rules; he does not know the right order of words; he does not know the sequence of statements.*";
P_HTM[10913]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā nānuyuñjitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10914]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā anuyuñjitabbaṃ.**But when a monk has five qualities, he may be examined:*";
P_HTM[10915]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10916]="*Vatthuṃ jānāti, nidānaṃ jānāti, paññattiṃ jānāti, padapaccābhaṭṭhaṃ jānāti, anusandhivacanapathaṃ jānāti—**he knows the actions that are the basis for offenses; he knows the origin stories; he knows the rules; he knows the right order of words; he knows the sequence of statements.*";
P_HTM[10917]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā anuyuñjitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10918]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā nānuyuñjitabbaṃ.**When a monk has five other qualities, he should not be examined:*";
P_HTM[10919]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10920]="*Āpattiṃ na jānāti, āpattisamuṭṭhānaṃ na jānāti, āpattiyā payogaṃ na jānāti, āpattiyā vūpasamaṃ na jānāti, āpattiyā na vinicchayakusalo hoti—**he does not know the offenses; he does not know the origin of the offenses; he does not know the kind of effort required to commit the offenses; he does not know the settling of offenses; he is not skilled in deciding on offenses.*";
P_HTM[10921]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā nānuyuñjitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10922]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā anuyuñjitabbaṃ.**But when a monk has five qualities, he may be examined:*";
P_HTM[10923]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10924]="*Āpattiṃ jānāti, āpattisamuṭṭhānaṃ jānāti, āpattiyā payogaṃ jānāti, āpattiyā vūpasamaṃ jānāti, āpattiyā vinicchayakusalo hoti—**he knows the offenses; he know the origin of the offenses; he knows the kind of effort required to commit the offenses; he knows the settling of offenses; he is skilled in deciding on offenses.*";
P_HTM[10925]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā anuyuñjitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10926]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā nānuyuñjitabbaṃ.**When a monk has five other qualities, he should not be examined:*";
P_HTM[10927]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10928]="*Adhikaraṇaṃ na jānāti, adhikaraṇasamuṭṭhānaṃ na jānāti, adhikaraṇassa payogaṃ na jānāti, adhikaraṇassa vūpasamaṃ na jānāti, adhikaraṇassa na vinicchayakusalo hoti—**he does not know the legal issues; he does not know the origin of the legal issues; he does not know the kind of effort that is the source of the legal issues; he does not know the settling of legal issues; he is not skilled in deciding legal issues.*";
P_HTM[10929]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā nānuyuñjitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10930]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā anuyuñjitabbaṃ.**But when a monk has five qualities, he may be examined:*";
P_HTM[10931]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10932]="*Adhikaraṇaṃ jānāti, adhikaraṇasamuṭṭhānaṃ jānāti, adhikaraṇassa payogaṃ jānāti, adhikaraṇassa vūpasamaṃ jānāti, adhikaraṇassa vinicchayakusalo hoti—**he knows the legal issues; he knows the origin of the legal issues; he knows the kind of effort that is the source of the legal issues; he knows the settling of legal issues; he is skilled in deciding legal issues.”*";
P_HTM[10933]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā anuyuñjitabban”ti.* **";
P_HTM[10934]="*Attādānavaggo niṭṭhito pañcamo.**The fifth sub-chapter on raising an issue is finished.*";
P_HTM[10935]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[10936]="*Parisuddhañca kālena,**“And pure, at an appropriate time,*";
P_HTM[10937]="*Kāruññaṃ okāsena ca;**Compassion, and with permission;*";
P_HTM[10938]="*Attādānaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ,**To raise an issue, legal issue,*";
P_HTM[10939]="*Aparehipi vatthuñca;**And other, and actions that are the basis;*";
P_HTM[10940]="*Suttaṃ dhammaṃ puna vatthuñca,**The Monastic Code, the Teaching, and the actions that are the basis,*";
P_HTM[10941]="*Āpatti adhikaraṇena cāti.**Offenses, and with legal issue.”*";
P_HTM[10942]="*6. Dhutaṅgavagga**6. The sub-chapter on ascetic practices*";
P_HTM[10943]="*“Kati nu kho, bhante, āraññikā”ti?**“Sir, how many kinds of wilderness dwellers are there?”*";
P_HTM[10944]="*“Pañcime, upāli, āraññikā.**“There are five kinds:*";
P_HTM[10945]="*Katame pañca?* **";
P_HTM[10946]="*Mandattā momūhattā āraññiko hoti, pāpiccho icchāpakato āraññiko hoti, ummādā cittakkhepā āraññiko hoti, vaṇṇitaṃ buddhehi buddhasāvakehīti āraññiko hoti, api ca appicchaññeva nissāya santuṭṭhiññeva nissāya, sallekhaññeva nissāya pavivekaññeva nissāya idamatthitaññeva nissāya āraññiko hoti—**those who are wilderness dwellers because of stupidity and folly; because they are overcome by bad desires; because of insanity and derangement; because it was praised by the Buddhas and their disciples; or because of fewness of wishes, contentment, self-elimination, seclusion, and wanting it.”*";
P_HTM[10947]="*ime kho, upāli, pañca āraññikā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[10948]="*“Kati nu kho, bhante, piṇḍapātikāti …pe…**“How many kinds of people are there who only eat almsfood?” …*";
P_HTM[10949]="*kati nu kho, bhante, paṃsukūlikāti …pe…**“How many kinds of rag-robe wearers are there?” …*";
P_HTM[10950]="*kati nu kho, bhante, rukkhamūlikāti …pe…**“How many kinds of people are there who live at the foot of a tree?” …*";
P_HTM[10951]="*kati nu kho, bhante, sosānikāti …pe…**“How many kinds of people are there who live in charnel grounds?” …*";
P_HTM[10952]="*kati nu kho, bhante, abbhokāsikāti …pe…**“How many kinds of people are there who live out in the open?” …*";
P_HTM[10953]="*kati nu kho, bhante, tecīvarikāti …pe…**“How many kinds of people are there who only have three robes?” …*";
P_HTM[10954]="*kati nu kho, bhante, sapadānacārikāti …pe…**“How many kinds of people are there who go on continuous almsround?” …*";
P_HTM[10955]="*kati nu kho, bhante, nesajjikāti …pe…**“How many kinds of people are there who never lie down?” …*";
P_HTM[10956]="*kati nu kho, bhante, yathāsanthatikāti …pe…**“How many kinds of people are there who accept any resting place?” …*";
P_HTM[10957]="*kati nu kho, bhante, ekāsanikāti …pe…**“How many kinds of people are there who eat in one sitting per day?” …*";
P_HTM[10958]="*kati nu kho, bhante, khalupacchābhattikāti …pe…**“How many kinds of people are there who refuse to accept food offered after the meal has begun?” …*";
P_HTM[10959]="*kati nu kho, bhante, pattapiṇḍikā”ti?**“How many kinds of people are there who eat only from the almsbowl?”*";
P_HTM[10960]="*“Pañcime, upāli, pattapiṇḍikā.**“There are five kinds:*";
P_HTM[10961]="*Katame pañca?* **";
P_HTM[10962]="*Mandattā momūhattā pattapiṇḍiko hoti, pāpiccho icchāpakato pattapiṇḍiko hoti, ummādā cittakkhepā pattapiṇḍiko hoti, vaṇṇitaṃ buddhehi buddhasāvakehīti pattapiṇḍiko hoti, api ca appicchaññeva nissāya santuṭṭhiññeva nissāya sallekhaññeva nissāya pavivekaññeva nissāya idamatthitaññeva nissāya pattapiṇḍiko hoti—**those who eat only from the almsbowl because of stupidity and folly; because they are overcome by bad desires; because of insanity and derangement; because it was praised by the Buddhas and their disciples; or because of fewness of wishes, contentment, self-elimination, seclusion, and wanting it.”*";
P_HTM[10963]="*ime kho, upāli, pañca pattapiṇḍikā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[10964]="*Dhutaṅgavaggo niṭṭhito chaṭṭho.**The sixth sub-chapter on ascetic practices is fimished.*";
P_HTM[10965]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[10966]="*Āraññiko piṇḍipaṃsu,**Wilderness dweller, almsfood, rag-robe,*";
P_HTM[10967]="*Rukkhasusānapañcamaṃ;**Tree, charnel ground is the fifth;*";
P_HTM[10968]="*Abbho tecīvarañceva,**Out in the open, and the three robes,*";
P_HTM[10969]="*Sapadānanesajjikā;**Continuous, those who never lie down;*";
P_HTM[10970]="*Santhatekāsanañceva,**Resting place, and one sitting,*";
P_HTM[10971]="*Khalupacchā pattapiṇḍikāti.**After, those who eat only from the bowl.”*";
P_HTM[10972]="*7. Musāvādavagga**7. The sub-chapter on lying*";
P_HTM[10973]="*“Kati nu kho, bhante, musāvādā”ti?**“Sir, how many kinds of lying are there?”*";
P_HTM[10974]="*“Pañcime, upāli, musāvādā.**“There are five kinds:*";
P_HTM[10975]="*Katame pañca?* **";
P_HTM[10976]="*Atthi musāvādo pārājikagāmī, atthi musāvādo saṅghādisesagāmī, atthi musāvādo thullaccayagāmī, atthi musāvādo pācittiyagāmī, atthi musāvādo dukkaṭagāmī—**There is lying that leads to an offense entailing expulsion; there is lying that leads to an offense entailing suspension; there is lying that leads to a serious offense; there is lying that leads to an offense entailing confession; there is lying that leads to an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[10977]="*ime kho, upāli, pañca musāvādā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[10978]="*“Katihi nu kho, bhante, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno saṅghamajjhe uposathaṃ vā pavāraṇaṃ vā ṭhapentassa—‘alaṃ, bhikkhu, mā bhaṇḍanaṃ, mā kalahaṃ, mā viggahaṃ, mā vivādan’ti omadditvā saṅghena uposatho vā pavāraṇā vā kātabbā”ti?**“When a monk has a number of qualities, and he is canceling the observance day or the invitation day in the midst of the Sangha, then they should press him by saying, ‘Enough. No more arguing and disputing,’ and the Sangha should then do the invitation procedure. How many qualities does he have?”*";
P_HTM[10979]="*“Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno saṅghamajjhe uposathaṃ vā pavāraṇaṃ vā ṭhapentassa—‘alaṃ, bhikkhu, mā bhaṇḍanaṃ, mā kalahaṃ, mā viggahaṃ, mā vivādan’ti omadditvā saṅghena uposatho vā pavāraṇā vā kātabbā.**“He has five qualities:*";
P_HTM[10980]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10981]="*Alajjī ca hoti, bālo ca, apakatatto ca, cāvanādhippāyo vattā hoti, no vuṭṭhānādhippāyo—**he is shameless; he is ignorant; he is not a regular monk; he speaks to make someone disrobe; he is not aiming to clear someone’s offense.*";
P_HTM[10982]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno saṅghamajjhe uposathaṃ vā pavāraṇaṃ vā ṭhapentassa—* **";
P_HTM[10983]="*‘alaṃ, bhikkhu, mā bhaṇḍanaṃ, mā kalahaṃ, mā viggahaṃ, mā vivādan’ti omadditvā saṅghena uposatho vā pavāraṇā vā kātabbā.* **";
P_HTM[10984]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno saṅghamajjhe uposathaṃ vā pavāraṇaṃ vā ṭhapentassa—‘alaṃ, bhikkhu, mā bhaṇḍanaṃ, mā kalahaṃ, mā viggahaṃ, mā vivādan’ti omadditvā saṅghena uposatho vā pavāraṇā vā kātabbā.**Or he has five other qualities:*";
P_HTM[10985]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10986]="*Aparisuddhakāyasamācāro hoti, aparisuddhavacīsamācāro hoti, aparisuddhājīvo hoti, bālo hoti abyatto, bhaṇḍanakārako hoti kalahakārako—**he is impure in bodily conduct; he is impure in verbal conduct; he is impure in livelihood; he is ignorant and incompetent; he is quarrelsome and argumentative.”*";
P_HTM[10987]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno saṅghamajjhe uposathaṃ vā pavāraṇaṃ vā ṭhapentassa—‘alaṃ, bhikkhu, mā bhaṇḍanaṃ, mā kalahaṃ, mā viggahaṃ, mā vivādan’ti omadditvā saṅghena uposatho vā pavāraṇā vā kātabbā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[10988]="*“Katihi nu kho, bhante, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno anuyogo na dātabbo”ti?**“When a monk has how many qualities, should he not be allowed to question?”*";
P_HTM[10989]="*“Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno anuyogo na dātabbo.**“When he has five qualities:*";
P_HTM[10990]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10991]="*Āpattānāpattiṃ na jānāti, lahukagarukaṃ āpattiṃ na jānāti, sāvasesānavasesaṃ āpattiṃ na jānāti, duṭṭhullāduṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ na jānāti, sappaṭikammāpaṭikammaṃ āpattiṃ na jānāti—**he does not know the offenses and non-offenses; he does not know the light and heavy offenses; he does not know the curable and incurable offenses; he does not know the grave and minor offenses; he does not know the offenses that are clearable by making amends and the offenses that are not clearable by making amends.*";
P_HTM[10992]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno anuyogo na dātabbo.* **";
P_HTM[10993]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno anuyogo dātabbo.**But when a monk has five other qualities, he may question:*";
P_HTM[10994]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[10995]="*Āpattānāpattiṃ jānāti, lahukagarukaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, sāvasesānavasesaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, duṭṭhullāduṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, sappaṭikammāpaṭikammaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti—**he knows the offenses and non-offenses; he knows the light and heavy offenses; he knows the curable and incurable offenses; he knows the grave and minor offenses; he knows the offenses that are clearable by making amends and the offenses that are not clearable by making amends.”*";
P_HTM[10996]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno anuyogo dātabbo”ti.* **";
P_HTM[10997]="*“Katihi nu kho, bhante, ākārehi bhikkhu āpattiṃ āpajjatī”ti?**“For how many reasons does a monk commit an offense?”*";
P_HTM[10998]="*“Pañcahupāli, ākārehi bhikkhu āpattiṃ āpajjati.**“For five reasons:*";
P_HTM[10999]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11000]="*Alajjitā, aññāṇatā, kukkuccapakatatā, akappiye kappiyasaññitā, kappiye akappiyasaññitā—**because of shamelessness, because of ignorance, because of being overcome by anxiety, because of perceiving what is unallowable as allowable, because of perceiving what is allowable as unallowable.*";
P_HTM[11001]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahākārehi bhikkhu āpattiṃ āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[11002]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahākārehi bhikkhu āpattiṃ āpajjati.**A monk also commits an offense for five other reasons:*";
P_HTM[11003]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11004]="*Adassanena, assavanena, pasuttakatā, tathāsaññī, satisammosā—**because of not seeing; because of not hearing; because of sleeping; because of perceiving it as allowable; because of absentmindedness.”*";
P_HTM[11005]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahākārehi bhikkhu āpattiṃ āpajjatī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[11006]="*“Kati nu kho, bhante, verā”ti?**“How many kinds of fear are there?”*";
P_HTM[11007]="*“Pañcime, upāli, verā.**“There are five:*";
P_HTM[11008]="*Katame pañca?* **";
P_HTM[11009]="*Pāṇātipāto, adinnādānaṃ, kāmesumicchācāro, musāvādo, surāmerayamajjappamādaṭṭhānaṃ—**killing living beings; stealing; sexual misconduct; lying; alcohol, which causes heedlessness.”*";
P_HTM[11010]="*ime kho, upāli, pañca verā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[11011]="*“Kati nu kho, bhante, veramaṇiyo”ti?**“How many kinds of abstentions are there?”*";
P_HTM[11012]="*“Pañcimā, upāli, veramaṇiyo.**“There are five:*";
P_HTM[11013]="*Katamā pañca?* **";
P_HTM[11014]="*Pāṇātipātā veramaṇī, adinnādānā veramaṇī, kāmesumicchācārā veramaṇī, musāvādā veramaṇī, surāmerayamajjappamādaṭṭhānā veramaṇī—**abstention from killing living beings; from stealing; from sexual misconduct; from lying; from alcohol, which causes heedlessness.”*";
P_HTM[11015]="*imā kho, upāli, pañca veramaṇiyo”ti.* **";
P_HTM[11016]="*“Kati nu kho, bhante, byasanānī”ti?**“How many kinds of losses are there?”*";
P_HTM[11017]="*“Pañcimāni, upāli, byasanāni.**“There are five:*";
P_HTM[11018]="*Katamāni pañca?* **";
P_HTM[11019]="*Ñātibyasanaṃ, bhogabyasanaṃ, rogabyasanaṃ, sīlabyasanaṃ, diṭṭhibyasanaṃ—**loss of relatives, property, health, morality, and view.”*";
P_HTM[11020]="*imāni kho, upāli, pañca byasanānī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[11021]="*“Kati nu kho, bhante, sampadā”ti?**“How many kinds of successes are there?”*";
P_HTM[11022]="*“Pañcimā, upāli, sampadā.**“There are five:*";
P_HTM[11023]="*Katamā pañca?* **";
P_HTM[11024]="*Ñātisampadā, bhogasampadā, ārogyasampadā, sīlasampadā, diṭṭhisampadā—**success in relatives, property, health, morality, and view.”*";
P_HTM[11025]="*imā kho, upāli, pañca sampadā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[11026]="*Musāvādavaggo niṭṭhito sattamo.**The seventh sub-chapter on lying is finished.*";
P_HTM[11027]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[11028]="*Musāvādo ca omaddi,**“And lying, pressed,*";
P_HTM[11029]="*aparehi anuyogo;**Other, question;*";
P_HTM[11030]="*Āpattiñca aparehi,**And offense, other,*";
P_HTM[11031]="*verā veramaṇīpi ca;**Fear, and abstention;*";
P_HTM[11032]="*Byasanaṃ sampadā ceva,**Loss, and success—*";
P_HTM[11033]="*sattamo vaggasaṅgahoti.**The compilation of the seventh sub-chapter is finished.”*";
P_HTM[11034]="*8. Bhikkhunovādavagga**8. The sub-chapter on instructing the nuns*";
P_HTM[11035]="*“Katihi nu kho, bhante, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno bhikkhunisaṅgheneva kammaṃ kātabban”ti?**“Sir, when a monk has how many qualities, should the Sangha of nuns do a legal procedure against him?”*";
P_HTM[11036]="*“Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno bhikkhunisaṅgheneva kammaṃ kātabbaṃ, avandiyo so bhikkhu bhikkhunisaṅghena.**“They should do a legal procedure against him, prohibiting the Sangha of nuns from paying respect to him, when he has five qualities:*";
P_HTM[11037]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11038]="*Vivaritvā kāyaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ dasseti, ūruṃ dasseti, aṅgajātaṃ dasseti, ubho aṃsakūṭe dasseti, obhāsati, gihī sampayojeti—**he exposes his body to the nuns; he exposes his thighs to the nuns; he exposes his genitals to the nuns; he exposes both shoulders to the nuns; he speaks indecently to the nuns; and he associates inappropriately with householders.*";
P_HTM[11039]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno bhikkhunisaṅgheneva kammaṃ kātabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[11040]="*Avandiyo so bhikkhu bhikkhunisaṅghena.* **";
P_HTM[11041]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno bhikkhunisaṅgheneva kammaṃ kātabbaṃ, avandiyo so bhikkhu bhikkhunisaṅghena.**They should also do a legal procedure against him, prohibiting the Sangha of nuns from paying respect to him, when he has five other qualities:*";
P_HTM[11042]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11043]="*Bhikkhunīnaṃ alābhāya parisakkati, bhikkhunīnaṃ anatthāya parisakkati, bhikkhunīnaṃ avāsāya parisakkati, bhikkhuniyo akkosati paribhāsati, bhikkhū bhikkhunīhi bhedeti—**he is trying to stop nuns from acquiring material gains; he is trying to harm nuns; he is trying to get nuns to lose their place of residence; he abuses and reviles nuns; he causes the monks to dissociate from the nuns.*";
P_HTM[11044]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno bhikkhunisaṅgheneva kammaṃ kātabbaṃ, avandiyo so bhikkhu bhikkhunisaṅghena.* **";
P_HTM[11045]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno bhikkhunisaṅgheneva kammaṃ kātabbaṃ, avandiyo so bhikkhu bhikkhunisaṅghena.**They should also do a legal procedure against him, prohibiting the Sangha of nuns from paying respect to him, when he has five other qualities:*";
P_HTM[11046]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11047]="*Bhikkhunīnaṃ alābhāya parisakkati, bhikkhunīnaṃ anatthāya parisakkati, bhikkhunīnaṃ avāsāya parisakkati, bhikkhuniyo akkosati paribhāsati, bhikkhū bhikkhunīhi sampayojeti—**he is trying to stop nuns from acquiring material gains; he is trying to harm nuns; he is trying to get nuns to lose their place of residence; he abuses and reviles nuns; he makes the monks associate inappropriately with the nuns.”*";
P_HTM[11048]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno bhikkhunisaṅgheneva kammaṃ kātabbaṃ, avandiyo so bhikkhu bhikkhunisaṅghenā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[11049]="*“Katihi nu kho, bhante, aṅgehi samannāgatāya bhikkhuniyā kammaṃ kātabban”ti?**“When a nun has how many qualities, should a legal procedure be done against her?”*";
P_HTM[11050]="*“Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgatāya bhikkhuniyā kammaṃ kātabbaṃ.**“When she has five qualities:*";
P_HTM[11051]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11052]="*Vivaritvā kāyaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ dasseti, ūruṃ dasseti, aṅgajātaṃ dasseti, ubho aṃsakūṭe dasseti, obhāsati, gihī sampayojeti—**she exposes her body to the monks; she exposes her thighs to the monks; she exposes her genitals to the monks; she exposes both shoulders to the monks; she speaks indecently to the monks; and she associates inappropriately with householders.*";
P_HTM[11053]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatāya bhikkhuniyā kammaṃ kātabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[11054]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatāya bhikkhuniyā kammaṃ kātabbaṃ.**When a nun has five other qualities, should a legal procedure be done against her:*";
P_HTM[11055]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11056]="*Bhikkhūnaṃ alābhāya parisakkati, bhikkhūnaṃ anatthāya parisakkati, bhikkhūnaṃ avāsāya parisakkati, bhikkhū akkosati paribhāsati, bhikkhuniyo bhikkhūhi bhedeti—**she is trying to stop monks from acquiring material gains; she is trying to harm monks; she is trying to get monks to lose their place of residence; she abuses and reviles monks; she causes the nuns to dissociate from the monks.*";
P_HTM[11057]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatāya bhikkhuniyā kammaṃ kātabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[11058]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatāya bhikkhuniyā kammaṃ kātabbaṃ.**When a nun has five other qualities, should a legal procedure be done against her:*";
P_HTM[11059]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11060]="*Bhikkhūnaṃ alābhāya parisakkati, bhikkhūnaṃ anatthāya parisakkati, bhikkhūnaṃ avāsāya parisakkati, bhikkhū akkosati paribhāsati, bhikkhuniyo bhikkhūhi sampayojeti—**she is trying to stop monks from acquiring material gains; she is trying to harm monks; she is trying to get monks to lose their place of residence; she abuses and reviles monks; she makes the nuns associate inappropriately with the monks.”*";
P_HTM[11061]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatāya bhikkhuniyā kammaṃ kātabban”ti.* **";
P_HTM[11062]="*“Katihi nu kho, bhante, aṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā bhikkhunīnaṃ ovādo na ṭhapetabbo”ti?**“When a monk has how many qualities, should he not cancel the instruction of the nuns?”*";
P_HTM[11063]="*“Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā bhikkhunīnaṃ ovādo na ṭhapetabbo.**“When he has five qualities:*";
P_HTM[11064]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11065]="*Alajjī ca hoti, bālo ca, apakatatto ca, cāvanādhippāyo vattā hoti, no vuṭṭhānādhippāyo—**he is shameless; he is ignorant; he is not a regular monk; he speaks to make someone disrobe; he is not aiming to clear someone’s offense.*";
P_HTM[11066]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā bhikkhunīnaṃ ovādo na ṭhapetabbo.* **";
P_HTM[11067]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā bhikkhunīnaṃ ovādo na ṭhapetabbo.**When a monk has five other qualities, he should not cancel the instruction of the nuns:*";
P_HTM[11068]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11069]="*Aparisuddhakāyasamācāro hoti, aparisuddhavacīsamācāro hoti, aparisuddhājīvo hoti, bālo hoti, abyatto, na paṭibalo anuyuñjiyamāno anuyogaṃ dātuṃ—**he is impure in bodily conduct; he is impure in verbal conduct; he is impure in livelihood; he is ignorant and incompetent; he is incapable of answering properly when questioned.*";
P_HTM[11070]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā bhikkhunīnaṃ ovādo na ṭhapetabbo.* **";
P_HTM[11071]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā bhikkhunīnaṃ ovādo na ṭhapetabbo.**When a monk has five other qualities, he should not cancel the instruction of the nuns:*";
P_HTM[11072]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11073]="*Kāyikena anācārena samannāgato hoti, vācasikena anācārena samannāgato hoti, kāyikavācasikena anācārena samannāgato hoti, bhikkhunīnaṃ akkosakaparibhāsako hoti, bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ saṃsaṭṭho viharati ananulomikena saṃsaggena—**he is improperly behaved by body; he is improperly behaved by speech; he is improperly behaved by body and speech; he abuses and reviles nuns; and he socializes improperly with the nuns.*";
P_HTM[11074]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā bhikkhunīnaṃ ovādo na ṭhapetabbo.* **";
P_HTM[11075]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā bhikkhunīnaṃ ovādo na ṭhapetabbo.**When a monk has five other qualities, he should not cancel the instruction of the nuns:*";
P_HTM[11076]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11077]="*Alajjī ca hoti, bālo ca, apakatatto ca, bhaṇḍanakārako ca hoti kalahakārako, sikkhāya ca na paripūrikārī—**he is shameless, ignorant, and not a regular monk, and he is quarrelsome and argumentative, and he does not fulfil the training.”*";
P_HTM[11078]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā bhikkhunīnaṃ ovādo na ṭhapetabbo”ti.* **";
P_HTM[11079]="*“Katihi nu kho, bhante, aṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā bhikkhunīnaṃ ovādo na gahetabbo”ti?**“When a monk has how many qualities, should he not agree to instruct the nuns?”*";
P_HTM[11080]="*“Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā bhikkhunīnaṃ ovādo na gahetabbo.**“When he has five qualities:*";
P_HTM[11081]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11082]="*Kāyikena anācārena samannāgato hoti, vācasikena anācārena samannāgato hoti, kāyikavācasikena anācārena samannāgato hoti, bhikkhunīnaṃ akkosakaparibhāsako hoti, bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ saṃsaṭṭho viharati ananulomikena saṃsaggena—**he is improperly behaved by body; he is improperly behaved by speech; he is improperly behaved by body and speech; he abuses and reviles nuns; and he socializes improperly with the nuns.*";
P_HTM[11083]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā bhikkhunīnaṃ ovādo na gahetabbo.* **";
P_HTM[11084]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā bhikkhunīnaṃ ovādo na gahetabbo.**When a monk has five other qualities, he should not agree to instruct the nuns:*";
P_HTM[11085]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11086]="*Alajjī ca hoti, bālo ca, apakatatto ca, gamiko vā hoti, gilāno vā—**he is shameless, ignorant, and not a regular monk, or he is about to depart, or he is sick.”*";
P_HTM[11087]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā bhikkhunīnaṃ ovādo na gahetabbo”ti.* **";
P_HTM[11088]="*“Katihi nu kho, bhante, aṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ na sākacchitabbo”ti?**“When a monk has how many qualities, should one not discuss with him?”*";
P_HTM[11089]="*“Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ na sākacchitabbo.**“When he has five qualities:*";
P_HTM[11090]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11091]="*Na asekkhena sīlakkhandhena samannāgato hoti, na asekkhena samādhikkhandhena samannāgato hoti, na asekkhena paññākkhandhena samannāgato hoti, na asekkhena vimuttikkhandhena samannāgato hoti, na asekkhena vimuttiñāṇadassanakkhandhena samannāgato hoti—**He doesn’t have the virtue, stillness, wisdom, freedom, or knowledge and vision of freedom of one who is fully trained.*";
P_HTM[11092]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ na sākacchitabbo.* **";
P_HTM[11093]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ sākacchitabbo.**But when a monk has five qualities, one may discuss with him:*";
P_HTM[11094]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11095]="*Asekkhena sīlakkhandhena samannāgato hoti, asekkhena samādhikkhandhena samannāgato hoti, asekkhena paññākkhandhena samannāgato hoti, asekkhena vimuttikkhandhena samannāgato hoti, asekkhena vimuttiñāṇadassanakkhandhena samannāgato hoti—**He has the virtue, stillness, wisdom, freedom, and knowledge and vision of freedom of one who is fully trained.*";
P_HTM[11096]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ sākacchitabbo.* **";
P_HTM[11097]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ na sākacchitabbo.**When a monk has five other qualities, one should not discuss with him:*";
P_HTM[11098]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11099]="*Na atthapaṭisambhidāpatto hoti, na dhammapaṭisambhidāpatto hoti, na niruttipaṭisambhidāpatto hoti, na paṭibhānapaṭisambhidāpatto hoti, yathāvimuttaṃ cittaṃ na paccavekkhitā—**he has not achieved the analysis of meaning, the analysis of text, the analysis of terminology, and the analysis of articulation, and he reviews the extent of his mind’s freedom.*";
P_HTM[11100]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ na sākacchitabbo.* **";
P_HTM[11101]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ sākacchitabbo.**But when a monk has five qualities, one may discuss with him:*";
P_HTM[11102]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11103]="*Atthapaṭisambhidāpatto hoti, dhammapaṭisambhidāpatto hoti, niruttipaṭisambhidāpatto hoti, paṭibhānapaṭisambhidāpatto hoti, yathāvimuttaṃ cittaṃ paccavekkhitā—**he has not achieved the analysis of meaning, the analysis of text, the analysis of terminology, and the analysis of articulation, and he reviews the extent of his mind’s freedom.”*";
P_HTM[11104]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ sākacchitabbo”ti.* **";
P_HTM[11105]="*Bhikkhunovādavaggo niṭṭhito aṭṭhamo.**The eighth sub-chapter on instructing the nuns is finished.*";
P_HTM[11106]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[11107]="*Bhikkhunīheva kātabbaṃ,**“The nuns should do,*";
P_HTM[11108]="*aparehi tathā duve;**And another two of the same;*";
P_HTM[11109]="*Bhikkhunīnaṃ tayo kammā,**Three on legal procedures against nuns,*";
P_HTM[11110]="*na ṭhapetabbā dve dukā;**Twice two on should not cancel;*";
P_HTM[11111]="*Na gahetabbā dve vuttā,**Two were spoken on should not agree,*";
P_HTM[11112]="*sākacchāsu ca dve dukāti.**And twice two on discussions.”*";
P_HTM[11113]="*9. Ubbāhikavagga**9. The sub-chapter on committees*";
P_HTM[11114]="*“Katihi nu kho, bhante, aṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu ubbāhikāya na sammannitabbo”ti?**“When a monk has how many qualities, should he not be appointed to a committee?”*";
P_HTM[11115]="*“Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu ubbāhikāya na sammannitabbo.**“When he has five qualities:*";
P_HTM[11116]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11117]="*Na atthakusalo hoti, na dhammakusalo hoti, na niruttikusalo hoti, na byañjanakusalo hoti, na pubbāparakusalo hoti—**he is not skilled in the meaning, the Teaching, the terminology, the wording, or the sequence.*";
P_HTM[11118]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu ubbāhikāya na sammannitabbo.* **";
P_HTM[11119]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu ubbāhikāya sammannitabbo.**But when a monk has five qualities, he may be appointed to a committee:*";
P_HTM[11120]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11121]="*Atthakusalo hoti, dhammakusalo hoti, niruttikusalo hoti, byañjanakusalo hoti, pubbāparakusalo hoti—**he is skilled in the meaning, the Teaching, the terminology, the wording, and the sequence.*";
P_HTM[11122]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu ubbāhikāya sammannitabbo.* **";
P_HTM[11123]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu ubbāhikāya na sammannitabbo.**When a monk has five other qualities, he should not be appointed to a committee:*";
P_HTM[11124]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11125]="*Kodhano hoti kodhābhibhūto, makkhī hoti makkhābhibhūto, paḷāsī hoti paḷāsābhibhūto, issukī hoti issābhibhūto, sandiṭṭhiparāmāsī hoti ādhānaggāhī duppaṭinissaggī—**He is angry, overcome by anger; he is denigrating, overcome by denigration; he is controlling, overcome by being controlling, and he is envious, overcome by envy; and he obstinately grasps his own views and only gives them up with difficulty.*";
P_HTM[11126]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu ubbāhikāya na sammannitabbo.* **";
P_HTM[11127]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu ubbāhikāya sammannitabbo.**But when a monk has five qualities, he may be appointed to a committee:*";
P_HTM[11128]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11129]="*Na kodhano hoti na kodhābhibhūto, na makkhī hoti na makkhābhibhūto, na paḷāsī hoti na paḷāsābhibhūto, na issukī hoti na issābhibhūto, asandiṭṭhiparāmāsī hoti anādhānaggāhī suppaṭinissaggī—**He is not angry or overcome by anger; he is not denigrating or overcome by denigration; he is not controlling or overcome by being controlling, and he is not envious or overcome by envy; and he does not obstinately grasps his own views and only gives them up with difficulty.*";
P_HTM[11130]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu ubbāhikāya sammannitabbo.* **";
P_HTM[11131]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu ubbāhikāya na sammannitabbo.**When a monk has five other qualities, he should not be appointed to a committee:*";
P_HTM[11132]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11133]="*Kuppati, byāpajjati, patiṭṭhiyati, kopaṃ janeti, akkhamo hoti apadakkhiṇaggāhī anusāsaniṃ—**he gets agitated, has ill will, becomes hardhearted, gives rise to anger, and is resistant and does not receive instructions respectfully.*";
P_HTM[11134]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu ubbāhikāya na sammannitabbo.* **";
P_HTM[11135]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu ubbāhikāya sammannitabbo.**But when a monk has five qualities, he may be appointed to a committee:*";
P_HTM[11136]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11137]="*Na kuppati, na byāpajjati, na patiṭṭhiyati, na kopaṃ janeti, khamo hoti padakkhiṇaggāhī anusāsaniṃ—**he does not get agitated, does not have ill will, does not become hardhearted, does not give rise to anger, and is not resistant but receives instructions respectfully.*";
P_HTM[11138]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu ubbāhikāya sammannitabbo.* **";
P_HTM[11139]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu ubbāhikāya na sammannitabbo.**When a monk has five other qualities, he should not be appointed to a committee:*";
P_HTM[11140]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11141]="*Pasāretā hoti no sāretā, anokāsakammaṃ kāretvā pavattā hoti, na yathādhamme yathāvinaye yathāpattiyā codetā hoti, na yathādhamme yathāvinaye yathāpattiyā kāretā hoti, na yathādiṭṭhiyā byākatā hoti—**he causes confusion, not clarity of mind; he speaks without having obtained permission; he does not accuse others according to the Teaching, the Monastic Law, or their offense; he does not make amends according to the Teaching, the Monastic Law, or his offense; he does not explain things according to his own view.*";
P_HTM[11142]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu ubbāhikāya na sammannitabbo.* **";
P_HTM[11143]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu ubbāhikāya sammannitabbo.**But when a monk has five qualities, he may be appointed to a committee:*";
P_HTM[11144]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11145]="*Sāretā hoti no pasāretā, okāsakammaṃ kāretvā pavattā hoti, yathādhamme yathāvinaye yathāpattiyā codetā hoti, yathādhamme yathāvinaye yathāpattiyā kāretā hoti, yathādiṭṭhiyā byākatā hoti—**he causes clarity of mind, not confusion; he speaks after obtaining permission; he accuses others according to the Teaching, the Monastic Law, and their offense; he makes amends according to the Teaching, the Monastic Law, and his offense; he explains things according to his own view.*";
P_HTM[11146]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu ubbāhikāya sammannitabbo.* **";
P_HTM[11147]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu ubbāhikāya na sammannitabbo.**When a monk has five other qualities, he should not be appointed to a committee:*";
P_HTM[11148]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11149]="*Chandāgatiṃ gacchati, dosāgatiṃ gacchati, mohāgatiṃ gacchati, bhayāgatiṃ gacchati, alajjī ca hoti—**he is swayed by desire, ill will, confusion, and fear, and he is shameless.*";
P_HTM[11150]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu ubbāhikāya na sammannitabbo.* **";
P_HTM[11151]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu ubbāhikāya sammannitabbo.**But when a monk has five qualities, he may be appointed to a committee:*";
P_HTM[11152]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11153]="*Na chandāgatiṃ gacchati, na dosāgatiṃ gacchati, na mohāgatiṃ gacchati, na bhayāgatiṃ gacchati, lajjī ca hoti—**he is not swayed by desire, ill will, confusion, or fear, and he has a sense of conscience.*";
P_HTM[11154]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu ubbāhikāya sammannitabbo.* **";
P_HTM[11155]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu ubbāhikāya na sammannitabbo.**When a monk has five other qualities, he should not be appointed to a committee:*";
P_HTM[11156]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11157]="*Chandāgatiṃ gacchati, dosāgatiṃ gacchati, mohāgatiṃ gacchati, bhayāgatiṃ gacchati, akusalo ca hoti vinaye—**he is swayed by desire, ill will, confusion, and fear, and he is unskilled in the Monastic Law.*";
P_HTM[11158]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu ubbāhikāya na sammannitabbo.* **";
P_HTM[11159]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu ubbāhikāya sammannitabbo.**But when a monk has five qualities, he may be appointed to a committee:*";
P_HTM[11160]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11161]="*Na chandāgatiṃ gacchati, na dosāgatiṃ gacchati, na mohāgatiṃ gacchati, na bhayāgatiṃ gacchati, kusalo ca hoti vinaye—**he is not swayed by desire, ill will, confusion, or fear, and he is skilled in the Monastic Law.”*";
P_HTM[11162]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu ubbāhikāya sammannitabbo”ti.* **";
P_HTM[11163]="*“Katihi nu kho, bhante, aṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu bālotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchatī”ti?**“When a monk has how many qualities, is he considered ignorant?”*";
P_HTM[11164]="*“Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu bālotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.**“When he has five qualities:*";
P_HTM[11165]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11166]="*Suttaṃ na jānāti, suttānulomaṃ na jānāti, vinayaṃ na jānāti, vinayānulomaṃ na jānāti, na ca ṭhānāṭhānakusalo hoti—**he does not know the Monastic Code; he does not know what is in accordance with the Monastic Code; he does not know the Monastic Law; he does not know what is in accordance with the Monastic Law; he is not skilled in what is and what is not possible.*";
P_HTM[11167]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu bālotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.* **";
P_HTM[11168]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu paṇḍitotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.**But when a monk has five qualities, he is considered learned:*";
P_HTM[11169]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11170]="*Suttaṃ jānāti, suttānulomaṃ jānāti, vinayaṃ jānāti, vinayānulomaṃ jānāti, ṭhānāṭhānakusalo ca hoti—**he knows the Monastic Code; he knows what is in accordance with the Monastic Code; he knows the Monastic Law; he knows what is in accordance with the Monastic Law; he is skilled in what is and what is not possible.*";
P_HTM[11171]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu paṇḍitotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.* **";
P_HTM[11172]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu bālotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.**When a monk has five other qualities, he is considered ignorant:*";
P_HTM[11173]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11174]="*Dhammaṃ na jānāti, dhammānulomaṃ jānāti, vinayaṃ na jānāti, vinayānulomaṃ na jānāti, na ca pubbāparakusalo hoti—**he does not know the Teaching; he does not know what is in accordance with the Teaching; he does not know the Monastic Law; he does not know what is in accordance with the Monastic Law; he is not skilled in sequence.*";
P_HTM[11175]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu bālotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.* **";
P_HTM[11176]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu paṇḍitotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.**But when a monk has five qualities, he is considered learned:*";
P_HTM[11177]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11178]="*Dhammaṃ jānāti, dhammānulomaṃ jānāti, vinayaṃ jānāti, vinayānulomaṃ jānāti, pubbāparakusalo ca hoti—**he knows the Teaching; he knows what is in accordance with the Teaching; he knows the Monastic Law; he knows what is in accordance with the Monastic Law; he is skilled in sequence.*";
P_HTM[11179]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu paṇḍitotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.* **";
P_HTM[11180]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu bālotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.**When a monk has five other qualities, he is considered ignorant:*";
P_HTM[11181]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11182]="*Vatthuṃ na jānāti, nidānaṃ na jānāti, paññattiṃ na jānāti, padapaccābhaṭṭhaṃ na jānāti, anusandhivacanapathaṃ na jānāti—**he does not know the actions that are the basis for offenses; he does not know the origin stories; he does not know the rules; he does not know the right order of words; he does not know the sequence of statements.*";
P_HTM[11183]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu bālotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.* **";
P_HTM[11184]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu paṇḍitotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.**But when a monk has five qualities, he is considered learned:*";
P_HTM[11185]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11186]="*Vatthuṃ jānāti, nidānaṃ jānāti, paññattiṃ jānāti, padapaccābhaṭṭhaṃ jānāti, anusandhivacanapathaṃ jānāti—**he knows the actions that are the basis for offenses; he knows the origin stories; he knows the rules; he knows the right order of words; he knows the sequence of statements.*";
P_HTM[11187]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu paṇḍitotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.* **";
P_HTM[11188]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu bālotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.**When a monk has five other qualities, he is considered ignorant:*";
P_HTM[11189]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11190]="*Āpattiṃ na jānāti, āpattisamuṭṭhānaṃ na jānāti, āpattiyā payogaṃ na jānāti, āpattiyā vūpasamaṃ na jānāti, āpattiyā na vinicchayakusalo hoti—**he does not know the offenses; he does not know the origin of the offenses; he does not know the kind of effort required to commit the offenses; he does not know the settling of offenses; he is not skilled in deciding on offenses.*";
P_HTM[11191]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu bālotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.* **";
P_HTM[11192]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu paṇḍitotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.**But when a monk has five qualities, he is considered learned:*";
P_HTM[11193]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11194]="*Āpattiṃ jānāti, āpattisamuṭṭhānaṃ jānāti, āpattiyā payogaṃ jānāti, āpattiyā vūpasamaṃ jānāti, āpattiyā vinicchayakusalo hoti—**he knows the offenses; he know the origin of the offenses; he knows the kind of effort required to commit the offenses; he knows the settling of offenses; he is skilled in deciding on offenses.*";
P_HTM[11195]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu paṇḍitotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.* **";
P_HTM[11196]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu bālotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.**When a monk has five other qualities, he is considered ignorant:*";
P_HTM[11197]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11198]="*Adhikaraṇaṃ na jānāti, adhikaraṇasamuṭṭhānaṃ na jānāti, adhikaraṇassa payogaṃ na jānāti, adhikaraṇassa vūpasamaṃ na jānāti, adhikaraṇassa na vinicchayakusalo hoti—**he does not know the legal issues; he does not know the origin of the legal issues; he does not know the kind of effort that is the source of the legal issues; he does not know the settling of legal issues; he is not skilled in deciding legal issues.*";
P_HTM[11199]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu bālotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.* **";
P_HTM[11200]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu paṇḍitotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.**But when a monk has five qualities, he is considered as learned:*";
P_HTM[11201]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11202]="*Adhikaraṇaṃ jānāti, adhikaraṇasamuṭṭhānaṃ jānāti, adhikaraṇassa payogaṃ jānāti, adhikaraṇassa vūpasamaṃ jānāti, adhikaraṇassa vinicchayakusalo hoti—**he knows the legal issues; he knows the origin of the legal issues; he knows the kind of effort that is the source of the legal issues; he knows the settling of legal issues; he is skilled in deciding legal issues.”*";
P_HTM[11203]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu paṇḍitotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchatī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[11204]="*Ubbāhikavaggo niṭṭhito navamo.**The ninth sub-chapter on committees is finished.*";
P_HTM[11205]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[11206]="*Na atthakusalo ceva,**“And not skilled in the meaning,*";
P_HTM[11207]="*kodhano kuppatī ca yo;**Angry, and one who is agitated;*";
P_HTM[11208]="*Pasāretā chandāgatiṃ,**One who confuses, swayed by desire,*";
P_HTM[11209]="*akusalo tatheva ca.**And also unskilled.*";
P_HTM[11210]="*Suttaṃ dhammañca vatthuñca,**The Monastic Code, and the Teaching, and the actions that are the basis,*";
P_HTM[11211]="*āpatti adhikaraṇaṃ;**Offenses, legal issues—*";
P_HTM[11212]="*Dve dve pakāsitā sabbe,**All proclaimed in groups of two:*";
P_HTM[11213]="*kaṇhasukkaṃ vijānathāti.**You should understand the dark and the bright.”*";
P_HTM[11214]="*10. Adhikaraṇavūpasamavagga**10. The sub-chapter on the resolving of legal issues*";
P_HTM[11215]="*“Katihi nu kho, bhante, aṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu nālaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametun”ti?**“When a monk has how many qualities, is he unqualified to resolve a legal issue?”*";
P_HTM[11216]="*“Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu nālaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ.**“When he has five qualities:*";
P_HTM[11217]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11218]="*Āpattiṃ na jānāti, āpattisamuṭṭhānaṃ na jānāti, āpattiyā payogaṃ na jānāti, āpattiyā vūpasamaṃ na jānāti, āpattiyā na vinicchayakusalo hoti—**he does not know the offenses; he does not know the origin of the offenses; he does not know the kind of effort required to commit the offenses; he does not know the settling of offenses; he is not skilled in deciding on offenses.*";
P_HTM[11219]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu nālaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[11220]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu alaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ.**But when a monk has five qualities, he is qualified to resolve a legal issue:*";
P_HTM[11221]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11222]="*Āpattiṃ jānāti, āpattisamuṭṭhānaṃ jānāti, āpattiyā payogaṃ jānāti, āpattiyā vūpasamaṃ jānāti, āpattiyā vinicchayakusalo hoti—**he knows the offenses; he know the origin of the offenses; he knows the kind of effort required to commit the offenses; he knows the settling of offenses; he is skilled in deciding on offenses.*";
P_HTM[11223]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu alaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[11224]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu nālaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ.**When a monk has five other qualities, he is unqualified to resolve a legal issue:*";
P_HTM[11225]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11226]="*Adhikaraṇaṃ na jānāti, adhikaraṇasamuṭṭhānaṃ na jānāti, adhikaraṇassa payogaṃ na jānāti, adhikaraṇassa vūpasamaṃ na jānāti, adhikaraṇassa na vinicchayakusalo hoti—**he does not know the legal issues; he does not know the origin of the legal issues; he does not know the kind of effort that is the source of the legal issues; he does not know the settling of legal issues; he is not skilled in deciding legal issues.*";
P_HTM[11227]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu nālaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[11228]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu alaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ.**But when a monk has five qualities, he is qualified to resolve a legal issue:*";
P_HTM[11229]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11230]="*Adhikaraṇaṃ jānāti, adhikaraṇasamuṭṭhānaṃ jānāti, adhikaraṇassa payogaṃ jānāti, adhikaraṇassa vūpasamaṃ jānāti, adhikaraṇassa vinicchayakusalo hoti—**he knows the legal issues; he knows the origin of the legal issues; he knows the kind of effort that is the source of the legal issues; he knows the settling of legal issues; he is skilled in deciding legal issues.*";
P_HTM[11231]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu alaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[11232]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu nālaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ.**When a monk has five other qualities, he is unqualified to resolve a legal issue:*";
P_HTM[11233]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11234]="*Chandāgatiṃ gacchati, dosāgatiṃ gacchati, mohāgatiṃ gacchati, bhayāgatiṃ gacchati, alajjī ca hoti—**he is swayed by desire, ill will, confusion, and fear, and he is shameless.*";
P_HTM[11235]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu nālaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[11236]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu alaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ.**But when a monk has five qualities, he is qualified to resolve a legal issue:*";
P_HTM[11237]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11238]="*Na chandāgatiṃ gacchati, na dosāgatiṃ gacchati, na mohāgatiṃ gacchati, na bhayāgatiṃ gacchati, lajjī ca hoti—**he is not swayed by desire, ill will, confusion, or fear, and he has a sense of conscience.*";
P_HTM[11239]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu alaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[11240]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu nālaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ.**When a monk has five other qualities, he is unqualified to resolve a legal issue:*";
P_HTM[11241]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11242]="*Chandāgatiṃ gacchati, dosāgatiṃ gacchati, mohāgatiṃ gacchati, bhayāgatiṃ gacchati, appassuto ca hoti—**he is swayed by desire, ill will, confusion, and fear, and he is ignorant.*";
P_HTM[11243]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu nālaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[11244]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu alaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ.**But when a monk has five qualities, he is qualified to resolve a legal issue:*";
P_HTM[11245]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11246]="*Na chandāgatiṃ gacchati, na dosāgatiṃ gacchati, na mohāgatiṃ gacchati, na bhayāgatiṃ gacchati, bahussuto ca hoti—**he is not swayed by desire, ill will, confusion, or fear, and he is learned.*";
P_HTM[11247]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu alaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[11248]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu nālaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ.**When a monk has five other qualities, he is unqualified to resolve a legal issue:*";
P_HTM[11249]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11250]="*Vatthuṃ na jānāti, nidānaṃ na jānāti, paññattiṃ na jānāti, padapaccābhaṭṭhaṃ na jānāti, anusandhivacanapathaṃ na jānāti—**he does not know the actions that are the basis for offenses; he does not know the origin stories; he does not know the rules; he does not know the right order of words; he does not know the sequence of statements.*";
P_HTM[11251]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu nālaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[11252]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu alaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ.**But when a monk has five qualities, he is qualified to resolve a legal issue:*";
P_HTM[11253]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11254]="*Vatthuṃ jānāti, nidānaṃ jānāti, paññattiṃ jānāti, padapaccābhaṭṭhaṃ jānāti, anusandhivacanapathaṃ jānāti—**he knows the actions that are the basis for offenses; he knows the origin stories; he knows the rules; he knows the right order of words; he knows the sequence of statements.*";
P_HTM[11255]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu alaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[11256]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu nālaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ.**When a monk has five other qualities, he is unqualified to resolve a legal issue:*";
P_HTM[11257]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11258]="*Chandāgatiṃ gacchati, dosāgatiṃ gacchati, mohāgatiṃ gacchati, bhayāgatiṃ gacchati, akusalo ca hoti vinaye—**he is swayed by desire, ill will, confusion, and fear, and he is unskilled in the Monastic Law.*";
P_HTM[11259]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu nālaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[11260]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu alaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ.**But when a monk has five qualities, he is qualified to resolve a legal issue:*";
P_HTM[11261]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11262]="*Na chandāgatiṃ gacchati, na dosāgatiṃ gacchati, na mohāgatiṃ gacchati, na bhayāgatiṃ gacchati, kusalo ca hoti vinaye—**he is not swayed by desire, ill will, confusion, or fear, and he is skilled in the Monastic Law.*";
P_HTM[11263]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu alaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[11264]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu nālaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ.**When a monk has five other qualities, he is unqualified to resolve a legal issue:*";
P_HTM[11265]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11266]="*Chandāgatiṃ gacchati, dosāgatiṃ gacchati, mohāgatiṃ gacchati, bhayāgatiṃ gacchati, puggalagaru hoti no saṅghagaru—**he is swayed by desire, ill will, confusion, and fear, and he respects individuals, not the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[11267]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu nālaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[11268]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu alaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ.**But when a monk has five qualities, he is qualified to resolve a legal issue:*";
P_HTM[11269]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11270]="*Na chandāgatiṃ gacchati, na dosāgatiṃ gacchati, na mohāgatiṃ gacchati, na bhayāgatiṃ gacchati, saṅghagaru hoti no puggalagaru—**he is not swayed by desire, ill will, confusion, or fear, and he respects the Sangha, not individuals.*";
P_HTM[11271]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu alaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[11272]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu nālaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ.**When a monk has five other qualities, he is unqualified to resolve a legal issue:*";
P_HTM[11273]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11274]="*Chandāgatiṃ gacchati, dosāgatiṃ gacchati, mohāgatiṃ gacchati, bhayāgatiṃ gacchati, āmisagaru hoti no saddhammagaru—**he is swayed by desire, ill will, confusion, and fear; and he values worldly things, not the true Teaching.*";
P_HTM[11275]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu nālaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[11276]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu alaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ.**But when a monk has five qualities, he is qualified to resolve a legal issue:*";
P_HTM[11277]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11278]="*Na chandāgatiṃ gacchati, na dosāgatiṃ gacchati, na mohāgatiṃ gacchati, na bhayāgatiṃ gacchati, saddhammagaru hoti no āmisagaru—**he is not swayed by desire, ill will, confusion, or fear; and he values the true Teaching, not worldly things.”*";
P_HTM[11279]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu alaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametun”ti.* **";
P_HTM[11280]="*“Katihi nu kho, bhante, ākārehi saṅgho bhijjatī”ti?**“Sir, in how many ways is there schism in the Sangha?”*";
P_HTM[11281]="*“Pañcahupāli, ākārehi saṅgho bhijjati.**“In five ways, Upāli:*";
P_HTM[11282]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11283]="*Kammena, uddesena, voharanto, anussāvanena, salākaggāhena—**through a legal procedure, through recitation, through speaking, through a proclamation, and through voting.”*";
P_HTM[11284]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahākārehi saṅgho bhijjatī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[11285]="*“Saṅgharāji saṅgharājīti, bhante, vuccati.**“Sir, we speak of ‘fracture in the Sangha’.*";
P_HTM[11286]="*Kittāvatā nu kho, bhante, saṅgharāji hoti no ca saṅghabhedo?**But how is there fracture in the Sangha, yet not schism?*";
P_HTM[11287]="*Kittāvatā ca pana saṅgharāji ceva hoti saṅghabhedo cā”ti?**And how is there both fracture and schism in the Sangha?”*";
P_HTM[11288]="*“Paññattetaṃ, upāli, mayā āgantukānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ āgantukavattaṃ.**“Upāli, I have laid down the proper conduct for newly arrived monks.*";
P_HTM[11289]="*Evaṃ supaññatte kho, upāli, mayā sikkhāpade āgantukā bhikkhū āgantukavatte na vattanti.**Even though I have carefully laid down the training rules, the newly arrived monks do not practice that proper conduct.*";
P_HTM[11290]="*Evampi kho, upāli, saṅgharāji hoti no ca saṅghabhedo.**In this way, there is fracture in the Sangha, but not schism.*";
P_HTM[11291]="*Paññattetaṃ, upāli, mayā āvāsikānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ āvāsikavattaṃ.**I have laid down the proper conduct for resident monks.*";
P_HTM[11292]="*Evaṃ supaññatte kho, upāli, mayā sikkhāpade āvāsikā bhikkhū āvāsikavatte na vattanti.**Even though I have carefully laid down the training rules, the resident monks do not practice that proper conduct.*";
P_HTM[11293]="*Evampi kho, upāli, saṅgharāji hoti no ca saṅghabhedo.**In this way, there is fracture in the Sangha, but not schism.*";
P_HTM[11294]="*Paññattetaṃ, upāli, mayā bhikkhūnaṃ bhattagge bhattaggavattaṃ—**I have laid down the proper conduct for the monks in the dining hall:*";
P_HTM[11295]="*yathāvuḍḍhaṃ yathārattaṃ yathāpatirūpaṃ aggāsanaṃ aggodakaṃ aggapiṇḍaṃ.**the best seat, the best water, and the best almsfood is to be given out according to seniority and according to what is proper.*";
P_HTM[11296]="*Evaṃ supaññatte kho, upāli, mayā sikkhāpade navā bhikkhū bhattagge therānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ āsanaṃ paṭibāhanti.**Even though I have carefully laid down the training rules, the junior monks block the senior monks from seats.*";
P_HTM[11297]="*Evampi kho, upāli, saṅgharāji hoti no ca saṅghabhedo.**In this way, there is fracture in the Sangha, but not schism.*";
P_HTM[11298]="*Paññattetaṃ, upāli, mayā bhikkhūnaṃ senāsane senāsanavattaṃ—**I have laid down the proper conduct for the monks in regard to dwellings:*";
P_HTM[11299]="*yathāvuḍḍhaṃ yathārattaṃ yathāpatirūpaṃ.**it is to be given out according to seniority and according to what is proper.*";
P_HTM[11300]="*Evaṃ supaññatte kho, upāli, mayā sikkhāpade navā bhikkhū therānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ senāsanaṃ paṭibāhanti.**Even though I have carefully laid down the training rules, the junior monks block the senior monks from dwellings.*";
P_HTM[11301]="*Evampi kho, upāli, saṅgharāji hoti no ca saṅghabhedo.**In this way, there is fracture in the Sangha, but not schism.*";
P_HTM[11302]="*Paññattetaṃ, upāli, mayā bhikkhūnaṃ antosīmāya ekaṃ uposathaṃ ekaṃ pavāraṇaṃ ekaṃ saṅghakammaṃ ekaṃ kammākammaṃ.**For monks within the same monastic boundary I have laid down this: a joint observance-day procedure; a joint invitation-day procedure; joint legal procedures of the Sangha; joint legal procedures of whatever kind.*";
P_HTM[11303]="*Evaṃ supaññatte kho, upāli, mayā sikkhāpade tattheva antosīmāya āvenibhāvaṃ karitvā gaṇaṃ bandhitvā āveniṃ uposathaṃ karonti āveniṃ pavāraṇaṃ karonti āveniṃ saṅghakammaṃ karonti āveniṃ kammākammāni karonti.**Even though I have carefully laid down the training rules, they form a faction, a subgroup, right there within the monastic boundary. They then do a separate observance-day procedure, a separate invitation procedure, a separate legal procedures of the Sangha, or a separate legal procedures of whatever kind.*";
P_HTM[11304]="*Evaṃ kho, upāli, saṅgharāji ceva hoti saṅghabhedo cā”ti.**In this way, there is both fracture and schism in the Sangha.”*";
P_HTM[11305]="*Adhikaraṇavūpasamavaggo niṭṭhito dasamo.**The tenth sub-chapter on the resolving of legal issues is finished.*";
P_HTM[11306]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[11307]="*Āpattiṃ adhikaraṇaṃ,**“Offenses, legal issues,*";
P_HTM[11308]="*chandā appassutena ca;**Desire, and with one who is ignorant;*";
P_HTM[11309]="*Vatthuñca akusalo ca,**And actions that are the basis, and unskilled,*";
P_HTM[11310]="*puggalo āmisena ca;**Individuals, and with worldly things;*";
P_HTM[11311]="*Bhijjati saṅgharāji ca,**Schism, and fracture in the Sangha,*";
P_HTM[11312]="*saṅghabhedo tatheva cāti.**And so too schism in the Sangha.”*";
P_HTM[11313]="*11. Saṅghabhedakavagga**11. The sub-chapter on schism in the Sangha*";
P_HTM[11314]="*“Katihi nu kho, bhante, aṅgehi samannāgato saṅghabhedako āpāyiko nerayiko kappaṭṭho atekiccho”ti?**“Sir, when one who has caused a schism in the Sangha has how many qualities, is he irredeemably destined to an eon in hell?”*";
P_HTM[11315]="*“Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgato saṅghabhedako āpāyiko nerayiko kappaṭṭho atekiccho.**“When he has five qualities, Upāli:*";
P_HTM[11316]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11317]="*Idhupāli, bhikkhu adhammaṃ dhammoti dīpeti, dhammaṃ adhammoti dīpeti, avinayaṃ vinayoti dīpeti, vinayaṃ avinayoti dīpeti, vinidhāya diṭṭhiṃ kammena—**A monk proclaims what is contrary to the Teaching as the Teaching, what is the Teaching as contrary to the Teaching, what is contrary to the Monastic Law as the Monastic Law, what is the Monastic Law as contrary to the Monastic Law, and he misrepresents his view of what is true during the legal procedure that finalizes the schism.*";
P_HTM[11318]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato saṅghabhedako āpāyiko nerayiko kappaṭṭho atekiccho.* **";
P_HTM[11319]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato saṅghabhedako āpāyiko nerayiko kappaṭṭho atekiccho.**When one who has caused a schism in the Sangha has five other qualities, he is irredeemably destined to an eon in hell:*";
P_HTM[11320]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11321]="*Idhupāli, bhikkhu adhammaṃ dhammoti dīpeti, dhammaṃ adhammoti dīpeti, avinayaṃ vinayoti dīpeti, vinayaṃ avinayoti dīpeti, vinidhāya diṭṭhiṃ uddesena—**A monk proclaims what is contrary to the Teaching as the Teaching, what is the Teaching as contrary to the Teaching, what is contrary to the Monastic Law as the Monastic Law, what is the Monastic Law as contrary to the Monastic Law, and he misrepresents his view of what is true during the recitation that finalizes the schism.*";
P_HTM[11322]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato saṅghabhedako āpāyiko nerayiko kappaṭṭho atekiccho.* **";
P_HTM[11323]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato saṅghabhedako āpāyiko nerayiko kappaṭṭho atekiccho.**When one who has caused a schism in the Sangha has five other qualities, he is irredeemably destined to an eon in hell:*";
P_HTM[11324]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
