P_HTM[11395]="*avinidhāya khantiṃ salākaggāhena—**he does not misrepresent his belief of what is true during the voting that finalizes the schism.*";
P_HTM[11396]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato saṅghabhedako na āpāyiko na nerayiko na kappaṭṭho na atekiccho.* **";
P_HTM[11397]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato saṅghabhedako na āpāyiko na nerayiko na kappaṭṭho na atekiccho.**When one who has caused a schism in the Sangha has five other qualities, he is redeemable, not destined to an eon in hell:*";
P_HTM[11398]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11399]="*Idhupāli, bhikkhu adhammaṃ dhammoti dīpeti, dhammaṃ adhammoti dīpeti, avinayaṃ vinayoti dīpeti, vinayaṃ avinayoti dīpeti, avinidhāya ruciṃ kammena …pe…**A monk proclaims what is contrary to the Teaching as the Teaching, what is the Teaching as contrary to the Teaching, what is contrary to the Monastic Law as the Monastic Law, what is the Monastic Law as contrary to the Monastic Law, but he does not misrepresent his acceptance of what is true during the legal procedure that finalizes the schism. …*";
P_HTM[11400]="*avinidhāya ruciṃ uddesena …pe…**he does not misrepresent his acceptance of what is true during the recitation that finalizes the schism. …*";
P_HTM[11401]="*avinidhāya ruciṃ voharanto …pe…**he does not misrepresent his acceptance of what is true while he speaks to finalize the schism. …*";
P_HTM[11402]="*avinidhāya ruciṃ anussāvanena …pe…**he does not misrepresent his acceptance of what is true during the proclamation that finalizes the schism. …*";
P_HTM[11403]="*avinidhāya ruciṃ salākaggāhena—**he does not misrepresent his acceptance of what is true during the voting that finalizes the schism.*";
P_HTM[11404]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato saṅghabhedako na āpāyiko na nerayiko na kappaṭṭho na atekiccho.* **";
P_HTM[11405]="*Aparehipi, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato saṅghabhedako na āpāyiko na nerayiko na kappaṭṭho na atekiccho.**When one who has caused a schism in the Sangha has five other qualities, he is redeemable, not destined to an eon in hell:*";
P_HTM[11406]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11407]="*Idhupāli, bhikkhu adhammaṃ dhammoti dīpeti, dhammaṃ adhammoti dīpeti, avinayaṃ vinayoti dīpeti, vinayaṃ avinayoti dīpeti, avinidhāya saññaṃ kammena …pe…**A monk proclaims what is contrary to the Teaching as the Teaching, what is the Teaching as contrary to the Teaching, what is contrary to the Monastic Law as the Monastic Law, what is the Monastic Law as contrary to the Monastic Law, but he does not misrepresent his perception of what is true during the legal procedure that finalizes the schism. …*";
P_HTM[11408]="*avinidhāya saññaṃ uddesena …pe…**he does not misrepresent his perception of what is true during the recitation that finalizes the schism. …*";
P_HTM[11409]="*avinidhāya saññaṃ voharanto …pe…**he does not misrepresent his perception of what is true while he speaks to finalize the schism. …*";
P_HTM[11410]="*avinidhāya saññaṃ anussāvanena …pe…**he does not misrepresent his perception of what is true during the proclamation that finalizes the schism. …*";
P_HTM[11411]="*avinidhāya saññaṃ salākaggāhena—**he does not misrepresent his perception of what is true during the voting that finalizes the schism.”*";
P_HTM[11412]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato saṅghabhedako na āpāyiko na nerayiko na kappaṭṭho na atekiccho”ti.* **";
P_HTM[11413]="*Dutiyasaṅghabhedakavaggo niṭṭhito dvādasamo.**The twelfth sub-chapter, the second on schism in the Sangha, is finished.*";
P_HTM[11414]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[11415]="*Avinidhāya diṭṭhiṃ kammena,**“He does not misrepresent his view during the legal procedure,*";
P_HTM[11416]="*Uddese voharena ca;**During the recitation, and while he speaks;*";
P_HTM[11417]="*Anussāvane salākena,**During the proclamation, during the voting—*";
P_HTM[11418]="*Pañcete diṭṭhinissitā;**These five are dependent on view;*";
P_HTM[11419]="*Khantiṃ ruciñca saññañca,**Belief, and acceptance, and perception—*";
P_HTM[11420]="*Tayo te pañcadhā nayā.**These three by the fivefold method.*";
P_HTM[11421]="*Heṭṭhime kaṇhapakkhamhi,**As above these are on the dark side,*";
P_HTM[11422]="*samavīsati vidhī yathā;**The twenty ways;*";
P_HTM[11423]="*Tatheva sukkapakkhamhi,**So are there twenty on the bright side,*";
P_HTM[11424]="*samavīsati jānathāti.**You should understand.”*";
P_HTM[11425]="*13. Āvāsikavagga**13. The sub-chapter on resident monks*";
P_HTM[11426]="*“Katihi nu kho, bhante, aṅgehi samannāgato āvāsiko bhikkhu yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye”ti?**“Sir, when a resident monk has how many qualities, is he dumped in hell?”*";
P_HTM[11427]="*“Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgato āvāsiko bhikkhu yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**“When he has five qualities:*";
P_HTM[11428]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11429]="*Chandāgatiṃ gacchati, dosāgatiṃ gacchati, mohāgatiṃ gacchati, bhayāgatiṃ gacchati, saṅghikaṃ puggalikaparibhogena paribhuñjati—**he is swayed by desire, ill will, confusion, or fear, and he uses what belongs to the Sangha as if belonging to an individual.*";
P_HTM[11430]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato āvāsiko bhikkhu yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.* **";
P_HTM[11431]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgato āvāsiko bhikkhu yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge.**But when a resident monk has five qualities, he is deposited in heaven:*";
P_HTM[11432]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11433]="*Na chandāgatiṃ gacchati, na dosāgatiṃ gacchati, na mohāgatiṃ gacchati, na bhayāgatiṃ gacchati, saṅghikaṃ na puggalikaparibhogena paribhuñjati—**he is not swayed by desire, ill will, confusion, and fear, and he does not use what belongs to the Sangha as if belonging to an individual.”*";
P_HTM[11434]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato āvāsiko bhikkhu yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge”ti.* **";
P_HTM[11435]="*“Kati nu kho, bhante, adhammikā vinayabyākaraṇā”ti?**“How many illegitimate explanations of the Monastic Law are there?”*";
P_HTM[11436]="*“Pañcime, upāli, adhammikā vinayabyākaraṇā.**“There are five:*";
P_HTM[11437]="*Katame pañca?* **";
P_HTM[11438]="*Idhupāli, bhikkhu adhammaṃ dhammoti pariṇāmeti, dhammaṃ adhammoti pariṇāmeti, avinayaṃ vinayoti pariṇāmeti, vinayaṃ avinayoti pariṇāmeti, apaññattaṃ paññāpeti, paññattaṃ samucchindati—**A monk explains what is contrary to the Teaching as the Teaching, what is the Teaching as contrary to the Teaching, what is contrary to the Monastic Law as the Monastic Law, what is the Monastic Law as contrary to the Monastic Law, and he lays down new rules and gets rid of the existing ones.*";
P_HTM[11439]="*ime kho, upāli, pañca adhammikā vinayabyākaraṇā.* **";
P_HTM[11440]="*Pañcime, upāli, dhammikā vinayabyākaraṇā.**And there are five legitimate explanations of the Monastic Law:*";
P_HTM[11441]="*Katame pañca?* **";
P_HTM[11442]="*Idhupāli, bhikkhu adhammaṃ adhammoti pariṇāmeti, dhammaṃ dhammoti pariṇāmeti, avinayaṃ avinayoti pariṇāmeti, vinayaṃ vinayoti pariṇāmeti, apaññattaṃ na paññapeti, paññattaṃ na samucchindati—**A monk explains what is contrary to the Teaching as contrary to the Teaching, what is the Teaching as the Teaching, what is contrary to the Monastic Law as contrary to the Monastic Law, what is the Monastic Law as the Monastic Law, and he does not lay down new rules or get rid of the existing ones.”*";
P_HTM[11443]="*ime kho, upāli, pañca dhammikā vinayabyākaraṇā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[11444]="*“Katihi nu kho, bhante, aṅgehi samannāgato bhattuddesako yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye”ti?**“When a designator of meals has how many qualities, is he dumped in hell?”*";
P_HTM[11445]="*“Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgato bhattuddesako yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**“When he has five qualities:*";
P_HTM[11446]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11447]="*Chandāgatiṃ gacchati, dosāgatiṃ gacchati, mohāgatiṃ gacchati, bhayāgatiṃ gacchati, uddiṭṭhānuddiṭṭhaṃ na jānāti—**he is swayed by desire, ill will, confusion, and fear, and he does not know what has and has not been designated.*";
P_HTM[11448]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhattuddesako yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.* **";
P_HTM[11449]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgato bhattuddesako yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge.**But when a designator of meals has five qualities, he is deposited in heaven:*";
P_HTM[11450]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11451]="*Na chandāgatiṃ gacchati, na dosāgatiṃ gacchati, na mohāgatiṃ gacchati, na bhayāgatiṃ gacchati, uddiṭṭhānuddiṭṭhaṃ jānāti—**he is not swayed by desire, ill will, confusion, or fear, and he knows what has and has not been designated.*";
P_HTM[11452]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhattuddesako yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge”ti.* **";
P_HTM[11453]="*“Katihi nu kho, bhante, aṅgehi samannāgato senāsanapaññāpako …pe…**“When an assigner of dwellings has how many qualities, is he dumped in hell?” …*";
P_HTM[11454]="*bhaṇḍāgāriko …pe…**a storeman …*";
P_HTM[11455]="*cīvarapaṭiggāhako …pe…**a receiver of robe-cloths …*";
P_HTM[11456]="*cīvarabhājako …pe…**a distributor of robe-cloth …*";
P_HTM[11457]="*yāgubhājako …pe…**a distributor of rice porridge …*";
P_HTM[11458]="*phalabhājako …pe…**a distributor of fruit …*";
P_HTM[11459]="*khajjabhājako …pe…**a distributor of fresh foods …*";
P_HTM[11460]="*appamattakavissajjako …pe…**a distributor of minor requisites …*";
P_HTM[11461]="*sāṭiyaggāhāpako …pe…**a distributor of rainy-season bathing cloths …*";
P_HTM[11462]="*pattaggāhāpako …pe…**a distributor of almsbowls …*";
P_HTM[11463]="*ārāmikapesako …pe…**a supervisor of monastery workers …*";
P_HTM[11464]="*sāmaṇerapesako yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye”ti?**“When a supervisor of novice monks has how many qualities, is he dumped in hell?”*";
P_HTM[11465]="*“Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgato sāmaṇerapesako yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**“When he has five qualities:*";
P_HTM[11466]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11467]="*Chandāgatiṃ gacchati, dosāgatiṃ gacchati, mohāgatiṃ gacchati, bhayāgatiṃ gacchati, pesitāpesitaṃ na jānāti—**he is swayed by desire, ill will, confusion, and fear, and he does not know who is and is not supervised.*";
P_HTM[11468]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato sāmaṇerapesako yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.* **";
P_HTM[11469]="*Pañcahupāli, aṅgehi samannāgato sāmaṇerapesako yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge.**But when a supervisor of novice monks has five qualities, he is deposited in heaven:*";
P_HTM[11470]="*Katamehi pañcahi?* **";
P_HTM[11471]="*Na chandāgatiṃ gacchati, na dosāgatiṃ gacchati, na mohāgatiṃ gacchati, na bhayāgatiṃ gacchati, pesitāpesitaṃ jānāti—**he is not swayed by desire, ill will, confusion, or fear, and he knows who is and is not supervised.”*";
P_HTM[11472]="*imehi kho, upāli, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato sāmaṇerapesako yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge”ti.* **";
P_HTM[11473]="*Āvāsikavaggo niṭṭhito terasamo.**The thirteenth sub-chapter on resident monks is finished.*";
P_HTM[11474]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[11475]="*Āvāsikabyākaraṇā,**“Resident monk, explanations,*";
P_HTM[11476]="*bhattusenāsanāni ca;**Designator of meals, and dwellings;*";
P_HTM[11477]="*Bhaṇḍacīvaraggāho ca,**Storeman, and receiver of robe-cloth,*";
P_HTM[11478]="*cīvarassa ca bhājako.**And distributor of robe-cloth.*";
P_HTM[11479]="*Yāgu phalaṃ khajjakañca,**Rice porridge, fruit, and fresh foods,*";
P_HTM[11480]="*appasāṭiyagāhako;**Minor requisites, distributor of rainy-season bathing cloths;*";
P_HTM[11481]="*Patto ārāmiko ceva,**Bowl, and monastery worker,*";
P_HTM[11482]="*sāmaṇerena pesakoti.**Supervisor of novice monks.”*";
P_HTM[11483]="*14. Kathinatthāravagga**14. The sub-chapter on the robe-making procedure*";
P_HTM[11484]="*“Kati nu kho, bhante, ānisaṃsā kathinatthāre”ti?**“Sir, how many benefits are there in doing the robe-making procedure?”*";
P_HTM[11485]="*“Pañcime, upāli, ānisaṃsā kathinatthāre.**“There are five benefits, Upāli:*";
P_HTM[11486]="*Katame pañca?* **";
P_HTM[11487]="*Anāmantacāro, asamādānacāro, gaṇabhojanaṃ, yāvadatthacīvaraṃ, yo ca tattha cīvaruppādo so nesaṃ bhavissati—**visiting families before or after a meal invitation, staying apart from your robe for more than a day, eating in a group, keeping as much extra robe-cloth as you need, and whatever robe-cloth is given is only for those who have participated in the robe-making procedure.*";
P_HTM[11488]="*ime kho, upāli, pañca ānisaṃsā kathinatthāre”ti.* **";
P_HTM[11489]="*“Kati nu kho, bhante, ādīnavā muṭṭhassatissa asampajānassa niddaṃ okkamato”ti?**“How many dangers are there in falling asleep absentminded and heedless?”*";
P_HTM[11490]="*“Pañcime, upāli, ādīnavā muṭṭhassatissa asampajānassa niddaṃ okkamato.**“There are these five dangers:*";
P_HTM[11491]="*Katame pañca?* **";
P_HTM[11492]="*Dukkhaṃ supati, dukkhaṃ paṭibujjhati, pāpakaṃ supinaṃ passati, devatā na rakkhanti, asuci muccati—**you don’t sleep well; you wake up feeling miserable; you have nightmares; the gods don’t guard you; and you emit semen.*";
P_HTM[11493]="*ime kho, upāli, pañca ādīnavā muṭṭhassatissa asampajānassa niddaṃ okkamato.* **";
P_HTM[11494]="*Pañcime, upāli, ānisaṃsā upaṭṭhitassatissa sampajānassa niddaṃ okkamato.**But there are five benefits in falling asleep mindfully, with clear awareness:*";
P_HTM[11495]="*Katame pañca?* **";
P_HTM[11496]="*Sukhaṃ supati, sukhaṃ paṭibujjhati, na pāpakaṃ supinaṃ passati, devatā rakkhanti, asuci na muccati—**you sleep well; you wake up feeling good; you don’t have nightmares; the gods guard you; and you don’t emit semen.*";
P_HTM[11497]="*ime kho, upāli, pañca ānisaṃsā upaṭṭhitassatissa sampajānassa niddaṃ okkamato”ti.* **";
P_HTM[11498]="*“Kati nu kho, bhante, avandiyā”ti?**“How many kinds of people should one not pay respect to?”*";
P_HTM[11499]="*“Pañcime, upāli, avandiyā.**“These five:*";
P_HTM[11500]="*Katame pañca?* **";
P_HTM[11501]="*Antaragharaṃ paviṭṭho avandiyo, racchagato avandiyo, otamasiko avandiyo, asamannāharanto avandiyo, sutto avandiyo—**one who has entered an inhabited area; one who is walking along a street; one who is in the dark; one who is not paying attention; one who is asleep.*";
P_HTM[11502]="*ime kho, upāli, pañca avandiyā.* **";
P_HTM[11503]="*Aparepi, upāli, pañca avandiyā.**There are also five other kinds of people one should not pay respect to:*";
P_HTM[11504]="*Katame pañca?* **";
P_HTM[11505]="*Yāgupāne avandiyo, bhattagge avandiyo, ekāvatto avandiyo, aññavihito avandiyo, naggo avandiyo—**one who is drinking rice porridge; one who is in the dining hall; one who has turned away; one who is preoccupied with something else; one who is naked.*";
P_HTM[11506]="*ime kho, upāli, pañca avandiyā.* **";
P_HTM[11507]="*Aparepi, upāli, pañca avandiyā.**There are also five other kinds of people one should not pay respect to:*";
P_HTM[11508]="*Katame pañca?* **";
P_HTM[11509]="*Khādanto avandiyo, bhuñjanto avandiyo, uccāraṃ karonto avandiyo, passāvaṃ karonto avandiyo, ukkhittako avandiyo—**One who is eating fresh food; one who is eating cooked food; one who is defecating; one who is urinating; one who has been ejected.*";
P_HTM[11510]="*ime kho, upāli, pañca avandiyā.* **";
P_HTM[11511]="*Aparepi, upāli, pañca avandiyā.**There are also five other kinds of people one should not pay respect to:*";
P_HTM[11512]="*Katame pañca?* **";
P_HTM[11513]="*Pure upasampannena pacchā upasampanno avandiyo, anupasampanno avandiyo, nānāsaṃvāsako vuḍḍhataro adhammavādī avandiyo, mātugāmo avandiyo, paṇḍako avandiyo—**one who has been given the full ordination after you; one who isn’t fully ordained; one who belongs to a different Buddhist sect who is senior to you, but who speaks contrary to the Teaching; a woman; a _paṇḍaka_.*";
P_HTM[11514]="*ime kho, upāli, pañca avandiyā.* **";
P_HTM[11515]="*Aparepi, upāli, pañca avandiyā.**There are also five other kinds of people one should not pay respect to:*";
P_HTM[11516]="*Katame pañca?* **";
P_HTM[11517]="*Pārivāsiko avandiyo, mūlāyapaṭikassanāraho avandiyo, mānattāraho avandiyo, mānattacāriko avandiyo, abbhānāraho avandiyo—**one who is on probation; one who deserves to be sent back to the beginning; one who deserves the trial period; one who is undertaking the trial period; one who deserves rehabilitation.*";
P_HTM[11518]="*ime kho, upāli, pañca avandiyā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[11519]="*“Kati nu kho, bhante, vandiyā”ti?**“But how many kinds of people should one pay respect to?”*";
P_HTM[11520]="*“Pañcime, upāli, vandiyā.**“These five:*";
P_HTM[11521]="*Katame pañca?* **";
P_HTM[11522]="*Pacchā upasampannena pure upasampanno vandiyo, nānāsaṃvāsako vuḍḍhataro dhammavādī vandiyo, ācariyo vandiyo, upajjhāyo vandiyo, sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya tathāgato arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vandiyo—**one who has been given the full ordination before you; one who belongs to a different Buddhist sect who is senior to you and who speaks in accordance with the Teaching; your teacher; your preceptor; and in this world with its gods, lords of death, and supreme beings, in this society with its monastics and brahmins, its gods and humans, you should pay respect to the Buddha, perfected and fully awakened.”*";
P_HTM[11523]="*ime kho, upāli, pañca vandiyā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[11524]="*“Navakatarena, bhante, bhikkhunā vuḍḍhatarassa bhikkhuno pāde vandantena kati dhamme ajjhattaṃ upaṭṭhāpetvā pādā vanditabbā”ti?**“Sir, when a monk is paying respect to a more senior monk, how many qualities should he first set up in himself?”*";
P_HTM[11525]="*“Navakatarenupāli, bhikkhunā vuḍḍhatarassa bhikkhuno pāde vandantena pañca dhamme ajjhattaṃ upaṭṭhāpetvā pādā vanditabbā.**“He should set up five qualities in himself:*";
P_HTM[11526]="*Katame pañca?* **";
P_HTM[11527]="*Navakatarenupāli, bhikkhunā vuḍḍhatarassa bhikkhuno pāde vandantena ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā, añjaliṃ paggahetvā, ubhohi pāṇitalehi pādāni parisambāhantena, pemañca gāravañca upaṭṭhāpetvā pādā vanditabbā—**he should put his upper robe over one shoulder; he should raise his joined palms; he should stroke the feet with the palms of both hands; he should set up a sense of affection; he should set up a sense of respect.”*";
P_HTM[11528]="*navakatarenupāli bhikkhunā vuḍḍhatarassa bhikkhuno pāde vandantena ime pañca dhamme ajjhattaṃ upaṭṭhāpetvā pādā vanditabbā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[11529]="*Kathinatthāravaggo niṭṭhito cuddasamo.**The fourteenth sub-chapter on the robe-making procedure is finished.*";
P_HTM[11530]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[11531]="*Kathinatthāraniddā ca,**“The robe-making procedure, and asleep,*";
P_HTM[11532]="*antarā yāgukhādane;**Within, rice porridge, when eating fresh food;*";
P_HTM[11533]="*Pure ca pārivāsi ca,**And before, and one on probation,*";
P_HTM[11534]="*vandiyo vanditabbakanti.**Should pay respect to, one who should be paid respect.”*";
P_HTM[11535]="*Upālipañcakaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The groups of five with Upāli are finished.*";
P_HTM[11536]="*Tesaṃ vaggānaṃ uddānaṃ**This is the summary these sub-chapters:*";
P_HTM[11537]="*Anissitena kammañca,**“Without formal support, and legal procedure,*";
P_HTM[11538]="*vohārāvikammena ca;**Speech, and with revealing;*";
