P_HTM[12345]="*Adhiṭṭhitañcatthaṅgate,**And determined, after sunset,*";
P_HTM[12346]="*na rattaṃ na cāraññakaṃ.**Not lustful, and not the wilderness.*";
P_HTM[12347]="*Kāyikā vācasikā ca,**By body, and by speech,*";
P_HTM[12348]="*tissitthī cāpi mātaraṃ;**And three women, mother;*";
P_HTM[12349]="*Kuddho ārādhako tuṭṭho,**Angry person who is successful, contented,*";
P_HTM[12350]="*saṅghādisesā ca ubho.**And an offense entailing suspension, both.*";
P_HTM[12351]="*Akappakataṃ na deti,**Not marked, one does not give,*";
P_HTM[12352]="*Na detāpajjatī garuṃ;**One does not give, one commits a heavy offense—*";
P_HTM[12353]="*Sedamocanikā gāthā,**The sweat-inducing verses:*";
P_HTM[12354]="*Pañhā viññūhi vibhāvitāti.**Questions explained by the wise.”*";
P_HTM[12355]="*124. 1. Kammavagga **124.  1. The sub*";
P_HTM[12356]="*Cattāri kammāni.**There are four kinds of legal procedures:*";
P_HTM[12357]="*Apalokanakammaṃ, ñattikammaṃ, ñattidutiyakammaṃ, ñatticatutthakammaṃ—**a legal procedure consisting of getting permission, a legal procedure consisting of one motion, a legal procedure consisting of one motion and one announcement, or a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements.*";
P_HTM[12358]="*imāni cattāri kammāni.* **";
P_HTM[12359]="*Katihākārehi vipajjanti?**In how many ways do they fail?*";
P_HTM[12360]="*Imāni cattāri kammāni pañcahākārehi vipajjanti—**In five ways:*";
P_HTM[12361]="*vatthuto vā ñattito vā anussāvanato vā sīmato vā parisato vā.**in respect of subject, motion, announcement, monastic boundary, or gathering.*";
P_HTM[12362]="*Kathaṃ vatthuto kammāni vipajjanti?**How do legal procedures fail in respect of subject?*";
P_HTM[12363]="*Sammukhākaraṇīyaṃ kammaṃ asammukhā karoti, vatthuvipannaṃ adhammakammaṃ;**If they don’t do a legal procedure face-to-face that should be done face-to-face, that procedure has failed in subject and is illegitimate.*";
P_HTM[12364]="*paṭipucchākaraṇīyaṃ kammaṃ appaṭipucchā karoti, vatthuvipannaṃ adhammakammaṃ;**If they do a legal procedure without questioning that should be done with questioning, that procedure has failed in subject and is illegitimate.*";
P_HTM[12365]="*paṭiññāya karaṇīyaṃ kammaṃ appaṭiññāya karoti, vatthuvipannaṃ adhammakammaṃ;**If they do a legal procedure without admission that should be done by admission, that procedure has failed in subject and is illegitimate.*";
P_HTM[12366]="*sativinayārahassa amūḷhavinayaṃ deti, vatthuvipannaṃ adhammakammaṃ;**If they apply resolution because of past insanity to one deserving resolution through recollection, that procedure has failed in subject and is illegitimate.*";
P_HTM[12367]="*amūḷhavinayārahassa tassapāpiyasikākammaṃ karoti, vatthuvipannaṃ adhammakammaṃ;**If they do a legal procedure of further penalty against one deserving resolution because of past insanity, that procedure has failed in subject and is illegitimate.*";
P_HTM[12368]="*tassapāpiyasikākammārahassa tajjanīyakammaṃ karoti, vatthuvipannaṃ adhammakammaṃ;**If they do a legal procedure of condemnation against one deserving a procedure of further penalty, that procedure has failed in subject and is illegitimate.*";
P_HTM[12369]="*tajjanīyakammārahassa niyassakammaṃ karoti, vatthuvipannaṃ adhammakammaṃ;**If they do a legal procedure of demotion against one deserving a procedure of condemnation, that procedure has failed in subject and is illegitimate.*";
P_HTM[12370]="*niyassakammārahassa pabbājanīyakammaṃ karoti, vatthuvipannaṃ adhammakammaṃ;**If they do a procedure of banishment against one deserving a procedure of demotion, that procedure has failed in subject and is illegitimate.*";
P_HTM[12371]="*pabbājanīyakammārahassa paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ karoti, vatthuvipannaṃ adhammakammaṃ;**If they do a procedure of reconciliation against one deserving a procedure of banishment, that procedure has failed in subject and is illegitimate.*";
P_HTM[12372]="*paṭisāraṇīyakammārahassa ukkhepanīyakammaṃ karoti, vatthuvipannaṃ adhammakammaṃ;**If they do a legal procedure of ejection against one deserving a procedure of reconciliation, that procedure has failed in subject and is illegitimate.*";
P_HTM[12373]="*ukkhepanīyakammārahassa parivāsaṃ deti, vatthuvipannaṃ adhammakammaṃ;**If they give probation to one deserving a procedure of ejection, that procedure has failed in subject and is illegitimate.*";
P_HTM[12374]="*parivāsārahaṃ mūlāya paṭikassati, vatthuvipannaṃ adhammakammaṃ;**If they send back to the beginning one deserving probation, that procedure has failed in subject and is illegitimate.*";
P_HTM[12375]="*mūlāyapaṭikassanārahassa mānattaṃ deti, vatthuvipannaṃ adhammakammaṃ;**If they give the trial period to one deserving to be sent back to the beginning, that procedure has failed in subject and is illegitimate.*";
P_HTM[12376]="*mānattārahaṃ abbheti, vatthuvipannaṃ adhammakammaṃ;**If they rehabilitate one deserving the trial period, that procedure has failed in subject and is illegitimate.*";
P_HTM[12377]="*abbhānārahaṃ upasampādeti, vatthuvipannaṃ adhammakammaṃ;**If they give full ordination to one deserving rehabilitation, that procedure has failed in subject and is illegitimate.*";
P_HTM[12378]="*anuposathe uposathaṃ karoti, vatthuvipannaṃ adhammakammaṃ;**If they do the observance-day procedure on a non-observance day, that procedure has failed in subject and is illegitimate.*";
P_HTM[12379]="*apavāraṇāya pavāreti, vatthuvipannaṃ adhammakammaṃ.**If they do the invitation procedure on a non-invitation day, that procedure has failed in subject and is illegitimate.*";
P_HTM[12380]="*Evaṃ vatthuto kammāni vipajjanti.* **";
P_HTM[12381]="*Kathaṃ ñattito kammāni vipajjanti?**How do legal procedures fail in respect of motion?*";
P_HTM[12382]="*Pañcahākārehi ñattito kammāni vipajjanti—**In five ways:*";
P_HTM[12383]="*vatthuṃ na parāmasati, saṅghaṃ na parāmasati, puggalaṃ na parāmasati, ñattiṃ na parāmasati, pacchā vā ñattiṃ ṭhapeti—**they do not bring up the subject, the Sangha, the person, or the motion, or they put forward the motion after the announcement.*";
P_HTM[12384]="*imehi pañcahākārehi ñattito kammāni vipajjanti.* **";
P_HTM[12385]="*Kathaṃ anussāvanato kammāni vipajjanti?**How do legal procedures fail in respect of announcement?*";
P_HTM[12386]="*Pañcahākārehi anussāvanato kammāni vipajjanti—**In five ways:*";
P_HTM[12387]="*vatthuṃ na parāmasati, saṅghaṃ na parāmasati, puggalaṃ na parāmasati, sāvanaṃ hāpeti, akāle vā sāveti—**they do not bring up the subject, the Sangha, or the person, or they mangle the proclamation of the legal procedure, or they proclaim at the wrong time.*";
P_HTM[12388]="*imehi pañcahākārehi anussāvanato kammāni vipajjanti.* **";
P_HTM[12389]="*Kathaṃ sīmato kammāni vipajjanti?**How do legal procedures fail in respect of monastic boundary?*";
P_HTM[12390]="*Ekādasahi ākārehi sīmato kammāni vipajjanti—**In eleven ways:*";
P_HTM[12391]="*atikhuddakaṃ sīmaṃ sammannati, atimahatiṃ sīmaṃ sammannati, khaṇḍanimittaṃ sīmaṃ sammannati, chāyānimittaṃ sīmaṃ sammannati, animittaṃ sīmaṃ sammannati, bahisīme ṭhito sīmaṃ sammannati, nadiyā sīmaṃ sammannati, samudde sīmaṃ sammannati, jātassare sīmaṃ sammannati, sīmāya sīmaṃ sambhindati, sīmāya sīmaṃ ajjhottharati—**They establish a boundary that is too small; they establish a boundary that is too large; they establish an incomplete boundary; they establish a boundary with shade as a boundary marker; they establish a boundary without boundary markers; they establish a boundary while standing outside it; they establish a river as a boundary; they establish an ocean as a boundary; they establish a lake as a boundary; they establish a boundary that crosses an existing boundary; they establish a boundary that encloses an existing boundary.*";
P_HTM[12392]="*imehi ekādasahi ākārehi sīmato kammāni vipajjanti.* **";
P_HTM[12393]="*Kathaṃ parisato kammāni vipajjanti?**How do legal procedures fail in respect of gathering?*";
P_HTM[12394]="*Dvādasahi ākārehi parisato kammāni vipajjanti—**In twelve ways:*";
P_HTM[12395]="*catuvaggakaraṇe kamme yāvatikā bhikkhū kammapattā te anāgatā honti, chandārahānaṃ chando anāhaṭo hoti, sammukhībhūtā paṭikkosanti, catuvaggakaraṇe kamme yāvatikā bhikkhū kammapattā te āgatā honti, chandārahānaṃ chando anāhaṭo hoti, sammukhībhūtā paṭikkosanti, catuvaggakaraṇe kamme yāvatikā bhikkhū kammapattā te āgatā honti, chandārahānaṃ chando āhaṭo hoti, sammukhībhūtā paṭikkosanti.**In regard to a a legal procedure that requires group of four: the monks who should be present haven’t all arrived, the consent hasn’t been brought for those who are eligible to give their consent, or someone present objects to the decision; [2] the monks who should be present have arrived, but the consent hasn’t been brought for those who are eligible to give their consent, or someone present objects to the decision; [3] the monks who should be present have arrived, and the consent has been brought for those who are eligible to give their consent, but someone present objects to the decision.*";
P_HTM[12396]="*Pañcavaggakaraṇe kamme …pe…**In regard to a a legal procedure that requires group of five: …*";
P_HTM[12397]="*dasavaggakaraṇe kamme …pe…**In regard to a a legal procedure that requires group of ten: …*";
P_HTM[12398]="*vīsativaggakaraṇe kamme yāvatikā bhikkhū kammapattā te anāgatā honti, chandārahānaṃ chando anāhaṭo hoti, sammukhībhūtā paṭikkosanti, vīsativaggakaraṇe kamme yāvatikā bhikkhū kammapattā te āgatā honti, chandārahānaṃ chando anāhaṭo hoti, sammukhībhūtā paṭikkosanti, vīsativaggakaraṇe kamme yāvatikā bhikkhū kammapattā te āgatā honti, chandārahānaṃ chando āhaṭo hoti, sammukhībhūtā paṭikkosanti—**In regard to a a legal procedure that requires group of twenty: the monks who should be present haven’t all arrived, the consent hasn’t been brought for those who are eligible to give their consent, or someone present objects to the decision; [11] the monks who should be present have arrived, but the consent hasn’t been brought for those who are eligible to give their consent, or someone present objects to the decision; [12] the monks who should be present have arrived, and the consent has been brought for those who are eligible to give their consent, but someone present objects to the decision.*";
P_HTM[12399]="*imehi dvādasahi ākārehi parisato kammāni vipajjanti.* **";
P_HTM[12400]="*Catuvaggakaraṇe kamme cattāro bhikkhū pakatattā kammapattā, avasesā pakatattā chandārahā.**In regard to a a legal procedure that requires group of four, four regular monks should be present and for the remainder of regular monks it is proper to give their consent.*";
P_HTM[12401]="*Yassa saṅgho kammaṃ karoti so neva kammapatto nāpi chandāraho, api ca kammāraho.**The one who is subject to the legal procedure should neither take part in the decision nor give his consent, but is deserving of the legal procedure.*";
P_HTM[12402]="*Pañcavaggakaraṇe kamme pañca bhikkhū pakatattā kammapattā, avasesā pakatattā chandārahā.**In regard to a a legal procedure that requires group of five, five regular monks should be present and for the remainder of regular monks it is proper to give their consent.*";
P_HTM[12403]="*Yassa saṅgho kammaṃ karoti so neva kammapatto nāpi chandāraho, api ca kammāraho.**The one who is subject to the legal procedure should neither take part in the decision nor give his consent, but is deserving of the legal procedure.*";
P_HTM[12404]="*Dasavaggakaraṇe kamme dasa bhikkhū pakatattā kammapattā, avasesā pakatattā chandārahā.**In regard to a a legal procedure that requires group of ten, ten regular monks should be present and for the remainder of regular monks it is proper to give their consent.*";
P_HTM[12405]="*Yassa saṅgho kammaṃ karoti so neva kammapatto nāpi chandāraho, api ca kammāraho.**The one who is subject to the legal procedure should neither take part in the decision nor give his consent, but is deserving of the legal procedure.*";
P_HTM[12406]="*Vīsativaggakaraṇe kamme vīsati bhikkhū pakatattā kammapattā, avasesā pakatattā chandārahā.**In regard to a a legal procedure that requires group of twenty, twenty regular monks should be present and for the remainder of regular monks it is proper to give their consent.*";
P_HTM[12407]="*Yassa saṅgho kammaṃ karoti so neva kammapatto nāpi chandāraho, api ca kammāraho.**The one who is subject to the legal procedure should neither take part in the decision nor give his consent, but is deserving of the legal procedure.*";
P_HTM[12408]="*Cattāri kammāni—**There are four kinds of legal procedures:*";
P_HTM[12409]="*apalokanakammaṃ, ñattikammaṃ, ñattidutiyakammaṃ, ñatticatutthakammaṃ.**a procedure consisting of getting permission, a procedure consisting of one motion, a procedure consisting of one motion and one announcement, or a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements.*";
P_HTM[12410]="*Imāni cattāri kammāni katihākārehi vipajjanti?**In how many ways do they fail?*";
P_HTM[12411]="*Imāni cattāri kammāni pañcahākārehi vipajjanti—**In five ways:*";
P_HTM[12412]="*vatthuto vā ñattito vā anussāvanato vā sīmato vā parisato vā.**in respect of subject, motion, announcement, monastic boundary, or gathering.*";
P_HTM[12413]="*Kathaṃ vatthuto kammāni vipajjanti?**How do legal procedures fail in respect of subject?*";
P_HTM[12414]="*Paṇḍakaṃ upasampādeti, vatthuvipannaṃ adhammakammaṃ.**If they give the full ordination to a _paṇḍaka_, that procedure has failed in subject and is illegitimate.*";
P_HTM[12415]="*Theyyasaṃvāsakaṃ upasampādeti, vatthuvipannaṃ adhammakammaṃ.**If they give the full ordination to one who lives in the community by theft, that procedure has failed in subject and is illegitimate.*";
P_HTM[12416]="*Titthiyapakkantakaṃ upasampādeti, vatthuvipannaṃ adhammakammaṃ.**If they give the full ordination to one who has previously left to join another religion, that procedure has failed in subject and is illegitimate.*";
P_HTM[12417]="*Tiracchānagataṃ upasampādeti, vatthuvipannaṃ adhammakammaṃ.**If they give the full ordination to an animal, that procedure has failed in subject and is illegitimate.*";
P_HTM[12418]="*Mātughātakaṃ upasampādeti, vatthuvipannaṃ adhammakammaṃ.**If they give the full ordination to a matricide, that procedure has failed in subject and is illegitimate.*";
P_HTM[12419]="*Pitughātakaṃ upasampādeti, vatthuvipannaṃ adhammakammaṃ.**If they give the full ordination to a patricide, that procedure has failed in subject and is illegitimate.*";
P_HTM[12420]="*Arahantaghātakaṃ upasampādeti, vatthuvipannaṃ adhammakammaṃ.**If they give the full ordination to a murderer of a perfected one, that procedure has failed in subject and is illegitimate.*";
P_HTM[12421]="*Bhikkhunidūsakaṃ upasampādeti, vatthuvipannaṃ adhammakammaṃ.**If they give the full ordination to a rapist of a nun, that procedure has failed in subject and is illegitimate.*";
P_HTM[12422]="*Saṅghabhedakaṃ upasampādeti, vatthuvipannaṃ adhammakammaṃ.**If they give the full ordination to one who has created a schism in the Sangha, that procedure has failed in subject and is illegitimate.*";
P_HTM[12423]="*Lohituppādakaṃ upasampādeti, vatthuvipannaṃ adhammakammaṃ.**If they give the full ordination to one who has caused the Buddha to bleed, that procedure has failed in subject and is illegitimate.*";
P_HTM[12424]="*Ubhatobyañjanaṃ upasampādeti, vatthuvipannaṃ adhammakammaṃ.**If they give the full ordination to a hermaphrodite, that procedure has failed in subject and is illegitimate.*";
P_HTM[12425]="*Ūnavīsativassaṃ puggalaṃ upasampādeti, vatthuvipannaṃ adhammakammaṃ.**If they give the full ordination to a person less then twenty years old, that procedure has failed in subject and is illegitimate.*";
P_HTM[12426]="*Evaṃ vatthuto kammāni vipajjanti.* **";
P_HTM[12427]="*Kathaṃ ñattito kammāni vipajjanti?**How do legal procedures fail in respect of motion?*";
P_HTM[12428]="*Pañcahākārehi ñattito kammāni vipajjanti.**In five ways:*";
P_HTM[12429]="*Vatthuṃ na parāmasati, saṅghaṃ na parāmasati, puggalaṃ na parāmasati, ñattiṃ na parāmasati, pacchā vā ñattiṃ ṭhapeti—**they do not bring up the subject, the Sangha, the person, or the motion, or they put forward the motion after the announcement.*";
P_HTM[12430]="*imehi pañcahākārehi ñattito kammāni vipajjanti.* **";
P_HTM[12431]="*Kathaṃ anussāvanato kammāni vipajjanti?**How do legal procedures fail in respect of announcement?*";
P_HTM[12432]="*Pañcahākārehi anussāvanato kammāni vipajjanti—**In five ways:*";
P_HTM[12433]="*vatthuṃ na parāmasati, saṅghaṃ na parāmasati, puggalaṃ na parāmasati, sāvanaṃ hāpeti, akāle vā sāveti—**they do not bring up the subject, the Sangha, or the person, or they mangle the proclamation of the legal procedure, or they proclaim at the wrong time.*";
P_HTM[12434]="*imehi pañcahākārehi anussāvanato kammāni vipajjanti.* **";
P_HTM[12435]="*Kathaṃ sīmato kammāni vipajjanti?**How do legal procedures fail in respect of monastic boundary?*";
P_HTM[12436]="*Ekādasahi ākārehi sīmato kammāni vipajjanti.**In eleven ways:*";
P_HTM[12437]="*Atikhuddakaṃ sīmaṃ sammannati, atimahatiṃ sīmaṃ sammannati, khaṇḍanimittaṃ sīmaṃ sammannati, chāyānimittaṃ sīmaṃ sammannati, animittaṃ sīmaṃ sammannati, bahisīme ṭhito sīmaṃ sammannati, nadiyā sīmaṃ sammannati, samudde sīmaṃ sammannati, jātassare sīmaṃ sammannati, sīmāya sīmaṃ sambhindati, sīmāya sīmaṃ ajjhottharati—**They establish a boundary that is too small; they establish a boundary that is too large; they establish an incomplete boundary; they establish a boundary with shade as a boundary marker; they establish a boundary with no boundary markers; they establish a boundary while standing outside it; they establish a river as a boundary; they establish an ocean as a boundary; they establish a lake as a boundary; they establish a boundary that crosses an existing boundary; they establish a boundary that encloses an existing boundary.*";
P_HTM[12438]="*imehi ekādasahi ākārehi sīmato kammāni vipajjanti.* **";
P_HTM[12439]="*Kathaṃ parisato kammāni vipajjanti?**How do legal procedures fail in respect of gathering?*";
P_HTM[12440]="*Dvādasahi ākārehi parisato kammāni vipajjanti—**In twelve ways:*";
P_HTM[12441]="*catuvaggakaraṇe kamme yāvatikā bhikkhū kammapattā te anāgatā honti, chandārahānaṃ chando anāhaṭo hoti, sammukhībhūtā paṭikkosanti, catuvaggakaraṇe kamme yāvatikā bhikkhū kammapattā te āgatā honti, chandārahānaṃ chando anāhaṭo hoti, sammukhībhūtā paṭikkosanti. Catuvaggakaraṇe kamme yāvatikā bhikkhū kammapattā te āgatā honti, chandārahānaṃ chando āhaṭo hoti, sammukhībhūtā paṭikkosanti.**In regard to a a legal procedure that requires group of four: the monks who should be present haven’t all arrived, the consent hasn’t been brought for those who are eligible to give their consent, or someone present objects to the decision; [2] the monks who should be present have arrived, but the consent hasn’t been brought for those who are eligible to give their consent, or someone present objects to the decision; [3] the monks who should be present have arrived, and the consent has been brought for those who are eligible to give their consent, but someone present objects to the decision.*";
P_HTM[12442]="*Pañcavaggakaraṇe kamme …pe…**In regard to a a legal procedure that requires group of five: …*";
P_HTM[12443]="*dasavaggakaraṇe kamme …pe…**In regard to a a legal procedure that requires group of ten: …*";
P_HTM[12444]="*vīsativaggakaraṇe kamme yāvatikā bhikkhū kammapattā te anāgatā honti, chandārahānaṃ chando anāhaṭo hoti, sammukhībhūtā paṭikkosanti.**In regard to a a legal procedure that requires group of twenty: the monks who should be present haven’t all arrived, the consent hasn’t been brought for those who are eligible to give their consent, or someone present objects to the decision; [11] the monks who should be present have arrived, but the consent hasn’t been brought for those who are eligible to give their consent, or someone present objects to the decision; [12] the monks who should be present have arrived, and the consent has been brought for those who are eligible to give their consent, but someone present objects to the decision.*";
P_HTM[12445]="*Vīsativaggakaraṇe kamme yāvatikā bhikkhū kammapattā te āgatā honti, chandārahānaṃ chando anāhaṭo hoti, sammukhībhūtā paṭikkosanti. Vīsativaggakaraṇe kamme yāvatikā bhikkhū kammapattā te āgatā honti, chandārahānaṃ chando āhaṭo hoti, sammukhībhūtā paṭikkosanti—imehi dvādasahi ākārehi parisato kammāni vipajjanti.* **";
P_HTM[12446]="*Apalokanakammaṃ kati ṭhānāni gacchati?**In how many situations does the legal procedure consisting of getting permission apply?*";
P_HTM[12447]="*Ñattikammaṃ kati ṭhānāni gacchati?**In how many situations does the legal procedure consisting of one motion apply?*";
P_HTM[12448]="*Ñattidutiyakammaṃ kati ṭhānāni gacchati?**In how many situations does the legal procedure consisting of one motion and one announcement apply?*";
P_HTM[12449]="*Ñatticatutthakammaṃ kati ṭhānāni gacchati?**In how many situations does the legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements apply?*";
P_HTM[12450]="*Apalokanakammaṃ pañca ṭhānāni gacchati.**A legal procedure consisting of getting permission applies in five situations.*";
P_HTM[12451]="*Ñattikammaṃ nava ṭhānāni gacchati.**A legal procedure consisting of one motion applies in nine situations.*";
P_HTM[12452]="*Ñattidutiyakammaṃ satta ṭhānāni gacchati.**A legal procedure consisting of getting permission applies in seven situations.*";
P_HTM[12453]="*Ñatticatutthakammaṃ satta ṭhānāni gacchati.**A legal procedure consisting of getting permission applies in seven situations.*";
P_HTM[12454]="*Apalokanakammaṃ katamāni pañca ṭhānāni gacchati?**In which five situations does the legal procedure consisting of getting permission apply?*";
P_HTM[12455]="*Osāraṇaṃ, nissāraṇaṃ, bhaṇḍukammaṃ, brahmadaṇḍaṃ, kammalakkhaṇaññeva pañcamaṃ—**Admittance, sending away, shaving, the supreme penalty, and any situation with similar characteristics.*";
P_HTM[12456]="*apalokanakammaṃ imāni pañca ṭhānāni gacchati.* **";
P_HTM[12457]="*Ñattikammaṃ katamāni nava ṭhānāni gacchati?**In which nine situations does the legal procedure consisting of one motion apply?*";
P_HTM[12458]="*Osāraṇaṃ, nissāraṇaṃ, uposathaṃ, pavāraṇaṃ, sammutiṃ, dānaṃ, paṭiggahaṃ, paccukkaḍḍhanaṃ, kammalakkhaṇaññeva navamaṃ—**Admittance, sending away, the observance day, the invitation day, agreements, giving, receiving, postponement, and any situation with similar characteristics.*";
P_HTM[12459]="*ñattikammaṃ imāni nava ṭhānāni gacchati.* **";
P_HTM[12460]="*Ñattidutiyakammaṃ katamāni satta ṭhānāni gacchati?**In which seven situations does the legal procedure consisting of one motion and one announcement apply?*";
P_HTM[12461]="*Osāraṇaṃ, nissāraṇaṃ, sammutiṃ, dānaṃ, uddharaṇaṃ, desanaṃ, kammalakkhaṇaññeva sattamaṃ—**Admittance, sending away, agreements, giving, ending of the robe-making season, approval, and any situation with similar characteristics.*";
P_HTM[12462]="*ñattidutiyakammaṃ imāni satta ṭhānāni gacchati.* **";
