P_HTM[12569]="*5. Navasaṅgahavagga**5. The sub-chapter on nine kinds of “being found among”*";
P_HTM[12570]="*Navasaṅgahā—**There are nine kinds of “being found among”:*";
P_HTM[12571]="*vatthusaṅgaho, vipattisaṅgaho āpattisaṅgaho, nidānasaṅgaho, puggalasaṅgaho, khandhasaṅgaho, samuṭṭhānasaṅgaho, adhikaraṇasaṅgaho, samathasaṅgahoti.**being found among the actions that are the bases for offenses, being found among the failures, being found among the offenses, being found among the origin stories, being found among persons, being found among the classes, being found among the origins, being found among the legal issues, and being found among the settling of legal issues.*";
P_HTM[12572]="*Adhikaraṇe samuppanne sace ubho atthapaccatthikā āgacchanti ubhinnampi vatthu ārocāpetabbaṃ.**When a legal issue has arisen, if the two opponents, they should be told to inform about the action that was the basis for the disagreement.*";
P_HTM[12573]="*Ubhinnampi vatthuṃ ārocāpetvā ubhinnampi paṭiññā sotabbā.**After hearing the testimony of both,*";
P_HTM[12574]="*Ubhinnampi paṭiññaṃ sutvā ubhopi vattabbā—**they should be told,*";
P_HTM[12575]="*“amhākaṃ imasmiṃ adhikaraṇe vūpasamite ubhopi tuṭṭhā bhavissathā”ti.**“When we have resolved this legal issue, you should both be satisfied.”*";
P_HTM[12576]="*Sace āhaṃsu—**If they say,*";
P_HTM[12577]="*“ubhopi tuṭṭhā bhavissāmā”ti, saṅghena taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ sampaṭicchitabbaṃ.**“We will both be satisfied,” then the Sangha should take on that legal issue.*";
P_HTM[12578]="*Sace alajjussannā hoti, parisā ubbāhikāya vūpasametabbaṃ.**If there are many shameless people in the gathering, then the issue should be resolved by means of a committee.*";
P_HTM[12579]="*Sace bālussannā hoti, parisā vinayadharo pariyesitabbo yena dhammena yena vinayena yena satthusāsanena taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasammati.**If there are many ignorant people in the gathering, they should search for an expert on the Monastic Law to resolve that legal issue in accordance with the Teaching, the Monastic Law, and the Teacher’s instruction.*";
P_HTM[12580]="*Tathā taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametabbaṃ.**That legal issue should be resolved in this way.*";
P_HTM[12581]="*Vatthu jānitabbaṃ, gottaṃ jānitabbaṃ, nāmaṃ jānitabbaṃ, āpatti jānitabbā.**One should know the action that is the basis for the offense, one should know the category, one should know the name, and one should know the offense.*";
P_HTM[12582]="*Methunadhammoti vatthu ceva gottañca—**“Sexual intercourse is the action that is the basis for the offense, as well as the category;*";
P_HTM[12583]="*pārājikanti nāmañceva āpatti ca.**offense entailing expulsion is the name, as well as the offense.*";
P_HTM[12584]="*Adinnādānanti vatthu ceva gottañca—**Stealing is the action that is the basis for the offense, as well as the category;*";
P_HTM[12585]="*pārājikanti nāmañceva āpatti ca.**offense entailing expulsion is the name, as well as the offense.*";
P_HTM[12586]="*Manussaviggahoti vatthu ceva gottañca—**Human being is the basis for the offense, as well as the category;*";
P_HTM[12587]="*pārājikanti nāmañceva āpatti ca.**offense entailing expulsion is the name, as well as the offense.*";
P_HTM[12588]="*Uttarimanussadhammoti vatthu ceva gottañca—**Superhuman quality is the basis for the offense, as well as the category;*";
P_HTM[12589]="*pārājikanti nāmañceva āpatti ca.**offense entailing expulsion is the name, as well as the offense.*";
P_HTM[12590]="*Sukkavissaṭṭhīti vatthu ceva gottañca—**Emission of semen is the action that is the basis for the offense, as well as the category;*";
P_HTM[12591]="*saṅghādisesoti nāmañceva āpatti ca.**offense entailing suspension is the name, as well as the offense.*";
P_HTM[12592]="*Kāyasaṃsaggoti vatthu ceva gottañca—**Physical contact is the action that is the basis for the offense, as well as the category;*";
P_HTM[12593]="*saṅghādisesoti nāmañceva āpatti ca.**offense entailing suspension is the name, as well as the offense.*";
P_HTM[12594]="*Duṭṭhullavācāti vatthu ceva gottañca—**Indecent speech is the action that is the basis for the offense, as well as the category;*";
P_HTM[12595]="*saṅghādisesoti nāmañceva āpatti ca.**offense entailing suspension is the name, as well as the offense.*";
P_HTM[12596]="*Attakāmanti vatthu ceva gottañca—**One’s own desire is the basis for the offense, as well as the category;*";
P_HTM[12597]="*saṅghādisesoti nāmañceva āpatti ca.**offense entailing suspension is the name, as well as the offense.*";
P_HTM[12598]="*Sañcarittanti vatthu ceva gottañca—**Matchmaking is the action that is the basis for the offense, as well as the category;*";
P_HTM[12599]="*saṅghādisesoti nāmañceva āpatti ca.**offense entailing suspension is the name, as well as the offense.*";
P_HTM[12600]="*Saññācikāya kuṭiṃ kārāpananti vatthu ceva gottañca—**Building a hut by means of begging is the action that is the basis for the offense, as well as the category;*";
P_HTM[12601]="*saṅghādisesoti nāmañceva āpatti ca.**offense entailing suspension is the name, as well as the offense.*";
P_HTM[12602]="*Mahallakaṃ vihāraṃ kārāpananti vatthu ceva gottañca—**Building a large dwelling is the action that is the basis for the offense, as well as the category;*";
P_HTM[12603]="*saṅghādisesoti nāmañceva āpatti ca.**offense entailing suspension is the name, as well as the offense.*";
P_HTM[12604]="*Bhikkhuṃ amūlakena pārājikena dhammena anuddhaṃsananti vatthu ceva gottañca—**Groundlessly charging a monk with an offense entailing expulsion is the action that is the basis for the offense, as well as the category;*";
P_HTM[12605]="*saṅghādisesoti nāmañceva āpatti ca.**offense entailing suspension is the name, as well as the offense.*";
P_HTM[12606]="*Bhikkhuṃ aññabhāgiyassa adhikaraṇassa kiñci desaṃ lesamattaṃ upādāya pārājikena dhammena anuddhaṃsananti vatthu ceva gottañca—**Charging a monk with an offense entailing expulsion, using an unrelated legal issue as a pretext, is the action that is the basis for the offense, as well as the category;*";
P_HTM[12607]="*saṅghādisesoti nāmañceva āpatti ca.**offense entailing suspension is the name, as well as the offense.*";
P_HTM[12608]="*Saṅghabhedakassa bhikkhuno yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjananti vatthu ceva gottañca—**A monk not stopping, when pressed up to three times, the pursuit of schism in the Sangha—this is the action that is the basis for the offense, as well as the category;*";
P_HTM[12609]="*saṅghādisesoti nāmañceva āpatti ca.**offense entailing suspension is the name, as well as the offense.*";
P_HTM[12610]="*Bhedakānuvattakānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjananti vatthu ceva gottañca—**Monks not stopping, when pressed up to three times, to side with one who is pursuing schism in the Sangha—this is the action that is the basis for the offense, as well as the category;*";
P_HTM[12611]="*saṅghādisesoti nāmañceva āpatti ca.**offense entailing suspension is the name, as well as the offense.*";
P_HTM[12612]="*Dubbacassa bhikkhuno yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjananti vatthu ceva gottañca—**A monk not stopping, when pressed up to three times, with being difficult to correct—this is the action that is the basis for the offense, as well as the category;*";
P_HTM[12613]="*saṅghādisesoti nāmañceva āpatti ca.**offense entailing suspension is the name, as well as the offense.*";
P_HTM[12614]="*Kuladūsakassa bhikkhuno yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjananti vatthu ceva gottañca—**A monk not stopping, when pressed up to three times, with being a corrupter of families—this is the action that is the basis for the offense, as well as the category;*";
P_HTM[12615]="*saṅghādisesoti nāmañceva āpatti ca …pe….**offense entailing suspension is the name, as well as the offense. …*";
P_HTM[12616]="*Anādariyaṃ paṭicca udake uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā kheḷaṃ vā karaṇanti vatthu ceva gottañca—**Out of disrespect, defecating, urinating, or spitting in water is the action that is the basis for the offense, as well as the category;*";
P_HTM[12617]="*dukkaṭanti nāmañceva āpatti cāti.**offense of wrong conduct is the name, as well as the offense.”*";
P_HTM[12618]="*Navasaṅgahavaggo niṭṭhito pañcamo.**The sub-chapter on nine kinds of “being found among” is finished.*";
P_HTM[12619]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[12620]="*Apalokanaṃ ñatti ca,**“Getting permission, and motion,*";
P_HTM[12621]="*dutiyaṃ catutthena ca;**One motion and one announcement, and with one motion and three announcements;*";
P_HTM[12622]="*Vatthu ñatti anussāvanaṃ,**Subject, motion, announcement,*";
P_HTM[12623]="*sīmā parisameva ca.**Boundary, and gathering.*";
P_HTM[12624]="*Sammukhā paṭipucchā ca,**Face-to-face, and questioning,*";
P_HTM[12625]="*paṭiññā vinayāraho;**Admission, resolution, deserving;*";
P_HTM[12626]="*Vatthu saṅghapuggalañca,**Subject, Sangha, and person,*";
P_HTM[12627]="*ñattiṃ na pacchā ñatti ca.**Motions, and not the motion afterwards.*";
P_HTM[12628]="*Vatthuṃ saṅghapuggalañca,**Subject, Sangha, and person,*";
P_HTM[12629]="*sāvanaṃ akālena ca;**Proclamation, and at the wrong time;*";
P_HTM[12630]="*Atikhuddakā mahantā ca,**Too small, and too large,*";
P_HTM[12631]="*khaṇḍacchāyā nimittakā.**Incomplete, shade, without boundary markers.*";
P_HTM[12632]="*Bahinadī samudde ca,**Outside, river, and in the ocean,*";
P_HTM[12633]="*jātassare ca bhindati;**And in a lake, crossing;*";
P_HTM[12634]="*Ajjhottharati sīmāya,**Encloses with a boundary,*";
P_HTM[12635]="*catu pañca ca vaggikā.**A group of four, and of five.*";
P_HTM[12636]="*Dasa vīsativaggā ca,**A group of ten, and of twenty,*";
P_HTM[12637]="*anāhaṭā ca āhaṭā;**Not brought and brought;*";
P_HTM[12638]="*Kammapattā chandārahā,**Should be present, proper to give their consent,*";
P_HTM[12639]="*kammārahā ca puggalā.**And person deserving of the legal procedure.*";
P_HTM[12640]="*Apalokanaṃ pañcaṭṭhānaṃ,**Five cases for getting permission,*";
P_HTM[12641]="*ñatti ca navaṭhānikā;**And nine cases for one motion;*";
P_HTM[12642]="*Ñatti dutiyaṃ sattaṭṭhānaṃ,**Seven cases for one motion and one announcement,*";
P_HTM[12643]="*catutthā sattaṭhānikā.**Seven cases for one motion and three announcements.*";
P_HTM[12644]="*Suṭṭhu phāsu ca dummaṅku,**Well-being, comfort, bad,*";
P_HTM[12645]="*pesalā cāpi āsavā;**Good, corruptions;*";
P_HTM[12646]="*Veravajjabhayañceva,**Threats, offenses, dangers,*";
P_HTM[12647]="*akusalaṃ gihīnañca.**Unwholesome, and for householders.*";
P_HTM[12648]="*Pāpicchā appasannānaṃ,**Those with bad desires, in those without confidence,*";
P_HTM[12649]="*pasannā dhammaṭṭhapanā;**The confidence of those who have it, the longevity of the Teaching;*";
P_HTM[12650]="*Vinayānuggahā ceva,**And supporting the training,*";
P_HTM[12651]="*pātimokkhuddesena ca.**And with the recitation of the Monastic Code.*";
P_HTM[12652]="*Pātimokkhañca ṭhapanā,**And the canceling of the Monastic Code,*";
P_HTM[12653]="*Pavāraṇañca ṭhapanaṃ;**And the invitation, its suspension;*";
P_HTM[12654]="*Tajjanīyā niyassañca,**Condemnation, and demotion,*";
P_HTM[12655]="*Pabbājanīya paṭisāraṇī.**Banishment, reconciliation.*";
P_HTM[12656]="*Ukkhepana parivāsaṃ,**Ejection, probation,*";
P_HTM[12657]="*mūlamānattaabbhānaṃ;**Beginning, trial period, rehabilitation;*";
P_HTM[12658]="*Osāraṇaṃ nissāraṇaṃ,**Admittance, sending away,*";
P_HTM[12659]="*tatheva upasampadā.**And so ordination.*";
P_HTM[12660]="*Apalokanañatti ca,**Getting permission, and motion,*";
P_HTM[12661]="*dutiyañca catutthakaṃ;**One motion and one announcement, one motion and three announcements;*";
P_HTM[12662]="*Apaññattenupaññattaṃ,**When there was no existing rule, laid down an addition,*";
P_HTM[12663]="*sammukhāvinayo sati.**Resolution face-to-face, recollection.*";
P_HTM[12664]="*Amūḷhapaṭiyebhuyya,**Past insanity, admitted, majority,*";
P_HTM[12665]="*pāpiya tiṇavatthārakaṃ;**Further penalty, covering over as if with grass;*";
P_HTM[12666]="*Vatthu vipatti āpatti,**Basis, failure, offense,*";
P_HTM[12667]="*nidānaṃ puggalena ca.**Origin story, and with person.*";
P_HTM[12668]="*Khandhā ceva samuṭṭhānā,**And classes, origins,*";
P_HTM[12669]="*adhikaraṇameva ca;**And legal issue;*";
P_HTM[12670]="*Samathā saṅgahā ceva,**And found among settling,*";
P_HTM[12671]="*nāmaāpattikā tathāti.**Name, and so offense.”*";
P_HTM[12672]="*Parivāro niṭṭhito.**The Compendium is finished.*";
P_HTM[12673]="*Parivārapāḷi niṭṭhitā.**The canonical text of the Compendium is finished.*";
P_HTM[12674]="*Pariyosānagāthā**Concluding verses*";
P_HTM[12675]="*Bubbācariyamaggañca,**“Having asked this and that*";
P_HTM[12676]="*pucchitvā ca tahiṃ tahiṃ;**About the practice of past teachers:*";
P_HTM[12677]="*Dīpanāmo mahāpañño,**Dīpanāma, who had great wisdom,*";
P_HTM[12678]="*sutadhāriṃ vicakkhaṇo.**Superb memory, and clarity of sight.*";
P_HTM[12679]="*Imaṃ vitthārasaṅkhepaṃ,**This contraction of the detail,*";
P_HTM[12680]="*sajjhāmaggena majjhime;**With a path for study, in the middle,*";
P_HTM[12681]="*Cintayitvā likhāpesi,**Having thought it out, he had it written down,*";
P_HTM[12682]="*sissakānaṃ sukhāvahaṃ.**Bringing happiness to the disciples.*";
P_HTM[12683]="*Parivāranti yaṃ vuttaṃ,**When “Compendium” is said,*";
P_HTM[12684]="*sabbaṃ vatthuṃ salakkhaṇaṃ;**It means all bases for offenses have a characteristic,*";
P_HTM[12685]="*Atthaṃ atthena saddhamme,**Meaning accords with meaning in the true Teaching,*";
P_HTM[12686]="*dhammaṃ dhammena paññatte.**Teaching accords with Teaching in what is laid down.*";
P_HTM[12687]="*Sāsanaṃ parivāresi,**It accompanies the Instruction,*";
P_HTM[12688]="*jambudīpaṃva sāgaro;**Like the ocean accompanies India.*";
P_HTM[12689]="*Parivāraṃ ajānanto,**Not knowing the Compendium,*";
P_HTM[12690]="*kuto dhammavinicchayaṃ.**How does one distinguish the rules?*";
P_HTM[12691]="*Vipatti vatthu paññatti,**How does one distinguish failures, bases, rules,*";
P_HTM[12692]="*anupaññatti puggalo;**Additions to the rules, persons,*";
P_HTM[12693]="*Ekato ubhato ceva,**And whether they relate to one or both Sanghas?*";
P_HTM[12694]="*lokapaṇṇatti vajjato.**And how to distinguish a rule by convention from an offense?*";
P_HTM[12695]="*Yassa jāyati vimati,**When anyone gives rise to doubt,*";
P_HTM[12696]="*parivārena chijjati;**It is cut off by the Compendium.*";
P_HTM[12697]="*Cakkavatti mahāsene,**Like a universal monarch in the midst of his great army,*";
P_HTM[12698]="*migamajjheva kesari.**Like a lion in a herd of deer,*";
P_HTM[12699]="*Ravi raṃsiparikkiṇṇo,**Like the sun surrounded by its rays,*";
P_HTM[12700]="*cando tāragaṇe yathā;**Like the moon in the starry sky,*";
P_HTM[12701]="*Brahmā brahmaparisāya,**Like the Supreme Being in his assembly,*";
P_HTM[12702]="*gaṇamajjheva nāyako;**Like a leader with his retinue—*";
P_HTM[12703]="*Evaṃ saddhammavinayo,**In this way, the true Teaching and the Monastic Law*";
P_HTM[12704]="*parivārena sobhatīti.**Shine through the Compendium.”*";
